[{"phonetic_uk":"/ə; eɪ/","example":"We have a problem. 我们遇到了一个麻烦。","word":"a","phonetic_us":"/ə; e/","translation":"art. 一(个)；每一(个)"},{"example":"How could she abandon her own child? 她怎么能抛弃自己的孩子？","phonetic_uk":"/ə'bænd(ə)n/","word":"abandon","translation":"v. 丢弃；放弃，抛弃","phonetic_us":"/ə'bændən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'bɪləti/","translation":"n. 能力；能耐，本领","word":"ability","phonetic_uk":"/ə'bɪlɪtɪ/","example":"The test measures your mathematical ability. 这种测试考查的是数学能力。"},{"example":"one of my more able students 我班上能力比较强的学生之一","phonetic_uk":"/'eɪb(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 有能力的；出色的","phonetic_us":"/'ebl/","word":"able"},{"phonetic_uk":"/æb'nɔːml/","example":"abnormal behaviour 反常行为","translation":"adj. 不正常的；变态的","phonetic_us":"/æbˈnɔːrml/","word":"abnormal"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'bɔːd/","example":"The plane crashed, killing all 200 people aboard. 飞机失事，机上200人全部遇难。","translation":"adv. 在船(车)上；上船","phonetic_us":"/ə'bɔrd/","word":"aboard"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'baʊt/","example":"a book about politics 一本有关政治的书","phonetic_us":"/ə'baʊt/","translation":"prep. 关于；在…周围","word":"about"},{"word":"above","phonetic_us":"/ə'bʌv/","translation":"prep. 在…上面；高于","phonetic_uk":"/ə'bʌv/","example":"He lived in a flat above the shop. 他住在那商店上面的一套房间里。"},{"translation":"adv. (在)国外；到处","phonetic_us":"/ə'brɔd/","word":"abroad","example":"I’ve never lived abroad before. 我以前从未在国外生活过。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'brɔːd/"},{"example":"The path ends off abruptly. 这条路突然到头了。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'brʌptlɪ/","word":"abruptly","translation":"adv. 突然地","phonetic_us":"/ə'brʌptli/"},{"example":"In the absence of any evidence, the police had to let Myers go. 警察没有证据，只好把迈尔斯放了。","phonetic_uk":"/'æbs(ə)ns/","translation":"n. 缺席，不在场；缺乏","phonetic_us":"/'æbsns/","word":"absence"},{"word":"absent","translation":"adj. 缺席的","phonetic_us":"/ˈæbsənt/","example":"He has been absent from his desk for two weeks. 他已经两个星期没来了。","phonetic_uk":"/'æbs(ə)nt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'æbsəluːt/","example":"Some of the stuff on TV is absolute rubbish. 电视上播放的有些东西简直就是垃圾。","phonetic_us":"/'æbsəlut/","translation":"adj. 绝对的；纯粹的","word":"absolute"},{"word":"absolutely","phonetic_us":"/'æbsəlutli/","translation":"adv. 完全地；绝对地","example":"He made his reasons for resigning absolutely clear. 他把辞职的理由讲得一清二楚。","phonetic_uk":"/'æbsəluːtlɪ/"},{"word":"absorb","translation":"v. 吸收（液体、气体等）","phonetic_us":"/æbˈsɔrb; æbˈzɔrb; əbˈsɔrb/","example":"Plants absorb nutrients from the soil. 植物从土壤中吸收养分。","phonetic_uk":"/əb'sɔ:b/"},{"word":"abstract","translation":"adj. 抽象的","phonetic_us":"/'æbstrækt/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈæbstrækt/","example":"By the age of seven, children are capable of thinking in abstract terms . 儿童到了七岁就具有抽象思维的能力。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'bʌndənt/","example":"an abundant supply of fresh water 充足的淡水供应","word":"abundant","phonetic_us":"/ə'bʌndənt/","translation":"adj. 大量的，丰富的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'bjuːz/","example":"Williams abused his position as Mayor to give jobs to his friends. 威廉斯滥用市长权力，给不少朋友安排了工作。","phonetic_us":"/ə'bjus/","translation":"v. 滥用，虐待","word":"abuse"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,ækə'demik/","example":"He possessed no academic qualifications. 他没有学历。","word":"academic","phonetic_us":"/,ækə'dɛmɪk/","translation":"adj. 学校(院)的，学术的"},{"word":"academy","phonetic_us":"/ə'kædəmi/","translation":"n. 私立中学；专科院校","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kædəmɪ/","example":"a military academy 军事学院"},{"phonetic_us":"/əkˈsɛləˌret/","translation":"v. 加速","word":"accelerate","phonetic_uk":"/ək'seləreɪt/","example":"measures to accelerate the rate of economic growth 加快经济增长速度的措施"},{"phonetic_us":"/ək'sɛlə'reʃən/","translation":"n. 加速；加速度","word":"acceleration","example":"The latest model has excellent acceleration. 这款最新型号加速性能优异。","phonetic_uk":"/əkselə'reɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"word":"accent","translation":"n. 口音，腔调；重音","phonetic_us":"/'æksɛnt/","phonetic_uk":"/'æks(ə)nt; -sent/","example":"He had a strong Irish accent 他有浓重的爱尔兰口音。"},{"translation":"v. 接受；同意","phonetic_us":"/ækˈsɛpt; əkˈsɛpt/","word":"accept","example":"Rick accepted her offer of coffee. 她请里克喝咖啡，他接受了。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'ksept/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ək'sɛptəbl/","translation":"adj. 可接受的，合意的","word":"acceptable","phonetic_uk":"/ək'septəb(ə)l/","example":"Students who achieve an acceptable standard will progress to degree studies. 达到一定程度的学生可以进一步攻读学位。"},{"example":"He wrote a letter of acceptance (=  a letter in which you agree to accept a job, university place etc  ) to the university. 他给那所大学写了一封接受函。","phonetic_uk":"/ək'sept(ə)ns/","phonetic_us":"/ək'sɛptəns/","translation":"n. 接受，验收；承认","word":"acceptance"},{"phonetic_us":"/'æksɛs/","translation":"v. 获取；n. 接近，入口","word":"access","example":"Users can access their voice mail remotely. 用户可以远程获取语音邮件。","phonetic_uk":"/'ækses/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ək'sesərɪ/","word":"accessary","translation":"n. 同谋，从犯","phonetic_us":"/æk'sɛsəri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əkˈsesəbl/","example":"The island is only accessible by boat. 这个岛只有坐船才能到。","translation":"adj. 易接近的","phonetic_us":"/ək'sɛsəbl/","word":"accessible"},{"phonetic_us":"/'æksədənt/","translation":"n. 意外的；事故","word":"accident","phonetic_uk":"/'æksɪdənt/","example":"Over 70,000 people are seriously injured every year in road accidents. 每年在道路事故中受重伤的有七万多人。"},{"example":"an accidental discharge of toxic waste 有毒废料的意外排放","phonetic_uk":"/æksɪ'dent(ə)l/","word":"accidental","phonetic_us":"/,æksɪ'dɛntl/","translation":"adj. 偶然的；非本质的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'kɒmədeɪt/","example":"The island was used to accommodate child refugees. 该岛用于收容儿童难民。","phonetic_us":"/ə'kɑmədet/","translation":"v. 适合， 提供住宿","word":"accommodate"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/əkɒmə'deɪʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/ə,kɑmə'deʃən/","translation":"n. 招待设备；预定铺位","word":"accommodation"},{"word":"accompany","phonetic_us":"/ə'kʌmpəni/","translation":"v. 陪伴","example":"Children under 14 must be accompanied by an adult. 14岁以下儿童必须有成人陪同。","phonetic_uk":"/əˈkʌmpəni/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'kʌmplɪʃ/","example":"We have accomplished all we set out to do. 所有计划要做的事情，我们都已完成。","phonetic_us":"/ə'kɑmplɪʃ/","translation":"v. 完成","word":"accomplish"},{"example":"You will not be accorded any special treatment. 你不会得到任何特殊待遇。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kɔːd/","translation":"v. 使一致；给予","phonetic_us":"/ə'kɔrd/","word":"accord"},{"word":"accordance","translation":"n. 一致；和谐；授予","phonetic_us":"/ə'kɔrdns/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kɔːd(ə)ns/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'kɔrdɪŋ/","translation":"adj.  相等的， 一致的， 依…而定的","word":"according","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kɔːdɪŋ/","example":""},{"example":"Some of the laws were contradictory. Accordingly, measures were taken to clarify them. 有些法律相互矛盾，因此，采取了措施将其阐明。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kɔːdɪŋlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/ə'kɔrdɪŋli/","translation":"adv. 因此，所以；照着","word":"accordingly"},{"translation":"n. 记述；解释；帐目","phonetic_us":"/ə'kaʊnt/","word":"account","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kaʊnt/","example":"The accounts for last year showed a profit of $2 million. 去年的账目显示利润为200万美元。"},{"translation":"n.  会计工作； 会计学","phonetic_us":"/ə'kaʊntənsi/","word":"accountancy","example":"He is studying accountancy or he is an accountancy student. 他正在学习会计学或他是一名会计专业的学生。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kauntənsi/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'kaʊntənt/","translation":"n.  会计人员， 会计师","word":"accountant","example":"Do you want me to invite your accountant to this meeting? 你想让我把你的会计师也邀请到会议里么？","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kauntənt/"},{"word":"accumulate","phonetic_us":"/ə'kjumjəlet/","translation":"v. 积累，增加","example":"It is unjust that a privileged few should continue to accumulate wealth. 少数特权阶级继续积聚财富，这是不公平的。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kju:mjəleɪt/"},{"word":"accuracy","translation":"n. 准确(性)；准确度","phonetic_us":"/'ækjərəsi/","example":"He passes the ball with unerring accuracy. 他传球准确无误。","phonetic_uk":"/'ækjʊrəsɪ/"},{"example":"The brochure tries to give a fair and accurate description of each hotel. 该手册尽量公正、准确地介绍每一家酒店。","phonetic_uk":"/'ækjʊrət/","word":"accurate","phonetic_us":"/'ækjərət/","translation":"adj. 精确的，准确的"},{"word":"accusation","translation":"n.  谴责； 【律】 指控","phonetic_us":"/,ækju'zeʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌækju'zeɪʃn/","example":"The main accusation levelled against him was that he tried to avoid military service. 对他提出的主要指控是他想逃避兵役。"},{"word":"accuse","translation":"v. 指责；归咎于","phonetic_us":"/ə'kjuz/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kjuːz/","example":"The professor stands accused of (=  has been accused of  ) stealing his student’s ideas and publishing them. 那位教授被指控剽窃学生的观点拿去发表。"},{"word":"accustom","phonetic_us":"/ə'kʌstəm/","translation":"v. 使习惯","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kʌstəm/","example":"She tried to accustom herself to the tight bandages. 她尝试着使自己习惯那些紧绷的绷带。"},{"word":"accustomed","phonetic_us":"/ə'kʌstəmd/","translation":"adj. 惯常的；习惯的","example":"The pans were in their accustomed places. 那些锅在老地方。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kʌstəmd/"},{"word":"ache","translation":"v. 痛；想念；n. 疼痛","phonetic_us":"/ek/","example":"His feet were aching from standing so long. 他站了那么久，双脚隐隐作痛。","phonetic_uk":"/eɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'tʃiːv/","example":"Frances achieved very good exam results. 弗朗西丝考试取得了优异成绩。","word":"achieve","phonetic_us":"/ə'tʃiv/","translation":"v. 完成，实现"},{"example":"His great achievement is to make all the players into a united team. 他的伟大成就在于把所有选手组织成一支团结的队伍。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'tʃiːvm(ə)nt/","word":"achievement","phonetic_us":"/ə'tʃivmənt/","translation":"n. 完成；成就，成绩"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'æsɪd/","example":"sulphuric acid 硫酸","word":"acid","translation":"n. 酸；酸的，酸性的","phonetic_us":"/'æsɪd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ək'nɔlidʒ/","example":"The family acknowledge the need for change. 全家人都承认需要改变一下。","word":"acknowledge","translation":"v. 承认(…的权威)","phonetic_us":"/ək'nɑlɪdʒ/"},{"word":"acquaint","phonetic_us":"/ə'kwent/","translation":"vt.  使认识， 使了解","example":"Have steps been taken to acquaint breeders with their right to apply for licenses? 已经采取措施让饲养动物者了解他们申请执照的权利了吗？","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kweɪnt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'kweɪnt(ə)ns/","example":"She was a casual acquaintance of my family in Vienna. 她是我们家在维也纳的一个交情不深的朋友。","translation":"n. 认识；了解；熟人","phonetic_us":"/ə'kwentəns/","word":"acquaintance"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'kwaɪə/","example":"Manning hoped to acquire valuable works of art as cheaply as possible. 曼宁希望以尽可能低的价格买到有价值的艺术品。","word":"acquire","phonetic_us":"/ə'kwaɪr/","translation":"v. 获得"},{"example":"the acquisition of language 语言的习得","phonetic_uk":"/ˌækwɪ'zɪʃn/","translation":"n.  取得， 获得， 习得； 获得物， 增添的人","phonetic_us":"/,ækwɪ'zɪʃən/","word":"acquisition"},{"word":"acre","phonetic_us":"/'ekɚ/","translation":"n. 英亩(=607亩)","phonetic_uk":"/'eɪkə/","example":"They own 200 acres of farmland. 他们拥有200英亩农田。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ə'krɒs/","phonetic_us":"/ə'krɔs/","translation":"prep. 横过；在…对面","word":"across"},{"translation":"v. 行动；见效；n. 行为","phonetic_us":"/ækt/","word":"act","phonetic_uk":"/ækt/","example":"The company acted correctly in sacking him. 公司解雇他做得对。"},{"example":"The government must take action (=  do something  ) now to stop the rise in violent crime. 政府现在必须采取行动遏止暴力犯罪的上升。","phonetic_uk":"/'ækʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'ækʃən/","translation":"n. 行动；作用；功能","word":"action"},{"phonetic_us":"/'æktɪv/","translation":"adj. 活跃的；积极的","word":"active","example":"games for active youngsters 活跃好动的年轻人玩的游戏","phonetic_uk":"/'æktɪv/"},{"example":"Everyone is free to engage in peaceful political activity. 每个人都可以自由参加和平的政治活动。","phonetic_uk":"/æk'tɪvɪtɪ/","word":"activity","phonetic_us":"/æk'tɪviti/","translation":"n. 活动；活力；行动"},{"phonetic_us":"/'æktɚ/","translation":"n. 男演员；演剧的人","word":"actor","example":"His father was an actor in the Cantonese Opera Company. 他父亲曾是粤剧团的一名演员。","phonetic_uk":"/'æktə/"},{"translation":"n. 女演员","phonetic_us":"/'æktrɪs/","word":"actress","phonetic_uk":"/'æktrɪs/","example":"She's not only a great dramatic actress but she's also very funny. 她不仅是一位伟大的女戏剧演员，而且也很幽默。"},{"example":"I’m not joking. Those were his actual words. 我没开玩笑，那都是他的原话。","phonetic_uk":"/'æktʃʊəl; -tjʊəl/","phonetic_us":"/'æktʃuəl/","translation":"adj. 实际的；现行的","word":"actual"},{"translation":"adv. 实际上；竟然","phonetic_us":"/'æktʃuəli/","word":"actually","phonetic_uk":"/'æktjʊəlɪ; -tʃʊ-/","example":"I’ve known Barbara for years. Since we were babies, actually. 我认识芭芭拉很多年了，实际上我们从小就认识。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'kjuːt/","example":"Young children have a particularly acute sense of smell. 幼儿的嗅觉特别灵敏。","word":"acute","phonetic_us":"/ə'kjut/","translation":"adj. 敏锐的"},{"example":"She replied to a lonely hearts ad she spotted in the New York Times. 她回复了在《纽约时报》上看到的一则求友广告。","phonetic_uk":"/æd/","word":"ad","translation":"n. 广告","phonetic_us":"/'e 'di/"},{"example":"The ability to adapt is a definite asset in this job. 适应能力是做这份工作的绝对有利条件。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'dæpt/","word":"adapt","phonetic_us":"/ə'dæpt/","translation":"v. 适应于"},{"word":"add","translation":"v. 添加，附加，掺加","phonetic_us":"/æd/","example":"If the mixture seems dry, add water. 如果混合物看上去干，加点水。","phonetic_uk":"/æd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'dikʃən/","example":"She helped him fight his drug addiction. 她帮助了他对抗自己的毒瘾。","phonetic_us":"/ə'dɪkʃən/","translation":"n. 上瘾","word":"addiction"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'dɪʃən/","translation":"n. 加，加法；附加物","word":"addition","phonetic_uk":"/ə'dɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"This is a fine book; a worthy addition to the series. 这是一本好书——是对这套丛书有价值的增补。"},{"word":"additional","phonetic_us":"/ə'dɪʃənl/","translation":"adj. 额外的","example":"Additional information can be obtained from the centre. 可以从中心获取更多信息。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'dɪʃənl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'dres/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/ə'drɛs/","translation":"v. 解决","word":"address"},{"word":"adequate","translation":"adj. 足够的","phonetic_us":"/ˈædɪkwət/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈædɪkwət/","example":"Farmers have been slow to make adequate provision for their retirement. 农民们迟迟没有为退休做好适当安排。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ædʒɪktɪv/","example":"In “the black cat” the adjective “black”modifies the noun “cat”. 在“那只黑猫”中，形容词“黑的”修饰名词“猫”。","translation":"n. 形容词；adj. 形容词的","phonetic_us":"/'ædʒɪktɪv/","word":"adjective"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'dʒʌst/","example":"Check and adjust the brakes regularly. 经常检查并调节刹车装置。","translation":"v. 调整，调节；校正","phonetic_us":"/ə'dʒʌst/","word":"adjust"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ədmɪnɪ'streɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"We’re looking for someone with experience in administration. 我们正在寻找一个有管理经验的人。","phonetic_us":"/əd,mɪnɪ'streʃən/","translation":"n. 管理，政府","word":"administration"},{"word":"administrative","phonetic_us":"/əd'mɪnɪstretɪv/","translation":"adj. 管理的","phonetic_uk":"/ədˈmɪnɪstrətɪv/","example":"The job is mainly administrative. 这份工作主要是行政方面的。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ædmə'reʃən/","translation":"n. 钦佩，称赞","word":"admiration","phonetic_uk":"/ædmə'reɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Daniel gazed at her in admiration . 丹尼尔用爱慕的眼神注视着她。"},{"example":"I really admire the way she brings up those kids all on her own. 我十分佩服她独力把那些孩子抚养大。","phonetic_uk":"/əd'maiə/","translation":"v. 钦佩，称赞","phonetic_us":"/ədˈmaɪr/","word":"admire"},{"example":"Reese, by his own admission , lacks the necessary experience. 里斯自己也承认缺乏必要的经验。","phonetic_uk":"/əd'miʃən/","word":"admission","phonetic_us":"/əd'mɪʃən/","translation":"n. 准许进(加)入；入场费；承认"},{"word":"admit","phonetic_us":"/əd'mɪt/","translation":"v. 承认，容许","phonetic_uk":"/əd'mɪt/","example":"‘Okay, so maybe I was a little bit scared,’ Jenny admitted. “行了，也许我是有点害怕。”珍妮承认道。"},{"word":"adopt","phonetic_us":"/ə'dɑpt/","translation":"v. 收养；采用；采取","example":"Sally was adopted when she was four. 莎莉四岁时被人收养。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'dɒpt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'dɒptɪv/","example":"He was brought up by adoptive parents in Kentucky. 他是被他在肯塔基州的养父母抚养大的。","phonetic_us":"/ə'dɑptɪv/","translation":"adj.  收养关系的； 采用的","word":"adoptive"},{"translation":"n. 成年人；adj. 成年的","phonetic_us":"/'ædʌlt/","word":"adult","example":"Some children find it difficult to talk to adults. 一些孩子觉得与大人很难谈得来。","phonetic_uk":"/'ædʌlt; ə'dʌlt/"},{"translation":"v & n. 前进，提前","phonetic_us":"/əd'væns/","word":"advance","phonetic_uk":"/əd'vɑ:ns/","example":"I should warn you in advance that I’m not a very good dancer. 我要先提醒你，我跳舞不是很好。"},{"phonetic_us":"/əd'vænst/","translation":"adj. 高级的","word":"advanced","phonetic_uk":"/ədˈvɑ:nst/","example":"advanced learners of English 高级程度的英语学习者"},{"translation":"n. 进步，提升","phonetic_us":"/əd'vænsmənt/","word":"advancement","phonetic_uk":"/əd'vɑːnsm(ə)nt/","example":"career advancement 职业发展"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əd'vɑːntɪdʒ/","example":"Younger workers tend to be at an advantage (=  have an advantage  ) when applying for jobs. 年轻点的工人申请工作时往往处于优势地位。","word":"advantage","translation":"n. 优点，优势；好处","phonetic_us":"/əd'væntɪdʒ/"},{"translation":"n. 冒险；惊险活动","phonetic_us":"/əd'vɛntʃɚ/","word":"adventure","phonetic_uk":"/əd'ventʃə/","example":"Come on – where’s your sense of adventure? 来吧——你的冒险精神哪里去了？"},{"word":"adverb","translation":"n. 副词","phonetic_us":"/'ædvɝb/","example":"Will you please compare the adverb “well”? 请你说出副词“well”的原级、比较级和最高级好吗?","phonetic_uk":"/'ædvɜːb/"},{"translation":"n. 逆境，不幸","phonetic_us":"/əd'vɝsəti/","word":"adversity","phonetic_uk":"/ədˈvɜ:səti/","example":"his courage in the face of adversity 他面对逆境的勇气"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ædvətaɪz/","example":"They no longer advertise alcohol or cigarettes at sporting events. 他们不再在体育赛事上做烟酒广告了。","word":"advertise","translation":"vt.  为…做广告， 宣传； 公告； 登广告","phonetic_us":"/'ædvɚtaɪz/"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ædvɚ'taɪzmənt/","translation":"n. 广告；公告；登广告","word":"advertisement","example":"They put an advertisement in ‘The Morning News’, offering a high salary for the right person. 他们在《晨报》上刊登了一则启事，出高薪寻找合适的人选。","phonetic_uk":"/əd'vɜːtɪzm(ə)nt; -tɪs-/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ədˈvaɪs/","example":"You should have followed my advice. 你真该听我的建议。","translation":"n. 建议","phonetic_us":"/ædˈvaɪs; əd'vaɪs/","word":"advice"},{"phonetic_us":"/əd'vaɪzəbl/","translation":"n. 明智的；可取的","word":"advisable","phonetic_uk":"/əd'vaɪzəb(ə)l/","example":"I deem it advisable to buy property now. 我认为现在购置房地产是明智的。"},{"phonetic_us":"/əd'vaɪz/","translation":"v. 劝告；建议；通知","word":"advise","example":"She needed someone to advise her. 她需要有个人给她出主意。","phonetic_uk":"/əd'vaɪz/"},{"word":"advisory","phonetic_us":"/əd'vaɪzəri/","translation":"n. 报告","phonetic_uk":"/əd'vaɪzərɪ/","example":"The State Department issues travel advisories about conditions overseas. 国务院就海外局势发布旅游警报。"},{"translation":"n & v. 倡导","phonetic_us":"/ˈædvəkeɪt；-et/","word":"advocate","phonetic_uk":"/'ædvəkeɪt/","example":"Mr. Williams is a conservative who advocates fewer government controls on business. 威廉斯先生是一位提倡减少政府对商业的控制的保守人士。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ædvəkeɪtə/","example":"","word":"advocator","translation":"n. 主张者，倡导者","phonetic_us":""},{"word":"aeroplane","phonetic_us":"/'ɛrə'plen/","translation":"n. 飞机","phonetic_uk":"/'eərəpleɪn/","example":"The aeroplane landed us at the airport in Barcelona. 飞机把我们降落在巴塞罗那机场。"},{"word":"affair","translation":"n. 事情，事件；事务","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɛr/","example":"Are you interested in world affairs? 你对世界大事感兴趣吗？","phonetic_uk":"/ə'feə/"},{"word":"affect","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɛkt/","translation":"v. 影响；感动","example":"the areas affected by the hurricane 受飓风影响的地区","phonetic_uk":"/ə'fekt/"},{"translation":"n. 慈爱，爱；爱慕","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɛkʃən/","word":"affection","example":"She looked back on those days with affection . 她深情地回顾那些日子。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'fekʃ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'fɛkʃənət/","translation":"adj. 深情的，柔情的","word":"affectionate","phonetic_uk":"/ə'fekʃ(ə)nət/","example":"an affectionate hug 亲切的拥抱"},{"example":"The general affirmed rumors of an attack. 将军证实了袭击的传闻。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'fɜːm/","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɝm/","translation":"v. 断言，声明","word":"affirm"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,æfə:'meiʃən/","example":"On the other hand, when he/she is being positive, reply in affirmation and enthusiasm. 另一方面，当他处于积极状态时，要用肯定和热情的话语来答复。","translation":"n. 断言，肯定","phonetic_us":"/,æfɚ'meʃən/","word":"affirmation"},{"word":"afford","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɔrd/","translation":"v. 负担得起","example":"I couldn’t afford the rent on my own. 我单靠自己付不起房租。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'fɔːd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'fred/","translation":"adj. 害怕的；担心的","word":"afraid","phonetic_uk":"/ə'freɪd/","example":"There’s no need to be afraid. 没有必要害怕。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'æfrɪkə/","example":"The giraffe ranges in Africa. 长颈鹿生长在非洲。","phonetic_us":"/ˈæfrɪkə/","translation":"n. 非洲","word":"Africa"},{"word":"African","phonetic_us":"/'æfrɪkən/","translation":"adj. 非洲的；n. 非洲人","phonetic_uk":"/'æfrɪk(ə)n/","example":"...the African continent. …非洲大陆。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːftə/","example":"After the war many soldiers stayed in France. 战后，许多士兵留在法国。","word":"after","translation":"prep. 在…以后；次于","phonetic_us":"/'æftɚ/"},{"word":"afternoon","phonetic_us":"/,æftɚ'nun/","translation":"n. 下午，午后","example":"There’s a meeting on Thursday afternoon . 星期四下午有个会议。","phonetic_uk":"/ɑːftə'nuːn/"},{"word":"afterward","translation":"adv. 后来，以后","phonetic_us":"/ˈæftərwərd/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːftəwəd/","example":"Shortly afterward, police arrested four suspects. 之后不久，警方逮捕了４名嫌疑犯。"},{"example":"Can you say that again? I didn’t hear. 你能再说一遍吗？ 我没听见。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'gen; ə'geɪn/","word":"again","translation":"adv. 又一次；而且","phonetic_us":"/ə'ɡɛn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'genst; ə'geɪnst/","example":"There was a ladder propped up against the wall. 有一把梯子靠在墙边。","word":"against","phonetic_us":"/ə'ɡɛnst/","translation":"prep. 倚在；逆，对着"},{"phonetic_uk":"/eɪdʒ/","example":"Francis is the same age as me. 弗朗西斯和我同年岁。","translation":"n. 年龄；时代；v. 变老","phonetic_us":"/edʒ/","word":"age"},{"word":"agency","translation":"n. 机构","phonetic_us":"/'edʒənsi/","example":"a UN agency responsible for helping refugees 负责为难民提供帮助的联合国机构","phonetic_uk":"/'eɪdʒənsɪ/"},{"example":"The Republicans have stuck to their conservative agenda. 共和党人坚持自己的保守议题。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'dʒendə/","translation":"n.  议事日程","phonetic_us":"/ə'dʒɛndə/","word":"agenda"},{"translation":"n. 代理商","phonetic_us":"/'edʒənt/","word":"agent","example":"Our agent in Rio deals with all our Brazilian business. 我们在里约热内卢的业务代表处理我们在巴西的全部业务。","phonetic_uk":"/'eɪdʒ(ə)nt/"},{"example":"Jim’s voice became aggressive. 吉姆的声音凶了起来。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'gresɪv/","translation":"adj. 挑衅的，好斗的；有上进心的","phonetic_us":"/ə'ɡrɛsɪv/","word":"aggressive"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'gəʊ/","example":"They moved to a new house some time ago (=  a fairly long time ago  ) . 他们搬进新居已有些日子了。","word":"ago","translation":"adv. 以前","phonetic_us":"/ə'ɡo/"},{"word":"agony","translation":"n. 极度痛苦","phonetic_us":"/'æɡəni/","phonetic_uk":"/'ægənɪ/","example":"the agony of arthritis 关节炎的剧烈疼痛"},{"example":"Teenagers and their parents rarely agree. 十几岁的孩子跟父母意见很少一致。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'griː/","translation":"v. 同意；持相同意见","phonetic_us":"/ə'ɡri/","word":"agree"},{"example":"It is easier for two parties to reach agreement than for three. 两方达成一致比三方达成一致容易。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'griːm(ə)nt/","word":"agreement","phonetic_us":"/ə'grimənt/","translation":"n. 协定，协议；同意"},{"word":"agriculture","translation":"n. 农业，农艺；农学","phonetic_us":"/'æɡrɪkʌltʃɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'ægrɪkʌltʃə/","example":"More than 75% of the land is used for agriculture. 75%以上的土地用于农耕。"},{"example":"He kept his gaze fixed on the car ahead. 他的目光一直盯着前面的那辆汽车。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'hed/","phonetic_us":"/ə'hɛd/","translation":"adv. 在前；向前；提前","word":"ahead"},{"phonetic_uk":"/eɪd/","example":"Foreign aid from many countries poured into the famine area. 来自许多国家的救援物资纷纷送到饥荒地区。","phonetic_us":"/ed/","translation":"n. 帮助，救护；助手","word":"aid"},{"word":"aim","phonetic_us":"/em/","translation":"v. 瞄准，针对；致力","phonetic_uk":"/eɪm/","example":"Denver aimed his gun but did not shoot. 丹佛举枪瞄准，但是没有射击。"},{"example":"Let’s go outside and get some fresh air. 我们出去呼吸些新鲜空气吧。","phonetic_uk":"/eə/","word":"air","translation":"n. 空气；空中；外观","phonetic_us":"/ɛr/"},{"example":"The return flight of the aircraft was delayed. 飞机的返回航程被推迟了。","phonetic_uk":"/'eəkrɑːft/","translation":"n. 飞机，飞行器","phonetic_us":"/'ɛr'kræft/","word":"aircraft"},{"example":"an airline pilot 航空公司飞行员","phonetic_uk":"/'eəlaɪn/","word":"airline","phonetic_us":"/'ɛrlaɪn/","translation":"n. 航空公司；航线"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'eəpleɪn/","example":"The airplane cracked up in landing. 这架飞机在着陆时坠毁。","phonetic_us":"/ˈerpleɪn/","translation":"n. 飞机","word":"airplane"},{"translation":"n. 机场，航空站","phonetic_us":"/'ɛr'pɔrt/","word":"airport","phonetic_uk":"/'eəpɔːt/","example":"The plane landed at Heathrow Airport. 飞机降落在希思罗机场。"},{"example":"I forgot to set the burglar alarm. 我忘记打开防盗警报器了。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'lɑːm/","phonetic_us":"/ə'lɑrm/","translation":"n. 惊恐，忧虑；警报","word":"alarm"},{"example":"a photograph album 相册","phonetic_uk":"/'ælbəm/","translation":"n. 粘贴簿，集邮簿，像册","phonetic_us":"/'ælbəm/","word":"album"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ælkəhɒl/","example":"I don’t drink alcohol anymore. 我不再喝酒了。","phonetic_us":"/'ælkəhɔl/","translation":"n. 酒精","word":"alcohol"},{"word":"alert","translation":"v. 提醒；；adj. 机警的","phonetic_us":"/ə'lɝt/","example":"The animal raised its head, suddenly alert. 那只动物突然警觉地抬起头来。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'lɜːt/"},{"word":"alike","phonetic_us":"/ə'laɪk/","translation":"adj. 同样的，相同的","phonetic_uk":"/ə'laɪk/","example":"My mother and I are alike in many ways. 我和母亲在许多方面很相似。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'laɪv/","example":"It was a bad accident – they’re lucky to be alive. 这是一宗严重事故——他们能活着实属幸运。","word":"alive","translation":"adj. 活着的；活跃的","phonetic_us":"/ə'laɪv/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɔl/","translation":"adj. 全部的；prep. 全部","word":"all","phonetic_uk":"/ɔːl/","example":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'laɪəns/","example":"independent organizations and alliances 独立组织和联盟","translation":"n.  结盟， 联盟","phonetic_us":"/ə'laɪəns/","word":"alliance"},{"word":"allocate","translation":"vt.  分配， 分派， 把…拨给","phonetic_us":"/'æləket/","phonetic_uk":"/'æləkeɪt/","example":"Tickets are limited and will be allocated to those who apply first. 票数有限，将分配给那些先申请的人。"},{"example":"We don’t allow diving in the pool. 泳池内禁止跳水。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'laʊ/","word":"allow","phonetic_us":"/ə'laʊ/","translation":"v. 允许，准许；任"},{"word":"allowance","translation":"n.  津贴， 补贴； 零用钱","phonetic_us":"/ə'laʊəns/","example":"Sales staff get a generous mileage allowance or a company car. 销售人员有优厚的里程补贴或者公司提供的专用汽车。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'lauəns/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ælɔɪ/","translation":"n. 合金；(金属的)成色","word":"alloy","phonetic_uk":"/'ælɒɪ/","example":"Brass is an alloy of copper and zinc. 黄铜是铜和锌的合金。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ælaɪ/","example":"He will have no choice but to ally himself with the new movement. 他将别无选择，只能与这个新运动结盟。","word":"ally","translation":"v.  结盟， 联合；n.  同盟国， 同盟者； 支持者","phonetic_us":"/'ælaɪ/"},{"word":"almost","phonetic_us":"/'ɔlmost/","translation":"adv. 几乎，差不多","example":"Have you almost finished? 你差不多完成了吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːlməʊst/"},{"example":"She lives alone . 她一个人生活。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'ləʊn/","phonetic_us":"/ə'lon/","translation":"adj. 单独的；adv. 单独地","word":"alone"},{"example":"We were driving along Follyfoot Road. 我们沿着福莱福特路行驶。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'lɒŋ/","word":"along","translation":"prep. 沿着；adv. 向前","phonetic_us":"/ə'lɔŋ/"},{"word":"alongside","translation":"adv. 在旁边，沿着边，并排地；prep.  在…旁边， 沿着…的边； 和…在一起","phonetic_us":"/ə'lɔŋ'saɪd/","phonetic_uk":"/əˌlɒŋ'saɪd/","example":"A car drew up alongside . 一辆车在旁边停了下来。"},{"word":"aloud","phonetic_us":"/ə'laʊd/","translation":"adv. 出声地，大声地","example":"When we were children, our father read aloud to us. 当我们是孩子时，我们的父亲大声地朗读给我们听。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'laʊd/"},{"word":"alphabet","phonetic_us":"/'ælfə'bɛt/","translation":"n. 字母表，字母系统","example":"The modern Russian alphabet has 31 letters. 现代俄语字母表有31个字母。","phonetic_uk":"/'ælfəbet/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɔl'rɛdi/","translation":"adv. 早已，已经","word":"already","phonetic_uk":"/ɔːl'redɪ/","example":"The design of the new house is similar to those that have already been built. 新房的设计与那些已建好的房子相似。"},{"translation":"adv. 亦，也；而且，还","phonetic_us":"/'ɔlso/","word":"also","example":"Information is also available on women’s health care. 还可以获得有关女性保健方面的资料。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːlsəʊ/"},{"translation":"v. 改变","phonetic_us":"/'ɔltɚ/","word":"alter","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔ:ltə(r)/","example":"Her face hadn’t altered much over the years. 过了这么多年，她的容貌并没有多大改变。"},{"example":"New ways to treat arthritis may provide an alternative to painkillers. 治疗关节炎的新方法可能会提供一种止痛药的替代品。","phonetic_uk":"/ɔ:lˈtɜ:nətɪv/","word":"alternative","phonetic_us":"/ɔl'tɝnətɪv/","translation":"n. 代替品"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɔːl'ðəʊ; ɒl-/","example":"Although in poor health, she continued to carry out her duties. 尽管身体不好，她仍继续执行任务。","translation":"conj. 尽管，虽然","phonetic_us":"/ɔl'ðo/","word":"although"},{"word":"altitude","phonetic_us":"/'æltɪtud/","translation":"n. 海拔, 高度","example":"The aircraft had reached its cruising altitude of about 39,000 feet. 那架飞机已经达到了大约三万九千英尺的巡航高度。","phonetic_uk":"/'ælti,tju:d/"},{"example":"an old custom that has vanished altogether 一个彻底消亡的古老习俗","phonetic_uk":"/ɔːltə'geðə; ɒl-/","phonetic_us":"/,ɔltə'ɡɛðɚ/","translation":"adv. 完全；总而言之","word":"altogether"},{"phonetic_us":"/,æljə'mɪnɪəm/","translation":"n. 铝","word":"aluminium","example":"recycled aluminium cans 再生铝罐","phonetic_uk":"/æl(j)ʊ'mɪnɪəm/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːlweɪz; -ɪz/","example":"Always lock your bicycle to something secure. 每次都要把自行车锁在牢固的物体上。","word":"always","phonetic_us":"/'ɔlwez/","translation":"adv. 总是，一直；永远"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈæmətər/","translation":"adj.  业余爱好的， 业余的； 外行的；n. 业余爱好者；外行","word":"amateur","example":"...professional athletes and amateur runners. …专业运动员和业余赛跑运动员。","phonetic_uk":"/'æmətə/"},{"word":"amaze","translation":"v. 使吃惊","phonetic_us":"/ə'mez/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'meɪz/","example":"Dave amazed his friends by suddenly getting married. 戴夫突然结婚，令朋友们非常吃惊。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/æm'bæsədə/","example":"...the German ambassador to Poland. …德国驻波兰大使。","phonetic_us":"/æm'bæsədɚ/","translation":"n.  大使， 使节， 派驻国际组织的代表","word":"ambassador"},{"example":"He was young and full of ambition. 他年轻，而且雄心勃勃。","phonetic_uk":"/æm'bɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"ambition","phonetic_us":"/æm'bɪʃən/","translation":"n. 雄心，抱负，野心"},{"word":"ambitious","phonetic_us":"/æm'bɪʃəs/","translation":"adj. 有雄心的，野心勃勃的","example":"Alfred was intensely ambitious, obsessed with the idea of becoming rich. 艾尔弗雷德雄心勃勃，一心想着发财。","phonetic_uk":"/æm'biʃəs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'æmbjʊl(ə)ns/","example":"the ambulance service 救护车服务","phonetic_us":"/'æmbjələns/","translation":"n. 救护车；野战医院","word":"ambulance"},{"word":"America","translation":"n. 美洲；美国","phonetic_us":"/əˈmɛrɪkə/","example":"I may go to America or I may not,it all depends. 我也许去美国，也许不去，要视情况而定。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'merɪkə/"},{"word":"American","phonetic_us":"/əˈmɛrɪkən/","translation":"adj. 美洲的；n. 美国人","example":"Her mother is American. 她妈妈是美国人。","phonetic_uk":"/əmerɪkən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'mɪd/","example":"He sat amid the trees. 他坐在树丛中。","word":"amid","phonetic_us":"/ə'mɪd/","translation":"prep.  在…中间， 在…之中， 被…围绕"},{"example":"The girl quickly disappeared among the crowd. 女孩转眼消失在人群中。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'mʌŋ/","word":"among","translation":"prep. 在…之中","phonetic_us":"/ə'mʌŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'mʌŋst/","example":"Here in Trinity it is right that I should give you an account of how he lived amongst you during these years of his greatest achievement. 正是在三一学院这儿，我将对你们阐述他如何在你们中间生活，如何在这些年中取得他的最伟大的成就。","phonetic_us":"/ə'mʌŋst/","translation":"prep. 在…之中(=among)","word":"amongst"},{"translation":"n. 总数；数量；和","phonetic_us":"/ə'maʊnt/","word":"amount","phonetic_uk":"/ə'maʊnt/","example":"Please pay the full amount (=  of money  ) by the end of the month. 请在月底前全额付清。"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"And I prefer to an ampere meter being made of aluminum even though it has analog to another one. 我还想要一个铝制的安培表，虽然它与另一个类似。","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 安培","word":"ampere"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'æmplɪfaɪ/","example":"an amplified guitar 带有扩音设备的电吉他","translation":"v. 放大，增强；扩大","phonetic_us":"/'æmplɪfaɪ/","word":"amplify"},{"example":"Doing jigsaws would amuse Amy for hours on end. 拼图能让埃米连续玩上几个小时。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'mjuːz/","word":"amuse","phonetic_us":"/ə'mjuz/","translation":"v. 逗…乐；给…娱乐"},{"word":"amusing","translation":"adj. 有趣的，好玩儿的","phonetic_us":"/ə'mjuzɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'mjuːzɪŋ/","example":"I don’t find his jokes at all amusing . 我觉得他的笑话一点都不好笑。"},{"word":"analyse","phonetic_us":"/'æn(ə)laɪz/","translation":"v. 分析，分解，解析","phonetic_uk":"/'æn(ə)laɪz/","example":"She still needs to analyse the data. 她仍需要分析这些数据。"},{"word":"analysis","phonetic_us":"/ə'næləsɪs/","translation":"n. 分析，分解，解析","phonetic_uk":"/ə'nælɪsɪs/","example":"She’s been in analysis for three years. 她接受精神分析治疗已经三年了。"},{"word":"analyze","phonetic_us":"/'ænə,laɪz/","translation":"v. 分析","phonetic_uk":"/'ænə,laɪz/","example":"How do you analyze this change? 你该如何分析这种变化？"},{"word":"ancestor","phonetic_us":"/'ænsɛstɚ/","translation":"n. 祖宗，祖先","example":"My ancestors were French. 我的祖先是法国人。","phonetic_uk":"/'ænsestə/"},{"example":"We dropped anchor a few yards offshore. 我们在离岸几码远的地方抛锚停航。","phonetic_uk":"/'æŋkə/","word":"anchor","translation":"n. 锚；v. 抛锚，停泊","phonetic_us":"/'æŋkɚ/"},{"example":"the ancient civilizations of Asia 亚洲的古代文明","phonetic_uk":"/'eɪnʃənt/","phonetic_us":"/ˈeɪnʃənt/","translation":"adj. 古代的","word":"ancient"},{"word":"and","phonetic_us":"/ənd, ən,ænd/","translation":"conj. 和，又，并，则","example":"He’s gone to get some fish and chips. 他去买炸鱼薯条了。","phonetic_uk":"/ənd; (ə)n; ænd/"},{"word":"angel","phonetic_us":"/'endʒl/","translation":"n. 天使，神差，安琪儿","example":"the angel Gabriel 天使加百列","phonetic_uk":"/'eɪndʒ(ə)l/"},{"example":"There is growing anger among the people against the government. 民众对政府越来越不满。","phonetic_uk":"/'æŋgə/","phonetic_us":"/'æŋɡɚ/","translation":"n. 怒，愤怒；v. 使发怒","word":"anger"},{"example":"You didn’t measure the angle accurately. 你没有量准角度。","phonetic_uk":"/'æŋg(ə)l/","translation":"n. 角，角度","phonetic_us":"/'æŋɡl/","word":"angle"},{"word":"angry","translation":"adj. 愤怒的，生气的","phonetic_us":"/'æŋɡri/","phonetic_uk":"/'æŋgrɪ/","example":"I was angry because he hadn’t told me his plans. 我很生气，因为他没有告诉我他的计划。"},{"example":"furry little animals 毛茸茸的小动物","phonetic_uk":"/'ænɪm(ə)l/","translation":"n. 动物，兽；adj. 动物的","phonetic_us":"/'ænɪml/","word":"animal"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'æŋk(ə)l/","example":"slender ankles 纤细的脚踝","word":"ankle","phonetic_us":"/'æŋkl/","translation":"n. 踝，踝节部"},{"example":"Jack and Kim celebrated their twentieth wedding anniversary in January. 1月，杰克和金庆祝了他们的结婚20周年纪念日。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌænɪ'vɜːsəri/","word":"anniversary","translation":"n.  周年纪念日","phonetic_us":"/,ænɪ'vɝsəri/"},{"translation":"v. 宣布，声称","phonetic_us":"/ə'naʊns/","word":"announce","phonetic_uk":"/ə'nauns/","example":"They announced their engagement in ‘The Times’. 他们在《泰晤士报》上宣布了订婚的消息。"},{"example":"The radio announcer said it was nine o'clock. 电台播音员报了9点。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'naʊnsə/","translation":"n. 宣告者；播音员","phonetic_us":"/ə'naʊnsɚ/","word":"announcer"},{"word":"annoy","translation":"v. 使反感，厌烦","phonetic_us":"/ə'nɔɪ/","example":"Try making a note of the things that annoy you. 试着把让你心烦的事记下来。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'nɒɪ/"},{"word":"annual","phonetic_us":"/'ænjuəl/","translation":"adj. 每年的","example":"The school trip has become an annual event. 学校组织的旅行成了一年一度的活动。","phonetic_uk":"/'ænjuəl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ænjʊəlɪ/","example":"This is a perennating rhizome from which flowering shoots arise annually. 这是一种每年发芽开花的多年生根茎。","phonetic_us":"/'ænjuəli/","translation":"adv. 每年，一年一次","word":"annually"},{"translation":"adj.  匿名的； 无名的； 无特色的","phonetic_us":"/ə'nɑnəməs/","word":"anonymous","phonetic_uk":"/ə'nɒnɪməs/","example":"the anonymous author of a collection of poems 一本诗集的佚名作者"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'nʌðə/","example":"Can you cite another case like this one? 你能举出另一个像这样的例子吗?","word":"another","phonetic_us":"/ə'nʌðɚ/","translation":"adj. 再一个的；别的"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ænsɚ/","translation":"v. 回答；响应；适应","word":"answer","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːnsə/","example":"She thought for a moment before answering. 她想了一会儿才回答。"},{"word":"ant","translation":"n. 蚂蚁","phonetic_us":"/ænt/","phonetic_uk":"/ænt/","example":"Ants swarmed up out of the ground and covered her shoes and legs. 蚂蚁从地里成群地爬出来，爬满了她的鞋和腿。"},{"example":"Sales are better than anticipated. 销量比预期要好。","phonetic_uk":"/æn'tɪsɪpeɪt/","phonetic_us":"/æn'tɪsə'pet/","translation":"v. 预感","word":"anticipate"},{"word":"antique","phonetic_us":"/æn'tik/","translation":"n. 古玩，古董","phonetic_uk":"/æn'ti:k/","example":"The palace is full of priceless antiques. 宫殿里到处都是价值连城的古董。"},{"word":"anxiety","phonetic_us":"/æŋ'zaɪəti/","translation":"n. 焦虑，忧虑；渴望","example":"his feelings of anxiety 他焦虑的心情","phonetic_uk":"/æŋ'zaɪətɪ/"},{"example":"She gave me an anxious look. 她焦急地看了我一眼。","phonetic_uk":"/'æŋ(k)ʃəs/","word":"anxious","phonetic_us":"/'æŋkʃəs/","translation":"adj. 忧虑的；渴望的"},{"example":"We could not reason out which way the robbers escaped, because we were unable to find any trace of them. 我们推断不出这些强盗是从哪个方向逃走的，因为我们找不到他们的任何踪迹。","phonetic_uk":"/'enɪ/","word":"any","phonetic_us":"/'ɛni/","translation":"adj. 什么，一些；任何的"},{"word":"anybody","translation":"prep. 任何人","phonetic_us":"","phonetic_uk":"","example":"You should have a try, don't swallow anybody. 不要轻信任何人，你得亲自去试一试。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'enɪhaʊ/","example":"You know nothing about her really, or about yourself in relation to her, and anyhow it's only one of those things and therefore it's of no importance. 你对她一点儿都不了解，也不了解自己和她的关系，无论如何它只是那些事情之一,因此没有任何重要性。","word":"anyhow","phonetic_us":"/'ɛnɪ'haʊ/","translation":"adv. 无论如何"},{"word":"anyone","translation":"pron. 任何人","phonetic_us":"/'ɛnɪ'wʌn/","phonetic_uk":"/'enɪwʌn/","example":"Anyone could win tonight. 今晚任何人都可能赢。"},{"word":"anything","phonetic_us":"/'ɛnɪ'θɪŋ/","translation":"pron. 任何事物；一切","phonetic_uk":"/'enɪθɪŋ/","example":"You can buy anything you want. 你想要什么都可以买。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'enɪweɪ/","translation":"adv. 无论如何","phonetic_us":"/'ɛnɪ'we/","word":"anyway"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɛnɪwɛr/","translation":"adv. 在什么地方","word":"anywhere","phonetic_uk":"/'enɪweə/","example":"I haven't got anywhere to live. 我没有任何地方住。"},{"word":"apart","translation":"adv. 相隔；分开；除去","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɑrt/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'pɑːt/","example":"They have offices in countries as far apart as India and Peru. 他们的办事处远至印度、秘鲁等国。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əˈpɑ:tmənt/","example":"She lives in a small apartment. 她住在一套小公寓里。","translation":"n. 公寓","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɑrtmənt/","word":"apartment"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'pɑlədʒaɪz/","translation":"v. 道歉，谢罪，认错","word":"apologize","phonetic_uk":"/ə'pɒlədʒaɪz/","example":"I’m so sorry, I do apologize. 非常对不起，我真心道歉。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pɒlədʒɪ/","example":"Edward can’t be here today, but he sends his apologies . 爱德华今天来不了，他向大家表示歉意。","word":"apology","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɑlədʒi/","translation":"n. 道歉，认错，谢罪"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌæpəˈreɪtəs/","example":"Astronauts have special breathing apparatus. 航天员有专门的呼吸装装备。","translation":"n. 器械，仪器；器官","phonetic_us":"/ˌæpəˈrætəs/","word":"apparatus"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pær(ə)nt/","example":"The difference in quality was immediately apparent . 质量的差异显而易见。","word":"apparent","translation":"adj. 表面上的；明显的","phonetic_us":"/ə'pærənt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'piːl/","example":"The girl’s family have made a public appeal for help to try and catch her killer. 那名遇害女孩的家人吁请公众协助捉拿凶手。","phonetic_us":"/ə'pil/","translation":"n &v. 吸引，呼吁","word":"appeal"},{"example":"The city offers an appealing combination of sporting and cultural events. 这座城市集体育活动和文化活动于一身，颇具吸引力。","phonetic_uk":"/əˈpi:lɪŋ/","phonetic_us":"/əˈpiːlɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 吸引人的","word":"appealing"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pɪə/","example":"Police have found what appear to be human remains. 警方发现了疑似人体遗骸的东西。","translation":"v. 出现；来到；似乎","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɪr/","word":"appear"},{"example":"He was always criticising his wife’s appearance. 他老是批评妻子的外表。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'pɪər(ə)ns/","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɪrəns/","translation":"n. 外表, 出现","word":"appearance"},{"example":"Her husband always had a huge appetite. 她丈夫向来胃口极大。","phonetic_uk":"/'æpɪtaɪt/","translation":"n. 欲望, 胃口","phonetic_us":"/'æpɪtaɪt/","word":"appetite"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'plɔːz/","example":"She got a round of applause (=  a short period of applause  ) when she finished. 她结束的时候获得一阵掌声。","phonetic_us":"/ə'plɔz/","translation":"n.  鼓掌， 掌声","word":"applause"},{"example":"apple pie 苹果馅饼","phonetic_uk":"/'æp(ə)l/","translation":"n. 苹果，苹果树","phonetic_us":"/'æpl/","word":"apple"},{"word":"appliance","translation":"n. 用具，器具，器械","phonetic_us":"/ə'plaɪəns/","example":"The device most often used to do this is a load balancer, which is an appliance that accepts requests from the outside world and hands them off to the next available application server. 进行这一操作最常用的设备是一个负载均衡器，这是一个从外部接收请求并将它们移交给下一个可用应用程序服务器的装置。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'plaɪəns/"},{"example":"What is a reasonable standard for one family is not applicable for another. 对一个家庭合理的标准对于另一个家庭并不适用。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'plɪkəb(ə)l; 'æplɪk-/","translation":"adj. 能应用的；适当的","phonetic_us":"/'æplɪkəbl/","word":"applicable"},{"phonetic_us":"/'æplɪkənt/","translation":"n. 申请人","word":"applicant","phonetic_uk":"/'æplikənt/","example":"We have had lots of applicants for these positions. 对这些职位我们已有了很多申请人。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˌæpləˈkeʃən/","translation":"n. 申请，应用","word":"application","phonetic_uk":"/ˌæplɪ'keɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"We receive hundreds of job applications each year. 我们每年收到数百封求职信。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'plaɪ/","example":"We need to apply for planning permission to build a garage. 我们建车库需要申请规划许可。","phonetic_us":"/ə'plaɪ/","translation":"v. 应用, 申请","word":"apply"},{"word":"appoint","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɔɪnt/","translation":"v. 任命，委派；约定，确定，指定","phonetic_uk":"/ə'pɔint/","example":"officials appointed by the government 政府任命的官员"},{"example":"All consultations are by appointment only . 就诊必须预约。","phonetic_uk":"/əˈpɔɪntmənt/","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɔɪntmənt/","translation":"n. 约会","word":"appointment"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'priʃɪet/","translation":"v. 感激，欣赏","word":"appreciate","phonetic_uk":"/ə'pri:ʃɪeɪt/","example":"Thanks ever so much for your help, I really appreciate it. 多谢你的帮助，我真的很感激。"},{"word":"appreciation","translation":"n. 评价，感激","phonetic_us":"/ə,priʃɪ'eʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ə,pri:ʃi'eiʃən/","example":"He was presented with a watch in appreciation of his long service. 他获赠一块手表，作为对其长期服务的感谢。"},{"word":"approach","translation":"v. 靠近；n. 接近，方法","phonetic_us":"/ə'protʃ/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'prəutʃ/","example":"As I approached the house, I noticed a light on upstairs. 我走近那幢房子的时候注意到楼上有灯光。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'prəʊprɪət/","example":"The timing of the announcement was particularly appropriate . 通告发布的时机很合适。","phonetic_us":"/əˈpropriɪt/","translation":"adj. 适当的，恰当的","word":"appropriate"},{"translation":"n. 批准，认可，赞成","phonetic_us":"/əˈpruvl/","word":"approval","phonetic_uk":"/ə'pruːv(ə)l/","example":"The president has already given his approval to the plan. 总统已经批准了这个计划。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pru:v/","example":"You've never approved of Henry, have you? 你从未赞赏过亨利，是吧？","word":"approve","phonetic_us":"/ə'prʊv/","translation":"v. 赞成，同意"},{"word":"approximate","translation":"adj. 近似的；v. 近似","phonetic_us":"/ə'prɑksɪmət/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'prɒksɪmət/","example":"For each approximate solution of a parameterized problem, the app also displays the margin of error. 对于每一个参数化问题的近似结果，这个程序也会显示误差的边界。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'prɔksimitli/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/ə'prɑksɪmətli/","translation":"adv. 大约","word":"approximately"},{"word":"April","translation":"n. 四月","phonetic_us":"/'eprəl/","phonetic_uk":"/'eɪprəl/","example":"The changes will be introduced in April. 这些变更将于4月实施。"},{"example":"...the Arabian Peninsula. ...阿拉伯半岛。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'reɪbɪən/","translation":"adj. 阿拉伯的","phonetic_us":"/ə'rebiən/","word":"Arabian"},{"translation":"adj. 随心所欲的；专断的","phonetic_us":"/ˈɑːrbətreri/","word":"arbitrary","example":"an arbitrary decision 武断的决定","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːbɪt(rə)rɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 建筑师","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrkɪtɛkt/","word":"architect","example":"But I am an architect. 但是我是一名建筑师。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːkɪtekt/"},{"example":"He studied architecture at university. 他在大学里读的是建筑学。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːkɪtektʃə/","translation":"n. 建筑学；建筑式样","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrkə'tɛktʃɚ/","word":"architecture"},{"translation":"n. 档案文件","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrkaɪv/","word":"archive","example":"an archive of the writer’s unpublished work 那位作家未发表作品的档案","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑ:kaɪv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'eərɪə/","example":"Only cheeses made in this area may be labelled ‘Roquefort.’ 只有这个地区出产的干酪才能被称作“罗克福尔干酪”。","phonetic_us":"/'ɛrɪə/","translation":"n. 面积；地区；领域","word":"area"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːgjuː/","example":"We could hear the neighbours arguing. 我们听到邻居在争吵。","word":"argue","translation":"v. 争论，争辩，辩论","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrgjʊ/"},{"translation":"n. 争论，辩论；理由","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrɡjumənt/","word":"argument","example":"We need to provide a convincing argument as to why the system should be changed. 我们得提出有说服力的论据，证明为何要改变体制。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːgjʊm(ə)nt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'raɪz/","translation":"v. 出现；由…引起","word":"arise","example":"A crisis has arisen in the Foreign Office. 外交部出现了危机。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'raɪz/"},{"word":"arithmetic","phonetic_us":"/ə'rɪθmətɪk/","translation":"n. 算术，四则运算","example":"...teaching the basics of reading, writing and arithmetic. …教授读、写、算的基本知识。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'rɪθmətɪk/"},{"word":"arm","phonetic_us":"/ɑrm/","translation":"n. 臂；臂状物；武器","phonetic_uk":"/ɑːm/","example":"Dave has a broken arm . 戴夫手臂断了。"},{"translation":"n. 军队；陆军","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrmi/","word":"army","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːmɪ/","example":"The army are helping to clear up after the floods. 陆军部队正协助洪灾后的清理工作。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'raʊnd/","translation":"prep. 在…周围","word":"around","example":"What an inspiration she was to all around her! 她对于她周围所有的人是一种多么大的鼓舞!","phonetic_uk":"/ə'raʊnd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'raʊz/","example":"Matt’s behavior was arousing the interest of the neighbors. 马特的行为渐渐引起了邻居的兴趣。","word":"arouse","phonetic_us":"/ə'raʊz/","translation":"v. 引起，唤起；唤醒"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ə'reɪndʒ/","translation":"v. 把…（系统地）分类","phonetic_us":"/ə'rendʒ/","word":"arrange"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'reɪn(d)ʒm(ə)nt/","example":"Have you made all your travel arrangements? 你的旅行都安排好了吗？","word":"arrangement","phonetic_us":"/ə'rendʒmənt/","translation":"n. 整理，排列；安排"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'rest/","example":"He was arrested and charged with murder. 他遭到逮捕并被指控谋杀。","word":"arrest","phonetic_us":"/ə'rɛst/","translation":"v. 逮捕"},{"word":"arrival","phonetic_us":"/ə'raɪvəl/","translation":"n. 到达；到来；到达者","phonetic_uk":"/ə'raɪv(ə)l/","example":"Only the timely arrival of the police prevented the situation from becoming worse. 警方及时赶到才阻止了事态恶化。"},{"word":"arrive","translation":"v. 到达；来临；达到","phonetic_us":"/ə'raɪv/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'raɪv/","example":"Give me a call to let me know you’ve arrived safely. 打个电话给我，告诉我你已平安到达。"},{"example":"Follow the arrows to the X-ray department. 顺着箭头指示的方向去X光科。","phonetic_uk":"/'ærəʊ/","word":"arrow","phonetic_us":"/'æro/","translation":"n. 箭；箭状物"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɑːt/","example":"the Museum of Modern Art in New York 纽约现代艺术博物馆","word":"art","phonetic_us":"/ɑrt/","translation":"n. 艺术，美术；技术"},{"word":"article","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrtɪkl/","translation":"n. 文章；条款；物品","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːtɪk(ə)l/","example":"The paper’s leading article (=  the main article  ) described the government as weak. 该报社论称政府软弱。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɑːtɪ'fɪʃ(ə)l/","example":"artificial flowers 假花","word":"artificial","phonetic_us":"/,ɑrtɪ'fɪʃl/","translation":"adj. 人工的；娇揉造作的"},{"word":"artist","phonetic_us":"/'ɑrtɪst/","translation":"n. 艺术家，美术家","example":"an exhibition of paintings by local artists 当地画家的画展","phonetic_uk":"/'ɑːtɪst/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɑː'tɪstɪk/","example":"artistic work 艺术作品","word":"artistic","phonetic_us":"/ɑr'tɪstɪk/","translation":"adj. 艺术的；艺术家的"},{"example":"I saw Peter as I was getting off the bus. 我下公共汽车的时候看见了彼得。","phonetic_uk":"/æz; əz/","word":"as","translation":"conj. 当…的时候","phonetic_us":"/æz,əz/"},{"example":"cigarette ash 香烟灰","phonetic_uk":"/æʃ/","translation":"n. 灰，灰末；骨灰","phonetic_us":"/æʃ/","word":"ash"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'ʃeɪmd/","example":"Everyone cries sometimes – it’s nothing to be ashamed of. 每个人都会有哭的时候——没什么好难为情的。","word":"ashamed","phonetic_us":"/ə'ʃemd/","translation":"adj. 害羞的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈeɪʒə;ˈeɪʃə/","example":"The European powers extended their authority in Asia. 欧洲列强在亚洲扩大他们的管辖权。","phonetic_us":"/ˈeʒə;ˈeʃə/","translation":"n. 亚洲","word":"Asia"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈeʒən, ˈeʃən/","translation":"adj. 亚洲的；n. 亚洲人","word":"Asian","phonetic_uk":"/'eiʃən/","example":"The financial crisis devitalized the economy of the Asian countries. 这次金融危机使亚洲国家的经济大伤元气。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'saɪd/","example":"He pushed his half-eaten salad aside and left. 他推开吃了一半的色拉走了。","translation":"adv. 在旁边，到旁边","phonetic_us":"/ə'saɪd/","word":"aside"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɑːsk/","example":"‘What’s your name?’ she asked. “你叫什么名字？”她问道 。","translation":"v. 问；要求；邀请","phonetic_us":"/æsk/","word":"ask"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'sliːp/","example":"Quiet! The baby’s asleep. 安静！ 宝宝在睡觉。","translation":"adj. 睡着的，睡熟的","phonetic_us":"/ə'slip/","word":"asleep"},{"translation":"n. 方面；样子，外表","phonetic_us":"/'æspɛkt/","word":"aspect","phonetic_uk":"/'æspekt/","example":"a south-facing aspect 朝南方向"},{"example":"A large crowd had assembled outside the American embassy. 一大群人聚集在美国大使馆外。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'sembl/","word":"assemble","phonetic_us":"/ə'sɛmbl/","translation":"v. 组装；集合"},{"example":"instructions for assembly 装配说明（书）","phonetic_uk":"/ə'semblɪ/","word":"assembly","translation":"n. 装配","phonetic_us":"/ə'sɛmbli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əˈses/","example":"The test was to assess aptitude rather than academic achievement. 该测试将评估能力而不是学业成绩。","word":"assess","translation":"v. 评价","phonetic_us":"/ə'sɛs/"},{"translation":"n. 有价值的人(或物)资产","phonetic_us":"/'æsɛt/","word":"asset","phonetic_uk":"/'æset/","example":"the value of a company’s assets 公司的资产价值"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'saɪn/","example":"When I taught, I would assign a topic to children that they would write about. 教书时，我会给孩子们布置个写作题。","word":"assign","phonetic_us":"/ə'saɪn/","translation":"v. 分配，布置"},{"word":"assignment","phonetic_us":"/ə'saɪnmənt/","translation":"n. 作业","example":"a history assignment 历史作业","phonetic_uk":"/ə'sainmənt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'sɪst/","example":"The family decided to assist me with my chores. 家人决定分担我的琐事。","phonetic_us":"/ə'sɪst/","translation":"v. 援助，帮助；搀扶","word":"assist"},{"translation":"n.  协助， 援助","phonetic_us":"/ə'sɪstəns/","word":"assistance","phonetic_uk":"/ə'sɪstəns/","example":"We offer financial assistance to students. 我们向学生提供经济援助。"},{"word":"assistant","phonetic_us":"/ə'sɪstənt/","translation":"n. 助手，助理；助教","phonetic_uk":"/ə'sɪst(ə)nt/","example":"a clerical assistant 文书助理"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'səuʃieit/","example":"Through science we've got the idea of associating progress with the future. 通过科学我们已有了将进步与未来联系起来的观念。","word":"associate","translation":"v. 交往；把……联系起来","phonetic_us":"/ə'soʃɪet/"},{"word":"association","phonetic_us":"/ə,soʃɪ'eʃən/","translation":"n. 协会，团体；联合","example":"the Association of Master Builders 建筑师协会","phonetic_uk":"/əsəʊsɪ'eɪʃ(ə)n; -ʃɪ-/"},{"example":"I think we can safely assume (=  it is almost certain  ) that interest rates will go up again soon. 我想我们几乎可以肯定，利率很快会再次上调。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'sjuːm/","word":"assume","phonetic_us":"/ə'sum/","translation":"v. 假定，认为"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'sʌmpʃn/","example":"You would be making an assumption that's not based on any fact that you could report. 你会做出不以你能报道的任何事实为依据的一种假设。","translation":"n. 假定，假设","phonetic_us":"/ə'sʌmpʃən/","word":"assumption"},{"word":"assure","translation":"v. 使确信；向…保证","phonetic_us":"/ə'ʃʊr/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'ʃʊə; ə'ʃɔː/","example":"The document is genuine, I can assure you . 我能向你保证，这文件是真的。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'stɑnɪʃ/","translation":"v. 使惊讶，使大为吃惊","word":"astonish","example":"Her reply astonished me. 她的回答让我大吃一惊。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'stɒnɪʃ/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'æstrənɔːt/","word":"astronaut","phonetic_us":"/'æstrə'nɔt/","translation":"n. 宇宙航行员，宇航员"},{"example":"We provide courses in the field of physics, astrophysics and mathematics. 我们提供物理、 天体物理和数学领域的课程。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌæstrəu'fɪzɪks/","word":"astrophysics","translation":"n.  天体物理学","phonetic_us":"/,æstro'fɪzɪks/"},{"example":"They live at 18 Victoria Street. 他们住在维多利亚街18 号。","phonetic_uk":"/æt; ət/","phonetic_us":"","translation":"prep. 在…里；在…时","word":"at"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'æθliːt/","example":"a professional athlete 一位专业运动员","phonetic_us":"/'æθlit/","translation":"n. 运动员；田径运动员","word":"athlete"},{"example":"They underlaid the Atlantic with a cable. 他们在大西洋海底铺设了一条电缆。","phonetic_uk":"/æt'læntɪk/","translation":"adj. 大西洋的；n. 大西洋","phonetic_us":"/ət'læntɪk/","word":"Atlantic"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ætmə,sfiə/","example":"The hotel had a lovely relaxed atmosphere . 那家宾馆的气氛轻松愉快。","phonetic_us":"/'ætməsfɪr/","translation":"n. 气氛；大气；空气","word":"atmosphere"},{"example":"atmospheric pressure 大气压力","phonetic_uk":"/ætməs'ferɪk/","phonetic_us":"/,ætməs'fɛrɪk/","translation":"adj. 大气的；大气层的","word":"atmospheric"},{"example":"carbon atoms 碳原子","phonetic_uk":"/'ætəm/","translation":"n. 原子；微粒；微量","phonetic_us":"/'ætəm/","word":"atom"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'tɒmɪk/","example":"atomic power 核动力","word":"atomic","phonetic_us":"/ə'tɑmɪk/","translation":"adj. 原子的；原子能的"},{"word":"attach","phonetic_us":"/ə'tætʃ/","translation":"v. 缚，系，贴；附加","example":"We attach labels to things before we file them away. 我们在把东西归档前先给它们贴上标签。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'tætʃ/"},{"word":"attack","phonetic_us":"","translation":"vt&vi&n. 攻击，进攻","example":"The king hight them to attack the castle. 国王命令他们向城堡发起进攻。","phonetic_uk":""},{"example":"More women are attaining positions of power. 越来越多的女性获得要职。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'teɪn/","phonetic_us":"/ə'ten/","translation":"v. 达到，获得，完成","word":"attain"},{"word":"attempt","phonetic_us":"/ə'tɛmpt/","translation":"n & v. 尝试，试图","example":"Weather conditions prevented them from attempting the jump. 天气状况使他们无法尝试跳伞。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'tem(p)t/"},{"translation":"v. 出席；照顾，护理","phonetic_us":"/ə'tɛnd/","word":"attend","example":"Only 12 people attended the meeting. 只有12个人出席了会议。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'tend/"},{"example":"We have an average attendance of 4,000 fans per game. 每场比赛平均有4,000名球迷来观战。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'tend(ə)ns/","translation":"n. 出席，到场","phonetic_us":"/ə'tɛndəns/","word":"attendance"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'tenʃ(ə)n/","example":"My attention wasn’t really on the game. 我的注意力其实不在比赛上。","word":"attention","translation":"n. 注意，留心；注意力","phonetic_us":"/ə'tɛnʃən/"},{"word":"attentive","phonetic_us":"/ə'tɛntɪv/","translation":"adj. 注意的；有礼貌的","phonetic_uk":"/ə'tentɪv/","example":"an attentive audience 聚精会神的听众"},{"example":"As soon as they found out I was a doctor, their whole attitude changed. 他们一听说我是医生，态度就完全改变了。","phonetic_uk":"/'ætɪtjuːd/","word":"attitude","translation":"n. 态度，看法；姿势","phonetic_us":"/'ætɪtʊd/"},{"word":"attorney","translation":"n.  律师， 代理人","phonetic_us":"/ə'tɝni/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'tɜːni/","example":"...a prosecuting attorney. …一位公诉律师。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'trækt/","example":"I’m not usually attracted to blondes. 我一般不喜欢金发女子。","phonetic_us":"/ə'trækt/","translation":"v. 吸引；引起，诱惑","word":"attract"},{"translation":"n. 吸引；吸引力；引力","phonetic_us":"/ə'trækʃən/","word":"attraction","phonetic_uk":"/ə'trækʃ(ə)n/","example":"The beautiful beaches are the island’s main attraction (=  most popular place, activity etc  ) . 美丽的海滩是这个岛上的主要魅力所在。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'træktɪv/","translation":"adj. 有吸引力的","word":"attractive","example":"an attractive young woman 妩媚动人的年轻女子","phonetic_uk":"/ə'træktɪv/"},{"example":"Women tend to attribute their success to external causes such as luck. 女性往往把她们的成功归因于外因，如运气。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'trɪbjuːt/","translation":"v. 归因于","phonetic_us":"/ə'trɪbjut/","word":"attribute"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɔdɪəns/","translation":"n. 听众，观众，读者","word":"audience","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːdɪəns/","example":"The audience began clapping and cheering. 观众开始鼓掌欢呼。"},{"word":"audio","translation":"adj.  听觉的， 声音的","phonetic_us":"/'ɔdɪo/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːdiəu/","example":"audio and video equipment 音频视频设备"},{"example":"The world premiere took place in August 1956. 全球首映是在1956年8月。","phonetic_uk":"/ɔ:ˈgʌst/","translation":"n. 八月","phonetic_us":"/ɔɡəst/","word":"August"},{"translation":"n. 伯母，婶母，姑母","phonetic_us":"/ænt/","word":"aunt","phonetic_uk":"/ɑːnt/","example":"Aunt Mary 玛丽姑妈"},{"word":"aural","translation":"adj. 耳的，听觉的","phonetic_us":"","example":"an aural stimulus 听觉刺激","phonetic_uk":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɒ'streɪlɪə/","example":"He transplanted his family to Australia. 他把家迁到澳大利亚。","word":"Australia","phonetic_us":"/ɔ'streljə/","translation":"n. 澳大利亚"},{"example":"She went solo backpacking for eight months in the Australian outback. 她在澳大利亚内陆独自背包旅行了八个月。","phonetic_uk":"","word":"Australian","phonetic_us":"/ɑ'strelɪən/","translation":"adj. 澳大利亚的"},{"word":"author","phonetic_us":"/'ɔθɚ/","translation":"n. 作者，作家","example":"Nothomb is a Belgian author. 诺东是位比利时作家。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːθə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ə'θɔrətetɪv/","translation":"adj. 权威的","word":"authoritative","phonetic_uk":"/ɔː'θɒrɪtətɪv/","example":"the most authoritative work on English surnames 有关英语姓氏的最权威著作"},{"word":"authority","phonetic_us":"/ə'θɔrəti/","translation":"n. 当局，官方；权力","example":"an agreement between the US and Colombian authorities 美国和哥伦比亚当局的一份协议","phonetic_uk":"/ɔː'θɒrɪtɪ/"},{"word":"auto","translation":"n. (口语)汽车","phonetic_us":"/'ɔto/","example":"imported autos 进口汽车","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːtəʊ/"},{"word":"automatic","translation":"adj. 自动的","phonetic_us":"/'ɔtə'mætɪk/","example":"an automatic weapon 自动武器","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɔ:tə'mætɪk/"},{"word":"automation","translation":"n. 自动，自动化","phonetic_us":"/,ɔtə'meʃən/","example":"They phrase in new machinery for increased automation. 他们逐步采用新机器以提高自动化程度。","phonetic_uk":"/ɔːtə'meɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"translation":"n. 汽车，机动车","phonetic_us":"/,ɔtəmə'bil/","word":"automobile","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːtəməbiːl/","example":"the automobile industry 汽车工业"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːtəm/","example":"autumn mists 秋天的雾霭","word":"autumn","phonetic_us":"/'ɔtəm/","translation":"n. 秋，秋季"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɔːɡ'zɪlɪəri/","translation":"adj. 辅助的；附属的","word":"auxiliary","phonetic_uk":"/ɔːg'zɪlɪərɪ; ɒg-/","example":"an auxiliary nurse 助理护士"},{"word":"avail","translation":"v. 有益, 有帮助","phonetic_us":"/ə'vel/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ə'veɪl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'veiləbl/","example":"Tickets are available from the box office. 售票处有票出售。","word":"available","translation":"adj. 可利用的，现有的；可获得的","phonetic_us":"/ə'veləbl/"},{"word":"avenue","phonetic_us":"/'ævənu/","translation":"n. 林荫道，道路；大街","phonetic_uk":"/'æv(ə)njuː/","example":"Fifth Avenue 第五大街"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ævərɪdʒ/","example":"The age of the candidates ranged from 29 to 49 with an average age of 37. 候选人的年龄29岁至49岁不等，平均37岁。","word":"average","phonetic_us":"/'ævərɪdʒ/","translation":"adj. 平常的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'eɪvɪeɪt/","example":"There is long-distance medical system in the boat, aviate board has near one thousand square meters , can help many model copters rise and drop. 飞行甲板面积近千平方米，可供多种型号的直升机起降；","word":"aviate","translation":"v. 驾驶飞机","phonetic_us":"/'evɪet/"},{"word":"aviation","translation":"n. 航空","phonetic_us":"/,evɪ'eʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/,eivi'eiʃən/","example":"...the aviation industry. …航空工业。"},{"example":"Road safety is taught to young children to avoid road accidents. 小孩子受到道路安全知识的教育，以避免交通事故。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'vɔɪd/","word":"avoid","phonetic_us":"/ə'vɔɪd/","translation":"v. 避免"},{"word":"await","phonetic_us":"/ə'wet/","translation":"v. 等候，期待","example":"Several men are awaiting trial for robbery. 几个人因抢劫正在候审。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'weɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'weɪk/","example":"I hope he’s awake now. 我希望他现在醒着。","translation":"adj. 醒着的；v. 唤醒","phonetic_us":"/ə'wek/","word":"awake"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'wɔ:d/","example":"Moodie has been awarded a golf scholarship at the University of Hawaii. 穆迪获授夏威夷大学高尔夫奖学金。","translation":"v. 授予；判给；n. 奖(金)","phonetic_us":"/ə'wɔrd/","word":"award"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'weə/","example":"Mr Braley has been made aware of the need for absolute secrecy. 布雷利先生被告知需要绝对保密。","translation":"adj. 知道的，意识到的","phonetic_us":"/ə'wɛr/","word":"aware"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əˈweənəs/","example":"Health officials have tried to raise awareness (=  improve people’s knowledge  ) about AIDS. 卫生部官员努力提高人们对艾滋病的认识。","word":"awareness","phonetic_us":"/ə'wɛrnəs/","translation":"n. 意识"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'weɪ/","example":"Go away! 走开！","word":"away","translation":"adv. 离开，远离；…去","phonetic_us":"/əˈwe/"},{"word":"awful","translation":"adj. 可怕的，骇人的","phonetic_us":"/'ɔfl/","example":"The weather was awful. 天气很糟糕。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɔ:fl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːfʊlɪ/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/'ɔfli/","translation":"adv. 令人畏惧的；很","word":"awfully"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɔkwɚd/","translation":"adj. 笨拙的；尴尬的","word":"awkward","example":"I hoped he would stop asking awkward questions . 我希望他不要再问令人难堪的问题。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːkwəd/"},{"translation":"n. 斧子","phonetic_us":"/æks/","word":"ax","example":"He grinds ax on the grindstone. 他在磨石上磨斧。","phonetic_uk":"/æks/"},{"example":"The Earth rotates on an axis between the north and south poles. 地球绕着南北两极之间的地轴自转。","phonetic_uk":"/'æksɪs/","translation":"n. 轴，轴线；中心线","phonetic_us":"/'æksɪs/","word":"axis"},{"word":"baby","phonetic_us":"/bebɪ/","translation":"n. 婴儿；孩子气的人","phonetic_uk":"/'beɪbɪ/","example":"The baby is crying. 宝宝在哭。"},{"translation":"adv. 在后；回原处；回","phonetic_us":"/bæk/","word":"back","phonetic_uk":"/bæk/","example":"I’ll be back in a minute. 我马上回来。"},{"word":"background","translation":"n. 背景","phonetic_us":"/'bækɡraʊnd/","example":"Students with a background in chemistry will probably find the course easier. 学过化学的学生可能会觉得这门课程容易些。","phonetic_uk":"/'bækgraʊnd/"},{"example":"But if you backslide, Hiram says, “Start over. 但假如你倒退了，海勒姆说，“那就重新开始。","phonetic_uk":"/'bækslaɪd/","word":"backslide","translation":"n & v. 倒退，退步","phonetic_us":"/,bæk'slaid/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'bækwəd/","example":"The diver flipped over backward into the water. 跳水运动员向后翻转跳入水中。","word":"backward","translation":"adv. 向后的","phonetic_us":"/'bækwɚd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'bekən/","translation":"n.  咸肉","word":"bacon","phonetic_uk":"/'beɪkən/","example":"bacon and eggs 咸猪肉煎蛋"},{"phonetic_us":"/bæk'tɪrɪə/","translation":"n. 细菌","word":"bacteria","phonetic_uk":"/bæk'tɪərɪə/","example":"Is it possible to multiply bacteria in the laboratory? 有可能在实验室繁殖细菌吗?"},{"translation":"adj. 坏的，恶的；严重的","phonetic_us":"/bæd/","word":"bad","example":"I have some bad news for you. 我有坏消息要告诉你。","phonetic_uk":"/bæd/"},{"example":"He’s been limping badly ever since the skiing accident. 出了那次滑雪事故以后，他的腿跛得很厉害。","phonetic_uk":"/'bædlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'bædli/","translation":"adv. 坏，差；严重地","word":"badly"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'bædmɪnt(ə)n/","example":"Can I try you new badminton racket? 我可以试用你的羽毛球拍吗？","translation":"n. 羽毛球","phonetic_us":"/'bædmɪntən/","word":"badminton"},{"example":"She left the hotel carrying a shopping bag. 她拎着一个购物袋离开了宾馆。","phonetic_uk":"/bæg/","word":"bag","translation":"n. 袋，包，钱包，背包","phonetic_us":"/bæɡ/"},{"word":"baggage","phonetic_us":"/'bæɡɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 行李","example":"Check your baggage in at the desk. 在服务台托运行李。","phonetic_uk":"/'bægɪdʒ/"},{"translation":"v. 烤，烘，焙；烧硬","phonetic_us":"/bek/","word":"bake","phonetic_uk":"/beɪk/","example":"I’m baking some bread. 我在烤一些面包。"},{"example":"A smell of bread drifted from some distant bakery. 一股面包的味道从远处的某个面包店飘来。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈbeɪkəri/","word":"bakery","translation":"n. 面包店","phonetic_us":"/'bekəri/"},{"example":"Job losses in manufacturing were balanced by job increases in the service sector. 制造业职位减少了，而服务行业就业机会却增加了，正好相抵。","phonetic_uk":"/'bæl(ə)ns/","word":"balance","phonetic_us":"/'bæləns/","translation":"v. 使平衡；称；n. 天平"},{"example":"Has your flat got a balcony? 你的公寓有阳台吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'bælkəni/","word":"balcony","phonetic_us":"/'bælkənɪ/","translation":"n.  阳台； 楼厅， 楼座"},{"phonetic_us":"/bɔl/","translation":"n. 球，球状物；舞会","word":"ball","example":"a ball of string 线团","phonetic_uk":"/bɔːl/"},{"word":"balloon","translation":"n. 气球，玩具气球","phonetic_us":"/bə'lun/","example":"Can you help me blow up these balloons? 你帮我把这些气球吹起来好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/bə'luːn/"},{"word":"ban","translation":"v. 禁止","phonetic_us":"/bæn/","example":"Smoking is banned in the building. 大楼内禁止吸烟。","phonetic_uk":"/bæn/"},{"word":"banana","translation":"n. 香蕉；芭蕉属植物","phonetic_us":"/bə'nænə/","example":"...a bunch of bananas. …一串香蕉。","phonetic_uk":"/bə'nɑːnə/"},{"word":"band","phonetic_us":"/bænd/","translation":"n. 乐队；带；波段","example":"The band was playing old Beatles songs. 乐队正在演奏披头士的老歌。","phonetic_uk":"/bænd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bæŋ/","example":"a bang on the head 头上一记猛烈的撞击","translation":"n. 巨响，枪声；猛击","phonetic_us":"/bæŋ/","word":"bang"},{"phonetic_us":"/bæŋk/","translation":"n. 银行；库；岩，堤","word":"bank","phonetic_uk":"/bæŋk/","example":"the river bank 河岸"},{"word":"bankrupt","phonetic_us":"/'bæŋkrʌpt/","translation":"adj. 破产的，倒闭的","phonetic_uk":"/'bæŋkrʌpt/","example":"The firm went bankrupt before the building work was completed. 建筑工程尚未竣工，公司就破产了。"},{"example":"The onlookers were shouting, cheering, and waving banners. 观众挥动着横幅，又是叫喊又是欢呼。","phonetic_uk":"/'bænə/","word":"banner","translation":"n. 旗，旗帜，横幅","phonetic_us":"/'bænɚ/"},{"example":"houses with bars across the windows 窗户上钉有铁条的房屋","phonetic_uk":"/bɑː/","word":"bar","translation":"n. 酒吧间；条，杆；栅","phonetic_us":"/bɑr/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'bɑːbə/","example":"My father marched me over to Otto, the local barber, to have my hair cut short. 爸爸把我拽到当地理发师奥托跟前，让他把我的头发剪短。","word":"barber","translation":"n. 理发师","phonetic_us":"/'bɑrbɚ/"},{"word":"bare","phonetic_us":"/bɛr/","translation":"adj. 赤裸的；仅仅的","example":"a ragged child with bare feet 一个衣衫褴褛、光着脚的小孩","phonetic_uk":"/beə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈbeəli/","example":"She was barely aware of his presence. 她几乎没有注意到他的存在。","translation":"adv. 仅仅，几乎不","phonetic_us":"/'bɛrli/","word":"barely"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈbɑːɡɪn/","translation":"n. 讨价还价","word":"bargain","phonetic_uk":"/ˈbɑːɡən/","example":"Is she a bawd that she should bargain? 她会是一个要讨价还价的鸨母吗?"},{"word":"bark","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 吠叫声；vi. 吠，叫","phonetic_uk":"","example":"Amy’s voice was a hoarse bark. 艾美发出的是粗哑的吼声。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/bɑːn/","phonetic_us":"/bɑrn/","translation":"n. 谷仓；牲口棚","word":"barn"},{"word":"barrel","phonetic_us":"/'bærəl/","translation":"n. 桶；圆筒；枪管","phonetic_uk":"/'bær(ə)l/","example":"The wine is aged in oak barrels. 这种葡萄酒是用橡木酒桶放陈的。"},{"example":"He advocated the removal of trade barriers. 他提倡消除贸易壁垒。","phonetic_uk":"/'bærɪə/","word":"barrier","phonetic_us":"/'bærɪɚ/","translation":"n. 栅栏，屏障；障碍"},{"phonetic_uk":"/beɪs/","example":"India has a good scientific research base. 印度有良好的科研基础。","word":"base","phonetic_us":"/bes/","translation":"n. 基础，底层；基地"},{"phonetic_us":"/'besbɔl/","translation":"n.  棒球","word":"baseball","phonetic_uk":"/'beɪsbɔːl/","example":"Yes, I like basketball and baseball. 是的，我喜欢篮球和棒球。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'besɪk/","translation":"adj. 基本的，基础的","word":"basic","example":"the basic principles of chemistry 化学的基本原理","phonetic_uk":"/'beɪsɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'besɪkli/","translation":"adv. 基本上","word":"basically","example":"Basically, I’m just lazy. 说穿了，我就是懒。","phonetic_uk":"/'beɪsɪk(ə)lɪ/"},{"word":"basin","translation":"n. 盆，洗脸盆；盆地","phonetic_us":"/'besn/","phonetic_uk":"/'beɪs(ə)n/","example":"a wash basin 洗脸盆"},{"example":"Their claim had no basis in fact (=  it was not true  ) . 他们的说法没有事实根据。","phonetic_uk":"/'beɪsɪs/","word":"basis","phonetic_us":"/'besɪs/","translation":"n. 基础，根据"},{"translation":"n. 篮，篓，筐","phonetic_us":"/'bæskɪt/","word":"basket","phonetic_uk":"/'bɑːskɪt/","example":"a shopping basket 购物篮"},{"phonetic_us":"/'bæskɪtbɔl/","translation":"n. 篮球；篮球运动","word":"basketball","phonetic_uk":"/'bɑːskɪtbɔːl/","example":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/bæt/","example":"...a baseball bat. …一只棒球棒。","phonetic_us":"/bæt/","translation":"n. 球拍；短棍；蝙蝠","word":"bat"},{"word":"bath","translation":"n. 浴，洗澡；浴缸","phonetic_us":"","phonetic_uk":"/bɑːθ/","example":"After a week of camping, I really needed a bath. 我露营了一个星期，实在得洗个澡了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/beð/","translation":"v. 给…洗澡；弄湿","word":"bathe","example":"I bathed, washed my hair, and got dressed. 我洗了澡，洗了头，然后穿上衣服。","phonetic_uk":"/beɪð/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'bɑːθruːm; -rʊm/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/'bæθrum/","translation":"n. 浴室；盥洗室","word":"bathroom"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'bætri/","example":"You have to take the top off to change the batteries . 你得把顶盖拿掉才能更换电池。","word":"battery","translation":"n. 电池；一套，一组","phonetic_us":"/'bæt(ə)rɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 战争，战役","phonetic_us":"/'bætl/","word":"battle","example":"the Battle of Trafalgar 特拉法尔加战役","phonetic_uk":"/'bætl/"},{"word":"bay","translation":"n. 湾；山脉中的凹处","phonetic_us":"/be/","example":"a house with a view across the bay 能看到海湾全景的一幢房子","phonetic_uk":"/beɪ/"},{"translation":"aux. v&vi是，在，做","phonetic_us":"/bi/","word":"be","example":"Don’t disturb me while I’m working. 我工作的时候不要打扰我。","phonetic_uk":"/biː/"},{"word":"beach","phonetic_us":"/bitʃ/","translation":"n. 海滩，湖滩，河滩","phonetic_uk":"/biːtʃ/","example":"a sandy beach 沙滩"},{"word":"beam","translation":"n. 梁；横梁；束，柱","phonetic_us":"/bim/","example":"...high-energy laser beams. …高能激光束。","phonetic_uk":"/biːm/"},{"word":"bean","phonetic_us":"/bin/","translation":"n. 豆，蚕豆","example":"baked beans 烘豆","phonetic_uk":"/biːn/"},{"example":"a mother bear and her cubs 母熊和它的熊崽们","phonetic_uk":"/beə/","word":"bear","translation":"n. 熊；粗鲁的人","phonetic_us":"/bɛr/"},{"example":"He's decided to grow a beard. 他已经决定蓄胡须。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪəd/","word":"beard","translation":"n. 胡须，络腮胡子","phonetic_us":"/bɪrd/"},{"example":"Exercise has a direct bearing on how healthy you are. 锻炼直接影响你的身体状况。","phonetic_uk":"/'beərɪŋ/","phonetic_us":"/'bɛrɪŋ/","translation":"n.  举止， 风度； 方位， 方向感； 影响","word":"bearing"},{"example":"You beast! Let go! 你这畜生，放开我！","phonetic_uk":"/biːst/","translation":"n. 兽，野兽；牲畜","phonetic_us":"/bist/","word":"beast"},{"word":"beat","translation":"vt&vi. 打，敲；打败","phonetic_us":"/bit/","phonetic_uk":"/biːt/","example":"Brazil were beaten 2–1. 巴西队以1比2告负。"},{"example":"She was even more beautiful than I had remembered. 她比我记忆中更美。","phonetic_uk":"/'bjuːtɪfʊl; -f(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 美的，美丽的","phonetic_us":"/'bjʊtəfəl/","word":"beautiful"},{"word":"beauty","phonetic_us":"/'bjuti/","translation":"n. 美，美丽；美人","phonetic_uk":"/'bjuːtɪ/","example":"her beauty and grace 她的美貌和优雅风姿"},{"word":"because","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'kɔz/","translation":"conj. 由于，因为","example":"We didn’t enjoy the day because the weather was so awful. 那天我们很不尽兴，因为天气实在太糟。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'kɒz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'kʌm/","example":"The weather became warmer. 天气变暖和了。","translation":"v. 变成；成为，变得","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'kʌm/","word":"become"},{"translation":"n. 床，床位；圃；河床","phonetic_us":"/bɛd/","word":"bed","phonetic_uk":"/bed/","example":"You should go to bed early. 你应该早点上床。"},{"translation":"n. 蜂，密蜂；忙碌的人","phonetic_us":"/bi/","word":"bee","phonetic_uk":"/biː/","example":"a swarm of bees 一群蜜蜂"},{"example":"roast beef 烤牛肉","phonetic_uk":"/biːf/","word":"beef","translation":"n. 牛肉；菜牛","phonetic_us":"/bif/"},{"word":"beer","phonetic_us":"/bɪr/","translation":"n. 啤酒","phonetic_uk":"/bɪə/","example":"a pint of beer 一品脱啤酒"},{"word":"before","translation":"prep. 在…以前；向…","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'fɔr/","example":"The new road should be completed before the end of the year. 这条新公路应该在年底前完工。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'fɔː/"},{"example":"She begged and pleaded with them until they finally agreed. 她一再恳求，后来他们终于同意了。","phonetic_uk":"/beg/","word":"beg","translation":"vt&vi. 乞求；请求","phonetic_us":"/bɛɡ/"},{"translation":"n. 乞丐，穷人","phonetic_us":"/'bɛɡɚ/","word":"beggar","example":"the beggars on the streets 街头乞丐","phonetic_uk":"/'begə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'gɪn/","example":"As everybody’s here, let’s begin. 大家都到齐了，我们就开始吧。","translation":"v. 开始；v. 开始","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'ɡɪn/","word":"begin"},{"translation":"n. 初学者，生手","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'gɪnɚ/","word":"beginner","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'gɪnə/","example":"an absolute beginner 不折不扣的初学者"},{"example":"There’s a short poem at the beginning of every chapter. 每一章的开头都有一首短诗。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'gɪnɪŋ/","word":"beginning","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'ɡɪnɪŋ/","translation":"n. 开始，开端；起源"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'hɑːf/","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'hæf/","translation":"n. 利益，维护，支持","word":"behalf"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'heɪv/","example":"She behaved in a very responsible way . 她表现得很有责任心。","translation":"v. 表现","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'hev/","word":"behave"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bɪˈheɪvjə/","example":"","word":"behavior","translation":"n. 行为，举止，态度","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'hevjɚ/"},{"word":"behind","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'haɪnd/","translation":"prep. 在…后面","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'haɪnd/","example":"I turned to speak to the person standing behind me. 我转身和站在我后面的那人说话。"},{"translation":"n. 存在；生物；生命","phonetic_us":"/'biɪŋ/","word":"being","phonetic_uk":"/'biːɪŋ/","example":"a law that first came into being in 1912 于1912年制定的一条法律"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'liːf/","example":"When you get something wrong, it can shake your belief in yourself. 如果有什么事情没做好，就会动摇你对自己的信心。","word":"belief","translation":"n. 信任，相信；信念","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'lif/"},{"example":"You shouldn’t believe everything you read. 你不应尽信书上看来的东西。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'liːv/","word":"believe","translation":"v. 相信；认为","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'liv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bel/","example":"church bells 教堂的钟","phonetic_us":"/bɛl/","translation":"n. 钟，铃，门铃；钟声","word":"bell"},{"translation":"v. 属于，附属","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'lɔŋ/","word":"belong","example":"The house had belonged to her family for three or four generations. 这座房子属于她家已有三四代了。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'lɒŋ/"},{"word":"beloved","translation":"adj. 为…的爱的；n. 爱人","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'lʌvd/","example":"He never recovered from the death of his beloved daughter. 他一直没有走出失去爱女的阴影。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'lʌvɪd; -'lʌvd/"},{"word":"below","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'lo/","translation":"prep. 在…下面(以下)","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'ləʊ/","example":"He had a bruise just below his right eye. 就在他的右眼下面有一块伤痕。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/belt/","example":"He unbuckled his leather belt. 他解开皮带。","word":"belt","translation":"n. 带，腰带；皮带；区","phonetic_us":"/bɛlt/"},{"word":"bench","phonetic_us":"/bɛntʃ/","translation":"n. 长凳，条凳；工作台","phonetic_uk":"/ben(t)ʃ/","example":"We sat on a park bench. 我们坐在公园的长椅上。"},{"translation":"v. 使弯曲；v. 弯曲","phonetic_us":"/bɛnd/","word":"bend","phonetic_uk":"/bend/","example":"Several branches started bending towards the ground. 数根枝条开始向地面弯垂。"},{"word":"beneath","phonetic_us":"/bɪˈniːθ/","translation":"prep. 在…下方","example":"The top layer should now point down to the layer beneath. 现在，顶部图层应当有小箭头指向下面的图层。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'niːθ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌbenɪˈfɪʃl/","example":"a drug that has a beneficial effect on the immune system 有益于免疫系统的一种药物","translation":"adj. 有利的，有益的","phonetic_us":"/,bɛnɪ'fɪʃl/","word":"beneficial"},{"example":"They are working together to benefit the whole community. 他们在为整个社区的利益共同努力。","phonetic_uk":"/'benɪfɪt/","translation":"v. 有益于，有助于","phonetic_us":"/'bɛnɪfɪt/","word":"benefit"},{"translation":"n. 浆果(如草莓等)","phonetic_us":"/'bɛri/","word":"berry","phonetic_uk":"/'berɪ/","example":"Whether the legend is true or not, the discovery of coffee dates back to 800 A.D. when Africans created a coffee-berry pulp. 不论这个传说是真是假，咖啡的发现要回溯到公元800年，那时非洲人制造出了一种咖啡浆果浆。"},{"example":"Wendy came up and sat beside me. 温迪走过来，坐在我身边。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'saɪd/","word":"beside","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'saɪd/","translation":"prep. 在…旁边"},{"translation":"adv. 而且prep除…之外","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'saɪdz/","word":"besides","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'saɪdz/","example":"I need the money. And besides, when I agree to do something, I do it. 我需要这笔钱，而且，我一旦答应做什么事情就会做到。"},{"example":"He won the best actor award. 他获得最佳男演员奖。","phonetic_uk":"/best/","phonetic_us":"/bɛst/","translation":"adj. 最好的；最大的","word":"best"},{"word":"bet","phonetic_us":"/bɛt/","translation":"vt&vi&n. 打赌","phonetic_uk":"/bet/","example":"How much do you want to bet? 你想赌多少钱？"},{"translation":"v. 背叛；辜负；泄漏","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'tre/","word":"betray","example":"He felt that she had betrayed him. 他感觉她背叛了自己。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'treɪ/"},{"word":"better","translation":"adj. 较好的；adv. 更好地","phonetic_us":"/'bɛtɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'betə/","example":"Your stereo is better than mine. 你的音响比我的好。"},{"word":"between","translation":"prep. 在…中间","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'twin/","example":"He supplements his regular meals by eating between meals. 他在两餐之间吃点东西来补充正餐。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'twiːn/"},{"example":"They crossed the mountains and headed for the valleys beyond. 他们翻过山，向更远处的山谷进发。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪ'jɒnd/","word":"beyond","phonetic_us":"/bɪ'jɑnd/","translation":"prep. 在…的那边"},{"word":"Bible","phonetic_us":"/'baɪbl/","translation":"n. 基督教《圣经》","phonetic_uk":"/'baɪb(ə)l/","example":"...a publisher of bibles and hymn books. …一家《圣经》册本和圣歌集出版商。"},{"example":"Can James ride a bicycle yet? 詹姆斯会骑自行车了吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'baɪsɪkl/","word":"bicycle","translation":"n. 自行车，脚踏车","phonetic_us":"/'baɪsɪkl/"},{"word":"bid","translation":"n & v. 出价，投标","phonetic_us":"/bɪd/","phonetic_uk":"/bɪd/","example":"the person who places the highest bid 出价最高的人"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bɪg/","example":"a big house 大房子","translation":"adj. 大的，巨大的","phonetic_us":"/bɪɡ/","word":"big"},{"word":"bike","translation":"n. 自行车；v. 骑自行车","phonetic_us":"/baɪk/","example":"Let’s go for a bike ride . 我们去骑会儿自行车吧。","phonetic_uk":"/baɪk/"},{"example":"Have you paid the phone bill? 电话费你付了吗？","phonetic_uk":"/bɪl/","word":"bill","translation":"n. 账单；招贴；票据","phonetic_us":"/bɪl/"},{"translation":"num. 万亿(英)","phonetic_us":"/'bɪljən/","word":"billion","phonetic_uk":"/'bɪljən/","example":"The final cost could be as much as one billion dollars. 最后的费用可能高达十亿美元。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/baɪnd/","example":"Bind the ends of the cord together with thread. 把细绳的两端用线系在一起。","word":"bind","phonetic_us":"/baɪnd/","translation":"v. 捆绑；包扎；装钉"},{"phonetic_us":"/,baɪə'lɑdʒɪkl/","translation":"adj. 生物的","word":"biological","phonetic_uk":"/ˌbaɪəˈlɒdʒɪkl/","example":"the biological functions of the body 人体的生物机能"},{"word":"biology","phonetic_us":"/baɪ'ɑlədʒi/","translation":"n. 生物学；生态学","example":"a degree in biology 生物学学位","phonetic_uk":"/baɪ'ɒlədʒɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'baɪotɛk'nɑlədʒi/","translation":"n.  生物工艺学","word":"biotechnology","example":"the biotech industries 生物技术产业","phonetic_uk":"/ˌbaɪəutek'nɒlədʒi/"},{"word":"bird","translation":"n. 鸟，禽","phonetic_us":"/bɝd/","example":"wild birds 野鸟","phonetic_uk":"/bɜːd/"},{"word":"birth","translation":"n. 分娩，出生；出身","phonetic_us":"/bɝθ/","phonetic_uk":"/bɜːθ/","example":"Congratulations on the birth of your daughter! 恭喜你生了个女儿！"},{"phonetic_us":"/'bɝθde/","translation":"n. 生日，诞生的日期","word":"birthday","phonetic_uk":"/'bɜːθdeɪ/","example":"It’s my birthday on Monday. 星期一是我的生日。"},{"word":"biscuit","phonetic_us":"/'bɪskɪt/","translation":"n. (英)饼干；(美)软饼","phonetic_uk":"/'bɪskɪt/","example":"a packet of chocolate biscuits 一包巧克力饼干"},{"translation":"n. 一点，一些，小片","phonetic_us":"/bɪt/","word":"bit","example":"He’s taken the engine to bits . 他把发动机拆开了。","phonetic_uk":"/bɪt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/baɪt/","translation":"v. 咬，叮，螫；剌穿","word":"bite","phonetic_uk":"/baɪt/","example":"The dog bit him and made his hand bleed. 那只狗把他的手咬出血了。"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 痛苦的；严寒的","word":"bitter","phonetic_uk":"","example":"His photo stirred up bitter memories. 他的照片勾起了痛苦的回忆。"},{"word":"bitterly","phonetic_us":"/'bɪtɚli/","translation":"adv. 苦苦地；悲痛地","example":"He complained bitterly about his exam grades. 他悲叹自己的考试成绩不好。","phonetic_uk":"/'bɪtəlɪ/"},{"translation":"adj. 黑色的；黑暗的","phonetic_us":"/blæk/","word":"black","example":"a black evening dress 黑色晚礼服","phonetic_uk":"/blæk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'blækbɔrd/","translation":"n. 黑板","word":"blackboard","example":"He chalked out a design on the blackboard. 他用粉笔在黑板上勾划出一个图样。","phonetic_uk":"/'blækbɔːd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bleɪd/","example":"a razor blade 剃刀刀片","word":"blade","translation":"n. 刀刃，刀片；叶片","phonetic_us":"/bled/"},{"word":"blame","phonetic_us":"/blem/","translation":"v. 指责，责怪","phonetic_uk":"/bleɪm/","example":"Don’t blame me – it’s not my fault. 别来怪我——又不是我的错。"},{"translation":"adj. 空白的；n. 空白","phonetic_us":"/blæŋk/","word":"blank","example":"Leave the last page blank . 最后一页留空。","phonetic_uk":"/blæŋk/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'blæŋkɪt/","phonetic_us":"/'blæŋkɪt/","translation":"n. 毛毯，毯子，羊毛毯","word":"blanket"},{"word":"blast","translation":"n. 爆炸，冲击波；v. 炸","phonetic_us":"/blæst/","phonetic_uk":"/blɑːst/","example":"250 people were killed in the blast. 250人在这次大爆炸中丧生。"},{"word":"blaze","translation":"n. 火；闪光；v. 燃烧","phonetic_us":"/blez/","example":"Some 4,000 firefighters are battling the blaze. 约有四千名消防人员正在与大火搏斗。","phonetic_uk":"/bleɪz/"},{"example":"Your nose is bleeding. 你的鼻子流血了。","phonetic_uk":"/bliːd/","word":"bleed","translation":"v. 出血，流血；泌脂","phonetic_us":"/blid/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/blend/","example":"Blend the sugar, eggs, and flour. 把糖、鸡蛋和面粉掺在一起。","word":"blend","translation":"vt&vi&n. 混和","phonetic_us":"/blɛnd/"},{"word":"bless","phonetic_us":"/blɛs/","translation":"v. 祝福","example":"May God bless you. 愿上帝保佑你。","phonetic_uk":"/bles/"},{"translation":"adj. 瞎的；盲目的","phonetic_us":"/blaɪnd/","word":"blind","phonetic_uk":"/blaɪnd/","example":"David's good looks and impeccable manners had always made her blind to his faults. 大卫俊朗的外表和完美的风度总是令她对他的缺点视而不见。"},{"word":"block","translation":"v. 阻碍；街区","phonetic_us":"/blɑk/","example":"The Senate blocked publication of the report. 参议院阻止这个报告发表。","phonetic_uk":"/blɒk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/blʌd/","example":"Her body was found in a pool of blood. 她的尸体被发现倒在血泊之中。","translation":"n. 血，血液；血统","phonetic_us":"/blʌd/","word":"blood"},{"word":"bloody","translation":"adv. [用于加强语气]非常，很；adj. [用于加强语气]非常的；该死的；流血的；嗜杀的；vt.  血染","phonetic_us":"/'blʌdi/","example":"It serves you bloody well right. 你实在是活该。","phonetic_uk":"/'blʌdi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bluːm/","example":"beautiful red blooms 美丽的红花","word":"bloom","phonetic_us":"/blum/","translation":"n. 花；开花，开花期"},{"example":"pale pink blossoms 淡粉色的花朵","phonetic_uk":"/'blɒs(ə)m/","phonetic_us":"/'blɑsəm/","translation":"n. 花，开花；v. 开花","word":"blossom"},{"word":"blow","translation":"v. 吹，吹动；吹响","phonetic_us":"/blo/","example":"A cold breeze was blowing hard . 寒风劲吹。","phonetic_uk":"/bləʊ/"},{"example":"the blue waters of the lake 蓝蓝的湖水","phonetic_uk":"/bluː/","phonetic_us":"/blu/","translation":"adj. 蓝色的；n. 蓝色","word":"blue"},{"phonetic_us":"/bɔrd/","translation":"n. 板；v. 上(船、车等)","word":"board","phonetic_uk":"/bɔːd/","example":"Martha was chopping vegetables on a wooden board. 玛莎正在用一块木砧板切蔬菜。"},{"word":"boast","translation":"v. 自夸；v. 吹嘘","phonetic_us":"/bost/","phonetic_uk":"/bəʊst/","example":"‘I wouldn’t be afraid,’ she boasted. “我才不怕呢。”她吹嘘道。"},{"example":"a fishing boat 渔船","phonetic_uk":"/bəʊt/","word":"boat","translation":"n. 小船，艇；渔船","phonetic_us":"/bot/"},{"translation":"n. 身体；主体；尸体","phonetic_us":"/'bɑdi/","word":"body","example":"the human body 人体","phonetic_uk":"/'bɒdɪ/"},{"translation":"adj. 假冒的","phonetic_us":"/'bogəs/","word":"bogus","phonetic_uk":"/'bəʊɡəs/","example":"bogus insurance claims 虚报的保险索赔"},{"translation":"v. 沸腾；汽化vt煮沸","phonetic_us":"/bɔɪl/","word":"boil","phonetic_uk":"/bɒɪl/","example":"Put the spaghetti into plenty of boiling salted water. 把意大利面放入大量煮沸的盐水中。"},{"word":"bold","phonetic_us":"/bold/","translation":"adj. 大胆的；冒失的","example":"In a surprisingly bold move , he is threatening court action against the company. 他出人意料地做出一个大胆举动，威胁要起诉这家公司。","phonetic_uk":"/bəʊld/"},{"example":"He reminded her that he would have to lock and bolt the kitchen door after her. 他提醒她，他得在她离开后锁上厨房的门并插上门闩。","phonetic_uk":"/bəʊlt/","phonetic_us":"/bolt/","translation":"n. 螺栓；插销；v. 闩门","word":"bolt"},{"word":"bomb","phonetic_us":"/bɑm/","translation":"n. 炸弹；v. 轰炸","phonetic_uk":"/bɒm/","example":"The bomb went off at 9.30 in the morning. 炸弹在早上9点半爆炸。"},{"example":"My father put all his money into stock market bonds. 我父亲把他所有的钱都投在上市债券上。","phonetic_uk":"/bɒnd/","translation":"n. 联结，联系；公债","phonetic_us":"/bɑnd/","word":"bond"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bəʊn/","example":"The X-ray showed that the bone was broken in two places. X光检查显示有两处骨折。","word":"bone","translation":"n. 骨，骨骼","phonetic_us":"/bon/"},{"translation":"n. 书，书籍；v. 预定","phonetic_us":"/bʊk/","word":"book","example":"I’ve just started reading a book by Graham Greene. 我刚开始看格雷厄姆·格林写的一本书。","phonetic_uk":"/bʊk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/buːm/","example":"Business was booming , and money wasn’t a problem. 生意非常兴隆，钱已不是问题。","phonetic_us":"/buːm/","translation":"vi.  激增， 繁荣， 迅速发展； 发出隆隆声；n. 激增，繁荣，迅速发展；隆隆声，嗡嗡声","word":"boom"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bu:st/","example":"It would get the economy going and give us the boost that we need. 这会推动经济发展并带给我们所需要的推动力。","word":"boost","phonetic_us":"/bʊst/","translation":"n. 推动,宣扬；v. 促使，促进"},{"word":"boot","translation":"n. 靴子，长统靴","phonetic_us":"/but/","phonetic_uk":"/buːt/","example":"hiking boots 远足靴"},{"phonetic_us":"/bʊθ/","translation":"n. 货摊；公用电话亭","word":"booth","example":"I called her from a public phone booth near the entrance to the bar. 我在酒吧入口附近的一个公用电话亭给她打了电话。","phonetic_uk":"/buːð; buːθ/"},{"translation":"n. 边，边缘；边界","phonetic_us":"","word":"border","example":"writing paper with a black border 饰有黑边的信纸","phonetic_uk":""},{"example":"He’s the sort of person who bores you at parties. 他这人会在派对上烦你。","phonetic_uk":"/bɔː/","translation":"v. 使厌烦；钻，挖","phonetic_us":"/bɔr/","word":"bore"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'bɔːrɪŋ/","example":"Her husband is about the most boring person I’ve ever met. 她丈夫可以说是我见过的最无聊的人。","word":"boring","translation":"adj.  令人厌烦的， 乏味的， 无聊的","phonetic_us":"/'bɔrɪŋ/"},{"example":"the skill of a born actor 天生的表演技巧","phonetic_uk":"/bɔːn/","word":"born","phonetic_us":"/bɔrn/","translation":"adj. 天生的；出生的"},{"word":"borrow","phonetic_us":"/'bɑro/","translation":"v. 借，借用，借人","example":"Can I borrow your pen for a minute? 我可以借你的笔用一下吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'bɒrəʊ/"},{"translation":"n. 胸，胸部；内心","phonetic_us":"/'bʊzəm/","word":"bosom","phonetic_uk":"/'bʊz(ə)m/","example":"She cradled the child to her bosom. 她把那孩子抱入怀中。"},{"translation":"n. 老板，上司；v. 指挥","phonetic_us":"/bɑs/","word":"boss","phonetic_uk":"/bɒs/","example":"I’ll have to ask my boss for a day off. 我得向老板请一天假。"},{"translation":"pron. 两者(都)","phonetic_us":"/boθ/","word":"both","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/bəʊθ/"},{"example":"Why bother to go abroad, when there are so many nice places here? 这里有这么多好地方，干吗还要费事去国外？","phonetic_uk":"/'bɔðə/","word":"bother","phonetic_us":"/'bɑðɚ/","translation":"v. 打扰；麻烦"},{"phonetic_us":"/'bɑtl/","translation":"n. 瓶，酒瓶；一瓶","word":"bottle","example":"an empty bottle 一个空瓶子","phonetic_uk":"/'bɒt(ə)l/"},{"word":"bottom","translation":"n. 底，底部，根基","phonetic_us":"/'bɑtəm/","phonetic_uk":"/'bɒtəm/","example":"The drugs had been hidden in a suitcase with a false bottom. 毒品藏在一个带假底板的行李箱里。"},{"translation":"n. 树枝","phonetic_us":"/baʊ/","word":"bough","example":"I rested my fishing rod against a pine bough. 我把我的鱼竿靠在松树的一个大树枝上。","phonetic_uk":"/baʊ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/baʊns/","translation":"v. 反跳，弹起；跳起","word":"bounce","example":"Stop bouncing up and down on the sofa. 别在沙发上蹦来蹦去了。","phonetic_uk":"/baʊns/"},{"word":"bound","translation":"adj. 一定的；有义务的","phonetic_us":"/baʊnd/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/baʊnd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'baʊnd(ə)rɪ/","example":"National boundaries are becoming increasingly meaningless in the global economy. 在全球经济中，国界已经变得越来越没有意义。","word":"boundary","translation":"n. 分界线，边界","phonetic_us":"/'baʊndri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/baʊ/","example":"She bowed and left the stage. 她鞠了一躬，离开了舞台。","phonetic_us":"/baʊ/","translation":"v. 鞠躬","word":"bow"},{"word":"bowl","phonetic_us":"/bol/","translation":"n. 碗，钵；碗状物","example":"Mix all the ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl. 将所有配料放在大碗里搅拌均匀。","phonetic_uk":"/bəʊl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bɒks/","example":"Jim watched the game from a private box. 吉姆在私人包厢里观看比赛。","phonetic_us":"/bɑks/","translation":"n. 箱，盒；包箱","word":"box"},{"translation":"n. 男孩，少年；家伙","phonetic_us":"/bɔɪ/","word":"boy","example":"The boys wanted to play football. 男孩子们想踢足球。","phonetic_uk":"/bɒɪ/"},{"word":"bracket","translation":"n. 括号；vt.  把…归为同一类","phonetic_us":"/'brækɪt/","example":"I think you should bracket this word. 我认为你应该给这个字加上括号。","phonetic_uk":"/'brækɪt/"},{"word":"brain","phonetic_us":"/bren/","translation":"n. 脑，脑髓；脑力","example":"Messages from the brain are carried by the central nervous system. 大脑发出的信息是通过中枢神经系统传递的。","phonetic_uk":"/breɪn/"},{"word":"brake","translation":"n. 闸，刹车；v. 制动","phonetic_us":"/brek/","phonetic_uk":"/breɪk/","example":"Test your brakes after driving through water. 车子涉水之后要检验一下刹车。"},{"example":"After the storm, the ground was littered with twigs and branches. 暴风雨过后，满地都是大大小小的树枝。","phonetic_uk":"/brɑːn(t)ʃ/","phonetic_us":"/bræntʃ/","translation":"n. 树枝；分部；分科","word":"branch"},{"example":"Winston is a brand of cigarette. 云斯顿是一种香烟品牌。","phonetic_uk":"/brænd/","word":"brand","phonetic_us":"/brænd/","translation":"n. 商品；烙印；v. 铭刻"},{"word":"brandy","phonetic_us":"/'brændi/","translation":"n. 白兰地酒","phonetic_uk":"/'brændɪ/","example":"After a couple of brandies Michael started telling me his life story. 几杯白兰地酒过后,迈克尔开始向我讲述他的人生故事。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/brɑːs/","example":"an old brass bedstead 老式黄铜床架","word":"brass","phonetic_us":"/bræs/","translation":"n. 黄铜；黄铜器"},{"example":"brave soldiers 勇敢的士兵","phonetic_uk":"/breɪv/","word":"brave","translation":"adj. 勇敢的，华丽的","phonetic_us":"/brev/"},{"translation":"n. 面包；食物，粮食","phonetic_us":"/brɛd/","word":"bread","example":"Would you like some bread with your soup? 你喝汤时要吃点面包吗？","phonetic_uk":"/bred/"},{"word":"breadth","phonetic_us":"/brɛdθ/","translation":"n. 宽度，幅度；幅面","phonetic_uk":"/bredθ; -t-/","example":"We need to provide more breadth in the college curriculum. 我们需要扩大学院课程的范围。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/breɪk/","example":"The silence was broken by a loud scream. 一声尖叫打破了寂静。","phonetic_us":"/brek/","translation":"v. 打破；损坏；破坏","word":"break"},{"word":"breakdown","phonetic_us":"/'brek'daʊn/","translation":"n.  垮， 衰竭； 损坏， 故障； 倒塌","phonetic_uk":"/'breɪkdaun/","example":"Always carry a phone with you in case you have a breakdown on the motorway. 一定要随身带电话，以防汽车在高速公路上抛锚。"},{"translation":"n. 早饭，早餐","phonetic_us":"/'brɛkfəst/","word":"breakfast","example":"We had bacon and eggs for breakfast . 我们早餐吃了熏肉鸡蛋。","phonetic_uk":"/'brekfəst/"},{"word":"breakthrough","phonetic_us":"/'brek'θrʊ/","translation":"n. 突破","example":"The company looks poised to make a significant breakthrough in China. 该公司看上去稳将在中国实现一次重大突破。","phonetic_uk":"/'breɪkθruː/"},{"word":"breast","phonetic_us":"/brɛst/","translation":"n. 乳房；胸脯，胸膛","example":"These bras are specially designed for women with large breasts. 这些胸罩专为乳房丰满的女性设计。","phonetic_uk":"/brest/"},{"phonetic_us":"/brɛθ/","translation":"n. 气息，呼吸；气味","word":"breath","phonetic_uk":"/breθ/","example":"Slow down, I need to catch my breath. 慢一点，我要喘口气。"},{"example":"The room filled with smoke, and it was becoming difficult to breathe. 房间里全是烟，呼吸越来越困难。","phonetic_uk":"/briːð/","phonetic_us":"/brið/","translation":"v. 呼吸；v. 呼吸","word":"breathe"},{"translation":"n. 品种；v. 使繁殖","phonetic_us":"/brid/","word":"breed","phonetic_uk":"/briːd/","example":"Real cowboys are a dying breed (=  not many exist anymore  ) . 真正的牛仔现在已非常少见。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/briːz/","example":"flowers waving in the breeze 在微风中摇曳的花儿","word":"breeze","phonetic_us":"/briz/","translation":"n. 微风，和风"},{"word":"brick","translation":"n. 砖，砖块；砖状物","phonetic_us":"/brɪk/","example":"a brick wall 砖墙","phonetic_uk":"/brɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/braɪd/","example":"Guests toasted the bride and groom with champagne. 客人们以香槟为新娘新郎敬酒。","word":"bride","phonetic_us":"/braɪd/","translation":"n. 新娘"},{"example":"He walked back over the railway bridge. 他从铁路桥上走了回去。","phonetic_uk":"/brɪdʒ/","word":"bridge","translation":"n. 桥，桥梁；桥牌","phonetic_us":"/brɪdʒ/"},{"example":"We stopped by Alice’s house for a brief visit. 我们顺路在艾丽斯家小坐片刻。","phonetic_uk":"/briːf/","word":"brief","phonetic_us":"/brif/","translation":"adj. 简短的；短暂的"},{"word":"bright","phonetic_us":"/braɪt/","translation":"adj. 明亮的；聪明的","phonetic_uk":"/braɪt/","example":"Her eyes were hurting from the bright lights. 明亮的光线刺痛了她的眼睛。"},{"example":"Use blonde highlights to brighten your hair. 用点金色的挑染，让你的发色明亮起来。","phonetic_uk":"/'braɪt(ə)n/","translation":"v. 使发光；使快活","phonetic_us":"/'braɪtn/","word":"brighten"},{"example":"She closed her eyes against the brilliant light . 强烈的光线下，她闭起了眼睛。","phonetic_uk":"/'brɪlj(ə)nt/","word":"brilliant","translation":"adj. 光辉的；卓越的","phonetic_us":"/'brɪljənt/"},{"translation":"n. 边，边缘；帽沿","phonetic_us":"/brɪm/","word":"brim","example":"an old straw hat with a broad brim 一顶旧的宽边草帽","phonetic_uk":"/brɪm/"},{"word":"bring","translation":"v. 带来；引出；促使","phonetic_us":"/brɪŋ/","example":"The discovery of gold brought thousands of people to the Transvaal. 黄金的发现把成千上万的人引到了德兰士瓦。","phonetic_uk":"/brɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/brɪsk/","example":"a brisk walk 轻快的行走","phonetic_us":"/brɪsk/","translation":"adj. 活泼的；清新的","word":"brisk"},{"word":"bristle","phonetic_us":"/'brɪsl/","translation":"n. 短而硬的毛；鬃毛","phonetic_uk":"/'brɪs(ə)l/","example":"His chin was covered with bristles. 他满下巴都是胡茬。"},{"example":"This is the stud  naturalized from Britain. 这是从不列颠引进的种马。","phonetic_uk":"/'brɪt(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'brɪtən/","translation":"n. 不列颠，英国","word":"Britain"},{"phonetic_us":"/'brɪtɪʃ/","translation":"adj. 不列颠的，英联邦的","word":"British","example":"the British government 英国政府","phonetic_uk":"/'brɪtɪʃ/"},{"example":"But while our screens are brittle, theirs is flexible––at what they say is one tenth the price. 但我们的屏幕都很脆弱，他们的却很柔软，而且价钱是我们的十分之一。","phonetic_uk":"","word":"brittle","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 脆的；易损坏的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/brɔːd/","example":"We went along a broad passage. 我们走在一条宽阔的走廊上。","translation":"adj. 宽的","phonetic_us":"/brɔd/","word":"broad"},{"example":"a news broadcast 一档新闻节目","phonetic_uk":"/'brɔːdkɑːst/","translation":"n. 广播，播音","phonetic_us":"/'brɔdkæst/","word":"broadcast"},{"example":"a badly broken leg 严重骨折的腿","phonetic_uk":"/'brəʊk(ə)n/","word":"broken","translation":"adj. 被打碎的，骨折的","phonetic_us":"/'brokən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/brɒnz/","example":"a bell cast in bronze 青铜浇铸的一口钟","word":"bronze","translation":"n. 青铜；青铜制品","phonetic_us":"/brɑnz/"},{"translation":"n. 同窝幼鸟；v. 孵(蛋)","phonetic_us":"/brud/","word":"brood","phonetic_uk":"/bruːd/","example":"...a hungry brood of fledglings. …一窝饥饿的雏鸟。"},{"word":"brook","phonetic_us":"/brʊk/","translation":"n. 小河，溪流","phonetic_uk":"/brʊk/","example":"a babbling brook 潺潺的小溪"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bruːm/","example":"The lobby is empty but for the postman and his broom. 大厅里除了邮差和他的扫帚以外别无他人。","translation":"n. 扫帚","phonetic_us":"/brum/","word":"broom"},{"example":"I have two brothers, William and Mark. 我有两个兄弟，威廉和马克。","phonetic_uk":"/'brʌðə/","word":"brother","translation":"n. 兄弟；同事，同胞","phonetic_us":"/'brʌðɚ/"},{"example":"He wiped his brow with the back of his hand. 他用手背擦了擦额头。","phonetic_uk":"/braʊ/","phonetic_us":"/braʊ/","translation":"n. 额；眉，眉毛","word":"brow"},{"example":"This particular model is available in brown, white, or grey. 这个型号的产品有棕色、白色和灰色的。","phonetic_uk":"/braʊn/","word":"brown","translation":"n. 褐色，棕色","phonetic_us":"/braʊn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bruːz/","example":"minor cuts and bruises 轻微的伤口和淤青","translation":"n. 青肿，伤痕；擦伤","phonetic_us":"/bruz/","word":"bruise"},{"example":"a scrubbing brush 硬毛刷，板刷","phonetic_uk":"/brʌʃ/","word":"brush","phonetic_us":"/brʌʃ/","translation":"n. 刷子，毛刷；画笔"},{"phonetic_uk":"/bruːt/","example":"","word":"brute","phonetic_us":"/brut/","translation":"n. 禽兽，畜生"},{"example":"When water boils, bubbles rise to the surface. 水烧开时，水面会冒泡泡。","phonetic_uk":"/'bʌb(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/'bʌbl/","translation":"n. 泡；v. 冒泡，沸腾","word":"bubble"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'bʌkɪt/","translation":"n. 水桶；吊桶；铲斗","phonetic_us":"/'bʌkɪt/","word":"bucket"},{"example":"rose buds 玫瑰花苞","phonetic_uk":"/bʌd/","word":"bud","translation":"n. 芽，萌芽；蓓蕾","phonetic_us":"/bʌd/"},{"example":"We had a really tight budget . 我们的预算很紧。","phonetic_uk":"/'bʌdʒit/","word":"budget","phonetic_us":"/'bʌdʒɪt/","translation":"n. 预算；v. 编预算"},{"phonetic_us":"/bɪld/","translation":"v. 建筑；建立；创立","word":"build","phonetic_uk":"/bɪld/","example":"The purpose is to build new houses for local people. 目的是要为当地居民建造新的住宅。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'bɪldɪŋ/","translation":"n. 建筑物，大楼；建筑","word":"building","phonetic_uk":"/'bɪldɪŋ/","example":"The offices are on the top two floors of the building. 办公室在大楼最高的两层。"},{"translation":"n. 电灯泡；球状物","phonetic_us":"/bʌlb/","word":"bulb","phonetic_uk":"/bʌlb/","example":"a 100-watt bulb 一个100瓦的灯泡"},{"word":"bulk","phonetic_us":"/bʌlk/","translation":"n. 物体，容积，大批","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/bʌlk/"},{"example":"a herd of cows with one bull 一群母牛加一头公牛","phonetic_uk":"/bʊl/","translation":"n. 公牛；雄的象","phonetic_us":"","word":"bull"},{"translation":"n. 枪弹，子弹，弹丸","phonetic_us":"/'bʊlɪt/","word":"bullet","phonetic_uk":"/'bʊlɪt/","example":"He was killed by a single bullet. 他被一枪打死。"},{"word":"bump","translation":"vi. 碰，撞；颠簸着前进；n.  碰撞， 猛撞； 肿块； 隆起物","phonetic_us":"/bʌmp/","phonetic_uk":"/bʌmp/","example":"The roof was so low he bumped his head (=  his head hit the roof  ) . 屋顶很低，他都碰到头了。"},{"word":"bunch","translation":"n. 束，球，串；一群","phonetic_us":"/bʌntʃ/","phonetic_uk":"/bʌn(t)ʃ/","example":"The ancient Egyptians were a clever bunch. 古埃及人很聪明。"},{"word":"bundle","phonetic_us":"/'bʌndl/","translation":"n. 捆，包，束；包袱","example":"a small bundle containing mostly clothing 一个小包袱，里面主要是衣服","phonetic_uk":"/'bʌnd(ə)l/"},{"example":"His family responsibilities had started to become a burden. 家庭责任已开始成为他的负担。","phonetic_uk":"/'bɜ:dn/","word":"burden","phonetic_us":"/'bɝdn/","translation":"n. 负担，包袱"},{"word":"bureau","phonetic_us":"/'bjʊro/","translation":"n. 局","example":"the Federal Bureau of Investigation 联邦调查局","phonetic_uk":"/'bjʊərəʊ/"},{"translation":"v. 烧，燃烧；n. 烧伤","phonetic_us":"/bɝn/","word":"burn","phonetic_uk":"/bɜːn/","example":"I burnt all his old letters. 我把他以前的信全烧了。"},{"example":"The pipes had burst and the house was under two feet of water. 水管爆裂，房子被水淹了两英尺。","phonetic_uk":"/bɜːst/","phonetic_us":"/bɝst/","translation":"v. 使爆裂；vi&n. 爆炸","word":"burst"},{"example":"Electric cables are buried beneath the streets. 电缆埋在街道的下面。","phonetic_uk":"/'berɪ/","translation":"v. 埋葬，葬；埋藏","phonetic_us":"/'bɛri/","word":"bury"},{"word":"bus","translation":"n. 公共汽车","phonetic_us":"/bʌs/","example":"I took a bus to San Francisco. 我乘公共汽车去旧金山。","phonetic_uk":"/bʌs/"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 灌木，灌木丛，矮树","word":"bush","phonetic_uk":"/bʊʃ/","example":"a rose bush 玫瑰丛"},{"word":"business","phonetic_us":"/ˈbɪznəs/","translation":"n. 商业，生意；事务","example":"Students on the course learn about all aspects of business. 这门课程的学生要学习商业活动的各个方面。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈbɪznɪs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'bɪzɪ/","example":"She’s busy now – can you phone later? 她现在正忙，你稍后打来好吗？","phonetic_us":"/'bɪzi/","translation":"adj. 忙的，繁忙的","word":"busy"},{"phonetic_us":"/bʌt/","translation":"conj. 但是，可是","word":"but","example":"It’s an old car, but it’s very reliable. 这是一辆旧车，但是性能非常可靠。","phonetic_uk":"/bʌt; bət/"},{"word":"butcher","translation":"n. 屠夫；屠杀者","phonetic_us":"/ˈbʊtʃər/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ˈbʊtʃə(r)/"},{"word":"butter","translation":"n. 黄油；奶油","phonetic_us":"/'bʌtɚ/","example":"He spread some butter on his bread. 他在面包上涂了些黄油。","phonetic_uk":"/'bʌtə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'bʌtɚflaɪ/","translation":"n. 蝴蝶","word":"butterfly","phonetic_uk":"/'bʌtəflaɪ/","example":"Butterflies and moths are attracted to the wild flowers. 蝴蝶和飞蛾为野花所吸引。"},{"word":"button","phonetic_us":"/'bʌtn/","translation":"n. 扣子；按钮；v. 扣紧","phonetic_uk":"/[ˈbʌtn]/","example":"small pearl buttons 小的珍珠纽扣"},{"phonetic_uk":"/baɪ/","example":"People say the judge had been bought by the Mafia. 人们都说法官被黑手党收买了。","translation":"v. 买，购买；v. 买","phonetic_us":"/baɪ/","word":"buy"},{"example":"I was attacked by a dog. 我被一条狗袭击。","phonetic_uk":"/baɪ/","word":"by","translation":"prep. 在…旁；被，由","phonetic_us":"/baɪ/"},{"example":"I hate eating cabbage. 我讨厌吃卷心菜。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkæbɪdʒ/","word":"cabbage","phonetic_us":"/ˈkæbɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 洋白菜，卷心菜"},{"translation":"n. 小屋；船舱，机舱","phonetic_us":"/'kæbɪn/","word":"cabin","phonetic_uk":"/'kæbɪn/","example":"a log cabin 原木小屋"},{"translation":"n. 橱，柜；内阁","phonetic_us":"/'kæbɪnət/","word":"cabinet","example":"a cabinet meeting 内阁会议","phonetic_uk":"/'kæbɪnɪt/"},{"example":"cables and switches for computers 电脑的缆线和开关","phonetic_uk":"/'keɪb(ə)l/","word":"cable","translation":"n. 缆，索；电缆；电报","phonetic_us":"/'kebl/"},{"word":"cafe","phonetic_us":"/kæ'fe/","translation":"n. 咖啡馆；小餐厅","phonetic_uk":"/'kæfeɪ; 'kæfɪ/","example":"We went to a cafe and lazed the whole afternoon away there. 我们去了一间咖啡馆，在那儿消磨了整个下午。"},{"translation":"n. 自助食堂","phonetic_us":"/,kæfə'tɪrɪə/","word":"cafeteria","example":"the school cafeteria 学校餐厅","phonetic_uk":"/kæfɪ'tɪərɪə/"},{"translation":"n. 笼；鸟笼，囚笼","phonetic_us":"/kedʒ/","word":"cage","phonetic_uk":"/keɪdʒ/","example":"I hate to see birds in cages. 我不喜欢看到鸟在笼子里。"},{"translation":"n. 饼，糕，蛋糕","phonetic_us":"/kek/","word":"cake","phonetic_uk":"/keɪk/","example":"We had cake and ice cream. 我们吃了蛋糕和冰激凌。"},{"word":"calculate","translation":"v. 计算","phonetic_us":"/'kælkjulet/","example":"These instruments calculate distances precisely. 这些仪器计算距离非常精确。","phonetic_uk":"/'kælkjʊleɪt/"},{"word":"calculation","phonetic_us":"/,kælkju'leʃən/","translation":"n. 计算，计算结果","example":"Leonard made a rapid calculation: he'd never make it in time. 伦纳德做了个快速的估算：他不可能及时做完。","phonetic_uk":"/kælkjʊ'leɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"example":"...a pocket calculator. …一个袖珍计算器。","phonetic_uk":"/'kælkjʊleɪtə/","word":"calculator","phonetic_us":"/'kælkjuletɚ/","translation":"n. 计算器，计算者"},{"word":"calendar","translation":"n. 日历，历书；历法","phonetic_us":"/'kæləndɚ/","example":"There was a calendar on the wall above, with large squares around the dates. 墙的上方曾有一本日历，日期框在大方格里。","phonetic_uk":"/'kælɪndə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɔːl/","example":"You may call it harmless fun, but I call it pornography. 你可能会说这是无恶意的小玩笑，但是我却认为这是色情。","translation":"v. 把…叫做；叫，喊","phonetic_us":"/kɔl/","word":"call"},{"example":"Glen was calm and composed at the funeral. 格伦在葬礼上表现得平静而镇定。","phonetic_uk":"/kɑːm/","phonetic_us":"/kɑm/","translation":"adj. 静的，平静的","word":"calm"},{"translation":"n. 骆驼","phonetic_us":"/'kæml/","word":"camel","example":"When fresh food and water are not available,the camel can feed off its hump. 在没有新食物和水供应时，骆驼从它的驼峰中获取能量。","phonetic_uk":"/'kæm(ə)l/"},{"example":"Her grandmother lent her a camera for a school trip to Venice and Egypt. 她的祖母借给她一部相机，让她在学校组织的到威尼斯和埃及的旅行中使用。","phonetic_uk":"/'kæm(ə)rə/","phonetic_us":"/'kæmərə/","translation":"n. 照相机，摄影机","word":"camera"},{"translation":"n. 野营，营地，兵营","phonetic_us":"/kæmp/","word":"camp","example":"Let’s go back to camp – it’s getting dark. 我们回营地吧，天快黑了。","phonetic_uk":"/kæmp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kæm'peɪn/","example":"Jones ran a good campaign. 琼斯的活动搞得很成功。","translation":"n. 活动","phonetic_us":"/kæm'pen/","word":"campaign"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kæmpəs/","translation":"n. 校园，学校场地","word":"campus","example":"a beautiful campus in New England 新英格兰的一个美丽校园","phonetic_uk":"/'kæmpəs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kæn/","example":"","translation":"n. 罐头，听头；容器","phonetic_us":"/kæn/","word":"can"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kænədə/","example":"She was domiciliated in Canada. 她在加拿大定居。","word":"Canada","phonetic_us":"/'kænədə/","translation":"n. 加拿大"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kə'neɪdɪən/","example":"What about the Canadian policy? 那么加拿大的政策呢？","word":"Canadian","phonetic_us":"/kə'nedɪən/","translation":"adj. 加拿大的"},{"phonetic_us":"/kə'næl/","translation":"n. 运河；沟渠；管","word":"canal","phonetic_uk":"/kə'næl/","example":"We walked along by the side of the canal. 我们沿着运河边往前走。"},{"word":"cancel","translation":"v. 取消","phonetic_us":"/'kænsl/","example":"Our flight was cancelled. 我们的航班取消了。","phonetic_uk":"/'kænsl/"},{"example":"A lot of cancers can now be treated successfully. 现在许多癌症可以治愈。","phonetic_uk":"/'kænsə/","word":"cancer","phonetic_us":"/'kænsɚ/","translation":"n. 癌，癌症，肿瘤"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kændidit/","example":"a presidential candidate 总统候选人","word":"candidate","translation":"n. 申请求职者；投考者；候选人","phonetic_us":"/ˈkændɪˌdet, -dɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kænd(ə)l/","example":"When the candle was only half an inch high it flickered out and the room became dark. 蜡烛只有半英寸长时，烛光忽闪忽闪地熄灭了，于是房间一片漆黑。","word":"candle","translation":"n. 蜡烛；烛形物；烛光","phonetic_us":"/'kændl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kændi/","translation":"n. 糖果；砂糖结晶","word":"candy","phonetic_uk":"/'kændɪ/","example":"a box of candies 一盒糖果"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kænən/","example":"The cannons boom, the band plays. 炮声隆隆，鼓乐齐鸣。","word":"cannon","phonetic_us":"/'kænən/","translation":"n. 大炮，火炮；榴弹炮"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kə'nuː/","example":"At a summer job working as park naturalists that year, I flipped the canoe Air and I were paddling and we had to push it to shore. 那年我在公园里做暑期兼职，我把独木舟翻转个身，然后我们一起合力将它推到岸边，这样我们就可以划船了。","translation":"n. 独木舟，皮艇，划子","phonetic_us":"/kə'nu/","word":"canoe"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kæn'tiːn/","example":"Rennie had eaten his supper in the canteen. 伦尼已在食堂吃过晚饭。","word":"canteen","phonetic_us":"/kænˈtiːn/","translation":"n. 食堂"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kænvəs/","example":"a canvas bag 帆布包","word":"canvas","translation":"n. 粗帆布；一块油画布","phonetic_us":"/'kænvəs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kæp/","example":"...a dark blue baseball cap. …一顶深蓝色的棒球帽。","translation":"n. 帽子，便帽；帽状物","phonetic_us":"/kæp/","word":"cap"},{"example":"I don’t think he’s capable of murder. 我认为他没有能力杀人。","phonetic_uk":"/'keɪpəbl/","phonetic_us":"/'kepəbl/","translation":"adj. 能干的，有能力的","word":"capable"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kə'pæsɪtɪ/","example":"The room had seating capacity for about 80. 这房间能坐80个人左右。","translation":"n. 容量；能力；能量","phonetic_us":"/kə'pæsəti/","word":"capacity"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kæpɪt(ə)l/","example":"Washington D.C., the capital of the United States 美国首都华盛顿特区","phonetic_us":"/'kæpɪtl/","translation":"n. 资本，资金；首都","word":"capital"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kæptɪn/","example":"The captain and crew welcome you aboard. 机长和全体机组人员欢迎各位乘坐本次航班。","word":"captain","phonetic_us":"/ˈkæptən/","translation":"n. 陆军上尉；队长"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kæptɪv/","example":"He described the difficulties of surviving for four months as a captive. 他讲述了沦为阶下囚的4个月中生存的种种不易。","word":"captive","phonetic_us":"/'kæptɪv/","translation":"n. 俘虏，被监禁的人"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kæptʃə/","example":"Government troops have succeeded in capturing the rebel leader. 政府军已经成功抓获叛乱分子的头目。","phonetic_us":"/'kæptʃɚ/","translation":"v. 捕获，俘获；夺得","word":"capture"},{"translation":"n. 汽车，小汽车，轿车","phonetic_us":"/kɑr/","word":"car","example":"Dan got out of the car and locked the door. 丹下了车，锁上车门。","phonetic_uk":"/kɑː/"},{"word":"carbon","translation":"n. 碳","phonetic_us":"/'kɑrbən/","phonetic_uk":"/'kɑːb(ə)n/","example":"I dread to think what the carbon footprint must be like of moving that coal but we have no choice. 我都不敢想象为了运这些煤产生了多少碳足迹，但我们没有选择。"},{"word":"card","phonetic_us":"/kɑrd/","translation":"n. 卡，卡片，名片","phonetic_uk":"/kɑːd/","example":"Employees must show their identity cards at the gate. 雇员在大门口必须出示自己的身份卡。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/keə/","example":"She felt that nobody cared. 她觉得没有人在乎。","word":"care","translation":"v. 关心，介意；n. 小心","phonetic_us":"/kɛr/"},{"word":"career","translation":"n. 生涯，职业，经历","phonetic_us":"/kə'rɪr/","phonetic_uk":"/kə'rɪə/","example":"a teaching career 教学事业"},{"word":"careful","phonetic_us":"/'kɛrfl/","translation":"adj. 仔细的；细致的","example":"Any school trip requires careful planning. 学校的任何出游活动都需要周密的安排。","phonetic_uk":"/'keəfʊl; -f(ə)l/"},{"word":"caregiver","translation":"n. 照料者","phonetic_us":"/ˈkerɡɪvər/","example":"In addition to fulfilling the traditional roles of caregiver and homemaker, many Orthodox women also assume the role of primary breadwinner so their husbands can pursue religious studies full time. 除了要践行传统的照料者和主妇角色，许多东正教女性也要承担起养家的责任以便她们的丈夫可以全身心进行宗教研究。","phonetic_uk":"/'keəgɪvə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɛrləs/","translation":"adj. 粗心的","word":"careless","phonetic_uk":"/'keələs/","example":"It was careless of him to leave the door unlocked. 他忘了锁门，真是粗心大意。"},{"example":"a cargo plane 货机","phonetic_uk":"/'kɑːgəʊ/","word":"cargo","translation":"n. 船货，货物","phonetic_us":"/'kɑrɡo/"},{"word":"carpenter","translation":"n. 木匠","phonetic_us":"/ˈkɑːrpəntər/","example":"He is a carpenter by profession. 他以木工为业。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɑːpəntə(r)/"},{"translation":"n. 地毯，毡毯，毛毯","phonetic_us":"/'kɑrpɪt/","word":"carpet","example":"My bedroom carpet is green. 我卧室里的地毯是绿色的。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɑːpɪt/"},{"word":"carriage","translation":"n. 客车厢；四轮马车","phonetic_us":"/'kærɪdʒ/","example":"The president-elect followed in an open carriage drawn by six beautiful grey horses. 新当选的总统紧随其后，坐着6匹灰色骏马开道的敞篷马车。","phonetic_uk":"/'kærɪdʒ/"},{"word":"carrier","phonetic_us":"/'kærɪɚ/","translation":"n. 运输工具；运载工具","example":"an international carrier 跨国运输公司","phonetic_uk":"/'kærɪə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kærət/","translation":"n. 胡罗卜","word":"carrot","example":"grated carrots 磨碎的胡萝卜","phonetic_uk":"/'kærət/"},{"example":"The ship was carrying drugs. 这艘船上载有毒品。","phonetic_uk":"/'kærɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'kæri/","translation":"v. 携带；运载；传送","word":"carry"},{"phonetic_us":"/kɑrt/","translation":"n. 二轮运货马车","word":"cart","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/kɑːt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɑː'tuːn/","example":"cartoon characters such as Donald Duck 唐老鸭一类的卡通人物","translation":"n.  卡通画， 幽默画； 动画片， 卡通片","phonetic_us":"/kɑr'tun/","word":"cartoon"},{"example":"carved wooden chairs 木雕椅子","phonetic_uk":"/kɑːv/","translation":"v. 刻，雕刻；切开","phonetic_us":"/kɑrv/","word":"carve"},{"phonetic_us":"/kes/","translation":"n. 情况；事实；病例","word":"case","phonetic_uk":"/keɪs/","example":"Tom’s career is a case in point (= a clear example of something that you are discussing or explaining ) . 汤姆的事业就是个明证。"},{"example":"Cash was taken during a burglary of the apartment. 在一次公寓盗窃案中现金被盗。","phonetic_uk":"/kæʃ/","translation":"n. 现金，现款","phonetic_us":"/kæʃ/","word":"cash"},{"translation":"n.  出纳","phonetic_us":"/kæ'ʃɪr/","word":"cashier","example":"Do you have any experience as a cashier? 你是否有出纳员的工作经验？","phonetic_uk":"/kæ'ʃɪə/"},{"example":"His two albums released on cassette have sold 10 million copies. 他以磁带形式发行的两张专辑已售出1000万份。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'set/","word":"cassette","translation":"n. 盒式录音带；盒子","phonetic_us":"/kə'sɛt/"},{"word":"cast","phonetic_us":"/kæst/","translation":"v. 投，扔，抛；浇铸","phonetic_uk":"/kɑːst/","example":"the shade cast by low-hanging branches 低垂的树枝投下的阴影"},{"translation":"n. 城堡；巨大建筑物","phonetic_us":"/'kæsl/","word":"castle","phonetic_uk":"/'kɑːs(ə)l/","example":"Edinburgh Castle 爱丁堡城堡"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈkæʒuəl/","example":"a casual manner 漫不经心的态度","word":"casual","phonetic_us":"/'kæʒʊəl/","translation":"adj. 偶然的，随便的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kæt/","example":"The police played an elaborate game of cat and mouse to trap him. 警方跟他玩了一场精心布局的猫捉老鼠游戏，诱他落网。","word":"cat","translation":"n. 猫，猫科，猫皮","phonetic_us":"/kæt/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'kætəlɒɡ/","word":"catalog","phonetic_us":"/'kætəlɔg/","translation":"n. 目录，目录册"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kætəlɔɡ/","translation":"v. 把……编入目录","word":"catalogue","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkætəlɒg/","example":"The manuscripts have never been systematically catalogued. 一直没有系统地为这些手稿编过目录。"},{"example":"Did you catch any fish? 你捕到鱼了吗？","phonetic_uk":"/kætʃ/","translation":"v. 捉住；赶上；领会","phonetic_us":"/kætʃ/","word":"catch"},{"example":"people in the over-45 age category 属45岁以上年龄组的人","phonetic_uk":"/'kætəgəri/","word":"category","translation":"n.  种类， 类， 类别","phonetic_us":"/'kætəɡɔri/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ketɚ/","translation":"v. 迎合","word":"cater","example":"We cater to an exclusive clientele. 我们满足一个特殊客户群的需求。","phonetic_uk":"/'keɪtə/"},{"word":"cathedral","phonetic_us":"/kə'θidrəl/","translation":"n. 总教堂；大教堂","example":"St Paul’s Cathedral 圣保罗大教堂","phonetic_uk":"/kə'θiːdr(ə)l/"},{"example":"herds of cattle 成群的牛","phonetic_uk":"/'kæt(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/'kætl/","translation":"n. 牛；牲口，家畜","word":"cattle"},{"phonetic_us":"/kɔz/","translation":"n. 原因，理由；事业","word":"cause","example":"It’s our job to establish the cause of the fire. 查明起火原因是我们的责任。","phonetic_uk":"/kɔːz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɔ:ʃən/","example":"The physician must exercise caution when prescribing antidepressants. 医师在开抗抑郁药处方时必须谨慎。","word":"caution","phonetic_us":"/'kɔʃən/","translation":"v & n. 小心，谨慎"},{"word":"cautious","translation":"adj. 谨慎的","phonetic_us":"/'kɔʃəs/","example":"a cautious driver 一位谨慎的司机","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔːʃəs/"},{"word":"cave","translation":"n. 山洞，洞穴，窑洞","phonetic_us":"/kev/","phonetic_uk":"/keɪv/","example":"the entrance to a cave 洞穴的入口"},{"word":"cease","translation":"vi&vi&n. 停止，停息","phonetic_us":"/sis/","example":"The things people will do for charity never cease to amaze me (= I am always surprised by them ) . 人们的慈善义举总是让我感到惊讶。","phonetic_uk":"/siːs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'siːlɪŋ/","example":"rooms with high ceilings 天花板很高的房间","word":"ceiling","translation":"n. 天花板，顶蓬","phonetic_us":"/'silɪŋ/"},{"translation":"v. 庆祝；歌颂，赞美","phonetic_us":"/'sɛlɪbret/","word":"celebrate","phonetic_uk":"/'selɪbreɪt/","example":"It’s Dad’s birthday and we’re going out for a meal to celebrate. 今天是爸爸的生日，我们打算出去吃饭庆祝一下。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sel/","example":"cancer cells 癌细胞","word":"cell","translation":"n. 细胞；小房间","phonetic_us":"/sɛl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'selə/","example":"a coal cellar 煤窖","word":"cellar","phonetic_us":"/'sɛlɚ/","translation":"n. 地窑，地下室"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'ment/","example":"a bag of cement 一袋水泥","word":"cement","phonetic_us":"/sə'mɛnt/","translation":"n. 水泥；胶泥；v. 粘结"},{"example":"A cup of rice which cost thirty cents a few weeks ago is now being sold for up to one dollar. 几周前价值30美分的1杯米如今卖到了1美元。","phonetic_uk":"/sent/","translation":"n. 分；分币；百","phonetic_us":"/sɛnt/","word":"cent"},{"example":"In this example, you rotate a square on its center, but do not fill the square. 在这个例子中，您会以中心为原点旋转一个正方形，但不填充这个正方形。","phonetic_uk":"/'sentə/","translation":"n.  圆心， 正中； 中心","phonetic_us":"/'sɛntɚ/","word":"center"},{"example":"This thermometer is calibrated by centigrade. 这种温度计是用摄氏百分度标定的。","phonetic_uk":"/'sentɪgreɪd/","translation":"adj. 百分度的","phonetic_us":"/'sɛntɪɡred/","word":"centigrade"},{"example":"...a tiny fossil plant, only a few centimetres high. …一块小小的植物化石，只有几厘米高。","phonetic_uk":"/'sentɪmiːtə/","translation":"n. 公分，厘米","phonetic_us":"/'sɛntɪmitɚ/","word":"centimetre"},{"word":"central","translation":"adj. 中心的；主要的","phonetic_us":"/'sɛntrəl/","example":"He lives in central London. 他住在伦敦市中心。","phonetic_uk":"/'sentr(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sentə/","example":"lines radiating out from the centre 从中心向外辐射的线条","translation":"n. 中心；中枢；v. 集中","phonetic_us":"/sɛntɚ/","word":"centre"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɛntʃəri/","translation":"n. 世纪，百年","word":"century","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsentʃərɪ/","example":"the story of life on a small farm at the turn of the century 讲述世纪初一个小农场生活的故事"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈsɛrəˌmoʊni/","translation":"n. 典礼，仪式","word":"ceremony","phonetic_uk":"/'serəmənɪ/","example":"a wedding ceremony 婚礼"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɝtn/","translation":"adj. 确实的；肯定的","word":"certain","phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːt(ə)n; -tɪn/","example":"I felt certain that I’d passed the test. 我感觉自己肯定通过这次测验了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈsəːt(ə)nli/","example":"‘I’d like a beer, please.’ ‘Certainly, sir.’ “请给我来杯啤酒。”“好的，先生。”","translation":"adv. 一定，必定；当然","phonetic_us":"/'sɝtnli/","word":"certainly"},{"example":"He usually does quite well, but it’s not a certainty. 通常他都做得相当好，但也并不一定。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːt(ə)ntɪ; -tɪn-/","translation":"n. 必然；肯定","phonetic_us":"/'sɝtnti/","word":"certainty"},{"phonetic_us":"/sɚˈtɪfɪkɪt; (for v.,) sɚˈtɪfɪˌket/","translation":"n. 证书，证件，执照","word":"certificate","example":"a degree certificate 学位证书","phonetic_uk":"/səˈtɪfɪkɪt; (for v.,) səˈtɪfɪˌkeɪt/"},{"example":"She had a gold chain around her neck. 她脖子上戴了条金项链。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃeɪn/","phonetic_us":"/tʃen/","translation":"n. 链，链条，项圈","word":"chain"},{"word":"chair","translation":"n. 椅子；主席","phonetic_us":"/tʃɛr/","example":"a kitchen chair 厨房椅","phonetic_uk":"/tʃeə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'tʃɛrmən/","translation":"n. 主席；议长，会长","word":"chairman","example":"deputy/vice chairman Barrett serves as vice chairman. 巴雷特担任副主席一职。","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃeəmən/"},{"word":"chalk","phonetic_us":"/tʃɔk/","translation":"n. 白垩；粉笔","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɔːk/","example":"chalk cliffs 白垩质峭壁"},{"word":"challenge","translation":"n & v. 挑战；质疑","phonetic_us":"/'tʃælɪndʒ/","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃælɪn(d)ʒ/","example":"They threw down the challenge that he couldn’t wash 40 cars in one hour (= invited him to try to do it ) . 他们激将他，说他不可能在1小时内擦洗40辆汽车。"},{"word":"chamber","translation":"n. 会议室；房间；腔","phonetic_us":"/ˈtʃeɪmbər/","example":"a combustion chamber 燃烧室","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃeɪmbə/"},{"word":"champion","translation":"n. 冠军，得胜者","phonetic_us":"/'tʃæmpɪən/","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃæmpɪən/","example":"the world heavyweight boxing champion 世界重量级拳击冠军"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃɑːns/","example":"There’s always the chance that something will go wrong. 总有可能会出现问题。","translation":"n. 机会，机遇；可能性","phonetic_us":"/tʃæns/","word":"chance"},{"word":"change","phonetic_us":"/tʃendʒ/","translation":"n. 改变，变化；零钱","phonetic_uk":"/tʃeɪn(d)ʒ/","example":"I find it hard to cope with change. 我觉得很难适应变化。"},{"word":"channel","phonetic_us":"/'tʃænl/","translation":"n. 海峡；渠道；频道","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃæn(ə)l/","example":"the news on Channel 4 第四频道播出的新闻"},{"translation":"n.  混乱， 紊乱","phonetic_us":"/'keɑs/","word":"chaos","phonetic_uk":"/'keɪɒs/","example":"The country was plunged into economic chaos. 这个国家陷入了经济大混乱。"},{"phonetic_us":"/tʃæp/","translation":"n. 小伙子，小家伙，家伙","word":"chap","example":"a decent sort of chap 一个正派的小伙子","phonetic_uk":"/tʃæp/"},{"translation":"n. 章，回，篇","phonetic_us":"/'tʃæptɚ/","word":"chapter","example":"Read Chapter 11 as your homework. 家庭作业是阅读第 11 章。","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃæptə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kærəktə(r)/","example":"A soulless shopping centre stands across from one of the few buildings with character, the town hall. 一座毫无生气的购物中心对面就是少有的几个别具特色的建筑物之一：市政厅。","phonetic_us":"/'kærəktɚ/","translation":"n. 角色","word":"character"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌkærəktəˈrɪstɪk/","example":"Genes determine the characteristics of every living thing. 基因决定每个生物的特征。","translation":"n. 特点","phonetic_us":"/,kærəktə'rɪstɪk/","word":"characteristic"},{"word":"characterize","translation":"v. 以……特点","phonetic_us":"/'kærəktə'raɪz/","phonetic_uk":"/'kærəktəraɪz/","example":"Bright colours characterize his paintings. 明亮的色彩是他绘画作品的特点。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃɑːdʒ/","example":"They have the evidence to charge him. 他们有证据来指控他。","phonetic_us":"/tʃɑrdʒ/","translation":"v. 索价；控告；n. 费用","word":"charge"},{"example":"Several charities sent aid to the flood victims. 有几家慈善机构已向洪灾灾民送去了救援物资。","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃærətɪ/","translation":"n. 慈善（行为）","phonetic_us":"/'tʃærəti/","word":"charity"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃɑːm/","example":"\"Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs,\" the 1937 Disney classic, has lost none of its original charm. 迪斯尼1937年的经典之作《白雪公主和七个小矮人》从未丧失其最初的魅力。","word":"charm","translation":"n. 迷人的特性，魅力；符咒，咒文；vt.  吸引， 迷住","phonetic_us":"/tʃɑrm/"},{"word":"charming","phonetic_us":"/'tʃɑrmɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 迷人的，可爱的","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃɑːmɪŋ/","example":"a charming little Italian restaurant 一家有吸引力的意大利小餐厅"},{"translation":"n. 图，图表；海图","phonetic_us":"/tʃɑrt/","word":"chart","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɑːt/","example":"a chart showing last year’s sales 显示去年销售情况的一份图表"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'tʃɑːtə/","example":"...the last charter plane carrying out foreign nationals. …运出外国侨民的最后一班包机。","translation":"adj.  包租的， 租用的；n. 宪章，共同纲领；特许状，许可证；包租；vt. 包，租","phonetic_us":"/'tʃɑrtɚ/","word":"charter"},{"translation":"n. 追逐，追赶，追求","phonetic_us":"","word":"chase","example":"a high-speed car chase 高速汽车追逐","phonetic_uk":"/tʃeɪs/"},{"translation":"v. 聊天","phonetic_us":"/tʃæt/","word":"chat","example":"John and I sat up until the early hours chatting. 我和约翰聊到凌晨才睡。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃæt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃiːp/","example":"cheap rail fares 便宜的火车票","translation":"adj. 廉价的；劣质的","phonetic_us":"/tʃip/","word":"cheap"},{"example":"He had cheated in the test by using a calculator. 他在考试时作弊，用了计算器。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃiːt/","word":"cheat","phonetic_us":"/tʃit/","translation":"v. 欺骗, 作弊"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃek/","example":"Check the tiles carefully before you buy them. 购买之前要把瓷砖仔细检查一下。","word":"check","phonetic_us":"/tʃɛk/","translation":"v. 检查；制止；n. 检查"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃi:k/","example":"Lucy stretched up to kiss his cheek. 露西伸长了脖子去亲吻他的脸颊。","word":"cheek","phonetic_us":"/tʃik/","translation":"n. 脸颊"},{"phonetic_us":"/tʃɪr/","translation":"v. 使振作；欢呼","word":"cheer","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɪə/","example":"Everybody cheered when the firemen arrived. 消防员到达时，大家都欢呼起来。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'tʃɪəfʊl; -f(ə)l/","example":"a bright cheerful Italian restaurant 一家明亮宜人的意大利餐馆","word":"cheerful","translation":"adj. 快乐的，愉快的","phonetic_us":"/'tʃɪrfl/"},{"word":"cheese","translation":"n. 奶酪，干酪","phonetic_us":"/tʃiz/","example":"half a kilo of cheese 半公斤干酪","phonetic_uk":"/tʃiːz/"},{"example":"a master chef 手艺高超的厨师长","phonetic_uk":"/ʃef/","translation":"n. 厨师","phonetic_us":"/ʃɛf/","word":"chef"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kemikəl/","example":"the chemical composition of bleach 漂白剂的化学成分","translation":"adj. 化学的 n. 化学制品","phonetic_us":"/'kɛmɪkl/","word":"chemical"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kemɪst/","example":"She worked as a research chemist. 她是一名化学研究员。","word":"chemist","translation":"n. 化学家；药剂师","phonetic_us":"/'kɛmɪst/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kemɪstrɪ/","example":"a person’s body chemistry 人体的化学组成","phonetic_us":"/'kɛmɪstri/","translation":"n. 化学","word":"chemistry"},{"example":"You could write her a cheque . 你可以给她开张支票。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃek/","phonetic_us":"/tʃɛk/","translation":"n. 支票","word":"cheque"},{"example":"In marriage, a man promises to cherish his wife. 在婚姻中，男人承诺要爱护妻子。","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃerɪʃ/","translation":"vt.  珍爱； 怀有","phonetic_us":"/'tʃɛrɪʃ/","word":"cherish"},{"example":"a bunch of cherries 一串樱桃","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃerɪ/","word":"cherry","phonetic_us":"/'tʃɛri/","translation":"n. 樱桃；樱桃树"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃes/","example":"They meet fairly often to play chess . 他们经常在一起下国际象棋。","word":"chess","translation":"n. 棋；国际象棋","phonetic_us":"/tʃɛs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃest/","example":"Her heart was pounding in her chest. 她的心在胸口怦怦直跳。","word":"chest","translation":"n. 胸腔，胸膛；箱子","phonetic_us":"/tʃɛst/"},{"word":"chew","phonetic_us":"/tʃʊ/","translation":"v. 咀嚼，嚼碎","example":"This meat’s so tough I can hardly chew it! 这肉太老了，我几乎嚼不动！","phonetic_uk":"/tʃuː/"},{"word":"chicken","phonetic_us":"/ˈtʃɪkən/","translation":"n. 小鸡，小鸟；鸡肉","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃɪkɪn/","example":"roast chicken 烤鸡"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃiːf/","example":"He was recently appointed chief economist at the Bank of Scotland. 他最近被任命为苏格兰银行的首席经济学家。","word":"chief","translation":"adj. 主要的；首席的","phonetic_us":"/tʃif/"},{"example":"The hotel is ideal for families with young children. 这家宾馆对带小孩的家庭再合适不过。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃaɪld/","translation":"n. 小孩，儿童；儿子","phonetic_us":"/tʃaɪld/","word":"child"},{"word":"childhood","phonetic_us":"/'tʃaɪldhʊd/","translation":"n. 童年，幼年；早期","example":"I had a very happy childhood. 我的童年很快乐。","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃaɪldhʊd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'tʃaɪldɪʃ/","example":"a high childish laugh 孩子气的高声大笑","phonetic_us":"/'tʃaɪldɪʃ/","translation":"adj. 孩子的；幼稚的","word":"childish"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʃɪl/","example":"The wind blew across her body, chilling her wet skin. 风吹在她身上，她湿漉漉的皮肤感到非常寒冷。","translation":"v. 使变冷；n. 寒冷","phonetic_us":"/tʃɪl/","word":"chill"},{"phonetic_us":"/'tʃɪmni/","translation":"n. 烟囱，烟筒；玻璃罩","word":"chimney","example":"We can’t light a fire because the chimney hasn’t been swept. 烟囱管没有清扫过，我们生不了火。","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃɪmnɪ/"},{"example":"He rubbed his chin thoughtfully. 他若有所思地抚摸着下巴。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɪn/","word":"chin","translation":"n. 颏，下巴","phonetic_us":"/tʃɪn/"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 中国","word":"China","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/tʃaɪnə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,tʃai'ni:z/","example":"Do you fancy going out for a Chinese? 你想不想出去吃顿中餐？","word":"Chinese","translation":"adj. 中国的；n. 中国人","phonetic_us":""},{"translation":"n.  屑片， 碎片； 炸土豆条； 集成电路片， 集成块； 缺口， 瑕疵","phonetic_us":"/tʃɪp/","word":"chip","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɪp/","example":"the age of the silicon chip 芯片时代"},{"word":"chocolate","translation":"n. 巧克力；巧克力糖","phonetic_us":"/'tʃɑklət/","example":"a chocolate bar 巧克力条","phonetic_uk":"/'tʃɒk(ə)lət/"},{"translation":"n. 选择，抉择","phonetic_us":"/tʃɔɪs/","word":"choice","example":"He has to make some important choices. 他得作出一些重要的抉择。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɒɪs/"},{"word":"choke","phonetic_us":"/tʃok/","translation":"v. 使窒息","phonetic_uk":"/tʃəʊk/","example":"Six people choked to death on the fumes. 六人被烟呛死。"},{"example":"It took us ages to choose a new carpet. 我们挑选新地毯花了很长时间。","phonetic_uk":"/tʃuːz/","word":"choose","translation":"v. 选择，挑选；情愿","phonetic_us":"/tʃuz/"},{"translation":"v. 砍，劈；切细；v. 砍","phonetic_us":"/tʃɑp/","word":"chop","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɒp/","example":"He went outside to chop some more wood for the fire. 他出去再砍些木材来生火。"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n.  基督， 救世主","word":"Christ","example":"a follower of Christ 耶稣的门徒","phonetic_uk":"/kraɪst/"},{"example":"He was a devout Christian. 他曾是一个虔诚的基督教徒。","phonetic_uk":"/'krɪstɪən; -tʃ(ə)n/","word":"Christian","translation":"n. 基督教徒；信徒","phonetic_us":"/'krɪstʃən/"},{"word":"Christmas","translation":"n. 圣诞节","phonetic_us":"","example":"Are you going home for Christmas? 你回家过圣诞节吗？","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkrɪsməs/"},{"word":"church","translation":"n. 教堂，礼拜堂；教会","phonetic_us":"/tʃɝtʃ/","example":"a short church service 简短的教堂礼拜仪式","phonetic_uk":"/tʃɜːtʃ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/sɪ'ɡɑr/","translation":"n.  雪茄烟","word":"cigar","example":"He was smoking a big cigar. 他在抽一只大雪茄。","phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'gɑː/"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 香烟，纸烟，卷烟","word":"cigaret","phonetic_uk":"","example":"RA 7171 plows back annually 15 percent of cigaret excise tax revenues collected by the National Government to the virginia leaf producing provinces of Ilocos Sur, Ilocos Norte, La Union and Abra. RA 7171把国家政府每年征收的卷烟消费税，每年向弗吉尼亚烟叶生产省南伊洛克斯省、北伊洛克斯省、拉乌尼翁和埃尔阿布拉再投资15%。"},{"example":"a packet of cigarettes 一包香烟","phonetic_uk":"/ˌsɪgə'ret/","word":"cigarette","phonetic_us":"/ˌsɪɡəˈrɛt, ˈsɪɡəˌrɛt/","translation":"n.  香烟， 纸烟， 卷烟"},{"example":"It’s on at the local cinema. 此片正在当地影院上映。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪnɪmə; -mɑː/","word":"cinema","translation":"n. 电影院；电影，影片","phonetic_us":"/'sɪnəmə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɝkl/","translation":"n. 圆，圆周；圈子","word":"circle","phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːk(ə)l/","example":"Draw a circle 10cm in diameter. 画一个直径10厘米的圆形。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɝkɪt/","translation":"n. 电路；环行；巡行","word":"circuit","phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːkɪt/","example":"We did a circuit of the old city. 我们绕着老城走了一圈。"},{"translation":"adj. 圆的；循环的","phonetic_us":"/'sɝkjəlɚ/","word":"circular","phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːkjʊlə/","example":"a circular table 圆桌"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːkjʊleɪt/","example":"Swimming helps to get the blood circulating through the muscles. 游泳有助于肌肉的血液循环。","phonetic_us":"/'sɝkjəlet/","translation":"v. 使循环；v. 循环","word":"circulate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌsɜːkjə'leɪʃn/","example":"Exercise improves the circulation. 运动能促进血液循环。","word":"circulation","phonetic_us":"/,sɝkjə'leʃən/","translation":"n.  循环； 流传； 发行， 流通"},{"phonetic_us":"/sɚ'kʌmfərəns/","translation":"n. 圆周，周长，圆周线","word":"circumference","example":"...a scientist calculating the Earth's circumference. …一位正在计算地球周长的科学家。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'kʌmf(ə)r(ə)ns/"},{"word":"circumstance","translation":"n. 环境，境遇","phonetic_us":"/'sɝkəmstæns/","example":"He was a victim of circumstance . 他是客观环境的牺牲品。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɜ:kəmstəns/"},{"word":"cite","phonetic_us":"/saɪt/","translation":"v. 引用","phonetic_uk":"/sait/","example":"The judge cited a 1956 Supreme Court ruling in her decision. 法官在她的判决中引用了1956年最高法院的一项裁决。"},{"example":"We need our schools to teach students to be good citizens. 我们需要学校把学生培养为好公民。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪtɪzn/","phonetic_us":"/'sɪtɪzn/","translation":"n. 公民","word":"citizen"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɪtɪ/","example":"The nearest big city was St. Louis. 最近的大城市是圣路易斯。","phonetic_us":"/'sɪti/","translation":"n. 城市，都市","word":"city"},{"example":"They were married in a civil ceremony in May. 他们在五月份举行了世俗婚礼。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪv(ə)l; -ɪl/","word":"civil","translation":"adj. 公民的；文职的","phonetic_us":"/'sɪvl/"},{"word":"civilian","phonetic_us":"/sə'vɪlɪən/","translation":"n. 平民，百姓","example":"Many innocent civilians were killed during the war. 许多无辜的平民在战争中丧生。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'vɪlɪən/"},{"word":"civilization","translation":"n. 文明","phonetic_us":"/,sɪvələ'zeʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌsɪvɪlaɪˈzeɪʃən/","example":"modern American civilization 现代美国文明"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɪvəlaɪz/","translation":"v. 使文明；教育","word":"civilize","example":"Ellis was credited with civilizing the Texas prison system. 据信是埃利斯改良了得克萨斯州的监狱制度。","phonetic_uk":"/'sivilaiz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈsɪvəlaɪzd/","example":"Such things should not happen in a civilized society. 文明社会不应该有这种事情发生。","word":"civilized","translation":"adj. 文明的","phonetic_us":"/sɪvlˌaɪzd/"},{"translation":"v. 声称，主张；索取","phonetic_us":"/klem/","word":"claim","phonetic_uk":"/kleɪm/","example":"I don’t claim to be a feminist, but I’d like to see more women in top jobs. 我不会自称是女权主义者，但我希望看到更多的女性担任高职。"},{"phonetic_us":"/klæp/","translation":"v. 拍手；v. 拍，轻拍","word":"clap","example":"One man began to clap, and others joined in. 一个人鼓起了掌，其他人也跟着鼓掌。","phonetic_uk":"/klæp/"},{"word":"clarify","phonetic_us":"/'klærəfaɪ/","translation":"v. 澄清，阐明","phonetic_uk":"/'klærɪfaɪ/","example":"Reporters asked him to clarify his position (= say exactly what his beliefs are ) on welfare reform. 记者们要求他阐明他在福利改革问题上的立场。"},{"example":"Troops clashed near the border. 军队在边境附近发生了冲突。","phonetic_uk":"/klæʃ/","word":"clash","translation":"vi. 发生冲突；不协调；砰地相撞，发出刺耳的撞击声；n.  冲突； 不协调； 刺耳的撞击声","phonetic_us":"/klæʃ/"},{"word":"clasp","phonetic_us":"/klæsp/","translation":"n. 扣子，钩子；别针","phonetic_uk":"/klɑːsp/","example":"...the clasp of her handbag. …她的手包扣。"},{"translation":"n. 班，班级；阶级","phonetic_us":"/klæs/","word":"class","phonetic_uk":"/klɑːs/","example":"He’s not in the same class (= not as good ) as her at tennis. 他的网球水平并不如她。"},{"word":"classic","phonetic_us":"/'klæsɪk/","translation":"adj. 最优秀的，典型的，标准的；传统式样的，典雅的；n.  文学名著， 经典作品， 杰作； 优秀的典范； 古典文学， 古典语文研究","phonetic_uk":"/'klæsɪk/","example":"The Coca-Cola bottle is one of the classic designs of the last century. 可口可乐瓶是上个世纪的经典设计之一。"},{"example":"the classical theory of relativity 经典相对论","phonetic_uk":"/'klæsɪk(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/'klæsɪkl/","translation":"adj. 古典的；经典的","word":"classical"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,klæsɪfɪ'keɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"the classification of wines according to quality 葡萄酒按品质的分类","translation":"n. 分类，级别","phonetic_us":"/,klæsɪfɪ'keʃən/","word":"classification"},{"phonetic_us":"/'klæsɪfaɪ/","translation":"v. 把…分类，把…分级","word":"classify","phonetic_uk":"/'klæsifai/","example":"We’d classify Drabble’s novels under ‘Romance’. 我们把德拉布尔的小说归类为“言情小说”。"},{"word":"classmate","translation":"n. 同班同学","phonetic_us":"/'klæsmet/","example":"He acquainted his classmate with my sister. 他把我妹妹介绍给他的同班同学。","phonetic_uk":"/'klɑːsmeɪt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'klæs'rʊm; 'klæs'rʊm/","translation":"n. 教室，课堂","word":"classroom","phonetic_uk":"/'klɑːsruːm; -rʊm/","example":"The boy bounced out of the classroom. 那男孩突然从教室里奔出去。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/klɔːz/","example":"A confidentiality clause was added to the contract. 合同中加上了一项保密条款。","translation":"n.  条款； 从句， 分句","phonetic_us":"/klɔz/","word":"clause"},{"phonetic_us":"/klɔ/","translation":"n. 爪，脚爪，螯","word":"claw","phonetic_uk":"/klɔː/","example":"The cat dug his claws into my leg. 猫的爪子抓进了我的腿中。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/kleɪ/","phonetic_us":"/kle/","translation":"n. 粘土，泥土；肉体","word":"clay"},{"word":"clean","translation":"adj. 清洁的；纯洁的","phonetic_us":"/klin/","phonetic_uk":"/kliːn/","example":"Are your hands clean? 你的手干净吗？"},{"phonetic_us":"/klɪr/","translation":"adj. 清晰的；v. 清除","word":"clear","example":"clear instructions 明确的指示","phonetic_uk":"/klɪə/"},{"word":"clearly","phonetic_us":"/'klɪrli/","translation":"adv. 明白地，清晰地","phonetic_uk":"/'klɪəlɪ/","example":"Please speak clearly. 请说得清楚点。"},{"phonetic_us":"/klɝk/","translation":"n. 店员；办事员，职员","word":"clerk","phonetic_uk":"/klɑːk/","example":"a clerk in a commercial firm 一家商行的文员"},{"phonetic_us":"/'klɛvɚ/","translation":"adj. 聪明的；机敏的","word":"clever","example":"a clever man 聪明的人","phonetic_uk":"/'klevə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/klɪk/","example":"The door clicked shut behind me. 门在我身后咔嗒一声关上了。","word":"click","translation":"v. 发出咔嗒声；点击；n.  咔嗒声","phonetic_us":"/klɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'klaɪənt/","translation":"n. 客户","word":"client","phonetic_uk":"/'klaɪənt/","example":"a meeting with an important client 与一位重要客户的会面"},{"word":"cliff","translation":"n. 悬崖，峭壁","phonetic_us":"/klɪf/","phonetic_uk":"/klɪf/","example":"The car rolled over the edge of a cliff. 汽车翻下了悬崖边。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈklaɪmət/","example":"Los Angeles’ warm dry climate 洛杉矶温暖干燥的气候","phonetic_us":"/'klaɪmət/","translation":"n. 气候；风土，地带","word":"climate"},{"translation":"v. 攀登，爬；v. 爬","phonetic_us":"/klaɪm/","word":"climb","example":"Harry climbed the stairs. 哈里爬上楼梯。","phonetic_uk":"/klaɪm/"},{"example":"an appointment at an outpatient clinic 门诊预约","phonetic_uk":"/'klɪnɪk/","phonetic_us":"/'klɪnɪk/","translation":"n. 诊所","word":"clinic"},{"phonetic_us":"/klok/","translation":"n. 斗篷；覆盖(物)","word":"cloak","example":"Today most of New England will be under a cloak of thick mist. 今天新英格兰大部分地区会在浓雾的笼罩中。","phonetic_uk":"/kləʊk/"},{"word":"clock","translation":"n. 钟，仪表","phonetic_us":"/klɑk/","example":"I heard the clock strike six (= make six loud sounds ) . 我听到钟敲了六下。","phonetic_uk":"/klɒk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kloz/","translation":"v. 关，闭；结束","word":"close","example":"Would you mind if I closed the window? 我把窗户关上你不介意吧？","phonetic_uk":"/kləʊs/"},{"translation":"adv. 紧密地，接近地","phonetic_us":"/'klosli/","word":"closely","example":"The detective watched him closely , waiting for a reply. 侦探紧盯着他看，等着他回答。","phonetic_uk":"/'kləʊslɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/klɔθ/","translation":"n. 布；衣料；桌布","word":"cloth","phonetic_uk":"/klɒθ/","example":"Clean the surface with a damp cloth. 用一块湿布清洗表面。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kləʊð/","example":"They could barely keep the family fed and clothed. 他们几乎无力为家人提供衣食。","word":"clothe","phonetic_us":"/kloð/","translation":"v. 给…穿衣服"},{"word":"clothes","phonetic_us":"/kloz/","translation":"n. 衣服，服装；被褥","example":"What sort of clothes was he wearing? 他穿着什么样的衣服？","phonetic_uk":"/kləʊ(ð)z/"},{"translation":"n. 衣服，被褥","phonetic_us":"/'kloðɪŋ/","word":"clothing","example":"basic necessities such as food and clothing 食物和衣服这类基本的生活必需品","phonetic_uk":"/'kləʊðɪŋ/"},{"example":"Fears of renewed terrorist attacks cast a cloud over the event (= spoilt the happy situation ) . 对恐怖分子再次发动袭击的担心给这次活动蒙上了一层阴影。","phonetic_uk":"/klaʊd/","phonetic_us":"/klaʊd/","translation":"n. 云；云状物；阴影","word":"cloud"},{"translation":"adj. 多云的；云一般的","phonetic_us":"/'klaʊdi/","word":"cloudy","phonetic_uk":"/'klaʊdɪ/","example":"a cloudy night with some light rain 伴有些许小雨的多云的夜晚"},{"phonetic_uk":"/klʌb/","example":"Manchester United Football Club 曼联（队）足球俱乐部","word":"club","phonetic_us":"/klʌb/","translation":"n. 俱乐部，夜总会"},{"example":"Police have found a vital clue . 警方发现了至关重要的线索。","phonetic_uk":"/kluː/","translation":"n. 线索","phonetic_us":"/klʊ/","word":"clue"},{"word":"clumsy","translation":"adj. 笨拙的，不圆滑的","phonetic_us":"/'klʌmzi/","example":"A clumsy waiter spilled wine all over her new skirt. 一名笨手笨脚的服务员把葡萄酒洒得她新裙子上到处都是。","phonetic_uk":"/'klʌmzi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəʊtʃ/","example":"a tennis coach 网球教练","word":"coach","phonetic_us":"/kotʃ/","translation":"v & n. 教练"},{"word":"coal","phonetic_us":"/kol/","translation":"n. 煤，煤块","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊl/","example":"Put some coal on the fire. 往火里加点煤。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɔːs/","example":"a jacket of coarse wool 粗羊毛夹克衫","phonetic_us":"/kɔrs/","translation":"adj. 粗的，粗糙的","word":"coarse"},{"example":"We drove along the Pacific coast to Seattle. 我们沿着太平洋海岸驾车前往西雅图。","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊst/","word":"coast","translation":"n. 海岸，海滨(地区)","phonetic_us":"/kost/"},{"translation":"n. 外套，上衣；表皮","phonetic_us":"/kot/","word":"coat","example":"Billy! Put your coat on , it’s cold outside! 比利！穿上外套，外面很冷！","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊt/"},{"word":"cock","translation":"n. 公鸡；雄禽；旋塞","phonetic_us":"/kɑk/","example":"A cock crowed in the distance. 远处有只公鸡在打鸣。","phonetic_uk":"/kɒk/"},{"word":"code","translation":"n. 代码，密码","phonetic_us":"/kod/","example":"The spy sent his message in code. 这个间谍用密码发送情报。","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊd/"},{"word":"coffee","translation":"n. 咖啡，咖啡茶","phonetic_us":"/'kɔfi/","example":"Do you want a cup of coffee? 你要来杯咖啡吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒfɪ/"},{"example":"the coil in a light bulb 灯丝","phonetic_uk":"/kɒɪl/","translation":"n. (一)卷；线圈；v. 卷","phonetic_us":"/kɔɪl/","word":"coil"},{"word":"coin","phonetic_us":"/kɔɪn/","translation":"n. 硬币；铸造(硬币)","phonetic_uk":"/kɒɪn/","example":"Toss a coin to see who goes first. 抛硬币决定谁先来。"},{"phonetic_us":"/kold/","translation":"adj. 冷的；冷淡的；n. 冷","word":"cold","example":"She splashed her face with cold water. 她往脸上泼冷水。","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊld/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kə'læbərətɪv/","example":"...a collaborative research project. …一个合作研究项目。","translation":"adj.  合作的， 协作的， 协力完成的","phonetic_us":"/kə'læbəretɪv/","word":"collaborative"},{"word":"collapse","phonetic_us":"/kə'læps/","translation":"v. 倒坍；崩溃，瓦解","phonetic_uk":"/kə'læps/","example":"Uncle Ted’s chair collapsed under his weight. 椅子承受不了特德叔叔的重量，塌架了。"},{"word":"collar","phonetic_us":"/'kɑlɚ/","translation":"n. 衣领，项圈","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒlə/","example":"He grabbed me by the collar. 他抓住我的衣领。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒliːg/","example":"a colleague of mine from the bank 我在银行的一位同事","translation":"n. 同事","phonetic_us":"/'kɑliɡ/","word":"colleague"},{"translation":"v. 收集；v. 收款","phonetic_us":"/kə'lɛkt/","word":"collect","phonetic_uk":"/kə'lekt/","example":"After 25 years of collecting recipes, she has compiled them into a cookbook. 她搜集了25年食谱，把它们编成一本烹饪书。"},{"translation":"n. 搜集，收集；收藏品","phonetic_us":"/kə'lɛkʃən/","word":"collection","phonetic_uk":"/kə'lekʃ(ə)n/","example":"a debt collection agency 收债服务机构"},{"translation":"adj. 集体的；集合性的","phonetic_us":"/kə'lɛktɪv/","word":"collective","phonetic_uk":"/kə'lektɪv/","example":"a collective decision made by all board members 董事会所有成员作出的集体决定"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒlɪdʒ/","example":"a teacher training college 师范学院","word":"college","phonetic_us":"/'kɑlɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 学院；大学"},{"example":"They were on their way to the airport when their van was involved in a collision with a car. 他们正往机场赶路的时候，其货车和一辆小汽车相撞了。","phonetic_uk":"/kəˈlɪʒn/","translation":"n. 撞击；冲突","phonetic_us":"/kə'lɪʒən/","word":"collision"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɜːn(ə)l/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/'kɝnl/","translation":"n. 陆军上校；中校","word":"colonel"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒlənɪ/","example":"Algeria was formerly a French colony. 阿尔及利亚以前是法国的殖民地。","word":"colony","phonetic_us":"/'kɑləni/","translation":"n. 殖民地；侨居地"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌlə(r)/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/'kʌlɚ/","translation":"n. 颜色，彩色；颜料","word":"color"},{"word":"column","phonetic_us":"/'kɑləm/","translation":"n. 专栏","example":"He writes a weekly column for ‘The Times’. 他每周为《泰晤士报》写一篇专栏文章。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɒləm/"},{"example":"Your hair needs a good comb. 你的头发需要好好梳理一下。","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊm/","translation":"n. 梳子；v. 梳理","phonetic_us":"/kom/","word":"comb"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmbæt/","example":"We flew over 200 combat missions in the war. 我们在战争中执行过两百多次战斗飞行任务。","translation":"n. 战争，斗争，格斗；vt.  与…斗争， 与…战斗","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmbæt/","word":"combat"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɒmbɪ'neɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"a combination nightclub and café 夜总会兼咖啡馆","word":"combination","phonetic_us":"/,kɑmbɪ'neʃən/","translation":"n. 联合，结合"},{"example":"Diets are most effective when combined with exercise. 节食和锻炼相结合是最有效的。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'baɪn/","word":"combine","phonetic_us":"/kəm'baɪn/","translation":"v. 联合，结合"},{"word":"come","phonetic_us":"/kʌm/","translation":"v. 来，来到；出现","phonetic_uk":"/kʌm/","example":"Let me know when they come. 他们来了就告诉我。"},{"word":"comedy","translation":"n.  喜剧， 喜剧性","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmədi/","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmədi/","example":"a career in stand-up comedy 单口喜剧表演职业"},{"word":"comfort","phonetic_us":"/'kʌmfɚt/","translation":"n. 舒适；安慰；v. 安慰","example":"I dress for comfort, not fashion. 我穿衣服只讲舒服，不追求时髦。","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌmfət/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kʌmftəbl/","translation":"adj. 舒适的，安慰的","word":"comfortable","example":"I was so comfortable and warm in bed I didn’t want to get up. 床上又舒服又暖和，我都不想起来。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkʌmftəbl/"},{"translation":"v. 命令，指挥；控制","phonetic_us":"/kə'mænd/","word":"command","example":"He commands the 4th Battalion. 他指挥第四营。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'mɑːnd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kə'mɑːndə/","example":"the American Commander, General Otis 美军指挥官奥蒂斯将军","word":"commander","phonetic_us":"/kə'mændɚ/","translation":"n. 司令官，指挥员"},{"phonetic_us":"/kə'mɛnsmənt/","translation":"n. 毕业典礼","word":"commencement","example":"President Bush gave the commencement address today at the University of Notre Dame. 布什总统今天在巴黎圣母院大学发表了毕业典礼演说。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'mensm(ə)nt/"},{"word":"comment","translation":"n. 评论","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmɛnt/","example":"He was fined for making abusive comments to the referee. 他因谩骂裁判而被罚款。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒment/"},{"translation":"n. 商业，贸易；社交","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmɝs/","word":"commerce","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmɜːs/","example":"measures promoting local commerce and industry 促进地方工商业发展的措施"},{"word":"commercial","translation":"adj. 商业的；商品化的","phonetic_us":"/kə'mɝʃəl/","phonetic_uk":"/kə'mɜːʃ(ə)l/","example":"Our top priorities must be profit and commercial growth. 我们必须把利润和贸易增长作为我们的第一要务。"},{"example":"The Government set up a commission to investigate allegations of police violence. 政府成立了一个委员会调查对警察施暴行为的指控。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'mɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"commission","translation":"n. 委任状；委员会","phonetic_us":"/kə'mɪʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kə'mit/","example":"Women commit fewer crimes than men. 女性犯罪比男性少。","translation":"v. 犯罪，承担义务","phonetic_us":"/kə'mɪt/","word":"commit"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kə'mɪtm(ə)nt/","example":"Are you ready to make a long-term commitment ? 你是否准备好作出长久的承诺？","word":"commitment","translation":"n. 承诺，保证","phonetic_us":"/kə'mɪtmənt/"},{"word":"committee","phonetic_us":"/kə'mɪti/","translation":"n. 委员会","phonetic_uk":"/kəˈmɪti/","example":"a committee meeting 委员会会议"},{"word":"common","translation":"adj. 普通的；共同的","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmən/","example":"Heart disease is one of the commonest causes of death. 心脏病是最常见的死因之一。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmən/"},{"translation":"adv. 普通地，一般地","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmənli/","word":"commonly","example":"Sodium chloride is more commonly known as salt. 氯化钠通常都称为盐。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmənlɪ/"},{"word":"communicate","phonetic_us":"/kə'mjunɪket/","translation":"v. 通讯；传达；传播","phonetic_uk":"/kə'mjuːnɪkeɪt/","example":"A baby communicates its needs by crying. 婴儿用哭来表达需要。"},{"phonetic_us":"/kə,mjunɪ'keʃən/","translation":"n. 通讯；传达；交通","word":"communication","phonetic_uk":"/kəmjuːnɪ'keɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"a week’s course in improving communication skills 为期一周的提高沟通技巧的课程"},{"word":"communism","translation":"n. 共产主义","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmjʊ'nɪzəm/","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmjʊnɪz(ə)m/","example":"...the ultimate triumph of communism in the world. …共产主义在全世界的最终胜利。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɑmjənɪst/","translation":"n. 共产党员","word":"communist","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmjʊnɪst/","example":"Without the communists in France, the resistance might not have succeeded in World War II.  如果没有法国的共产主义者，二战中的抵抗运动可能不会成功。"},{"example":"The new arts centre will serve the whole community. 这座新的艺术中心将为整个社区服务。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'mjuːnɪtɪ/","word":"community","translation":"n. 社区；社会；公社","phonetic_us":"/kə'mjʊnəti/"},{"word":"companion","translation":"n. 同伴；共事者；伴侣","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pænɪən/","example":"For ten years he had been her constant companion . 十年来他一直陪伴她左右。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pænjən/"},{"example":"Which company do you work for? 你在哪家公司上班？","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌmp(ə)nɪ/","translation":"n. 公司，商号；同伴","phonetic_us":"/'kʌmpəni/","word":"company"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmpərəbl/","example":"A car of comparable size would cost far more abroad. 同样大小的汽车在国外要贵得多。","word":"comparable","translation":"adj.  可比较的； 类似的； 比得上的","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmpərəbl/"},{"word":"comparative","translation":"adj. 比较的，相对的","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pærətɪv/","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pærətɪv/","example":"After a lifetime of poverty, his last few years were spent in comparable comfort. 他穷了一辈子，最后几年还算过得比较舒适。"},{"phonetic_us":"/kəm'pɛr/","translation":"v. 比较，对照","word":"compare","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'peə(r)/","example":"The report compares the different types of home computer available. 这份报告比较了市场上不同类型的家用计算机。"},{"translation":"n. 比较，对照；比似","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pærɪsn/","word":"comparison","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pærɪs(ə)n/","example":"Her paintings invite comparison with those of the early Impressionists (= they remind you of them ) . 她的画作让人想起早期的印象派作品。"},{"example":"a map and compass 地图和指南针","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌmpəs/","word":"compass","translation":"n. 罗盘，指南针；圆规","phonetic_us":"/'kʌmpəs/"},{"word":"compassion","translation":"n.  同情， 怜悯","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pæʃən/","example":"I was shocked by the doctor’s lack of compassion . 我对这个医生如此缺乏同情心感到震惊。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pæʃn/"},{"example":"...the introduction of legislation to compel cyclists to wear a helmet. …强制骑车人戴头盔的法律的引入。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pel/","word":"compel","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pɛl/","translation":"v. 强迫"},{"example":"Because my left eye is so weak, my right eye has to work harder to compensate. 因为我左眼视力差，右眼就要辛苦点来弥补一下。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmpenseɪt/","word":"compensate","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmpɛnset/","translation":"v. 弥补，补偿"},{"word":"compensation","phonetic_us":"/,kɑmpɛn'seʃən/","translation":"n. 弥补，补偿","example":"People who are wrongly arrested may be paid compensation . 被误抓的人有可能得到补偿费。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌkɒmpenˈseɪʃn/"},{"word":"compete","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pit/","translation":"v. 竞争","example":"Me: What do you mean \"compete\"? 我：你的“竞争”是什么意思？","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'piːt/"},{"word":"competent","translation":"adj. 胜任的，有能力的","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmpɪtənt/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɒmpɪtənt/","example":"A competent mechanic should be able to fix the problem. 一名合格的机修工应该能够解决这个问题。"},{"example":"Going to trade fairs is an ideal opportunity to size up the competition . 参加商品交易会是估量竞争规模的理想机会。","phonetic_uk":"/kɒmpɪ'tɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"competition","translation":"n. 竞争，比赛","phonetic_us":"/,kɑmpə'tɪʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəm'petətɪv/","example":"Some US industries are not as competitive as they have been in the past. 美国有些行业不如以前有竞争力了。","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pɛtətɪv/","translation":"adj.  竞争的， 比赛的； 好竞争的， 求胜心切的； 有竞争力的","word":"competitive"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəm'petətɪvnɪs/","example":"New machinery has enhanced the company’s productivity and competitiveness. 新机器帮助公司提高了生产力，增强了竞争力。","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pɛtətɪvnɪs/","translation":"n. 竞争力","word":"competitiveness"},{"word":"competitor","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pɛtɪtɚ/","translation":"n. 竞争者，对手","example":"Last year they sold twice as many computers as their competitors. 去年他们的计算机销量是竞争对手的两倍。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'petitə/"},{"example":"The document was compiled by the Department of Health. 这份文件是由卫生部汇编的。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'paɪl/","phonetic_us":"/kəm'paɪl/","translation":"v. 编辑，编制，搜集","word":"compile"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəmˈpleɪsnsi/","example":"Doctors have warned against complacency in fighting common diseases. 医生警告说，治疗常见病不能一见好就掉以轻心。","word":"complacency","translation":"n. 自满，满足","phonetic_us":"/kəm'plesnsi/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kəm'plen/","translation":"v. 抱怨","word":"complain","example":"Residents are complaining because traffic in the area has increased. 由于这个地区的交通流量有所增加，居民都在抱怨。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pleɪn/"},{"word":"complaint","translation":"n. 抱怨; 投诉","phonetic_us":"/kəm'plent/","example":"If you wish to make a complaint, you should see the manager. 如果你要投诉，应该去找经理。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pleint/"},{"example":"John and Bob complemented each other well. 约翰和鲍勃互相配合得很好。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmplɪm(ə)nt/","word":"complement","translation":"v. 补充","phonetic_us":"/ˈkɑːmplɪment/"},{"example":"Students must complete the course. 学生必须学完这门课程。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pli:t/","word":"complete","phonetic_us":"/kəm'plit/","translation":"v. 完成；adj. 完整的，彻底的"},{"example":"I completely forgot that it’s his birthday today. 我完全忘了今天是他的生日。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pliːtlɪ/","translation":"adv. 十分，完全地","phonetic_us":"/kəm'plitli/","word":"completely"},{"word":"complex","translation":"adj. 复杂的","phonetic_us":"/kəm'plɛks; 'kɑm,plɛks/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɒmpleks/","example":"a complex system of highways 复杂的公路网"},{"word":"complicate","translation":"vt. 使复杂；使陷入","phonetic_us":"","phonetic_uk":"","example":"If the answer to all of these questions is no, a framework will only complicate matters. 如果所有这些问题的答案都为否，那么使用框架只会把事情变复杂。"},{"example":"a complicated voting system 复杂的选举制度","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔmplikeitid/","translation":"adj. 复杂的，难懂的","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmplɪketɪd/","word":"complicated"},{"phonetic_us":"/kəm'plaɪ/","translation":"v. 遵从","word":"comply","example":"The newspaper was asked by federal agents for assistance and agreed to comply. 联邦探员要求这家报社给予协助，报社同意配合。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'plaɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kəm'ponənt/","translation":"n. 成分","word":"component","phonetic_uk":"/kəmˈpəʊnənt/","example":"companies that make electronic components for computer products 为计算机产品生产电子零件的公司"},{"phonetic_us":"/kəm'poz/","translation":"v. 组成，构成；创作","word":"compose","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pəʊz/","example":"Barrington has composed the music for a new production of ‘A Midsummer Night’s Dream’. 巴林顿为新版的《仲夏夜之梦》谱了曲。"},{"word":"composition","phonetic_us":"/,kɑmpə'zɪʃən/","translation":"n. 构成；作品；写作","example":"Some minerals have complex chemical compositions. 有些矿物的化学构成很复杂。","phonetic_uk":"/kɒmpə'zɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"translation":"n. 化合物；复合词","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmpaʊnd/","word":"compound","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmpaʊnd/","example":"man-made organic compounds 人造有机化合物"},{"example":"Why you let her talk you into doing such a foolish thing is beyond my comprehension (= impossible for me to understand ) . 你怎么会被她说服去做这种蠢事，我实在是无法理解。","phonetic_uk":"/kɒmprɪ'henʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/,kɑmprɪ'hɛnʃən/","translation":"n. 理解，理解力；领悟","word":"comprehension"},{"example":"We offer our customers a comprehensive range of financial products. 我们为客户提供全面的金融产品。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌkɒmprɪˈhensɪv/","word":"comprehensive","translation":"adj. 综合的，全面的","phonetic_us":"/ˌkɑːmprɪˈhensɪv/"},{"word":"compress","phonetic_us":"/kəm'prɛs/","translation":"v. 压紧，压缩","example":"Light silk is best for parachutes, as it compresses well and then expands rapidly. 轻质丝绸最适合制作降落伞，因为这种面料便于压缩，而且展开迅速。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pres/"},{"example":"The house comprises two bedrooms, a kitchen, and a living room. 这座房子有两间卧室、一间厨房和一间起居室。","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'praɪz/","translation":"v. 包含，包括；构成","phonetic_us":"/kəm'praɪz/","word":"comprise"},{"translation":"n. 妥协，和解","phonetic_us":"/'kɑmprəmaɪz/","word":"compromise","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmprəmaɪz/","example":"Compromise is an inevitable part of marriage. 妥协是婚姻生活中必不可少的。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pjuːt/","example":"Final results had not yet been computed. 最终的结果还未计算出来。","word":"compute","translation":"v. 计算，估计，估算","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pjʊt/"},{"example":"a huge global computer network 巨大的全球计算机网络","phonetic_uk":"/kəm'pjuːtə/","translation":"n. 计算机，电脑","phonetic_us":"/kəm'pjutɚ/","word":"computer"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɑmræd/","translation":"n. 同志，亲密的同伴","word":"comrade","example":"Comrades, please support this motion. 同志们，请支持这项动议。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒmreɪd/"},{"example":"The shadows concealed her as she crept up to the house. 她借着阴影蹑手蹑脚地走向房子。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'siːl/","phonetic_us":"/kən'sil/","translation":"v. 把…隐藏起来","word":"conceal"},{"example":"‘That’s the only possible solution.’ ‘Yes, I suppose so,’ Charles conceded. “那是唯一可行的解决办法。”“对，我想是。”查尔斯承认道。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'siːd/","word":"concede","phonetic_us":"/kən'sid/","translation":"vt.  承认， 承认…为真； 承认失败； 允许， 让予； 让步， 认输"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒns(ə)ntreɪt/","example":"Now please concentrate. 现在请集中注意力。","word":"concentrate","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnsn'tret/","translation":"v. 集中；聚集；浓缩"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɒns(ə)n'treɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"The area has one of the world's greatest concentrations of wildlife. 该地区有世界上野生生物最集中的区域之一。","translation":"n. 集中","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnsn'treʃən/","word":"concentration"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɑnsɛpt/","translation":"n. 观点，观念","word":"concept","example":"a new concept in business travel 商务旅行的新理念","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔnsept/"},{"example":"His main concern is to be able to provide for his family. 他最为关心的事就是能够养家。","phonetic_uk":"/kənˈsɜ:n/","word":"concern","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɝn/","translation":"v & n. 涉及，关系到"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'sɜːnɪŋ/","example":"calls from young children concerning lost pets 小孩子打来的有关宠物走失的电话","word":"concerning","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɝnɪŋ/","translation":"prep. 关于"},{"translation":"n. 音乐会，演奏会","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnsɚt/","word":"concert","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnsət/","example":"a rock concert 摇滚音乐会"},{"phonetic_us":"/kən'sɛʃən/","translation":"n.  让步， 妥协； 特许， 特许权； 承认， 认可","word":"concession","phonetic_uk":"/kən'seʃn/","example":"The British were not prepared to make any concessions . 英国人没有打算作出让步。"},{"word":"conclude","translation":"v. 推断出；结束","phonetic_us":"/kən'klud/","phonetic_uk":"/kən'kluːd/","example":"When the investigation is concluded, the results will be sent to the US Attorney’s office. 等到调查结束后，结果会被送到联邦检察官办公室。"},{"word":"conclusion","phonetic_us":"/kən'kluʒn/","translation":"n. 结论","phonetic_uk":"/kən'kluːʒ(ə)n/","example":"These are the report’s main conclusions. 这些就是这篇报告的主要结论。"},{"word":"concrete","phonetic_us":"/'kɑŋkrit/","translation":"adj. 具体的","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒŋkriːt/","example":"What does that mean in concrete terms ? 具体来说那到底是什么意思？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'dem/","example":"Politicians were quick to condemn the bombing. 政治家们立即对爆炸事件进行了谴责。","word":"condemn","translation":"v. 谴责，指责；判刑","phonetic_us":"/kən'dɛm/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'dens/","example":"the mist which condensed on every cold surface 每个冰冷的表面上凝结的水汽","phonetic_us":"/kən'dɛns/","translation":"v. 压缩，使缩短","word":"condense"},{"word":"condition","translation":"n. 状况，状态；环境","phonetic_us":"/kən'dɪʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/kən'dɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Profits increased by £1.5m, despite the difficult economic conditions. 尽管经济形势不佳，利润还是增长了150万英镑。"},{"example":"The Senator’s conduct is being investigated by the Ethics Committee. 该参议员的行为正受到道德委员会的调查。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒndʌkt/","translation":"n. 举止，行为；指导","phonetic_us":"/kən'dʌkt/","word":"conduct"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'dʌktə/","example":"Graphite is a highly efficient conductor of electricity. 石墨是一种高效的电导体。","phonetic_us":"/kən'dʌktɚ/","translation":"n. 售票员；(乐队)指挥","word":"conductor"},{"example":"Representatives from over 100 countries attended the International Peace Conference in Geneva. 来自一百多个国家的代表出席了在日内瓦举行的国际和平大会。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnf(ə)r(ə)ns/","translation":"n. 会议，讨论会","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnfərəns/","word":"conference"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'fes/","example":"Occasionally people confess to crimes they haven’t committed just to get attention. 偶尔人们会承认自己并未犯过的罪行，那只是为了引人注意。","word":"confess","phonetic_us":"/kən'fɛs/","translation":"v. 供认，承认；坦白"},{"example":"I felt I was doing well and my confidence began to grow. 我觉得自己干得不错，自信心就开始增加了。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnfɪdəns/","word":"confidence","translation":"n. 信心","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnfɪdəns/"},{"example":"Despite her disability, Philippa is very confident. 菲莉帕虽然有残疾，却很自信。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnfɪd(ə)nt/","translation":"adj. 确信的，自信的","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnfɪdənt/","word":"confident"},{"word":"confidential","phonetic_us":"/,kɑnfɪ'dɛnʃl/","translation":"adj.  秘密的， 机密的； 亲信的","example":"a confidential government report 一份机密的政府报告","phonetic_uk":"/ˌkɒnfɪ'denʃl/"},{"example":"Vaughan is confined to a wheelchair . 沃恩离不开轮椅。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'faɪn/","word":"confine","translation":"v. 限制；禁闭","phonetic_us":"/kən'faɪn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'fə:m/","example":"New evidence has confirmed the first witness’s story. 新的证据证实了第一个证人的说法。","word":"confirm","phonetic_us":"/kən'fɝm/","translation":"v. 确认；证实；批准"},{"example":"Personal ethics and professional ethics sometimes conflict. 个人道德与职业道德之间有时会相冲突。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnflɪkt/","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnflɪkt/","translation":"v. 冲突","word":"conflict"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'fɔ:m/","example":"It is a solid, proven solution for adopting multiple standards -- whether your goal is to conform to the law or to improve your business practices. 它是一个坚固的、已经证实采用多个标准的解决方案，不管你的目标是遵守法律还是改善你的商业实践。","translation":"v. 相一致，遵守","phonetic_us":"/kən'fɔrm/","word":"conform"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'frʌnt/","example":"The problems confronting the new government were enormous. 新政府面临的难题是巨大的。","word":"confront","phonetic_us":"/kən'frʌnt/","translation":"v. 面对"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,kɒnfrʌn'teɪʃn/","example":"She had stayed in her room to avoid another confrontation. 她待在自己的房间里，以避免再次发生冲突。","word":"confrontation","translation":"n. 冲突，对抗","phonetic_us":"/,kɑnfrən'teʃən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kən'fjʊz/","translation":"v. 使混淆，迷惑","word":"confuse","phonetic_uk":"/kənˈfju:z/","example":"People might well confuse the two products. 人们很容易混淆这两种产品。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'fjuːʒ(ə)n/","example":"To avoid confusion, the teams wore different colours. 为了避免混淆，各队穿着不同颜色的服装。","word":"confusion","phonetic_us":"/kən'fjʊʒən/","translation":"n. 混乱；骚乱；混淆"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'grætjʊleɪt/","example":"He never even stopped to congratulate me. 他甚至没有过来向我祝贺。","translation":"v. 祝贺，向…道喜","phonetic_us":"/kən'ɡrætʃulet/","word":"congratulate"},{"translation":"n. 祝贺；祝贺词","phonetic_us":"/kən,ɡrætʃu'leʃən/","word":"congratulation","phonetic_uk":"/kəngrætjʊ'leɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"letters of congratulation 祝贺信"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒŋgres/","example":"a congress of the ruling Labor Party 执政党工党的代表大会","word":"congress","phonetic_us":"/'kɑŋɡrəs/","translation":"n. 大会；国会，议会"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'dʒʌŋ(k)ʃ(ə)n/","example":"The worksheets are designed to be used in conjunction with the new course books. 这些活页练习题专门用来与新课本配套使用。","word":"conjunction","phonetic_us":"/kən'dʒʌŋkʃən/","translation":"n. 接合，连接；连接词"},{"example":"We’d like two rooms with connecting doors (= doors that join the rooms ) . 我们想要两个有门相通的房间。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'nekt/","word":"connect","phonetic_us":"/kə'nɛkt/","translation":"v. 连接，连结；联系"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəˈnekʃn/","example":"Police have so far failed to establish a connection between the two murders. 到目前为止警方尚未确定两宗凶杀案之间有关联。","translation":"n. 连接，联系；连贯性","phonetic_us":"/kə'nɛkʃən/","word":"connection"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɒnek'tɪvɪtɪ/","example":"a growing demand for high-speed connectivity 对高速连接功能日益增长的需求","word":"connectivity","phonetic_us":"/,kɑnɛk'tɪvɪti/","translation":"n. 连接，联系"},{"word":"connexion","phonetic_us":"/kə'nekʃən/","translation":"n. connection的英式拼法","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/kə'nekʃn/"},{"example":"The Normans conquered England in 1066. 诺曼人于 1066 年征服英格兰。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒŋkə/","word":"conquer","phonetic_us":"/'kɑŋkɚ/","translation":"v. 征服，战胜；破除"},{"word":"conquest","phonetic_us":"/'kɑŋkwɛst/","translation":"n. 攻取，征服；克服","example":"the Norman Conquest (= the conquest of England by the Normans ) 诺曼征服","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒŋkwest/"},{"translation":"n. 良心","phonetic_us":"/ˈkɑːnʃəns/","word":"conscience","example":"Well, at least I can face them all with a clear conscience (= the knowledge that you have done nothing wrong ) . 好吧，至少我可以问心无愧地面对他们所有人。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔnʃəns/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnʃəs/","example":"The driver was still conscious when the ambulance arrived. 救护车赶到时，司机仍然神志清醒。","word":"conscious","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnʃəs/","translation":"adj. 意识到的；有意的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnʃəsnɪs/","example":"The painful memories eventually faded from her consciousness. 那些痛苦的回忆最终从她的意识中淡去了。","word":"consciousness","translation":"n. 意识","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnʃəsnəs/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kən'sɛnsəs/","translation":"n. 一致意见","word":"consensus","example":"The EU Council of Finance Ministers failed to reach a consensus on the pace of integration. 欧盟财政部长会议未能就一体化的进度达成共识。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sensəs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'sent/","example":"He finally consented to go. 他最终同意去。","word":"consent","translation":"v. 允许，同意；n. 同意，一致","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɛnt/"},{"word":"consequence","translation":"n. 结果，成果","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnsəkwɛns/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɔnsikwəns/","example":"Her lawyer said she understood the consequences of her actions and was prepared to go to jail. 她的律师说她明白自己行为的后果并准备去坐牢。"},{"word":"consequently","translation":"adv. 结果","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnsəkwɛntli/","example":"Most computer users have never received any formal keyboard training. Consequently, their keyboard skills are inefficient. 大多数的电脑使用者都没有经过正规的键盘操作训练，因此他们的键盘技巧不够熟练。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɒnsɪkwəntli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌkɒnsəˈveɪʃn/","example":"wildlife conservation 野生生物保护","phonetic_us":"/,kɑnsɚ'veʃən/","translation":"n. 保护，保存","word":"conservation"},{"example":"a very conservative attitude to education 对待教育非常守旧的态度","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sə:vətiv/","translation":"adj. 保守的，传统的","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɝvətɪv/","word":"conservative"},{"example":"We will have to consider your offer carefully . 我们得仔细考虑你的提议。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sɪdə/","word":"consider","translation":"v. 认为；考虑；关心","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɪdɚ/"},{"word":"considerable","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɪdərəbl/","translation":"adj. 相当大(或多)的","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sidərəbl/","example":"Michael has already spent considerable time in Barcelona. 迈克尔在巴塞罗那已经待了相当长的时间了。"},{"example":"It’s considerably colder today. 今天冷多了。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sɪd(ə)rəblɪ/","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɪdərəbli/","translation":"adv. 相当地，非常地","word":"considerably"},{"phonetic_us":"/kənˈsɪdərɪt/","translation":"adj. 体贴的；考虑周到的","word":"considerate","phonetic_uk":"/kənˈsɪdərət/","example":"He was always kind and considerate. 他总是很善良，为别人着想。"},{"word":"consideration","translation":"n. 考虑，思考；体贴","phonetic_us":"/kən,sɪdə'reʃən/","example":"proposals put forward for consideration 提请考虑的建议","phonetic_uk":"/kənsɪdə'reɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"translation":"prep.  鉴于， 考虑到， 顾及","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɪdərɪŋ/","word":"considering","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sɪdərɪŋ/","example":"Considering the strength of the opposition, we did very well to score two goals. 考虑到对方实力强大，我们能攻进两球已经很不错了。"},{"word":"consist","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɪst/","translation":"v. 由……组成","example":"My diet consisted almost exclusively of chocolate-covered cookies and glasses of milk. 我的饮食几乎只包含裹上巧克力的曲奇饼和一杯杯牛奶。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sɪst/"},{"word":"consistent","translation":"adj. 一致的","phonetic_us":"/kən'sɪstənt/","phonetic_uk":"/kənˈsɪstənt/","example":"She’s the team’s most consistent player. 她是该队中表现最为稳定的选手。"},{"word":"conspicuous","phonetic_us":"/kən'spɪkjʊəs/","translation":"adj. 显著地","phonetic_uk":"/kən'spɪkjʊəs/","example":"The notice must be displayed in a conspicuous place. 通告一定要贴在显眼的地方。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnstənt/","example":"There was a constant stream of visitors to the house. 参观这幢房子的游客川流不息。","word":"constant","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnstənt/","translation":"adj. 不断的，持续的"},{"example":"He talked constantly about his work. 他不断地谈到他的工作。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnst(ə)ntlɪ/","word":"constantly","translation":"adv. 不断地，时常地","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnstəntli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnstɪtjuːt/","example":"We must redefine what constitutes a family. 我们必须对家庭的构成重新定义。","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnstətut/","translation":"v. 组成","word":"constitute"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɒnstɪ'tjuːʃ(ə)n/","example":"The right to speak freely is written into the Constitution of the United States. 言论自由的权利被写入美国宪法。","translation":"n. 章程；体质；构造","phonetic_us":"/'kɑnstə'tʊʃən/","word":"constitution"},{"word":"construct","phonetic_us":"/kən'strʌkt/","translation":"v. 建造；建设；构筑","example":"There are plans to construct a new road bridge across the river. 有计划要建造一条新的跨河公路桥。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'strʌkt/"},{"word":"construction","phonetic_us":"/kən'strʌkʃən/","translation":"n. 建筑","example":"a road construction project 道路修建计划","phonetic_uk":"/kən'strʌkʃn/"},{"example":"The meeting was very constructive. 这次会议很有建设性。","phonetic_uk":"/kənˈstrʌktɪv/","translation":"adj. 建设的，建设性的","phonetic_us":"/kən'strʌktɪv/","word":"constructive"},{"example":"If symptoms persist, consult a doctor without delay. 如果症状持续的话，马上咨询医生。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sʌlt/","word":"consult","translation":"v. 咨询","phonetic_us":"/kən'sʌlt/"},{"word":"consultancy","translation":"n.  咨询公司","phonetic_us":"/kən'sʌltənsi/","phonetic_uk":"/kən'sʌltənsi/","example":"a management consultancy 管理咨询公司"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'sʌlt(ə)nt/","example":"a management consultant 管理顾问","word":"consultant","translation":"n. 顾问","phonetic_us":"/kən'sʌltənt/"},{"example":"Only 27% of the paper we consume is recycled. 我们消耗的纸张只有 27% 得到回收利用。","phonetic_uk":"/kənˈsju:m/","word":"consume","translation":"v. 消费，消耗","phonetic_us":"/kənˈsum/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'sjuːmə/","example":"Consumers will soon be paying higher airfares. 不久消费者就要支付更高的机票价了。","phonetic_us":"/kən'sumɚ/","translation":"n.  消费者， 用户， 消耗者","word":"consumer"},{"word":"consumption","phonetic_us":"/kən'sʌmpʃən/","translation":"n. 消费，消耗","phonetic_uk":"/kənˈsʌmpʃn/","example":"Vigorous exercise increases oxygen consumption. 剧烈运动增加氧的消耗。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɑntækt/","translation":"v & n. 联系，接触","word":"contact","example":"The town is cut off from contact with the outside world. 小镇与外界的联系被切断了。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔntækt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'teɪn/","example":"The thieves stole a purse containing bank-notes. 小偷们偷到了一个里面有钞票的钱包。","word":"contain","phonetic_us":"/kən'ten/","translation":"v. 包含，容纳；等于"},{"example":"ice cream in plastic containers 塑料容器里的冰激凌","phonetic_uk":"/kən'teɪnə/","translation":"n. 容器；集装箱","phonetic_us":"/kən'tenɚ/","word":"container"},{"example":"Drinking water supplies are believed to have been contaminated. 据信饮用水已受到污染。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'tæmɪneɪt/","word":"contaminate","phonetic_us":"/kən'tæmɪnet/","translation":"v. 污染，弄脏"},{"word":"contemporary","translation":"adj. 当代的，现代的","phonetic_us":"/kən'tɛmpərɛri/","example":"She writes a lot of contemporary music for people like Whitney Houston. 她为惠特尼·休斯敦等人创作大量当代音乐作品。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'temprərɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'tem(p)t/","example":"The public is treated with contempt by broadcasters. 公众受到了节目主持人的轻蔑对待。","translation":"n. 轻蔑；藐视；受辱","phonetic_us":"/kən'tɛmpt/","word":"contempt"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒntent/","example":"The content of the media course includes scripting, editing and camera work. 大众传媒课程的内容包括稿件写作、剪辑和摄像操作。","word":"content","phonetic_us":"/'kɑntɛnt/","translation":"n. 内容"},{"word":"contest","translation":"n. 比赛","phonetic_us":"/kən'tɛst/","example":"Stone decided to hold a contest to see who could write the best song. 斯通决定举行一场比赛，看谁能够写出最佳歌曲。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒntest/"},{"translation":"n. 背景，环境","phonetic_us":"/'kɑntɛkst/","word":"context","example":"The meaning of ‘mad’ depends on its context. mad 一词的意义要视上下文而定。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔntekst/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒntɪnənt/","example":"the continents of Asia and Africa 亚洲及非洲大陆","translation":"n. 大陆；陆地；洲","phonetic_us":"/'kɑntɪnənt/","word":"continent"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'tɪnjʊəl/","example":"five weeks of continual rain 持续了五个星期的降雨","translation":"adj. 不断的；连续的","phonetic_us":"/kən'tɪnjuəl/","word":"continual"},{"example":"He will be continuing his education in the US. 他将在美国继续求学。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'tɪnjuː/","word":"continue","translation":"v. 继续，连续；延伸","phonetic_us":"/kən'tɪnju/"},{"example":"continuous economic growth 持续的经济增长","phonetic_uk":"/kən'tɪnjʊəs/","phonetic_us":"/kən'tɪnjʊəs/","translation":"adj. 连续不断的，持续的","word":"continuous"},{"translation":"n. 合同","phonetic_us":"/'kɑntrækt/","word":"contract","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔntrækt/","example":"Employees who refuse to relocate are in breach of contract (= have done something not allowed by their contracts ) . 员工拒绝调动岗位是违反合约的。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɒntrə'dɪkʃ(ə)n/","example":"apparent contradictions in the defendant’s testimony 被告证词中的明显矛盾","phonetic_us":"/,kɑntrə'dɪkʃən/","translation":"n. 矛盾，不一致；否认","word":"contradiction"},{"translation":"adj. 相反的；n. 相反","phonetic_us":"/'kɑntrɛri/","word":"contrary","example":"Two contrary views emerged. 出现了两种相反的观点。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒntrərɪ/"},{"example":"The sauce is quite sweet, so add dried thyme as a contrast. 这调味汁很甜，所以要加点干百里香作为陪衬。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔntræst/","word":"contrast","translation":"n. 对比，反差；v. 对比","phonetic_us":"/'kɑntræst/"},{"example":"The three sons also contribute to the family business. 3个儿子也为家族企业做贡献。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'tribju:t/","translation":"v. 捐款，贡献","phonetic_us":"/kən'trɪbjut/","word":"contribute"},{"word":"contribution","translation":"n. 贡献；捐献","phonetic_us":"/,kɑntrɪ'bjuʃən/","example":"a campaign contribution 竞选捐款","phonetic_uk":"/kɒntrɪ'bjuːʃ(ə)n/"},{"translation":"v. 控制，克制；n. 控制","phonetic_us":"/kən'trol/","word":"control","phonetic_uk":"/kən'trəʊl/","example":"Police had to be called in to control the crowds. 只好调来警察控制人群。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌkɒntrə'vɜːʃl/","example":"the controversial issue of welfare reform 福利改革这一有争议的话题","phonetic_us":"/,kɑntrə'vɝʃl/","translation":"adj.  引起争论的， 有争议的","word":"controversial"},{"word":"controversy","translation":"n.  争论， 辩论","phonetic_us":"/ˈkɑntrəvɝ​sɪ/","example":"a political controversy 政治争议","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒntrəvɜːsi/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kən'vinɪəns/","translation":"n. 便利，方便；厕所","word":"convenience","example":"Ready meals sell well because of their convenience. 即食餐因为方便销路好。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'viːnɪəns/"},{"word":"convenient","translation":"adj. 方便的","phonetic_us":"/kən'vinɪənt/","phonetic_uk":"/kən'viːnɪənt/","example":"Mail-order catalogs are a convenient way to shop. 使用邮购目录是一种方便的购物方式。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'venʃ(ə)n/","example":"Playing together teaches children social conventions such as sharing. 一起玩耍可教会儿童与人分享等社会常规。","phonetic_us":"/kən'vɛnʃən/","translation":"n. 习俗，惯例；公约","word":"convention"},{"phonetic_us":"/kən'vɛnʃənl/","translation":"adj. 传统的","word":"conventional","phonetic_uk":"/kən'venʃənl/","example":"Internet connections through conventional phone lines are fairly slow. 通过传统的电话线来连接因特网速度很慢。"},{"word":"conversation","phonetic_us":"/,kɑnvɚ'seʃən/","translation":"n. 会话，非正式会谈","phonetic_uk":"/kɒnvə'seɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"a telephone conversation 电话交谈"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɑnvɝsli/","translation":"adv. 相反地","word":"conversely","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒnvɜːslɪ; kən'vɜːslɪ/","example":"American consumers prefer white eggs; conversely, British buyers like brown eggs. 美国的消费者喜欢白色的鸡蛋，而英国的消费者却相反，他们喜欢棕色的鸡蛋。"},{"translation":"n. 转变，转化；改变","phonetic_us":"/kən'vɝʒn/","word":"conversion","example":"...the conversion of disused rail lines into cycle routes. …把废弃的铁路改变成自行车道。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'vɜːʃ(ə)n/"},{"word":"convert","translation":"v. 使转变；使改变","phonetic_us":"/kən'vɝt/","phonetic_uk":"/kən'vɜːt/","example":"a 19th-century converted barn 由19世纪谷仓改建的房子"},{"word":"convey","phonetic_us":"/kən've/","translation":"v. 传达，传递","example":"All this information can be conveyed in a simple diagram. 所有这些信息可以通过一张简单的图表来表示。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'veɪ/"},{"translation":"v. 证明…有罪","phonetic_us":"/kən'vɪkt/","word":"convict","phonetic_uk":"/kən'vɪkt/","example":"a convicted murderer 已定罪的谋杀犯"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kən'vɪkʃn/","example":"It was a reasonable explanation, but his voice lacked conviction . 这解释合情合理，只是他的语气不坚定。","word":"conviction","phonetic_us":"/kən'vɪkʃən/","translation":"n.  确信； 坚定的信仰； 说服， 信服； 定罪， 判罪"},{"phonetic_us":"/kən'vɪns/","translation":"v. 使相信","word":"convince","example":"Her arguments didn’t convince everyone, but changes were made. 她的论点不能说服每个人，但还是引起了一些变化。","phonetic_uk":"/kən'vɪns/"},{"example":"convincing evidence of his guilt 证明他有罪的有力证据","phonetic_uk":"/kən'vɪnsɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 令人信服的","phonetic_us":"/kən'vɪnsɪŋ/","word":"convincing"},{"example":"Where did you learn to cook? 你在哪里学烹调的？","phonetic_uk":"/kʊk/","word":"cook","phonetic_us":"/kʊk/","translation":"v. 烹调，煮；v. 烧菜"},{"word":"cool","phonetic_us":"/kul/","translation":"adj. 凉的，冷静的","phonetic_uk":"/kuːl/","example":"She swam out into the cool water. 她往外游向清凉的水里。"},{"example":"They agreed to co-operate with Brazil on a programme to protect the rain forests. 他们同意和巴西合作进行一个保护热带雨林的项目。","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊ'ɒpəreɪt/","phonetic_us":"/koʊˈɑːpəreɪt/","translation":"v. 合作，协作；配合","word":"cooperate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəʊ'ɒpərətɪv/","example":"He was doing his best to be cooperative. 他在尽全力配合。","word":"cooperative","phonetic_us":"/ko'ɑpərətɪv/","translation":"adj. 合作的"},{"word":"coordinate","phonetic_us":"/ko'ɔrdɪnet/","translation":"v. 使协调，调节","example":"The agencies are working together to co-ordinate policy on food safety. 这些机构在共同合作为食品安全政策做协调工作。","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊ'ɔ:dɪneɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kəuˌɔːdɪ'neɪʃn/","example":"Too much alcohol affects your coordination. 喝酒太多会影响你动作的协调。","phonetic_us":"/ko,ɔrdɪ'neʃən/","translation":"n.  同等； 调和","word":"coordination"},{"example":"the local cop 本地警察","phonetic_uk":"/kɒp/","word":"cop","phonetic_us":"/kɑp/","translation":"n.  警察"},{"phonetic_us":"/kop/","translation":"v. 对付，应付","word":"cope","phonetic_uk":"/kəʊp/","example":"Sometimes I find it hard to cope. 有时候我觉得很难应付。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒpə/","example":"He offered to do the job for a few coppers. 他说他来做这份工作，给他几个铜板就行。","word":"copper","phonetic_us":"/'kɑpɚ/","translation":"n. 铜；铜币，铜制器"},{"translation":"n. 抄件；v. 抄写，复制","phonetic_us":"/'kɑpi/","word":"copy","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒpɪ/","example":"back-up copies of your files 你的文档的备份"},{"translation":"n.  版权","phonetic_us":"/'kɑpɪraɪt/","word":"copyright","example":"Who owns the copyright of this book? 谁拥有这本书的版权？","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒpiraɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɔːd/","example":"The robe was held at the waist by a cord. 在袍子腰处束了根细绳。","word":"cord","phonetic_us":"/kɔrd/","translation":"n. 细绳，粗线，索"},{"word":"cordial","translation":"adj. 真诚的，诚恳的","phonetic_us":"/'kɔrdʒəl/","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔːdɪəl/","example":"The talks were conducted in a cordial atmosphere. 会谈在友好的气氛中进行。"},{"translation":"n. 果实的心，核心","phonetic_us":"/kɔr/","word":"core","example":"Remove the cores, and bake the apples for 40 minutes. 去除果心，然后把苹果烤40分钟。","phonetic_uk":"/kɔː/"},{"translation":"n. 谷物；(英)小麦","phonetic_us":"/kɔrn/","word":"corn","phonetic_uk":"/kɔːn/","example":"fields of corn 一片片麦田"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɔrnɚ/","translation":"n. 角；犄角；边远地区","word":"corner","example":"He pulled a dirty handkerchief out by its corner and waved it at me. 他拽出一块脏手帕，捏着一角向我挥动。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɔːnə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɔ:pərət/","example":"corporate responsibility 共同的责任","phonetic_us":"/ˈkɔːrpərət/","translation":"adj. 法人的；团体的；社团的","word":"corporate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɔːpə'reɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"He works for a large American corporation. 他在一家美国大公司工作。","word":"corporation","translation":"n. 公司，企业；社团","phonetic_us":"/,kɔrpə'reʃən/"},{"example":"If my calculations are correct, we’re about ten miles from Exeter. 如果我计算得没错的话，我们离埃克塞特大约十英里。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'rekt/","phonetic_us":"/kə'rɛkt/","translation":"adj. 正确的；v. 纠正","word":"correct"},{"word":"correction","phonetic_us":"/kə'rɛkʃən/","translation":"n. 改正，纠正，修改","phonetic_uk":"/kə'rekʃ(ə)n/","example":"I just need to make a few corrections , and then we can send it to the printer. 我只要修改几个地方，然后就可以把它发送到打印机。"},{"word":"correspond","phonetic_us":"/,kɔrə'spɑnd/","translation":"v. 相符合；相当","phonetic_uk":"/kɒrɪ'spɒnd/","example":"The two halves of the document did not correspond. 这份文件的前后两部分不相符。"},{"example":"A secretary came in twice a week to deal with his correspondence. 一个秘书每个星期来两次处理他的信件。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌkɒrə'spɒndəns/","translation":"n.  信件， 函件； 通信， 通信联系； 符合， 一致， 相似","phonetic_us":"/,kɔrə'spɑndəns/","word":"correspondence"},{"example":"Our correspondent in South Africa sent this report. 我们的驻南非记者发来这份报道。","phonetic_uk":"/kɒrɪ'spɒnd(ə)nt/","phonetic_us":"/,kɔrə'spɑndənt/","translation":"n. 通信者；通讯员","word":"correspondent"},{"word":"corresponding","phonetic_us":"/,kɔrə'spɑndɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 相应的；符合的","example":"The war and the corresponding fall in trade have had a devastating effect on the country. 战争以及由此所导致的贸易量下降对这个国家产生了致命的影响。","phonetic_uk":"/,kɒrɪ'spɒndɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒrɪdɔː/","example":"Go down here and the bathroom’s at the end of the corridor. 沿着这儿走，浴室就在走廊的尽头。","phonetic_us":"/'kɔrɪdɔr/","translation":"n. 走廊，回廊，通路","word":"corridor"},{"phonetic_us":"/kɔst/","translation":"n. 价格，代价；成本","word":"cost","example":"I offered to pay the cost of the taxi. 我提出支付出租车费。","phonetic_uk":"/kɒst/"},{"word":"costly","phonetic_us":"/'kɔstli/","translation":"adj. 昂贵的；价值高的","example":"Such a database would be extremely costly to set up. 建立这样一个数据库要花很多钱。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒs(t)lɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kɑtɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 村舍，小屋","word":"cottage","phonetic_uk":"/'kɒtɪdʒ/","example":"a country cottage 乡间小屋"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɒt(ə)n/","example":"a white cotton shirt 白色棉布衬衫","word":"cotton","translation":"n. 棉；棉线；棉布","phonetic_us":"/'kɑtn/"},{"example":"Matthew coughed and cleared his throat. 马修咳了一声清清喉咙。","phonetic_uk":"/kɒf/","word":"cough","translation":"v. 咳，咳嗽；n. 咳嗽","phonetic_us":"/kɔf/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/kəd; kʊd/","word":"could","phonetic_us":"/kʊd/","translation":"aux. v(can的过去式)"},{"example":"the council for civil liberties 公民自由委员会","phonetic_uk":"/'kaʊnsl/","translation":"n. 议会","phonetic_us":"/'kaʊnsl/","word":"council"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kaʊns(ə)l/","example":"My advisers counselled me to do nothing. 我的顾问建议我不要做任何事情。","phonetic_us":"/'kaʊnsl/","translation":"v. 忠告，建议","word":"counsel"},{"translation":"n. 咨询服务","phonetic_us":"/'kaʊnslɪŋ/","word":"counseling","example":"If the answer is no, you really need to get some professional counseling to determine if this marriage should be saved. 如果回答是否定的，你就真的该去咨询一下专家，决定一下你是否改维持这段婚姻了。","phonetic_uk":"/'kaʊnsəlɪŋ/"},{"example":"I was amazed at the number of plants - I counted 147. 我对植物的数量之多感到惊讶，我数了有147棵。","phonetic_uk":"/kaʊnt/","phonetic_us":"/kaʊnt/","translation":"v. 计算；v. 数，计数","word":"count"},{"example":"He wondered if the girl behind the counter recognised him. 他在想柜台后面的那个女孩是否认出了他。","phonetic_uk":"/'kaʊntə/","phonetic_us":"/'kaʊntɚ/","translation":"n. 柜台；计数器","word":"counter"},{"example":"the Scandinavian countries 斯堪的纳维亚国家","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌntrɪ/","word":"country","translation":"n. 国家，国土；农村","phonetic_us":"/'kʌntri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌntrɪsaɪd/","example":"The house had lovely views over open countryside . 这房子望出去是开阔的乡村美景。","word":"countryside","translation":"n. 乡下，农村","phonetic_us":"/'kʌntrɪsaɪd/"},{"word":"county","phonetic_us":"/'kaʊnti/","translation":"n. 英国的郡，美国的县","phonetic_uk":"/'kaʊntɪ/","example":"Fairfax County, Virginia 弗吉尼亚州费尔法克斯县"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌp(ə)l/","example":"a newly married couple 一对新婚夫妇","word":"couple","phonetic_us":"/'kʌpl/","translation":"n. 夫妻，情侣"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kupɑn/","translation":"n.  礼券， 优惠券， 配给券； 联票； 票证","word":"coupon","example":"The coupon entitles you to ten cents off your next purchase. 这张优惠券可以让你在下次购物时节省10分钱。","phonetic_uk":"/'kuːpɒn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌrɪdʒ/","example":"Sue showed great courage throughout her illness. 休在生病期间表现出了极大的勇气。","word":"courage","translation":"n. 勇气，胆量，胆识","phonetic_us":"/ 'kɝrɪdʒ/"},{"translation":"adj. 有勇气的","phonetic_us":"/kə'redʒəs/","word":"courageous","example":"He was wrong, and courageous enough to admit it. 他是错了，而且有勇气承认自己错了。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'reɪdʒəs/"},{"translation":"n. 课程；过程；一道菜","phonetic_us":"/kɔrs/","word":"course","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/kɔːs/"},{"word":"court","phonetic_us":"/kɔrt/","translation":"n. 法院，法庭；庭院","phonetic_uk":"/kɔːt/","example":"It could not be proved in a court of law. 这无法在法庭上证实。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɔːtjɑːd/","example":"the castle courtyard 城堡的庭院","word":"courtyard","translation":"n.  庭院， 院子","phonetic_us":"/'kɔrtjɑrd/"},{"example":"My cousin Mark helped me to bring in the bags. 我表弟马克帮我把包提了进来。","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌz(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'kʌzn/","translation":"n. 堂(或表)兄弟(姐妹)","word":"cousin"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌvə/","example":"Cover the pot and bake for an hour. 把锅盖上，烘烤一小时。","word":"cover","translation":"v. 盖，包括；n. 盖子","phonetic_us":"/'kʌvɚ/"},{"example":"a herd of cows 一群牛","phonetic_uk":"/kaʊ/","word":"cow","translation":"n. 母牛，奶牛；母兽","phonetic_us":"/kaʊ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kaʊɚd/","translation":"n. 懦夫；胆怯者","word":"coward","example":"Try it. Don’t be such a coward. 试一下，别那么胆小。","phonetic_uk":"/'kaʊəd/"},{"translation":"adj. 舒适的","phonetic_us":"/'kozi/","word":"cozy","phonetic_uk":"/'kozi/","example":"Come over to the fire and cozy up a bit. 到火炉这边来会感到舒适一点。"},{"example":"She opened the door a crack and peeped into the room. 她把门打开一条缝，往房间里偷看。","phonetic_uk":"/kræk/","phonetic_us":"/kræk/","translation":"n. 裂缝，裂纹；v. 爆裂","word":"crack"},{"word":"craft","phonetic_us":"/kræft/","translation":"n. 工艺；手艺，行业","example":"traditional rural crafts 传统的乡村手工艺","phonetic_uk":"/krɑːft/"},{"translation":"n. 起重机，摄影升降机","phonetic_us":"/kren/","word":"crane","phonetic_uk":"/kreɪn/","example":"The little prefabricated hut was lifted away by a huge crane. 那间小小的预制棚屋被一台巨大的起重机吊走了。"},{"example":"The jet crashed after take-off. 这架喷气式飞机起飞后就坠毁了。","phonetic_uk":"/kræʃ/","word":"crash","translation":"n & v. 坠落;坠毁;撞击","phonetic_us":"/kræʃ/"},{"word":"crawl","translation":"v. 爬，爬行","phonetic_us":"/krɔl/","example":"We crawled into bed at 2 am. 我们凌晨两点爬上了床。","phonetic_uk":"/krɔːl/"},{"word":"crazy","translation":"adj. 疯狂的，荒唐的","phonetic_us":"/'krezi/","example":"The neighbours must think we’re crazy. 邻居一定会认为我们疯了。","phonetic_uk":"/'kreɪzɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/krim/","translation":"n. 奶油，乳脂；奶油色","word":"cream","example":"fresh cream 鲜奶油","phonetic_uk":"/kriːm/"},{"phonetic_us":"/krɪ'et/","translation":"v. 创造；引起，产生","word":"create","example":"Some people believe the universe was created by a big explosion. 有些人认为宇宙是通过一次大爆炸创造出来的。","phonetic_uk":"/kriː'eɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kriː'eɪtɪv/","example":"This job is so boring. I wish I could do something more creative. 这工作太单调了，我希望能做些更有创造性的事情。","translation":"adj. 创造性的，创作的","phonetic_us":"/krɪ'etɪv/","word":"creative"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌkri:eɪ'tɪvətɪ/","example":"artistic creativity 艺术创造力","word":"creativity","translation":"n. 创造力","phonetic_us":"/,krie'tɪvəti/"},{"example":"all the living creatures in the sea 海洋中所有的生物","phonetic_uk":"/'kriːtʃə/","word":"creature","phonetic_us":"/'kritʃɚ/","translation":"n. 生物，动物，家畜"},{"example":"The store agreed to let him have credit. 商店同意他赊购。","phonetic_uk":"/'kredɪt/","word":"credit","translation":"n. 信用贷款；信用","phonetic_us":"/'krɛdɪt/"},{"example":"He crept back up the stairs, trying to avoid the ones that creaked. 他蹑手蹑脚地回楼上，尽量避开那些嘎吱作响的梯级。","phonetic_uk":"/kriːp/","translation":"v. 爬行；缓慢地行进","phonetic_us":"/krip/","word":"creep"},{"word":"crew","phonetic_us":"/krʊ/","translation":"n. 全体船员","phonetic_uk":"/kruː/","example":"The plane crashed, killing two of the crew and four passengers. 飞机坠毁，造成两名机组人员和四名乘客死亡。"},{"word":"cricket","phonetic_us":"/'krɪkɪt/","translation":"n. 板球；蟋蟀","example":"The boy traded his knife for a cricket bat. 那男孩用他的刀子换了一个板球棒。","phonetic_uk":"/'krɪkɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kraɪm/","example":"We moved here because there was very little crime. 我们搬到这里来是因为这里的犯罪率很低。","word":"crime","translation":"n. 罪，罪行；犯罪","phonetic_us":"/kraɪm/"},{"translation":"n. 犯人，罪犯，刑事犯","phonetic_us":"/'krɪmɪnl/","word":"criminal","example":"Police have described the man as a violent and dangerous criminal. 警方形容那名男子是个凶暴而危险的罪犯。","phonetic_uk":"/'krɪmɪn(ə)l/"},{"translation":"n.  犯罪学， 刑事学","phonetic_us":"/,krɪmɪ'nɑlədʒi/","word":"criminology","example":"The relationship between victimology and criminology is a longstanding issue within the academic realm. 被害人学与犯罪学之间的关系问题是学界的一个宿疑。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌkrɪmɪ'nɒlədʒi/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'krɪpl/","translation":"n. 跛子；残废的人","word":"cripple","example":"She has gone from being a healthy, fit, and sporty young woman to being a cripple. 她从一个健康、强壮、爱好体育运动的年轻姑娘变成了一个残疾人。","phonetic_uk":"/'krɪp(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kraɪsɪs/","example":"The country now faces an economic crisis . 该国目前正面临一场经济危机。","translation":"n. 危机","phonetic_us":"/'kraɪsɪs/","word":"crisis"},{"word":"critic","translation":"n. 批评家，评论家","phonetic_us":"/'krɪtɪk/","phonetic_uk":"/'kritik/","example":"Mather was a film critic for many years. 马瑟做过多年的电影评论家。"},{"example":"He made some highly critical remarks. 他发表了一些严厉的批判性言论。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkrɪtɪkl/","translation":"adj. 批评的，爱挑剔的","phonetic_us":"/'krɪtɪkl/","word":"critical"},{"word":"criticism","phonetic_us":"/'krɪtə'sɪzəm/","translation":"n. 批评","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkrɪtɪsɪzəm/","example":"Despite strong criticism , the new system is still in place. 尽管遭到了猛烈的批评，新制度依然原封不动。"},{"example":"Ron does nothing but criticize and complain all the time. 罗恩什么也不干，只是一味指责和抱怨。","phonetic_uk":"/'krɪtɪsaɪz/","word":"criticize","phonetic_us":"/'krɪtə'saɪz/","translation":"v. 批评；评论"},{"phonetic_uk":"/krɒp/","example":"The main crops were oats and barley. 主要作物是燕麦和大麦。","translation":"n. 农作物，庄稼；一熟","phonetic_us":"/krɑp/","word":"crop"},{"example":"He raised his arms in triumph as he crossed the line for his 100-metres win. 他以胜利的姿态高举双手跑过终点线，赢得了这场百米赛。","phonetic_uk":"/krɒs/","phonetic_us":"/krɔs/","translation":"v. 穿过；使交叉","word":"cross"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'krɒsɪŋ/","example":"You must give way to any pedestrians on the crossing. 必须让人行横道上的行人先行。","word":"crossing","translation":"n.  人行横道， 交叉口； 横渡","phonetic_us":"/'krɔsɪŋ/"},{"translation":"n. 鸦，乌鸦；v. 啼","phonetic_us":"/kro/","word":"crow","example":"The crows roosted in Fonsa's Tower. 那些乌鸦栖息在风萨塔里。","phonetic_uk":"/krəʊ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kraʊd/","translation":"n. 群；大众；一伙人","word":"crowd","phonetic_uk":"/kraʊd/","example":"A vast crowd gathered in the main square. 主广场上聚集了一大群人。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kraʊn/","example":"How long does it take to have crowns fitted? 镶齿冠需要多长时间？","phonetic_us":"/kraʊn/","translation":"n. 王冠，冕；花冠","word":"crown"},{"word":"crucial","translation":"adj. 至关重要的","phonetic_us":"/'krʊʃəl/","example":"The conservation of tropical forests is of crucial importance . 保护热带雨林至关重要。","phonetic_uk":"/'kruːʃ(ə)l/"},{"example":"a crude estimate of the population available for work 对劳动力人口的粗略估计","phonetic_uk":"/kruːd/","word":"crude","phonetic_us":"/krud/","translation":"adj. 简陋的；天然的"},{"word":"cruel","phonetic_us":"/'kruəl/","translation":"adj. 残忍的，残酷的","example":"His death was a cruel blow . 他的死是个无情的打击。","phonetic_uk":"/krʊəl/"},{"example":"The children had suffered cruelty and neglect. 这些孩子遭受虐待，无人照管。","phonetic_uk":"/'krʊəltɪ/","translation":"n. 残暴，残酷","phonetic_us":"/'krʊəlti/","word":"cruelty"},{"word":"cruise","phonetic_us":"/krʊz/","translation":"vi. 航游，巡航；缓慢巡行；n.  航游， 游弋","phonetic_uk":"/kruːz/","example":"She wants to cruise the canals of France in a barge. 她想坐驳船游览法国的运河。"},{"phonetic_us":"/krʌʃ/","translation":"v. 压碎，碾碎；镇压","word":"crush","phonetic_uk":"/krʌʃ/","example":"His leg was crushed in the accident. 他的腿在事故中被压断。"},{"example":"sandwiches with the crusts cut off 切去边皮的三明治","phonetic_uk":"/krʌst/","word":"crust","translation":"n. 面包皮；硬外皮","phonetic_us":"/krʌst/"},{"example":"Don’t cry, Laura. It’ll be OK. 不要哭，劳拉，没事的。","phonetic_uk":"/kraɪ/","phonetic_us":"/kraɪ/","translation":"v. 哭，哭泣；叫喊","word":"cry"},{"example":"a set of six crystal glasses 六件套水晶玻璃杯","phonetic_uk":"/'krɪst(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/'krɪstl/","translation":"n. 水晶，结晶体；晶粒","word":"crystal"},{"phonetic_us":"/kjʊb/","translation":"n. 立方形；立方","word":"cube","phonetic_uk":"/kjuːb/","example":"a sugar cube 一块方糖"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kjuːbɪk/","example":"the cubic capacity of an engine 引擎汽缸的容积","translation":"adj. 立方形的；立方的","phonetic_us":"/'kjubɪk/","word":"cubic"},{"translation":"n. 黄瓜","phonetic_us":"/'kjʊ,kʌmbɚ/","word":"cucumber","example":"The \"gurkophone\" is one of their classics, made from a hollowed cucumber, a pepper and a carrot. 黄瓜管\"是他们的经典乐器之一,那是用掏空的黄瓜、辣椒和胡萝卜做的。","phonetic_uk":"/'kjuːkʌmbə/"},{"example":"She stood nervously in the wings waiting for her cue. 她紧张地站在台侧等待出场的提示。","phonetic_uk":"/kjuː/","word":"cue","translation":"n. 暗示，信号；提示；vt.  提示； 暗示","phonetic_us":"/kju/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kʌltɪvet/","translation":"v. 培养","word":"cultivate","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌltɪveɪt/","example":"We cultivated maize and watermelons. 我们种植玉米和西瓜。"},{"translation":"n. 文化，文明；教养","phonetic_us":"/'kʌltʃɚ/","word":"culture","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌltʃə/","example":"We speak Danish at home so that the boys don’t lose touch with their language and culture. 我们在家说丹麦语，这样男孩子们就不会脱离他们的语言和文化。"},{"word":"cunning","translation":"adj. 狡猾的，狡诈的","phonetic_us":"/'kʌnɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌnɪŋ/","example":"a cunning opponent 狡猾的对手"},{"word":"cup","translation":"n. 杯子；(一)杯；奖杯","phonetic_us":"/kʌp/","example":"Mathew picked up the cup and sipped his coffee. 马修拿起杯子抿了口咖啡。","phonetic_uk":"/kʌp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌbəd/","example":"It’s in the kitchen cupboard. 它在厨房的碗柜里。","word":"cupboard","translation":"n. 碗柜，碗碟橱；食橱","phonetic_us":"/'kʌbɚd/"},{"word":"curb","translation":"v & n. 控制","phonetic_us":"/kɝb/","example":"measures to curb the spread of the virus 控制病毒扩散的措施","phonetic_uk":"/kəb/"},{"word":"cure","translation":"v. 医治；消除；n. 治愈","phonetic_us":"/kjʊr/","phonetic_uk":"/kjʊə; kjɔː/","example":"She had some acupuncture treatment which seems to have cured her. 她接受了某种针刺疗法，好像把她的病治好了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kjʊərɪ'ɒsɪtɪ/","example":"I opened the packet just to satisfy my curiosity . 我打开包裹只是为了满足我的好奇心。","phonetic_us":"/,kjʊrɪ'ɑsəti/","translation":"n. 好奇心","word":"curiosity"},{"example":"Puppies are naturally curious. 小狗天生好奇。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkjʊəriəs/","phonetic_us":"/'kjʊrɪəs/","translation":"adj. 好奇的","word":"curious"},{"example":"Use a diffuser to maximise the volume and curl of your hair. 使用电吹风罩把头发吹得蓬松卷曲。","phonetic_uk":"/kɜːl/","word":"curl","phonetic_us":"/kɝl/","translation":"n. 卷毛；螺旋；v. 卷曲"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌrənsi/","example":"The bank can supply you with foreign currency . 这家银行能为你提供外币。","translation":"n.  通货， 货币； 通行， 流行","phonetic_us":"/ˈkɜrənsi/","word":"currency"},{"example":"the current President 现任总统","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌrənt/","word":"current","phonetic_us":"/kɝ​ənt/","translation":"adj. 当前的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌrəntlɪ/","example":"the products that are currently available 目前供应的产品","word":"currently","translation":"adv. 当前；一般地","phonetic_us":"/'kɝrəntlɪ/"},{"example":"Languages are an essential part of the school curriculum. 语言是学校课程中必不可少的部分。","phonetic_uk":"/kə'rɪkjələm/","word":"curriculum","phonetic_us":"/kə'rɪkjələm/","translation":"n.  课程， 全部课程"},{"translation":"n. 诅咒，咒骂；天谴","phonetic_us":"/kɝs/","word":"curse","example":"He believed that someone had put a curse on the house. 他相信有人对这房子下了诅咒。","phonetic_uk":"/kɜːs/"},{"example":"red velvet curtains 红色的丝绒窗帘","phonetic_uk":"/'kɜːt(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'kɝtn/","translation":"n. 帘，窗帘；幕(布)","word":"curtain"},{"word":"curve","translation":"n. 曲线；弯；v. 弄弯","phonetic_us":"/kɝv/","phonetic_uk":"/kɜːv/","example":"The curve illustrates costs per capita. 这条曲线显示人均费用。"},{"example":"a velvet cushion 天鹅绒垫子","phonetic_uk":"/'kʊʃ(ə)n/","word":"cushion","translation":"n. 垫子，坐垫，靠垫","phonetic_us":"/'kʊʃən/"},{"word":"custom","phonetic_us":"/'kʌstəm/","translation":"n. 习惯，风俗；海关","phonetic_uk":"/'kʌstəm/","example":"He awoke early, as was his custom. 他很早醒来，这是他的习惯。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kʌstəmə/","example":"We aim to offer good value and service to all our customers. 我们力求为所有的客户提供物有所值的商品和服务。","word":"customer","translation":"n. 顾客，主顾","phonetic_us":"/'kʌstəmɚ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kʌt/","translation":"v. 切，割，剪；减少","word":"cut","example":"They’re introducing CCTV cameras in an attempt to cut street crime in the area. 为了减少该地区的街头犯罪，他们安装了闭路电视摄像机。","phonetic_uk":"/kʌt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'saɪk(ə)l/","example":"a woman’s menstrual cycle 女性的月经周期","word":"cycle","phonetic_us":"/'saɪkl/","translation":"n. n自行车，循环"},{"phonetic_us":"/'delɪ/","translation":"adj. 每日的；n. 日报","word":"daily","example":"daily flights to Miami 每日飞往迈阿密的航班","phonetic_uk":"/'deɪlɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 牛奶场；乳制品","phonetic_us":"/'dɛri/","word":"dairy","example":"In my childhood, local dairies bought milk from local farmers. 在我小时候，本地的乳品公司向当地农场主收购牛奶。","phonetic_uk":"/'deərɪ/"},{"word":"dam","translation":"n. 水坝，水堤；障碍物","phonetic_us":"/dæm/","example":"Before the dam was built, Campbell River used to flood in the spring. 大坝建好之前，坎贝尔河常在春季发大水。","phonetic_uk":"/dæm/"},{"example":"insects that damage crops 破坏庄稼的昆虫","phonetic_uk":"/'dæmɪdʒ/","phonetic_us":"/'dæmɪdʒ/","translation":"v. 损害，毁坏；n. 损害","word":"damage"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dæm/","example":"Damn! I’ve left my keys in the office. 见鬼！我把钥匙忘在办公室了。","phonetic_us":"/dæm/","translation":"interjection. 该死，见鬼〔表示很生气或失望〕；adv. 非常，很；adj. 该死的〔表示对某人或某事物生气〕","word":"damn"},{"word":"damp","translation":"adj. 潮湿的，有湿气的","phonetic_us":"/dæmp/","phonetic_uk":"/dæmp/","example":"Wipe the leather with a damp cloth. 用湿布擦拭皮面。"},{"word":"dampen","phonetic_us":"/'dæmpən/","translation":"v. 抑制","phonetic_uk":"/'dæmp(ə)n/","example":"The light rain dampened the crowd’s enthusiasm. 小雨使观众的热情减退了。"},{"example":"Come on, let’s dance. 来吧，我们跳舞吧。","phonetic_uk":"/dɑːns/","word":"dance","phonetic_us":"/dæns/","translation":"v. 跳舞；摇晃；n. 舞"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dendʒɚ/","translation":"n. 危险；危险事物","word":"danger","example":"Danger! No boats beyond this point. 危险！船只不可越过此处。","phonetic_uk":"/'deɪn(d)ʒə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'deɪn(d)ʒ(ə)rəs/","example":"laws about dangerous dogs 有关危险犬类的法律","translation":"adj. 危险的，不安全的","phonetic_us":"/'dendʒərəs/","word":"dangerous"},{"word":"dare","phonetic_us":"/dɛr/","translation":"vt&aux. v敢；竟敢","example":"He wanted to ask her, but he didn’t dare. 他想问她，但又不敢。","phonetic_uk":"/deə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'deərɪŋ/","example":"a daring rescue attempt 大胆的营救行动","word":"daring","translation":"adj. 大胆的，勇敢的","phonetic_us":"/'dɛrɪŋ/"},{"example":"The church was dark and quiet. 教堂里黑魆魆的，寂静无声。","phonetic_uk":"/dɑːk/","word":"dark","translation":"adj. 暗的；黑色的","phonetic_us":"/dɑrk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɑːlɪŋ/","example":"Look, darling, there’s Mary. 看呀，亲爱的，玛丽来了。","word":"darling","translation":"n. 亲爱的人；宠儿","phonetic_us":"/'dɑrlɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dæʃ/","example":"Suddenly she dashed down to the cellar. 她猛地朝地窖冲过去。","word":"dash","phonetic_us":"/dæʃ/","translation":"v. 使猛撞；溅；n. 猛冲"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'deɪtə/","example":"The research involves collecting data from two random samples. 该项研究需要从两个随机样本里收集资料。","word":"data","translation":"n. 数据;；n. 资料","phonetic_us":"/'detə/"},{"word":"date","translation":"n. 日期；v. 注…日期","phonetic_us":"/det/","example":"The date on the letter was 30th August 1962. 信上的日期是1962年8月30日。","phonetic_uk":"/deɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɔːtə/","example":"She’s got two daughters and one son. 她有两个女儿和一个儿子。","translation":"n. 女儿","phonetic_us":"/'dɔtɚ/","word":"daughter"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɔːn/","example":"When dawn broke (= the first light of the day appeared ) , we were still 50 miles from Calcutta. 破晓的时候，我们离加尔各答还有50英里。","phonetic_us":"/dɔn/","translation":"n. 黎明；开端；v. 破晓","word":"dawn"},{"example":"She only leaves her house during the day. 她只在白天出门。","phonetic_uk":"/deɪ/","word":"day","translation":"n. (一)天，白昼，白天","phonetic_us":"/de/"},{"translation":"n. 白昼，日光；黎明","phonetic_us":"/'delaɪt/","word":"daylight","example":"The park is open to the public during daylight hours . 公园白天对公众开放。","phonetic_uk":"/'deɪlaɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ded/","example":"Her mother had been dead for ten years. 她母亲去世十年了。","word":"dead","phonetic_us":"/dɛd/","translation":"adj. 死的，无生命的"},{"word":"deadline","phonetic_us":"/ˈdedlaɪn/","translation":"n. 最后期限","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdedlaɪn/","example":"I’m always working under pressure to meet deadlines (= finish something on time ) . 我总是在赶工期的压力下工作。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dedlɪ/","example":"a deadly poison 致命的毒药","word":"deadly","phonetic_us":"/'dɛdli/","translation":"adj. 致命的，死一般的"},{"example":"communication between deaf and hearing people 失聪者和听力正常者之间的交流","phonetic_uk":"/def/","phonetic_us":"/dɛf/","translation":"adj. 聋的；不愿听的","word":"deaf"},{"word":"deal","translation":"n. 买卖；待遇；v. 给予","phonetic_us":"/dil/","example":"The prime minister promised farmers a new deal (= a new and fairer system ) . 首相向农民保证推行一项新政策。","phonetic_uk":"/diːl/"},{"translation":"adj. 亲爱的；int. 啊","phonetic_us":"/dɪr/","word":"dear","phonetic_uk":"/dɪə/","example":"Dear Sir or Madam, ... 尊敬的先生或女士，…"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɛθ/","translation":"n. 死，死亡；灭亡","word":"death","phonetic_uk":"/deθ/","example":"1.5 million people are in immediate danger of death from starvation. 150万人正因饥饿而即将面临死亡的危险。"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'bet/","translation":"n&vi. 争论，辩论","word":"debate","example":"the gun-control debate in the US 美国有关控制枪支的争论","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'beɪt/"},{"translation":"n. 债务","phonetic_us":"/dɛt/","word":"debt","phonetic_uk":"/det/","example":"He had enough money to pay off his outstanding debts. 他有足够的钱偿还亏欠的债务。"},{"word":"decade","translation":"n. 十年，十年期","phonetic_us":"/'dɛked/","example":"...the last decade of the nineteenth century. …19世纪的最后10年。","phonetic_uk":"/'dekeɪd; dɪ'keɪd/"},{"word":"decay","translation":"v. 腐烂；衰败；n. 腐烂","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'ke/","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'keɪ/","example":"Her body was already starting to decay. 她的尸体已经开始腐烂。"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'sit/","translation":"n. 欺骗，欺诈","word":"deceit","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'siːt/","example":"an atmosphere of hypocrisy and deceit 充满虚伪和欺骗的氛围"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'siːv/","example":"He had been deceived by a young man claiming to be the son of a millionaire. 他被一个自称是百万富翁之子的年轻人骗了。","translation":"v. 欺骗，蒙蔽，行骗","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'siv/","word":"deceive"},{"translation":"n. 十二月","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'sɛmbɚ/","word":"December","example":"In the dark of December. 在十二月的黑夜里。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'sembə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈdi:snt/","example":"a decent burial 得体的葬礼","word":"decent","translation":"adj. 正派的，体面的","phonetic_us":"/'disnt/"},{"word":"deception","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'sɛpʃən/","translation":"n.  欺骗； 诡计， 骗局","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'sepʃn/","example":"She didn’t have the courage to admit to her deception. 她没有勇气承认自己的欺骗行为。"},{"example":"Has anything been decided yet? 已经作出什么决定了吗？","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'saɪd/","word":"decide","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'saɪd/","translation":"v. 决定，决心；解决"},{"translation":"n. 决定，决心；果断","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'sɪʒn/","word":"decision","example":"Do you ever wonder if you made the right decision? 你怀疑过自己所作的决定是否正确吗？","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'sɪʒ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dek/","example":"Eddie returned to the flight deck (= the part of an aircraft where the pilot sits ) . 埃迪回到了驾驶舱。","word":"deck","translation":"n. 甲板；舱面；层面","phonetic_us":"/dɛk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌdeklə'reɪʃn/","example":"a ceasefire declaration 停火声明","translation":"n.  宣布， 宣告； 宣言， 声明； 申报","phonetic_us":"/,dɛklə'reʃən/","word":"declaration"},{"example":"A state of emergency has been declared. 已宣布进入紧急状态。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'kleə/","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'klɛr/","translation":"v. 断言；声明；表明","word":"declare"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'klaɪn/","example":"Spending on information technology has declined. 用于信息技术的支出减少了。","translation":"v. 下降，减少；拒绝","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'klaɪn/","word":"decline"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dɛkəret/","translation":"v. 装饰","word":"decorate","phonetic_uk":"/'dekəreɪt/","example":"The bathroom is decorated in green and yellow. 浴室里是用绿色和黄色装潢的。"},{"word":"decrease","translation":"vi&n. 减少，减少","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'kris/","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'kriːs/","example":"The number of people who have the disease has decreased significantly in recent years. 近年来，这种病的患者人数明显下降。"},{"word":"deduce","translation":"v. 演绎，推论，推断","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'dʊs/","example":"Alison cleverly deduced that I was the author of the letter. 艾莉森聪明地推断出我是这封信的作者。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'djuːs/"},{"word":"deed","phonetic_us":"/did/","translation":"n. 行为；功绩；契约","example":"After the morning’s good deeds he deserved a rest. 上午做了好事之后，他理应休息一下。","phonetic_uk":"/diːd/"},{"example":"a deep wound 很深的伤口","phonetic_uk":"/diːp/","word":"deep","translation":"adj. 深的；纵深的","phonetic_us":"/dip/"},{"translation":"v. 使加深，加剧","phonetic_us":"/'dipən/","word":"deepen","example":"The recession continues to deepen. 经济衰退继续加剧。","phonetic_uk":"/'diːp(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪə/","example":"The hunter wounded the deer. 猎人打伤了鹿。","translation":"n. 鹿","phonetic_us":"/dɪr/","word":"deer"},{"translation":"v. 战胜，击败；挫败","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'fit/","word":"defeat","example":"They hoped to defeat the enemy at sea. 他们希望在海上击败敌人。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'fiːt/"},{"example":"All the cars are tested for defects before they leave the factory. 所有汽车在出厂前都经过品质检验。","phonetic_uk":"/'diːfekt; dɪ'fekt/","word":"defect","phonetic_us":"/‘dɪfɛkt/","translation":"n. 缺点，缺陷，欠缺"},{"phonetic_us":"/di'fens/","translation":"n. 防御；防务；辩护","word":"defence","example":"The land was flat, giving no scope for defence. 土地非常平坦，无法做防卫之用。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'fens/"},{"translation":"v. 保卫，防守","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'fɛnd/","word":"defend","example":"a struggle to defend our homeland 保卫我们祖国的斗争","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'fend/"},{"word":"define","translation":"v. 下定义，确定","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'faɪn/","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'faɪn/","example":"the ability to define clients’ needs 确定客户需求的能力"},{"word":"definite","translation":"adj. 明确的；肯定的","phonetic_us":"/'dɛfɪnət/","phonetic_uk":"/'defɪnɪt/","example":"It’s impossible for me to give you a definite answer. 我不可能给你明确的答复。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dɛfɪnətli/","translation":"adv. 一定地，明确地","word":"definitely","example":"‘Do you reckon Margot will be there?’ ‘ Definitely not .’ “你估计玛戈会在那里吗？” “肯定不会。”","phonetic_uk":"/'defɪnɪtlɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/defɪ'nɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"a dictionary definition 词典里的释义","phonetic_us":"/,dɛfɪ'nɪʃən/","translation":"n. 定义","word":"definition"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'ɡri/","translation":"n. 程度","word":"degree","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈgri:/","example":"Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. 把烘箱预热至425度。"},{"example":"Don’t delay – send off for the information now. 别犹豫——即刻去函索取信息。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'leɪ/","word":"delay","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'le/","translation":"v. 推迟，延期"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈdɛlɪˌɡeɪt; -ɡɪt; (for v.,) ˈdɛlɪˌɡeɪt/","example":"Around 350 delegates attended the conference. 大约有350名代表参加了大会。","word":"delegate","phonetic_us":"/ˈdɛləgɪt; (for v.,) ˈdɛləˌgeɪt/","translation":"n.  代表， 代表团成员；vt.  委派…为代表； 授 ， 把…委托给"},{"phonetic_uk":"/delɪ'geɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"A trade delegation will visit Kuwait. 一个贸易代表团将访问科威特。","translation":"n. 代表团","phonetic_us":"/,dɛlɪ'ɡeʃən/","word":"delegation"},{"translation":"v. 删除；擦掉","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'lit/","word":"delete","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'liːt/","example":"His name was deleted from the list. 他的名字从名单上删掉了。"},{"word":"deliberate","translation":"adj. 故意的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'lɪbərət/","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'lɪb(ə)rət/","example":"a deliberate attempt to humiliate her 对她的故意羞辱"},{"example":"delicate hand-cut glass 易碎的手工刻花玻璃","phonetic_uk":"/'delɪkət/","translation":"adj. 纤细的；易碎的","phonetic_us":"/ˈdɛlɪkɪt/","word":"delicate"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'lɪʃəs/","translation":"adj. 美味的，怡人的","word":"delicious","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'lɪʃəs/","example":"‘The meal was absolutely delicious,’ she said politely. “这顿饭味道好极了。” 她礼貌地说道。"},{"example":"Throughout the house, the views are a constant source of surprise and delight. 整个房子，目之所及不停带来惊奇和欣喜。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'laɪt/","word":"delight","translation":"n. 高兴","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'laɪt/"},{"word":"delightful","translation":"adj. 高兴的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'laɪtfl/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'laɪtfʊl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'lɪvə(r)/","example":"The king delivered a televised speech to the nation on November 5. 国王在11月5日向全国发表了电视讲话。","word":"deliver","translation":"v. 发表","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'lɪvɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'lɪv(ə)rɪ/","example":"Most Indian restaurants offer free delivery. 大多数印度餐馆提供免费外送服务。","translation":"n. 投递；交付；分娩","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'lɪvəri/","word":"delivery"},{"phonetic_uk":"/di'mɑ:nd/","example":"Production is still increasing faster than demand. 生产仍比需求增长快。","translation":"v & n. 需求，要求","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'mænd/","word":"demand"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪˈmɑkrəsi/","translation":"n. 民主，民主制","word":"democracy","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'mɒkrəsɪ/","example":"a return to democracy after 16 years of military rule 16年军人统治后民主制度的恢复"},{"word":"democratic","translation":"adj. 民主的","phonetic_us":"/'dɛmə'krætɪk/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌdeməˈkrætɪk/","example":"a democratic government 民主政府"},{"example":"The study demonstrates the link between poverty and malnutrition. 这项研究证明了贫困与营养不良之间的联系。","phonetic_uk":"/'demənstreɪt/","phonetic_us":"/'dɛmən'stret/","translation":"v. 证明；展示","word":"demonstrate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dens/","example":"a dense rurally-based population 居住在乡村的密集人口","word":"dense","phonetic_us":"/dɛns/","translation":"adj. 密集的；浓厚的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'densətɪ/","example":"areas of high population density 人口密度高的地区","phonetic_us":"/'dɛnsəti/","translation":"n. 密度","word":"density"},{"example":"Good oral hygiene and regular dental care are important, whatever your age. 无论年龄大小，良好的口腔卫生和定期的牙齿保健都非常重要。","phonetic_uk":"/'dentl/","word":"dental","phonetic_us":"/'dɛntl/","translation":"adj.  牙齿的， 牙科的"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'nai/","translation":"v. 否定；拒绝相信","word":"deny","example":"The government denied the existence of poverty among 16- and 17-year-olds. 政府否认十六七岁的青少年当中存在贫困问题。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'naɪ/"},{"word":"depart","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'pɑrt/","translation":"v. 离开，起程；出发","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'pɑːt/","example":"Flights by Air Europe depart Gatwick on Tuesdays. 欧洲航空公司的航班每逢周二从盖特威克机场起飞。"},{"example":"the personnel department 人事部","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'pɑ:tmənt/","word":"department","translation":"n. 部门","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'pɑrtmənt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'pɑrtʃɚ/","translation":"n. 离开，出发，起程","word":"departure","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'pɑːtʃə/","example":"There are several departures for New York every day. 每天有好几个班次去纽约。"},{"translation":"v. 依靠，依赖；相信","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'pɛnd/","word":"depend","example":"He depended on his writing for his income. 他靠写作谋生。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'pend/"},{"word":"dependent","translation":"adj. 依靠的，依赖的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'pɛndənt/","phonetic_uk":"/di'pendənt/","example":"Jan’s mother was dependent on her for physical care. 简的母亲要靠简来照顾。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'pɒzɪt/","example":"The female deposits her eggs directly into the water. 雌性把卵直接产在水中。","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'pɑzɪt/","translation":"v. 使沉淀；存放","word":"deposit"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'pres/","example":"The thought of taking the exam again depressed him. 想到要补考，他就心情沮丧。","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'prɛs/","translation":"v. 使沮丧；按下","word":"depress"},{"example":"Britain’s depressed housing market 英国不景气的房产市场","phonetic_uk":"/di'prest/","word":"depressed","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'prɛst/","translation":"adj. 沮丧的；萧条的"},{"word":"depressing","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'prɛsɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 令人沮丧的","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'presɪŋ/","example":"It’s a depressing thought. 这是个令人沮丧的想法。"},{"translation":"n.  抑郁， 沮丧； 不景气， 萧条； 洼地， 凹陷","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'prɛʃən/","word":"depression","example":"Mr. Thomas was suffering from depression. 托马斯先生当时正受抑郁症折磨。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'preʃn/"},{"example":"They've been deprived of the fuel necessary to heat their homes. 他们无法得到住房取暖必需的燃料。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'praɪv/","translation":"v. 剥夺，夺去，使丧失","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'praɪv/","word":"deprive"},{"translation":"n. 深度；深厚；深处","phonetic_us":"/dɛpθ/","word":"depth","phonetic_uk":"/depθ/","example":"Astronomers may one day travel to the depths of space. 天文学家也许有一天可以到太空深处去。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'depjuti/","example":"...Jack Lang, France's minister for culture, and his deputy, Catherine Tasca. …法国文化部长杰克·朗和他的副手凯瑟琳·塔斯卡。","word":"deputy","translation":"n.  副职， 副手； 代表， 代理人","phonetic_us":"/'dɛpjuti/"},{"word":"derive","translation":"v. 得到，导出","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'raɪv/","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'raɪv/","example":"Mr. Ying is one of those happy people who derive pleasure from helping others. 英先生是那种助人为乐的快活人。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'send/","example":"Our plane started to descend. 我们的飞机开始下降。","word":"descend","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'sɛnd/","translation":"v. 下来，下降；下倾"},{"example":"The police asked her to describe the man. 警察叫她描述一下那名男子。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'skraɪb/","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'skraɪb/","translation":"v. 形容；描写，描绘","word":"describe"},{"example":"The booklet gives a brief description of each place. 这本小册子对每一个地方都作了简短的介绍。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'skrɪpʃ(ə)n/","word":"description","translation":"n. 描写，形容；种类","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'skrɪpʃən/"},{"word":"desert","phonetic_us":"/(for v.) dɪˈzɝ​t; (for n.) 'dɛzɚt/","translation":"v. 抛弃","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zɜːt/","example":"Helen was deserted by her husband. 海伦被丈夫遗弃了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'zɝv/","translation":"v. 值得","word":"deserve","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zɜːv/","example":"What have I done to deserve this? 我做了什么事，要得到这样的报应？"},{"word":"design","translation":"v. 设计；n. 设计；图样","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'zaɪn/","example":"The tower was designed by Gilbert Scott. 这座塔楼是吉尔伯特·斯科特设计的。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zaɪn/"},{"example":"The ability to speak a foreign language is highly desirable . 能说一门外语是非常理想的。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zaɪərəb(ə)l/","word":"desirable","translation":"adj. 值得相望的；可取的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'zaɪərəbl/"},{"example":"female sexual desire 女性的性欲","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zaɪə(r)/","translation":"n. 渴望，欲望","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'zaɪɚ/","word":"desire"},{"translation":"n. 书桌，办公桌","phonetic_us":"","word":"desk","example":"","phonetic_uk":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'speə/","example":"The noise from the neighbours used to drive him to despair . 过去，邻居的噪音常常吵得他心烦意乱。","translation":"n. 绝望；v. 绝望","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'spɛr/","word":"despair"},{"word":"desperate","translation":"adj. 拼死的；绝望的","phonetic_us":"/'dɛspərət/","phonetic_uk":"/'desp(ə)rət/","example":"I had no money left and was desperate. 我身无分文，已经走投无路了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'spaɪz/","example":"She despised her neighbours. 她看不起她的邻居。","translation":"v. 鄙视，蔑视","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'spaɪz/","word":"despise"},{"example":"Despite all our efforts to save the school, the authorities decided to close it. 尽管我们竭力想保住这所学校，当局还是决定把它关闭。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈspaɪt/","translation":"prep. 不管","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'spaɪt/","word":"despite"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zɜ:t/","example":"She had homemade ice cream for dessert. 她吃了些自制冰淇淋当餐后甜点。","word":"dessert","translation":"n. 甜点","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'zɝt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,destɪ'neɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Ellis Island has become one of America's most popular tourist destinations. 埃利斯岛已经成为美国最受欢迎的游览地之一。","word":"destination","phonetic_us":"/,dɛstɪ'neʃən/","translation":"n. 目的地，终点；目标"},{"translation":"v. 破坏；消灭；打破","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'strɔɪ/","word":"destroy","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'strɒɪ/","example":"companies that are polluting and destroying the environment 污染和破坏环境的公司"},{"word":"destruction","translation":"n. 破坏","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'strʌkʃən/","example":"{\"COLLOINEXA\":[\"weapons of mass destruction\"]} 大规模杀伤性武器","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈstrʌkʃn/"},{"word":"detail","phonetic_us":"/'ditel/","translation":"n. 细节","phonetic_uk":"/'diːteɪl/","example":"This issue will be discussed in more detail in Chapter 5. 这个问题将在第五章里作更为详细的论述。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'di:teild/","example":"a beautifully detailed carving 漂亮精致的雕刻","translation":"adj. 细节的，详细的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'teld/","word":"detailed"},{"example":"Many forms of cancer can be cured if detected early. 如果发现得早，许多种癌症都可以治愈。","phonetic_uk":"/di'tekt/","word":"detect","translation":"v. 觉察;检测","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'tɛkt/"},{"example":"...the early detection of breast cancer. …乳腺癌的早期发现。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'tekʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 侦查；察觉","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'tɛkʃən/","word":"detection"},{"example":"She hired a detective to find out if her husband was having an affair. 她雇了一个私人侦探调查她丈夫是否有外遇。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'tektɪv/","word":"detective","translation":"n. 侦探","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'tɛktɪv/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ,tɜːmɪ'neɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"determination","translation":"n. 意志","phonetic_us":"/dɪˌtɜːrmɪˈneɪʃn/"},{"word":"determine","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'tɝmɪn/","translation":"v. 决定；下决心","example":"The amount of available water determines the number of houses that can be built. 可用的水量决定可以建造多少房子。","phonetic_uk":"/di'tə:min/"},{"translation":"v. 发展；形成；开发","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'vɛləp/","word":"develop","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'veləp/","example":"Knowledge in the field of genetics has been developing very rapidly. 遗传学领域的知识发展非常迅速。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'veləpm(ə)nt/","example":"child development 儿童发育","word":"development","translation":"n. 发展；开发；生长","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'vɛləpmənt/"},{"translation":"adj.  发展的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ,vɛləp'mɛntl/","word":"developmental","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˌveləp'mentl/","example":"the developmental stages of childhood 儿童时期的各个发育阶段"},{"word":"device","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'vaɪs/","translation":"n. 装置，设备","example":"The recording device has activated. 录音装置已开动起来。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈvaɪs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dev(ə)l/","example":"The villagers believed a devil had taken control of his body. 村民们认为他被邪魔附身了。","word":"devil","phonetic_us":"/'dɛvl/","translation":"n. 魔鬼，恶魔"},{"word":"devise","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'vaɪz/","translation":"v. 设计，发明","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'vaɪz/","example":"She devised a method for quicker communications between offices. 她想出一种加快办公室之间通信联络的方法。"},{"translation":"v. 奉献，致力于","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'vot/","word":"devote","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'vəʊt/","example":"He decided to devote the rest of his life to scientific investigation. 他决定把余生奉献给科学研究。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'vəuʃn/","example":"At first she was flattered by his devotion. 最初他的挚爱使她感到受宠若惊。","translation":"n.  献身， 奉献； 忠实； 热爱； 虔诚","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'voʃən/","word":"devotion"},{"translation":"n. 露，露水","phonetic_us":"/du/","word":"dew","example":"The dew gathered on the leaves. 露水在叶片上聚集。","phonetic_uk":"/'djuː/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'daɪəgnəuz/","example":"He could diagnose an engine problem simply by listening. 他仅靠听就能判断发动机出了什么问题。","word":"diagnose","phonetic_us":"/,daɪəɡ'nos/","translation":"vt.  诊断"},{"phonetic_us":"/'daɪəɡræm/","translation":"n. 图解，图表，简图","word":"diagram","phonetic_uk":"/'daɪəgræm/","example":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/'daɪəl/","example":"The lighted dial of her watch said 1.20. 她手表上的夜光表面显示时间为1点20分。","translation":"n. 钟面；拨号盘；v. 拨","phonetic_us":"/'daɪəl/","word":"dial"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'daɪəlekt/","example":"the local dialect 当地方言","translation":"n. 方言，土语，地方话","phonetic_us":"/'daɪə'lɛkt/","word":"dialect"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'daɪəlɒɡ/","example":"In this dialog, you can only open an artifact in the editor. 在这个对话框中，您只可以在编辑器中打开一个工件。","word":"dialog","phonetic_us":"/'daɪə,lɑg/","translation":"n. 对话，对白"},{"example":"...a tube less than a fifth of the diameter of a human hair. …一根直径不到头发五分之一的微管。","phonetic_uk":"/daɪ'æmɪtə/","phonetic_us":"/daɪ'æmɪtɚ/","translation":"n. 直径","word":"diameter"},{"phonetic_us":"/'daɪəmənd/","translation":"n. 金钢石，钻石；菱形","word":"diamond","example":"a diamond engagement ring 订婚钻戒","phonetic_uk":"/'daɪəmənd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'daɪərɪ/","example":"Inge kept a diary (= wrote in a diary ) during the war years. 英奇在战争年代里一直写日记。","translation":"n. 日记，日记簿","phonetic_us":"/'daɪəri/","word":"diary"},{"translation":"v & n. 命令，规定","phonetic_us":"/'dɪktet/","word":"dictate","phonetic_uk":"/dɪkˈteɪt/","example":"Federal funds have to be used as dictated by Washington. 联邦款项得按照华盛顿规定的途径使用。"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪk'teʃən/","translation":"n. 口授笔录，听写","word":"dictation","example":"There were no secretaries available to take dictation (= write down what someone is saying ) . 身边没有秘书记录口授内容。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪk'teɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dɪktetɚ/","translation":"n. 独裁者；专制者","word":"dictator","example":"the downfall of the hated dictator 遭人痛恨的独裁者的垮台","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdɪkˌteɪtə/"},{"word":"dictionary","phonetic_us":"/'dɪkʃə'nɛri/","translation":"n. 词典，字典","example":"a German-English dictionary 一本德英词典","phonetic_uk":"/'dɪkʃ(ə)n(ə)rɪ/"},{"translation":"v. 死，死亡；灭亡","phonetic_us":"/daɪ/","word":"die","phonetic_uk":"/daɪ/","example":"He died in 1985 at the age of 76. 他1985年去世，终年76岁。"},{"word":"differ","phonetic_us":"/'dɪfɚ/","translation":"v. 不同，相异","phonetic_uk":"/'dɪfə/","example":"The two systems differ in many respects. 这两个系统在许多方面不同。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dɪfrəns/","translation":"n. 差别；差；分歧","word":"difference","example":"(= there’s a very big difference ) between us. 我们之间有着天壤之别。","phonetic_uk":"/'dɪf(ə)r(ə)ns/"},{"translation":"adj. 差异的；各种的","phonetic_us":"/'dɪfrənt/","word":"different","phonetic_uk":"/'dɪf(ə)r(ə)nt/","example":"The place looks completely different now. 这地方现在完全变了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɪfɪk(ə)lt/","example":"a difficult question 难解的问题","phonetic_us":"/'dɪfɪkəlt/","translation":"adj. 困难的；难对付的","word":"difficult"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'dɪfɪk(ə)ltɪ/","word":"difficulty","translation":"adj. 困难；难事；困境","phonetic_us":"/'dɪfɪkəlti/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪg/","example":"freshly dug carrots 刚挖出来的胡萝卜","translation":"v. 掘，挖；采掘","phonetic_us":"/dɪɡ/","word":"dig"},{"example":"Most babies can digest a wide range of food easily. 大多数婴儿能轻易地消化很多种食物。","phonetic_uk":"/daɪ'dʒest; dɪ-/","phonetic_us":"/daɪ'dʒɛst/","translation":"v. 消化；领会；n. 文摘","word":"digest"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɪdʒɪt(ə)l/","example":"digital TV 数字电视","word":"digital","translation":"adj. 数字的，计数的","phonetic_us":"/'dɪdʒɪtl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈlemə/","example":"a moral dilemma 道德上进退两难的窘境","word":"dilemma","phonetic_us":"/dɪˈlemə/","translation":"n. 困境"},{"word":"diligent","phonetic_us":"/'dɪlɪdʒənt/","translation":"adj. 勤奋的","example":"a diligent student 勤勉的学生","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdɪlɪdʒənt/"},{"word":"dim","phonetic_us":"/dɪm/","translation":"adj. 昏暗的；朦胧的","phonetic_uk":"/dɪm/","example":"in the dim light of the early dawn 在微弱的晨曦里"},{"word":"dimension","translation":"n. 尺寸，尺度；面积","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'mɛnʃ(ə)n; daɪ-/","example":"a rectangle with the dimensions 5cm × 2cm 长五厘米、宽两厘米的长方形","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'menʃ(ə)n; daɪ-/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɪnə/","example":"What time do you usually have dinner? 你通常什么时候吃饭？","translation":"n. 正餐，主餐；宴会","phonetic_us":"/'dɪnɚ/","word":"dinner"},{"word":"dip","phonetic_us":"/dɪp/","translation":"v. 浸，蘸；v. 浸一浸","phonetic_uk":"/dɪp/","example":"Dip each apple in the syrup until thickly coated. 把每个苹果在糖浆里蘸一下，直到被厚厚地裹上糖浆。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈpləʊmə/","example":"...a new two-year course leading to a diploma in social work. ...一门可以获得社会工作文凭的2年制的新课程。","word":"diploma","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'plomə/","translation":"n. 文凭"},{"example":"Diplomatic efforts to end the fighting began on October 25. 停战的外交努力于10月25日开始。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪplə'mætɪk/","translation":"adj. 外交的","phonetic_us":"/,dɪplə'mætɪk/","word":"diplomatic"},{"word":"direct","phonetic_us":"/dɪˈrɛkt; daɪˈrɛkt/","translation":"adj. 直接的；直率的","phonetic_uk":"/dəˈrekt; daɪˈrekt/","example":"Experienced users have direct access to the main data files. 高级用户可直接浏览主数据文档。"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"","word":"direction","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 方向，方位；指导"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'rektlɪ; daɪ-/","example":"The new property tax law won’t directly affect us. 新的财产税法不会直接影响到我们。","translation":"adv. 直接地；立即","phonetic_us":"/dəˈrektli/","word":"directly"},{"word":"director","translation":"n. 指导者；理事；导演","phonetic_us":"/dɪˈrɛktɚ; daɪˈrɛktɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'rektə; daɪ-/","example":"The company is run by a board of directors (= a group of directors ) . 这家公司由董事会管理。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɜːt/","example":"You should have seen the dirt on that car! 你没看见那车上沾了多少泥！","word":"dirt","translation":"n. 尘，土；污物，污垢","phonetic_us":"/dɝt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈdɝ​tɪ/","translation":"adj. 脏的；下流的","word":"dirty","example":"a stack of dirty dishes in the sink 洗涤槽里的一堆脏碟子","phonetic_uk":"/'dɜːtɪ/"},{"translation":"v. 使无能，使伤残","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'ebl/","word":"disable","phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'eɪb(ə)l/","example":"Carter was permanently disabled in the war. 卡特在那场战争中成了终生残废。"},{"example":"Criminal behaviour can be linked to economic disadvantage. 犯罪行为可能会与经济困难有关。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪsəd'vɑːntɪdʒ/","phonetic_us":"/,dɪsəd'væntɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 不利情况，缺点","word":"disadvantage"},{"example":"Barr strongly disagreed with Kronfeld’s statement. 巴尔强烈反对克龙费尔德的说法。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪsə'griː/","word":"disagree","phonetic_us":"/,dɪsə'ɡri/","translation":"v. 有分歧；不一致"},{"example":"At this point the path seemed to disappear altogether (= disappear completely ) . 小路到这里好像完全消失了。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌdɪsə'pɪə(r)/","word":"disappear","translation":"v. 不见，消失","phonetic_us":"/'dɪsə'pɪr/"},{"example":"I hated to disappoint her. 我不愿意让她失望。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪsə'pɒɪnt/","translation":"v. 使失望，使受挫折","phonetic_us":"/'dɪsə'pɔɪnt/","word":"disappoint"},{"translation":"adj. 令人失望的","phonetic_us":"/,dɪsə'pɔɪntɪŋ/","word":"disappointing","phonetic_uk":"/dɪsə'pɒɪntɪŋ/","example":"disappointing profit figures 令人失望的盈利数字"},{"example":"One hundred and twenty people died in China’s worst air disaster . 有120人在中国这起最惨烈的空难事故中丧生。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zɑːstə/","word":"disaster","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'zæstɚ/","translation":"n. 灾难，灾祸；天灾"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'skɑːd/","example":"Read the manufacturer's guidelines before discarding the box. 先阅读制造商的说明书再把盒子丢掉。","word":"discard","phonetic_us":"/dɪsˈkɑːrd/","translation":"v. 丢弃，抛弃，遗弃"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dis'tʃɑ:dʒ/","example":"Hospitals now tend to discharge patients earlier than in the past. 与过去相比，现在医院更趋向于让病人早些出院。","word":"discharge","translation":"v. 释放；排出 解雇","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'tʃɑrdʒ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɪsɪplɪn/","example":"The book gives parents advice on discipline. 这本书指导父母如何管教孩子。","translation":"n. 纪律；训练；v. 训练","phonetic_us":"/'dɪsəplɪn/","word":"discipline"},{"example":"Some companies have already voluntarily disclosed similar information . 一些公司已经主动透露了类似的信息。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'kləʊz/","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'kloz/","translation":"v. 揭开，揭发；透露","word":"disclose"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪs'kaʊnt/","translation":"n. 折扣","word":"discount","phonetic_uk":"/'diskaunt/","example":"They are often available at a discount. 它们经常可以以折扣价买到。"},{"example":"It may be difficult to do at first. Don't let this discourage you. 开始时做起来也许比较困难。不要让这个泄你的气。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'kʌrɪdʒ/","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'kɝɪdʒ/","translation":"v. 使气馁, 阻碍","word":"discourage"},{"word":"discover","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'skʌvɚ/","translation":"v. 发现","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'skʌvə/","example":"The body was discovered in a field. 尸体是在一块田地里找到的。"},{"example":"I felt I'd made an incredible discovery. 我感到自己有了一个惊人的发现。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'skʌv(ə)rɪ/","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'skʌvəri/","translation":"n. 发现；被发现的事物","word":"discovery"},{"word":"discrimination","translation":"n. 歧视","phonetic_us":"/dɪ,skrɪmɪ'neʃən/","example":"laws to prevent discrimination 防止歧视的法律","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ,skrɪmɪ'neɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"translation":"v. 讨论，谈论；论述","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'skʌs/","word":"discuss","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'skʌs/","example":"Littman refused to discuss the case publicly. 利特曼拒绝公开讨论此案。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'skʌʃ(ə)n/","example":"class discussions 课堂讨论","word":"discussion","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'skʌʃən/","translation":"n. 讨论，谈论；论述"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'ziːz/","example":"His father died of heart disease. 他父亲死于心脏病。","translation":"n. 病，疾病；病害","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'ziz/","word":"disease"},{"translation":"v. 隐瞒，掩埋；n. 假装","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'ɡaɪz/","word":"disguise","phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'gaɪz/","example":"He made no attempt to disguise his agitation. 他无意掩饰他的不安。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'gʌst/","example":"He reached into the bin with a look of disgust on his face. 他把手伸进垃圾箱，脸上带着厌恶的表情。","translation":"n. 厌恶，憎恶","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'ɡʌst/","word":"disgust"},{"example":"a serving dish 上菜用的盘子","phonetic_uk":"/dɪʃ/","translation":"n. 碟，盘子；菜肴","phonetic_us":"/dɪʃ/","word":"dish"},{"word":"dishonest","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'ɑnɪst/","translation":"adj. 不诚实的","phonetic_uk":"/dɪsˈɒnɪst/","example":"dishonest traders 奸商"},{"word":"dishonour","translation":"n. 不光彩；丢脸的人","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'ɑnɚ/","phonetic_uk":"","example":"I dare not quit my post, though an unfaithful sentinel, whose sure reward is death and dishonour, when his dreary watch shall come to an end! 虽说我是个不忠于职守的哨兵，等到这种沉网的守望终了的时候，我所能得到的报酬只能是不光彩的死亡，但我仍不敢擅离岗位！"},{"translation":"n. 洗碗机","phonetic_us":"/'dɪʃwɔʃɚ/","word":"dishwasher","example":"I was a short-order cook and a dishwasher. 我曾是一名快餐厨师兼洗碗工。","phonetic_uk":"/'dɪʃwɒʃə/"},{"translation":"n. 圆盘，唱片；磁盘","phonetic_us":"/dɪsk/","word":"disk","phonetic_uk":"/dɪsk/","example":"The program takes up 2.5 megabytes of disk space and can be run on a standard personal computer. 这个程序占用2.5 兆字节的磁盘空间，可以在标准个人电脑上运行。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'laɪk/","example":"Why do you dislike her so much? 你为什么那么讨厌她？","translation":"vt&n. 不喜爱，厌恶","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'laɪk/","word":"dislike"},{"word":"dismiss","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'mɪs/","translation":"v. 不再考虑；解雇","example":"The government has dismissed criticisms that the country’s health policy is a mess. 有人认为国家医疗政策一塌糊涂，政府对这种批评持否认态度。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'mɪs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"severe eating disorders such as bulimia and anorexia 像贪食症和厌食症这类严重的进食障碍","word":"disorder","translation":"n. 混乱，杂乱；骚乱","phonetic_us":""},{"word":"disorderly","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'ɔrdɚli/","translation":"adj. 杂乱的","example":"clothes left in a disorderly heap 乱七八糟堆在一起的衣服","phonetic_uk":"/dɪsˈɔ:dəli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈspleɪ/","example":"a dazzling display (= very good display ) of flowers 令人目眩神迷的花卉展","word":"display","translation":"n & v. 展览","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'sple/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪs'pliːz/","example":"If there are aspects of your life that displease you make you feel regret, this is an opportunity to change direction. 如果你生活中那些使你不愉快的方面让你觉得懊悔，那么这正是你改变方向的时机。","translation":"v. 使不愉快，使生气","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'pliz/","word":"displease"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'spəʊz(ə)l/","example":"bomb disposal experts 拆弹专家","translation":"n. 丢掉，处理，销毁","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'spozl/","word":"disposal"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'spəʊz/","example":"","translation":"v. 去掉，丢掉；销毁","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'spoz/","word":"dispose"},{"example":"It is beyond dispute that advances in medicine have enabled people to live longer. 医学的发展使人们更加长寿，这是无可置疑的。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'spju:t/","word":"dispute","translation":"n & v. 辩论，争论","phonetic_us":"/'dɪs'pjʊt/"},{"word":"dissatisfy","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'sætɪs,fai/","translation":"v. 不满意","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ(s)'sætɪsfaɪ/","example":"More or other, they still dissatisfy. 更多或另外一些，它们仍然不满足。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪsˈsɜ:vɪs/","example":"He said the protesters were doing a disservice to the nation. 他表示，抗议者们的行为正对国家造成危害。","word":"disservice","translation":"n. 伤害，帮倒忙","phonetic_us":"/dɪs'sɝvɪs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'zɒlv/","example":"Stir until the sugar dissolves. 一直搅拌到糖溶解掉。","translation":"v. 使溶解；解散","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'zɑlv/","word":"dissolve"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɪstəns/","example":"Measure the distance between the two points. 量出两点之间的距离。","phonetic_us":"/'dɪstəns/","translation":"n. 距离","word":"distance"},{"translation":"adj. 遥远的","phonetic_us":"/'dɪstənt/","word":"distant","phonetic_uk":"/'dɪst(ə)nt/","example":"the sound of distant gunfire 远处的炮火声"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'stɪŋ(k)t/","example":"two entirely distinct languages 两种完全不同的语言","translation":"adj. 明显的；有区别的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'stɪŋkt/","word":"distinct"},{"example":"Eliot’s distinction as a poet 艾略特作为诗人的杰出才能","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'stɪŋ(k)ʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 差别，不同，区分","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'stɪŋkʃən/","word":"distinction"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'stɪŋktɪv/","translation":"adj. 独特的，与众不同的","word":"distinctive","example":"a rock band with a distinctive sound 音色独特的摇滚乐队","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈstɪŋktɪv/"},{"word":"distinguish","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'stɪŋɡwɪʃ/","translation":"v. 区别，区分","phonetic_uk":"/di'stiŋgwiʃ/","example":"Could he distinguish right from wrong? 他能辨别是非吗？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈstɪŋgwɪʃt/","example":"a long and distinguished career 漫长而卓越的职业生涯","word":"distinguished","translation":"adj. 显著的，杰出的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'stɪŋgwɪʃt/"},{"example":"Try not to distract the other students. 尽量不要让其他学生分心。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'strækt/","translation":"v. 分心","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'strækt/","word":"distract"},{"translation":"adj. 分心的","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'stræktɪd/","word":"distracted","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈstræktɪd/","example":"She had seemed curiously distracted. 她不知为什么显得心不在焉。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈstrækʃn/","example":"I study in the library as there are too many distractions at home. 我在图书馆学习，家里分心的事太多。","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'strækʃən/","translation":"n. 消遣；分心","word":"distraction"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'strɛs/","translation":"v. 使痛苦，悲痛","word":"distress","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'stres/","example":"The dream had distressed her greatly. 这场梦使她深感不安。"},{"word":"distribute","translation":"v. 分发","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'strɪbjut/","example":"a man distributing leaflets to passers-by 一个向路人派发传单的男子","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'strɪbjuːt/"},{"example":"a distribution centre 经销中心","phonetic_uk":"/dɪstrɪ'bjuːʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'dɪstrə'bjʊʃən/","translation":"n. 分发，分配；分布","word":"distribution"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɪstrɪkt/","example":"a postal district 邮政区","translation":"n. 区","phonetic_us":"/'dɪstrɪkt/","word":"district"},{"phonetic_us":"/dɪ'stɝb/","translation":"v. 打扰，扰乱；弄乱","word":"disturb","example":"Sorry to disturb you, but I have an urgent message. 对不起打扰一下，我有个紧急消息。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'stɜːb/"},{"word":"ditch","translation":"n. 沟，沟渠，渠道","phonetic_us":"/dɪtʃ/","example":"Both vehicles ended up in a ditch. 两辆车都掉进了沟里。","phonetic_uk":"/dɪtʃ/"},{"word":"dive","translation":"v. 跳水；潜水；俯冲","phonetic_us":"/daɪv/","phonetic_uk":"/daɪv/","example":"Diving off the cliffs is dangerous. 从悬崖上跳水是很危险的。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/daɪ'vɜːs/","example":"subjects as diverse as pop music and archaeology 像流行音乐和考古学这样各不相同的学科","phonetic_us":"/daɪ'vɝs/","translation":"adj. 各种各样的","word":"diverse"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dai'və:səti/","example":"...the cultural diversity of Latin America. …拉丁美洲文化的多样性。","translation":"n. 多样性；差异","phonetic_us":"/dɪˈvəsɪti/","word":"diversity"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'vaɪd/","example":"The Wall used to divide East and West Berlin. 过去这堵墙把东、西柏林隔开。","translation":"v. 分开","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'vaɪd/","word":"divide"},{"word":"divine","phonetic_us":"/dɪ'vaɪn/","translation":"adj. 神圣的","example":"divine power 神的力量","phonetic_uk":"/dɪˈvaɪn/"},{"word":"division","phonetic_us":"/də'vɪʒən/","translation":"n. 除法；部门","example":"the Computer Services Division 电脑维修部","phonetic_uk":"/dɪ'vɪʒ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"Why doesn’t she get a divorce ? 她为什么不离婚呢？","translation":"n. 离婚，离异；vi. 离婚","phonetic_us":"","word":"divorce"},{"translation":"aux. v；v. 做，干，办","phonetic_us":"/du/","word":"do","phonetic_uk":"/duː/","example":"‘Will Kay come?’ ‘She may do.’ “凯来吗？” “或许吧。”"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dɒk/","example":"A crowd was waiting at the dock to greet them. 一群人在码头等着迎接他们。","word":"dock","translation":"n. 船坞；码头；船厂","phonetic_us":"/dɑk/"},{"word":"doctor","phonetic_us":"/'dɑktɚ/","translation":"n. 医生，医师；博士","example":"She was treated by her local doctor. 她由她的本区医生治疗。","phonetic_uk":"/'dɒktə/"},{"example":"a doctoral thesis 博士论文","phonetic_uk":"/'dɒktərəl/","word":"doctoral","translation":"adj.  博士的","phonetic_us":"/'dɔktərəl/"},{"word":"document","translation":"n. 文件","phonetic_us":"/dɑkjəmənt/","example":"She produces legal documents for a downtown Seattle law firm. 她为西雅图市区的一家法律事务所撰写法律文件。","phonetic_uk":"/'dɒkjʊmənt/"},{"word":"dog","phonetic_us":"/dɔɡ/","translation":"n. 狗，犬，犬科动物","phonetic_uk":"/dɒg/","example":"I could hear a dog barking . 我听到了狗吠声。"},{"example":"It cost three dollars. 它要三美元。","phonetic_uk":"/'dɒlə/","word":"dollar","phonetic_us":"/'dɑlɚ/","translation":"n. 元(货币单位)"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dəˈmestɪk/","example":"...over 100 domestic flights a day to 30 leading U.S. destinations. …每天飞往美国30个主要目的地的100多个国内航班。","word":"domestic","phonetic_us":"/də'mɛstɪk/","translation":"adj. 国内的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈdɒmɪnənt/","example":"The dominant male gorilla is the largest in the group. 领头的公猩猩是这群大猩猩中体形最大的一个。","translation":"adj. 占优势的","phonetic_us":"/'dɑmɪnənt/","word":"dominant"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dɒmɪneɪt/","example":"The industry is dominated by five multinational companies. 这个行业受五家跨国公司控制。","phonetic_us":"/'dɑmɪnet/","translation":"vi.  拥有优势；vt. 在…中占首要地位；支配，统治，控制；耸立于，俯视","word":"dominate"},{"example":"The imperialists use this ideology and culture as a lever for easily realizing their domination and subjugation, aggression and plunder of other countries.  帝国主义者使用这种思想和文化作为一种杠杆，轻易地实现其统治、征服、侵略以及掠夺他国的目的。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌdɒmɪ'neɪʃn/","phonetic_us":"/,dɑmə'neʃən/","translation":"n. 主导","word":"domination"},{"example":"people who volunteer to donate blood 自愿献血者","phonetic_uk":"/də(ʊ)'neɪt/","phonetic_us":"/'donet/","translation":"v. 捐赠","word":"donate"},{"word":"donation","phonetic_us":"/do'neʃən/","translation":"n. 捐赠","example":"There have been generous donations from EU funds. 欧盟基金给予了慷慨的捐款。","phonetic_uk":"/dəu'neiʃən/"},{"word":"donkey","phonetic_us":"/'dɔŋki/","translation":"n. 驴；笨蛋","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'dɒŋkɪ/"},{"example":"Could you open the door for me? 请你帮我开门好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/dɔː/","translation":"n. 门，通道；一家","phonetic_us":"/dɔr/","word":"door"},{"word":"dorm","translation":"n. 宿舍","phonetic_us":"/dɔrm/","example":"But I had no food in my dorm, so I had to go to canteen. 但是我在宿舍没有东西可吃，所以我只能去餐厅了。","phonetic_uk":"/dɔːm/"},{"example":"She lived in a college dormitory. 她住在一幢大学宿舍楼里。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdɔːmətri/","phonetic_us":"/'dɔrmətɔri/","translation":"n. 宿舍","word":"dormitory"},{"word":"dose","phonetic_us":"/dos/","translation":"n. 剂量，用量；一剂","phonetic_uk":"/dəʊs/","example":"I quite like Jamie in small doses (= in limited amounts but not a lot or often ) . 如果偶尔在一起的话，我还是蛮喜欢杰米的。"},{"example":"a pattern of dots 圆点图案","phonetic_uk":"/dɒt/","phonetic_us":"/dɑt/","translation":"n. 点，圆点；v. 打点于","word":"dot"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dʌb(ə)l/","example":"a double sink 双水槽","word":"double","phonetic_us":"/'dʌbl/","translation":"adj. 两倍的；双的"},{"translation":"n. 怀疑；疑虑；v. 怀疑","phonetic_us":"/daʊt/","word":"doubt","example":"There was still one little nagging doubt at the back of his mind. 他的心头仍有一丝挥之不去的疑虑。","phonetic_uk":"/daʊt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'daʊtfʊl; -f(ə)l/","example":"‘Everything’s going to be all right, you’ll see.’ Jenny looked doubtful . “一切都会顺顺当当的，你等着看好了。” 珍妮看起来不大相信的样子。","phonetic_us":"/'daʊtfəl/","translation":"adj. 难以预测的；怀疑的","word":"doubtful"},{"word":"doubtless","phonetic_us":"/'daʊtləs/","translation":"adv. 无疑地；很可能","example":"Doubtless there would be lots of rumours. 无疑会谣言四起。","phonetic_uk":"/'daʊtlɪs/"},{"example":"David bent down to tie his shoelace. 戴维弯腰系鞋带。","phonetic_uk":"/daʊn/","phonetic_us":"/daʊn/","translation":"adv. 向下，在下面","word":"down"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'daʊnfɔ:l/","translation":"n. （雨等的）大下特下","phonetic_us":"/'daʊnfɔl/","word":"downfall"},{"word":"download","translation":"v. 下载","phonetic_us":"/,daʊn'lod/","example":"games that can be downloaded free from the Internet 可以从因特网上免费下载的游戏","phonetic_uk":"/'daʊnləʊd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'daʊnsaɪz/","translation":"v. 裁员","word":"downsize","example":"The airline has downsized its workforce by 30%. 这家航空公司裁员30%。","phonetic_uk":"/'daʊnsaɪz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/daʊn'steəz/","example":"Rosie ran downstairs to answer the door. 罗茜跑下楼去开门。","word":"downstairs","translation":"adv. 在楼下；adj. 楼下的","phonetic_us":"/'daʊn'stɛrz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'daʊnwəd/","example":"a gentle downward slope 缓坡","translation":"adj. 向下的；adv. 向下地","phonetic_us":"/'daʊnwɚd/","word":"downward"},{"word":"dozen","translation":"n. 一打，十二个","phonetic_us":"/'dʌzn/","example":"a dozen eggs 一打鸡蛋","phonetic_uk":"/'dʌz(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/drɑːft/","example":"the rough draft of his new novel 他的新小说的草稿","phonetic_us":"/dræft/","translation":"n. 草稿；汇票；v. 起草","word":"draft"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dræg/","example":"He grabbed her arm and dragged her into the room. 他抓住她的手臂把她拖进房间。","word":"drag","phonetic_us":"/dræg/","translation":"v. 拖，拉；拖曳"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dræg(ə)n/","example":"","word":"dragon","translation":"n. 龙；凶暴的人","phonetic_us":"/'dræɡən/"},{"word":"drain","phonetic_us":"/dren/","translation":"v. 排去；放水；n. 耗竭","example":"He flushed the drain. 他用水冲排水沟。","phonetic_uk":"/dreɪn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"the great traditions of ancient Greek drama 古希腊戏剧的伟大传统","word":"drama","translation":"n. 一出戏剧，剧本","phonetic_us":""},{"example":"the amateur dramatic society 业余剧团","phonetic_uk":"/drə'mætɪk/","word":"dramatic","translation":"adj. 引人注目的，戏剧的","phonetic_us":"/drə'mætɪk/"},{"word":"dramatically","phonetic_us":"/drə'mætɪkli/","translation":"adv. 戏剧性地，引人注目地","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/drə'mætɪklɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/drɑːft/","example":"Can you close the window? I’m in a draught . 你把窗户关上好吗？我正对着风口。","word":"draught","translation":"n. 穿堂风，冷风；adj. 〔啤酒〕桶装的，散装的","phonetic_us":"/drɑft/"},{"example":"Katie had drawn a cottage with a little stream running next to it. 凯蒂画了一间小茅舍，旁边流淌着一条小溪。","phonetic_uk":"/drɔː/","translation":"v. 画，划；拖；拨出","phonetic_us":"/drɔ/","word":"draw"},{"phonetic_uk":"/drɔ:(r)/","example":"She took a file from her desk drawer . 她从书桌的抽屉里拿出了一个文件夹。","word":"drawer","translation":"n. 抽屉","phonetic_us":"/drɔr/"},{"example":"I’ve never been very good at drawing. 我向来不擅长画图。","phonetic_uk":"/'drɔː(r)ɪŋ/","word":"drawing","phonetic_us":"/'drɔɪŋ/","translation":"n. 图画，素描；绘图"},{"phonetic_us":"/drɛd/","translation":"n. 畏惧；恐怖；v. 惧怕","word":"dread","example":"The prospect of flying filled me with dread . 想到要乘飞机我充满了恐惧。","phonetic_uk":"/dred/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/driːm/","example":"I had lots of dreams last night. 昨晚我做了很多梦。","word":"dream","translation":"n. 梦；梦想；v. 做梦","phonetic_us":"/drim/"},{"phonetic_us":"/drɛs/","translation":"n. 女服，童装；服装","word":"dress","phonetic_uk":"/dres/","example":"a gentleman in evening dress 穿晚礼服的绅士"},{"example":"Smoke drifted up from the jungle ahead of us. 我们前方的丛林里有烟升起。","phonetic_uk":"/drɪft/","translation":"v. 漂流，漂泊；n. 漂流","phonetic_us":"/drɪft/","word":"drift"},{"word":"drill","translation":"n. 钻头；操练；v. 钻孔","phonetic_us":"/drɪl/","phonetic_uk":"/drɪl/","example":"rifle drill 步枪操练"},{"phonetic_us":"/drɪŋk/","translation":"v. 饮；v. 喝；n. 饮料","word":"drink","phonetic_uk":"/drɪŋk/","example":"You should drink plenty of water. 你应该大量喝水。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/drɪp/","example":"The tap’s dripping . 水龙头在滴水。","word":"drip","translation":"v. 滴下；漏水；n. 水滴","phonetic_us":"/drɪp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/draɪv/","example":"Torrential rain drove the players off the course. 滂沱大雨迫使选手们离开了赛场。","translation":"v. 驾驶；打入；驱","phonetic_us":"/draɪv/","word":"drive"},{"phonetic_us":"/'draɪvɚ/","translation":"n. 驾驶员，司机","word":"driver","phonetic_uk":"/'draɪvə/","example":"a taxi driver 出租车司机"},{"phonetic_us":"/drɑp/","translation":"v. 使落下；降低","word":"drop","example":"Your button has dropped off. 你的纽扣掉了。","phonetic_uk":"/drɒp/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'drɑpaʊt/","translation":"n. 辍学","word":"dropout","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdrɒpaʊt/","example":"a high school dropout 中学退学者"},{"translation":"n. 旱灾，干旱","phonetic_us":"/draʊt/","word":"drought","phonetic_uk":"/draʊt/","example":"...a country where drought and famines have killed up to two million people during the last eighteen years. …过去18年来干旱和饥荒致死达两百万人的一个国家。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/draʊn/","example":"Many people drowned when the boat overturned. 船翻后许多人淹死了。","word":"drown","translation":"v. 淹死，溺死","phonetic_us":"/draʊn/"},{"translation":"n. 药，药物，药材","phonetic_us":"/drʌg/","word":"drug","example":"a drug used in the treatment of cancer 用于治疗癌症的一种药物","phonetic_uk":"/drʌg/"},{"word":"drum","phonetic_us":"/drʌm/","translation":"n. 鼓；鼓状物，圆桶","example":"a big bass drum 一面低音大鼓","phonetic_uk":"/drʌm/"},{"example":"You’re drunk. 你喝醉了。","phonetic_uk":"/drʌŋk/","word":"drunk","phonetic_us":"/drʌŋk/","translation":"adj. 醉的；陶醉的"},{"example":"I need to change into some dry clothes . 我要换上干衣服。","phonetic_uk":"/draɪ/","translation":"adj. 干的，干燥的","phonetic_us":"/draɪ/","word":"dry"},{"word":"duck","translation":"n. 鸭，雌鸭；鸭肉","phonetic_us":"/dʌk/","phonetic_uk":"/dʌk/","example":"roast duck with orange sauce 烤鸭配橘子酱"},{"translation":"adj. 到期的","phonetic_us":"/du/","word":"due","phonetic_uk":"/dju:/","example":"The next income tax payment is due on 31 January. 下一次的所得税支付期限是1月31日。"},{"word":"dull","translation":"adj. 枯燥的；不鲜明的","phonetic_us":"/dʌl/","example":"Life is never dull when Elizabeth is here. 有伊丽莎白在这里生活绝不会无聊。","phonetic_uk":"/dʌl/"},{"word":"dumb","translation":"adj. 哑的；无言的","phonetic_us":"/dʌm/","phonetic_uk":"/dʌm/","example":"...a young deaf and dumb man. …一名年轻的聋哑人。"},{"word":"dump","phonetic_us":"/dʌmp/","translation":"v. 倾倒；倾销","example":"We dumped our bags at the nearby Grand Hotel and hurried toward the market. 我们把包扔在附近的格兰德旅馆，急匆匆地向市场赶去。","phonetic_uk":"/dʌmp/"},{"example":"A: Why do we have to do durability test? 我们为什么要做耐久性测试?","phonetic_uk":"/ˌdjʊərə'bɪlətɪ/","translation":"n. 持久","phonetic_us":"","word":"durability"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dʊrəbl/","translation":"adj. 持久的，耐用的","word":"durable","phonetic_uk":"/'djʊərəb(ə)l/","example":"Wood is a durable material. 木头是耐用材料。"},{"phonetic_us":"/du'reʃən/","translation":"n. 持续，持久","word":"duration","phonetic_uk":"/djʊ'reɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"The course is of three years’ duration. 该课程为期三年。"},{"example":"During the summer she worked as a lifeguard. 夏天她当过救生员。","phonetic_uk":"/'djʊərɪŋ/","word":"during","translation":"prep. 在…期间","phonetic_us":"/'dʊrɪŋ/"},{"translation":"n. 薄暮，黄昏，幽暗","phonetic_us":"/dʌsk/","word":"dusk","example":"The street lights go on at dusk. 街灯在黄昏时亮起来。","phonetic_uk":"/dʌsk/"},{"example":"All the furniture was covered in dust . 所有的家具都蒙上了灰尘。","phonetic_uk":"/dʌst/","phonetic_us":"/dʌst/","translation":"n. 灰尘","word":"dust"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'djuːtɪ/","example":"I promise I will do my duty . 我保证会尽到我的责任。","translation":"n. 职责；责任；税","phonetic_us":"/'dʊti/","word":"duty"},{"translation":"n. 住处，寓所","phonetic_us":"/'dwɛlɪŋ/","word":"dwelling","phonetic_uk":"/'dwelɪŋ/","example":"Some 3,500 new dwellings are planned for the area. 大约三千五百套新住宅计划在这个地区新建。"},{"word":"dye","translation":"v. 染；n. 染料；染色","phonetic_us":"/daɪ/","phonetic_uk":"/daɪ/","example":"The women prepared, spun, and dyed the wool. 妇女们将羊毛预备、纺线并染色。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'daɪɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 垂死的；临终的","word":"dying","phonetic_uk":"/'daɪɪŋ/","example":"It was her dying wish to have a simple burial. 她的临终遗愿是办个简朴的葬礼。"},{"phonetic_us":"/daɪ'næmɪk/","translation":"adj. 有活力的；动力的","word":"dynamic","example":"dynamic and ambitious people 精力充沛且雄心勃勃的人","phonetic_uk":"/daɪ'næmɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/iːtʃ/","example":"They reviewed each aspect of the plan bit by bit. 他们对计划的各个方面逐一地进行了审核。","word":"each","phonetic_us":"/itʃ/","translation":"pron. 各，各自；adj. 各"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'iːgə/","example":"He’s a bright kid and eager to learn. 他是个聪明的孩子，热爱学习。","word":"eager","translation":"adj. 渴望的，热切的","phonetic_us":"/'igɚ/"},{"word":"eagle","translation":"n. 鹰","phonetic_us":"/'igl/","example":"The eagle drooped its wings. 那只鹰收拢双翅做俯冲。","phonetic_uk":"/'iːg(ə)l/"},{"example":"She tucked her hair behind her ears. 她把头发拢到耳朵背后。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪə/","word":"ear","translation":"n. 耳朵；听力，听觉","phonetic_us":"/ɪr/"},{"example":"We arrived early. 我们提早到了。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɜːlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'ɝli/","translation":"adv. 早；adj. 早的，早期的","word":"early"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɝn/","translation":"v. 赚得，挣得；获得","word":"earn","phonetic_uk":"/ɜːn/","example":"He earns nearly £20,000 a year. 他每年挣近20,000英镑。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɜːnɪst/","example":"a rather earnest young man 相当认真的一个年轻人","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 认真的，诚恳的","word":"earnest"},{"word":"earth","phonetic_us":"/ɝθ/","translation":"n. 地球；陆地，地面","example":"the planet Earth 地球","phonetic_uk":"/ɜːθ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɜːθkweɪk/","example":"An earthquake measuring 6.1 on the Richter scale struck southern California on June 28. 6月28日加州南部地区发生了里氏6.1级地震。","phonetic_us":"/'ɝθ'kwek/","translation":"n. 地震；大震荡","word":"earthquake"},{"phonetic_us":"/iz/","translation":"n. 轻松，舒适","word":"ease","phonetic_uk":"/i:z/","example":"She lived a life of ease. 她过着悠闲自在的生活。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'izəli/","translation":"adv. 容易地；舒适的","word":"easily","example":"They won quite easily. 他们赢得相当轻松。","phonetic_uk":"/'iːzɪlɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/iːst/","example":"Which way is east? 哪边是东？","phonetic_us":"/ist/","translation":"n. 东；东部；adv. 在东方","word":"east"},{"example":"the eastern shore of the island 岛的东岸","phonetic_uk":"/'iːst(ə)n/","word":"eastern","phonetic_us":"/'istɚn/","translation":"adj. 东方的；朝东的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'iːzɪ/","example":"The test was easy. 考试很容易。","word":"easy","translation":"adj. 容易的；安逸的","phonetic_us":"/'izi/"},{"translation":"adj. 脾气随和的，温和的","phonetic_us":"/'izɪ,goɪŋ/","word":"easygoing","phonetic_uk":"/'i:zɪˌgəʊɪŋ/","example":"They thought she would be popular, warm and easygoing, but not demanding and difficult. 他们认为她会是受人欢迎的，温情的，随和的，而非挑三拣四难以追求的。"},{"example":"Felix chatted cheerfully as he ate. 费利克斯一边吃一边兴奋地聊天。","phonetic_uk":"/iːt/","word":"eat","phonetic_us":"/it/","translation":"v. 吃，喝；v. 吃饭"},{"translation":"n. 回声，反响；v. 重复","phonetic_us":"/'ɛko/","word":"echo","example":"Her scream was followed by a loud echo. 她的尖叫声过后是响亮的回声。","phonetic_uk":"/'ekəʊ/"},{"example":"Economic growth is slow. 经济增长缓慢。","phonetic_uk":"/,iːkə'nɒmɪk; ek-/","word":"economic","translation":"adj. 经济的，经济学的","phonetic_us":"/ˌikəˈnɑmɪk, ˌɛkəˈ-nɑmɪk/"},{"example":"A small car is more economical to run. 开小型汽车比较省油。","phonetic_uk":"/iːkə'nɒmɪk(ə)l; ek-/","translation":"adj. 节约的；经济学的","phonetic_us":"/,ɛkə'nɑmɪkl/","word":"economical"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'kɒnəmɪ/","example":"a successful economy 发展成功的经济","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'kɑnəmi/","translation":"n. 经济；节约，节省","word":"economy"},{"translation":"n. 边缘，边；刀口","phonetic_us":"/ɛdʒ/","word":"edge","example":"Put the eggs in the centre of the dish, with the vegetables and herbs around the edge. 把鸡蛋放在盘子中间，盘边一圈放些蔬菜和香草。","phonetic_uk":"/edʒ/"},{"translation":"n. 版，版本，版次","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'dɪʃən/","word":"edition","example":"a paperback edition 平装本","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'dɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɛdɪtɚ/","translation":"n. 编辑，编者，校订者","word":"editor","phonetic_uk":"/'edɪtə/","example":"the editor of a book of essays on modern poetry 现代诗歌论文集的编者"},{"word":"editorial","phonetic_us":"/,ɛdɪ'tɔrɪəl/","translation":"adj. 编辑的，主笔的，编者的；社论的，社论式的；n.  社论， 重要评论","phonetic_uk":"/ˌedɪ'tɔːriəl/","example":"an editorial assistant 编辑助理"},{"example":"The Ormerod School educates handicapped children. 奥默罗德学校的教育对象为残疾儿童。","phonetic_uk":"/'edjʊkeɪt/","word":"educate","phonetic_us":"/'ɛdʒuket/","translation":"v. 教育；培养；训练"},{"example":"She also hopes her children will get a good education. 她也希望她的孩子可以受到良好的教育。","phonetic_uk":"/edjʊ'keɪʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 教育；训导；教育学","phonetic_us":"/,ɛdʒu'keʃən/","word":"education"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'fekt/","example":"the long-term effects of the drug 这种毒品的长期影响","word":"effect","translation":"n. 影响","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'fɛkt/"},{"example":"The cheaper drugs are just as effective in treating arthritis. 较便宜的药品对治疗关节炎同样有效。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'fektɪv/","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'fɛktɪv/","translation":"adj. 有效的；有影响的","word":"effective"},{"word":"efficiency","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'fɪʃənsi/","translation":"n. 效率；功效，效能","example":"considerable advancements in energy efficiency 能源效率的显著提高","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'fɪʃ(ə)nsɪ/"},{"word":"efficient","translation":"adj. 效率高的，有能力的","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'fɪʃnt/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'fɪʃ(ə)nt/","example":"a very efficient secretary 效率高的秘书"},{"example":"This oil lubricates efficiently. 这油能有效地起润滑作用。","phonetic_uk":"/i'fiʃəntli/","translation":"adj. 有效地","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'fɪʃəntli/","word":"efficiently"},{"translation":"n. 努力；努力的成果","phonetic_us":"/'ɛfɚt/","word":"effort","phonetic_uk":"/'efət/","example":"Lou lifted the box easily, without using much effort. 卢没费多大力气就把箱子搬了起来。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɛɡ/","translation":"n. 蛋，鸡蛋，卵","word":"egg","phonetic_uk":"/eg/","example":"Blackbirds lay their eggs in March. 乌鸫在3月产蛋。"},{"word":"eight","translation":"num. 八，八个，第八","phonetic_us":"/et/","example":"It’s only eight days till Christmas. 还有8天就到圣诞节了。","phonetic_uk":"/eɪt/"},{"word":"eighteen","translation":"num. 十八，十八个","phonetic_us":"/,e'tin/","example":"At least eighteen bullets were fired. 至少射出了18颗子弹。","phonetic_uk":"/eɪ'tiːn; 'eɪtiːn/"},{"word":"eighth","phonetic_us":"/etθ/","translation":"num. 第八；n. 八分之一","example":"Until then, students could leave after the eighth grade, and a lot of them did. 那时，学生上完八年级就可以辍学，许多学生的确这样做了。","phonetic_uk":"/eɪtθ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'eɪtɪ/","example":"The band was incredibly successful in the eighties. 这支乐队在80年代红透半边天。","translation":"num. 八十，八十个","phonetic_us":"/ˈeti/","word":"eighty"},{"phonetic_us":"/'iðɚ/","translation":"pron. (两者)任何一个","word":"either","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'aɪðə; 'iː-/"},{"word":"elaborate","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'læbəret/","translation":"adj. 复杂的；精心制作的","example":"pure silks embroidered with elaborate patterns 绣有精美图案的真丝衣服","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'læb(ə)rət/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪ'læstɪk/","translation":"n. 松紧带；adj. 有弹性的","word":"elastic","example":"Make a mask with long ears and attach a piece of elastic to go around the back of the head. 做一个带长耳朵的面具，安上一条松紧带绕过后脑。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'læstɪk/"},{"translation":"n. 肘，肘部；弯管","phonetic_us":"/'ɛlbo/","word":"elbow","example":"He slipped and fell, badly bruising an elbow. 他滑倒了，严重挫伤了一只胳膊肘。","phonetic_uk":"/'elbəʊ/"},{"word":"elder","phonetic_us":"/'ɛldɚ/","translation":"adj. 年龄较大的；n. 长者","example":"Sarah is the elder of the two. 两人当中萨拉年纪较长。","phonetic_uk":"/'eldə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'eldəli/","example":"a well-dressed elderly woman 穿着考究的老妇人","word":"elderly","phonetic_us":"/'ɛldɚli/","translation":"adj. 较老的，年长的；n.  到了晚年的人， 老年人"},{"translation":"v. 选举，推选；选择","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛkt/","word":"elect","example":"the country’s first democratically elected government 该国第一个民主选举产生的政府","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lekt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛkʃən/","translation":"n. 选举，选择权；当选","word":"election","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lekʃ(ə)n/","example":"The Labour Party won the 2001 election by a huge majority. 工党在2001年选举中以巨大优势获胜。"},{"word":"elective","translation":"adj. 选举的，有选举权的；可任意选择的；n.  选修课程","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛktɪv/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lektɪv/","example":"the 34 elective seats in the National Assembly 国民议会中的34个选举席位"},{"word":"electric","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛktrɪk/","translation":"adj. 电的，电动的","example":"an electric blanket 电热毯","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lektrɪk/"},{"word":"electrical","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛktrɪkl/","translation":"adj. 电的，电气科学的","example":"The fire was caused by an electrical fault. 大火是电力故障引起的。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lektrɪk(ə)l/"},{"word":"electricity","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛk'trɪsəti/","translation":"n. 电，电学；电流","phonetic_uk":"/,ɪlek'trɪsɪtɪ; ,el-; ,iːl-/","example":"The farm was very isolated, but it had electricity. 那个农场非常偏远，但有电力供应。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lektrɒn/","example":"Most things are balanced - with equal numbers of electrons and protons. 大部分物体都是电荷平衡的——含等量的电子和质子。","word":"electron","translation":"n. 电子","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛktrɑn/"},{"example":"electronic games 电子游戏","phonetic_uk":"/ɪˌlekˈtrɒnɪk/","translation":"adj. 电子的","phonetic_us":"/ɪˌlekˈtrɑːnɪk/","word":"electronic"},{"word":"electronics","translation":"n. 电子学","phonetic_us":"/ɪ,lɛk'trɑnɪks/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪlek'trɒnɪks; el-/","example":"an electronics engineer 电子工程师"},{"translation":"adj. 优雅的","phonetic_us":"/'ɛləgənt/","word":"elegant","example":"a tall, elegant young woman 身材高挑、举止优雅的年轻女子","phonetic_uk":"/'elɪg(ə)nt/"},{"word":"element","translation":"n. 元素，要素","phonetic_us":"/'ɛləmənt/","example":"Business and management elements are built into the course. 本课程加入了商务和管理方面的内容。","phonetic_uk":"/'elɪm(ə)nt/"},{"word":"elementary","translation":"adj. 基本的；初级的","phonetic_us":"/,ɛlɪ'mɛntri/","example":"the elementary principles of justice and democracy 正义和民主的基本信条","phonetic_uk":"/elɪ'ment(ə)rɪ/"},{"example":"A trunk distinguishes the elephant. 长鼻是象的特征。","phonetic_uk":"/'elɪf(ə)nt/","word":"elephant","phonetic_us":"/'ɛlɪfənt/","translation":"n. 象"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'elɪveɪtə/","example":"We’ll have to take the elevator. 我们只好坐电梯了。","word":"elevator","phonetic_us":"/'ɛlɪvetɚ/","translation":"n. 电梯；升降机"},{"example":"She was sent to jail for eleven months. 她被判入狱11个月。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lev(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛvn/","translation":"num. 十一，十一个","word":"eleven"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lev(ə)nθ/","example":"Moving up from tenth to eleventh grade was a major one. 从十年级升到十一年级是个重要的阶段。","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɛvnθ/","translation":"num. 第十一(个)","word":"eleventh"},{"example":"a ruthless dictator who eliminated all his rivals 铲除所有异己的残酷独裁者","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'lɪmɪneɪt/","word":"eliminate","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'lɪmɪnet/","translation":"v. 消除"},{"example":"Breast-feeding is as natural as sex or elimination or any other bodily function. 母乳哺养是天生的，就像性交、排泄或者其他任何身体功能一样。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ,lɪmɪ'neɪʃən/","translation":"n. 消灭，排除，消除","phonetic_us":"/ɪ,lɪmə'neʃən/","word":"elimination"},{"word":"else","phonetic_us":"/ɛls/","translation":"adv. 其它，另外；adj. 别的","example":"There’s something else I’d like to talk about as well. 我还有其他事情要谈一谈。","phonetic_uk":"/els/"},{"translation":"adv. 在别处，向别处","phonetic_us":"","word":"elsewhere","example":"She is becoming famous in Australia and elsewhere. 她在澳大利亚和其他地方渐渐出名了。","phonetic_uk":"/els'weə; 'elsweə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'bærəs/","example":"He didn’t want to embarrass her by asking questions. 他不想提问让她尴尬。","word":"embarrass","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'bærəs/","translation":"v. 尴尬"},{"phonetic_uk":"/im'bærəst/","example":"Lori gets embarrassed if we ask her to sing. 我们要是请洛丽唱歌，她就会难为情。","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'bærəst/","translation":"adj. 尴尬的；窘迫的","word":"embarrassed"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɛmbəsi/","translation":"n.  大使馆； 大使馆全体成员","word":"embassy","example":"the American Embassy in Paris 美国驻巴黎大使馆","phonetic_uk":"/'embəsi/"},{"translation":"v. 拥抱；接受；采纳","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'bres/","word":"embrace","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'breɪs/","example":"Jack warmly embraced his son. 杰克热情拥抱他的儿子。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'mɜːdʒ/","example":"The flowers emerge in the spring. 花儿在春天开放。","word":"emerge","translation":"v. 出现","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mɝdʒ/"},{"example":"The day after that, the emergence of a new competitor. 今后的每一天都可能出现新的竞争对手。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'mɜ:dʒəns/","word":"emergence","translation":"n. 出现，发生","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mɝdʒəns/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/i'mə:dʒənsi/","example":"Lifeguards are trained to deal with emergencies. 救生员接受过应对紧急情况的训练。","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mɝdʒənsi/","translation":"n. 紧急情况","word":"emergency"},{"word":"emission","translation":"n. 排放，辐射","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mɪʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'mɪʃn/","example":"Britain agreed to cut emissions of nitrogen oxide from power stations. 英国同意减少发电站氮氧化物的排放量。"},{"word":"emit","translation":"v. 发出，排出","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mɪt/","phonetic_uk":"/i'mit/","example":"The kettle emitted a shrill whistle. 水壶发出了刺耳的鸣笛声。"},{"example":"Her voice was full of emotion. 她的声音充满了激情。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'məʊʃ(ə)n/","word":"emotion","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'moʃən/","translation":"n. 情感，感情；激动"},{"phonetic_uk":"/i'məuʃənəl/","example":"She provided emotional support at a very distressing time for me. 在我非常痛苦的时候，她是我的情感支柱。","translation":"adj. 情绪的；容易激动的；感动人的","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'moʃənl/","word":"emotional"},{"word":"emperor","phonetic_us":"/'ɛmpərɚ/","translation":"n. 皇帝","phonetic_uk":"/'emp(ə)rə/","example":"They  bowed before the emperor as he entered the court. 皇帝进入朝廷时他们都向他鞠躬致敬。"},{"example":"a change of emphasis in government policy 政府政策重心的变化","phonetic_uk":"/'emfəsɪs/","translation":"n. 强调，重点，重要性","phonetic_us":"/'ɛmfəsɪs/","word":"emphasis"},{"example":"The report emphasizes the importance of improving safety standards. 报告强调了改进安全标准的重要性。","phonetic_uk":"/'emfəsaiz/","word":"emphasize","translation":"v. 强调","phonetic_us":"/'ɛmfəsaɪz/"},{"word":"empire","phonetic_us":"/'ɛmpaɪr/","translation":"n. 帝国","phonetic_uk":"/'empaɪə/","example":"the Roman empire 罗马帝国"},{"word":"employ","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'plɔɪ/","translation":"v. 雇用；用；使忙于","example":"The factory employs over 2,000 people. 这家工厂雇用了2,000多名员工。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'plɒɪ; em-/"},{"example":"a government employee 政府雇员","phonetic_uk":"/emplɒɪ'iː; em'plɒɪiː; ɪm-/","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'plɔɪi/","translation":"n. 受雇者，雇员，雇工","word":"employee"},{"example":"The shoe factory is the largest employer in this area. 这家制鞋厂是本地区最大的雇主。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'plɒɪə; em-/","translation":"n. 雇佣者，雇主","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'plɔɪɚ/","word":"employer"},{"example":"She was offered employment in the sales office. 她获聘在销售部工作。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'plɒɪm(ə)nt; em-/","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'plɔɪmənt/","translation":"n. 工业；雇用；使用","word":"employment"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pauə/","example":"The Voting Rights Act was needed to empower minority groups. 《选举权法案》对于赋予少数民族自主权是必不可少的。","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'paʊɚ/","translation":"vt.  授权于； 使能够","word":"empower"},{"word":"empty","phonetic_us":"/ˈɛmptɪ/","translation":"adj. 空的；空洞的","phonetic_uk":"/'em(p)tɪ/","example":"an empty box 空盒子"},{"translation":"v. 使能够……","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'nebl/","word":"enable","example":"The new test should enable doctors to detect the disease early. 新的检验使医生能在早期发现该种疾病。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'eɪb(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kləʊz; en-/","example":"Please enclose a cheque with your order. 请随订单附上支票。","word":"enclose","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'kloz/","translation":"v. 围住，圈起；附上"},{"example":"The doctor had encountered several similar cases in the past. 那位医生过去曾碰到过好几个类似病例。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kaʊntə; en-/","translation":"v. 遭遇，遇到；n. 遭遇","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'kaʊntɚ/","word":"encounter"},{"word":"encourage","translation":"v. 鼓励","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'kɝrɪdʒ/","example":"I want to thank everyone who has encouraged and supported me. 我要感谢每一位鼓励和支持过我的人。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kʌrɪdʒ/"},{"word":"end","phonetic_us":"/ɛnd/","translation":"n. 末端；目标；v. 结束","phonetic_uk":"/end/","example":"He wore spectacles perched on the very end of his nose. 他的眼镜架在鼻尖上。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈdeɪndʒə(r)/","example":"Smoking during pregnancy endangers your baby’s life. 孕期吸烟会危及胎儿生命。","word":"endanger","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dendʒɚ/","translation":"v. 危及，危害，濒临危险"},{"translation":"n. 结尾，结局；死亡","phonetic_us":"/'ɛndɪŋ/","word":"ending","phonetic_uk":"/'endɪŋ/","example":"Verbal nouns have the ending -ing. 动名词以-ing结尾。"},{"example":"an endless stream of visitors 川流不息的游客","phonetic_uk":"/'endlɪs/","word":"endless","translation":"adj. 无止境的","phonetic_us":"/'ɛndləs/"},{"translation":"n. 耐力","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dʊrəns/","word":"endurance","phonetic_uk":"/in'djuərəns/","example":"She was pushed beyond her powers of endurance. 她被逼得忍无可忍。"},{"word":"endure","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dʊr/","translation":"v. 忍耐；容忍","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'djʊə/","example":"It seemed impossible that anyone could endure such pain. 似乎谁都不可能忍受这样的疼痛。"},{"word":"enemy","phonetic_us":"/'ɛnəmi/","translation":"n. 敌人；仇敌；敌兵","phonetic_uk":"/'enəmɪ/","example":"She’s a dangerous enemy to have. 与她为敌很危险。"},{"word":"energetic","phonetic_us":"/,ɛnɚ'dʒɛtɪk/","translation":"adj. 精力充沛的","phonetic_uk":"/ˌenəˈdʒetɪk/","example":"an energetic man 精力旺盛的男子"},{"word":"energy","translation":"n. 活力；精力；能","phonetic_us":"/'ɛnɚdʒi/","phonetic_uk":"/'enədʒɪ/","example":"The water is heated using energy from the sun. 水是利用太阳能加热的。"},{"example":"Parking restrictions will be strictly enforced. 停车限制将会严格执行。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'fɔːs; en-/","translation":"v. 实施，执行；强制","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'fɔrs/","word":"enforce"},{"word":"engage","translation":"v. 忙于，从事；吸引","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ɡedʒ/","example":"I have never engaged in drug trafficking. 我从来没有从事过贩毒。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'geɪdʒ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ɡedʒmənt/","translation":"n. 约会","word":"engagement","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈgeɪdʒmənt/","example":"Their engagement was announced in the paper. 他们订婚的消息在报上公布了。"},{"example":"Is the engine running smoothly? 发动机运转平稳吗？","phonetic_uk":"/ˈendʒɪn/","translation":"n. 引擎，发动机","phonetic_us":"/'ɛndʒɪn/","word":"engine"},{"word":"engineer","translation":"n. 工程师，技师","phonetic_us":"/,ɛndʒɪ'nɪr/","example":"He trained as a civil engineer (= one who designs and builds roads, bridges etc ). 他接受过土木工程师培训。","phonetic_uk":"/endʒɪ'nɪə/"},{"example":"Their inventions have contributed to the development of electrical engineering. 他们的发明有助于电气工程学的发展。","phonetic_uk":"/endʒɪ'nɪərɪŋ/","translation":"n. 工程，工程学","phonetic_us":"/'ɛndʒə'nɪrɪŋ/","word":"engineering"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɪŋɡlənd/","phonetic_us":"/'iŋɡlənd/","translation":"n. 英格兰；英国","word":"England"},{"example":"Do you speak English? 你会说英语吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪŋɡlɪʃ/","word":"English","phonetic_us":"/ɪŋɡlɪʃ/","translation":"n. 英语；adj. 英国人的"},{"phonetic_us":"/'iŋɡliʃmən/","translation":"n. 英国男子","word":"Englishman","phonetic_uk":"/'iŋɡliʃmən/","example":"He was the only Englishman present. 他是在场的唯一一名英国人。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/in'hɑ:ns/","example":"Good lighting will enhance any room. 良好的照明能给房间增色不少。","word":"enhance","translation":"v. 提高；加强；增加","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'hæns/"},{"example":"Sandra enjoys her job in the city. 桑德拉很喜欢她在城里的这份工作。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'dʒɒɪ; en-/","word":"enjoy","translation":"v. 享受；欣赏，喜爱","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dʒɔɪ/"},{"translation":"v. 扩大，扩展；放大","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'lɑrdʒ/","word":"enlarge","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'lɑːdʒ; en-/","example":"an operation to enlarge her breasts 她的丰胸手术"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪ'nɔrməs/","translation":"adj. 巨大的","word":"enormous","example":"an enormous bunch of flowers 巨大的花束","phonetic_uk":"/i'nɔ:məs/"},{"translation":"adj. 足够的；adv. 足够地","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'nʌf/","word":"enough","example":"Her disappearance and death would give proof enough of Charles' guilt. 她的失踪和死亡将提供足够的证据证明查尔斯有罪。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'nʌf/"},{"word":"enquire","translation":"v.  询问","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'kwaɪr/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kwaɪə/","example":"Day and day I take pains to enquire myself my reason for doing so, in no time will I stoop so low as to beg you sympathy, though I can feel your scoff all the time. 日复一日，我不厌其详地询问我自己，我在任何时候都这样低俯恳求你同情，但我能感受到你对这一切一切嗤之以鼻。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɛnˈkwaɪri, ˈɛnkwəri/","translation":"n.  询问","word":"enquiry","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kwaɪəri/","example":"We are pleased to receive your enquiry. 我们很高兴收到您的询问函。"},{"word":"enrich","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'rɪtʃ/","translation":"v. 丰富；使富有","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'rɪtʃ/","example":"Add fertilizer to enrich the soil. 施上肥料使土壤肥沃。"},{"word":"enroll","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'rol/","translation":"v. 注册","phonetic_uk":"/inˈrəul/","example":""},{"word":"enrollment","translation":"n. 入学人数","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'rolmənt/","example":"Class enrollment, where each student has all of the course schedule selections, each student having his own bucket in the CGTT. 班级入学，每个学生都有所有的课程安排选择，每个学生都将自己的选择放在 CGTT 中。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'rəʊlmənt/"},{"example":"facilities to ensure the safety of cyclists 确保骑车人安全的设施","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'ʃʊə(r)/","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ʃʊr/","translation":"v. 确保","word":"ensure"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'entə/","example":"He entered the election as the clear favourite. 他参加竞选时显然最有希望获胜。","translation":"v. 走进，进入；参加","phonetic_us":"/'ɛntɚ/","word":"enter"},{"example":"Mark usually does the cooking when we entertain. 我们招待客人时通常都是马克下厨。","phonetic_uk":"/entə'teɪn/","phonetic_us":"/,ɛntɚ'ten/","translation":"v. 使欢乐；招待","word":"entertain"},{"translation":"adj. 有趣的，使人愉快的","phonetic_us":"/,ɛntɚ'tenɪŋ/","word":"entertaining","example":"Children’s TV nowadays is much more entertaining. 如今的儿童电视节目要比过去有趣多了。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌentəˈteɪnɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌentəˈteɪnmənt/","example":"The town provides a wide choice of entertainment. 该镇提供各式各样的娱乐活动。","word":"entertainment","translation":"n. 娱乐","phonetic_us":"/'ɛntɚ'tenmənt/"},{"word":"enthusiasm","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'θuzɪæzəm/","translation":"n. 热情，热心，热忱","example":"Gillian and Darren greeted the speakers with great enthusiasm. 吉利恩和达伦非常热情地接待了演讲者。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'θjuːzɪæz(ə)m; en-/"},{"example":"an enthusiastic supporter of reform 改革的热心支持者","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn,θjuːzɪ'æstɪk; en-/","translation":"adj. 热情的，热心的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn,θuzɪ'æstɪk/","word":"enthusiastic"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'taɪə; en-/","example":"It was the worst day in my entire life. 那是我一生中最糟糕的一天。","translation":"adj. 全部的，整个的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'taɪɚ/","word":"entire"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'taɪtl/","translation":"v. 使具有权利，使具有资格","word":"entitle","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈtaɪtl/","example":"If the warranty is limited, the terms may entitle you to a replacement or refund. 如果保修单有限制，这些条款可让你有权换货或退款。"},{"word":"entrance","phonetic_us":"/'ɛntrəns/","translation":"n. 入口，门口；进入","example":"the station entrance 车站的入口处","phonetic_uk":"/'entr(ə)ns/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈɒntreɪ/","example":"There was no sign of a forced entry. 没有强行闯入的迹象。","word":"entry","translation":"n. 入口处；登记；进入","phonetic_us":"/'ɛntri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'envələʊp; 'ɒn-/","example":"envelopes and stamps 信封和邮票","word":"envelope","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 信封；封套；封皮"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vaɪrənm(ə)nt; en-/","example":"Some of these chemicals are very damaging to the environment. 这些化学品中有些对环境非常有害。","translation":"n. 环境，外界；围绕","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vaɪrənmənt/","word":"environment"},{"example":"I really envy you and Ian, you seem so happy together. 我真是羡慕你和伊恩，你俩在一起看起来多幸福。","phonetic_uk":"/'envɪ/","word":"envy","phonetic_us":"/'ɛnvi/","translation":"vt&n. 妒忌；羡慕"},{"word":"epidemic","phonetic_us":"/,ɛpɪ'dɛmɪk/","translation":"adj. 流行性的；传染的；n.  流行病； 传播","phonetic_uk":"/ˌepɪ'demɪk/","example":"Over 500 people died during last year’s flu epidemic. 去年流感大暴发期间有五百多人死亡。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'epɪsəud/","example":"Watch next week’s thrilling episode! 请收看下周精彩的一集！","word":"episode","phonetic_us":"/'ɛpɪsod/","translation":"n.  一个事件； 插曲， 片段； 连续剧的一集"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'i:kwəl/","example":"Our constitution states that all men are equal. 我们的宪法规定人人平等。","phonetic_us":"/'ikwəl/","translation":"adj. 相等的，平等的","word":"equal"},{"word":"equality","translation":"n. 平等","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'kwɑləti/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'kwɒlətɪ/","example":"...equality of the sexes. …性别平等。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪ'kweʒn/","translation":"n. 方程(式)；等式","word":"equation","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'kweɪʒ(ə)n/","example":"In the equation 2x + 1 = 7, what is x? 在方程式2x+1=7中，x的值为多少？"},{"translation":"v. 装备，配备","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'kwɪp/","word":"equip","example":"They try to equip their vehicles with gadgets to deal with every possible contingency. 他们尽量给他们的车辆配备各种小装置以应付任何可能的突发状况。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'kwɪp/"},{"example":"a shop selling camping equipment 出售露营装备的商店","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'kwɪpm(ə)nt/","translation":"n. 装备，设备，配备","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'kwɪpmənt/","word":"equipment"},{"translation":"n. 等值，相等","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'kwɪvələns/","word":"equivalence","example":"...the equivalence of science and rationality. ...科学和理性的相等。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'kwɪv(ə)l(ə)ns/"},{"word":"equivalent","translation":"adj. 相等的，相当的","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'kwɪvələnt/","example":"I had no dollars, but offered him an equivalent amount of sterling. 我没有美金，但给了他等值的英镑。","phonetic_uk":"/i'kwivələnt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪərə/","example":"His death marked the end of an era. 他的去世标志着一个时代的终结。","word":"era","phonetic_us":"/'ɪrə/","translation":"n. 纪元，年代"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'rekt/","example":"an imposing town hall, erected in 1892 一座气势宏伟的市政厅，建于1892年","word":"erect","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'rɛkt/","translation":"v. 建造；使竖立"},{"word":"erroneous","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'ronɪəs/","translation":"adj.  错误的， 不正确的","example":"His economic predictions are based on some erroneous assumptions. 他的经济预测是基于错误假设之上的。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'rəuniəs/"},{"example":"an error message 出错信息","phonetic_uk":"/'erə/","translation":"n. 错误，谬误；差错","phonetic_us":"/'ɛrɚ/","word":"error"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'skeɪp; e-/","example":"Vents allow any steam to escape if the system overheats. 如果系统过热，排放口可使蒸汽逸出。","word":"escape","phonetic_us":"/ɪˈskep/","translation":"v. 逃跑；逸出；n. 逃跑"},{"example":"I never liked long walks, especially in winter. 我向来不喜欢长距离散步，尤其在冬天。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'speʃ(ə)lɪ; e-/","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'spɛʃəli/","translation":"adv. 特别，尤其，格外","word":"especially"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɛse/","translation":"n. 散文，文章","word":"essay","example":"We asked Jason to write an essay about his hometown. 我们让杰森写一篇关于他家乡的短文。","phonetic_uk":"/'eseɪ/"},{"word":"essential","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'sɛnʃl/","translation":"adj. 本质的，必须的","example":"Window locks are fairly cheap and absolutely essential. 窗锁相当便宜，绝对有必要安装。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪˈsenʃl/"},{"word":"essentially","translation":"adv. 本质上地；必须的","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'sɛnʃəli/","example":"Ballet is essentially a middle-class interest. 芭蕾舞基本上是中产阶级感兴趣的东西。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'senʃ(ə)lɪ/"},{"word":"establish","phonetic_us":"/ɪˈstæblɪʃ/","translation":"v. 建立，创办，设立","example":"The city of Boerne was established by German settlers in the 1840s. 博恩市是德国移民于19世纪40年代建立的。","phonetic_uk":"/i'stæbliʃ/"},{"translation":"n. 确立，制定；公司；设施","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'stæblɪʃmənt/","word":"establishment","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'stæblɪʃm(ə)nt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'steɪt/","example":"a country estate 乡村的庄园","word":"estate","translation":"n.  土地， 住宅区， 地产； 财产， 遗产； 庄园， 种植园","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'stet/"},{"word":"esteem","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'stim/","translation":"n. 自尊","example":"After that, we could go for esteem and respect. 而再往上，我们可能需要自尊和尊重。","phonetic_uk":"/is'ti:m/"},{"example":"Try to estimate how many steps it will take to get to a close object. 估计一下需要多少步才能到达一个近距目标。","phonetic_uk":"/'estɪmeɪt/","word":"estimate","translation":"v. 估计","phonetic_us":"/'ɛstə,met/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'jʊrəp/","translation":"n. 欧洲","word":"Europe","phonetic_uk":"/'jʊrəp/","example":"eastern Europe 东欧"},{"word":"European","translation":"adj. 欧洲的；n. 欧洲人","phonetic_us":"/'jʊrə'piən/","example":"European languages 欧洲的语言","phonetic_uk":"/jʊərə'piːən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪ'væljʊ'et/","translation":"v. 评价","word":"evaluate","phonetic_uk":"/ɪˈvæljueɪt/","example":"You should be able to evaluate your own work. 你应该能够评估自己的工作。"},{"word":"evaluation","phonetic_us":"/ɪ,væljʊ'eʃən/","translation":"n. 评价，评估","phonetic_uk":"/ɪˌvæljuˈeɪʃn/","example":"We need to carry out a proper evaluation of the new system. 我们要对新系统进行合理的评估。"},{"word":"evaporate","translation":"v. 使蒸发；v. 蒸发","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'væpəret/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'væpəreɪt/","example":"Most of the water had evaporated. 大部分的水都蒸发了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/iːv/","example":"We’re arriving on Christmas Eve. 我们将在平安夜到达。","word":"eve","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 前夜，前夕，前一刻"},{"example":"Most companies have suffered a drop in their profits, even very large companies. 大多数公司的利润都出现下滑，甚至连很大的公司也不例外。","phonetic_uk":"/'iːv(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'ivən/","translation":"adv. 甚至；甚至更，还","word":"even"},{"example":"I do most of my studying in the evening. 我学习大都在晚上。","phonetic_uk":"/'iːv(ə)nɪŋ/","translation":"n. 傍晚，黄昏，晚上","phonetic_us":"/'ivnɪŋ/","word":"evening"},{"example":"one of the most important events in the history of mankind 人类历史上最重大的事件之一","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'vent/","word":"event","translation":"n. 事件，大事；事变","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'vɛnt/"},{"example":"He eventually escaped and made his way back to England. 他终于逃脱并返回英格兰。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'ventʃʊəlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'vɛntʃuəli/","translation":"adv. 终于；最后","word":"eventually"},{"word":"ever","translation":"adv. 在任何时候；曾经","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvɚ/","example":"Nothing ever seems to upset him. 似乎从来没有什么事情会使他烦恼。","phonetic_uk":"/'evə/"},{"word":"everlasting","translation":"adj. 永恒的","phonetic_us":"/,ɛvɚ'læstɪŋ/","example":"everlasting fame 永久的名声","phonetic_uk":"/ˌevəˈlɑ:stɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɛvri/","translation":"adj. 每一的；每隔…的","word":"every","phonetic_uk":"/'evrɪ/","example":"His every utterance will be scrutinized. 他说的每句话都会被细查。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'evrɪbɒdɪ/","example":"","word":"everybody","translation":"pron. 每人，人人","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvrɪbɑdi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'evrɪdeɪ; -'deɪ/","example":"the problems of everyday life 日常生活中的问题","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvrɪde/","translation":"adj. 每天的，日常的","word":"everyday"},{"example":"If everyone is ready, I’ll begin. 如果大家都准备好了，我就开始。","phonetic_uk":"/'evrɪwʌn/","word":"everyone","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvrɪwʌn/","translation":"pron. 每人，人人"},{"example":"Everything was covered in a thick layer of dust. 所有东西上面都蒙着厚厚一层灰。","phonetic_uk":"/'evrɪθɪŋ/","translation":"pron. 每件事，事事","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvrɪ'θɪŋ/","word":"everything"},{"example":"I’ve looked everywhere but I can’t find the map. 我到处都找过了，但就是找不到地图。","phonetic_uk":"/'evrɪweə/","word":"everywhere","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvrɪwɛr/","translation":"adv. 到处，处处"},{"example":"Murrow’s evidence was enough to convict Hayes of murder. 默罗的证词足以证明海斯犯了谋杀罪。","phonetic_uk":"/'evidəns/","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvɪdəns/","translation":"n. 根据，证据，迹象","word":"evidence"},{"word":"evident","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvɪdənt/","translation":"adj. 明显的","example":"Bob ate his lunch with evident enjoyment. 显然鲍勃吃午饭吃得津津有味。","phonetic_uk":"/'evɪd(ə)nt/"},{"translation":"adv.  明显地， 显然","phonetic_us":"/'ɛvɪdəntli/","word":"evidently","phonetic_uk":"/'evɪdəntli/","example":"She was evidently a heavy smoker. 她显然烟瘾很大。"},{"word":"evil","phonetic_us":"/'ivl/","translation":"n. 邪恶，罪恶","example":"She wanted to protect her children from the evils of the outside world. 她想保护她的孩子不受外界的不良影响。","phonetic_uk":"/'i:vl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ivəˈluʃən/","example":"the theory of evolution 进化论","phonetic_us":"/ˌɛvəˈluʃən; (occas.) ˌ ivəˈluʃən/","translation":"n. 演变，进化","word":"evolution"},{"example":"the evolutionary development of birds 鸟类的进化过程","phonetic_uk":"/ˌi:vəˈlu:ʃənri/","word":"evolutionary","phonetic_us":"/,ivə'luʃənɛri/","translation":"adj. 演变的，进化的"},{"example":"The school has evolved its own style of teaching. 学校逐步形成了自己的教学风格。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'vɒlv/","translation":"v. 使发展","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'vɑlv/","word":"evolve"},{"example":"Police are still investigating the exact cause of the accident. 警方还在调查这起事故的确切原因。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zækt; eg-/","translation":"adj. 确切的；精确的","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zækt/","word":"exact"},{"example":"It’s exactly half past five. 一分不差，正好5点半。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zæk(t)lɪ; eg-/","word":"exactly","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zæktli/","translation":"adv. 确切地；恰恰正是"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zædʒəreɪt/","example":"I couldn’t sleep for three days – I’m not exaggerating. 我三天没睡觉了——一点不夸张。","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zædʒəret/","translation":"v. 夸张","word":"exaggerate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zæm; eg-/","example":"At the end of each level, there’s an exam. 在每一级别结束时都有一次考试。","translation":"n. 考试；检查，细查","phonetic_us":"/ɪg'zæm/","word":"exam"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪg,zæmɪ'neɪʃ(ə)n; eg-/","example":"The examination results will be announced in September. 考试成绩将于9月公布。","word":"examination","translation":"n. 考试；检查，细查","phonetic_us":"/ɪg'zæmə'neʃən/"},{"word":"examine","phonetic_us":"/ɪg'zæmɪn/","translation":"v. 检查，仔细观察","phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zæmɪn; eg-/","example":"A team of divers was sent down to examine the wreck. 一组潜水员被送到水下检查沉船。"},{"translation":"n. 例子，实例；模范","phonetic_us":"/ɪg'zæmpl/","word":"example","example":"Many countries, for example Mexico and Japan, have a lot of earthquakes. 许多国家，例如墨西哥和日本，经常发生地震。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zɑːmp(ə)l; eg-/"},{"translation":"v. 超过，胜过；超出","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sid/","word":"exceed","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'siːd; ek-/","example":"Working hours must not exceed 42 hours a week. 工作时间每周不得超过42小时。"},{"example":"Thank you. You’ve been exceedingly kind. 谢谢，你真是太好了。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'siːdɪŋlɪ; ek-/","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sidɪŋli/","translation":"adv. 极端地，非常","word":"exceedingly"},{"translation":"adj. 卓越的，杰出的，极好的","phonetic_us":"/'ɛksələnt/","word":"excellent","phonetic_uk":"/'eksələnt/","example":"an excellent suggestion 极好的建议"},{"example":"They were all there except me. 除了我以外他们都在那里。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'sept; ek-/","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sɛpt/","translation":"prep. 除…之外","word":"except"},{"example":"It’s been cold, but today’s an exception. 天气一直寒冷，但今天是个例外。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪkˈsepʃn/","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sɛpʃən/","translation":"n. 例外","word":"exception"},{"example":"After you apply the oil, wait 20 minutes before wiping off any excess. 涂上油以后，等20分钟再擦掉多余部分。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪkˈses/","word":"excess","phonetic_us":"/'ɛk'sɛs/","translation":"n. 过量，过度"},{"word":"excessive","phonetic_us":"/ɪkˈsɛsɪv/","translation":"adj. 过度的","phonetic_uk":"/ɪkˈsesɪv/","example":"his excessive drinking 他的酗酒"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪks'tʃendʒ/","translation":"n & v. 交换，交流","word":"exchange","phonetic_uk":"/ɪks'tʃeɪndʒ/","example":"Four of my cassettes for your Madonna CD is a fair exchange. 我用四盒磁带换你的麦当娜激光唱片很公平。"},{"word":"excite","translation":"v. 使激动；引起","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'saɪt/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'saɪt; ek-/","example":"His playing is technically brilliant, but it doesn’t excite me. 他的演奏技巧娴熟，但并不让我激动。"},{"word":"excitement","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'saɪtmənt/","translation":"n.  刺激， 激动， 兴奋； 令人兴奋的事， 刺激的因素","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'saɪtmənt/","example":"We were both new to the excitements of life in the big city. 我们俩都是初次感受大城市多姿多彩的生活。"},{"example":"an exciting discovery 激动人心的发现","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'saɪtɪŋ; ek-/","word":"exciting","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'saɪtɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 令人兴奋的"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sklem/","translation":"v. 呼喊；惊叫","word":"exclaim","example":"‘No!’ she exclaimed in shock. “不！”她惊呼道。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'skleɪm; ek-/"},{"translation":"v. 排除，不包括","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sklʊd/","word":"exclude","example":"a special diet that excludes dairy products 不包含奶制品的特别食谱","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'sklu:d/"},{"example":"Bel Air is an exclusive suburb of Los Angeles. 贝莱尔是洛杉矶郊外一处高级住宅区。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'skluːsɪv/","word":"exclusive","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sklusɪv/","translation":"adj. 奢华的，高级的；独有的，独享的；排斥的，排他的；不包括…的，不把…计算在内的；n.  独家新闻"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'skluːsɪvlɪ/","example":"These are not involved as exclusively as ministers in \"soul-work,\" but they certainly cultivate the inner life more than the third group. 他们虽不像牧师那样专门做“灵魂方面的工作”，但是肯定比第三群体更注重于建造人类的生命。","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sklʊsɪvli/","translation":"adv. 专门地","word":"exclusively"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'skɜːʃ(ə)n; ek-/","example":"a shopping excursion 购物游","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'skɝʒn/","translation":"n. 远足；短途旅行","word":"excursion"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪk'skjʊs/","translation":"v. 原谅；免除；n. 借口","word":"excuse","example":"I’ll excuse you this time, but don’t be late again. 这次我原谅你，但别再迟到了。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'skjuːz; ek-/"},{"word":"execute","translation":"v. 将…处死；实施","phonetic_us":"/'ɛksɪkjut/","phonetic_uk":"/'eksɪkjuːt/","example":"13 people were summarily executed (= killed without any trial or legal process ) by the guerrillas. 有13人被游击队员就地处决。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zɛkjətɪv/","translation":"adj. 执行的；n. 执行者","word":"executive","phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zekjʊtɪv; eg-/","example":"a commission with executive powers 有执行权的委员会"},{"word":"exercise","translation":"n. 锻炼，训练；v. 练习","phonetic_us":"/'ɛksɚsaɪz/","example":"Try to fit some regular exercise into your daily routine. 尽量在日常生活中安排一些经常性的锻炼。","phonetic_uk":"/'eksəsaɪz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zɜːt; eg-/","example":"They exerted considerable influence within the school. 他们在校内施加了很大的影响力。","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zɝt/","translation":"v. 尽(力)，运用","word":"exert"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪgˈzɔ:st/","example":"A full day’s teaching exhausts me. 讲一整天课令我精疲力竭。","word":"exhaust","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zɔst/","translation":"v. 使筋疲力尽"},{"word":"exhibit","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zɪbɪt/","translation":"v. 显示；陈列，展览","phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zɪbɪt; eg-/","example":"Her paintings have been exhibited all over the world. 她的绘画作品在世界各地展出。"},{"word":"exhibition","phonetic_us":"/,ɛksɪ'bɪʃən/","translation":"n. 展览","phonetic_uk":"/ˌeksɪˈbɪʃn/","example":"...an exhibition of expressionist art. …一场印象主义艺术展览会。"},{"translation":"n. 流放，放逐","phonetic_us":"/'ɛksaɪl/","word":"exile","example":"political exiles 政治流亡者","phonetic_uk":"/'eksaɪl/"},{"example":"The custom of arranged marriages still exists in many countries. 许多国家仍存在包办婚姻的习俗。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zɪst; eg-/","word":"exist","translation":"v. 存在；生存，生活","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zɪst/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪg'zɪst(ə)ns; eg-/","example":"Scientists have many theories about how the universe first came into existence (= started to exist ). 关于宇宙的起源，科学家有多种理论。","word":"existence","translation":"n. 存在，实在；生存","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'zɪstəns/"},{"translation":"n. 出口；退场；v. 退出","phonetic_us":"/'ɛɡzɪt/","word":"exit","example":"We made for the nearest exit. 我们走向最近的出口。","phonetic_uk":"/'eksɪt; 'egzɪt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spænd/","translation":"v. 扩大","word":"expand","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spænd/","example":"Water expands as it freezes. 水结冰时会膨胀。"},{"example":"The industry underwent a period of rapid expansion. 该产业经历了一轮快速扩张。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spænʃ(ə)n; ek-/","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spænʃən/","translation":"n. 扩大，扩充；扩张","word":"expansion"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spekt; ek-/","example":"He will be hard to beat. I fully expect (= am completely sure about ) that and I’m ready. 他很难击败。我确信这一点，不过我准备好了。","translation":"v. 预料，预期；等待","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spɛkt/","word":"expect"},{"example":"Having raised expectations (= made people more hopeful ), he went on to help only a few people. 他唤起了大家的希望，但接着只是帮助了几个人。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌekspekˈteɪʃn/","translation":"n. 期望","phonetic_us":"/,ɛkspɛk'teʃən/","word":"expectation"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spens; ek-/","example":"He borrowed £150,000 and used the money for legal expenses. 他借了15万英镑用于支付律师费。","word":"expense","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spɛns/","translation":"n. 花费，消费；费用"},{"translation":"adj. 昂贵的，花钱多的","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spɛnsɪv/","word":"expensive","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spensɪv; ek-/","example":"the most expensive restaurant in town 城里最贵的餐馆"},{"example":"The advice in the booklet reflects the practical experience we have gained (= experience gained by actually doing something, rather than knowledge from books etc ). 小册子中的建议反映了我们所获得的实践经验。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spɪərɪəns; ek-/","translation":"n. 经验，感受；经历","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spɪrɪəns/","word":"experience"},{"translation":"n. 实验；试验","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sperɪmənt/","word":"experiment","example":"The astronauts are conducting a series of experiments to learn more about how the body adapts to weightlessness. 那些宇航员正在进行一系列实验，以便更多地了解人体如何适应失重状态。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'sperɪm(ə)nt; ek-/"},{"word":"experimental","translation":"adj. 实验的，试验的","phonetic_us":"/ɛk'spɛrɪ'mɛntəl/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk,sperɪ'ment(ə)l; ek-/","example":"experimental animals 用于实验的动物"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ekspɜːt/","example":"He cast his expert eye on the gardener’s work. 他用内行的眼光看了看园丁干的活。","word":"expert","phonetic_us":"/'ɛkspɝt; (for adj., also) ɛksˈpɝt ; ɪkˈspɝt/","translation":"adj. 熟练的，内行的"},{"word":"explain","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'splen/","translation":"v. 解释；为…辩解","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spleɪn/","example":"He carefully explained the procedure. 他仔细解释了程序。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/eksplə'neɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"She told the court she would give a full explanation of the prosecution's decision on Monday. 她告诉法庭她将在星期一就控方的决定做出详尽的解释。","phonetic_us":"/,ɛksplə'neʃən/","translation":"n. 解释，说明；辩解","word":"explanation"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'splɪsɪtli/","example":"You have to grant us control explicitly. 你们必须允许我们明确地控制。","word":"explicitly","translation":"adv. 直接地，明确地","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'splɪsɪtli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spləʊd; ek-/","example":"The device was thrown at an army patrol but failed to explode. 炸弹投向了陆军巡逻队，但没有爆炸。","translation":"v. 使爆炸；v. 爆炸","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'splod/","word":"explode"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'splɔɪt/","example":"the urgent need to exploit the resources of the Irish Sea 开发爱尔兰海资源的迫切需要","word":"exploit","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'splɔɪt/","translation":"v. 开采"},{"translation":"v. 探索","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'splɔr/","word":"explore","example":"Management need to explore ways of improving office security. 管理层需要探讨如何加强办事处的安全措施。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'splɔ:(r)/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪkˈspləʊʒn/","example":"We heard a loud explosion. 我们听到一声巨大的爆炸声。","word":"explosion","translation":"n. 爆炸","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sploʒən/"},{"word":"explosive","translation":"n. 炸药；adj. 爆炸的","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'splosɪv; ɪk'splozɪv/","example":"...one-hundred-and-fifty pounds of Semtex explosive. …150磅的塞姆汀塑料炸药。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spləʊsɪv; ek-/"},{"translation":"v. 输出，出口；运走","phonetic_us":"/ˈekspɔːrt；ɪkˈ-/","word":"export","example":"Italian food has been exported all over the world. 意大利食品已传遍世界。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈekspɔːt；ɪkˈ-/"},{"example":"He lifted his T-shirt to expose a jagged scar across his chest. 他撩起T恤衫，露出横贯胸部的锯齿状伤疤。","phonetic_uk":"/ik'spəuz/","word":"expose","translation":"v. 暴露","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spoz；ek-/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spəʊʒə/","example":"Exposure to lead is known to damage the brains of young children. 已知接触铅会损害幼童的大脑。","word":"exposure","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'spoʒɚ/","translation":"n. 暴露；揭露"},{"example":"Parents have expressed their concerns about their children’s safety. 父母对自己孩子的安全表示忧虑。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'spres; ek-/","translation":"v. 表示；n. 快车，快递","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sprɛs/","word":"express"},{"word":"expression","translation":"n. 词句；表达；表情","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'sprɛʃən/","example":"Student leaders are demanding greater freedom of expression (= the right to say what you think without being punished ). 学生领袖要求得到更多的言论自由。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪkˈspreʃn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ik'spresivnis/","example":"Moreover, it offers the expressiveness which helps to “simplify complex tasks”. 此外，它更具表现力，这有助于“简化复杂任务”。","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 表达","word":"expressiveness"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'stend; ek-/","example":"Management have agreed to extend the deadline. 管理层已同意延长最后期限。","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'stɛnd/","translation":"v. 延长；扩大；致","word":"extend"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'stenʃn/","example":"a loft extension 增建的阁楼","word":"extension","translation":"n. 分机","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'stɛnʃən/"},{"example":"The house stands in extensive grounds. 这栋房子占地面积很大。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'stensɪv; ek-/","translation":"adj. 广阔的；广泛的","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'stɛnsɪv/","word":"extensive"},{"word":"extensively","translation":"adv. 广泛地","phonetic_us":"/ik'stensivli/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'stensɪvlɪ/","example":"The new rocket was extensively tested and debugged by the army. 这种新式火箭由军方进行了广泛的测试和调试。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"","translation":"n. 广度；范围；程度","phonetic_us":"","word":"extent"},{"example":"The exterior walls need a new coat of paint. 外墙需要刷新漆了。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'stɪərɪə; ek-/","word":"exterior","translation":"adj. 外部的；对外的","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'stɪrɪɚ/"},{"example":"the external appearance of the building 大楼的外观","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'stɜːn(ə)l; ek-/","word":"external","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'stɝnl/","translation":"adj. 外部的，外面的"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɛkstrə/","translation":"adj. 额外的；adv. 特别地","word":"extra","phonetic_uk":"/'ekstrə/","example":"Could you get an extra loaf of bread? 你能多拿一条面包吗？"},{"word":"extracurricular","phonetic_us":"/,ɛkstrəkə'rɪkjəlɚ/","translation":"adj. 课外的","phonetic_uk":"/ekstrəkə'rɪkjʊlə/","example":"Each child had participated in extracurricular activities at school. 每个孩子都参加了学校的课外活动。"},{"example":"a woman of extraordinary beauty 容貌出众的女子","phonetic_uk":"/ɪkˈstrɔːdnri/","phonetic_us":"/ɛkˈstrɔrdənˌɛri; ɪkˈstrɔrdəˌnɛri; ˌɛkstrəˈɔrdəˌnɛri/","translation":"adj. 非凡的","word":"extraordinary"},{"translation":"adj. 极度的；尽头的","phonetic_us":"/ɪk'strim/","word":"extreme","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'striːm; ek-/","example":"Extreme poverty still exists in many rural areas. 许多农村地区仍处于赤贫状态。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪk'strimli/","translation":"adv. 极端，极其，非常","word":"extremely","example":"Earthquakes are extremely difficult to predict. 地震非常难以预测。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪk'striːmlɪ; ek-/"},{"word":"eye","translation":"n. 眼睛；眼力；鉴赏力","phonetic_us":"/aɪ/","phonetic_uk":"/aɪ/","example":"He’s got beautiful eyes. 他有一双漂亮的眼睛。"},{"word":"eyesight","translation":"n. 视力，目力","phonetic_us":"/'aɪsaɪt/","example":"He had a problem with his eyesight. 他的视力有问题。","phonetic_uk":"/'aɪsaɪt/"},{"example":"the fable of the fox and the crow 狐狸和乌鸦的寓言故事","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪb(ə)l/","word":"fable","translation":"n. 寓言；虚构的故事","phonetic_us":"/'febl/"},{"example":"our new range of fabrics and wallpapers 我们新的织物和墙纸系列","phonetic_uk":"/'fæbrɪk/","phonetic_us":"/'fæbrɪk/","translation":"n. 织物，纺织品；结构","word":"fabric"},{"translation":"n. 脸；表面；外表","phonetic_us":"/fes/","word":"face","phonetic_uk":"/feɪs/","example":"She had a beautiful face. 她面容秀美。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fəˈsɪlɪteɪt/","example":"The new airport will facilitate the development of tourism. 新机场将促进旅游业的发展。","translation":"v. 使便利，促进","phonetic_us":"/fə'sɪlə'tet/","word":"facilitate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fə'sɪləti/","example":"What recreational facilities are now available? 什么娱乐设施现在是可用的？","translation":"n. 设施","phonetic_us":"/fə'sɪləti/","word":"facility"},{"phonetic_us":"/fækt/","translation":"n. 事实；实际，实情","word":"fact","phonetic_uk":"/fækt/","example":"Our decision to build the museum in Hartlepool was influenced by the fact that there were no national museums in the North East. 我们之所以决定在哈特尔浦建造博物馆，是因为东北地区没有国家级的博物馆。"},{"example":"The rise in crime is mainly due to social and economic factors. 犯罪率上升主要由社会和经济因素造成。","phonetic_uk":"/'fæktə/","word":"factor","translation":"n. 因素；因子，系数","phonetic_us":"/'fæktɚ/"},{"word":"factory","translation":"n. 工厂，制造厂","phonetic_us":"/'fæktri/","example":"a car factory 汽车制造厂","phonetic_uk":"/'fækt(ə)rɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fæklti/","translation":"n. 才能，能力；系，科","word":"faculty","example":"the Engineering Faculty 工程学院","phonetic_uk":"/'fæk(ə)ltɪ/"},{"translation":"v. 逐渐消失","phonetic_us":"/fed/","word":"fade","phonetic_uk":"/feɪd/","example":"Hopes of a peace settlement are beginning to fade. 达成和平协议的希望日渐渺茫。"},{"example":"72˚ Fahrenheit (= 72 degrees on the Fahrenheit scale ) 72华氏度","phonetic_uk":"/'fær(ə)nhaɪt; 'fɑː-/","word":"Fahrenheit","translation":"n. 华氏温度计","phonetic_us":"/'færən'haɪt/"},{"word":"fail","phonetic_us":"/fel/","translation":"v. 失败；失灵；不能","phonetic_uk":"/feɪl/","example":"It looks likely that the peace talks will fail. 看来和平谈判可能会失败。"},{"example":"Successful people often aren’t very good at dealing with failure. 一帆风顺的人往往不太擅长应对失败。","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪljə/","word":"failure","phonetic_us":"/'feljɚ/","translation":"n. 失败；失败的人"},{"phonetic_uk":"/feɪnt/","example":"a faint hope that they might be alive 他们渺茫的生还希望","translation":"adj. 微弱的；虚弱的","phonetic_us":"/fent/","word":"faint"},{"phonetic_uk":"/feə(r)/","example":"a horse fair 马市","word":"fair","translation":"n. 集市","phonetic_us":"/fɛr/"},{"example":"The house had a fairly large garden. 那幢房子有个不小的花园。","phonetic_uk":"/'feəlɪ/","translation":"adv. 相当；公平地","phonetic_us":"/'fɛrli/","word":"fairly"},{"translation":"n.  小精灵， 小仙子","phonetic_us":"/'fɛri/","word":"fairy","example":"In his dream, he became a fairy. 在梦中，他变成了一个小精灵。","phonetic_uk":"/'feəri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/feɪθ/","example":"People have lost faith in the government. 人们已失去了对政府的信心。","word":"faith","translation":"n. 信任","phonetic_us":"/feθ/"},{"example":"a faithful friend 忠诚的朋友","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪθfʊl; -f(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 忠诚的；如实的","phonetic_us":"/'feθfəl/","word":"faithful"},{"example":"The tree was about to fall. 那棵树快要倒下了。","phonetic_uk":"/fɔːl/","phonetic_us":"/fɔl/","translation":"v. 落下；跌倒；陷落","word":"fall"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɔːls; fɒls/","example":"...a set of false teeth. …一副假牙。","phonetic_us":"/fɔls/","translation":"adj. 不真实的；伪造的","word":"FALSE"},{"example":"He claims he is not really interested in fame. 他称自己对出名真的没有兴趣。","phonetic_uk":"/feɪm/","phonetic_us":"/fem/","translation":"n. 名声，名望","word":"fame"},{"phonetic_us":"/fə'mɪljɚ/","translation":"adj. 熟悉的","word":"familiar","example":"a familiar tune 熟悉的曲调","phonetic_uk":"/fəˈmɪliə(r)/"},{"example":"Do you know the family next door? 你认识隔壁那家人吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'fæmɪlɪ; -m(ə)l-/","word":"family","translation":"n. 家，家庭；家族","phonetic_us":"/'fæməli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fæmɪn/","example":"the great potato famine in Ireland 爱尔兰严重的土豆荒","translation":"n. 饥荒；严重的缺乏","phonetic_us":"/'fæmɪn/","word":"famine"},{"phonetic_us":"/'feməs/","translation":"adj. 著名的，出名的","word":"famous","example":"a famous actor 著名演员","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪməs/"},{"example":"Groups of football fans began heading towards the ground. 成群结队的球迷开始向球场走去。","phonetic_uk":"/fæn/","word":"fan","translation":"n. (运动等)狂热爱好者","phonetic_us":"/fæn/"},{"example":"Harry took me to a fancy restaurant for our anniversary. 哈里带我去了一家豪华餐厅，庆祝我们的结婚纪念日。","phonetic_uk":"/'fænsɪ/","translation":"adj. 华丽的，别致的","phonetic_us":"/'fænsi/","word":"fancy"},{"example":"I fantasized about writing music. 我曾幻想作曲。","phonetic_uk":"/'fæntəsaɪz/","phonetic_us":"/'fæntəsaɪz/","translation":"v. 想象，幻想","word":"fantasize"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fæn'tæstɪk/","example":"You look fantastic! 你看上去棒极了！","word":"fantastic","translation":"adj.  极好的， 极出色的， 了不起的； 极大的； 难以相信的； 异想天开的， 不实际的； 奇异的， 古怪的","phonetic_us":"/fæn'tæstɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fæntəsi/","example":"I used to have fantasies about living in Paris with an artist. 我过去常幻想着在巴黎与一位艺术家同住。","phonetic_us":"/'fæntəsi/","translation":"n.  想象， 幻想； 想象的产物","word":"fantasy"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɑː/","example":"We can walk to my house from here. It isn’t far. 我们可以从这里步行去我家，不远。","translation":"adj. 远的；adv. 远，遥远","phonetic_us":"/fɑr/","word":"far"},{"phonetic_uk":"/feə/","example":"He could barely afford the fare. 他几乎付不起车费。","word":"fare","translation":"n. 车费，船费，票价","phonetic_us":"/fɛr/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/feə'wel/","example":"40 of her colleagues gathered for her farewell presentation. 40位同事来参加了她的欢送会。","word":"farewell","phonetic_us":"/,fɛr'wɛl/","translation":"int. 再会；n. 告别"},{"translation":"n. 农场，农庄；饲养场","phonetic_us":"/fɑrm/","word":"farm","example":"a 300-hectare farm 一座300公顷的农场","phonetic_uk":"/fɑːm/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɑːmə/","example":"","word":"farmer","phonetic_us":"/'fɑmɚ/","translation":"n. 农民，农夫；农场主"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fɑrðɚ/","translation":"adv. 更远地；adj. 更远的","word":"farther","phonetic_uk":"/'fɑːðə/","example":"We decided not to go any farther. 我们决定不再往前走了。"},{"word":"fascinate","translation":"v. 强烈地吸引，迷住","phonetic_us":"/'fæsə'net/","example":"The idea of travelling through time fascinates me. 穿越时光的想法深深吸引着我。","phonetic_uk":"/'fæsineit/"},{"example":"a fascinating book 一本引人入胜的书","phonetic_uk":"/'fæsɪneɪtɪŋ/","word":"fascinating","phonetic_us":"/'fæsɪnetɪŋ/","translation":"adj.  迷人的， 有极大吸引力的"},{"translation":"n. 魅力；入迷","phonetic_us":"/,fæsɪ'neʃən/","word":"fascination","example":"The fascination lay in the mystery of what was inside the box. 吸引力就在于这神秘感——不知道盒子里是什么东西。","phonetic_uk":"/,fæsɪ'neɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fæʃ(ə)n/","example":"Please leave the building in an orderly fashion. 请大家有秩序地离开大楼。","translation":"n. 样子，方式；风尚","phonetic_us":"/'fæʃən/","word":"fashion"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fæʃnəbl/","translation":"adj. 流行的，时髦的","word":"fashionable","example":"Strong colours are very fashionable at the moment. 眼下流行艳丽的色彩。","phonetic_uk":"/'fæʃ(ə)nəb(ə)l/"},{"word":"fast","phonetic_us":"/fæst/","translation":"adj. 快的；偏快的；adv. 快","phonetic_uk":"/fɑːst/","example":"a fast car 速度很快的汽车"},{"translation":"v. 扎牢，扣住","phonetic_us":"/'fæsən/","word":"fasten","phonetic_uk":"/'fɑːs(ə)n/","example":"Make sure all the windows are securely fastened before you leave. 离开前要确保所有的窗子都已关严。"},{"translation":"adj. 致命的，攸关的","phonetic_us":"/'fetl/","word":"fatal","example":"potentially fatal diseases 潜在致命的疾病","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪtl/"},{"example":"I wouldn’t wish such a fate on my worst enemy. 就算是我不共戴天的仇敌，我也不希望他遭遇这样的命运。","phonetic_uk":"/feɪt/","word":"fate","phonetic_us":"/fet/","translation":"n. 命运"},{"translation":"n. 父亲；神父；创始人","phonetic_us":"/'fɑðɚ/","word":"father","phonetic_uk":"/'fɑːðə/","example":"Ask your father to help you. 叫你父亲帮你。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fə'ti:ɡ/","example":"{\"COLLOINEXA\":[\"metal fatigue\"]} 金属疲劳","translation":"n. 疲劳，疲乏","phonetic_us":"/fə'tig/","word":"fatigue"},{"word":"fault","translation":"n. 缺点；过失；故障","phonetic_us":"/fɔlt/","phonetic_uk":"/fɔːlt; fɒlt/","example":"His worst fault is his arrogance. 他最大的缺点是傲慢。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fɔlti/","translation":"adj. 有错误的，有缺点的","word":"faulty","example":"Customers may ask for a refund if the goods are faulty. 商品有问题的话，顾客可以要求退货。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːltɪ; 'fɒltɪ/"},{"translation":"v. 偏好, 赞同","phonetic_us":"/'fevɚ/","word":"favor","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪvə/","example":""},{"word":"favorable","phonetic_us":"/'fevərəbl/","translation":"adj. 赞同的","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪvərəbl/","example":""},{"word":"favour","translation":"n. 好感；赞同；恩惠","phonetic_us":"/ˈfevɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'feɪvə/","example":"Could you do me a favour and tell Kelly I can’t make it? 你帮个忙告诉凯莉说我来不了好吗？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'feɪv(ə)rəb(ə)l/","example":"favourable film reviews 正面的影评","word":"favourable","translation":"adj. 有利的；赞成的","phonetic_us":"/'feivərəbl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'feɪv(ə)rɪt/","example":"a child’s favourite toy 孩子最喜欢的玩具","phonetic_us":"/'fevərɪt/","translation":"adj. 特别受喜爱的","word":"favourite"},{"example":"I was sitting on the floor shivering with fear because a bullet had been fired through a window. 我坐在地板上吓得浑身发抖，因为有一颗子弹射穿窗户打了进来。","phonetic_uk":"/fɪə/","translation":"n. 害怕；担心；v. 害怕","phonetic_us":"/fɪr/","word":"fear"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fɪrfəl/","translation":"adj. 害怕的，可怕的","word":"fearful","example":"a shy and fearful child 一个羞涩、胆怯的小孩","phonetic_uk":"/'fɪəfʊl; -f(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fi:zəbl/","example":"a feasible solution 可行的解决方法","word":"feasible","translation":"adj. 可行的；可能的；可用的","phonetic_us":"/'fizəbl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fiːst/","example":"a wedding feast 婚筵","word":"feast","phonetic_us":"/fist/","translation":"n. 盛宴，筵席；节日"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fɛðɚ/","translation":"n. 羽毛；翎毛；羽状物","word":"feather","example":"an ostrich feather 一根鸵鸟羽毛","phonetic_uk":"/'feðə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fiːtʃə/","example":"Air bags are a standard feature in most new cars. 气囊是大多数新车的标准配置。","translation":"n. 特点","phonetic_us":"/'fitʃɚ/","word":"feature"},{"example":"He joined the Army in February 1943. 他1943年2月参军。","phonetic_uk":"/'febrʊərɪ; 'febjʊərɪ/","word":"February","translation":"n. 二月","phonetic_us":"/'fɛbrʊ'ɛri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fed(ə)r(ə)l/","example":"Switzerland is a federal republic. 瑞士是一个联邦共和国。","word":"federal","translation":"adj. 联邦的；联盟的","phonetic_us":"/'fɛdərəl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fiː/","example":"You can use the gym and pool for a fee of £35 a month. 月付35英镑，即可使用健身房和游泳池。","phonetic_us":"/fi/","translation":"n. 费，酬金；赏金","word":"fee"},{"word":"feeble","phonetic_us":"/'fibl/","translation":"adj. 虚弱的；微弱的","phonetic_uk":"/'fiːb(ə)l/","example":"His voice sounded feeble and far away. 他的声音听上去既无力又遥远。"},{"word":"feed","phonetic_us":"/fid/","translation":"v. 喂(养)；v. 吃饲料","phonetic_uk":"/fiːd/","example":"Have you fed the cat? 你喂猫了吗？"},{"example":"How can I provide feedback without making someone angry? 我怎样才能提出反馈意见又不会得罪人呢？","phonetic_uk":"/ˈfi:dbæk/","word":"feedback","phonetic_us":"/'fidbæk/","translation":"n. 反馈"},{"translation":"v. 有知觉；v. 触，摸","phonetic_us":"/fiːl/","word":"feel","phonetic_uk":"/fiːl/","example":"I am feeling very depressed. 我感到很沮丧。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fiːlɪŋ/","example":"Knowing we’d won was a wonderful feeling. 得知我们赢了，感觉真好。","translation":"n. 感情；感觉，知觉","phonetic_us":"/'filɪŋ/","word":"feeling"},{"example":"Paul’s an easy-going sort of fellow. 保罗人很随和。","phonetic_uk":"/'feləʊ/","translation":"n. 人，家伙；伙伴","phonetic_us":"/'fɛlo/","word":"fellow"},{"word":"female","translation":"n. 雌性的动物；女子","phonetic_us":"/'fimel/","example":"As a group, females performed better on the test than males. 整体来说，女性在这次测试中胜过男性。","phonetic_uk":"/'fiːmeɪl/"},{"example":"Villagers say the fence would restrict public access to the hills. 村民们说栅栏将限制公众进入山区。","phonetic_uk":"/fens/","word":"fence","translation":"n. 栅栏","phonetic_us":"/fɛns/"},{"example":"800 acres of fertile cropland 800英亩的肥沃耕地","phonetic_uk":"/'fɜːtaɪl/","translation":"adj. 肥沃的；多产的","phonetic_us":"/ˈfɝtəl; (canadian) ˈfɝˌtaɪl/","word":"fertile"},{"translation":"n. 肥料","phonetic_us":"/'fɝtəlaɪzɚ/","word":"fertilizer","example":"...farming without any purchased chemical, fertilizer or pesticide. …不使用任何购买的化学品、肥料或杀虫剂的耕作。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɜːtɪlaɪzə/"},{"word":"festival","translation":"n. 节日；音乐节","phonetic_us":"/ˈfɛstəvəl/","phonetic_uk":"/'festɪv(ə)l/","example":"Christmas is one of the main festivals in the Christian Calendar. 圣诞节是基督教历的重大节日之一。"},{"word":"fetch","phonetic_us":"/fɛtʃ/","translation":"v. 取回","example":"Sylvia fetched a towel from the bathroom. 西尔维娅从浴室拿来一条毛巾。","phonetic_uk":"/fetʃ/"},{"translation":"n. 发热，发烧；狂热","phonetic_us":"/'fivɚ/","word":"fever","phonetic_uk":"/'fiːvə/","example":"Andy has a fever and won’t be coming into work today. 安迪发烧了，今天不来上班。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fjuː/","example":"...spending her few waking hours in front of the TV. …把她清醒的个把钟头花在电视机前。","word":"few","phonetic_us":"/fju/","translation":"adj. 很少的；少数的"},{"translation":"n. 纤维，纤维质","phonetic_us":"/'faibə/","word":"fibre","example":"Fruit and vegetables are high in fibre content . 水果和蔬菜的纤维素含量很高。","phonetic_uk":"/'faɪbə/"},{"translation":"n. 小说，虚构的文学作品","phonetic_us":"/'fɪkʃən/","word":"fiction","phonetic_uk":"/ˈfɪkʃn/","example":"romantic fiction 爱情小说"},{"example":"a view of green fields and rolling hills 田野青翠、丘陵起伏的景色","phonetic_uk":"/fiːld/","word":"field","translation":"n. 田野；田；运动场","phonetic_us":"/fild/"},{"word":"fierce","phonetic_us":"/fɪrs/","translation":"adj. 凶猛的，狂热的","example":"fierce fighting in the city 城里的激烈战斗","phonetic_uk":"/fɪəs/"},{"example":"a coastal village fifteen miles south of Tourane 土伦以南15英里的一个滨海村落","phonetic_uk":"/fɪf'tiːn; 'fɪftiːn/","phonetic_us":"/,fɪf'tin/","translation":"num. 十五；十五个","word":"fifteen"},{"word":"fifth","phonetic_us":"/fɪfθ/","translation":"num. 第五；n. 五分之一","example":"a fifth of bourbon 五分之一加仑的波旁威士忌酒","phonetic_uk":"/fɪfθ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɪftɪ/","example":"Standards of living rose in the fifties. 50年代生活水平提高了。","word":"fifty","translation":"num. 五十，五十个","phonetic_us":"/'fɪfti/"},{"translation":"v. 打(仗)；斗争","phonetic_us":"/faɪt/","word":"fight","example":"Neither country is capable of fighting a long war . 两个国家都没有能力打持久战。","phonetic_uk":"/faɪt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fɪɡjɚ/","translation":"n. 人物；数字","word":"figure","example":"Government figures underestimate the problem. 政府的数据对这一问题反映不足。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈfiɡə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/faɪl/","example":"We will keep your details on file (= store them for later use ) . 我们将把你的详细资料存档。","word":"file","translation":"n. 档案；v. 把…归档","phonetic_us":"/faɪl/"},{"example":"He poured her a drink, then filled his own glass. 他给她倒了一杯，然后将自己的杯子斟满。","phonetic_uk":"/fɪl/","translation":"v. 装满，盛满；占满","phonetic_us":"/fɪl/","word":"fill"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɪlm/","example":"Have you seen any good films recently? 你最近看过什么好的影片吗？","phonetic_us":"/fɪlm/","translation":"n. 影片；胶卷；薄层","word":"film"},{"example":"The water in the tank is constantly filtered. 鱼缸里的水在不停地被过滤。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɪltə/","word":"filter","phonetic_us":"/'fɪltɚ/","translation":"v. 过滤；n. 滤纸"},{"word":"final","phonetic_us":"/'faɪnl/","translation":"adj. 最后的；决定性的","example":"The final episode will be shown tonight. 最后一集将于今晚播出。","phonetic_uk":"/'faɪn(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'faɪnəli/","translation":"adv. 最后；不可更改的","word":"finally","phonetic_uk":"/'faɪnəlɪ/","example":"After several delays we finally took off at six o’clock. 几经耽搁后，我们终于在六点起飞了。"},{"example":"leasing and other forms of business finance 租赁及其他商业金融形式","phonetic_uk":"/faɪ'næns/","phonetic_us":"/'faɪnæns/","translation":"n. 财政；v. 筹集资金","word":"finance"},{"word":"financial","phonetic_us":"/faɪ'nænʃl/","translation":"adj. 财政的，经济的","example":"financial transactions 财务往来","phonetic_uk":"/faɪ'nænʃəl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/faɪnd/","example":"I can’t find the car keys. 我找不到汽车钥匙。","word":"find","translation":"v. 找到；发觉；找出","phonetic_us":"/faɪnd/"},{"word":"finding","translation":"n. 发现；调查的结果","phonetic_us":"/'faɪndɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/'faɪndɪŋ/","example":"Surveys conducted in other countries reported similar findings. 在其他国家进行的调查也报告说有类似的结果。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/faɪn/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/faɪn/","translation":"v. 罚款","word":"fine"},{"example":"The woman had a ring on her finger, so I assumed she was married. 那女人手指上戴着戒指，因此我猜想她已经结婚了。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɪŋgə/","word":"finger","translation":"n. 手指；指状物","phonetic_us":"/'fɪŋɡɚ/"},{"example":"You can’t go anywhere until you’ve finished your homework. 没完成家庭作业前你哪儿也不能去。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɪnɪʃ/","word":"finish","translation":"v. 完成，结束；n. 结束","phonetic_us":"/'fɪnɪʃ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/faɪr/","translation":"n. 火；火灾；v. 开火","word":"fire","example":"The warehouse was completely destroyed by fire. 仓库全给烧毁了。","phonetic_uk":"/'faɪə/"},{"word":"fireman","translation":"n. 消防队员；司炉工","phonetic_us":"/'faɪrmən/","example":"Would you like to be a fireman? 你愿意是一名消防队员吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'faɪəmən/"},{"word":"firm","phonetic_us":"/fɝm/","translation":"n. 商行，商号，公司","example":"The firm's employees were expecting large bonuses. 这家公司的雇员们正期待着大笔的奖金。","phonetic_uk":"/fɜːm/"},{"phonetic_us":"/fɝst/","translation":"num. 第一；adv. 最初","word":"first","example":"These results are firsts in the history of women’s athletics. 这些成绩在女运动员历史上是第一次。","phonetic_uk":"/fɜːst/"},{"example":"Over 1,500 different species of fish inhabit the waters around the reef. 那片礁石周围的水域生活着1,500多种不同的鱼类。","phonetic_uk":"/fɪʃ/","translation":"n. 鱼，鱼肉；v. 钓鱼","phonetic_us":"/fɪʃ/","word":"fish"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɪʃəmən/","example":"The Algarve is a paradise for fishermen whether river anglers or deep-sea fishermen. 阿尔加维对河边的垂钓者或深海的渔民都是一个天堂。","word":"fisherman","translation":"n. 渔民，渔夫，打鱼人","phonetic_us":"/'fɪʃɚmən/"},{"word":"fist","translation":"n. 拳(头)","phonetic_us":"/fɪst/","phonetic_uk":"/fɪst/","example":"She held the money tightly in her fist. 她把钱紧紧地攥在手中。"},{"word":"fit","phonetic_us":"/fɪt/","translation":"v. 适合；安装；v. 适合","example":"The sash, kimono, and other garments were made to fit a child. 这些腰带、和服和其他衣服都做得适合孩子穿。","phonetic_uk":"/fɪt/"},{"example":"an exercise programme to improve your fitness 增进健康的锻炼计划","phonetic_uk":"/ˈfɪtnəs/","phonetic_us":"/ˈfɪtnɪs/","translation":"n. 健康","word":"fitness"},{"phonetic_uk":"/faɪv/","example":"There is also a golf course five miles away. 五英里外还有个高尔夫球场。","translation":"num. 五，五个，第五","phonetic_us":"/faɪv/","word":"five"},{"translation":"v. 使固定；决定","phonetic_us":"/fɪks/","word":"fix","phonetic_uk":"/fɪks/","example":"He's going to fix a time when I can see him. 他将确定一个我可以见他的时间。"},{"example":"Children waving flags greeted the Russian leader. 孩子们挥舞着旗帜，欢迎俄罗斯领导人。","phonetic_uk":"/flæg/","translation":"n. 旗，旗帜；旗舰旗","phonetic_us":"/flæg/","word":"flag"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fleɪm/","example":"Flames poured out of the windows of the building. 火焰从大楼窗口冒出来。","translation":"n. 火焰；光辉；热情","phonetic_us":"/flem/","word":"flame"},{"example":"One possibility is that the blast was like an ultra-powerful solar flare. 一种可能的原因是这种爆炸很像有超级能量的太阳耀斑。","phonetic_uk":"/fleə/","word":"flare","phonetic_us":"/flɛr/","translation":"v. 闪耀；v. 使闪亮"},{"phonetic_us":"/flæʃ/","translation":"n. 闪光；v. 闪，闪烁","word":"flash","example":"Two flashes mean danger. 两次闪光表示危险。","phonetic_uk":"/flæʃ/"},{"example":"houses with flat roofs 平顶房","phonetic_uk":"/flæt/","translation":"adj. 平的，扁平的","phonetic_us":"/flæt/","word":"flat"},{"translation":"n. 味，味道；风味","phonetic_us":"/'fleivə/","word":"flavour","example":"Which flavour do you want - chocolate or vanilla? 你要哪种味道的，巧克力还是香草？","phonetic_uk":"/'fleɪvə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/flɔ/","translation":"n. 缺点，错误","word":"flaw","phonetic_uk":"/flɔː/","example":"A design flaw (= a mistake or weakness in the way something was made ) caused the engine to explode. 一个设计缺陷导致了引擎爆炸。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fliː/","example":"His attackers turned and fled. 袭击他的人转身逃走了。","word":"flee","phonetic_us":"/fli/","translation":"v.  逃走， 逃掉， 逃离； 避开， 逃避"},{"word":"fleet","phonetic_us":"/flit/","translation":"n. 舰队；船队，机群","phonetic_uk":"/fliːt/","example":"the US seventh fleet 美国第七舰队"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fleʃ/","example":"a freshwater fish with firm white flesh 一种肉色雪白、肉质紧实的淡水鱼","phonetic_us":"/flɛʃ/","translation":"n. 肉，肌肉；肉体","word":"flesh"},{"translation":"n. 灵活性；适应性","phonetic_us":"/,flɛksə'bɪləti/","word":"flexibility","phonetic_uk":"/,fleksɪ'bɪlɪtɪ/","example":"Employees expect flexibility in the workplace. 员工们盼望工作安排有弹性。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈfleksəbl/","example":"We can be flexible about your starting date. 你具体从哪天开始，我们可以灵活一点。","phonetic_us":"/'flɛksəbl/","translation":"adj. 灵活的","word":"flexible"},{"example":"He immediately booked a flight to Toulouse. 他当即就订了去图卢兹的航班。","phonetic_uk":"/flaɪt/","translation":"n. 航班；飞行；逃跑","phonetic_us":"/flaɪt/","word":"flight"},{"example":"I looked up at the clouds floating in the sky. 我仰望着天上的浮云。","phonetic_uk":"/fləʊt/","phonetic_us":"/flot/","translation":"v. 漂浮；v. 使漂浮","word":"float"},{"word":"flock","translation":"n. 羊群，群；大量","phonetic_us":"/flɑk/","phonetic_uk":"/flɒk/","example":"They kept a small flock of sheep. 他们养了一小群绵羊。"},{"example":"The village was cut off by floods. 那个村子因洪水而与外界中断了联系。","phonetic_uk":"/flʌd/","word":"flood","phonetic_us":"/flʌd/","translation":"n. 洪水；v. 淹没"},{"translation":"n. 地板；楼层","phonetic_us":"/flɔr/","word":"floor","phonetic_uk":"/flɔː/","example":"a polished wooden floor 上过蜡的木地板"},{"translation":"n. 面粉，粉；粉状物质","phonetic_us":"/'flaʊɚ/","word":"flour","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'flaʊə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈflɜːrɪʃ/","translation":"v. 繁荣，茂盛，兴旺","word":"flourish","example":"The economy is booming and small businesses are flourishing. 经济繁荣，小企业蒸蒸日上。","phonetic_uk":"/'flʌrɪʃ/"},{"example":"a new road system to improve traffic flow through the city centre 疏导市中心车流的新道路系统","phonetic_uk":"/fləʊ/","word":"flow","translation":"n&v. 流动","phonetic_us":"/flo/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'flaʊə/","example":"a lovely rose bush with delicate pink flowers 一簇开着娇嫩的粉红色花朵的美丽蔷薇","phonetic_us":"/'flaʊɚ/","translation":"n. 花，花卉；开花","word":"flower"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fluː/","example":"Steven’s still in bed with flu . 史蒂文患了流感，仍卧病在床。","translation":"n. 流行性感冒","phonetic_us":"/flu/","word":"flu"},{"word":"fluent","phonetic_us":"/'fluənt/","translation":"adj. 流利的，流畅的","example":"He spoke in fluent Italian. 他用流利的意大利语讲话。","phonetic_uk":"/'fluːənt/"},{"example":"He is not allowed solid food yet, only fluids. 他还不能吃固体食物，只能进流食。","phonetic_uk":"/'fluːɪd/","word":"fluid","phonetic_us":"/'fluɪd/","translation":"n. 流体，液体"},{"phonetic_uk":"/flʌʃ/","example":"Susan flushed deeply and looked away. 苏珊脸涨得通红，目光转向别处。","word":"flush","translation":"v. 奔流；(脸)发红","phonetic_us":"/flʌʃ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/flaɪ/","example":"There were flies buzzing all around us. 苍蝇嗡嗡地在我们周围飞来飞去。","translation":"n. 蝇，苍蝇；v. 飞行","phonetic_us":"/flaɪ/","word":"fly"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fəʊkəs/","example":"His eyes were focussed straight ahead. 他的双眼盯着正前方。","translation":"v. 聚焦，注视；n. 焦点","phonetic_us":"/'fokəs/","word":"focus"},{"word":"fog","translation":"n. 雾；烟雾，尘雾","phonetic_us":"/fɔɡ/","example":"It will be a cold night, and there may be fog patches . 今夜天气寒冷，部分地区可能有雾。","phonetic_uk":"/fɒg/"},{"word":"fold","phonetic_us":"/fold/","translation":"v. 折叠；合拢；n. 褶","phonetic_uk":"/fəʊld/","example":"Fold the paper along the dotted line. 沿虚线将纸折起来。"},{"phonetic_us":"/fok/","translation":"n. 人们，家属，亲属","word":"folk","phonetic_uk":"/fəʊk/","example":"I’m sure there are some folk who would rather they weren’t here. 我敢肯定有些人宁愿自己不在这里。"},{"word":"follow","translation":"v. 跟随；结果是","phonetic_us":"/'fɑlo/","example":"Are those men following us? 那些人在跟着我们吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'fɒləʊ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɒləʊɪŋ/","example":"Write down the following information: name of product, type, date purchased and price. 写下以下信息：产品名称、型号、购买日期和价格。","phonetic_us":"/'fɑloɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 接着的；下列的","word":"following"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɒnd/","example":"I am very fond of Michael. 我很喜欢迈克尔。","translation":"adj. 喜爱的；溺爱的","phonetic_us":"/fɑnd/","word":"fond"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fuːd/","example":"The restaurant serves good food at affordable prices. 那家餐厅物美价廉。","word":"food","phonetic_us":"/fud/","translation":"n. 食物，食品，养料"},{"word":"fool","phonetic_us":"/ful/","translation":"n. 蠢人，傻子；v. 欺骗","example":"What a fool she had been to think that he would stay. 她竟然那么傻，以为他会留下来。","phonetic_uk":"/fuːl/"},{"example":"I’ve never heard anything so foolish in all my life. 我这辈子从没听到过这么愚蠢的话。","phonetic_uk":"/'fuːlɪʃ/","word":"foolish","translation":"adj. 愚蠢的；鲁莽的","phonetic_us":"/'fulɪʃ/"},{"word":"foot","translation":"n. 脚；最下部；英尺","phonetic_us":"/fʊt/","phonetic_uk":"/fʊt/","example":"My foot hurts. 我脚痛。"},{"word":"football","phonetic_us":"/'fʊtbɔl/","translation":"n. 足球比赛；足球","example":"Which football team do you support? 你支持哪个球队？","phonetic_uk":"/'fʊtbɔːl/"},{"word":"foothold","phonetic_us":"/'fʊt'hold/","translation":"n. 立足处（攀登时脚踩的地方）","phonetic_uk":"/ˈfʊthəʊld/","example":"Businesses are investing millions of dollars to gain a foothold in this new market. 商家们正投资数百万美元以求在新市场中赢得立足点。"},{"example":"He heard someone’s footsteps in the hall. 他听见门厅里有脚步声。","phonetic_uk":"/'fʊtstep/","word":"footstep","translation":"n. 脚步；脚步声；足迹","phonetic_us":"/'fʊtstɛp/"},{"example":"I’ve got a present for you. 我有件礼物送给你。","phonetic_uk":"/fə(r); strong form fɔ:(r)/","word":"for","translation":"prep. 为；给；因为","phonetic_us":"/fɚ; strong form fɔr/"},{"word":"forbid","phonetic_us":"/fɚ'bɪd/","translation":"v. 禁止，不许；阻止","example":"Lack of space forbids listing the names of all those who contributed. 由于篇幅限制，无法列出所有捐款人的姓名。","phonetic_uk":"/fə'bɪd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɔːs/","example":"Due to the high cost of borrowing, many companies have been forced to close. 由于借贷成本高，许多公司被迫关门。","word":"force","phonetic_us":"/fɔrs/","translation":"v. 强迫；n. 力，力量"},{"word":"forecast","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrkæst/","translation":"n. 预测，预报；v. 预示","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːkɑːst/","example":"The weather forecast is good for tomorrow. 天气预报说明天是晴天。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːfɪŋgə/","example":"He took the pen between his thumb and forefinger. 他用拇指和食指夹起笔。","translation":"n. 食指","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrfɪŋɡɚ/","word":"forefinger"},{"translation":"n. 额头，前部","phonetic_us":"/'fɔr'hɛd/","word":"forehead","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːhed; 'fɒrɪd/","example":"...the lines on her forehead. …她前额上的皱纹。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɒrɪn/","example":"foreign students 外国学生","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrən/","translation":"adj. 外国的；外来的","word":"foreign"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɒrɪnə/","example":"Some of the local people are suspicious of foreigners. 有些当地人不信任外国人。","word":"foreigner","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrənɚ/","translation":"n. 外国人"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːməʊst/","example":"Economic concerns are foremost on many voters’ minds. 经济是许多选民关心的首要问题。","phonetic_us":"/'fɔr'most/","translation":"adj. 最初的；第一流的","word":"foremost"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɔː'siːəbl/","example":"The situation is likely to continue for the foreseeable future. 这种局面在可预见的将来可能还会持续下去。","translation":"adj. 可以预见的","phonetic_us":"/fɔr'siəbl/","word":"foreseeable"},{"example":"a tropical forest 热带森林","phonetic_uk":"/'fɒrɪst/","word":"forest","translation":"n. 森林；森林地带","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrɪst/"},{"phonetic_us":"/fɚ'ɛvɚ/","translation":"adv. 永远，总是，老是","word":"forever","example":"I wanted that moment to last forever . 我希望那一刻成为永远。","phonetic_uk":"/fə'revə/"},{"example":"Someone stole my credit card and forged my signature. 有人偷了我的信用卡，并假冒我的签名。","phonetic_uk":"/fɔːdʒ/","word":"forge","translation":"vt.  打制， 锻造； 伪造","phonetic_us":"/fɔrdʒ/"},{"word":"forget","phonetic_us":"/fɚ'ɡɛt/","translation":"v. 忘记，遗忘","phonetic_uk":"/fə'get/","example":"I’m sorry, I’ve forgotten your name. 对不起，我忘记你的名字了。"},{"example":"He didn’t look the sort of man to forgive and forget (= forgive someone and no longer think about it ) . 他看上去不是那种不记仇的人。","phonetic_uk":"/fə'gɪv/","translation":"v. 原谅，饶恕，宽恕","phonetic_us":"/fɚ'ɡɪv/","word":"forgive"},{"translation":"n. 餐叉；叉；分叉","phonetic_us":"/fɔrk/","word":"fork","phonetic_uk":"/fɔːk/","example":"Put the knives and forks on the table. 把刀叉摆放在桌子上。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɔːm/","example":"We oppose racism in all its forms. 我们反对各种形式的种族主义。","word":"form","phonetic_us":"/fɔrm/","translation":"n. 形式；形状；v. 形成"},{"example":"formal recognition of the reformed church 改革后的教会所获得的官方承认","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːm(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 正式的；礼仪上的","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrml/","word":"formal"},{"word":"format","translation":"n. 设计，安排；格式，样式，版式；vt.  使格式化","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrmæt/","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːmæt/","example":"The courses were run to a consistent format. 这些课程的编排是有连续性的。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɔː'meɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"We now know a lot more about the early stages of planetary formation. 我们现在对行星形成过程的早期阶段有了更多的了解。","word":"formation","translation":"n. 形成；构成；形成物","phonetic_us":"/fɔr'meʃən/"},{"example":"the former Soviet Union 前苏联","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːmə/","word":"former","translation":"adj. 在前的；n. 前者","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrmɚ/"},{"example":"the formula for calculating distance 计算距离的公式","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːmjʊlə/","translation":"n. 公式，式","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrmjələ/","word":"formula"},{"word":"formulate","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrmjə'let/","translation":"v. 规定，制定","example":"By visualizing where you want to be, you start helping your mind formulate ways to achieve that next goal in your life. 通过把你想达到的程度形象化，你就开始帮助自己的头脑制定目标——为了达到你生活中的下一个目标。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːmjʊleɪt/"},{"translation":"adv. 向前；向外，往外","phonetic_us":"/fɔrθ/","word":"forth","example":"The house was still burning, pouring forth thick black smoke. 房子仍在燃烧，冒出浓浓的黑烟。","phonetic_uk":"/fɔːθ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːtnaɪt/","example":"a fortnight’s holiday 十四天的假期","translation":"n. 两星期，十四天","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrtnaɪt/","word":"fortnight"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːtʃ(ə)nət/","example":"By a fortunate coincidence, a passer-by heard her cries for help. 所幸正巧有个过路人听到了她的呼救。","word":"fortunate","translation":"adj. 幸运的，侥幸的","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrtʃənət/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɔitʃənitli/","example":"Fortunately, everything worked out all right in the end. 幸运的是，最后一切顺利。","word":"fortunately","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrtʃənətli/","translation":"adv. 幸运地"},{"example":"I had the good fortune to work with a brilliant head of department. 我有幸与一位出色的部门主管共事。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːtʃuːn; -tʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 命运，运气；财产","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrtʃən/","word":"fortune"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːtɪ/","example":"The place was built as a casino in the forties. 这个地方建于20世纪40年代，起初是一座赌场。","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrti/","translation":"num. 四十，第四十","word":"forty"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fɔrəm/","translation":"n. 论坛","word":"forum","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːrəm/","example":"Members of the council agreed that was an important forum for discussion. 理事会成员们一致认为那是一个用于讨论的重要论坛。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːwəd/","example":"He leaned forward , his elbows resting on the table. 他身体前倾，胳膊肘撑在桌子上。","word":"forward","translation":"adv. 向前；今后，往后","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrwɚd/"},{"example":"Founded in 1935 in Ohio, Alcoholics Anonymous is now a world-wide organization. 嗜酒者互诫协会1935年创立于俄亥俄州，现在是一个世界性的组织。","phonetic_uk":"/faʊnd/","phonetic_us":"/faʊnd/","translation":"v. 创立，创办；建立","word":"found"},{"phonetic_uk":"/faun'deiʃən/","example":"It took the builders three weeks to lay the foundations . 建筑工人花了三星期的时间打地基。","word":"foundation","phonetic_us":"/faʊn'deʃən/","translation":"n. 地基；基础；基金会"},{"example":"He was a fountain of information on Asian affairs. 他是亚洲事务的信息源。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈfaʊntən/","phonetic_us":"/'faʊntn/","translation":"n. 泉水，喷泉；源泉","word":"fountain"},{"phonetic_us":"/fɔr/","translation":"num. 四，四个，第四","word":"four","example":"She is married with four children. 她已婚，有四个孩子。","phonetic_uk":"/fɔː/"},{"translation":"adv.  四倍， 四重；adj. 四倍的，四重的","phonetic_us":"/'fɔrfold/","word":"fourfold","phonetic_uk":"/'fɔːfəuld/","example":"Further down the supply chain, garlic prices have jumped tenfold on wholesale markets in big cities and fourfold nationwide. 沿供应链向下，其大城市批发价格跳升十倍，而全国售价则上升四倍。"},{"translation":"num. 十四，第十四","phonetic_us":"/,fɔr'tin/","word":"fourteen","example":"He used to work fourteen hours a day. 他过去一天工作14个小时。","phonetic_uk":"/fɔː'tiːn; 'fɔːtiːn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/fɔrθ/","translation":"num. 第四，四分之一","word":"fourth","phonetic_uk":"/fɔːθ/","example":"Then, we plot the different graphs so that they each take up one fourth of the screen. 然后，我们绘制不同的曲线图，从而它们可以每个图占据屏幕的四分之一。"},{"word":"fox","phonetic_us":"/fɑks/","translation":"n. 狐狸；狡猾的人","phonetic_uk":"/fɒks/","example":"He was a sly old fox. 他是个狡猾的老狐狸。"},{"word":"fraction","translation":"n. 小部分；片断；分数","phonetic_us":"/'frækʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/'frækʃ(ə)n/","example":""},{"example":"glass fragments 玻璃碎片","phonetic_uk":"/'frægm(ə)nt/","translation":"n. 碎片，破片，碎块","phonetic_us":"/'fræɡmənt/","word":"fragment"},{"phonetic_uk":"/freɪm/","example":"They removed the picture from its wooden frame. 他们把画从木镜框中取下来。","word":"frame","translation":"n. 框架","phonetic_us":"/frem/"},{"word":"framework","phonetic_us":"/'fremwɝk/","translation":"n. 框架，构架，结构","example":"We have to act within the existing legal framework. 我们必须在现行的法律框架下行事。","phonetic_uk":"/'freɪmwɜːk/"},{"translation":"n. 法国，法兰西","phonetic_us":"","word":"France","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/frɑːns/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fræŋk/","example":"To be perfectly frank, I think it’s a bad idea. 老实说，我认为这个主意不好。","phonetic_us":"/fræŋk/","translation":"adj. 坦白的，直率的","word":"frank"},{"translation":"adj. 自由的；空闲的","phonetic_us":"/fri/","word":"free","example":"He knew he could be free in as little as three years. 他知道只要再过三年他就能自由了。","phonetic_uk":"/friː/"},{"example":"People here like their freedom and privacy. 这里的人喜欢他们所拥有的自由与隐私权。","phonetic_uk":"/'friːdəm/","translation":"n. 自由；自主","phonetic_us":"/'fridəm/","word":"freedom"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'friːlɪ/","example":"the country’s first freely elected president 该国首位自由选举产生的总统","word":"freely","translation":"adv. 自由地；直率地","phonetic_us":"/'frili/"},{"word":"freeze","phonetic_us":"/friz/","translation":"v. 冻；结冻；v. 使结冰","example":"The lake had frozen overnight. 湖上一夜之间就结了冰。","phonetic_uk":"/friːz/"},{"example":"freight services 货运公司","phonetic_uk":"/freɪt/","phonetic_us":"/fret/","translation":"n. 货运；货物；运费","word":"freight"},{"word":"French","translation":"adj. 法国的；n. 法国人","phonetic_us":"","phonetic_uk":"/fren(t)ʃ/","example":"an excellent French wine 上等的法国葡萄酒"},{"example":"Side effects from prescribed drugs are being reported with increasing frequency (= more and more often ) . 处方药的副作用正越来越频繁地被报道出来。","phonetic_uk":"/'friːkw(ə)nsɪ/","word":"frequency","translation":"n. 屡次；次数；频率","phonetic_us":"/'frikwənsi/"},{"example":"Trains rushed past at frequent intervals . 火车频频驶过。","phonetic_uk":"/'friːkw(ə)nt/","translation":"adj. 时常发生的；经常的","phonetic_us":"/'frikwənt/","word":"frequent"},{"example":"He was frequently drunk. 他经常喝醉。","phonetic_uk":"/'friːkw(ə)ntlɪ/","word":"frequently","translation":"adv. 时常，常常","phonetic_us":"/'frikwəntli/"},{"example":"I’ll just make some fresh coffee. 我来重新煮点咖啡。","phonetic_uk":"/freʃ/","translation":"adj. 新的；新鲜的","phonetic_us":"/frɛʃ/","word":"fresh"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'frɪkʃ(ə)n/","example":"Putting oil on both surfaces reduces friction. 两面都上油可减小摩擦力。","word":"friction","translation":"n. 摩擦，摩擦力","phonetic_us":"/'frɪkʃən/"},{"example":"Diane won’t be here Friday. 星期五黛安娜不来这里。","phonetic_uk":"/'fraɪdeɪ; (occas.,) ˈfraɪdi/","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 星期五","word":"Friday"},{"phonetic_uk":"/frɪdʒ/","example":"Then all three of you sign the contract and post in on the fridge. 然后你们三个人要都在协议上签名，并把它贴在冰箱上。","phonetic_us":"/frɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 电冰箱","word":"fridge"},{"word":"friend","phonetic_us":"/frɛnd/","translation":"n. 朋友，友人","phonetic_uk":"/frend/","example":"Jerry, this is my friend Sue. 杰里，这是我的朋友休。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fren(d)lɪ/","example":"a friendly smile 亲切的微笑","word":"friendly","translation":"adj. 友好的，友谊的","phonetic_us":"/'frɛndli/"},{"translation":"n. 友谊，友好","phonetic_us":"/'frɛndʃɪp/","word":"friendship","phonetic_uk":"/'fren(d)ʃɪp/","example":"her close friendship with her aunt 她与姑母的亲密友谊"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fraɪtn/","example":"Don’t stand so near the edge! You’re frightening me. 别站得那么靠边！你要把我吓坏了。","word":"frighten","translation":"v. 使惊恐，使恐慌","phonetic_us":"/'fraɪtn/"},{"example":"The tadpole has become a frog. 这个蝌蚪已长成青蛙。","phonetic_uk":"/frɒg/","word":"frog","phonetic_us":"/frɔɡ/","translation":"n. 蛙"},{"word":"from","translation":"prep. 从…来；离开","phonetic_us":"","example":"","phonetic_uk":""},{"phonetic_us":"/frʌnt/","translation":"adj. 前面的；n. 前部","word":"front","example":"Two of his front teeth had been knocked out. 他有两颗门牙被打落了。","phonetic_uk":"/frʌnt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'frʌntɪə(r)/","example":"a novel about a family’s struggle on the American frontier 描写一家人在美国边远地区奋斗的小说","translation":"n. 边境","phonetic_us":"/frʌn'tɪr/","word":"frontier"},{"phonetic_us":"/frɔst/","translation":"n. 冰冻，严寒；霜","word":"frost","phonetic_uk":"/frɒst/","example":"the risk of frost damage to crops 庄稼遭受霜冻灾害的危险"},{"word":"frown","translation":"v. 皱眉","phonetic_us":"/fraʊn/","phonetic_uk":"/fraʊn/","example":"She frowned as she read the letter. 她看着信皱起了眉头。"},{"word":"fruit","phonetic_us":"/frut/","translation":"n. 水果；果实；成果","example":"Try to eat plenty of fresh fruit . 尽量多吃新鲜水果。","phonetic_uk":"/fruːt/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'fruːtfʊl; -f(ə)l/","word":"fruitful","translation":"adj. 多产的；肥沃的","phonetic_us":"/'frutfl/"},{"example":"The fact that he’s working with amateurs really frustrates him. 与生手共事着实让他沮丧。","phonetic_uk":"/frʌ'streɪt/","translation":"vt.  使沮丧， 使灰心； 挫败， 使受挫折","phonetic_us":"/'frʌstret/","word":"frustrate"},{"translation":"v. 油煎，油炸，油炒","phonetic_us":"/fraɪ/","word":"fry","example":"Fry the potatoes, covered, for about 20 minutes. 盖上盖，将马铃薯煎20分钟左右。","phonetic_uk":"/fraɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fjuəl/","translation":"n. 燃料；v. 给…加燃料","word":"fuel","phonetic_uk":"/fjʊəl/","example":"Coal is one of the cheapest fuels. 煤是最廉价的燃料之一。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ful'fil/","translation":"v. 履行；满足；完成","word":"fulfil","phonetic_uk":"/fʊl'fɪl/","example":"There is little doubt that the scheme fulfils a need for our community. 毫无疑问，这计划会满足我们社区的需求。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ful'fɪl/","word":"fulfill","translation":"vt.  履行， 实现， 完成； 满足， 使满意","phonetic_us":""},{"example":"The train was completely full. 火车坐得满满的。","phonetic_uk":"/fʊl/","phonetic_us":"/fʊl/","translation":"adj. 满的；完全的","word":"full"},{"word":"fun","phonetic_us":"/fʌn/","translation":"n. 乐趣，娱乐；玩笑","phonetic_uk":"/fʌn/","example":"There’s plenty of fun for all the family. 可以让全家人玩得很开心。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fʌŋkʃən/","example":"The nervous system regulates our bodily functions (= eating, breathing, going to the toilet etc ) . 神经系统控制着我们身体的功能。","phonetic_us":"/'fʌŋkʃən/","translation":"v & n. 功能，运行","word":"function"},{"phonetic_us":"/fʌnd/","translation":"n. 基金，储备；；v. 提供资金","word":"fund","phonetic_uk":"/fʌnd/","example":"The fund was set up to try to save the cathedral. 设立基金以挽救大教堂。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,fʌndə'mɛntl/","translation":"adj. 基础的，基本的","word":"fundamental","example":"We have to tackle the fundamental cause of the problem. 我们必须解决问题的根本原因。","phonetic_uk":"/fʌndə'ment(ə)l/"},{"translation":"adv. 根本上","phonetic_us":"/,fʌndə'mɛntəli/","word":"fundamentally","example":"The conclusions of the report are fundamentally wrong . 这份报告的结论从根本上来说就是错误的。","phonetic_uk":"/,fʌndə'mɛntəli/"},{"word":"funeral","phonetic_us":"/'fjunərəl/","translation":"n. 葬礼，丧礼，丧葬","phonetic_uk":"/'fjuːn(ə)r(ə)l/","example":"The funeral will be held at St. Martin’s Church. 葬礼将在圣马丁教堂举行。"},{"example":"the funniest man in Britain 英国最滑稽的男人","phonetic_uk":"/'fʌnɪ/","translation":"adj. 古怪的；滑稽的","phonetic_us":"/'fʌni/","word":"funny"},{"example":"a fur coat 裘皮大衣","phonetic_uk":"/fɜː/","translation":"n. 软毛；毛皮，裘皮","phonetic_us":"/fɝ/","word":"fur"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fjʊrɪəs/","translation":"adj. 狂怒的；狂暴的","word":"furious","phonetic_uk":"/'fjʊərɪəs/","example":"She was absolutely furious . 她怒不可遏。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'fɜːnɪs/","word":"furnace","phonetic_us":"/'fɝnɪs/","translation":"n. 炉子，熔炉；鼓风炉"},{"word":"furnish","translation":"v. 供应，提供；装备","phonetic_us":"/'fɝnɪʃ/","example":"Will these finds furnish more information on prehistoric man? 这些发现是否能提供更多有关史前人类的资料？","phonetic_uk":"/'fɜːnɪʃ/"},{"translation":"n. 家具；装置，设备","phonetic_us":"","word":"furniture","phonetic_uk":"","example":"I helped him choose the furniture for his house. 我帮他挑选房子里用的家具。"},{"example":"They walked a little further. 他们又往前走了一点。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɜːðə/","phonetic_us":"/'fɝðɚ/","translation":"adv. 更远地；adj. 更远的","word":"further"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɜːðə'mɔː/","example":"He is old and unpopular. Furthermore, he has at best only two years of political life ahead of him. 他年纪已老，又不得人心，而且他最多也只有两年的政治生命了。","phonetic_us":"/,fɝðɚ'mɔr/","translation":"adv. 而且，此外","word":"furthermore"},{"word":"fuss","phonetic_us":"/fʌs/","translation":"n. 大惊小怪","example":"James said he’d better be getting back or there’d be a fuss . 詹姆斯说他最好回来，否则就会有人小题大做了。","phonetic_uk":"/fʌs/"},{"example":"A lot of small children are fussy eaters (= they dislike many types of food ) . 许多小孩子挑食。","phonetic_uk":"/'fʌsɪ/","word":"fussy","phonetic_us":"/'fʌsi/","translation":"adj. 大惊小怪的，小题大做的"},{"example":"The islands should have the right to decide their own future. 这些岛屿应当有权决定自己的未来。","phonetic_uk":"/'fjuːtʃə/","translation":"n. 将来，未来；前途","phonetic_us":"/'fjʊtʃɚ/","word":"future"},{"phonetic_uk":"/geɪn/","example":"After gaining independence in 1957, it was renamed ‘Ghana’. 1957年获得独立后，该国改名为“加纳”。","word":"gain","translation":"v. 获得；增加；n. 增进","phonetic_us":"/ɡen/"},{"word":"gallery","phonetic_us":"/'gæləri/","translation":"n. 美术馆","example":"an exhibition of African art at the Hayward Gallery 海沃德美术馆的非洲艺术展览","phonetic_uk":"/ˈgæləri/"},{"example":"a 20 gallon fish tank 一个20加仑的鱼缸","phonetic_uk":"/'gælən/","word":"gallon","phonetic_us":"/'ɡælən/","translation":"n. 加仑"},{"translation":"n. 赌博","phonetic_us":"/'gæmblɪŋ/","word":"gambling","example":"The lottery is probably the most popular form of gambling. 彩票可能是最普遍的一种赌博形式。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɡæmblɪŋ/"},{"word":"game","phonetic_us":"/ɡem/","translation":"n. 游戏；比赛；猎物","example":"The boys were playing a game in the backyard. 男孩们在后院里玩游戏。","phonetic_uk":"/geɪm/"},{"word":"gang","phonetic_us":"/ɡæŋ/","translation":"n. 一帮，一伙","example":"Several gangs were operating in the area. 有好几个犯罪团伙在这个地区活动。","phonetic_uk":"/gæŋ/"},{"word":"gaol","translation":"vt. 监禁；n. 监狱","phonetic_us":"/dʒeɪl/","example":"Hundreds and thousands of africans are thrown into gaol each year under pass laws. 由于《通行证法》，每年有成千上万的南非黑人被关进监狱。","phonetic_uk":"/dʒeɪl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɡæp/","translation":"n. 差距;缝隙缺口","word":"gap","phonetic_uk":"/ɡæp/","example":"a gap in the traffic 车流中的一个空档"},{"word":"garage","phonetic_us":"/gəˈrɑʒ; gəˈrɑdʒ/","translation":"n. 车库","phonetic_uk":"/'gærɑː(d)ʒ/","example":"I’ll just go and put the car in the garage. 我把车停到车库去。"},{"example":"Can you take out the garbage when you go? 你走的时候把垃圾带出去好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'gɑːbɪdʒ/","phonetic_us":"/'ɡɑrbɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 垃圾，污物，废料","word":"garbage"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gɑːd(ə)n/","example":"He’s outside in the garden. 他在外面花园里。","phonetic_us":"/'ɡɑrdn/","translation":"n. 花园，菜园；公园","word":"garden"},{"word":"gardener","translation":"n. 园丁，花匠","phonetic_us":"/'gɑrdənɚ/","example":"She employed a gardener. 她雇了一个园丁。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɡɑːdənə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gɑːlɪk/","example":"Add a crushed clove of garlic (= single section of it ). 加一瓣压碎的大蒜。","phonetic_us":"/'ɡɑrlɪk/","translation":"n.  大蒜","word":"garlic"},{"phonetic_uk":"/gæs/","example":"hydrogen gas 氢气","word":"gas","phonetic_us":"/ɡæs/","translation":"n. 煤气；气体；汽油"},{"word":"gaseous","translation":"adj. 气体的，气态的","phonetic_us":"/'ɡæsɪəs/","phonetic_uk":"/'gæsɪəs; 'geɪsɪəs/","example":"Freon exists both in liquid and gaseous states. 氟利昂既有液态也有气态。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gæsəliːn/","example":"A gasoline engine drives the motorboat. 汽油引擎推动汽船。","word":"gasoline","translation":"n. (美)汽油","phonetic_us":"/'gæsəlin/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/gɑːsp/","example":"‘My leg!’ he gasped. ‘I think it’s broken!’ “我的腿！”他倒抽一口气喊道，“我觉得腿断了！”","phonetic_us":"/ɡæsp/","translation":"v. 气喘，喘息","word":"gasp"},{"example":"We went through the gate into the orchard. 我们穿过大门进了果园。","phonetic_uk":"/geɪt/","word":"gate","translation":"n. 大门；篱笆门","phonetic_us":"/ɡet/"},{"example":"A crowd gathered to watch the fight. 一群人聚拢来围观打架。","phonetic_uk":"/'gæðə/","word":"gather","translation":"v. 聚集；集合vt收集","phonetic_us":"/'ɡæðɚ/"},{"word":"gauge","translation":"v. 量，测量；n. 量器","phonetic_us":"/gedʒ/","phonetic_uk":"/geɪdʒ/","example":"The thermostat will gauge the temperature and control the heat. 恒温器可测量温度并控制热量。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/geɪ/","example":"gay colours 鲜艳的色彩","translation":"adj. 快乐的；鲜明的","phonetic_us":"/ɡe/","word":"gay"},{"example":"Patrick sat gazing into space  (= looking straight in front, not at any particular person or thing ). 帕特里克坐着，茫然地看着前方。","phonetic_uk":"/geɪz/","phonetic_us":"/ɡeɪz/","translation":"v. 凝视，盯，注视","word":"gaze"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɡɪr/","translation":"n. 齿轮；v. 使合适","word":"gear","phonetic_uk":"/ɡɪə(r)/","example":"When she put the car in gear it began to buck wildly. 当她把汽车搭上齿轮时，汽车便开始颠簸地行进。"},{"word":"gender","translation":"n. 性别","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛndɚ/","example":"people of the same gender 同性别的人","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒendə(r)/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dʒiːn/","example":"human genes 人类基因","translation":"n.  基因","phonetic_us":"/dʒin/","word":"gene"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dʒen(ə)r(ə)l/","example":"There has been a general decline in standards. 道德水准普遍下降。","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛnrəl/","translation":"adj. 总的；一般的n将军","word":"general"},{"phonetic_us":"/,dʒɛnrələ'zeʃən/","translation":"n. 一般化","word":"generalization","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/,dʒenrələ'zeɪʃən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛnrəli/","translation":"adv. 一般地；通常地","word":"generally","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒen(ə)rəlɪ/","example":"Generally speaking, the more expensive the stereo, the better it is. 一般说来，立体声音响越贵的越好。"},{"translation":"v. 产生","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛnəret/","word":"generate","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdʒenəreɪt/","example":"a useful technique for generating new ideas 能产生新创意的有用技术"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dʒenə'reɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Like most of my generation, I had never known a war. 和我们这一代的大多数人一样，我并没有经历过战争。","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛnə'reʃən/","translation":"n. 一代人，产生","word":"generation"},{"example":"an emergency generator 应急发电机","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒenəreɪtə/","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛnəretɚ/","translation":"n. 发电机；发生者","word":"generator"},{"example":"Parmesan is a generic term used to describe a family of hard Italian cheeses. 巴尔马干酪是一个用来描述一类坚硬的意大利奶酪的通用名称。","phonetic_uk":"/dʒə'nerɪk/","translation":"adj.  【生物】 属的， 类的； 一般的， 普通的","phonetic_us":"/dʒə'nɛrɪk/","word":"generic"},{"word":"generosity","phonetic_us":"/,dʒɛnə'rɑsəti/","translation":"n. 慷慨，大方","example":"an act of great generosity 十分慷慨的行为","phonetic_uk":"/ˌdʒenə'rɒsətɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈdʒenərəs/","example":"Dietler is generous with his time and money. 迪特勒在他的时间和金钱方面慷慨大方。","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛnərəs/","translation":"adj. 慷慨的","word":"generous"},{"example":"The film reveals Fellini’s genius. 这部影片展现了费里尼的天赋。","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒiːnɪəs/","translation":"n. 天才，天赋，天资","phonetic_us":"/'dʒinjəs/","word":"genius"},{"example":"Arthur was a very gentle, caring person. 阿瑟是一个非常温柔体贴的人。","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒent(ə)l/","word":"gentle","translation":"adj. 和蔼的；轻柔的","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛntl/"},{"word":"gentleman","translation":"n. 绅士；有教养的人","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛntlmən/","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒent(ə)lmən/","example":"Martin – always the perfect gentleman – got to his feet when my mother walked in. 马丁在我母亲进来时站了起来——他一向是十足的绅士派头。"},{"translation":"adv. 有礼貌地；柔和地","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛntli/","word":"gently","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒentlɪ/","example":"‘You go back to bed now,’ he said gently. “你回去睡觉吧。”他温柔地说道。"},{"translation":"adj. 真正的","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛnjʊɪn/","word":"genuine","example":"‘Did he really?’ Her surprise seemed genuine. “他真的这样？”她好像是真的惊讶。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdʒenjuɪn/"},{"translation":"adj. 地理的","phonetic_us":"/,dʒiə'ɡræfɪk/","word":"geographic","example":"User community and geographic distribution of users. 用户社区和用户的地理分布。","phonetic_uk":"/,dʒɪə'græfɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/dʒɪ'ɑɡrəfi/","translation":"n. 地理，地理学","word":"geography","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɪ'ɒgrəfɪ/","example":"a geography lesson 地理课"},{"word":"geometry","translation":"n. 几何，几何学","phonetic_us":"/dʒɪ'ɑmətri/","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɪ'ɒmɪtrɪ/","example":"...the very ordered way in which mathematics and geometry describe nature. …数学和几何学描述自然的条理性。"},{"word":"germ","translation":"n. 微生物，细菌，幼芽","phonetic_us":"/dʒɝm/","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɜːm/","example":"Put disinfectant down the toilet to kill any germs. 在抽水马桶里投放消毒剂杀菌。"},{"translation":"adj. 德国的；n. 德国人","phonetic_us":"","word":"German","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒɜːmən/","example":"German history 德国历史"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dʒɜːmənɪ/","example":"","translation":"n. 德意志，德国","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɝməni/","word":"Germany"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dʒestʃə/","example":"Luke made an obscene gesture with his finger. 卢克用手指做了一个下流的手势。","word":"gesture","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛstʃɚ/","translation":"n. 手势，姿势"},{"example":"We need to get help quickly! 我们需要马上得到帮助！","phonetic_uk":"/get/","word":"get","phonetic_us":"/ɡɛt/","translation":"v. 变得，成为；到达"},{"example":"They say the young girl’s ghost still haunts (= often appears in ) the house. 他们说那个少女的鬼魂依旧在那房子里出没。","phonetic_uk":"/gəʊst/","phonetic_us":"/ɡost/","translation":"n. 鬼，灵魂；鬼魂","word":"ghost"},{"word":"giant","translation":"n. 巨人；巨物","phonetic_us":"/'dʒaɪənt/","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒaɪənt/","example":"...a Nordic saga of giants. …一部关于巨人的北欧传奇。"},{"example":"The earrings were a gift from my aunt. 这副耳环是我姑姑送给我的礼物。","phonetic_uk":"/ɡɪft/","phonetic_us":"/ɡɪft/","translation":"n. 礼物；天赋","word":"gift"},{"word":"girl","phonetic_us":"/ɡɝl/","translation":"n. 女孩子，姑娘；女儿","phonetic_uk":"/gɜːl/","example":"Both boys and girls can apply to join the choir. 男孩和女孩均可申请加入合唱团。"},{"word":"give","translation":"v. 做，作；送给","phonetic_us":"/ɡɪv/","phonetic_uk":"/gɪv/","example":"Researchers were given a £10,000 grant to continue their work. 研究人员得到一万英镑的经费以继续他们的研究。"},{"example":"On any given day in the Houston area, half the hospital beds are empty. 在休斯敦地区，任何一天医院的床位都有一半是空的。","phonetic_uk":"/'gɪvn/","word":"given","translation":"adj. 规定的，特定的；假设的；已知的；有癖好的，有倾向的；prep.  考虑到","phonetic_us":"/'ɡɪvn/"},{"translation":"adj. 高兴的；乐意的","phonetic_us":"/ɡlæd/","word":"glad","example":"We’re so glad you came. 你来了我们真高兴。","phonetic_uk":"/glæd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/glɑːns/","example":"Wyatt glanced around the restaurant. 怀亚特环视了一下餐馆。","phonetic_us":"/ɡlæns/","translation":"v. 看一下；n. 一瞥","word":"glance"},{"example":"The sun glared down on us. 刺眼的阳光照在我们身上。","phonetic_uk":"/gleə/","word":"glare","phonetic_us":"/ɡlɛr/","translation":"v. 瞪眼；n. 瞪眼"},{"example":"a glass bowl 玻璃碗","phonetic_uk":"/glɑːs/","word":"glass","translation":"n. 玻璃；玻璃杯","phonetic_us":"/ɡlæs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/glaɪd/","example":"Waiters glide between tightly packed tables bearing trays of pasta. 侍者们托着一盘盘的意大利面食在拥挤的餐桌间自如穿行。","translation":"v. 滑动；消逝；n. 滑行","phonetic_us":"/ɡlaɪd/","word":"glide"},{"word":"glimpse","translation":"v. 瞥见；n. 一瞥，一看","phonetic_us":"/ɡlɪmps/","example":"I glimpsed a figure at the window. 我瞥见窗前有个身影。","phonetic_uk":"/glɪm(p)s/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'glɪtə/","example":"The river glittered in the sunlight. 阳光下河面波光粼粼。","translation":"v. 闪闪发光；n. 闪光","phonetic_us":"/'ɡlɪtɚ/","word":"glitter"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gləubl/","example":"global climate change 全球气候变化","word":"global","phonetic_us":"/'ɡlobl/","translation":"adj.  全球的， 全世界的； 总的， 完整的"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɡlob/","translation":"n. 地球，世界；地界仪","word":"globe","phonetic_uk":"/gləʊb/","example":"We export our goods all over the globe. 我们的商品出口到世界各地。"},{"example":"The report paints a gloomy picture of the economy. 这篇报告描绘了一幅惨淡的经济现状。","phonetic_uk":"/'gluːmɪ/","word":"gloomy","phonetic_us":"/'ɡlumi/","translation":"adj. 阴沉的，沮丧的"},{"word":"glorious","translation":"adj. 辉煌的","phonetic_us":"/'ɡlɔriəs; 'ɡloriəs/","example":"a truly glorious future 无比美好的将来","phonetic_uk":"/ˈglɔ:riəs/"},{"word":"glory","phonetic_us":"/'ɡlɔri/","translation":"n. 光荣；荣誉的事","phonetic_uk":"/'glɔːrɪ/","example":"She dreamt of future glory as an Olympic champion. 她梦想着将来能得到奥运冠军的荣誉。"},{"translation":"n. 手套","phonetic_us":"/ɡlʌv/","word":"glove","example":"a pair of gloves 一副手套","phonetic_uk":"/glʌv/"},{"word":"glow","phonetic_us":"/ɡlo/","translation":"n. 白热光；v. 发白热光","phonetic_uk":"/gləʊ/","example":"The moisturizer gave my face a healthy glow that lasted all day. 这种润肤霜给我脸上带来了持续整天的一种健康的红光。"},{"example":"...a tube of glue. …一管胶水。","phonetic_uk":"/gluː/","phonetic_us":"/ɡlu/","translation":"n. 胶，胶水；v. 胶合","word":"glue"},{"example":"The plate went crashing to the floor. 盘子哗啦一声掉在地板上。","phonetic_uk":"/gəʊ/","translation":"v. 去；走；变为","phonetic_us":"/go/","word":"go"},{"word":"goal","translation":"n. 球门；得分；目的","phonetic_us":"/ɡol/","phonetic_uk":"/gəʊl/","example":"Your goal as a parent is to help your child become an independent adult. 身为父母，你的目标就是要培养孩子成为独立的成年人。"},{"translation":"n. 山羊","phonetic_us":"/ɡot/","word":"goat","phonetic_uk":"/gəʊt/","example":"The tiger sprang on the goat. 老虎向山羊扑去。"},{"example":"He believes in God. 他信奉上帝。","phonetic_uk":"/ɡɒd/","translation":"n. 神，神像；上帝","phonetic_us":"/ɡɑd/","word":"God"},{"word":"gold","translation":"n. 金；钱财；adj. 金制的","phonetic_us":"/ɡold/","phonetic_uk":"/gəʊld/","example":"She came to the party dripping with gold (= wearing a lot of gold ) . 她披金戴银地来参加派对。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gəʊld(ə)n/","example":"golden hair 金发","translation":"adj. 金色的；极好的","phonetic_us":"/'ɡoldən/","word":"golden"},{"translation":"n. 高尔夫球","phonetic_us":"/gɔlf/","word":"golf","example":"He plays golf on Sundays. 他星期天都去打高尔夫球。","phonetic_uk":"/gɒlf/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɡʊd/","translation":"adj. 好的；有本事的","word":"good","example":"a good hotel 一家不错的宾馆","phonetic_uk":"/gʊd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gʊdnɪs/","example":"He retains a faith in human goodness. 他依然相信人性的善。","word":"goodness","phonetic_us":"/'ɡʊdnəs/","translation":"n. 优良，德性，仁慈"},{"word":"goods","phonetic_us":"/ɡʊdz/","translation":"n. 货物，商品","example":"the large market for consumer goods 庞大的消费品市场","phonetic_uk":"/ɡʊdz/"},{"word":"goose","translation":"n. 鹅，雌鹅","phonetic_us":"/ɡus/","example":"...roast goose. …烤鹅。","phonetic_uk":"/guːs/"},{"translation":"v. 管理，支配","phonetic_us":"/'ɡʌvɚn/","word":"govern","example":"the leaders who govern the country 治理这个国家的领导人","phonetic_uk":"/'ɡʌvən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gʌv(ə)n,m(ə)nt; 'gʌvəm(ə)nt/","example":"The Government are planning further cuts in public spending. 政府正计划进一步削减公共支出。","word":"government","translation":"n. 政府；治理；政治","phonetic_us":"/'ɡʌvɚnmənt/"},{"word":"governor","translation":"n. 州长；主管人员","phonetic_us":"/'ɡʌvɚnɚ/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'gʌv(ə)nə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/gaʊn/","example":"","word":"gown","translation":"n. 长袍，长外衣","phonetic_us":"/ɡaʊn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɡræb/","example":"Try to get there early and grab good seats. 尽量早点去，抢个好位子。","phonetic_us":"/ɡræb/","translation":"v. 抢先，抢占，抢夺","word":"grab"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɡres/","translation":"n. 优美，文雅；雅致","word":"grace","phonetic_uk":"/greɪs/","example":"Lena moved with the grace of a dancer. 莉娜走路姿势有着舞者般的优美。"},{"word":"graceful","phonetic_us":"/'ɡresfl/","translation":"adj. 优美的，优雅的","example":"Her movements were graceful and elegant. 她举手投足优雅而高贵。","phonetic_uk":"/'greɪsfʊl; -f(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɡreʃəs/","translation":"adj. 有礼貌的；仁慈的","word":"gracious","phonetic_uk":"/'greɪʃəs/","example":"Sibyl was the most gracious, helpful, and generous person to work with. 西比尔非常和蔼，乐于助人，而且为人慷慨，和她共事最愉快。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/greɪd/","example":"All the parks are regularly checked and graded by tourist board inspectors. 所有公园都由旅游协会的检查员进行定期检查和评级。","word":"grade","translation":"v. 给…分等级；n. 等级","phonetic_us":"/ɡred/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'grædʒʊəl/","example":"There has been a gradual change in climate. 气候渐渐发生了变化。","translation":"adj. 逐渐的；渐进的","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrædʒuəl/","word":"gradual"},{"word":"gradually","phonetic_us":"/'grædʒʊəli/","translation":"adv. 逐渐地，逐步地","phonetic_uk":"/'grædʒʊlɪ; 'grædjʊəlɪ/","example":"Jill gradually became aware of an awful smell. 吉尔渐渐地闻到了一股难闻的气味。"},{"translation":"n. 毕业生；v. 大学毕业","phonetic_us":"/ˈɡrædʒuˌet/","word":"graduate","example":"a Harvard graduate 哈佛毕业生","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɡradʒʊeɪt/"},{"example":"big sacks of grain 大袋大袋的粮食","phonetic_uk":"/greɪn/","translation":"n. 谷物，粮食","phonetic_us":"/ɡren/","word":"grain"},{"word":"gram","translation":"n.  克","phonetic_us":"/ɡræm/","phonetic_uk":"/græm/","example":"Then they chose one gram for weighing water in a cubic centimetre. 然后他们将一立方厘米的水的重量定为一克。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'græmɚ/","translation":"n. 语法；语法书","word":"grammar","phonetic_uk":"/'græmə/","example":"Check your spelling and grammar. 检查你的拼写和语法。"},{"word":"grammatical","phonetic_us":"/grə'mætɪkl/","translation":"adj. 语法上的","example":"grammatical rules 语法规则","phonetic_uk":"/grə'mætɪk(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɡræm/","example":"","word":"gramme","translation":"n. 克(重量单位)","phonetic_us":"/ɡræm/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɡrænd/","translation":"adj. 宏伟的；重大的","word":"grand","example":"a grand country house 豪华的乡间大宅","phonetic_uk":"/grænd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'grændɔːtə/","example":"...a drawing of my granddaughter Amelia. …一幅我孙女阿梅莉亚的画像。","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrændɔtɚ/","translation":"n. 孙女，外孙女","word":"granddaughter"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'græn(d)fɑːðə/","example":"His grandfather was a professor. 他爷爷曾是位教授。","phonetic_us":"/'græn'fɑðɚ/","translation":"n. 祖父；外祖父","word":"grandfather"},{"example":"My grandmothers are both widows. 我的祖母和外祖母都是寡妇。","phonetic_uk":"/'græn(d)mʌðə/","translation":"n. 祖母，外祖母","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrænmʌðɚ/","word":"grandmother"},{"word":"grandson","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrænsʌn/","translation":"n. 孙子，外孙子","phonetic_uk":"/'græn(d)sʌn/","example":"My grandson's birthday was on Tuesday. 我孙子的生日是星期二。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/grɑːnt/","example":"France has agreed to grant him political asylum. 法国已经同意给予他政治庇护。","phonetic_us":"/ɡrænt/","translation":"v. 授予；允许","word":"grant"},{"example":"a bunch of grapes 一串葡萄","phonetic_uk":"/greɪp/","translation":"n. 葡萄；葡萄藤","phonetic_us":"/ɡrep/","word":"grape"},{"phonetic_uk":"/grɑːf; græf/","example":"Martin showed me a graph of their recent sales. 马丁给我看了他们最近销售情况的图表。","phonetic_us":"/ɡræf/","translation":"n. (曲线)图，图表","word":"graph"},{"word":"grasp","phonetic_us":"/ɡræsp/","translation":"v. 抓紧；掌握；n. 抓","phonetic_uk":"/grɑːsp/","example":"I grasped his arm firmly and led him away. 我紧紧抓住他的胳膊把他带走。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/grɑːs/","example":"I walked across the grass. 我走在草地上。","word":"grass","phonetic_us":"/ɡræs/","translation":"n. 草；牧草；草地"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'greɪtfʊl; -f(ə)l/","example":"Our grateful thanks go to all who participated. 我们衷心感谢所有参与者。","word":"grateful","translation":"adj. 感激的；令人愉快的","phonetic_us":"/'ɡretfl/"},{"word":"gratitude","translation":"adj. 感激，感谢，感恩","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrætɪtud/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'grætɪtjuːd/"},{"word":"grave","phonetic_us":"/ɡrev/","translation":"n. 坟墓","phonetic_uk":"/greɪv/","example":"At the head of the grave there was a small wooden cross. 坟头上有一个小小的木十字架。"},{"translation":"n. 重力，引力；严重性","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrævəti/","word":"gravity","phonetic_uk":"/'grævɪtɪ/","example":"the force of gravity 重力"},{"phonetic_uk":"/greɪ/","example":"I like that little gray one. The kids like that one too. 我喜欢那只灰色的小鸭子， 孩子们也喜欢那只。","translation":"adj. 灰色的；n. 灰色","phonetic_us":"/ɡre/","word":"gray"},{"example":"The movie was a great success. 这部影片大获成功。","phonetic_uk":"/greɪt/","word":"great","phonetic_us":"/ɡret/","translation":"adj. 大的；伟大的"},{"word":"greatly","phonetic_us":"/'ɡretli/","translation":"adv. 大大地，非常","phonetic_uk":"/'greɪtlɪ/","example":"All offers of help will be greatly appreciated . 如蒙帮助，感激不尽。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'gridi/","translation":"adj. 贪吃的；贪婪的","word":"greedy","phonetic_uk":"/'griːdɪ/","example":"a greedy and selfish society 一个贪婪自私的社会"},{"example":"Greek yoghurt 希腊式酸奶","phonetic_uk":"/griːk/","word":"Greek","phonetic_us":"/grik/","translation":"adj. 希腊的；n. 希腊人"},{"phonetic_uk":"/griːn/","example":"beautiful green eyes 漂亮的碧眼","word":"green","translation":"adj. 绿色的；n. 绿色","phonetic_us":"/ɡrin/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'griːnhaʊs/","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrinhaʊs/","translation":"n. 温室，玻璃暖房","word":"greenhouse"},{"translation":"v. 问候，招呼；反应","phonetic_us":"/ɡrit/","word":"greet","phonetic_uk":"/griːt/","example":"Belinda greeted her warmly. 贝琳达热情地招呼她。"},{"example":"I smiled a polite greeting, but the woman hardly acknowledged me. 我客气地笑着打了个招呼，可是那女人没有答理我。","phonetic_uk":"/'griːtɪŋ/","phonetic_us":"/'ɡritɪŋ/","translation":"n. 问候，招呼，致敬","word":"greeting"},{"phonetic_uk":"/greɪ/","example":"an old lady with grey hair 头发灰白的老太太","word":"grey","phonetic_us":"/ɡre/","translation":"adj. 灰色的；n. 灰色"},{"example":"the national grid 国家电网","phonetic_uk":"/grɪd/","word":"grid","phonetic_us":"/ɡrɪd/","translation":"n. 输电网"},{"example":"Every change in our lives brings with it griefs. 我们生活当中的每一个变化都有让人伤心的一面。","phonetic_uk":"/gri:f/","word":"grief","translation":"n. 悲伤","phonetic_us":"/ɡrif/"},{"example":"People need time to grieve after the death of a loved one. 人们在所爱之人去世后会有一段悲伤期。","phonetic_uk":"/griːv/","word":"grieve","translation":"v. 使悲痛；v. 悲痛","phonetic_us":"/griv/"},{"translation":"v. 磨(碎)；磨快","phonetic_us":"/ɡraɪnd/","word":"grind","example":"a stone for grinding knives and scissors 磨刀剪的石头","phonetic_uk":"/graɪnd/"},{"word":"grip","phonetic_us":"/ɡrɪp/","translation":"v. 握紧，抓牢；n. 紧握","phonetic_uk":"/grɪp/","example":"I gripped the rail and tried not to look down. 我紧紧抓住栏杆，尽量不往下看。"},{"example":"The kids all groaned when I switched off the TV. 我关掉电视时，孩子们都发出不满的抱怨声。","phonetic_uk":"/grəʊn/","phonetic_us":"/ɡron/","translation":"v. 哼，呻吟；n. 呻吟","word":"groan"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'grəʊsə/","example":"The cook and the grocer haggled over the price of eggs. 厨师和杂货商为蛋价计较个没完。","phonetic_us":"/ɡrosɚ/","translation":"n. 食品商；杂货商","word":"grocer"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'grəʊs(ə)rɪ/","example":"They run a small grocery store. 他们经营一家小食品杂货店。","phonetic_us":"/'ɡrosəri/","translation":"n. 杂货店","word":"grocery"},{"phonetic_uk":"/grəʊs/","example":"The company was guilty of gross negligence. 该公司犯了重大的失职罪。","phonetic_us":"/ɡros/","translation":"adj. 总的；严重的","word":"gross"},{"example":"There are strong grounds for believing his statement. 有充分的理由可以相信他的话。","phonetic_uk":"/graʊnd/","phonetic_us":"/ɡraʊnd/","translation":"n. 地；场地；根据","word":"ground"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'graundlisli/","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adv. 无缘无故地，无根据地","word":"groundlessly"},{"example":"One more thing, remind me to get some kind of groundsheet or we'll end up getting filthy. 还有一件事，记得提醒我带一些防潮布之类的东西，否则我们结束的时候会一片狼籍。","phonetic_uk":"/'graʊn(d)ʃiːt/","word":"groundsheet","phonetic_us":"/'graʊnd'ʃit/","translation":"n. 防潮布"},{"phonetic_uk":"/gruːp/","example":"A group of us are going to London. 我们有一群人要去伦敦。","word":"group","translation":"n. 小组，群；v. 聚集","phonetic_us":"/ɡrup/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/grəʊ/","example":"You’ve really grown since I last saw you. 你比我上次见到时长了不少啊。","phonetic_us":"/ɡro/","translation":"v. 生长；变得；增长","word":"grow"},{"example":"measures to stimulate economic growth 刺激经济增长的措施","phonetic_uk":"/grəʊθ/","phonetic_us":"/ɡroθ/","translation":"n. 增长；增长量；生长","word":"growth"},{"word":"guarantee","translation":"n & v. 保证，担保","phonetic_us":"/,ɡærən'ti/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɡærən'ti:/","example":"The bank will only lend me money if my parents guarantee the loan. 只有我父母作担保，银行才会给我贷款。"},{"word":"guard","phonetic_us":"/ɡɑrd/","translation":"v. 守卫；看守；n. 卫兵","example":"The Sergeant told Swift to guard the entrance. 中士叫斯威夫特守着入口。","phonetic_uk":"/gɑːd/"},{"word":"guess","translation":"vt&vi&n. 猜测，推测","phonetic_us":"/ɡɛs/","example":"I’d say he’s around 50, but I’m only guessing. 我想他50岁左右，不过也只是猜测。","phonetic_uk":"/ges/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/gest/","example":"a banquet for 250 distinguished guests 250位贵宾出席的宴会","phonetic_us":"/ɡɛst/","translation":"n. 客人，宾客；旅客","word":"guest"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gaɪd(ə)ns/","example":"a missile with a sophisticated electronic guidance system 有精密电子制导系统的导弹","word":"guidance","phonetic_us":"/'gaɪdns/","translation":"n. 引导，指导，领导"},{"example":"a tour guide 导游","phonetic_uk":"/gaɪd/","phonetic_us":"/ɡaɪd/","translation":"n. 导游者；v. 给…导游","word":"guide"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gaɪdlaɪn/","example":"This chapter gives you some guidelines to help you in your work. 本章将介绍一些指导性原则，为你的工作提供帮助。","word":"guideline","phonetic_us":"/'ɡaɪdlaɪn/","translation":"n. 指导原则"},{"word":"guilt","translation":"n. 有罪，犯罪行为","phonetic_us":"/ɡɪlt/","phonetic_uk":"/gɪlt/","example":"He did not deny his guilt. 他没有否认自己有罪。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'gɪltɪ/","example":"She looked self-conscious and guilty. 她看上去很不自然，很内疚的样子。","word":"guilty","translation":"adj. 内疚的；有罪的","phonetic_us":"/'ɡɪlti/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɡɪ'tɑr/","translation":"n.  吉他， 六弦琴","word":"guitar","phonetic_uk":"/gɪ'tɑː/","example":""},{"word":"gulf","phonetic_us":"/ɡʌlf/","translation":"n. 海湾","phonetic_uk":"/gʌlf/","example":"the Gulf of Mexico 墨西哥湾"},{"phonetic_uk":"/gʌm/","example":"The toothbrush gently removes plaque without damaging the gums or causing bleeding. 牙刷轻轻地刷去齿菌斑，没有伤及牙床或引起出血。","translation":"n. 牙龈","phonetic_us":"/ɡʌm/","word":"gum"},{"example":"I’ve never fired a gun in my life. 我这辈子从来没开过枪。","phonetic_uk":"/gʌn/","phonetic_us":"/ɡʌn/","translation":"n. 枪，炮，手枪","word":"gun"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɡʌnpaʊdɚ/","translation":"n. 黑色火药；有烟火药","word":"gunpowder","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'gʌnpaʊdə/"},{"word":"guy","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n.  家伙， 伙计","example":"Dave’s a nice guy when you get to know him. 戴夫是个好人，你了解他后就知道了。","phonetic_uk":"/gaɪ/"},{"word":"gym","translation":"n. 体育馆，健身房","phonetic_us":"/dʒɪm/","phonetic_uk":"/dʒim/","example":"I go to the gym as often as I can. 我一有空就去健身房健身。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dʒɪm'neɪzɪəm/","example":"I have found a new gymnasium. 我找到一个新的健身房。","translation":"n. 体育馆，健身房","phonetic_us":"/dʒɪm'nezɪəm/","word":"gymnasium"},{"word":"habit","phonetic_us":"/'hæbɪt/","translation":"n. 习惯；习性","phonetic_uk":"/'hæbɪt/","example":"Regular exercise is a good habit. 经常锻炼是个好习惯。"},{"phonetic_us":"/hə'bɪtʃuəl/","translation":"adj. 习惯性的，惯常的","word":"habitual","example":"James took his habitual morning walk around the garden. 詹姆斯又像往常习惯的那样绕花园作晨间散步去了。","phonetic_uk":"/hə'bɪtʃʊəl; -tjʊəl/"},{"example":"Her hair was short and dark. 她的头发又短又黑。","phonetic_uk":"/heə/","word":"hair","translation":"n. 头发，毛发；毛","phonetic_us":"/hɛr/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'heəkʌt/","example":"Do you like my new haircut? 你喜欢我的新发型吗？","phonetic_us":"/'hɛrkʌt/","translation":"n. 理发","word":"haircut"},{"translation":"n. 半，一半；adj. 一半的","phonetic_us":"/hæf/","word":"half","example":"Only half the guests had arrived by seven o’clock. 7点钟前只来了一半客人。","phonetic_uk":"/hɑːf/"},{"word":"halfway","translation":"adv.  半路地； 在中途， 在半途；adj. 中途的；部分的；不彻底的","phonetic_us":"/,hæf'we/","example":"He was halfway up the ladder. 他梯子上到了一半。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌhɑːf'weɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 门厅；过道；会堂","phonetic_us":"/hɔl/","word":"hall","phonetic_uk":"/hɔːl/","example":"a huge tiled entrance hall 铺着地砖的大门厅"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɔːlt/","example":"The government has failed to halt economic decline. 政府没能阻止经济衰退。","translation":"v. 停止；立定；n. 停住","phonetic_us":"/hɔlt/","word":"halt"},{"phonetic_us":"/hæmbɝ​ɡɚ/","translation":"n. 汉堡包，牛肉饼","word":"hamburger","phonetic_uk":"/ˈhæmbɜ:gə/","example":"The whole stadium stink of the hamburger. 整个体育场内散发着汉堡包的香味。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hæmɚ/","translation":"n. 锤，榔头；v. 锤击","word":"hammer","example":"I had no hammer,so I had to pound the nail in with a stone. 我没有锤子，所以只得用石头把钉子敲进去。","phonetic_uk":"/'hæmə/"},{"example":"Steve gripped the steering wheel tightly with both hands. 史蒂夫双手紧握方向盘。","phonetic_uk":"/hænd/","word":"hand","phonetic_us":"/hænd/","translation":"n. 手；人手；指针"},{"translation":"n.  手提包","phonetic_us":"/'hænd'bæg/","word":"handbag","phonetic_uk":"/'hændbæg/","example":"Rice: No, I only have a handbag. 没有，我只有一个手提包。"},{"example":"There were only a handful of people there. 那里只有几个人。","phonetic_uk":"/'hæn(d)fʊl; -f(ə)l/","word":"handful","translation":"n. 一把；少数，一小撮","phonetic_us":"/'hænd,fʊl/"},{"example":"He flicked at spot with handkerchief. 他轻轻地用手帕拂拭污点。","phonetic_uk":"/'hæŋkətʃɪf/","word":"handkerchief","translation":"n. 手帕","phonetic_us":"/'hæŋkɚtʃɪf/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hændl/","example":"I handled most of the paperwork. 大部分文书工作是我做的。","translation":"v. 控制，处理","phonetic_us":"/'hændl/","word":"handle"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hæns(ə)m/","example":"They won a handsome victory in the elections. 他们在选举中取得了重大的胜利。","word":"handsome","translation":"adj. 英俊的；相当大的","phonetic_us":"/'hænsəm/"},{"word":"handwriting","phonetic_us":"/'hænd'raɪtɪŋ/","translation":"n. 笔迹，手迹，书法","example":"I recognised her handwriting on the envelope. 我认出了信封上她的笔迹。","phonetic_uk":"/'hændraɪtɪŋ/"},{"example":"It’s quite a handy little tool. 这件小工具非常有用。","phonetic_uk":"/'hændɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'hændi/","translation":"adj. 手边的；便于使用的","word":"handy"},{"example":"If he is found guilty, he will almost certainly hang. 如果被判有罪，他几乎肯定会被处以绞刑。","phonetic_uk":"/hæŋ/","word":"hang","phonetic_us":"/hæŋ/","translation":"v. 挂，悬；吊死"},{"translation":"v. 发生；碰巧，恰好","phonetic_us":"/'hæpən/","word":"happen","phonetic_uk":"/'hæp(ə)n/","example":"When did the accident happen? 事故什么时候发生的？"},{"word":"happiness","phonetic_us":"/ˈhæpinəs/","translation":"n. 幸福，幸运；快乐","example":"Juliet’s eyes shone with happiness. 朱丽叶的双眼闪耀着幸福的光芒。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈhæpinəs/"},{"word":"happy","translation":"adj. 快乐的；幸福的","phonetic_us":"/'hæpɪ/","example":"It’s a lovely house and we’ve been very happy here. 房子很漂亮，我们住在这里非常开心。","phonetic_uk":"/'hæpɪ/"},{"word":"harbour","phonetic_us":"/hɑrbɚ/","translation":"n. 海港，港口；v. 庇护","example":"as they sailed into Portsmouth Harbour 当他们驶入朴次茅斯港的时候","phonetic_uk":"/ˈhɑ:bə(r)/"},{"example":"a hard wooden chair 一把硬木椅","phonetic_uk":"/hɑːd/","word":"hard","translation":"adj. 硬的；困难的","phonetic_us":"/hɑrd/"},{"word":"harden","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrdn/","translation":"v. 使变硬；v. 变硬","phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːd(ə)n/","example":"It will take about 24 hours for the glue to harden. 胶水干透大约需要24小时。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hɑrdli/","translation":"adv. 几乎不，简直不","word":"hardly","phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːdlɪ/","example":"My parents divorced when I was six, and I hardly knew my father. 我六岁时父母离婚，我对父亲几乎一无所知。"},{"word":"hardship","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrdʃɪp/","translation":"n. 艰难，困苦","example":"an economic policy that caused great hardship for many people 造成许多人贫困的经济政策","phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːdʃɪp/"},{"translation":"n. 五金器具；硬件","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrdwɛr/","word":"hardware","example":"...a shop from which an uncle had sold hardware and timber. …一家叔叔曾经在那里卖五金器具和木材的店铺。","phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːdweə/"},{"word":"hardworking","translation":"adj. 苦干的，不辞辛劳的","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrd,wɝkɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/hɑ:d'wɜ:kɪŋ/","example":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/heə/","example":"Because it makes its home in an extreme environment, the desert hare is biologically designed to radiate excess heat through its lanky limbs and oversized ears. 因为生长在极端环境中，沙漠兔子形成了独特的生物学构造，通过瘦长的四肢和超大的耳朵辐射多余的热量。","word":"hare","phonetic_us":"/hɛr/","translation":"n. 野兔"},{"word":"harm","translation":"n & v. 有害","phonetic_us":"/hɑrm/","example":"The scandal did his career a lot of harm. 丑闻对他的职业生涯造成很大损害。","phonetic_uk":"/hɑ:m/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːmfʊl/","example":"the harmful effects of smoking 吸烟的害处","translation":"adj. 有害的","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrmfəl/","word":"harmful"},{"word":"harmony","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrməni/","translation":"n. 和谐","example":"the gorgeous vocal harmonies on ‘Mexicali Rose’ 《墨西哥玫瑰》的精彩和声演唱","phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːmənɪ/"},{"word":"harness","translation":"v. 治理；n. 马具，挽具","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrnɪs/","phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːnɪs/","example":"We must harness the rivers which overflow annually. 我们必须治理那些每年泛滥的河流。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɑːʃ/","example":"The hostages are being held in harsh conditions. 人质被拘押在恶劣环境中。","word":"harsh","translation":"adj. 严酷的","phonetic_us":"/hɑrʃ/"},{"translation":"n. 丰收，收获","phonetic_us":"/'hɑrvɪst/","word":"harvest","example":"There was about 300 million tons of grain in the fields at the start of the harvest. 收割伊始田间大约有三亿吨的谷物。","phonetic_uk":"/'hɑːvɪst/"},{"translation":"n. 急速，急忙；草率","phonetic_us":"/hest/","word":"haste","example":"I soon regretted my haste. 我很快就对自己的仓促感到后悔。","phonetic_uk":"/heɪst/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'heɪs(ə)n/","example":"Their departure was hastened by an abnormally cold winter. 那个冬天异常寒冷，所以他们提前走了。","word":"hasten","translation":"v. 催促；v. 赶紧","phonetic_us":"/'hesn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'heɪstɪ/","example":"He soon regretted his hasty decision. 他很快就对自己仓促作出的决定感到后悔了。","word":"hasty","phonetic_us":"/'hesti/","translation":"adj. 急速的；仓促的"},{"word":"hat","translation":"n. 帽子(一般指有边的)","phonetic_us":"/hæt/","example":"Maria was wearing a beautiful new hat. 玛丽亚戴着一顶漂亮的新帽子。","phonetic_uk":"/hæt/"},{"word":"hatch","translation":"v. 孵出；v. (蛋)孵化","phonetic_us":"/hætʃ/","example":"The eggs take three days to hatch. 这些蛋要三天时间才能孵化。","phonetic_uk":"/hætʃ/"},{"word":"hate","phonetic_us":"/het/","translation":"v. 恨，憎恨；不喜欢","example":"It’s the kind of movie you either love or hate. 这是那种你要么喜欢要么讨厌的电影。","phonetic_uk":"/heɪt/"},{"word":"hateful","translation":"adj. 可恨的，可恶的","phonetic_us":"/'hetfəl/","phonetic_uk":"/'heɪtfʊl; -f(ə)l/","example":"It was all the fault of that hateful man! 都是那个可恶的人造的孽！"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hetrɪd/","translation":"n. 憎恶，憎恨，仇恨","word":"hatred","example":"A look of pure hatred flashed across her face. 她脸上闪过十足的仇恨表情。","phonetic_uk":"/'heɪtrɪd/"},{"word":"have","translation":"v. aux已经；v. 有；吃","phonetic_us":"/hæv; (also, as before 'to') hæf/","phonetic_uk":"/hæv/","example":"Our guests have arrived. 我们的客人到了。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/hɔːk/","phonetic_us":"/hɔk/","translation":"n. 鹰，隼","word":"hawk"},{"phonetic_uk":"/heɪ/","example":"...bales of hay. …一捆捆的干草。","word":"hay","translation":"n. 干草","phonetic_us":""},{"translation":"n. 危险","phonetic_us":"/'hæzɚd/","word":"hazard","example":"That pile of rubbish is a fire hazard (= something that is likely to cause a fire ). 那堆垃圾是火灾隐患。","phonetic_uk":"/'hæzəd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/hi/","translation":"pron. (主格)他","word":"he","phonetic_uk":"/hiː/","example":"‘Where’s Paul?’ ‘He’s gone to the cinema.’ “保罗在哪儿？”“他去看电影了。”"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hed/","example":"He kissed the top of her head. 他吻了一下她的头顶。","word":"head","translation":"n. 头；上端；v. 率领","phonetic_us":"/hɛd/"},{"word":"headache","translation":"n. 头痛；头痛的事","phonetic_us":"/ˈhɛdˌek/","example":"If you have a headache, you should take some aspirin. 要是头痛，你该吃点阿司匹林。","phonetic_uk":"/'hedeɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hedɪŋ/","example":"chapter headings 章节标题","word":"heading","translation":"n. 标题，题词，题名","phonetic_us":"/'hɛdɪŋ/"},{"word":"headline","translation":"n. 大字标题；新闻提要","phonetic_us":"/'hɛdlaɪn/","phonetic_uk":"/'hedlaɪn/","example":"a paper carrying the front-page headline: ‘Space Aliens meet with President’ 头版报道题为“天外来客会见总统”的报纸"},{"example":"This headmaster is very modest. 这位校长很谦虚。","phonetic_uk":"/hed'mɑːstə/","word":"headmaster","phonetic_us":"/,hɛd'mæstɚ/","translation":"n. 校长"},{"translation":"v. 设立总部，在…设立总部","phonetic_us":"/'hɛd'kwɔrtɚ/","word":"headquarter","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'hedkwɔːtə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hɛdkwɔrtɚz/","translation":"n. 司令部；总部","word":"headquarters","phonetic_uk":"/hed'kwɔːtəz/","example":"the headquarters of the United Nations 联合国总部"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hiːl/","example":"a preacher who claims that he can heal the sick 自称可以治病的传道士","translation":"v. 治愈；使和解","phonetic_us":"/hil/","word":"heal"},{"example":"I’m worried about my husband’s health. 我担心我丈夫的健康状况。","phonetic_uk":"/helθ/","word":"health","translation":"n. 健康，健康状况","phonetic_us":"/hɛlθ/"},{"word":"healthy","phonetic_us":"/'hɛlθi/","translation":"adj. 健康的；有益健康的","phonetic_uk":"/'helθɪ/","example":"a healthy baby boy 健康的男婴"},{"word":"heap","translation":"n. (一)堆；大量","phonetic_us":"/hip/","example":"a rubbish heap 垃圾堆","phonetic_uk":"/hiːp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɪə/","example":"Blanche heard a crash as the back door was flung open. 布兰奇听见后门哗啦一声被推开。","phonetic_us":"/hɪr/","translation":"v. 听见；审讯；听说","word":"hear"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hɪrɪŋ/","translation":"n.  听力， 听觉； 听力所及之距离； 意见听取会； 申辩的机会","word":"hearing","phonetic_uk":"/'hɪərɪŋ/","example":"a child with a hearing disability 有听力障碍的儿童"},{"example":"Regular exercise is good for the heart. 经常锻炼对心脏有好处。","phonetic_uk":"/hɑːt/","word":"heart","translation":"n. 心，内心；勇气","phonetic_us":"/hɑrt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/hit/","translation":"n. 热，炎热；v. 变热","word":"heat","phonetic_uk":"/hiːt/","example":"Ice needs heat to melt. 冰需要热才能融化。"},{"example":"We wanted to reduce the cost of heating and air-conditioning. 我们想减少供暖与空调的开支。","phonetic_uk":"/'hiːtɪŋ/","word":"heating","phonetic_us":"/'hitɪŋ/","translation":"n. 加热，供暖"},{"phonetic_us":"/hiv/","translation":"vi. 起伏，隆起；呕吐，恶心；vt. 举起，提起，拉起，拖；扔；发出；n.  举起； 起伏， 升降","word":"heave","example":"Michael’s shoulders heaved with silent laughter. 迈克尔憋着不笑出声来，双肩直抖。","phonetic_uk":"/hiːv/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hɛvn/","translation":"n. 天堂；天，天空","word":"heaven","example":"He looked up towards the heavens. 他仰望苍穹。","phonetic_uk":"/'hev(ə)n/"},{"example":"I became heavily involved in politics. 我深陷政治之中。","phonetic_uk":"/'hevɪlɪ/","word":"heavily","phonetic_us":"/'hɛvɪli/","translation":"adv. 重重地；大量地"},{"example":"The wardrobe was too heavy for me to move on my own. 衣橱太重，我一个人移不动。","phonetic_uk":"/'hevɪ/","translation":"adj. 重的；大的；充满的","phonetic_us":"/'hɛvi/","word":"heavy"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hedʒ/","example":"","translation":"n. 篱笆，树篱；障碍物","phonetic_us":"/hɛdʒ/","word":"hedge"},{"word":"heel","translation":"n. 脚后跟，踵，后跟","phonetic_us":"/hil/","example":"black boots with high heels 有高跟的黑靴子","phonetic_uk":"/hiːl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/haɪt/","example":"Sam’s about the same height as his sister now. 萨姆现在身高和他姐姐差不多了。","word":"height","translation":"n. 高，高度；高处","phonetic_us":"/haɪt/"},{"example":"Jonson was his political heir as leader of the party. 琼森是他的政治接班人，他将担任该党派的领袖。","phonetic_uk":"/eə/","phonetic_us":"/ɛr/","translation":"n. 后嗣，继承人","word":"heir"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'helɪkɒptə/","example":"You can helicopter to the island. 你可以乘坐直升机去那个岛。","phonetic_us":"/'hɛlɪkɑptɚ/","translation":"n. 直升机","word":"helicopter"},{"example":"War is hell. 战争是人间地狱。","phonetic_uk":"/hel/","phonetic_us":"/hɛl/","translation":"n. 地狱；极大的痛苦","word":"hell"},{"translation":"int. 喂","phonetic_us":"/hɛˈlo, hə-/","word":"hello","example":"Hello, John! How are you? 喂，约翰！你好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/hə'ləʊ; he-/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hɛlmɪt/","translation":"n. 头盔，钢盔","word":"helmet","example":"The Sword split the Knight's helmet and bit him fatally. 剑劈开了骑士的头盔并致命地刺进他。","phonetic_uk":"/'helmɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/help/","example":"If there’s anything I can do to help, just give me a call. 如果需要我帮忙，就给我打个电话。","word":"help","phonetic_us":"/hɛlp/","translation":"v. 帮助；援助；n. 帮手"},{"example":"Thank you for your advice; it’s been very helpful. 谢谢你的建议，它非常有用。","phonetic_uk":"/'helpfʊl; -f(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/'hɛlpfl/","translation":"adj. 给予帮助的；有用的","word":"helpful"},{"word":"helpless","phonetic_us":"/'hɛlpləs/","translation":"adj. 无助的；无能的","example":"He began to feel depressed and helpless. 他开始觉得沮丧、无助。","phonetic_uk":"/'helplɪs/"},{"word":"hen","translation":"n. 母鸡，雌禽","phonetic_us":"/hɛn/","example":"The chickens gathered under the hen. 小鸡聚集在母鸡翅膀下面。","phonetic_uk":"/hen/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hens/","example":"The cost of transport is a major expense for an industry. Hence factory location is an important consideration. 运输成本是企业的一大支出，因此工厂选址是重要的考虑因素。","translation":"adv. 因此，所以；今后","phonetic_us":"/hɛns/","word":"hence"},{"word":"her","translation":"pron. (宾格)她；她的","phonetic_us":"/hɚ/","example":"Jane? I don’t really know her. 简？我不太认识她。","phonetic_uk":"/hɜː/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɜːd/","example":"Chobe is also renowned for its large herds of elephant and buffalo. 乔贝还以其大群的大象和水牛而闻名。","phonetic_us":"/hɝd/","translation":"n. 兽群，牧群；v. 放牧","word":"herd"},{"phonetic_us":"/hɪr/","translation":"adv. 这里；向这里","word":"here","example":"What are you doing here? 你们在这里干什么？","phonetic_uk":"/hɪə/"},{"example":"He had dared to speak out against injustice, and overnight he became a national hero . 他敢于站出来抨击不公正的现象，一夜之间就成了国家英雄。","phonetic_uk":"/'hɪərəʊ/","translation":"n. 男主角；英雄；勇士","phonetic_us":"/'hɪro/","word":"hero"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɪ'rəʊɪk/","example":"her heroic efforts to save her family 她拯救家人的英勇行为","word":"heroic","translation":"adj. 英雄的；英勇的","phonetic_us":"/hə'roɪk/"},{"translation":"n. 女主角；女英雄","phonetic_us":"/'hɛroɪn/","word":"heroine","example":"The heroine is a senior TV executive. 女主人公是一位电视台高级主管。","phonetic_uk":"/'herəʊɪn/"},{"example":"He bent and touched his mouth to hers. 他俯身吻她的嘴唇。","phonetic_uk":"/hɜːz/","word":"hers","phonetic_us":"/hɝz/","translation":"pron. 她的(所有物)"},{"phonetic_us":"/hɝ'sɛlf/","translation":"pron. 她自己；她亲自","word":"herself","phonetic_uk":"/hɜː'self/","example":"She cut herself on some broken glass. 碎玻璃把她割伤了。"},{"translation":"adj.  犹豫的； 吞吞吐吐的","phonetic_us":"/'hɛzɪtənt/","word":"hesitant","example":"Gail gave me a hesitant little smile. 盖尔迟疑地对我微微一笑。","phonetic_uk":"/'hezɪtənt/"},{"word":"hesitate","phonetic_us":"/'hɛzɪtet/","translation":"v. 犹豫，踌躇；含糊","example":"I hesitate. 我犹豫。","phonetic_uk":"/'hezɪteɪt/"},{"word":"heterogeneity","translation":"n.  异种， 异质， 不同成分","phonetic_us":"","example":"Such political communities are characterized by heterogeneity and difference with no shared object of design. 这样的政治共同体的特征是不会共享别人的设计的异质性和区别。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌhetərədʒə'niːəti/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/haɪ/","example":"Hi! How are you? 嗨！你好吗？","phonetic_us":"/haɪ/","translation":"int. 嗨(表示问候等)","word":"hi"},{"phonetic_uk":"/haɪd/","example":"She keeps a bottle of gin hidden behind a stack of books. 她在一堆书的后面藏了一瓶杜松子酒。","phonetic_us":"/haɪd/","translation":"v. 把…藏起来；隐瞒","word":"hide"},{"example":"This is the highest mountain in Japan. 这是日本最高的山。","phonetic_uk":"/haɪ/","word":"high","translation":"adj. 高的；高级的；adv. 高","phonetic_us":"/haɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'haɪlaɪt/","translation":"v & n. 照亮；突出；强调","word":"highlight","phonetic_uk":"/'hailait/","example":"Your résumé should highlight your skills and achievements. 你的简历应该突出自己的技能和成绩。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'haɪlɪ/","example":"Tom’s mother was highly critical of the school’s approach. 汤姆的母亲对学校的处理方法持强烈的批评态度。","translation":"adv. 高度地，很，非常","phonetic_us":"/'haɪli/","word":"highly"},{"example":"Interstate Highway 75 75号州际公路","phonetic_uk":"/'haɪweɪ/","word":"highway","translation":"n. 公路；大路","phonetic_us":"/'haɪwe/"},{"example":"Their house is on a hill overlooking the sea. 他们的房子建在可以俯视大海的小山上。","phonetic_uk":"/hɪl/","phonetic_us":"/hɪl/","translation":"n. 小山，山岗；丘陵","word":"hill"},{"translation":"n. (小山)山腰，山坡","phonetic_us":"/'hɪl'saɪd/","word":"hillside","phonetic_uk":"/'hɪlsaɪd/","example":"The airplane crashed on a hillside. 飞机在山坡上坠毁。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɪm/","example":"Are you in love with him? 你爱上他了吗？","word":"him","translation":"pron. (宾格)他","phonetic_us":"/hɪm/"},{"translation":"pron. 他自己；他亲自","phonetic_us":"/hɪm'sɛlf/","word":"himself","example":"He repossessed himself of his farm. 他收回自己所有的农场。","phonetic_uk":"/hɪm'self/"},{"example":"His career has been hindered by injury. 由于受伤，他的事业受到了阻碍。","phonetic_uk":"/'hɪndə/","word":"hinder","translation":"v. 阻碍","phonetic_us":"/'hɪndɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɪnt/","example":"There have been hints that he may take up coaching. 他暗示过可能会出任教练。","word":"hint","translation":"n. 暗示，示意；建议","phonetic_us":"/hɪnt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɪp/","example":"She stood there with her hands on her hips glaring at him. 她站在那里，双手叉腰瞪着他。","word":"hip","phonetic_us":"/hɪp/","translation":"n.  臀部， 髋部"},{"word":"hire","phonetic_us":"/'haɪɚ/","translation":"v. 雇佣","phonetic_uk":"/'haɪə/","example":"Employers hire skilled people on fixed-term contracts. 雇主以签订固定期限的合同来雇用有技能的人。"},{"word":"his","phonetic_us":"/hɪz/","translation":"pron. 他的，他的东西","phonetic_uk":"/hɪz/","example":"He stated his views to me. 他向我说明了他的观点。"},{"translation":"adj.  历史上著名的， 具有重大历史意义的","phonetic_us":"/hɪ'stɔrɪk/","word":"historic","example":"a historic meeting of world leaders 具有历史意义的世界领导人会议","phonetic_uk":"/hɪ'stɒrɪk/"},{"translation":"adj. 历史的，有关历史的","phonetic_us":"/hɪ'stɔrɪkl/","word":"historical","example":"places of historical interest 历史名胜","phonetic_uk":"/hɪ'stɒrɪk(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈhɪstəri; ˈhɪstri/","translation":"n. 历史；个人经历","word":"history","example":"Throughout history the achievements of women have been largely ignored. 从古至今，妇女的成就都被大大地忽视了。","phonetic_uk":"/'hɪst(ə)rɪ/"},{"word":"hit","phonetic_us":"/hɪt/","translation":"n. 成功, 打击","phonetic_uk":"/hɪt/","example":"First a house took a direct hit and then the rocket exploded. 首先一幢房子被直接击中，接着火箭弹爆炸了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hɒbɪ/","example":"What are your hobbies? 你有些什么爱好？","phonetic_us":"/'hɑbi/","translation":"n. 业余爱好，癖好","word":"hobby"},{"translation":"v. 拿住；掌握；拥有","phonetic_us":"/hold/","word":"hold","phonetic_uk":"/həʊld/","example":"He holds shares in ICI. 他持有帝国化学工业集团的股份。"},{"phonetic_us":"/hol/","translation":"n. 洞；孔眼，裂开处","word":"hole","example":"I began digging a hole for the plant. 我开始挖洞种那棵植物。","phonetic_uk":"/həʊl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hɒlɪdeɪ; -dɪ/","example":"The school holidays start tomorrow. 学校假期从明天开始。","word":"holiday","phonetic_us":"/'hɑləde/","translation":"n. 假日，节日；假期"},{"example":"a hollow tree 空心树","phonetic_uk":"/'hɒləʊ/","translation":"adj. 空的；空洞的","phonetic_us":"/'hɑlo/","word":"hollow"},{"word":"holy","translation":"adj. 神圣的；圣洁的","phonetic_us":"/'holi/","example":"the holy city of Varanasi 圣城瓦拉纳西","phonetic_uk":"/'həʊlɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/həʊm/","example":"They have a beautiful home in California. 他们在加州有个美丽的家。","phonetic_us":"/hom/","translation":"n. 家；家乡；adj. 家庭的","word":"home"},{"word":"homemaker","translation":"n. 主妇","phonetic_us":"/'hommekɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈhəʊmmeɪkə(r)/","example":"Whether you are a carpenter or a therapist, a homemaker or a professor, it makes no difference. 不论你是一个木匠或是一个治疗师，一个家庭主妇还是教授，这都没有区别。"},{"example":"The unemployed are not a homogeneous group. 失业者并不都是同一类人。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌhɒmə'dʒiːniəs/","phonetic_us":"/,homə'dʒinɪəs/","translation":"adj.  同种类的， 同性质的， 有相同特征的","word":"homogeneous"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɑnɪst/","translation":"adj. 诚实的；可敬的","word":"honest","example":"He was a hard-working, honest man. 他勤奋老实。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒnɪst/"},{"word":"honesty","translation":"n. 诚实","phonetic_us":"/'ɑnəsti/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒnɪstɪ/","example":"a politician of rare honesty and courage 具备少见的诚实及勇气的政治家"},{"word":"honey","phonetic_us":"/'hʌni/","translation":"n. 蜜，蜂蜜；甜，甜蜜","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'hʌnɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 蜜月","phonetic_us":"/'hʌnɪmun/","word":"honeymoon","example":"By 1987, the honeymoon was over . 到1987年，蜜月期已经过去。","phonetic_uk":"/'hʌnɪmuːn/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒnə(r)/","word":"honor","phonetic_us":"/ɑnɚ/","translation":"v. 纪念"},{"example":"Over 100 players competed for the honour of representing the county in the National Finals. 100多位选手为争取代表郡参加全国总决赛的荣誉进行角逐。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒnə/","word":"honour","phonetic_us":"/'ɔnə/","translation":"n. 光荣；尊敬，敬意"},{"example":"My father didn’t think acting was an honorable profession. 我父亲认为当演员不是受人尊敬的职业。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒn(ə)rəb(ə)l/","word":"honourable","translation":"adj. 诚实的；光荣的","phonetic_us":"/'ɔnərəbl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/hʊk/","translation":"n. 钩，挂钩；v. 钩住","word":"hook","phonetic_uk":"/hʊk/","example":"Tom hung his coat on the hook behind the door. 汤姆把外套挂在门后的衣钩上。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/həʊp/","example":"I do hope everything goes well. 我真心希望一切顺利。","word":"hope","phonetic_us":"/hop/","translation":"n&vt&vi. 希望"},{"word":"hopeful","phonetic_us":"/'hopfl/","translation":"adj. 有希望的","example":"The vote is a hopeful sign that attitudes in the church are changing. 投票结果是个好兆头，表明教会的态度正在转变。","phonetic_uk":"/'həʊpfʊl; -f(ə)l/"},{"word":"hopeless","translation":"adj. 没有希望的，绝望的","phonetic_us":"/ˈhoʊpləs/","example":"We tried to stop the flames from spreading, but we knew it was hopeless. 我们试图阻止火势蔓延，但我们知道这是不可能的。","phonetic_uk":"/'həʊpləs/"},{"word":"horizon","translation":"n. 地平线；眼界，见识","phonetic_us":"/hə'raɪzn/","example":"In the distance, the dot of a boat appeared on the horizon. 远处小黑点般的一条小船出现在地平线上。","phonetic_uk":"/hə'raɪz(ə)n/"},{"translation":"adj. 地平的；水平的","phonetic_us":"/'hɔrə'zɑntl/","word":"horizontal","phonetic_uk":"/hɒrɪ'zɒnt(ə)l/","example":"a horizontal surface 水平面"},{"word":"horn","phonetic_us":"/hɔrn/","translation":"n. 号角；警报器；角","example":"A mature cow has horns. 成年母牛头上长有角。","phonetic_uk":"/hɔːn/"},{"word":"horrible","phonetic_us":"/ˈhɑːrəbl/","translation":"adj.  令人恐惧的， 可怕的； 骇人听闻的； 极讨厌的， 使人不愉快的； 糟透的","phonetic_uk":"/'hɒrəbl/","example":"The weather has been really horrible all week. 整个星期天气都很糟。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hɒrə/","example":"Dense smoke surrounded them, adding to the horror of the situation. 浓烟包围了他们，情形变得更加恐怖。","word":"horror","translation":"n. 恐怖；战栗；憎恶","phonetic_us":"/'hɔrɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hɔːs/","example":"a horse and cart 一辆马车","word":"horse","phonetic_us":"/hɔrs/","translation":"n. 马；马科动物"},{"example":"a two-hundred horsepower engine 两百马力的发动机","phonetic_uk":"/'hɔːspaʊə/","phonetic_us":"/'hɔrs'paʊɚ/","translation":"n. 马力","word":"horsepower"},{"example":"The local people were very kind and hospitable. 当地人非常友好热情。","phonetic_uk":"/hɑ'spɪtəbl/","word":"hospitable","translation":"adj. 热情友好的","phonetic_us":"/hɑ'spɪtəbl/"},{"translation":"n. 医院","phonetic_us":"/'hɑspɪtl/","word":"hospital","phonetic_uk":"/'hɒspɪt(ə)l/","example":"They are building a new hospital. 他们正在建一家新医院。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hɑspɪtə'laɪz/","translation":"v. 就医","word":"hospitalize","example":"When patients with SARS hospitalize massively, the department of nursing administration should take some measures to deploy timely, add and adjust nursing resource flexibly. 大规模收治SARS病人时医院护理部采取及时计划部署，灵活调整补充人力；","phonetic_uk":"/'hɒspɪtəlaɪz/"},{"translation":"n. 主人；东道主","phonetic_us":"/host/","word":"host","example":"Our host greeted us at the door. 主人在门口迎接我们。","phonetic_uk":"/həʊst/"},{"example":"The hostess introduced them. 女主人介绍了他们。","phonetic_uk":"/'həʊstɪs; -es; həʊ'stes/","word":"hostess","phonetic_us":"/'hostəs/","translation":"n. 女主人；空姐"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hɒstaɪl/","example":"Southampton fans gave their former coach a hostile reception . 南安普敦队的球迷对球队的前任教练很不友善。","word":"hostile","phonetic_us":"/ˈhɑstəl/","translation":"adj. 敌方的；不友善的"},{"example":"a hot curry 一种辛辣的咖喱","phonetic_uk":"/hɒt/","phonetic_us":"/hɑt/","translation":"adj. 热的；刺激的；辣的","word":"hot"},{"example":"I’ve booked the flights and the hotel. 我已订好机票和酒店。","phonetic_uk":"/həʊ'tel; əʊ-/","phonetic_us":"/ho'tɛl/","translation":"n. 旅馆","word":"hotel"},{"word":"hour","phonetic_us":"/'aʊɚ/","translation":"n. 小时；时间，时刻","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊə/","example":"The interview will last about two hours. 面试大概要持续两小时。"},{"word":"house","phonetic_us":"/haʊs/","translation":"n. 房屋，住宅；商号","phonetic_uk":"/haʊs/","example":"America’s oldest publishing house 美国历史最悠久的出版社"},{"word":"household","phonetic_us":"/'haʊshold/","translation":"n. 家庭，一家人","example":"A growing number of households have at least one computer. 越来越多的家庭拥有至少一台电脑。","phonetic_uk":"/'haʊshəʊld/"},{"example":"Married at nineteen, she was a traditional housewife and mother of four children. 她19岁就结婚了，是个传统的家庭主妇和4个孩子的母亲。","phonetic_uk":"/'haʊswaɪf/","phonetic_us":"/'haʊs'waɪf/","translation":"n. 家庭主妇","word":"housewife"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hauzɪŋ/","example":"health problems caused by bad housing 住房条件差引起的健康问题","translation":"n.  房屋， 住宅； 住房建筑， 住房供给； 外壳， 外罩","phonetic_us":"/'haʊzɪŋ/","word":"housing"},{"word":"how","phonetic_us":"/haʊ/","translation":"adv. 怎么；怎样；多少","phonetic_uk":"/haʊ/","example":"How do you spell your name? 你的名字怎么拼写？"},{"translation":"adv. 然而；不管怎样","phonetic_us":"/haʊ'ɛvɚ/","word":"however","phonetic_uk":"/haʊ'evə/","example":"This is a cheap and simple process. However, there are dangers. 这是个花钱少而又简单的方法，不过有危险。"},{"example":"the commercial hub of the region 该地区的商业中心","phonetic_uk":"/hʌb/","translation":"n. 中心","phonetic_us":"/hʌb/","word":"hub"},{"example":"a huge dog 一条大狗","phonetic_uk":"/hjuːdʒ/","translation":"adj. 巨大的，庞大的","phonetic_us":"/hjudʒ/","word":"huge"},{"word":"human","translation":"adj. 人的，人类的；n. 人","phonetic_us":"/'hjumən/","phonetic_uk":"/'hjuːmən/","example":"There are many different cell types in the human body . 人体中有许多种不同的细胞类型。"},{"translation":"n. 人类，总称人(性)","phonetic_us":"/hjʊ'mænəti/","word":"humanity","example":"We want a clean healthy environment for all humanity . 我们希望全人类拥有一个干净健康的生存环境。","phonetic_uk":"/hju:'mæniti/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hʌmbl/","example":"a modest and humble man 一个谦卑的男人","word":"humble","translation":"adj. 谦逊的；地位低下的","phonetic_us":"/'hʌmbl/"},{"word":"humid","phonetic_us":"/'hjumɪd/","translation":"adj. 湿的，湿气重的","example":"Tokyo is extremely humid in mid-summer. 仲夏的东京十分潮湿。","phonetic_uk":"/'hjuːmɪd/"},{"example":"humorous stories 诙谐的故事","phonetic_uk":"/'hjuːm(ə)rəs/","phonetic_us":"/'hjumərəs/","translation":"adj. 富于幽默的，诙谐的","word":"humorous"},{"example":"his humour and charm 他的幽默感和魅力","phonetic_uk":"/'hjuːmə/","word":"humour","translation":"n. 幽默，诙谐，幽默感","phonetic_us":"/'hju:mə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'hʌndrəd/","translation":"num. 百，百个；n. 许多","word":"hundred","example":"I’m not a hundred percent sure where she lives. 我不能完全确定她住在哪里。","phonetic_uk":"/'hʌndrəd/"},{"word":"hunger","translation":"n. 饿，饥饿；渴望","phonetic_us":"/'hʌŋɡɚ/","example":"Try to satisfy your hunger by eating some fruit. 吃些水果充充饥吧。","phonetic_uk":"/'hʌŋgə/"},{"translation":"adj. 饥饿的；渴望的","phonetic_us":"/'hʌŋɡri/","word":"hungry","phonetic_uk":"/'hʌŋgrɪ/","example":"I was cold, tired, and hungry. 我又冷，又累，又饿。"},{"phonetic_us":"/hʌnt/","translation":"n. 打猎；搜寻；v. 追猎","word":"hunt","phonetic_uk":"/hʌnt/","example":"The couple had helped in the hunt for the toddlers. 这对夫妇曾帮着寻找那些蹒跚学步的孩子。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hʌrɪ/","example":"If we hurry, we’ll get there in time. 要是赶紧的话，我们能及时到那里。","phonetic_us":"/'hɝrɪ/","translation":"v. 赶紧；v. 催促","word":"hurry"},{"word":"hurt","phonetic_us":"/hɝ​t/","translation":"v. 使受伤；使痛心","phonetic_uk":"/hɜːt/","example":"Was anyone hurt in the accident? 事故中有人受伤吗？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'hʌzbənd/","example":"Have you met my husband Roy? 你见过我的丈夫罗伊吗？","translation":"n. 丈夫","phonetic_us":"/'hʌzbənd/","word":"husband"},{"phonetic_uk":"/hʌt/","example":"a wooden hut 小木屋","translation":"n. 小屋，棚屋","phonetic_us":"/hʌt/","word":"hut"},{"translation":"n. 氢","phonetic_us":"/'haɪdrədʒən/","word":"hydrogen","phonetic_uk":"/'haɪdrədʒ(ə)n/","example":"Water contains hydrogen and oxygen. 水含有氢和氧。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/aɪ/","example":"I moved to this city six years ago. 六年前我搬到了这个城市。","translation":"pron. (主格)我","phonetic_us":"","word":"I"},{"translation":"n. 冰，冰块；v. 冰镇","phonetic_us":"/aɪs/","word":"ice","example":"Would you like some ice in your drink? 你饮料中要放点冰块吗？","phonetic_uk":"/aɪs/"},{"word":"idea","phonetic_us":"/aɪ'diə/","translation":"n. 想法；思想；意见","example":"You should talk to Ken – he's always full of good ideas. 你应该和肯谈谈，他总是满脑子好主意。","phonetic_uk":"/aɪ'dɪə/"},{"word":"ideal","translation":"adj. 理想的；观念的","phonetic_us":"/aɪ'diəl/","example":"advice on how to reach your ideal weight 如何达到理想体重的建议","phonetic_uk":"/aɪ'dɪəl; aɪ'diːəl/"},{"example":"four identical houses 四幢一模一样的房子","phonetic_uk":"/aɪˈdentɪkl/","translation":"adj. 相同的","phonetic_us":"/aɪ'dɛntɪkl/","word":"identical"},{"phonetic_us":"/aɪˌdentɪfɪ'keʃn/","translation":"n. 鉴定，识别；认同；身份证明","word":"identification","example":"Do you have any identification? 你有什么身份证明文件吗？","phonetic_uk":"/aɪ,dentɪfɪ'keɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"translation":"v. 认出，识别；视为","phonetic_us":"/aɪ'dɛntɪfaɪ/","word":"identify","example":"He was too far away to be able to identify faces. 他离得太远，没法看面孔认出谁是谁。","phonetic_uk":"/aɪ'dentifai/"},{"phonetic_us":"/aɪ'dɛntəti/","translation":"n. 身份","word":"identity","phonetic_uk":"/aɪ'dentɪtɪ/","example":"The identity of the killer is still unknown. 凶手的身份仍未查明。"},{"translation":"n. 习语，成语","phonetic_us":"/'ɪdɪəm/","word":"idiom","example":"the new musical idiom 新的音乐风格","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪdɪəm/"},{"word":"idle","phonetic_us":"/'aɪdl/","translation":"adj. 空闲的；懒散的","phonetic_uk":"/'aɪd(ə)l/","example":"I cannot afford to leave the land lying idle. 我不能让土地闲置。"},{"example":"We’ll stay at home if it rains. 如果下雨，我们就待在家里。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪf/","word":"if","phonetic_us":"/ɪf/","translation":"conj. 假如，如果"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪɡnərəns/","translation":"n. 无知，愚昧","word":"ignorance","phonetic_uk":"/'iɡnərəns/","example":"Excuse my ignorance, but how does it actually work? 请原谅我的无知，它究竟是如何运作的？"},{"word":"ignorant","translation":"adj. 无知的","phonetic_us":"/'ɪɡnərənt/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪgn(ə)r(ə)nt/","example":"an ignorant and uneducated man 不学无术的人"},{"word":"ignore","phonetic_us":"/ɪɡ'nɔr/","translation":"v. 忽视，不顾","phonetic_uk":"/ɪɡ'nɔ:(r)/","example":"The phone rang, but she ignored it. 电话铃响了，但她只当没听见。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪl/","translation":"adj. 有病的；坏的；adv. 坏","word":"ill","example":"Bridget can’t come – she’s ill. 布里奇特不能来了，她生病了。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪl/"},{"example":"illegal drugs 违禁药品","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'li:ɡl/","word":"illegal","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'ligl/","translation":"adj. 非法的"},{"word":"illness","phonetic_us":"/'ɪlnəs/","translation":"n. 病，疾病","example":"She had all the normal childhood illnesses. 儿童的常见病她小时候都得过。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɪlnəs/"},{"translation":"v. 说明,阐明","phonetic_us":"/'ɪləstret/","word":"illustrate","example":"Let me give an example to illustrate the point. 让我举个例子来说明这一点。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪləstreɪt/"},{"translation":"n. 说明，图解；例证","phonetic_us":"/,ɪlə'streʃən/","word":"illustration","phonetic_uk":"/ɪlə'streɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"The book contains 62 pages of illustrations. 这本书有62页插图。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪmɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 形象，声誉，印象","word":"image","example":"He had the clearest image in his mind of his mother and father. 他脑海中对父母的印象极其清晰。","phonetic_uk":"/'imidʒ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'mædʒɪn(ə)rɪ/","example":"As she listened, she played an imaginary piano on her knees. 她边听边在膝盖上作弹钢琴状。","word":"imaginary","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mædʒɪnɛri/","translation":"adj. 虚构的，想象的"},{"example":"a storyteller with an incredible imagination 想象力极丰富的讲故事者","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ,mædʒɪ'neɪʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/ɪ,mædʒɪ'neʃən/","translation":"n. 想象；想象力；空想","word":"imagination"},{"example":"Perhaps she’d never really been there at all – perhaps she’d just imagined it. 可能她从未到过那儿——也许这都是她的幻想。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'mædʒɪn/","translation":"v. 想象，设想；料想","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mædʒɪn/","word":"imagine"},{"example":"She was a splendid mimic and loved to imitate Winston Churchill. 她是个出色的模仿者，喜欢模仿温斯顿·丘吉尔。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪmɪteɪt/","phonetic_us":"/'ɪmɪtet/","translation":"v. 模仿","word":"imitate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'meʒ(ə)rəb(ə)l/","example":"The refugee problem has now reached immeasurable proportions. 难民问题现在已经到了无法估量的程度。","word":"immeasurable","translation":"adj. 无法估量的","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mɛʒərəbl/"},{"example":"Our immediate response to the attack was sheer horror. 我们对攻击的第一反应就是非常惊恐。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'miːdɪət/","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'midɪət/","translation":"adj. 立即的；直接的","word":"immediate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'miːdɪətlɪ/","example":"Those most immediately involved in the disaster will be given support. 灾害最直接受害者将获得援助。","word":"immediately","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'midɪətli/","translation":"adv. 立即；直接地"},{"example":"People who travel by rail still read an immense amount. 人们坐火车旅行时仍然会读很多书。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'mens/","word":"immense","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mɛns/","translation":"adj. 巨大的；极好的"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪmɪɡrənt/","translation":"n. 移民；adj. 移民的","word":"immigrant","example":"an illegal immigrant 非法移民","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪmɪgr(ə)nt/"},{"word":"immobile","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'mobl/","translation":"adj. 稳定的，不变的","example":"She could see a figure sitting immobile, facing the sea. 她看到一个人影面朝大海坐着，一动不动。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'məʊbaɪl/"},{"translation":"n. 影响","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'pækt/","word":"impact","example":"They say they expect the meeting to have a marked impact on the future of the country. 他们说期望这次会议对国家的未来产生显著的影响。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪmpækt/"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 不耐烦的，急躁的","word":"impatient","phonetic_uk":"","example":"The impatient drivers were beeping their horns. 不耐烦的司机们在按喇叭发嘟嘟声。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/im'pə:mənənsi/","word":"impermanency","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 非永久性"},{"example":"single-storey structures, built from cheap and impermanent materials 用廉价而不耐久的材料建成的单层建筑","phonetic_uk":"/im'pə:mənənt/","word":"impermanent","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'pɝmənənt/","translation":"adj. 非永久（性）的；不持久的，暂时的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪmplɪmənt/","example":"The government promised to implement a new system to control financial loan institutions. 政府许诺要实施新的制度来控制金融贷款机构。","word":"implement","phonetic_us":"/'ɪmplɪmɛnt/","translation":"v. 实施，执行"},{"word":"implementation","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 实现，履行","example":"They do, however, greatly affect the implementation of those patterns.  然而，它们的确对那些模式的 实现影响很大。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪmplɪmen'teɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"translation":"n. 含义，暗示","phonetic_us":"/'ɪmplɪ'keʃən/","word":"implication","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪmplɪˈkeɪʃn/","example":"They are called ‘Supertrams’, the implication being that (= which is meant to suggest that ) they are more advanced than earlier models. 它们被称作“超级电车”，这是暗指它们比先前的型号更先进。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/im'plai/","example":"an implied threat 隐含的威胁","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'plai/","translation":"v. 意味；暗示","word":"imply"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pɔːt/","translation":"n & v. 进口","phonetic_us":"/'ɪmpɔt/","word":"import"},{"example":"He was full of his own importance (= he behaved in an annoying way which showed that he thought he was very important ). 他自以为很了不起。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pɔːt(ə)ns/","word":"importance","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'pɔrtns/","translation":"n. 重要；重要性"},{"word":"important","translation":"adj. 重要的；有势力的","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'pɔrtnt/","example":"a very important meeting 很重要的会议","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pɔːt(ə)nt/"},{"word":"impose","translation":"v. 强加","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'poz/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pəʊz/","example":"The court can impose a fine. 法庭可以强制执行罚款。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pɒsɪb(ə)l/","example":"‘I want to speak to Mr Franks.’ ‘I’m afraid that’s impossible.’ “我想和弗兰克斯先生谈谈。”“恐怕不行。”","word":"impossible","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'pɑsəbl/","translation":"adj. 不可能的，办不到的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pres/","example":"Steve borrowed his dad’s sports car to impress his girlfriend. 史蒂夫借来他爸爸的跑车向女友炫耀。","word":"impress","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'prɛs/","translation":"v. 给…深刻印象"},{"word":"impression","translation":"n. 印；印象；印记","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'prɛʃən/","example":"When we looked around the school we got a very good impression. 我们参观了学校，对它的印象很好。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'preʃ(ə)n/"},{"example":"The figures certainly look impressive. 这些数字看上去确实很可观。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'presɪv/","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'prɛsɪv/","translation":"adj. 给人印象深刻的","word":"impressive"},{"example":"The government imprisoned all opposition leaders. 政府把反对派领导人全部监禁起来。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'prɪz(ə)n/","word":"imprison","translation":"v. 关押，监禁；限制","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'prɪzn/"},{"translation":"adj. 不合适的，不适当的","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'prɑpɚ/","word":"improper","phonetic_uk":"/ɪmˈprɒpə(r)/","example":"25 officers were investigated following allegations of improper conduct. 25名警官被指控行为不当而受到调查。"},{"word":"improve","translation":"v. 使更好；v. 改善","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'pruv/","example":"a course for students wishing to improve their English 为想提高英语水平的学生开设的一门课","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pruːv/"},{"translation":"n. 改进，改善；改进处","phonetic_us":"/ɪm'prʊvmənt/","word":"improvement","example":"Our results have shown some improvement this month. 我们的成绩这个月有所提高。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪm'pruːvm(ə)nt/"},{"translation":"prep. 在…里ad进，入","phonetic_us":"/ɪn/","word":"in","example":"There’s some sugar in the cupboard. 碗橱里有一些糖。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'ædɪkwəsɪ/","example":"Unemployment can cause feelings of inadequacy and low self-esteem. 失业会使人缺乏自信，产生自卑感。","word":"inadequacy","translation":"n. 不足","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ædɪkwəsi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'ædɪkwət/","example":"inadequate resources 资源缺乏","word":"inadequate","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ædɪkwət/","translation":"adj. 不足的，不够的"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪnə'proprɪət/","translation":"adj. 不合适的","word":"inappropriate","example":"There is no suggestion that clients have been sold inappropriate policies. 没有迹象表明向客户出售过不适当的保险单。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnə'prəʊprɪət/"},{"example":"As an added incentive, there’s a bottle of champagne for the best team. 给最优秀的队发一瓶香槟作为额外的鼓励。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'sentɪv/","word":"incentive","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'sɛntɪv/","translation":"n. 动机，刺激"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪntʃ/","translation":"n. 英寸","word":"inch","example":"The curtains were an inch too short. 窗帘短了一英寸。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn(t)ʃ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪnsɪdəns/","translation":"n. 几率，发生率","word":"incidence","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnsɪd(ə)ns/","example":"The incidence of breast cancer increases with age. 乳腺癌的发病率随着年龄的增长而上升。"},{"word":"incident","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnsɪdənt/","translation":"n. 发生的事；事件","example":"Am I at risk because of some incident in my sexual past? 我过去性生活中的某件事会使我处于危险境地吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnsɪd(ə)nt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈklaɪn/","example":"...the factors that incline us toward particular beliefs. …使我们倾向于特定信念的种种因素。","translation":"v. 倾向于","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'klaɪn/","word":"incline"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kluːd/","example":"Does the price include postage? 这个价格包含邮费吗？","translation":"v. 包含","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'klud/","word":"include"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪnkʌm/","translation":"n. 收入；收益；进款","word":"income","example":"low-income families 低收入家庭","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnkʌm/"},{"word":"incomparable","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'kɑmprəbl/","translation":"adj. 无比的，无可匹敌的","example":"an incomparable view of San Marco 圣马科美妙绝伦的景色","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kɒmp(ə)rəb(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ɪnkə'rɛkt/","translation":"adj. 不正确的，错误的","word":"incorrect","example":"The information you gave us was incorrect. 你给我们的信息不准确。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnkə'rekt/"},{"example":"The population increased dramatically in the first half of the century. 该世纪上半叶，人口大幅度增加。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kriːs/","word":"increase","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnkris/","translation":"vt&vi&n. 增加"},{"word":"increasingly","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'krisɪŋli/","translation":"adv. 日益，越来越多地","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kriːsɪŋlɪ/","example":"Marketing techniques are becoming increasingly sophisticated. 市场营销技巧越来越巧妙。"},{"example":"It’s incredible that he survived the fall. 他跌下去竟然能够生还，真不可思议。","phonetic_uk":"/in'kredəbl/","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'krɛdəbl/","translation":"adj. 不可思议的","word":"incredible"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'diːd/","example":"The blood tests prove that Vince is indeed the father. 验血证明文斯确实是父亲。","word":"indeed","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'did/","translation":"adv. 真正地；确实"},{"example":"Teachers find the report’s terminology so indefinite that it is confusing. 老师们发现报告的专门用语含义不明确，令人费解。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'defɪnɪt/","translation":"adj. 不明确的；不定的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dɛfɪnət/","word":"indefinite"},{"example":"The country has made great advances since independence. 该国自独立以来发展迅速。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪndɪ'pend(ə)ns/","word":"independence","phonetic_us":"/,ɪndɪ'pɛndəns/","translation":"n. 独立，自主，自立"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,ɪndɪ'pendənt/","example":"There are plans to split the corporation into a number of smaller independent companies. 有计划要把这家大企业分割成一些独立的小公司。","word":"independent","translation":"adj. 独立的；自主的","phonetic_us":"/'ɪndɪ'pɛndənt/"},{"word":"independently","phonetic_us":"/,ɪndɪ'pɛndəntli/","translation":"adv. 独立地","example":"In each of these cases, one of the models evolved independently of the other. 在这里的每种情况下，其中一个模型独立于另一个模型而发展。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪndɪ'pendəntlɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪndɛks/","translation":"n. 索引；指数；指标","word":"index","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪndeks/","example":"...the consumer price index. …消费价格指数。"},{"example":"Burma borders on India. 缅甸与印度毗邻。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪndɪə/","word":"India","translation":"n. 印度","phonetic_us":"/'ɪndɪə/"},{"word":"Indian","translation":"adj. 印度的；n. 印度人","phonetic_us":"/'ɪndɪən/","example":"...the Indian government. ...印度政府。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪndɪən/"},{"word":"indicate","phonetic_us":"/'ɪndɪket/","translation":"v. 表明","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪndɪkeɪt/","example":"The study indicates a connection between poverty and crime. 研究显示贫穷和犯罪有关联。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪndɪ'keɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Could you give me some indication as to when I am likely to receive a reply? 你能给我透露一下什么时候我能收到回复吗？","translation":"n. 指示；表示；表明","phonetic_us":"/,ɪndɪ'keʃən/","word":"indication"},{"word":"indifferent","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dɪfrənt/","translation":"adj. 冷漠的","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'dɪf(ə)r(ə)nt/","example":"People have become indifferent to the suffering of others. 人们已经变得对别人的痛苦漠不关心。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'dɪgnənt/","example":"an indignant reply 愤慨的回复","word":"indignant","translation":"adj. 愤慨的，义愤的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dɪɡnənt/"},{"example":"Losing weight is an indirect result of smoking cigarettes. 吸烟间接导致体重减轻。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪndɪ'rekt; ɪndaɪ-/","translation":"adj. 间接的；不坦率的","phonetic_us":"/,ɪndə'rɛkt/","word":"indirect"},{"word":"indispensable","translation":"adj. 必不可少的","phonetic_us":"/'ɪndɪ'spɛnsəbl/","phonetic_uk":"/,ɪndɪs'pɛnsəb!/","example":"Mobile phones have become an indispensable part of our lives. 移动电话已经成为我们生活中的必需品。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪndɪˈvɪdʒuəl/","example":"the rights of the individual 个人权利","translation":"n. 个人","phonetic_us":"/,ɪndɪ'vɪdʒuəl/","word":"individual"},{"example":"an indoor swimming pool 室内游泳池","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪndɔː/","word":"indoor","translation":"adv.  在室内， 在户内；adj. 室内的","phonetic_us":"/'ɪndɔr/"},{"word":"indoors","translation":"adv. 在室内，在屋里","phonetic_us":"/,ɪn'dɔrz/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'dɔːz/","example":"Let’s go indoors and have something to eat. 我们进屋吃点东西吧。"},{"word":"induce","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dus/","translation":"v. 引诱","example":"She had to be induced because the baby was four weeks late. 她的孩子晚了四星期仍未出生，因此要给她引产。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'djuːs/"},{"word":"industrial","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dʌstrɪəl/","translation":"adj. 工业的；产业的","example":"By 1900, Britain was a mainly industrial society. 到1900年英国已基本进入工业社会。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'dʌstrɪəl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈdʌstrɪəlʌɪz/","example":"Energy consumption rises as countries industrialize. 能源消耗随着各国工业化而增加。","word":"industrialize","translation":"v. 使工业化","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dʌstrɪəlaɪz/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪndəstri/","translation":"n. 工业，产业；勤劳","word":"industry","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪndəstrɪ/","example":"I work in the oil industry. 我在石油行业工作。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪnɪ'fɪʃ(ə)nt/","example":"an inefficient use of resources 资源的浪费","translation":"adj. 效率低的，无能的","phonetic_us":"/,ɪnɪ'fɪʃnt/","word":"inefficient"},{"translation":"adj. 不可避免的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ɛvɪtəbl/","word":"inevitable","example":"A further escalation of the crisis now seems inevitable. 危机的进一步升级现在看来已不可避免。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈevɪtəbl/"},{"word":"inexpensive","phonetic_us":"/,ɪnɪk'spɛnsɪv/","translation":"adj. 花费不多的，廉价的","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnɪk'spensɪv; ɪnek-/","example":"a good selection of inexpensive wines 可供选择的各种价格公道的葡萄酒"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnf(ə)nt/","example":"An infant’s skin is very sensitive. 幼儿的皮肤非常敏感。","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnfənt/","translation":"n. 婴儿；adj. 婴儿的","word":"infant"},{"translation":"v. 传染；感染","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'fɛkt/","word":"infect","example":"People with the virus may feel perfectly well, but they can still infect others. 带有这种病毒的人可能毫无症状，却仍可能传染他人。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'fekt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'fɜː/","example":"I inferred from what she said that you have not been well. 我从她的话里推断出你身体一直不大好。","translation":"v. 推论，推断；猜想","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'fɝ/","word":"infer"},{"word":"inference","translation":"n.  推断结果， 结论； 推论， 推理， 推断","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnfərəns/","example":"There were two inferences to be drawn from her letter. 从她的来信可以得到两种推论。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnfərəns/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'fɪrɪɚ/","translation":"adj. 下等的；劣等的","word":"inferior","example":"I felt very inferior among all those academics. 与那些大学教师在一起，我自惭形秽。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'fɪərɪə/"},{"example":"The universe is infinite. 宇宙是无限的。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnfɪnət/","word":"infinite","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnfɪnət/","translation":"adj. 无限的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'fleɪt/","example":"It took us half an hour to inflate the dinghy. 我们用了半小时给橡皮筏充好气。","translation":"v. 膨胀","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'flet/","word":"inflate"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'fleʃən/","translation":"n. 通货膨胀","word":"inflation","example":"Inflation is now at over 16%. 通货膨胀率现已超过16%。","phonetic_uk":"/in'fleiʃən/"},{"word":"influence","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnfluəns/","translation":"v & n. 影响","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnflʊəns/","example":"As a scientist, his influence was immense. 身为一名科学家，他的影响力极大。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪnfluˈenʃl/","example":"He had influential friends. 他有一些有影响力的朋友。","word":"influential","phonetic_us":"/,ɪnflu'ɛnʃl/","translation":"adj. 有影响力的"},{"example":"They decided to inform the police. 他们决定通知警察。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'fɔːm/","word":"inform","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'fɔrm/","translation":"v. 通知，向…报告"},{"translation":"n. 消息，信息；通知","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnfɚ'meʃən/","word":"information","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnfə'meɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"I need more information. 我需要更多信息。"},{"example":"Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl. 把所有食材都放在一个大碗里。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈgri:diənt/","translation":"n. 成分，原料","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ɡridɪənt/","word":"ingredient"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'hæbɪt/","translation":"v. 居住于，栖息于","word":"inhabit","example":"The woods are inhabited by many wild animals. 很多野生动物栖居在这片森林里。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'hæbɪt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'hæbɪtənt/","translation":"n. 居民，住户","word":"inhabitant","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'hæbɪt(ə)nt/","example":"a city of six million inhabitants 有600万居民的城市"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'herɪt/","example":"inherited wealth 继承的财富","word":"inherit","translation":"v. 继承","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'hɛrɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'nɪʃəl/","example":"an initial investment of £5,000 5,000英镑的初始投资","word":"initial","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'nɪʃəl/","translation":"adj. 最初的；词首的"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪ'nɪʃəli/","translation":"adv. 最初，起初","word":"initially","example":"Stan initially wanted to go to medical school. 斯坦最初想进医学院。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'nɪʃ(ə)lɪ/"},{"word":"initiate","translation":"v. 开始，发起","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'nɪʃɪet/","example":"They have decided to initiate legal proceedings against the newspaper. 他们决定向该报提起法律诉讼。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'nɪʃɪeɪt/"},{"example":"I wish my son would show more initiative. 我希望我的儿子能表现得再主动一些。","phonetic_uk":"/i'niʃətiv/","word":"initiative","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'nɪʃətɪv/","translation":"n. 主动权，自主权"},{"example":"The nurse gave me a tetanus injection. 护士给我打了破伤风预防针。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'dʒekʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 注射，注入；充满","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'dʒɛkʃən/","word":"injection"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪndʒə(r)/","example":"Angus injured his leg playing rugby. 安格斯在打橄榄球时弄伤了腿。","phonetic_us":"/'ɪndʒɚ/","translation":"v. 使受伤","word":"injure"},{"word":"injury","translation":"n. 损害，伤害；受伤处","phonetic_us":"","phonetic_uk":"","example":"She was taken to hospital with serious head injuries. 她头部受重伤被送到医院。"},{"word":"ink","translation":"n. 墨水，油墨","phonetic_us":"/ɪŋk/","example":"Please write in black ink. 请用黑色墨水书写。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪŋk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn/","example":"We’re staying at the Holiday Inn. 我们住在假日酒店。","phonetic_us":"/ɪn/","translation":"n. 小旅店；小酒店","word":"inn"},{"example":"an inner room 内室","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnə/","word":"inner","translation":"adj. 内部的；内心的","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnəs(ə)nt/","example":"Nobody would believe that I was innocent. 没人肯相信我是清白的。","word":"innocent","translation":"adj. 无辜的，天真的；","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnəsnt/"},{"example":"the need for large businesses to innovate 大公司革新的需要","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnəveɪt/","translation":"v. 创新，革新","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnəvet/","word":"innovate"},{"word":"innovation","phonetic_us":"/,ɪnə'veʃən/","translation":"n. 改革，创新","example":"We must encourage innovation if the company is to remain competitive. 公司要想保持竞争力，就必须鼓励革新。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪnəˈveɪʃn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪnəvetɪv/","translation":"adj.  创新的， 革新的","word":"innovative","example":"an innovative approach to language teaching 创新的语言教学法","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnəveɪtɪv/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪn'pʊt/","translation":"n. 输入；投入的资金","word":"input","example":"If the input data specified it, the file will close and the process terminates. 如果输入数据指定，该文件就会关闭，数据处理终止。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnpʊt/"},{"word":"inquire","translation":"v. 询问","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'kwaɪr/","example":"‘Why are you doing that?’ the boy inquired. “你为什么这么做？”男孩问道。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kwaɪə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'kwaɪri; 'ɪn,kwaɪri; 'ɪnkwəri; 'ɪŋkwaɪri/","translation":"n. 询问","word":"inquiry","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'kwaɪərɪ/","example":"I don’t know who sent the gift, but I’ll make some inquiries. 我不知道礼物是谁送的，但我会打听一下。"},{"example":"an insect bite 昆虫的叮咬","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnsekt/","word":"insect","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnsɛkt/","translation":"n. 昆虫，虫"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,ɪnsɪ'kjʊə;/","example":"Many of them work in low-paid insecure jobs. 他们当中的许多人都做着薪水低、不稳定的工作。","word":"insecure","translation":"adj. 不安全的","phonetic_us":"/,ɪnsɪ'kjʊr/"},{"translation":"v. 插入；嵌入；登载","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnsɝt/","word":"insert","example":"He took a small key from his pocket and slowly inserted it into the lock. 他从衣袋里掏出一把小钥匙，然后缓缓地将其插入锁孔里。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'sɜːt/"},{"translation":"prep. 在…里面；n. 内部","phonetic_us":"/'ɪn'saɪd/","word":"inside","example":"He concealed the key inside his tie. 他把钥匙藏在领带里面。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'saɪd/"},{"word":"insight","phonetic_us":"/'ɪn'saɪt/","translation":"n. 洞察力，洞悉","example":"a woman of great insight 一位极有眼光的妇女","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnsaɪt/"},{"word":"insist","translation":"v. 主张，坚持","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'sɪst/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'sɪst/","example":"Stay for supper – I insist! 留下来吃晚餐——一定的！"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'spɛkt/","translation":"v. 检查，审查；检阅","word":"inspect","example":"I got out of the car to inspect the damage. 我下车查看损坏情况。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'spekt/"},{"word":"inspection","translation":"n. 检查，审查；检阅","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'spɛkʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'spekʃn/","example":"An inspection was carried out at the school. 有人来学校视察了一遍。"},{"word":"inspector","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'spɛktɚ/","translation":"n. 检查员","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'spektə/","example":"ticket inspectors 查票员"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪnspə'reɪʃn/","example":"The Malvern Hills have provided inspiration for many artists and musicians over the decades. 几十年来，莫尔文丘陵为很多艺术家和音乐家提供了灵感。","translation":"n. 灵感","phonetic_us":"/ˌɪnspəˈreʃən/","word":"inspiration"},{"translation":"v. 激发；鼓舞；使产生灵感","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'spaɪɚ/","word":"inspire","example":"We need someone who can inspire the team. 我们需要一个能鼓舞团队士气的人。","phonetic_uk":"/in'spaɪə/"},{"word":"install","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'stɔl/","translation":"v. 安装","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈstɔ:l/","example":"They’ve installed the new computer network at last. 他们终于安装了新电脑网络。"},{"word":"installation","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnstə'leʃən/","translation":"n. 安装，就任","phonetic_uk":"/,ɪnstə'leɪʃən/","example":"the installation and maintenance of alarm systems 警报系统的安装和维护"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'stɔ:lmənt/","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'stɔlmənt/","translation":"n. 安装，分期付款","word":"installment"},{"word":"instance","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnstəns/","translation":"n. 情况，例子","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɪnstəns/","example":"We need to rethink the way we consume energy. Take, for instance, our approach to transport. 我们需要重新考虑我们使用能源的方式，例如我们的运输方式。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪnstənt/","translation":"adj. 立即的；紧急的；速溶的，方便的","word":"instant","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnstənt/","example":"an instant success 马到成功"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪnstəntli/","translation":"adv. 立即，即刻","word":"instantly","example":"All four victims died instantly. 四名受害人全部当即死亡。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnst(ə)ntlɪ/"},{"example":"You probably picked up my keys instead of yours. 你可能没拿你的钥匙而错拿了我的。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'sted/","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'stɛd/","translation":"adv. 代替，顶替；反而","word":"instead"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɪnstɪŋkt/","translation":"n. 本能；直觉；生性","word":"instinct","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnstɪŋ(k)t/","example":"Her instinct told her that something was wrong. 直觉告诉她有些不对劲。"},{"translation":"n & v. 建立","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnstɪtut/","word":"institute","example":"We will institute a number of measures to better safeguard the public. 我们将制定许多措施更好地保护公众。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnstɪtju:t/"},{"word":"institution","translation":"n. 社会公共机构；制度，习俗；设立，制定","phonetic_us":"/,ɪnstɪ'tuʃən/","example":"powerful institutions such as world banks 诸如世界银行之类的强大机构","phonetic_uk":"/,insti'tju:ʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'strʌkt/","example":"Eva went straight to the hotel, as instructed (= as she had been told ). 伊娃按照指示径直去了宾馆。","word":"instruct","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'strʌkt/","translation":"v. 指导；通知；命令；教授"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'strʌkʃən/","example":"Press ‘Enter’ and follow the on-screen instructions. 按回车键，然后按照电脑屏幕上的指示来操作。","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'strʌkʃən/","translation":"n. 命令，指示，用法说明","word":"instruction"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnstrumənt/","example":"surgical instruments 外科(手术)器械","translation":"n. 仪器，器械，工具","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnstrəmənt/","word":"instrument"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪnsə'fɪʃ(ə)nt/","example":"Insufficient resources have been devoted to the health service. 用于医疗保健服务的资源不足。","translation":"adj. 不足的；不适当的","phonetic_us":"/,ɪnsə'fɪʃnt/","word":"insufficient"},{"example":"Nobody insults my family and gets away with it! 谁也别想侮辱了我的家人之后就这么算了！","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'sʌlt/","translation":"v. 侮辱","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'sʌlt/","word":"insult"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'ʃʊər(ə)ns/","example":"Your father took out insurance to cover the mortgage. 你父亲购买了抵押借款保险。","word":"insurance","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ʃʊrəns/","translation":"n. 保险；保险费"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ʃʊr/","translation":"v. 给…保险；确保","word":"insure","example":"Have you insured the contents of your home? 你给家庭财产投保了吗？","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'ʃɔː; ɪn'ʃʊə/"},{"example":"Your intake of alcohol should not exceed two units per day. 你每天酒精摄入量不能超过两个单位。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɪnteɪk/","word":"intake","phonetic_us":"/'ɪn'tek/","translation":"n. 摄入"},{"example":"He didn't integrate successfully into the Italian way of life. 他没有成功融入到意大利的生活方式中去。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪntɪgreɪt/","word":"integrate","translation":"v.  成为一体， 合并","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntɪɡret/"},{"word":"integration","translation":"n.  综合","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntə'greʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪntɪ'greɪʃn/","example":"problems of racial integration 种族融合的问题"},{"example":"the territorial integrity of the country 国家的领土完整","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tegrɪtɪ/","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛɡrəti/","translation":"n. 完整，综合","word":"integrity"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ɪntə'lɛktʃuəl/","translation":"n. 知识分子；adj. 智力的","word":"intellectual","example":"a leading British intellectual 一位顶尖的英国知识分子","phonetic_uk":"/,ɪntə'lektʃʊəl; -tjʊəl/"},{"translation":"n. 智力，智慧，理解力","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛlɪdʒəns/","word":"intelligence","phonetic_uk":"/in'telidʒəns/","example":"To be good at the game, you need a reasonable level of intelligence. 要想把这种游戏玩好，需要一定的智力水平。"},{"word":"intelligent","translation":"adj. 智能的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛlɪdʒənt/","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'telɪdʒ(ə)nt/","example":"a group of highly intelligent (= very intelligent )students 一组聪明异常的学生"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tend/","example":"Oddly enough, that is precisely what I intend. 说也奇怪， 那正是我的打算。","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛnd/","translation":"v. 打算","word":"intend"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tens/","example":"Young people today are under intense pressure to succeed. 如今的年轻人面临要出人头地的巨大压力。","translation":"adj. 强烈的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛns/","word":"intense"},{"example":"The intensity of the hurricane was frightening. 飓风的猛烈程度令人恐惧。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tensɪtɪ/","word":"intensity","translation":"n. 强烈，剧烈；强度","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛnsəti/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tensɪv/","example":"a one-week intensive course in English 为期一周的英语强化课程","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛnsɪv/","translation":"adj. 加强的；精耕细作的","word":"intensive"},{"example":"They went into town with the intention of visiting the library. 他们进了城，打算参观图书馆。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnˈtenʃn/","translation":"n. 打算，意图","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛnʃən/","word":"intention"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tenʃ(ə)n(ə)l/","example":"I did trip him, but it wasn’t intentional. 我的确把他绊倒了，但不是故意的。","word":"intentional","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɛnʃənl/","translation":"adj. 故意的，有意识的"},{"example":"But you only get the maximum benefit if you implement all of them, because their power comes from their interaction. 但您只有在实现所有方法的情况下才能获得最多的收益，因为它们的力量来自于它们之间的相互作用。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪntər'ækʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 相互作用；干扰","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntə'rækʃən/","word":"interaction"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪntəkə'nekt/","example":"In Freud’s theory, the two areas of sexuality and violence are interconnected. 按照弗洛伊德的理论，性和暴力这两个方面是相互关联的。","translation":"v. 相互联系","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚkə'nɛkt/","word":"interconnect"},{"example":"...the interdependence of nations. …国家间的相互依赖。","phonetic_uk":"/,ɪntədɪ'pendəns/","word":"interdependence","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚdɪ'pɛndəns/","translation":"n. 相互依靠"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnt(ə)rɪst/","example":"I watched the first few episodes, but soon lost interest. 我看了前几集，但很快就失去了兴趣。","word":"interest","translation":"n. 兴趣；利益；利息","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntrəst/"},{"word":"interesting","translation":"adj. 有趣的，引人入胜的","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntrəstɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnt(ə)rɪstɪŋ/","example":"That’s an interesting question. 那是一个有趣的问题。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚ'fɪr/","translation":"v. 干涉，干预；妨碍","word":"interfere","phonetic_uk":"/ɪntə'fɪə/","example":"My daughter-in-law said that I was interfering, but I was only trying to help. 我的儿媳说我多管闲事，但我只是想帮忙。"},{"example":"Industrial relations should be free from state interference. 劳资关系应不受政府干预。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪntə'fɪər(ə)ns/","word":"interference","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚ'fɪrəns/","translation":"n. 干涉，干预；阻碍"},{"word":"interior","translation":"adj. 内的；内地的n内部","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɪrɪɚ/","example":"The interior walls are all painted white. 室内墙壁都粉刷成了白色。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tɪɜːrɪə/"},{"example":"an intermediate stage during which the disease is dormant 疾病处于潜伏状态的中期","phonetic_uk":"/,ɪntə'miːdɪət/","translation":"adj. 中间的；中级的","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚ'midɪət/","word":"intermediate"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɝnl/","translation":"adj. 内的；国内的","word":"internal","example":"We have no interest in interfering in the internal affairs of other countries. 我们对干涉其他国家内政不感兴趣。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tɜːn(ə)l/"},{"example":"the response of the international community 国际社会的反响","phonetic_uk":"/ɪntə'næʃ(ə)n(ə)l/","word":"international","translation":"adj. 国际的，世界(性)的","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚ'næʃnəl/"},{"word":"internship","translation":"n.  实习生身份； 实习医师期","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntɝnʃɪp/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪntɜːnʃɪp/","example":"...an internship in surgery in New York. …一个在纽约做外科实习的职位。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tɜ:prɪt/","example":"Freud’s attempts to interpret the meaning of dreams 弗洛伊德对梦的含义的解析","word":"interpret","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɝprɪt/","translation":"v. 解释"},{"translation":"n. 阐释，说明","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɝprɪ'teʃən/","word":"interpretation","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tɜːprɪ'teʃən/","example":"One possible interpretation is that they want you to resign. 一种可能的解释是，他们想要你辞职。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'tɜːprɪtə/","example":"Speaking through an interpreter (= using an interpreter ), Ahmed said, ‘I’m very worried about my wife and children.’ 艾哈迈德通过口译者说:“我很担心我的妻子和孩子们。”","translation":"n. 译员，口译者","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'tɝprɪtɚ/","word":"interpreter"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ɪntə'reʃl/","translation":"adj. 种族间的","word":"interracial","phonetic_uk":"/ɪntə'reɪʃ(ə)l/","example":"interracial marriage 种族间的通婚"},{"example":"Will you stop interrupting me! 别打断我的话！","phonetic_uk":"/ɪntə'rʌpt/","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntə'rʌpt/","translation":"v. 打断，打扰；中止","word":"interrupt"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ɪntə'rʌpʃən/","translation":"n. 打扰，中断","word":"interruption","example":"For tasks that execute code in a loop, it is common to check for interruption only once per loop iteration. 对于执行一个循环中的代码的任务，通常只需为每一个循环迭代检查一次中断。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪntəˈrʌpʃn/"},{"example":"He left the room, returning after a short interval with a message. 他离开房间，过了一会儿就带回来一条消息。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪntəv(ə)l/","translation":"n. 间隔；休息；间距","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntɚvl/","word":"interval"},{"example":"The army will have to intervene to prevent further fighting. 军队将不得不干预以阻止进一步的战斗。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪntə'viːn/","word":"intervene","translation":"vi.  干涉， 调停， 干预； 插入， 介入； 干扰， 打扰","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚ'vin/"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ɪntɚ'vɛnʃən/","translation":"n. 干涉","word":"intervention","example":"government intervention to regulate prices 政府介入控制物价","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɪntə'venʃn/"},{"example":"a portfolio of work presented at interview 在面试时呈递的工作成果样本","phonetic_uk":"/'intəvju:/","phonetic_us":"/'ɪntɚvju/","translation":"n. 会见；面谈（试）；v. 采访","word":"interview"},{"example":"an intimate friend of Picasso’s 毕加索的一个密友","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪntɪmət/","word":"intimate","phonetic_us":"/ˈɪntəmɪt/","translation":"adj. 亲密的；个人的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪntʊ; 'ɪntə/","example":"Come into the office. 到办公室里来。","phonetic_us":"/ˈɪntu/","translation":"prep. 进，入；进入到","word":"into"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪntrə'djuːs/","example":"Have you two been introduced? Tom, this is Greg. 有人给你们俩互相介绍了吗？汤姆，这位是格雷格。","word":"introduce","phonetic_us":"/ˌɪntrə'dus/","translation":"v. 介绍；引进，传入"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,ɪntrə'dʌkʃ(ə)n/","example":"Pete, are you going to make the introductions? 皮特，你来作一下介绍吧。","word":"introduction","translation":"n. 介绍；引进；引言","phonetic_us":"/,ɪntrə'dʌkʃən/"},{"word":"invade","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'ved/","translation":"v. 侵入，侵略","example":"The Romans invaded Britain 2,000 years ago. 2,000年前古罗马人入侵了英国。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'veɪd/"},{"example":"Without the right date stamped on it, your ticket will be invalid. 票上若没有加盖正确日期就是废票。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vælɪd/","phonetic_us":"/ˈɪnvəlɪd；ɪnˈvælɪd/","translation":"adj. 无效的","word":"invalid"},{"translation":"adv. 不变地，一直","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɛrɪəbli/","word":"invariably","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'veərɪəblɪ/","example":"It invariably rains when I go there. 我每次去那儿都下雨。"},{"word":"invasion","translation":"n. 入侵，侵略；侵犯","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'veʒn/","example":"the annual invasion of teenagers for the Glastonbury Festival 每年前来参加格拉斯顿伯里音乐节的青少年的涌入","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'veɪʒ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vent/","example":"Alexander Graham Bell invented the telephone in 1876. 亚历山大 · 格雷厄姆 · 贝尔于1876年发明了电话。","translation":"v. 发明，创造；捏造","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɛnt/","word":"invent"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɛnʃən/","translation":"n. 发明，创造；捏造","word":"invention","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'venʃ(ə)n/","example":"The dishwasher is a wonderful invention. 洗碗机是一项奇妙的发明。"},{"example":"...Alexander Graham Bell, the inventor of the telephone. …亚历山大·格雷厄姆·贝尔，电话的发明者。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'ventə/","word":"inventor","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɛntɚ/","translation":"n. 发明者；发明家"},{"word":"invest","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɛst/","translation":"v. 投资","example":"I’ve got a few thousand dollars I’m looking to invest. 我有几千美元想作投资。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vest/"},{"example":"The state police are investigating the incident. 州警察正调查此事。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vestɪgeɪt/","word":"investigate","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɛstɪɡet/","translation":"v. 调查"},{"example":"The investigation continued for nearly three years. 调查持续了近三年。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn,vestɪ'geɪʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 调查，调查研究","phonetic_us":"/ɪn,vɛstɪ'ɡeʃən/","word":"investigation"},{"word":"investment","translation":"n. 投资，投资额，投入","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɛstmənt/","example":"We plan to buy some property as an investment. 我们打算买些房地产作为投资。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'ves(t)m(ə)nt/"},{"translation":"adj.  不能征服的， 无敌的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɪnsəbl/","word":"invincible","example":"an invincible army 无敌的军队","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vɪnsəbl/"},{"translation":"adj. 看不见的，无形的","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɪzəbl/","word":"invisible","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vɪzɪb(ə)l/","example":"The house was surrounded by trees, and invisible from the road. 这所房子树木环绕，从路上是看不见的。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˌɪnvɪˈteɪʃn/","translation":"n. 邀请，招待；请柬","word":"invitation","phonetic_uk":"/ɪnvɪ'teɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"They were always dropping by, usually without invitation. 他们常常来串门，通常不请自来。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vaɪt/","translation":"v. 邀请，聘请；招待","word":"invite","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vaɪt/","example":"I’m afraid I wasn’t invited. 恐怕我没有受到邀请。"},{"word":"involve","translation":"v. 卷入，包含","phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɑlv/","example":"What will the job involve? 这份工作包括什么？","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vɒlv/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪn'vɔlvmənt/","translation":"n.  连累； 包含","word":"involvement","example":"School officials say they welcome parental involvement. 校方说他们欢迎学生父母参与。","phonetic_uk":"/ɪn'vɒlvmənt/"},{"word":"inward","phonetic_us":"/'ɪnwɚd/","translation":"adj. 里面的；adv. 向内","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪnwəd/","example":"He pushed open the front door, which swung inward with a groan. 他推开前门，门呀的一声向里开了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'aɪən/","example":"the iron and steel industry 钢铁工业","word":"iron","translation":"n. 铁；烙铁；v. 烫(衣)","phonetic_us":"/'aɪɚn/"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"adv. 不合理地，无理性地","word":"irrationally","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'ræʃnəlɪ/","example":""},{"word":"irregular","translation":"adj. 不规律的","phonetic_us":"/ɪ'rɛɡjəlɚ/","example":"a jagged, irregular coastline 锯齿状不规则的海岸线","phonetic_uk":"/ɪ'regjʊlə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɪrɪteɪt/","example":"It really irritates me when he doesn’t help around the house. 家里的事情他一点都不帮忙，真让我恼火。","phonetic_us":"/'ɪrɪtet/","translation":"v. 激怒","word":"irritate"},{"word":"island","translation":"n. 岛，岛屿","phonetic_us":"/'aɪlənd/","phonetic_uk":"/'aɪlənd/","example":"The Cayman Islands 开曼群岛"},{"translation":"v. 使隔离，使孤立","phonetic_us":"/aɪslˌet/","word":"isolate","example":"The town was isolated by the floods. 洪水使该镇与外界隔绝。","phonetic_uk":"/'aɪsəleɪt/"},{"word":"issue","translation":"v. 发行；n. 问题","phonetic_us":"/'ɪʃu/","example":"Silva issued a statement denying all knowledge of the affair. 西尔瓦发表声明，宣称对此事一无所知。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɪʃu:/"},{"word":"it","phonetic_us":"/aɪ ti/","translation":"pron. 这，那，它","example":"‘Where’s your office?’ ‘It’s on the third floor.’ “你的办公室在哪儿？”“在三楼。”","phonetic_uk":"/aɪ ti/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɪˈtælɪən/","example":"","word":"Italian","phonetic_us":"/ɪˈtæljən/","translation":"adj. 意大利的n意大利人"},{"example":"He opened the cardboard box and took out each item. 他打开纸板箱把里面的物品一一拿出来。","phonetic_uk":"/'aɪtəm/","translation":"n. 条，条款","phonetic_us":"/'aɪtəm/","word":"item"},{"phonetic_us":"/ɪts/","translation":"pron. 它的","word":"its","phonetic_uk":"/ɪts/","example":"He emphasized its importance to me. 他向我强调它的重要性。"},{"word":"itself","phonetic_us":"/ɪt'sɛlf/","translation":"pron. 它自己；自身","phonetic_uk":"/ɪt'self/","example":"The cat lay on the sofa, washing itself. 猫躺在沙发上把自己舔干。"},{"example":"Gene has to wear a jacket and tie to work. 吉恩上班得穿西装打领带。","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒækɪt/","phonetic_us":"/'dʒækɪt/","translation":"n. 短上衣，茄克衫","word":"jacket"},{"translation":"n. 监狱；v. 监禁","phonetic_us":"/dʒel/","word":"jail","phonetic_uk":"/dʒeɪl/","example":"He’s been in jail for three months already. 他已经入狱三个月。"},{"example":"strawberry jam 草莓酱","phonetic_uk":"/dʒæm/","word":"jam","phonetic_us":"/dʒæm/","translation":"n. 果酱"},{"example":"We always have snow in January. 我们这里1月份总会下雪。","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒænjʊ(ə)rɪ/","word":"January","translation":"n. 一月","phonetic_us":"/'dʒænjʊ'ɛri/"},{"phonetic_us":"/dʒə'pæn/","translation":"n. 日本，日本国","word":"Japan","phonetic_uk":"/dʒə'pæn/","example":""},{"example":"a Japanese car 日本(汽)车","phonetic_uk":"/ˌdʒæpə'ni:z/","translation":"adj. 日本的；n. 日本人","phonetic_us":"/,dʒæpə'niz/","word":"Japanese"},{"translation":"n. 罐子，坛子，广口瓶","phonetic_us":"/dʒɑr/","word":"jar","example":"a jam jar 果酱罐","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɑː/"},{"translation":"n. 颌，颚","phonetic_us":"/dʒɔ/","word":"jaw","example":"a broken jaw 碎裂的颌骨","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɔː/"},{"word":"jazz","translation":"n. 爵士音乐，爵士舞曲","phonetic_us":"/dʒæz/","example":"a jazz band 爵士乐队","phonetic_uk":"/dʒæz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dʒeləs/","example":"She got insanely jealous and there was a terrible fight. 她变得过分地猜忌，接着是一场激烈的打斗。","word":"jealous","translation":"adj. 妒忌的；猜疑的","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɛləs/"},{"example":"...a young man in jeans and a worn T-shirt. …一个穿着牛仔裤和破旧T恤衫的年轻人。","phonetic_uk":"/dʒiːnz/","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n.  工装裤， 牛仔裤","word":"jeans"},{"word":"jet","translation":"n. 喷气式飞机；喷嘴","phonetic_us":"/dʒɛt/","example":"He owns a private jet. 他拥有一架私人喷气式飞机。","phonetic_uk":"/jɛt/"},{"example":"She loved dressing up and wearing priceless jewels. 她喜欢穿上盛装，戴上极为昂贵的珠宝首饰。","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒuːəl/","word":"jewel","phonetic_us":"/'dʒuəl/","translation":"n. 宝石；宝石饰物"},{"word":"jewish","translation":"adj. 犹太人的","phonetic_us":"/'dʒʊɪʃ/","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒuːɪʃ/","example":"...the Jewish festival of Passover. …犹太逾越节。"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 职业；工作；零活","word":"job","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɒb/","example":"Do you enjoy your job? 你喜欢自己的工作吗？"},{"word":"join","phonetic_us":"/dʒɔɪn/","translation":"v. 参加；连接","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɒɪn/","example":"Many sacrificed their weekend to join the hunt for the missing girl. 许多人牺牲周末时间，加入了寻找失踪女孩的行动。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dʒɒɪnt/","example":"The two ministers have issued a joint statement. 两位部长发布了一项联合声明。","phonetic_us":"/dʒɔɪnt/","translation":"adj. 联合的","word":"joint"},{"example":"I couldn’t go out with someone for a joke, could you? 我可不能拿谈恋爱当儿戏，对不对？","phonetic_uk":"/dʒəʊk/","translation":"n. 笑话；v. 说笑话","phonetic_us":"/dʒok/","word":"joke"},{"example":"Everybody was in a very relaxed and jolly mood. 大家的心情都非常轻松愉快。","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒɒlɪ/","word":"jolly","translation":"adj. 快活的；令人高兴的","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɑli/"},{"word":"journal","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɝnl/","translation":"n. 日报，杂志；日志","example":"the British Medical Journal 《英国医学杂志》","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒɜːn(ə)l/"},{"example":"a well-known journalist and broadcaster 一位著名的新闻记者兼播音员","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒɜːn(ə)lɪst/","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɝnəlɪst/","translation":"n. 记者，新闻工作者","word":"journalist"},{"word":"journey","translation":"n. 旅行，旅程；n. 旅行","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɝni/","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒɜːnɪ/","example":"the friends they made on the journey 他们在旅途中交下的朋友"},{"example":"the look of joy on her face 她脸上的喜悦表情","phonetic_uk":"/dʒɒɪ/","word":"joy","translation":"n. 欢乐，喜悦；乐事","phonetic_us":"/dʒɔɪ/"},{"word":"joyful","phonetic_us":"/'dʒɔɪfl/","translation":"adj. 十分喜悦的，快乐的","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒɒɪfʊl; -f(ə)l/","example":"A wedding is a joyful celebration of love. 婚礼是令人喜悦的爱情庆典。"},{"word":"judge","phonetic_us":"/dʒʌdʒ/","translation":"n. 法官；裁判员","phonetic_uk":"/dʒʌdʒ/","example":"The trial judge specifies the number of years to be spent in prison. 由主审法官确定刑期。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'dʒʌdʒm(ə)nt/","example":"He trusted in his judgement. 他相信他的判断。","word":"judgement","phonetic_us":"/'dʒʌdʒmənt/","translation":"n. 判断，决定"},{"example":"a carton of orange juice 一纸盒橙汁","phonetic_uk":"/dʒuːs/","word":"juice","translation":"n. (水果等)汁，液","phonetic_us":"/dʒus/"},{"translation":"n. 七月","phonetic_us":"/dʒʊˈlaɪ/","word":"July","phonetic_uk":"/dʒʊˈlaɪ/","example":"But from February through July, Joy sat around with nothing to do. 但是从二月到七月，乔伊又无事可做了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/dʒʌmp/","example":"The cats jumped down and came to meet us. 这些猫跳下来，过来迎接我们。","phonetic_us":"/dʒʌmp/","translation":"v. 跳；暴涨；v. 跳过","word":"jump"},{"example":"He spent two and a half weeks with us in June 1986. 1986年6月，他和我们呆了两个半星期。","phonetic_uk":"/dʒu:n/","translation":"n. 六月","phonetic_us":"/dʒun/","word":"June"},{"translation":"n. 丛林，密林，莽丛","phonetic_us":"/'dʒʌŋɡl/","word":"jungle","example":"the Amazon jungle 亚马孙丛林","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒʌŋg(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'dʒunɪɚ/","translation":"adj. 年少的；n. 晚辈","word":"junior","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒuːnɪə/","example":"the junior football club 青少年足球俱乐部"},{"example":"the members of the jury 陪审团成员","phonetic_uk":"/'dʒʊərɪ/","word":"jury","phonetic_us":"/'dʒʊri/","translation":"n. 陪审团；评奖团"},{"word":"just","phonetic_us":"/dʒʌst/","translation":"adv. 刚才；只是；正好","phonetic_uk":"/dʒʌst/","example":"A good strong cup of coffee is just what I need right now. 我现在正需要喝一杯浓浓的咖啡。"},{"translation":"n. 公正","phonetic_us":"/'dʒʌstɪs/","word":"justice","example":"Children have a strong sense of justice. 儿童有很强的正义感。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdʒʌstɪs/"},{"translation":"v. 证明……正当","phonetic_us":"/'dʒʌstə'fai/","word":"justify","example":"Ministers must appear before Parliament and justify their actions. 大臣们必须就自己的行为向议会作出解释。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈdʒʌstɪfaɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kin/","translation":"adj. 热心的；激烈的","word":"keen","example":"a keen photographer 一个摄影迷","phonetic_uk":"/kiːn/"},{"word":"keenly","translation":"adv. 敏锐地","phonetic_us":"/'ki:nli/","phonetic_uk":"/ki:nlɪ/","example":"He observes keenly but says very little. 他观察敏锐， 但说得很少。"},{"word":"keep","phonetic_us":"/kip/","translation":"v. 保持；坚持","example":"The noise kept him awake. 噪音使他一直醒着。","phonetic_uk":"/kiːp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kiːpə/","example":"a beekeeper 养蜂人","phonetic_us":"/'kipɚ/","translation":"n. 看护人；饲养员","word":"keeper"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ket(ə)l/","example":"She filled the kettle and switched it on. 她把水壶灌满，打开了开关。","phonetic_us":"/'kɛtl/","translation":"n. 水壶，水锅","word":"kettle"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kiː/","example":"A bunch of keys hung from his belt. 他的皮带上挂着一串钥匙。","translation":"n. 钥匙；键；答案","phonetic_us":"","word":"key"},{"word":"keyboard","translation":"n. 键盘","phonetic_us":"/'ki'bɔrd/","example":"a computer keyboard 计算机键盘","phonetic_uk":"/'kiːbɔːd/"},{"example":"He kicked the door hard. 他用力踢门。","phonetic_uk":"/kɪk/","word":"kick","phonetic_us":"/kɪk/","translation":"vi&vt&n. 踢"},{"phonetic_us":"/kɪd/","translation":"n. 小孩，儿童，少年","word":"kid","example":"She’d always loved animals since she was a little kid. 她从小就喜爱动物。","phonetic_uk":"/kɪd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɪl/","example":"Why did she kill her husband? 她为什么杀死丈夫？","word":"kill","phonetic_us":"/kɪl/","translation":"v. 杀死；扼杀；消磨"},{"translation":"n. 千克，公斤","phonetic_us":"/'kɪləɡræm/","word":"kilogram","example":"By comparison, one kilogram of tomatoes requires 160 litres of water. 相比之下，生产一公斤的番茄需要160升水。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkɪləɡræm/"},{"word":"kilometre","phonetic_us":"/kɪ'lɔmɪtɚ/","translation":"n. 千米，公里","phonetic_uk":"/'kɪlə,miːtə; kɪ'lɒmɪtə/","example":"He was a kilometre out from home when the storm struck. 暴风雨袭来时他离家有一公里远。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kaɪnd/","example":"Get me a sandwich – any kind will do. 给我一份三明治，随便哪种都可以。","word":"kind","translation":"n. 种类","phonetic_us":"/kaɪnd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɪndəgɑːtn/","example":"I to the kindergarten at the age of three. 在我记忆中，我三岁就被送去幼儿园了。","word":"kindergarten","translation":"n.  幼儿园","phonetic_us":"/'kɪndɚɡɑrtn/"},{"word":"kindness","phonetic_us":"/'kaɪndnəs/","translation":"n. 仁慈，好意","phonetic_uk":"/'kaɪn(d)nɪs/","example":"I can’t thank you enough for your kindness. 你的好意我感激不尽。"},{"example":"On 2 December Henry VI was crowned king (= made the king at an official ceremony ). 12月2日，亨利六世加冕为王。","phonetic_uk":"/kɪŋ/","word":"king","phonetic_us":"/kɪŋ/","translation":"n. 国王，君主"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kɪŋdəm/","example":"the United Kingdom 联合王国","word":"kingdom","phonetic_us":"/'kɪŋdəm/","translation":"n. 王国；领域，界"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kɪs/","example":"Maggie leaned forward and kissed her cheek. 玛吉俯身吻了她的脸颊。","translation":"v. 吻；v. 接吻；n. 吻","phonetic_us":"/kɪs/","word":"kiss"},{"example":"Sam went into the kitchen to make a pot of tea. 萨姆走进厨房去沏一壶茶。","phonetic_uk":"/'kɪtʃɪn; -tʃ(ə)n/","word":"kitchen","translation":"n. 厨房，灶间","phonetic_us":"/'kɪtʃɪn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/kaɪt/","translation":"n. 风筝","word":"kite","phonetic_uk":"/kaɪt/","example":"She has a blue and green kite. 她有一只蓝色和绿色的风筝。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/niː/","example":"Lucy had a bandage round her knee. 露西的膝盖上缠着绷带。","phonetic_us":"/ni/","translation":"n. 膝，膝盖，膝关节","word":"knee"},{"phonetic_uk":"/niːl/","example":"Tom knelt down and patted the dog. 汤姆跪下来轻轻拍了拍那只狗。","translation":"v. 跪，跪下，跪着","phonetic_us":"/nil/","word":"kneel"},{"example":"a knife and fork 一副刀叉","phonetic_uk":"/naɪf/","word":"knife","translation":"n. 小刀，刀，餐刀","phonetic_us":"/naɪf/"},{"phonetic_us":"/nɪt/","translation":"v. 把…编结；v. 编织","word":"knit","phonetic_uk":"/nɪt/","example":"I had endless hours to knit and sew. 我有无数的时间来缝缝织织。"},{"phonetic_us":"/nɑb/","translation":"n. 门把，拉手；旋纽","word":"knob","phonetic_uk":"/nɒb/","example":"He thought the door was locked, but he turned the knob and the door opened. 他本以为门是锁住的，但是转了一下把手门就开了。"},{"example":"I knocked and knocked but nobody answered. 我把门敲了又敲，但无人回应。","phonetic_uk":"/nɒk/","phonetic_us":"/nɑk/","translation":"vi&vt&n. 敲，击，打","word":"knock"},{"example":"One lace had broken and been tied in a knot. 一根带子已经断了，被打成一个结。","phonetic_uk":"/nɒt/","word":"knot","phonetic_us":"/nɑt/","translation":"n. (绳的)结，(树的)节"},{"translation":"v. 知道；认识；通晓","phonetic_us":"/no/","word":"know","example":"Who knows the answer? 谁知道答案？","phonetic_uk":"/nəʊ/"},{"example":"He did not have much knowledge of American history. 他对美国历史所知不多。","phonetic_uk":"/'nɒlɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 知识，学识；知道","phonetic_us":"/'nɑlɪdʒ/","word":"knowledge"},{"example":"the school science lab 学校的科学实验室","phonetic_uk":"/læb/","phonetic_us":"/læb/","translation":"n. 实验室，研究室","word":"lab"},{"example":"a luggage label 行李标签","phonetic_uk":"/'leɪb(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/ˈlebəl/","translation":"n. 标签；标记，符号","word":"label"},{"example":"a research laboratory 研究实验室","phonetic_uk":"/lə'bɒrə,t(ə)rɪ; 'læb(ə)rə,t(ə)rɪ/","word":"laboratory","translation":"n. 实验室，研究室","phonetic_us":"/'læbrə'tɔri/"},{"translation":"adj. 费力的","phonetic_us":"/lə'bɔrɪəs/","word":"laborious","example":"the laborious business of drying the crops 把收获的庄稼晒干这一艰苦的工作","phonetic_uk":"/lə'bɔːrɪəs/"},{"word":"labour","translation":"n. 劳动；工作；劳工","phonetic_us":"/'leibə/","phonetic_uk":"/'leɪbə/","example":"The garage charges £30 an hour for labour. 汽车修理厂收取每小时30英镑的人工费。"},{"word":"lace","phonetic_us":"/les/","translation":"n. 鞋带，系带；花边","example":"a handkerchief trimmed with lace 饰有蕾丝花边的手绢","phonetic_uk":"/leɪs/"},{"example":"Too many teachers are treated with a lack of respect. 有太多老师得不到尊重。","phonetic_uk":"/læk/","phonetic_us":"/læk/","translation":"vi&vi&n. 缺乏，不足","word":"lack"},{"word":"lad","translation":"n.  男孩， 小伙子","phonetic_us":"/læd/","phonetic_uk":"/læd/","example":"a young lad 小伙子"},{"word":"ladder","phonetic_us":"/'lædɚ/","translation":"n. 梯子，梯状物","phonetic_uk":"/'lædə/","example":"She climbed up the ladder. 她爬上梯子。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'leɪdɪ/","example":"Ladies and gentlemen, may I have your attention please? 女士们、先生们，请大家注意！","word":"lady","translation":"n. 女士，夫人；贵妇人","phonetic_us":"/'ledi/"},{"word":"lag","phonetic_us":"/læɡ/","translation":"v. 走得慢；n. 落后","example":"In this scenario, due to the lag time required to assimilate new resources, the relationship between required resources and estimated delivery timeframe may even turn negative. 在这种情况下，由于时间已经落后，需要吸收新的人力资源，需要的资源和预计的交付时间的关系甚至更加复杂。","phonetic_uk":"/læg/"},{"word":"lake","translation":"n. 湖","phonetic_us":"/lek/","phonetic_uk":"/leɪk/","example":"Lake Michigan 密歇根湖"},{"translation":"n. 羔羊，小羊；羔羊肉","phonetic_us":"/læm/","word":"lamb","phonetic_uk":"/læm/","example":"roast lamb 烤羊肉"},{"phonetic_uk":"/leɪm/","example":"a lame dog 一条瘸腿的狗","phonetic_us":"/lem/","translation":"adj. 跛的；瘸的，残废的","word":"lame"},{"word":"lamp","translation":"n. 灯","phonetic_us":"/læmp/","example":"She switched on the bedside lamp. 她打开了床头灯。","phonetic_uk":"/læmp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lænd/","example":"They own a lot of land. 他们拥有许多土地。","word":"land","translation":"n. 陆地；土地；v. 上岸","phonetic_us":"/lænd/"},{"word":"landing","translation":"n. 上岸，登陆，着陆","phonetic_us":"/'lændɪŋ/","example":"take-off and landing procedures 起降程序","phonetic_uk":"/'lændɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'lændledi/","translation":"n. 女房东；女地主","word":"landlady","example":"There was a note under the door from my landlady. 门下有我女房东的一张便条。","phonetic_uk":"/'læn(d)leɪdɪ/"},{"word":"landlord","translation":"n. 地主；房东，店主","phonetic_us":"/'lændlɔrd/","example":"His landlord doubled the rent. 他的房东把房租提高了一倍。","phonetic_uk":"/'læn(d)lɔːd/"},{"word":"landscape","translation":"n. 风景，景色；风景画；全景；vt.  美化…的景观","phonetic_us":"/ˈlændskep/","example":"the beauty of the New England landscape 新英格兰风光之美","phonetic_uk":"/'lændskeɪp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/leɪn/","example":"a quiet country lane 一条宁静的乡间小路","phonetic_us":"/len/","translation":"n. (乡间)小路；跑道","word":"lane"},{"example":"How many languages do you speak? 你能说几种语言？","phonetic_uk":"/'læŋgwɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 语言，语言课程","phonetic_us":"/'læŋɡwɪdʒ/","word":"language"},{"translation":"n. 提灯，灯笼","phonetic_us":"/'læntɚn/","word":"lantern","phonetic_uk":"/'læntən/","example":"In the course of time, this kind of lantern has become an exclusive of the Shens. 后来， 这种灯笼成了沈家的绝活。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/læp/","phonetic_us":"/læp/","translation":"n. 膝盖","word":"lap"},{"translation":"adj. 大的；巨大的","phonetic_us":"/lɑrdʒ/","word":"large","phonetic_uk":"/lɑːdʒ/","example":"Los Angeles is the second largest city in the US. 洛杉矶是美国的第二大城市。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɑːdʒlɪ/","example":"The state of Nevada is largely desert. 内华达州大部分是沙漠。","word":"largely","phonetic_us":"/'lɑrdʒli/","translation":"adv. 大部分；大量地"},{"example":"laser surgery 激光(外科)手术","phonetic_uk":"/'leɪzə/","phonetic_us":"/'lezɚ/","translation":"n. 激光","word":"laser"},{"example":"Much has changed since my last visit. 自我上次来访后，变化很大。","phonetic_uk":"/lɑːst/","phonetic_us":"/læst/","translation":"adj. 最后的；adv. 最后","word":"last"},{"word":"late","translation":"adj. 迟的；adv. 迟，晚","phonetic_us":"/let/","example":"Sorry I’m late – I overslept. 对不起，来晚了——我睡过头了。","phonetic_uk":"/leɪt/"},{"word":"lately","translation":"adv. 最近，不久前","phonetic_us":"","example":"What have you been doing lately? 你最近在干什么？","phonetic_uk":""},{"example":"I’m going out for a bit – I’ll see you later. 我出去一会儿——回头见。","phonetic_uk":"/'leɪtə/","word":"later","phonetic_us":"/'letɚ/","translation":"adv. 后来；过一会儿"},{"example":"a Latin inscription 拉丁语碑文","phonetic_uk":"/'lætɪn/","word":"Latin","translation":"adj. 拉丁的；n. 拉丁语","phonetic_us":"/'lætn/"},{"translation":"adj. (两者中)后者的","phonetic_us":"/'lætɚ/","word":"latter","example":"In the latter case, buyers pay a 15% commission. 在后一种情况下，买家付15%的佣金。","phonetic_uk":"/'lætə/"},{"translation":"v. 笑，发笑；n. 笑","phonetic_us":"/læf/","word":"laugh","example":"Maria looked at him and laughed. 玛丽亚看着他大笑起来。","phonetic_uk":"/lɑːf/"},{"example":"Foster joined in the laughter. 福斯特也跟着笑了起来。","phonetic_uk":"/'lɑːftə/","phonetic_us":"/'læftɚ/","translation":"n. 笑，笑声","word":"laughter"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lɔ:ntʃ/","example":"The organization has launched a campaign to raise $150,000. 为了筹集15万美元，该组织发起了一场募捐活动。","phonetic_us":"/lɔntʃ/","translation":"v. 发射","word":"launch"},{"word":"laundry","translation":"n. 洗衣房；要洗的衣服","phonetic_us":"/'lɔndri/","example":"She did the laundry (= washed the clothes etc ) and hung it out to dry. 她洗了衣服，然后挂出去晾干。","phonetic_uk":"/'lɔ:ndrɪ/"},{"word":"lavatory","translation":"n. 盥洗室，厕所","phonetic_us":"/'lævətɔri/","example":"...the ladies' lavatory. …女厕所。","phonetic_uk":"/'lævət(ə)rɪ/"},{"word":"law","phonetic_us":"/lɔ/","translation":"n. 法律，法令；法则","example":"Elected officials ought to obey the law. 民选官员理应遵守法律。","phonetic_uk":"/lɔː/"},{"example":"I spent all morning mowing the lawn (= cutting the grass ). 我整个上午都在修剪草坪。","phonetic_uk":"/lɔːn/","phonetic_us":"/lɔn/","translation":"n. 草地，草坪，草场","word":"lawn"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɔːjə; 'lɒɪə/","example":"Prosecution and defence lawyers are expected to deliver closing arguments next week. 原告律师和被告律师下周将要作终结辩论。","word":"lawyer","phonetic_us":"/'lɔjɚ/","translation":"n. 律师；法学家"},{"phonetic_uk":"/leɪ/","example":"He laid his hand on my shoulder. 他把一只手搭在我的肩上。","word":"lay","translation":"v. 置放；铺设；设置","phonetic_us":"/le/"},{"word":"layer","phonetic_us":"/'leɪr/","translation":"n. 层，层次；铺设者","example":"He pulled off layer upon layer of clothing (= many layers of clothing ). 他把衣服一件件地脱掉。","phonetic_uk":"/'leɪə/"},{"translation":"n. 布局，安排，设计","phonetic_us":"","word":"layout","phonetic_uk":"","example":"All the flats in the building had the same layout. 大楼里所有的公寓布局都是一样的。"},{"example":"the laziest boy in the class 班上最懒的男孩","phonetic_uk":"/'leɪzɪ/","translation":"adj. 懒惰的，懒散的","phonetic_us":"/'lezi/","word":"lazy"},{"phonetic_us":"/lid/","translation":"n. 铅，铅制品","word":"lead","phonetic_uk":"/liːd/","example":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/'liːdə/","example":"the largest ever gathering of world leaders 全世界领导人史无前例的大聚会","word":"leader","translation":"n. 领袖，领导人；首领","phonetic_us":"/'lidɚ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'lidɚʃɪp/","translation":"n. 领导","word":"leadership","phonetic_uk":"/'liːdəʃɪp/","example":"The US must now take a firm leadership role. 美国现在必须扮演一个强有力的领导人角色。"},{"example":"The army played a leading role in organizing the attempted coup. 军队在策划这场未遂政变的过程中起了最主要的作用。","phonetic_uk":"/'liːdɪŋ/","word":"leading","phonetic_us":"/'lidɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 指导的；最主要的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/liːf/","example":"a flowering bush with large shiny leaves 叶子大而油亮的开花灌木","word":"leaf","phonetic_us":"/lif/","translation":"n. 叶，叶子"},{"example":"He makes his football league debut tomorrow. 明天他将在足球联赛中首次出战。","phonetic_uk":"/liːg/","word":"league","translation":"n. 同盟，联盟；联合会","phonetic_us":"/lig/"},{"example":"The roof is leaking. 屋顶在漏水。","phonetic_uk":"/liːk/","word":"leak","translation":"v. 漏；泄露；n. 漏洞","phonetic_us":"/lik/"},{"phonetic_us":"/lin/","translation":"v. 倾斜，屈身；靠","word":"lean","phonetic_uk":"/liːn/","example":"trees leaning in the wind 在风中东倒西歪的树木"},{"phonetic_uk":"/liːp/","example":"My heart leaped when I saw Paul at the airport. 在机场看到保罗时，我的心猛地一跳。","translation":"v. 跳，跃；n. 跳跃","phonetic_us":"/lip/","word":"leap"},{"word":"learn","phonetic_us":"/lɝn/","translation":"vi&vt. 学，学习","phonetic_uk":"/lɜːn/","example":"What’s the best way to learn a language? 学习语言的最佳方法是什么？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɜːnd; ˈlɜ:nɪd/","example":"a learned professor 一位博学的教授","translation":"adj. 有学问的；学术上的","phonetic_us":"/'lɝnd; lɝ​nɪd/","word":"learned"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɜːnɪŋ/","example":"a man of great learning 学识渊博的人","phonetic_us":"/'lɝnɪŋ/","translation":"n. 学习；学问，知识","word":"learning"},{"example":"The landlord refused to renew his lease. 房东拒绝和他续签租约。","phonetic_uk":"/liːs/","word":"lease","translation":"n. 租约，租契；vt.  出租； 租得， 租有","phonetic_us":"/lis/"},{"word":"least","phonetic_us":"/list/","translation":"adj. 最少的；adv. 最少","example":"I try to offend the least amount of people possible. 我尽可能少得罪人。","phonetic_uk":"/liːst/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'leðə/","example":"The inside of the bag was lined with soft leather. 这包的里面衬了软皮。","word":"leather","phonetic_us":"/'lɛðɚ/","translation":"n. 皮革；皮革制品"},{"phonetic_uk":"/liːv/","example":"My baby gets upset when I leave the room. 我一离开房间宝宝就会不安。","phonetic_us":"/liv/","translation":"v. 离去；v. 离开","word":"leave"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lektʃə/","example":"...a series of lectures by Professor Eric Robinson. …埃里克·鲁滨逊教授的系列讲座。","word":"lecture","phonetic_us":"/'lɛktʃɚ/","translation":"n&vi. 演讲，讲课"},{"translation":"adj. 左边的；adv. 在左边","phonetic_us":"/lɛft/","word":"left","phonetic_uk":"/left/","example":"She held out her left hand. 她伸出左手。"},{"word":"leg","phonetic_us":"/lɛɡ/","translation":"n. 腿，腿部","phonetic_uk":"/leg/","example":"a young boy with skinny legs 双腿干瘦的小男孩"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'li:ɡl/","example":"What the company has done is perfectly legal. 公司所做的这一切完全合法。","word":"legal","phonetic_us":"/'ligl/","translation":"adj. 法律的"},{"example":"Local legend has it that (= says that ) the island was the original Garden of Eden. 当地传说这个岛就是伊甸园的原型。","phonetic_uk":"/'ledʒ(ə)nd/","word":"legend","translation":"n. 传奇","phonetic_us":"/'lɛdʒənd/"},{"example":"This is a very important piece of legislation (= law ). 这是一条非常重要的法规。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌledʒɪs'leɪʃn/","translation":"n.  法律， 法规； 立法， 法律的制定","phonetic_us":"/,lɛdʒɪs'leʃən/","word":"legislation"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'leʒə(r)/","example":"Most people now enjoy shorter working hours and more leisure time. 现在大多数人都喜欢工作时间短些，闲暇时间多些。","word":"leisure","translation":"n. 悠闲，空闲","phonetic_us":"/'liʒɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lemən/","example":"a slice of lemon 一片柠檬","word":"lemon","translation":"n. 柠檬，柠檬树","phonetic_us":"/'lɛmən/"},{"word":"lend","phonetic_us":"/lɛnd/","translation":"v. 把…借给，贷(款)","phonetic_uk":"/lend/","example":"The bank is reassessing its criteria for lending money. 银行正在重新评估其贷款标准。"},{"translation":"n. 长，长度；一段","phonetic_us":"/[leŋθ]/","word":"length","phonetic_uk":"/leŋθ/","example":"We measured the length and width of the living room. 我们量了客厅的长和宽。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'leŋθɪ/","example":"A lengthy period of training is required. 需要很长一段时间的培训。","word":"lengthy","translation":"adj. 长的，漫长的","phonetic_us":"/'lɛŋθi/"},{"example":"a standard 50mm lens 50毫米标准镜头","phonetic_uk":"/lenz/","word":"lens","translation":"n. 透镜，镜片；镜头","phonetic_us":"/lɛnz/"},{"example":"Maybe he would worry less if he understood the situation. 他要是了解情况，也许就不会那么担心了。","phonetic_uk":"/les/","translation":"adj. 更少的；adv. 更少地","phonetic_us":"/lɛs/","word":"less"},{"example":"Gradually her anxiety lessened. 她的焦虑慢慢减轻了。","phonetic_uk":"/'les(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'lɛsn/","translation":"v. 减少","word":"lessen"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'les(ə)n/","example":"piano lessons 钢琴课","word":"lesson","translation":"n. 功课，课；课程","phonetic_us":"/'lɛsn/"},{"word":"lest","translation":"conj. 惟恐，以免","phonetic_us":"/lɛst/","phonetic_uk":"/lest/","example":"She turned away from the window lest anyone see them. 她转身离开窗边，免得有人看见他们。"},{"phonetic_us":"/lɛt/","translation":"v. 允许，让；使","word":"let","example":"I can’t come out tonight – my dad won’t let me. 今天晚上我不能出来，我爸爸不允许。","phonetic_uk":"/let/"},{"example":"There are 26 letters in the English alphabet. 英语字母表有26个字母。","phonetic_uk":"/'letə/","translation":"n. 信；证书；字母","phonetic_us":"/'lɛtɚ/","word":"letter"},{"phonetic_us":"/'lɛvl/","translation":"n. 水平面；adj. 水平的","word":"level","phonetic_uk":"/'lev(ə)l/","example":"Inflation fell to its lowest level in 30 years. 通货膨胀降至30年来最低点。"},{"translation":"n. 杆，杠杆；控制杆","phonetic_us":"/'lɛvɚ/","word":"lever","phonetic_uk":"/'liːvə/","example":"Pull this lever to open the gate. 拉此横杆开启大门。"},{"word":"liability","translation":"n. 责任","phonetic_us":"/'laɪə'bɪləti/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌlaɪəˈbɪləti/","example":"But without the formal business entity, you have no hope of limiting your personal liability. 因为没有正规的商务体制，你就没有希望限制你的个人责任。"},{"word":"liable","phonetic_us":"/'laɪəbl/","translation":"adj. 易于…的；可能的","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪəb(ə)l/","example":"The car is liable to overheat on long trips. 这辆汽车跑长途容易过热。"},{"word":"liar","translation":"n. 说谎的人","phonetic_us":"/'laɪɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪə/","example":"Are you calling me a liar? 你是说我在撒谎？"},{"example":"a liberal supply of drinks 饮料的充足供应","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪb(ə)r(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 心胸宽大的；慷慨的","phonetic_us":"/'lɪbərəl/","word":"liberal"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɪbəreɪt/","example":"A few days later, our armies liberated the city. 几天以后，我军解放了这座城市。","word":"liberate","translation":"v. 解放；释放","phonetic_us":"/'lɪbə'ret/"},{"example":"They pant after liberation. 他们渴望解放。","phonetic_uk":"/lɪbə'reɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"liberation","translation":"n. 解放","phonetic_us":"/,lɪbə'reʃən/"},{"word":"liberty","phonetic_us":"/'lɪbɚti/","translation":"n. 自由；释放；许可","example":"the fight for liberty and equality 争取自由和平等的斗争","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪbətɪ/"},{"word":"librarian","phonetic_us":"/laɪ'brɛrɪən/","translation":"n. 图书馆馆长","example":"The new librarian is a friend of mine. 这位新来的图书管理员是我的朋友。","phonetic_uk":"/laɪ'breərɪən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/laɪˌbrɛrɪ/","translation":"n. 图书馆；藏书","word":"library","phonetic_uk":"/ˈlaɪbrərɪ/","example":"a public library 公共图书馆"},{"word":"license","translation":"n. 许可；执照；v. 准许","phonetic_us":"/'laɪsns/","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪsns/","example":"No special license will be regranted to anyone from now on. 特殊许可证今后不得向任何人再行发放。"},{"translation":"v. 舔；舔吃","phonetic_us":"/lɪk/","word":"lick","example":"The dog jumped up and licked her face. 那只狗跳起来舔她的脸。","phonetic_uk":"/lɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/lɪd/","translation":"n. 盖子，盖，囊盖","word":"lid","example":"She lifted the lid of the box and displayed the contents. 她把盒盖掀起，展示了里边的东西。","phonetic_uk":"/lɪd/"},{"example":"The town lies in a small wooded valley. 该城镇坐落于一个林木茂盛的山谷中。","phonetic_uk":"/laɪ/","phonetic_us":"","translation":"v. 躺，平放；位于","word":"lie"},{"example":"He was preferred to lieutenant. 他被晋升为陆军中尉。","phonetic_uk":"/lef'tenənt/","translation":"n. 陆军中尉；副职官员","phonetic_us":"/lu'tɛnənt/","word":"lieutenant"},{"phonetic_us":"/laɪf/","translation":"n. 生命；一生；寿命","word":"life","example":"Learning goes on throughout life. 学习是一生的事。","phonetic_uk":"/laɪf/"},{"example":"It’s the sort of opportunity you see only once in a lifetime. 这种机会你一辈子也只能碰到一次。","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪftaɪm/","phonetic_us":"/'laɪftaɪm/","translation":"n. 一生，终身","word":"lifetime"},{"example":"Sophie lifted the phone before the second ring. 铃响了一下苏菲就接起了电话。","phonetic_uk":"/lɪft/","word":"lift","phonetic_us":"/lɪft/","translation":"v. 提起，提高；n. 电梯"},{"translation":"adj. 轻的，少量的","phonetic_us":"/laɪt/","word":"light","example":"You can carry this bag – it’s fairly light. 你可以拿这个袋子——它很轻。","phonetic_uk":"/laɪt/"},{"example":"As the sky lightened, we were able to see where we were. 天色渐亮，我们能看清楚身处何地了。","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪt(ə)n/","word":"lighten","translation":"v. 照亮，使明亮","phonetic_us":"/'laɪtn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'laɪtli/","translation":"adv. 轻轻地，轻松地","word":"lightly","example":"I knocked lightly on the door. 我轻轻地敲了敲门。","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪtlɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'laɪtnɪŋ/","example":"Two farmworkers were struck by lightning (= hit by lightning ). 两个农民遭闪电击中。","word":"lightning","translation":"n. 闪电，闪电放电","phonetic_us":"/'laɪtnɪŋ/"},{"example":"I like your jacket. 我喜欢你这件上衣。","phonetic_uk":"/laɪk/","phonetic_us":"/laɪk/","translation":"v. 喜欢；喜爱；希望","word":"like"},{"word":"likely","phonetic_us":"/'laɪkli/","translation":"adj. 可能的；adv. 很可能","example":"Snow showers are likely tomorrow. 明天可能有阵雪。","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪklɪ/"},{"example":"Nanny put on a shawl and told the girls to do likewise. 南妮披上披肩，并叫女孩们也这样做。","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪkwaɪz/","word":"likewise","phonetic_us":"/'laɪkwaɪz/","translation":"adv. 同样地；也，又"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lɪm/","example":"She would be able to stretch out her cramped limbs and rest for a few hours. 她将可以伸开蜷缩的四肢，休息几个小时。","translation":"n. 肢，臂，翼；树枝","phonetic_us":"/lɪm/","word":"limb"},{"translation":"n. 石灰","phonetic_us":"/laɪm/","word":"lime","phonetic_uk":"/laɪm/","example":"The lime has turned to powder. 石灰已经粉了。"},{"word":"limit","phonetic_us":"/'lɪmɪt/","translation":"n. 限度；限制；范围","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪmɪt/","example":"a 55 mph speed limit 55英里的时速限制"},{"example":"a nuclear limitation treaty 核限制条约","phonetic_uk":"/lɪmɪ'teɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"limitation","phonetic_us":"/,lɪmɪ'teʃən/","translation":"n. 限制；限度，局限"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɪmɪtɪd/","example":"My knowledge of the business is limited. 我对这一行了解有限。","word":"limited","translation":"adj. 有限的","phonetic_us":"/'lɪmɪtɪd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lɪmp/","example":"a limp handshake 无力的握手","translation":"adj. 软的；不强壮的；v. 〔因一腿受伤而〕跛行，一瘸一拐地走；n. 跛行","phonetic_us":"/lɪmp/","word":"limp"},{"phonetic_uk":"/laɪn/","example":"Draw a straight line across the top of the page. 在这一页的上方画一条直线。","word":"line","translation":"n. 线；排；路线；线条","phonetic_us":"/laɪn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɪnɪn/","example":"a linen jacket 亚麻布夹克","word":"linen","translation":"n. 亚麻布；亚麻织物","phonetic_us":"/'lɪnɪn/"},{"example":"Then he would take an air liner to another city for travel. 然后他会乘一架班机去另一个城市旅游。","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪnə/","translation":"n. 班船，班机","phonetic_us":"/'laɪnɚ/","word":"liner"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lɪŋk/","example":"He walked with her, linking arms (= putting his arm around her arm ). 他与她挽臂同行。","word":"link","phonetic_us":"/lɪŋk/","translation":"v. 有环连接；n. 环"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'laɪən/","example":"The wounded lion bellowed out. 受伤的狮子发出了怒吼。","word":"lion","translation":"n. 狮子；勇猛的人","phonetic_us":"/'laɪən/"},{"translation":"n. 嘴唇","phonetic_us":"/lɪp/","word":"lip","example":"She had big eyes and full lips (= large and round lips ). 她眼睛大大的，嘴唇很丰满。","phonetic_uk":"/lɪp/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'lɪkwɪd/","translation":"n. 液体；adj. 液体的","word":"liquid","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪkwɪd/","example":"Add a little more liquid to the sauce. 在酱汁中再加一点水。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɪkə/","example":"","phonetic_us":"/'lɪkɚ/","translation":"n. 酒；溶液，液剂","word":"liquor"},{"example":"High on the list of public demands is to end military control of broadcasting. 高居公众要求事项前列的是结束对广播的军事控制。","phonetic_uk":"/lɪst/","phonetic_us":"/lɪst/","translation":"n. 表，目录；n. 列举","word":"list"},{"phonetic_us":"/'lɪsn/","translation":"v. 听，留神听；听从","word":"listen","example":"Listen! There’s a strange noise in the engine. 听！引擎发出奇怪的声音。","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪs(ə)n/"},{"word":"listener","phonetic_us":"/'lɪsənɚ/","translation":"n. 听者，听众之一","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪs(ə)nə/","example":"a new programme for younger listeners 针对年轻听众的新节目"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈli:tə(r)/","example":"So this is moles per liter per second, right? It's disappearance of some concentration for time. 所以这里的单位是摩尔每升每秒，对吗？这代表浓度随着时间的减少。","translation":"n. 升(容量单位)","phonetic_us":"/litɚ/","word":"liter"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɪt(ə)(rə)rɪ/","example":"a literary prize 文学奖","translation":"adj. 文学(上)的","phonetic_us":"/lɪtərɛri/","word":"literary"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'litərətʃə/","example":"He has read many of the major works of literature. 他读过许多重要的文学作品。","word":"literature","translation":"n. 文学，文学作品；文献","phonetic_us":"/lɪtərəˌtʃʊr/"},{"example":"a little house 小屋","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪt(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 小的；少；幼小的","phonetic_us":"/'lɪtl/","word":"little"},{"phonetic_uk":"/laɪv；lɪv/","example":"He lives just across the street from me. 他就住在我街对面。","word":"live","translation":"v. 居住；活；adj. 活的","phonetic_us":"/laɪv；lɪv/"},{"word":"lively","translation":"adj. 活泼的；逼真的","phonetic_us":"/'laɪvli/","phonetic_uk":"/'laɪvlɪ/","example":"a lively child 精力充沛的孩子"},{"example":"Three weeks ago, it was discovered the cancer had spread to his liver. 三周前，发现癌已扩散到了他的肝脏。","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪvə/","word":"liver","phonetic_us":"/'lɪvɚ/","translation":"n. 肝；肝脏"},{"translation":"adj. 活的；n. 生活，生计","phonetic_us":"/'lɪvɪŋ/","word":"living","phonetic_uk":"/'lɪvɪŋ/","example":"He’s one of the greatest living composers. 他是仍然健在的最伟大的作曲家之一。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ləʊd/","example":"Have you finished loading up? 你装完货了吗？","word":"load","translation":"v. 装；装满；n. 负载","phonetic_us":"/lod/"},{"translation":"n. 一条面包，一个面包","phonetic_us":"/lof/","word":"loaf","phonetic_uk":"/ləʊf/","example":"a loaf of bread  一条面包"},{"word":"loan","phonetic_us":"/lon/","translation":"n. 贷款","phonetic_uk":"/ləʊn/","example":"We obtained a loan from the government. 我们得了一笔政府贷款。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɒbɪ/","example":"a hotel lobby 宾馆大堂","phonetic_us":"/'lɑbi/","translation":"n. 大堂；v. 游说","word":"lobby"},{"example":"local hospital 当地医院","phonetic_uk":"/'ləʊk(ə)l/","word":"local","phonetic_us":"/ˈloʊkl/","translation":"adj. 地方的；局部的"},{"word":"locate","translation":"v. 位于，定位","phonetic_us":"/ˈloˌket; loˈket/","example":"The business is located right in the center of town. 这家商店就在市中心。","phonetic_uk":"/lə(ʊ)'keɪt/"},{"example":"His apartment is in a really good location. 他的公寓地段很好。","phonetic_uk":"/lə(ʊ)'keɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"location","phonetic_us":"/lo'keʃən/","translation":"n. 位置，场所"},{"phonetic_us":"/lɑk/","translation":"n. 锁；v. 锁上，锁住","word":"lock","example":"I’m sorry, there isn’t a lock on the bathroom door. 对不起，浴室门上没有锁。","phonetic_uk":"/lɒk/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ləʊkə'məʊtɪv/","word":"locomotive","phonetic_us":"/,lokə'motɪv/","translation":"n. 火车头，机车"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lɒdʒ/","example":"a building used to lodge prisoners of war 一座关押战俘的建筑物","phonetic_us":"/lɑdʒ/","translation":"v. 住宿，暂住","word":"lodge"},{"translation":"n. 原木，木料","phonetic_us":"/lɔɡ/","word":"log","example":"a roaring log fire 原木燃烧的熊熊大火","phonetic_uk":"/lɒg/"},{"example":"There isa certain logicin their choice of architect. 他们对建筑师的选择是有一定道理的。","phonetic_uk":"/'lɒdʒɪk/","phonetic_us":"/'lɑdʒɪk/","translation":"n. 逻辑","word":"logic"},{"translation":"adj. 逻辑的；符合逻辑的","phonetic_us":"/'lɑdʒɪkl/","word":"logical","example":"The detective has to discover the murderer by logical deduction. 那位侦探得通过逻辑推理来找出凶手。","phonetic_uk":"/'lɒdʒɪk(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɑdʒɪkli/","example":"","word":"logically","translation":"adv. 合乎情理地，符合逻辑地","phonetic_us":"/'lɑdʒɪkli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ləʊnlɪ/","example":"a lonely old man 一个孤单的老人","word":"lonely","translation":"adj. 孤独的；荒凉的","phonetic_us":"/'lonli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lɒŋ/","example":"How long will it take to get there? 到那里去要多长时间？","word":"long","translation":"v. 渴望","phonetic_us":"/lɔŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lʊk/","example":"We sneaked out while Jessie’s mom wasn’t looking. 我们趁杰茜的妈妈没有看到，偷偷地溜了出去。","translation":"v. 看，显得；n. 看","phonetic_us":"/lʊk/","word":"look"},{"example":"Mrs. Morrell reached for a loop of garden hose. 莫雷尔夫人伸手去拿一圈橡胶软管。","phonetic_uk":"/luːp/","phonetic_us":"/lup/","translation":"n. 圈，环，环孔","word":"loop"},{"phonetic_uk":"/luːs/","example":"a loose floorboard 松动的地板","phonetic_us":"/lus/","translation":"adj. 松的；宽松的","word":"loose"},{"phonetic_us":"/'lusn/","translation":"v. 解开；使松驰","word":"loosen","phonetic_uk":"/'luːs(ə)n/","example":"You’ll need a spanner to loosen that bolt. 你需要扳手来拧开那个螺栓。"},{"word":"lord","phonetic_us":"/lɔrd/","translation":"n. 贵族；上帝","phonetic_uk":"/lɔːd/","example":"Lord Salisbury 索尔兹伯里勋爵"},{"word":"lorry","translation":"n. 运货汽车，卡车","phonetic_us":"/'lɔri/","phonetic_uk":"/'lɒrɪ/","example":"Now and then they heard the roar of a heavy lorry. 他们不时听见一辆重型卡车的轰响声。"},{"translation":"v. 失去；迷失；输掉","phonetic_us":"/luz/","word":"lose","example":"I’ve lost my appetite. 我已经没有了胃口。","phonetic_uk":"/luːz/"},{"example":"The company is closing down two of its factories, leading to 430 job losses . 公司要关闭其中的两家工厂，这将造成430人失业。","phonetic_uk":"/lɒs/","word":"loss","phonetic_us":"/lɔs/","translation":"n. 遗失；损失；失败"},{"example":"We’ve spent a lot on the children’s education. 我们在孩子的教育上花费甚多。","phonetic_uk":"/lɒt/","word":"lot","phonetic_us":"/lɑt/","translation":"n. 许多，大量；签，阄"},{"example":"The book fell to the floor with a loud bang. 书砰的一声掉落到地上。","phonetic_uk":"/laʊd/","translation":"adj. 响亮的；吵闹的","phonetic_us":"/laʊd/","word":"loud"},{"phonetic_uk":"/laʊd'spiːkə/","example":"The loudspeaker announced the arrival of the train. 广播说火车进站了。","word":"loudspeaker","translation":"n. 扬声器，喇叭","phonetic_us":"/,laʊd'spikɚ/"},{"translation":"v. 爱，喜欢；n. 爱","phonetic_us":"/lʌv/","word":"love","example":"I love you, Tracy. 我爱你，特雷西。","phonetic_uk":"/lʌv/"},{"example":"She had a lovely face. 她有一张漂亮的脸蛋。","phonetic_uk":"/'lʌvlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'lʌvli/","translation":"adj. 可爱的；令人愉快的","word":"lovely"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lʌvə/","example":"He killed his wife’s lover. 他杀了妻子的情人。","word":"lover","translation":"n. 爱好者；情人；情侣","phonetic_us":"/'lʌvɚ/"},{"example":"Their safety standards seem to be pretty low. 他们的安全标准似乎相当低。","phonetic_uk":"/ləʊ/","word":"low","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 低的，矮的；低下的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ləʊə/","example":"Temperatures will be lower over the weekend. 周末气温会下降。","translation":"adj. 较低的；v. 放下","phonetic_us":"/'loɚ/","word":"lower"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lɒɪəl/","example":"a loyal supporter of the team 球队的忠实支持者","translation":"adj. 忠诚的，忠心的","phonetic_us":"/'lɔɪəl/","word":"loyal"},{"word":"loyalty","translation":"n. 忠诚，忠实","phonetic_us":"/'lɔɪəlti/","phonetic_uk":"/'lɔɪəltɪ/","example":"the agony of divided loyalties (= loyalty to two different or opposing people ) for the children in a divorce 父母离婚过程中孩子两面都要依顺的痛苦"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lʌk/","example":"You’re not having much luck today, are you? 你今天运气不太好，是不是？","phonetic_us":"/lʌk/","translation":"n. 运气；好运，幸运","word":"luck"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lʌkɪ/","example":"I didn’t really know your name – it was just a lucky guess . 我并不知道你的名字―只是运气好猜中的。","translation":"adj. 幸运的；吉祥的","phonetic_us":"/'lʌki/","word":"lucky"},{"phonetic_us":"/'lʌɡɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 行李；皮箱，皮包","word":"luggage","phonetic_uk":"/'lʌgɪdʒ/","example":"They searched his luggage for illegal drugs. 他们搜查他的行李看是否藏有毒品。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'lʌmbə/","example":"It was made of soft lumber, spruce by the look of it. 它是软木做的，看样子是云杉。","phonetic_us":"/'lʌmbɚ/","translation":"n. 木材；木料；制材","word":"lumber"},{"translation":"n. 团，块；肿块","phonetic_us":"/lʌmp/","word":"lump","phonetic_uk":"/lʌmp/","example":"Strain the custard to remove lumps. 滤去牛奶蛋糊里的面块。"},{"word":"lunch","phonetic_us":"/lʌntʃ/","translation":"n. 午餐，(美)便餐","phonetic_uk":"/lʌn(t)ʃ/","example":"What’s for lunch? 午饭吃什么？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/lʌŋ/","example":"Smoking can cause lung cancer. 吸烟会引起肺癌。","phonetic_us":"/lʌŋ/","translation":"n. 肺脏，肺","word":"lung"},{"example":"He was leading a life of luxury in Australia. 他在澳大利亚过着豪华舒适的生活。","phonetic_uk":"/'lʌkʃ(ə)rɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'lʌɡʒəri/","translation":"n. 奢侈，奢华；奢侈品","word":"luxury"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mə'ʃiːn/","example":"Could you get me a coffee from the drinks machine ? 给我从自动饮料机里买一罐咖啡好吗？","word":"machine","translation":"n. 机器；机械","phonetic_us":"/mə'ʃin/"},{"translation":"n.  机器， 机械","phonetic_us":"/mə'ʃinəri/","word":"machinery","phonetic_uk":"/mə'ʃiːnəri/","example":"...quality tools and machinery. …优质工具和机械。"},{"phonetic_us":"/mæd/","translation":"adj. 发疯的；恼火的","word":"mad","example":"He can’t possibly get that finished in time. He must be mad ! 他不可能按时完成的。他一定是疯了！","phonetic_uk":"/mæd/"},{"translation":"n. 夫人，女士，太太","phonetic_us":"/'mædəm/","word":"madam","example":"Are you being served, Madam? 有人接待您吗，夫人？","phonetic_uk":"/'mædəm/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mægə'ziːn/","example":"a magazine article 杂志中的文章","translation":"n. 杂志，期刊","phonetic_us":"/'mæɡəzin/","word":"magazine"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mædʒɪk/","translation":"n. 魔法，巫术；戏法","word":"magic","example":"Do you believe in magic? 你相信魔法吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'mædʒɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mægnɪt/","translation":"n. 磁铁，磁石，磁体","word":"magnet","phonetic_uk":"/ˈmæɡnɪt/","example":"It's possible to hang a nail from a magnet and then use that nail to pick up another nail. 把一颗钉子挂在一个磁体上再用这颗钉子去吸起另一颗钉子是可能的。"},{"word":"magnetic","phonetic_us":"/mæg'nɛtɪk/","translation":"adj. 磁的，有吸引力的","example":"magnetic forces 磁力","phonetic_uk":"/mæg'netɪk/"},{"word":"magnificent","phonetic_us":"/mæg'nɪfəsnt/","translation":"n. 壮丽的；华丽的","phonetic_uk":"/mæg'nɪfɪs(ə)nt/","example":"The magnificent beau is dancing to the light of chandeliers. 这个衣着华丽的花花公子在枝形吊灯灯光下翩翩起舞。"},{"example":"a kitchen maid 厨房女佣人","phonetic_uk":"/meɪd/","word":"maid","translation":"n. 女佣，女仆；少女","phonetic_us":"/med/"},{"translation":"n. 邮件；v. 邮寄","phonetic_us":"/mel/","word":"mail","example":"You shouldn’t read other people’s mail. 你不应该看别人的信件。","phonetic_uk":"/meɪl/"},{"word":"main","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 主要的，最重要的","phonetic_uk":"/meɪn/","example":"The main reason for living in Spain is the weather. 居住在西班牙的主要原因是天气。"},{"word":"mainframe","translation":"n.  主机， 大型机","phonetic_us":"/'menfrem/","phonetic_uk":"/'meɪnfreɪm/","example":"If a problem does occur, a signal is automatically sent to the mainframe. 如果真有问题出现，就会有信号自动传送到主机。"},{"example":"flights between a Greek island and the mainland 希腊一海岛和本土之间的航班","phonetic_uk":"/'meɪnlənd; -lænd/","word":"mainland","phonetic_us":"/'menlænd/","translation":"n. 大陆"},{"example":"Her illness was caused mainly by stress. 她的病主要是由精神压力引起的。","phonetic_uk":"/'meɪnlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'menli/","translation":"adv. 主要地，大体上","word":"mainly"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'meɪnstri:m/","example":"Genet started as a rebel, but soon became part of the literary mainstream. 热内起初很叛逆，但不久就回归了文学主流。","word":"mainstream","phonetic_us":"/'menstrim/","translation":"n. 主流"},{"phonetic_uk":"/meɪn'teɪn/","example":"Careers Officers maintain contact with young people when they have left school. 年轻人离开学校以后，职业指导员和他们保持联系。","word":"maintain","phonetic_us":"/men'ten/","translation":"v. 维持，主张"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mentənəns/","translation":"n. 维持，保持；维修","word":"maintenance","example":"the cost of repairs and maintenance 维修保养费","phonetic_uk":"/'meɪnt(ə)nəns; -tɪn-/"},{"example":"There are two major political parties in the US. 美国有两大政党。","phonetic_uk":"/'meɪdʒə(r)/","word":"major","phonetic_us":"/'medʒɚ/","translation":"adj. 主要的；v. 主修"},{"example":"The Labour Party won a huge majority at the last general election. 工党在上次大选中以巨大的票数优势获胜。","phonetic_uk":"/mə'dʒɒrətɪ/","translation":"n. 多数","phonetic_us":"/mə'dʒɔrəti/","word":"majority"},{"word":"make","phonetic_us":"/mek/","translation":"v. 使；做，制造","example":"I’m going to show you how to make a box for your tools. 我来教你怎么做一个箱子存放工具。","phonetic_uk":"/meɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'meɪkʌp/","example":"Normally she wore little makeup, but this evening was clearly an exception. 通常她很少化妆，可今晚显然是个例外。","word":"makeup","phonetic_us":"/'mek,ʌp/","translation":"n. 化装"},{"example":"a deep male voice 低沉的男声","phonetic_uk":"/meɪl/","word":"male","phonetic_us":"/mel/","translation":"adj. 男的，雄的；n. 男子"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mæl'fʌŋ(k)ʃ(ə)n/","example":"a malfunction in one of the engines 其中一个引擎的失灵","translation":"n. 失灵，故障","phonetic_us":"/,mæl'fʌŋkʃən/","word":"malfunction"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mæn/","example":"There were two men and a woman in the car. 车上有两男一女。","word":"man","phonetic_us":"/mæn/","translation":"n. 男人；人；人类"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mænɪdʒ/","translation":"v. 管理；设法；对付","word":"manage","phonetic_uk":"/'mænɪdʒ/","example":"He was asked to manage a new department. 他被要求去管理一个新的部门。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mænɪdʒmənt/","translation":"n. 管理；经营，处理","word":"management","phonetic_uk":"/'mænɪdʒm(ə)nt/","example":"a lack of management skills 缺乏管理技巧"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mænɪdʒə/","example":"one of our regional managers 我们的一位地区经理","phonetic_us":"/'mænɪdʒɚ/","translation":"n. 经理，管理人","word":"manager"},{"word":"mankind","translation":"n. 人类","phonetic_us":"/mæn'kaɪnd/","phonetic_uk":"/,mæn'kaɪnd/","example":"Since earliest times, mankind has been fascinated by fire. 人类自远古以来就对火很感兴趣。"},{"word":"manly","phonetic_us":"/'mænli/","translation":"adj. 男子气概的，果断的","phonetic_uk":"/'mænlɪ/","example":"a deep manly voice 低沉雄浑的嗓音"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mænɚ/","translation":"n. 方式；态度；礼貌","word":"manner","phonetic_uk":"/'mænə/","example":"He felt some guilt over the manner of her death. 她以这种方式死去，他心里有些内疚。"},{"word":"manual","translation":"adj. 体力的；n. 手册","phonetic_us":"/'mænjuəl/","example":"People in manual occupations have a lower life expectancy. 干体力活的人预期寿命较短。","phonetic_uk":"/'mænjʊ(ə)l/"},{"word":"manufacture","translation":"v. 制造，生产","phonetic_us":"/'mænjə'fæktʃɚ/","example":"the company that manufactured the drug 生产这种药的公司","phonetic_uk":"/ˌmænjʊ'fæktʃə(r)/"},{"example":"Read the manufacturer’s instructions before using your new dishwasher. 使用新洗碗机之前，请先阅读厂家的说明书。","phonetic_uk":"/,mænjʊ'fæktʃ(ə)rə(r)/","phonetic_us":"/,mænju'fæktʃərɚ/","translation":"n. 制造商；制造厂","word":"manufacturer"},{"translation":"adj. 许多的；pron. 许多人","phonetic_us":"/'mɛni/","word":"many","phonetic_uk":"/'menɪ/","example":"Among his many hobbies was the breeding of fine horses. 在他的众多爱好中有饲养名马。"},{"example":"According to the map we should turn left. 从地图上看，我们应该左拐。","phonetic_uk":"/mæp/","word":"map","translation":"n. 地图；图；天体图","phonetic_us":"/mæp/"},{"translation":"n. 大理石","phonetic_us":"/'mɑrbl/","word":"marble","phonetic_uk":"/'mɑːb(ə)l/","example":"The columns were of white marble. 柱子是白色的大理石。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɑːtʃ/","example":"I flew to Milwaukee in early March. 我3月初飞到了密尔沃基。","translation":"n. 三月","phonetic_us":"/mɑrtʃ/","word":"March"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɑ:dʒɪn/","example":"the western margin of southern Africa 非洲南部的西隅","word":"margin","phonetic_us":"/'mɑrdʒən/","translation":"n. 边缘，范围"},{"word":"marginalize","phonetic_us":"/'mɑrdʒɪnəlaɪz/","translation":"v. 边缘化，排斥","phonetic_uk":"/'mɑːdʒɪn(ə)laɪz/","example":"Female employees complained of being marginalized by management. 女性雇员抱怨被管理层边缘化。"},{"example":"the enormous variety of marine life 海洋生物繁多的种类","phonetic_uk":"/mə'riːn/","translation":"adj. 海的；海上的","phonetic_us":"/mə'rin/","word":"marine"},{"example":"The kitten is mainly white with black marks on her back. 小猫身体基本为白色，背上有黑色斑点。","phonetic_uk":"/mɑːk/","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 斑点；记号；v. 标明","word":"mark"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɑːkɪt/","example":"Our main overseas market is Japan. 我们的主要海外市场是日本。","word":"market","translation":"n. 市场；集市；销路","phonetic_us":"/'mɑrkɪt/"},{"translation":"n. 结婚，婚姻；婚礼","phonetic_us":"/'mærɪdʒ/","word":"marriage","phonetic_uk":"/'mærɪdʒ/","example":"She has three daughters from a previous marriage. 她前一次婚姻生了三个女儿。"},{"word":"married","translation":"adj. 已婚的；婚姻的","phonetic_us":"/'mærɪd/","phonetic_uk":"/'mærɪd/","example":"Are you married or single? 你是已婚还是单身？"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mæri/","translation":"v. 娶，嫁；v. 结婚","word":"marry","phonetic_uk":"/'mærɪ/","example":"He married Bea in 1925. 他在1925年娶了贝亚。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɑrvələs/","translation":"adj. 奇迹般的；了不起的","word":"marvellous","example":"‘How was your holiday?’ ‘Marvellous!’ “假期过得好吗？”“好极了！”","phonetic_uk":"/'mɑːv(ə)ləs/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'mɑ:vɪləs/","word":"marvelous","phonetic_us":"/'mɑrvələs/","translation":"adj. 引起惊异的"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ma:ksizəm/","translation":"n. 马克思主义","word":"Marxism","phonetic_uk":"/'ma:ksizəm/","example":"They openly revised Marxism. 他们明目张胆地篡改马克思主义。"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"a Marxist perspective 马克思主义思想观","phonetic_us":"/'mɑrksɪst/","translation":"adj. 马克思主义的","word":"Marxist"},{"word":"masculine","translation":"adj. 男性的","phonetic_us":"/'mæskjəlɪn/","phonetic_uk":"/'mæskjʊlɪn/","example":"They’re nice curtains, but I’d prefer something a little more masculine. 这些窗帘很好，但我更喜欢男性化一点的。"},{"example":"Men often mask their true feelings with humour. 男人常常用幽默来掩饰他们真实的情感。","phonetic_uk":"/mɑːsk/","word":"mask","phonetic_us":"/mæsk/","translation":"v. 掩饰"},{"example":"The food had congealed into a sticky mass. 那食物结成了黏糊糊的一团。","phonetic_uk":"/mæs/","phonetic_us":"/mæs/","translation":"n. 众多；团；群众","word":"mass"},{"example":"The bell is massive, weighing over 40 tons. 那口钟非常大，有40多吨重。","phonetic_uk":"/'mæsiv/","translation":"adj. 巨大的 大量的","phonetic_us":"/'mæsɪv/","word":"massive"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɑːstə/","example":"a work of art by a true master 一件真正的大师之作","word":"master","translation":"n. 主人；能手；硕士","phonetic_us":"/'mæstɚ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mæstəpis/","translation":"n. 杰作，名著","word":"masterpiece","example":"Mary Shelley was just 18 when she wrote the horror masterpiece ‘Frankenstein’. 玛丽•雪莱创作《科学怪人》这部恐怖小说名作的时候年仅18岁。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɑːstəpiːs/"},{"example":"Wipe your feet on the mat. 在地垫上蹭蹭你的鞋底。","phonetic_uk":"/mæt/","word":"mat","phonetic_us":"/mæt/","translation":"n. 席子；草席；垫子"},{"example":"It’s our last match of the season. 这是我们本赛季最后一场比赛。","phonetic_uk":"/mætʃ/","word":"match","phonetic_us":"/mætʃ/","translation":"n. 比赛，竞赛；对手"},{"translation":"n. 伙伴，同事；配偶","phonetic_us":"/met/","word":"mate","example":"He has found his ideal mate. 他已经找到了理想的配偶。","phonetic_uk":"/meɪt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/mə'tɪrɪəl/","translation":"n. 材料；素材a物质的","word":"material","phonetic_uk":"/mə'tɪərɪəl/","example":"materials like wood or stone 木材或石头之类的材料"},{"example":"a reaction to a world full of shallow materialism 对充满浅薄的物质主义思想的世界作出的回应","phonetic_uk":"/mə'tɪərɪəlɪz(ə)m/","phonetic_us":"/mə'tɪrɪəlɪzəm/","translation":"n. 唯物主义","word":"materialism"},{"word":"mathematical","translation":"adj. 数学的，数学上的","phonetic_us":"/,mæθə'mætɪkl/","phonetic_uk":"/mæθ(ə)'mætɪk(ə)l/","example":"mathematical analysis 数学分析"},{"translation":"n. 数学","phonetic_us":"/,mæθə'mætɪks/","word":"mathematics","example":"...a professor of mathematics at Boston College. …一位波士顿大学的数学教授。","phonetic_uk":"/mæθ(ə)'mætɪks/"},{"phonetic_us":"/mæθs/","translation":"n. (英)数学","word":"maths","phonetic_uk":"/mæθs/","example":"the new maths teacher 新来的数学老师"},{"example":"If I have to stay late at work tonight, it won’t matter because we can go out another night. 如果今晚我必须工作到很晚的话，那也没关系，我们可以改天晚上再出去。","phonetic_uk":"/'mætə(r)/","translation":"v. 要紧，重要","phonetic_us":"/'mætɚ/","word":"matter"},{"phonetic_uk":"/məˈtʃʊə(r)/","example":"Laura is very mature for her age . 相对她的年龄来说劳拉是很成熟的。","word":"mature","translation":"adj. 成熟的","phonetic_us":"/mə'tʃʊr/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mæksɪməm/","example":"We might have a third child, but that’s the absolute maximum . 我们可能会要第三个孩子，但这绝对是极限了。","translation":"n & a. 最大值的，最大量的","phonetic_us":"/ˈmæksəməm/","word":"maximum"},{"word":"may","translation":"v. aux可能；可以，祝","phonetic_us":"/me/","example":"I may be late, so don’t wait for me. 我可能会迟到，所以别等我。","phonetic_uk":"/meɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'meɪbiː; -bɪ/","example":"Maybe it’s all just a big misunderstanding. 也许这只是一个很大的误会。","translation":"adv. 大概，或许；也许","phonetic_us":"/'mebi/","word":"maybe"},{"example":"the election of the London mayor 选举伦敦市长","phonetic_uk":"/ˈmeɪə/","word":"mayor","phonetic_us":"/'meɚ/","translation":"n. 市长"},{"phonetic_us":"/mi/","translation":"pron. (宾格)我","word":"me","example":"Stop, you’re hurting me. 住手，你弄疼我了。","phonetic_uk":"/miː/"},{"word":"meadow","translation":"n. 草地，牧草地","phonetic_us":"/'mɛdo/","phonetic_uk":"/'medəʊ/","example":""},{"translation":"n. 膳食，一餐","phonetic_us":"/mil/","word":"meal","example":"We must have a meal together some time. 我们一定要找个时间一起吃顿饭。","phonetic_uk":"/miːl/"},{"word":"mean","phonetic_us":"/min/","translation":"v. 作…解释；意指","phonetic_uk":"/miːn/","example":"\"Credible\" means \"believable.\" 的意思是。"},{"word":"meaning","translation":"n. 意义，意思；意图","phonetic_us":"/'minɪŋ/","example":"What’s the meaning of this? I asked you to be here an hour ago! 这是什么意思？我让你一小时之前就要到的！","phonetic_uk":"/'miːnɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mi:nz/","example":"The only means of communication was sign language. 唯一的交流方法是手语。","translation":"n. 方法","phonetic_us":"/minz/","word":"means"},{"word":"meantime","phonetic_us":"/'min'taɪm/","translation":"n. 其时，其间；adv. 当时","example":"The doctor will be here soon. In the meantime, try and relax. 医生很快就来，现在尽量放松一下。","phonetic_uk":"/'miːntaɪm/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'minwaɪl/","translation":"adv. 同时，当时","word":"meanwhile","example":"Cook the sauce over a medium heat until it thickens. Meanwhile start boiling the water for the pasta. 用中火把调味汁煮到变稠，同时烧水准备煮意大利面。","phonetic_uk":"/'miːnwaɪl/"},{"word":"measurable","phonetic_us":"/'mɛʒərəbl/","translation":"adj. 可测量的","phonetic_uk":"/'meʒ(ə)rəb(ə)l/","example":"measurable results 可衡量的结果"},{"word":"measure","translation":"n. 分量，尺寸，量具，测量；；v. 测量","phonetic_us":"/'mɛʒɚ/","example":"She soon got the measure of her opponent. 她很快就掂出了对手的分量。","phonetic_uk":"/'meʒə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɛʒɚmənt/","translation":"n. 衡量，测量；尺寸","word":"measurement","phonetic_uk":"/'meʒəm(ə)nt/","example":"accurate measurement of body temperature 体温的精确测量"},{"phonetic_uk":"/miːt/","example":"I gave up eating meat a few months ago. 我几个月以前开始不吃肉了。","word":"meat","phonetic_us":"/mit/","translation":"n. 肉"},{"example":"a garage mechanic 汽车修理厂的技工","phonetic_uk":"/mə'kænɪk/","phonetic_us":"/mə'kænɪk/","translation":"n. 机械师","word":"mechanic"},{"example":"The flight has been cancelled due to mechanical failure . 因机械故障航班被取消了。","phonetic_uk":"/mɪ'kænɪk(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 机械的；力学的","phonetic_us":"/mɪ'kænɪkəl/","word":"mechanical"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɪ'kænɪkəlɪ/","example":"Never copy foreign things blindly or mechanically. 不要盲目地或机械地照搬外国的东西。","translation":"adv. 机械地","phonetic_us":"/mɪ'kænɪkəli/","word":"mechanically"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɪ'kænɪks/","example":"He has not studied mechanics or engineering. 他没有学习过力学或者工程学。","phonetic_us":"/mə'kænɪks/","translation":"n. 力学；技术性细节","word":"mechanics"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɛkənɪzəm/","translation":"n. 机制，机能","word":"mechanism","phonetic_uk":"/'mekənɪzəm/","example":"the brake mechanism 刹车装置"},{"example":"She won a gold medal at the last Olympics. 她在上届奥运会上赢得一枚金牌。","phonetic_uk":"/'med(ə)l/","translation":"n. 奖章，勋章，纪念章","phonetic_us":"/'mɛdl/","word":"medal"},{"example":"The scandal was widely reported in the national media . 这一丑闻在全国媒体上被广泛报道。","phonetic_uk":"/'miːdiə/","word":"media","translation":"n.  新闻媒介， 传播媒介","phonetic_us":""},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɛdɪkl/","translation":"adj. 医学的；内科的","word":"medical","phonetic_uk":"/'medɪk(ə)l/","example":"medical research 医学研究"},{"example":"When somebody comes for treatment I always ask them if they are on any medication. 有人来治疗时，我总是会问他们是否在服药。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌmedi'keɪʃn/","translation":"n.  药物治疗； 药物","phonetic_us":"/'mɛdɪ'keʃən/","word":"medication"},{"word":"medicine","phonetic_us":"/'mɛdsn/","translation":"n. 内服药；医学","example":"She studied medicine at Johns Hopkins University. 她曾在约翰•霍普金斯大学学医。","phonetic_uk":"/'meds(ə)n; 'medɪsɪn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/,mɛdətə'renɪən/","translation":"n. 地中海；adj. 地中海的","word":"Mediterranean","example":"You have the choice of night fishing in the Mediterranean, or windsurfing on a lake in Switzerland. 你可选择在地中海夜间垂钓，或是在瑞士的湖上玩帆板。","phonetic_uk":""},{"example":"Advertising is a powerful medium. 广告是具有强大影响力的传播媒介。","phonetic_uk":"/'miːdɪəm/","word":"medium","translation":"n. 媒质；中间a中等的","phonetic_us":"/'midɪəm/"},{"word":"meet","phonetic_us":"/mit/","translation":"v. 遇见；v. 相遇","phonetic_uk":"/miːt/","example":"You’ll never guess who I met in town. 你绝对猜不出我在镇上碰到谁了。"},{"translation":"n. 聚集，会合，会见","phonetic_us":"/'mitɪŋ/","word":"meeting","example":"We’re having a meeting next week to discuss the matter. 我们下周将开会讨论此事。","phonetic_uk":"/'miːtɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɛlən/","translation":"n. 瓜，甜瓜","word":"melon","example":"...some juicy slices of melon. …几片多汁的甜瓜。","phonetic_uk":"/'melən/"},{"example":"It was warmer now, and the snow was beginning to melt. 现在天气暖和了，雪开始融化。","phonetic_uk":"/melt/","phonetic_us":"/mɛlt/","translation":"v. 融化","word":"melt"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'membə/","example":"The majority of union members voted in favour of a strike. 大多数工会成员投票赞成罢工。","translation":"n. 成员，会员","phonetic_us":"/'mɛmbɚ/","word":"member"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'membəʃɪp/","example":"You should carry your membership card with you at all times. 你应该随身携带会员卡。","translation":"n.  会员身份， 会籍； 全体会员， 会员数","phonetic_us":"/'mɛmbɚʃɪp/","word":"membership"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mə'mɔːrɪəl/","example":"A memorial service is being held for her at St. Paul's Church. 一场为她举行的纪念仪式正在圣保罗教堂举行。","translation":"adj. 纪念的；记忆的","phonetic_us":"/mə'morɪəl/","word":"memorial"},{"example":"He studied his map, trying to memorize the way to Rose's street. 他研究了地图，努力记住去罗丝家那条街的路。","phonetic_uk":"/'meməraɪz/","phonetic_us":"/'mɛmə'raɪz/","translation":"v. 熟记，牢记","word":"memorize"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɛməri/","translation":"n. 记忆；回忆；存储","word":"memory","example":"He has lots of happy memories of his stay in Japan. 他对在日本逗留的那段时光有许多美好的回忆。","phonetic_uk":"/'mem(ə)rɪ/"},{"example":"My father used to mend our shoes. 我父亲过去常为我们修补鞋子。","phonetic_uk":"/mend/","word":"mend","phonetic_us":"/mɛnd/","translation":"v. 修理，修补，缝补"},{"word":"mental","translation":"adj. 智力的；精神的","phonetic_us":"/'mɛntl/","example":"The centre provides help for people suffering from mental illness . 该中心对精神病患者提供帮助。","phonetic_uk":"/'ment(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɛnʃən/","translation":"vt&n. 提及，说起","word":"mention","phonetic_uk":"/'menʃ(ə)n/","example":"Was my name mentioned at all? 我的名字被提到过吗？"},{"example":"Could we have the menu, please? 请把菜单给我们，好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/ˈmenju:/","word":"menu","phonetic_us":"/'mɛnju/","translation":"n. 菜单"},{"word":"merchant","phonetic_us":"/'mɝtʃənt/","translation":"n. 商人；零售商","phonetic_uk":"/'mɜːtʃ(ə)nt/","example":"the son of a wealthy merchant 一名富商的儿子"},{"word":"mercury","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 水银，汞","example":"Some thieves have eaten off their irons with mercury water. 有些窃贼用汞水腐蚀他们的镣铐。","phonetic_uk":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɜːsɪ/","example":"He showed no mercy to his enemies. 他对敌人毫不仁慈。","word":"mercy","phonetic_us":"/'mɝsi/","translation":"n. 仁慈，慈悲，恩惠"},{"word":"mere","phonetic_us":"/mɪr/","translation":"adj. 仅仅的；纯粹的","example":"She lost the election by a mere 20 votes. 她仅仅以20票之差落选。","phonetic_uk":"/mɪə/"},{"example":"He’s merely a boy – you can’t expect him to understand. 他只是个孩子——你不要指望他能理解。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪəlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'mɪrli/","translation":"adv. 仅仅，只不过","word":"merely"},{"word":"merit","phonetic_us":"/'mɛrɪt/","translation":"n. 优点，成绩；v. 值得","example":"The merit of the report is its realistic assessment of the changes required. 这份报告的优点就是它对所要求的变动进行了实事求是的评估。","phonetic_uk":"/'merit/"},{"example":"He marched off, whistling a merry tune. 他吹着一首欢快的曲子大步走了。","phonetic_uk":"/'merɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'mɛri/","translation":"adj. 欢乐的，愉快的","word":"merry"},{"word":"mess","translation":"n. 混乱，混杂，肮脏","phonetic_us":"/mɛs/","example":"What a mess! 太乱了！","phonetic_uk":"/mes/"},{"word":"message","translation":"n. 信息，消息；启示","phonetic_us":"/'mɛsɪdʒ/","example":"He left a message saying he would probably be a little late. 他留言说可能会晚一点来。","phonetic_uk":"/'mesɪdʒ/"},{"word":"messenger","phonetic_us":"/'mɛsndʒɚ/","translation":"n. 送信者，信使","example":"There will be a messenger at the airport to collect the photographs from our courier. 机场会有一名信使从我们的快递员那儿取走照片。","phonetic_uk":"/'mesɪn(d)ʒə/"},{"translation":"n. 金属，金属制品","phonetic_us":"/'mɛtl/","word":"metal","phonetic_uk":"/'met(ə)l/","example":"The gate is made of metal. 这扇大门是用金属做成的。"},{"translation":"n. 计量器，计，表","phonetic_us":"/'mitɚr/","word":"meter","example":"A man came to read the electricity meter . 有个男的来抄电表。","phonetic_uk":"/'mitɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'meθəd/","example":"traditional teaching methods 传统的教学法","phonetic_us":"/'mɛθəd/","translation":"n. 方法，办法；教学法","word":"method"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mi:tə(r)/","example":"She's running the 1,500 metres here. 她正在这儿跑1500米。","translation":"n. 米，公尺","phonetic_us":"/ˈmitɚ/","word":"metre"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'metrɪk/","example":"a metric tonne 一公吨","translation":"adj. 公制的，米制的","phonetic_us":"/'mɛtrɪk/","word":"metric"},{"phonetic_us":"/'maɪkrokəm'pjʊtɚ/","translation":"n. 微型计算机，微机","word":"microcomputer","example":"The merchant sold electrical appliances, such as microcomputer, microphone, microprocessor and microwave ovens. 商人卖一些电器，比如微型计算机，话筒，微处理器和微波炉。","phonetic_uk":"/'maɪkrə(ʊ)kɒm,pjuːtə/"},{"word":"microphone","translation":"n. 话筒，麦克风","phonetic_us":"/'maɪkrə'fon/","example":"She spoke confidently into the microphone. 她自信地对着麦克风说话。","phonetic_uk":"/'maɪkrəfəʊn/"},{"example":"The slightest movement will defocus the microscope. 最轻微的运动都会使显微镜散焦。","phonetic_uk":"/'maɪkrəskəʊp/","word":"microscope","translation":"n. 显微镜","phonetic_us":"/'maɪkrəskop/"},{"example":"We stopped off in Colchester for our midday meal . 我们中途在科尔切斯特停留吃了午饭。","phonetic_uk":"/mɪd'deɪ/","word":"midday","phonetic_us":"/,mɪd'de/","translation":"n. 正午，中午"},{"translation":"n. 中部；adj. 中部的","phonetic_us":"/'mɪdl/","word":"middle","example":"There are plenty of small houses for sale, and quite a lot of very large ones, but very little in the middle. 在售的小房子很多，大房子也有不少，但是不大不小的很少。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪd(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɪdnaɪt/","translation":"n. 午夜，子夜，夜半","word":"midnight","example":"You can’t phone her now – it’s gone midnight (= after midnight ) ! 你现在不能打电话给她，都过午夜了！","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪdnaɪt/"},{"translation":"n. 中部，中间，当中","phonetic_us":"/mɪdst/","word":"midst","phonetic_uk":"/mɪdst/","example":"I fear we have an enemy in our midst. 我担心我们中间有内奸。"},{"translation":"v. aux可能，会，也许","phonetic_us":"/maɪt/","word":"might","phonetic_uk":"/maɪt/","example":"If you need more information, you might try the Internet. 如果你需要更多的信息，可以试试因特网。"},{"example":"What does this migration not do? 这种迁移不能做什么？","phonetic_uk":"/maɪˈgreɪʃn/","word":"migration","translation":"n. 迁移，移民","phonetic_us":"/maɪ'ɡreʃən/"},{"word":"mild","phonetic_us":"/maɪld/","translation":"adj. 和缓的；温柔的","example":"We had an exceptionally mild winter last year. 去年冬天我们这里异常暖和。","phonetic_uk":"/maɪld/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/maɪl/","example":"It’s 40 miles from here to the Polish border. 从这里到波兰边界有40英里。","phonetic_us":"/maɪl/","translation":"n. 英里","word":"mile"},{"word":"military","translation":"adj. 军队的，军事的","phonetic_us":"/'mɪlətɛri/","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪlətrɪ/","example":"a military helicopter 军用直升机"},{"phonetic_us":"/mɪlk/","translation":"n. 乳，牛奶；v. 挤(奶)","word":"milk","example":"a bottle of milk 一瓶奶","phonetic_uk":"/mɪlk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɪl/","example":"...a steel mill. …一家钢厂。","word":"mill","translation":"n. 工厂","phonetic_us":""},{"phonetic_us":"/'mili,mi:tə/","translation":"n. 毫米","word":"millimetre","phonetic_uk":"","example":"The creature is a tiny centipede, just 10 millimetres long. 那个生物是一只很小的蜈蚣，只有10毫米长。"},{"example":"The book sold more than a million copies. 这本书售出了一百多万册。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪljən/","word":"million","translation":"num. 百万；n. 许多","phonetic_us":"/'mɪljən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/maɪnd/","example":"It is impossible to understand the complex nature of the human mind . 要想了解人类思维复杂的特性是不可能的。","word":"mind","phonetic_us":"/maɪnd/","translation":"n. 头脑；理智；记忆"},{"word":"mine","translation":"pron. 我的","phonetic_us":"/maɪn/","example":"It was Glen’s idea, not mine. 这是格伦的主意，不是我的。","phonetic_uk":"/maɪn/"},{"word":"miner","translation":"n. 矿工","phonetic_us":"/'maɪnɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'maɪnə/","example":"Therefore, we should be more like a miner to stand in reality, excavate off wastes, and get gold mines. 所以我们更应该像一个矿工一样为执著于现实，挖开渣滓，淘出金矿。"},{"example":"Or they could be trained to use weeds as indicators of the soil's mineral properties to help them manage nutrients. 或者可以训练他们使用杂草作为土壤矿物属性的指示器，从而帮助他们管理营养物质。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪnərəl/","phonetic_us":"/'mɪnərəl/","translation":"adj. 矿物的，似矿物的","word":"mineral"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɪnɪmaɪz/","translation":"vt.  将…减少； 最小化","word":"minimize","example":"Every effort is being made to minimize civilian casualties. 正在尽最大努力减少平民伤亡。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪnɪmaɪz/"},{"translation":"n. 最小量；adj. 最小的","phonetic_us":"/'mɪnɪməm/","word":"minimum","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪnɪməm/","example":"This will take a minimum of one hour. 这最少要用一个小时。"},{"word":"minister","translation":"n. 部长，大臣；公使","phonetic_us":"/'mɪnɪstɚ/","example":"a senior Cabinet minister 资深的内阁部长","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪnɪstə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɪnɪstrɪ/","example":"...the Ministry of Justice. …司法部。","translation":"n. (政府的)部","phonetic_us":"/'mɪnɪstri/","word":"ministry"},{"example":"We have made some minor changes to the program. 我们对那个程序做了一些小改动。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈmaɪnə(r)/","word":"minor","phonetic_us":"/'maɪnɚ/","translation":"adj. 小的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/maɪ'nɒrɪtɪ; mɪ-/","example":"Gaelic is still spoken in Ireland by a tiny minority. 爱尔兰仍有极少数人在说盖尔语。","word":"minority","translation":"n. 少数；少数民族","phonetic_us":"/maɪ'nɔrəti/"},{"example":"‘Any minus points ?’ ‘Well, the engine is rather noisy.’ “有什么毛病吗？”“嗯，发动机噪音很大。”","phonetic_uk":"/'maɪnəs/","translation":"adj. 负的；prep. 减(去)","phonetic_us":"/'maɪnəs/","word":"minus"},{"example":"It takes me ten minutes to walk to work. 我步行上班要用十分钟。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪnɪt/","phonetic_us":"/'mɪnɪt/","translation":"n. 分，分钟；一会儿","word":"minute"},{"word":"miracle","phonetic_us":"/'mɪrəkl/","translation":"n. 奇迹，令人惊奇的人","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪrək(ə)l/","example":"It’s a miracle you weren’t killed! 你没有死真是奇迹！"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɪrə/","example":"He spends hours in front of the mirror ! 他老是照镜子！","word":"mirror","translation":"n. 镜子；v. 反映，反射","phonetic_us":"/'mɪrɚ/"},{"translation":"n. 算错，误算","phonetic_us":"","word":"miscalculation","example":"KAPLAN: Well, there's always the risk of a miscalculation or an accident at sea. 卡普兰：呃，在海上总会有误算的风险，也有发生事故的风险。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌmɪskælkjʊ'leɪʃn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌmɪskən'sepʃn/","example":"It is a misconception that Peggy was fabulously wealthy. 说佩吉以前极其富有，这是一个错误的看法。","translation":"n.  误解","phonetic_us":"/'mɪskən'sɛpʃən/","word":"misconception"},{"word":"miserable","phonetic_us":"/'mɪzrəbl/","translation":"adj. 痛苦的","phonetic_uk":"/ˈmɪzrəbl/","example":"I’ve been so miserable since Pat left me. 自从帕特离我而去后，我十分痛苦。"},{"phonetic_us":"/mɪs'gaɪd/","translation":"v. 误导","word":"misguide","phonetic_uk":"/mɪs'gaɪd/","example":"In addition, they will also misguide the innocent, which becomes a vicious circle. 此外，他们将误导那些思想单纯的人，这将导致一个恶心循环。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌmɪs'ɡaɪdɪd/","example":"His parents still clung to the misguided belief that his common sense would keep him out of serious trouble. 他的父母依然错误地认为他的常识能让他远离大的麻烦。","word":"misguided","phonetic_us":"/,mɪs'ɡaɪdɪd/","translation":"adj. 被误导的"},{"translation":"v. 误导","phonetic_us":"/'mɪs'lid/","word":"mislead","example":"Don’t be misled by appearances, he’s a good worker. 不要被表象迷惑，他工作干得挺不错的。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌmɪs'li:d/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɪs/","example":"I’d like to make an appointment with Miss Taylor. 我想约一下泰勒小姐。","translation":"n. 小姐","phonetic_us":"/mɪs/","word":"miss"},{"word":"missile","translation":"n. 发射物；导弹","phonetic_us":"/'mɪsl/","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪsaɪl/","example":"a nuclear missile 核导弹"},{"word":"missing","translation":"adj. 缺掉的，失去的","phonetic_us":"/'mɪsɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪsɪŋ/","example":"We found the missing piece of the jigsaw under the chair. 我们在椅子下面找到了那块丢失的拼图。"},{"translation":"n. 使命，任务；代表团","phonetic_us":"/'mɪʃən/","word":"mission","example":"He was sent on over 200 missions before being killed in action. 在阵亡之前他奉命执行过200多次军事任务。","phonetic_uk":"/'miʃən/"},{"word":"mist","translation":"n. 薄雾","phonetic_us":"/mɪst/","phonetic_uk":"/mɪst/","example":"We could just see the outline of the house through the mist. 薄雾中我们只能看到房子的轮廓。"},{"example":"The most common mistake is to plant them too deep. 最常见的错误就是把它们种得太深了。","phonetic_uk":"/mɪ'steɪk/","word":"mistake","phonetic_us":"/mɪ'stek/","translation":"n. 错误；v. 误解，弄错"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"Look, Mister, we know our job, so don't try to tell us what to do. 哎，先生，我们了解自己的工作，所以你不必告诉我们该干什么。","word":"Mister","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 先生"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɪstrəs/","translation":"n. 女主人；夫人","word":"mistress","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪstrɪs/","example":"The maid looked nervously at her mistress. 女仆紧张地看着女主人。"},{"word":"misunderstand","phonetic_us":"/,mɪsʌndɚ'stænd/","translation":"v. 误解","example":"Rachel, you must have misunderstood her! Ellie would never say something like that. 雷切尔，你一定是误会她了！埃莉绝不会说那样的话。","phonetic_uk":"/,mɪsʌndə'stænd/"},{"example":"Oil and water don’t mix. 油和水不相融。","phonetic_uk":"/mɪks/","phonetic_us":"/mɪks/","translation":"v. 使混合，混淆","word":"mix"},{"example":"Pour the mixture into four small dishes. 把混合料倒入四个小碟子里。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɪkstʃə/","phonetic_us":"/'mɪkstʃɚ/","translation":"n. 混合；混合物","word":"mixture"},{"example":"She gave a little moan of pleasure. 她轻轻地发出一声快乐的呻吟。","phonetic_uk":"/məʊn/","phonetic_us":"/mon/","translation":"n. 呻吟声；v. 呻吟","word":"moan"},{"translation":"adj. 运动的；流动的","phonetic_us":"/ˈmobəl; ˈmoˌbaɪl; ˈmoˌbil/","word":"mobile","example":"mobile air-conditioners 移动式空调器","phonetic_uk":"/ˈməʊbaɪl/"},{"word":"mode","translation":"n. 方式，样式","phonetic_us":"/mod/","phonetic_uk":"/məʊd/","example":"Set the monitor to 256 colour mode. 把显示器调成256色彩模式。"},{"word":"model","phonetic_us":"/'mɑdl/","translation":"n. 模型；模式；模特儿","example":"a working model (= one with parts which move ) of a steam engine 蒸汽机车的活动模型","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒdl/"},{"word":"moderate","phonetic_us":"/ˈmɑdərɪt; (for v.,) ˈmɑdərˌeɪt/","translation":"adj. 温和的；有节制的","example":"the more moderate members of the party 党内观点较为温和的党员","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒd(ə)rət/"},{"translation":"adj. 现代的，近代的","phonetic_us":"/'mɑdɚn/","word":"modern","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒd(ə)n/","example":"Such companies must change if they are to compete in the modern world . 此类公司如果想在现代社会中与别人竞争，就必须有所改变。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌmɒdənaɪ'zeɪʃn/","example":"We should all make contributions to the modernization of our country. 我们都应该对我国的现代化作出贡献。","translation":"n.  现代化","phonetic_us":"/,mɑdɚnə'zeʃən/","word":"modernization"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɒdɪst/","example":"You’re too modest! You’ve been a huge help to us. 你太谦虚了！你帮了我们大忙呢。","word":"modest","translation":"adj. 有节制的；谦虚的","phonetic_us":"/'mɑdɪst/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɑdɪfaɪ/","translation":"v. 更改，修改；修饰","word":"modify","example":"The feedback will be used to modify the course for next year. 这些反馈意见将用于修改明年的课程。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒdɪfaɪ/"},{"translation":"adj. 湿润的；多雨的","phonetic_us":"/mɔɪst/","word":"moist","example":"Make sure the soil is moist before planting the seeds. 播种之前要确保土壤湿润。","phonetic_uk":"/mɒɪst/"},{"example":"When the soil is dry, more moisture is lost from the plant. 土壤干燥时，植物就会失去更多的水分。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒɪstʃə/","word":"moisture","phonetic_us":"/'mɔɪstʃɚ/","translation":"n. 潮湿，湿气；温度"},{"phonetic_uk":"/məuld/","example":"","word":"mold","phonetic_us":"/mold/","translation":"n. 霉，霉菌；模型，铸模；性格；vt.  用模子制作， 塑造； 使形成， 影响…的形成"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɒlɪkjuːl/","example":"The molecules of oxygen gas contain just two atoms. 氧分子中只有两个原子。","word":"molecule","phonetic_us":"/'mɑlɪkjul/","translation":"n. 分子，克分子"},{"example":"It was one of the most exciting moments in his life. 这是他一生中最激动人心的时刻之一。","phonetic_uk":"/'məʊm(ə)nt/","word":"moment","translation":"n. 片刻，瞬间，时刻","phonetic_us":"/'momənt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈmʌndeɪ; ˈmʌndi/","example":"The president announced Monday that he would cancel the debt. 总统周一宣布他会取消这笔债务。","phonetic_us":"/ˈmʌnde; ˈmʌndɪ/","translation":"n. 星期一","word":"Monday"},{"example":"Don’t spend all your money on the first day of your holiday! 别在度假的第一天就把钱都花完了！","phonetic_uk":"/'mʌnɪ/","word":"money","phonetic_us":"/'mʌni/","translation":"n. 货币；金钱，财富"},{"translation":"v. 监控，监听","phonetic_us":"/'mɔnɪtɚ/","word":"monitor","example":"Patients who are given the new drug will be asked to monitor their progress. 使用这种新药的病人将被要求监测病情进展。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒnɪtə(r)/"},{"translation":"n. 猴子，猿","phonetic_us":"/'mʌŋki/","word":"monkey","example":"The monkey is beating up and down. 那只猴子到处乱窜。","phonetic_uk":"/'mʌŋkɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mʌnθ/","example":"I hope I’ll have finished the work by the end of the month . 我希望我这个月底能完成工作。","phonetic_us":"/mʌnθ/","translation":"n. 月，月份","word":"month"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mʌnθli/","translation":"adj. 每月的；adv. 每月","word":"monthly","example":"The mortgage is payable in monthly instalments. 抵押贷款每月分期偿还。","phonetic_uk":"/'mʌnθlɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 纪念碑；纪念馆","phonetic_us":"/'mɑnjumənt/","word":"monument","example":"He erected a monument on the spot where his daughter was killed. 他在女儿遇难的地方立了块纪念碑。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒnjʊm(ə)nt/"},{"example":"You’re in a good mood this morning! 你今天早晨心情不错啊！","phonetic_uk":"/muːd/","phonetic_us":"/mud/","translation":"n. 心情","word":"mood"},{"example":"the craters on the surface of the moon 月球表面的环形山","phonetic_uk":"/muːn/","word":"moon","translation":"n. 月球，月亮；卫星","phonetic_us":"/mun/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɔrəl/","translation":"adj. 精神上的, 道德的","word":"moral","example":"It is easy to have an opinion on a moral issue like the death penalty for murder. 对于判谋杀犯死刑这种涉及伦理道德的问题，有个观点并非难事。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɒr(ə)l/"},{"word":"more","translation":"adj. 更多的；adv. 更","phonetic_us":"/mɔr/","phonetic_uk":"/mɔː/","example":"The accident taught him to be more careful. 这起事故的教训使他变得更小心。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɔːr'əʊvə/","example":"The rent is reasonable and, moreover, the location is perfect. 租金合理，而且位置也非常好。","phonetic_us":"/mɔr'ovɚ/","translation":"adv. 再者，加之，此外","word":"moreover"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mɔːnɪŋ/","example":"I hated those cold winter mornings. 我讨厌冬天里寒冷的早晨。","word":"morning","translation":"n. 早晨，上午","phonetic_us":"/'mɔrnɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mɔrtl/","translation":"adj. 终有一死的；致死的","word":"mortal","phonetic_uk":"/'mɔːt(ə)l/","example":"Her father’s death reminded her that she was mortal. 父亲的去世让她认识到终有一天她也会死去。"},{"phonetic_us":"/məˈskiːtoʊ/","translation":"n. 蚊子","word":"mosquito","phonetic_uk":"/mɒ'skiːtəʊ/","example":"The male mosquito never stings. 雄蚊不叮。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/məʊst/","example":"The president himself won the most votes. 总统本人赢得了最多的选票。","phonetic_us":"/most/","translation":"adj. 最多的；adv. 最，很","word":"most"},{"word":"mostly","translation":"adv. 主要的，大部分","phonetic_us":"/'mostli/","phonetic_uk":"/'məʊs(t)lɪ/","example":"Green teas are mostly from China or Japan. 绿茶主要来自中国或日本。"},{"example":"His mother and father are both doctors. 他的父母都是医生。","phonetic_uk":"/'mʌðə/","word":"mother","translation":"n. 母亲，妈妈","phonetic_us":"/'mʌðɚ/"},{"word":"motion","phonetic_us":"/'moʃən/","translation":"n. 运动；手势；提议","example":"Newton’s first law of motion 牛顿第一运动定律","phonetic_uk":"/'məʊʃ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'məʊtɪveɪt/","example":"A good teacher has to be able to motivate her students. 好教师必须能够激发学生的积极性。","translation":"v. 促动，激发，诱导","phonetic_us":"/'motə'vet/","word":"motivate"},{"translation":"n. 激励，刺激","phonetic_us":"/,motə'veʃən/","word":"motivation","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ˌməʊtɪ'veɪʃn/"},{"translation":"n. 动机，目的","phonetic_us":"/'motɪv/","word":"motive","example":"What do you suppose the killer’s motive was? 你认为凶手的动机是什么？","phonetic_uk":"/'məʊtɪv/"},{"example":"an electric motor 电动马达","phonetic_uk":"/'məʊtə/","word":"motor","phonetic_us":"/'motɚ/","translation":"n. 发动机；机动车"},{"phonetic_uk":"/məʊld/","example":"Another method, used especially for figures, was to pour the clay into a mould. 另一个方法是把黏土倒入模具中，尤其用于铸造人像。","word":"mould","translation":"n. 模子，模型；v. 浇铸","phonetic_us":"/məuld/"},{"word":"mount","translation":"v. 登上，爬上；n. …山","phonetic_us":"/maʊnt/","example":"He mounted his horse and rode on. 他跨上马前行。","phonetic_uk":"/maʊnt/"},{"word":"mountain","phonetic_us":"/ˈmaʊntn/","translation":"n. 山，山岳；山脉","example":"the highest mountain in Austria 奥地利最高的山","phonetic_uk":"/ˈmaʊntən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɔːn/","example":"Hundreds of people gathered to mourn the slain president. 成百上千人聚集在一起悼念遇刺的总统。","word":"mourn","phonetic_us":"/mɔrn/","translation":"v. 哀痛，哀悼"},{"word":"mouse","translation":"n. 鼠，耗子","phonetic_us":"/maʊs/","example":"The cat laid a dead mouse at my feet. 猫把一只死老鼠放在我的脚边。","phonetic_uk":"/maʊs/"},{"word":"mouth","translation":"n. 嘴，口，口腔","phonetic_us":"/maʊθ/","example":"He lifted his glass to his mouth. 他把玻璃杯举到嘴边。","phonetic_uk":"/maʊθ/"},{"example":"Michael told his story between mouthfuls. 迈克尔边吃边讲他的故事。","phonetic_uk":"/'maʊθfʊl; -f(ə)l/","word":"mouthful","phonetic_us":"/'maʊθ'fʊl/","translation":"n. 满口，一口，少量"},{"phonetic_uk":"/muːv/","example":"Please keep the doors closed while the train is moving. 火车行驶时请保持车门关闭。","phonetic_us":"/muv/","translation":"v. 移动；感动；n. 动","word":"move"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'muːvm(ə)nt/","example":"It's part of a broader nationalist movement that's gaining strength throughout the country. 这是一场正在全国范围内日益壮大的更为广泛的民族主义运动的一部分。","word":"movement","phonetic_us":"/'muvmənt/","translation":"n. 动作，活动；移动"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'muːvɪ/","example":"It was like one of those old John Wayne movies. 这部电影有点像约翰•韦恩演的一部老片子。","phonetic_us":"/'muvi/","translation":"n. 电影；电影院","word":"movie"},{"translation":"adv. 非常，很；adj. 许多的","phonetic_us":"/mʌtʃ/","word":"much","phonetic_uk":"/mʌtʃ/","example":"The day ended much as it began. 这一天结束时还像开始时一样。"},{"example":"By the end of the game, all the kids were covered in mud. 到了比赛快结束的时候，所有的孩子都浑身是泥。","phonetic_uk":"/mʌd/","word":"mud","translation":"n. 软泥，泥浆","phonetic_us":"/mʌd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mʌdɪ/","example":"Take your boots off outside if they’re muddy. 要是靴子上都是泥，你就脱在门外吧。","word":"muddy","translation":"adj. 多泥的，泥泞的","phonetic_us":"/'mʌdi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mʌg/","example":"a coffee mug 一个咖啡杯","word":"mug","phonetic_us":"/mʌɡ/","translation":"n. 大杯"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌmʌlti'kʌltʃərəl/","example":"a multicultural society 一个多元文化的社会","word":"multicultural","translation":"adj.  融合多种文化的","phonetic_us":"/'mʌltɪ'kʌltʃərəl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mʌltɪpl/","example":"Baxter was rushed to the hospital with multiple stab wounds. 巴克斯特因多处刺伤被紧急送往医院。","translation":"adj. 复合的；并联的","phonetic_us":"/'mʌltəpl/","word":"multiple"},{"example":"Children will learn to multiply in the second grade. 儿童在二年级学习乘法。","phonetic_uk":"/'mʌltɪplaɪ/","word":"multiply","phonetic_us":"/'mʌltɪplaɪ/","translation":"v. 使增加；乘"},{"word":"murder","translation":"n&vi. 谋杀，凶杀","phonetic_us":"/'mɝdɚ/","example":"On the night the murder was committed , he was out of the country. 凶案发生当晚他不在国内。","phonetic_uk":"/'mɜːdə/"},{"example":"a convicted murderer 已定罪的谋杀犯","phonetic_uk":"/'mɜːd(ə)rə(r)/","translation":"n. 杀人犯，凶手","phonetic_us":"/'mɝdərɚ/","word":"murderer"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mʌs(ə)l/","example":"Relax your stomach muscles , then stretch again. 放松腹部肌肉，然后再绷紧。","word":"muscle","translation":"n. 肌肉，肌；体力","phonetic_us":"/'mʌsl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/mju'ziəm/","translation":"n. 博物馆；展览馆","word":"museum","example":"the Museum of Modern Art 现代艺术博物馆","phonetic_uk":"/mjuː'zɪəm/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mʌʃruːm; -rʊm/","example":"mushroom soup 蘑菇汤","phonetic_us":"/'mʌʃrʊm/","translation":"n. 蘑菇，菌类植物","word":"mushroom"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'mjuːzɪk/","example":"I often listen to classic music when I’m in the car. 我在车上经常听古典音乐。","word":"music","translation":"n. 音乐，乐曲，乐谱","phonetic_us":"/'mjuzɪk/"},{"example":"a musical version of the fairy tale ‘Cinderella’ 童话故事《灰姑娘》的音乐剧版","phonetic_uk":"/'mjuːzɪk(ə)l/","word":"musical","translation":"adj. 音乐的；和谐的","phonetic_us":"/'mjuzɪkl/"},{"example":"a talented young musician 有天赋的年轻音乐家","phonetic_uk":"/mjuː'zɪʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 音乐家；作曲家","phonetic_us":"/mjʊ'zɪʃən/","word":"musician"},{"translation":"v. aux必须；必然要","phonetic_us":"/mʌst/","word":"must","phonetic_uk":"/mʌst/","example":"All passengers must wear seat belts. 所有乘客都必须系安全带。"},{"word":"mute","translation":"adj. 缄默的；n. 哑巴","phonetic_us":"/mjut/","example":"Billy continued to stand there, mute and defiant. 比利还是站在那儿一声不吭，一副不服气的样子。","phonetic_uk":"/mjuːt/"},{"example":"Elsie muttered something I couldn’t catch and walked off. 埃尔茜咕哝了一句什么，我也没有听懂，她就走掉了。","phonetic_uk":"/'mʌtə/","word":"mutter","phonetic_us":"/'mʌtɚ/","translation":"v. 轻声低语；抱怨"},{"example":"...a leg of mutton. …一条羊腿。","phonetic_uk":"/'mʌt(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'mʌtn/","translation":"n. 羊肉","word":"mutton"},{"phonetic_us":"/'mjutʃuəl/","translation":"adj. 相互的","word":"mutual","phonetic_uk":"/'mjuːtʃʊəl/","example":"I didn’t like Dev, and the feeling seemed to be mutual. 我不喜欢德夫，他好像也不喜欢我。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈmjuːtʃuəli/","example":"Note that different users of the system have different goals, and that these goals are often mutually exclusive. 请注意系统的不同用户有不同的目标，而且这些目标经常是相互排斥的。","word":"mutually","phonetic_us":"/'mjutʃuəli/","translation":"adv. 互相地"},{"phonetic_uk":"/maɪ/","example":"All my friends do not smoke. 我的朋友并不全都吸烟。","word":"my","translation":"pron. 我的","phonetic_us":"/maɪ/"},{"word":"myself","translation":"pron. 我自己；我亲自","phonetic_us":"/maɪ'sɛlf/","phonetic_uk":"/maɪ'self/","example":"I blame myself for what has happened. 发生这一切都怪我自己。"},{"translation":"adj. 神秘的；难以理解的","phonetic_us":"/mɪ'stɪrɪəs/","word":"mysterious","phonetic_uk":"/mɪ'stɪərɪəs/","example":"The police are investigating the mysterious deaths of children at the hospital. 警察正在调查这家医院的儿童神秘死亡事件。"},{"translation":"n. 迷，神秘的事物","phonetic_us":"/ˈmɪstri/","word":"mystery","example":"Twenty years after the event, his death remains a mystery . 事情过去二十年了，他的死仍然是个谜。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈmɪstri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/mɪθ/","example":"a book of Greek myths 一本关于希腊神话的图书","word":"myth","phonetic_us":"/mɪθ/","translation":"n. 神话"},{"translation":"n. 钉；指甲；v. 钉","phonetic_us":"/nel/","word":"nail","example":"The key was hanging on a nail by the door. 钥匙挂在门边的一颗钉子上。","phonetic_uk":"/neɪl/"},{"example":"The children ran naked through the yard. 孩子们光着身子跑过院子。","phonetic_uk":"/'neɪkɪd/","phonetic_us":"/'nekɪd/","translation":"adj. 裸体的；无遮敝的","word":"naked"},{"example":"Her name is Mandy Wilson. 她的名字是曼迪•威尔逊。","phonetic_uk":"/neɪm/","word":"name","phonetic_us":"/nem/","translation":"n. 名字；名誉；v. 说出"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈneɪmli/","example":"Three students were mentioned, namely John, Sarah and Sylvia. 有三名学生被提到，即约翰、萨拉和西尔维娅。","translation":"adv. 即，也就是","phonetic_us":"/'nemli/","word":"namely"},{"word":"nap","translation":"n. 小睡，打盹，瞌睡","phonetic_us":"/næp/","example":"an afternoon nap 午睡","phonetic_uk":"/næp/"},{"word":"narrow","translation":"v. 限制","phonetic_us":"/'næro/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'nærəʊ/"},{"translation":"adj. 龌龊的；淫猥的","phonetic_us":"/'næsti/","word":"nasty","phonetic_uk":"/'nɑːstɪ/","example":"a nasty temper 坏脾气"},{"translation":"n. 民族；国家","phonetic_us":"/'neʃən/","word":"nation","phonetic_uk":"/'neɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"the President’s radio broadcast to the nation 总统对全国的广播讲话"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'næʃ(ə)n(ə)l/","example":"Religion matters very much at a national level. 宗教事务在全国都非常重要。","phonetic_us":"/'næʃnəl/","translation":"adj. 民族的；国家的","word":"national"},{"phonetic_us":"/,næʃə'næləti/","translation":"n. 国籍；民族，族","word":"nationality","example":"people of the same nationality 同国籍的人","phonetic_uk":"/næʃə'nælɪtɪ/"},{"word":"native","phonetic_us":"/'netɪv/","translation":"adj. 本土的；n. 本地人","phonetic_uk":"/'neɪtɪv/","example":"Singapore has many native species of palm. 新加坡有很多土生的棕榈树种。"},{"word":"natural","translation":"adj. 自然界的；天然的","phonetic_us":"/'nætʃrəl/","phonetic_uk":"/'nætʃ(ə)r(ə)l/","example":"the study of the natural world  对自然界的研究"},{"example":"Naturally, you’ll want to discuss this with your wife. 当然，你一定想和你妻子商量一下这件事。","phonetic_uk":"/'nætʃ(ə)rəlɪ/","word":"naturally","phonetic_us":"/'nætʃrəli/","translation":"adv. 自然地；天然地"},{"phonetic_us":"/'netʃɚ/","translation":"n. 大自然；本性；性质","word":"nature","example":"We grew up in the countryside, surrounded by the beauties of nature. 我们在乡村长大，周围是美丽的大自然。","phonetic_uk":"/'neɪtʃə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'nɔːtɪ/","example":"You’re a very naughty boy! Look what you’ve done! 你真是个淘气鬼！瞧你干了些什么！","phonetic_us":"/'nɔti/","translation":"adj. 顽皮的，淘气的","word":"naughty"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'neɪv(ə)l/","example":"The harbour is an important naval base. 该港是一个重要的海军基地。","phonetic_us":"/'nevl/","translation":"adj. 海军的，军舰的","word":"naval"},{"example":"compasses and other instruments of navigation 罗盘及其他导航仪器","phonetic_uk":"/nævɪ'geɪʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/'nævə'geʃən/","translation":"n. 航行；航海术；导航","word":"navigation"},{"phonetic_us":"/'nevi/","translation":"n. 海军","word":"navy","example":"the British Navy 英国海军","phonetic_uk":"/'neɪvɪ/"},{"translation":"adv. 近，接近；adj. 近的","phonetic_us":"/nɪr/","word":"near","phonetic_uk":"/nɪə/","example":"They live near London. 他们住在伦敦附近。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,nɪr'baɪ/","translation":"adj. 附近的；adv. 在附近","word":"nearby","phonetic_uk":"/'nɪəbaɪ/","example":"Lucy was staying in the nearby town of Hamilton. 露西当时住在附近的汉密尔顿镇。"},{"translation":"adv. 差不多；密切地","phonetic_us":"/'nɪrli/","word":"nearly","example":"It took nearly two hours to get here. 到这里花了将近两小时。","phonetic_uk":"/'nɪəlɪ/"},{"example":"neat handwriting 工整的笔迹","phonetic_uk":"/niːt/","phonetic_us":"/nit/","translation":"adj. 整洁的；熟练的","word":"neat"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'nesəs(ə)rɪlɪ; ,nesə'serɪlɪ/","example":"The care of old people necessarily involves quite a lot of heavy lifting. 照顾老年人必定要干很多搬重物的活儿。","word":"necessarily","phonetic_us":"/,nɛsə'sɛrəli/","translation":"adv. 必然，必定"},{"word":"necessary","phonetic_us":"/ˈnɛsəˌsɛri/","translation":"adj. 必要的；必然的","example":"The booklet provides all the necessary information about the college. 这本小册子提供了关于那所学院的所有必需信息。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈnɛsɪsərɪ/"},{"example":"I’m afraid it’s become a matter of economic necessity. 恐怕这已成了一个经济需求的问题。","phonetic_uk":"/nɪ'sesɪtɪ/","phonetic_us":"/nə'sɛsəti/","translation":"n. 必要性；必然性","word":"necessity"},{"phonetic_us":"/nɛk/","translation":"n. 颈，脖子","word":"neck","phonetic_uk":"/nek/","example":"Mike rubbed the back of his neck. 迈克揉了揉后颈。"},{"translation":"n. 项链，项圈","phonetic_us":"/'nɛkləs/","word":"necklace","phonetic_uk":"/'neklɪs/","example":"...a diamond necklace and matching earrings. …一条钻石项链和与之相配的耳环。"},{"word":"need","translation":"v. 需要；v. aux需要","phonetic_us":"/nid/","phonetic_uk":"/niːd/","example":"You don’t really need a car. 你其实并不需要一辆车。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'niːd(ə)l/","example":"She carried hypodermic needles and syringes in her bag. 她包里带着皮下注射针和针筒。","word":"needle","phonetic_us":"/'nidl/","translation":"n. 针，缝补，编织针"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 不需要的","word":"needless","example":"The report caused needless anxiety to women who have attended the clinic. 那份报告让去那家诊所就诊过的妇女产生了不必要的忧虑。","phonetic_uk":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ni:dɪ/","example":"a needy family 贫困家庭","translation":"adj. 贫穷的","phonetic_us":"/'nidi/","word":"needy"},{"example":"students with a negative attitude to school 对上学抱消极态度的学生","phonetic_uk":"/'negətiv/","word":"negative","translation":"adj. 否定的；消积的","phonetic_us":"/'nɛɡətɪv/"},{"example":"She smoked and drank, neglected the children, and left the clothes unmended. 她抽烟喝酒，既不照顾孩子，也不缝补衣服。","phonetic_uk":"/nɪˈglekt/","word":"neglect","translation":"v. 忽视","phonetic_us":"/nɪ'glɛkt/"},{"word":"negotiate","translation":"v. 谈判，协商，交涉","phonetic_us":"/nɪ'ɡoʃɪet/","phonetic_uk":"/nɪ'ɡəʊʃɪeɪt/","example":"His first aim is to get the warring parties back to the negotiating table (= discussing something ). 他的首要目标就是把交战各方拉回到谈判桌上。"},{"word":"Negro","translation":"n. 黑人","phonetic_us":"/'nigro/","example":"\"I do not accept the Negro as my equal, \" Douglas said. \"And I deny that he is my brother. “我不会接受黑人与我平等的思想，”道格拉斯说，“而且我拒绝把黑人当成我的兄弟。","phonetic_uk":"/'niːgrəʊ/"},{"translation":"n. 地区","phonetic_us":"/'nebɚ,hʊd/","word":"neighborhood","phonetic_uk":"/'neɪbəhʊd/","example":"Iterates may be categorized into stable and unstable sets depending on whether a neighborhood under iteration converges or diverges. Some move toward stability, others away. 根据一个受迭代影响的社区是聚合还是发散，迭代可以被归类到稳定和不稳定集。有些转向稳定，有些转离。"},{"example":"One of the neighbors complained about the noise from the party. 有位邻居抱怨聚会太吵。","phonetic_uk":"/'neɪbə/","translation":"n. 邻居，邻国，邻人","phonetic_us":"/'neɪbə(r); 'neɪbɚ/","word":"neighbour"},{"phonetic_us":"/nebɚˌhʊd/","translation":"n. 邻居关系；邻近","word":"neighbourhood","example":"...a suburban Boston neighbourhood close to where I live. …离我住处较近的波士顿城郊。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈneɪbəhʊd/"},{"word":"neither","translation":"adj. (两者)都不的","phonetic_us":"/ˈniðɚ; ˈnaɪðɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈnaɪðə; ˈniːðə/","example":"She lives in retirement, neither making nor receiving visits. 她过着隐退的生活， 既不访客， 也不见客。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'nefjuː; 'nevjuː/","example":"I am planning a 25th birthday party for my nephew. 我正在为侄子筹划他25岁的生日聚会。","phonetic_us":"/'nɛfju/","translation":"n. 侄子，外甥","word":"nephew"},{"phonetic_uk":"/nɜːv/","example":"a condition which affects the nerves in the back 影响背部神经的疾病","phonetic_us":"/nɝv/","translation":"n. 神经；勇敢，胆量","word":"nerve"},{"word":"nervous","phonetic_us":"/'nɝvəs/","translation":"adj. 神经的；易激动的","example":"I wish you’d stop looking at me like that. You’re making me nervous. 我希望你不要再那样看着我了，你让我紧张。","phonetic_uk":"/'nɜːvəs/"},{"translation":"n. 巢，窝，穴","phonetic_us":"/nɛst/","word":"nest","phonetic_uk":"/nest/","example":"a bird’s nest 鸟窝"},{"word":"net","phonetic_us":"/nɛt/","translation":"n. 网，网状物；通信网","example":"Bruce spends most evenings surfing the Net (= looking at information in different places on the Internet ). 布鲁斯晚上大多在网上浏览信息。","phonetic_uk":"/net/"},{"example":"Hungary’s telephone network 匈牙利的电话网","phonetic_uk":"/'netwɜːk/","translation":"n. 网状物；网络","phonetic_us":"/'nɛtwɝk/","word":"network"},{"word":"neutral","translation":"adj. 中立的","phonetic_us":"/'nʊtrəl/","example":"I always tried to remain neutral when they started arguing. 他们争论起来的时候我总是努力保持中立。","phonetic_uk":"/'njuːtr(ə)l/"},{"example":"He’s never been to Australia. 他从未去过澳大利亚。","phonetic_uk":"/'nevə/","phonetic_us":"/'nɛvɚ/","translation":"adv. 永不，决不；不","word":"never"},{"translation":"conj. 然而；adv. 仍然","phonetic_us":"/,nɛvɚðə'lɛs/","word":"nevertheless","example":"The news may be unexpected; nevertheless, it is true. 这消息可能是出乎意料的，然而是真实的。","phonetic_uk":"/nevəðə'les/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/njuː/","example":"the city’s new hospital 市里新建的医院","phonetic_us":"/nu/","translation":"adj. 新的；新近出现的","word":"new"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'njuːlɪ/","example":"She was young at the time, and newly married. 那时她还年轻，刚结婚。","word":"newly","phonetic_us":"/'nuli/","translation":"adv. 新近，最近"},{"example":"I hope to have some good news for you soon. 我希望很快就能给你好消息。","phonetic_uk":"/njuːz/","translation":"n. 新闻，消息","phonetic_us":"/nuz/","word":"news"},{"phonetic_us":"/'nuzpepɚ/","translation":"n. 报纸，报","word":"newspaper","phonetic_uk":"/'njuːzpeɪpə; 'njuːs-/","example":"She had read about it in the newspapers. 关于这件事她已经在报纸上看到了。"},{"example":"Eight new national newspapers have appeared on the newsstands since 1981. 自1981年以来，有八家全国性报纸已在报摊上有售。","phonetic_uk":"/'njuːzstænd/","translation":"n.  报摊， 杂志摊","phonetic_us":"/'njʊz,stænd/","word":"newsstand"},{"phonetic_uk":"/nekst/","example":"Grace sighed so heavily that Trish could hear it in the next room. 格雷丝沉重地叹气，特蕾什在隔壁房间都听到了。","word":"next","phonetic_us":"/nɛkst/","translation":"adj. 紧接的；贴近的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/naɪs/","example":"They’ve got a very nice house. 他们的房子真漂亮。","translation":"adj. 美好的，令人愉快的","phonetic_us":"/naɪs/","word":"nice"},{"phonetic_uk":"/niːs/","example":"...his niece, the daughter of his eldest sister. …他的外甥女，他大姐的女儿。","phonetic_us":"/nis/","translation":"n. 侄女，外甥女","word":"niece"},{"word":"night","phonetic_us":"/naɪt/","translation":"n. 夜，夜间","phonetic_uk":"/naɪt/","example":"It was a cold moonlit night. 那是个寒冷的月夜。"},{"translation":"n.  噩梦； 可怕的事物， 无法摆脱的恐惧","phonetic_us":"/'naɪt'mɛr/","word":"nightmare","phonetic_uk":"/'naɪtmeə/","example":"a recurring nightmare  一再出现的噩梦"},{"word":"nine","translation":"num. 九，九个","phonetic_us":"/naɪn/","phonetic_uk":"/naɪn/","example":"He’s only been in this job for nine months. 他干这份工作才九个月。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,naɪn'tin/","translation":"num. 十九，十九个","word":"nineteen","example":"It was nineteen minutes past seven. 当时是7点19分。","phonetic_uk":"/naɪn'tiːn; 'naɪntiːn/"},{"word":"ninety","phonetic_us":"/'naɪnti/","translation":"num. 九十，九十个","example":"America was far richer in the nineties. 90年代的美国要富裕得多。","phonetic_uk":"/'naɪntɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/naɪnθ/","translation":"num. 第九；九分之一","word":"ninth","phonetic_uk":"/'naɪnθ/","example":"In that region, Chile went from ninth to first, overall, as Chilean mobile web use increased by 3200% over the past year. 智利从这一地区的第九跃升到第一位，因为智利的移动网络用户在过去一年增长了 3200% 。"},{"example":"Well, we know nitrogen has what? 对于氮气我们知道什么？","phonetic_uk":"/'naɪtrədʒ(ə)n/","word":"nitrogen","phonetic_us":"/'naɪtrədʒən/","translation":"n. 氮"},{"word":"no","translation":"adv. 不；并不；adj. 没有","phonetic_us":"/no/","phonetic_uk":"/nəʊ/","example":"‘Are you Italian?’ ‘No, I’m Spanish.’ “你是意大利人吗？”“不，我是西班牙人。”"},{"translation":"adj. 贵族的；高尚的","phonetic_us":"/'nobl/","word":"noble","phonetic_uk":"/'nəʊb(ə)l/","example":"It’s very noble of you to spend all your weekends helping the old folk. 你心地真好，周末的时间全都用来帮助老人。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'nəubədi, -bɔdi/","translation":"pron. 谁也不；无人","word":"nobody","example":"I knocked on the door but nobody answered. 我敲了敲门，但没人应门。","phonetic_uk":"/'nəʊbədɪ/"},{"example":"I asked her if she was ready to go, and she nodded. 我问她是否已准备好出发，她点了点头。","phonetic_uk":"/nɒd/","translation":"v. 点(头)；点头表示","phonetic_us":"/nɑd/","word":"nod"},{"word":"noise","translation":"n. 喧闹声；响声；噪声","phonetic_us":"/nɔɪz/","phonetic_uk":"/nɒɪz/","example":"What’s that noise? 那是什么声音？"},{"example":"The kids have been really noisy today. 孩子们今天实在是吵。","phonetic_uk":"/'nɒɪzɪ/","word":"noisy","translation":"adj. 嘈杂的；喧闹的","phonetic_us":"/'nɔɪzi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/nʌn/","example":"I wish I could offer you some cake but there’s none left. 我真想能请你吃些蛋糕，但一点也没剩的了。","word":"none","translation":"pron. 没有人；adv. 毫不","phonetic_us":"/nʌn/"},{"word":"nonsense","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 胡说，废话","example":"‘I’m a prisoner in my own home.’ ‘Nonsense!’ “我在自己家里就像个囚犯。”“胡说！”","phonetic_uk":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/nuːn/","example":"We met at 12 noon. 我们中午12点见了面。","phonetic_us":"/nun/","translation":"n. 正午，中午","word":"noon"},{"example":"He can neither read nor write (= he cannot read or write ). 他既不会读也不会写。","phonetic_uk":"/nɔː; nə/","translation":"conj. 也不；不","phonetic_us":"/nɔr/","word":"nor"},{"word":"normal","translation":"adj. 正常的，普通的","phonetic_us":"/'nɔrml/","example":"A normal working week is 40 hours. 一个正常的工作周是40小时。","phonetic_uk":"/'nɔːm(ə)l/"},{"translation":"adv. 通常，正常地","phonetic_us":"/'nɔrmli/","word":"normally","example":"The journey normally takes about two hours. 这段旅程通常需要大约两小时。","phonetic_uk":"/'nɔːm(ə)lɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/nɔːθ/","example":"Which way is north? 哪边是北？","word":"north","translation":"n. 北，北方；adj. 北方的","phonetic_us":"/nɔrθ/"},{"word":"northeast","translation":"n. 东北；adj. 位于东北的","phonetic_us":"/'nɔrθ'ist/","phonetic_uk":"/,nɔ:θ'i:st/","example":"...the warm waters of Salt Springs Island to the northeast. …流向东北方向的盐泉岛的温泉水。"},{"translation":"adj. 北方的，北部的","phonetic_us":"/'nɔrðɚn/","word":"northern","phonetic_uk":"/'nɔːð(ə)n/","example":"a man with a northern accent 带有北方口音的男子"},{"phonetic_us":"/'nɔrθ'wɛst/","translation":"n. 西北；adj. 位于西北的","word":"northwest","example":"...four miles to the northwest. …西北方向4英里。","phonetic_uk":"/,nɔ:θ'west/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/nəʊz/","example":"Someone punched him on the nose. 有人一拳打在他的鼻子上。","phonetic_us":"/noz/","translation":"n. 鼻子；突出部分","word":"nose"},{"word":"not","phonetic_us":"/nɑt/","translation":"adv. 不，没有","example":"Most of the stores do not open until 10 am. 大多数商店要到上午10点才开始营业。","phonetic_uk":"/nɒt/"},{"example":"Can I borrow your lecture notes? 我能不能借用一下你的课堂笔记？","phonetic_uk":"/nəʊt/","word":"note","phonetic_us":"/not/","translation":"n. 笔记；便条；注释"},{"word":"notebook","phonetic_us":"/'notbʊk/","translation":"n. 笔记本，期票簿","example":"He brought out a notebook and pen from his pocket. 他从口袋里掏出了一个笔记本和一支钢笔。","phonetic_uk":"/'nəʊtbʊk/"},{"example":"Nothing ever happens in this town. 这镇上从来都不会发生什么特别的事。","phonetic_uk":"/'nʌθɪŋ/","translation":"n. 没有东西；adv. 毫不","phonetic_us":"/'nʌθɪŋ/","word":"nothing"},{"word":"notice","phonetic_us":"/'notɪs/","translation":"v. 注意；n. 通知；注意","phonetic_uk":"/'nəʊtɪs/","example":"He noticed a woman in a black dress sitting across from him. 他看到有位黑衣女子坐在他的对面。"},{"word":"noticeable","phonetic_us":"/'notɪsəbl/","translation":"adj. 显而易见的；重要的","example":"Alcohol has a noticeable effect on the body. 酒精对身体有明显的影响。","phonetic_uk":"/'nəʊtɪsəb(ə)l/"},{"example":"The skipper notified the coastguard of the tragedy. 船长通知了海岸警卫队这一灾难。","phonetic_uk":"/'nəutɪfaɪ/","word":"notify","translation":"vt.  通知， 告知， 报告","phonetic_us":"/'notə'fai/"},{"translation":"n.  概念， 观念； 意图， 想法， 念头","phonetic_us":"/'noʃən/","word":"notion","phonetic_uk":"/'nəuʃn/","example":"She had no notion what he meant. 她根本不明白他是什么意思。"},{"phonetic_us":"/naʊn/","translation":"n. 名词","word":"noun","example":"An adjective must agree with  its noun in mumber and case. 形容词在数和格方面必须符合其所修饰的名词。","phonetic_uk":"/naʊn/"},{"word":"nourish","translation":"vt.  提供养分， 养育","phonetic_us":"/'nɜrɪʃ/","phonetic_uk":"/'nʌrɪʃ/","example":"The food she eats nourishes both her and the baby. 她吃的食物为她和婴儿提供营养。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'nɒv(ə)l/","example":"a novel by Jane Austen 简·奥斯丁的小说","word":"novel","translation":"n. 小说；adj. 新的","phonetic_us":"/ˈnɑːvl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/nə(ʊ)'vembə/","example":"And again in November. 在十一月又一次。","phonetic_us":"/no'vɛmbɚ/","translation":"n. 十一月","word":"November"},{"example":"She's a widow now. 她现在是一个寡妇。","phonetic_uk":"/naʊ/","translation":"adv. 现在；立刻；于是","phonetic_us":"/naʊ/","word":"now"},{"example":"Nowadays people are rarely shocked by the sex they see on television. 如今人们在电视上看见性爱镜头不太会感到吃惊了。","phonetic_uk":"/'naʊədeɪz/","word":"nowadays","phonetic_us":"/'naʊədez/","translation":"adv. 现今，现在"},{"phonetic_us":"/'no'wɛr/","translation":"adv. 任何地方都不","word":"nowhere","phonetic_uk":"/'nəʊhweə/","example":"Nowhere is drug abuse more of a problem than in the US. 没有什么地方的吸毒问题比美国更严重。"},{"word":"nuclear","translation":"adj. 原子核的；核心的","phonetic_us":"/'nuklɪɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'njuːklɪə/","example":"France’s reliance on nuclear energy 法国对核能的依赖"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'njuːklɪəs/","example":"Neutrons and protons are bound together in the nucleus of an atom. 在一个原子的核内，中子和质子聚合在一起。","translation":"n. 核，核心；(原子)核","phonetic_us":"/'nuklɪəs/","word":"nucleus"},{"example":"He could be a bit of a nuisance when he was drunk. 他喝醉时会是一个有点令人讨厌的人。","phonetic_uk":"/'njuːs(ə)ns/","translation":"n. 讨厌的东西","phonetic_us":"/'nusns/","word":"nuisance"},{"word":"number","translation":"n. 数，数字；号码","phonetic_us":"/'nʌmbɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'nʌmbə/","example":"They wrote various numbers on a large sheet of paper. 他们在一张大纸上写下了很多不同的数字。"},{"word":"numerous","phonetic_us":"/'numərəs/","translation":"adj. 为数众多的；许多","phonetic_uk":"/'njuːm(ə)rəs/","example":"Numerous attempts have been made to hide the truth. 为掩盖事实作了很多尝试。"},{"example":"The nurse is coming to give you an injection. 护士会来给你打针。","phonetic_uk":"/nɜːs/","phonetic_us":"/nɝs/","translation":"n. 保姆；护士；v. 看护","word":"nurse"},{"example":"She puts her baby in this nursery and then goes back to work. 她把孩子送到这家托儿所然后回去上班。","phonetic_uk":"/'nɜːs(ə)rɪ/","translation":"n. 托儿所；苗圃","phonetic_us":"/'nɝsəri/","word":"nursery"},{"translation":"n. 坚果，干果；螺母","phonetic_us":"/nʌt/","word":"nut","example":"a pine nut 松子","phonetic_uk":"/nʌt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/njʊ'trɪʃəs/","example":"Wholemeal bread is more nutritious than white bread. 全麦面包比白面包更有营养。","word":"nutritious","translation":"adj. 营养的","phonetic_us":"/nʊ'trɪʃəs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'naɪlɒn/","example":"nylon fabric 尼龙织物","translation":"n. 尼龙，耐纶","phonetic_us":"/'naɪlɑn/","word":"nylon"},{"translation":"n. 栎属植物；栎木","phonetic_us":"/ok/","word":"oak","example":"an oak door 橡木门","phonetic_uk":"/əʊk/"},{"word":"oar","phonetic_us":"/ɔr/","translation":"n. 浆，橹","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ɔː/"},{"example":"The little boy made no effort to obey. 这小男孩不肯服从。","phonetic_uk":"/ə(ʊ)'beɪ/","phonetic_us":"/ə'be/","translation":"v. 顺从；v. 服从","word":"obey"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɒbdʒɪkt; -dʒekt/","example":"an everyday object such as a spoon 调羹之类的日常用品","word":"object","phonetic_us":"/'ɑbdʒɛkt/","translation":"n. 物，物体；目的"},{"example":"Her objection was that he was too young. 她反对的理由是他太小。","phonetic_uk":"/əb'dʒekʃ(ə)n/","word":"objection","translation":"n. 反对","phonetic_us":"/əb'dʒɛkʃən/"},{"translation":"adj. 客观的；无偏见的","phonetic_us":"/əb'dʒɛktɪv/","word":"objective","example":"Scientists need to be objective when doing research. 科学家做研究时要客观。","phonetic_uk":"/əb'dʒektɪv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌɒblɪ'geɪʃn/","example":"Employers have an obligation to treat all employees equally. 雇主有责任对所有员工一视同仁。","word":"obligation","translation":"n.  义务， 责任","phonetic_us":"/,ɑblɪ'ɡeʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'blaɪdʒ/","example":"The storm got worse and worse. Finally, I was obliged to abandon the car and continue on foot. 暴风雨越来越猛烈。最终，我被迫弃车徒步前行。","translation":"v. 迫使；施恩惠于","phonetic_us":"/ə'blaɪdʒ/","word":"oblige"},{"word":"observation","translation":"n. 注意；观察；观察力","phonetic_us":"/,ɑbzɚ'veʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ɒbzə'veɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"He spent two nights under close observation in hospital. 他在医院接受了两个晚上的严密观察。"},{"word":"observe","phonetic_us":"/əb'zɝv/","translation":"v. 遵守","example":"So far the ceasefire has been observed by both sides. 到目前为止，双方都遵守着停火协定。","phonetic_uk":"/əbˈzɜ:v/"},{"word":"observer","translation":"n. 观察员，观测者","phonetic_us":"/əb'zɝvɚ/","example":"political observers 政治观察员","phonetic_uk":"/əb'zɜːvə/"},{"example":"The tax puts obstacles in the way of companies trying to develop trade overseas. 这项税收为想在海外发展贸易的公司设置了障碍。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɒbstəkl/","translation":"n. 阻碍","phonetic_us":"/'ɑbstəkl/","word":"obstacle"},{"phonetic_us":"/əb'ten/","translation":"v. 获得","word":"obtain","example":"Evans was trying to obtain a false passport and other documents. 埃文斯当时正试图获取假护照和其他文件。","phonetic_uk":"/əb'teɪn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɑbvɪəs/","translation":"adj. 明显的，显而易见的","word":"obvious","example":"The obvious way of reducing pollution is to use cars less. 减少污染显而易见的办法就是少用汽车。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒbvɪəs/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɑbvɪəsli/","translation":"adv. 明显地，显然地","word":"obviously","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒbvɪəslɪ/","example":"We’re obviously going to need more help. 显然我们将需要更多的帮助。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əˈkeɪʒn/","example":"I often think fondly of an occasion some years ago in New Orleans. 我经常深情地想起一些年前在新奥尔良所发生的一幕。","word":"occasion","phonetic_us":"/ə'keʒn/","translation":"n. 场合"},{"word":"occasional","translation":"adj. 偶然的；临时的","phonetic_us":"/ə'keʒənl/","phonetic_uk":"/ə'keɪʒ(ə)n(ə)l/","example":"He made occasional visits to London. 他有时候会去伦敦。"},{"word":"occasionally","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adv. 偶然；非经常地","phonetic_uk":"","example":""},{"example":"Please state your name, address and occupation. 请写明你的姓名、地址和职业。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɒkjuˈpeɪʃn/","word":"occupation","translation":"n. 职业，工作","phonetic_us":"/,ɑkju'peʃən/"},{"example":"Football occupies most of my leisure time. 足球占去了我大部分的闲暇时间。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒkjʊpaɪ/","word":"occupy","phonetic_us":"/'ɑkjupaɪ/","translation":"v. 占领；占，占有"},{"example":"A third of accidental deaths occur in the home. 有三分之一的意外死亡发生在家里。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'kɜː/","word":"occur","phonetic_us":"/ə'kɝ/","translation":"v. 发生；出现，存在"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'kʌr(ə)ns/","example":"Complaints seemed to be an everyday occurrence. 投诉似乎成了天天发生的事。","phonetic_us":"/ə'kʌrəns/","translation":"n. 发生，出现；事件","word":"occurrence"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 海洋；洋","word":"ocean","example":"The cape extends far into the ocean. 那海岬伸向海洋远处。","phonetic_uk":""},{"word":"Oceania","phonetic_us":"/,oʃɪ'ænɪə/","translation":"n. 大洋洲","phonetic_uk":"/,əʊsɪ'ɑːnɪə; -ʃɪ-/","example":"The Mummies Of The World exhibition brings together a collection of mummies and related artefacts from South America, Europe, Asia, Oceania and Egypt. 汇集了来自南美，欧洲，亚洲，大洋洲和埃及的一系列干尸和艺术品将举办全球巡回展览。"},{"word":"October","translation":"n. 十月","phonetic_us":"/ɑk'tobɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/ɒk'təʊbə/","example":"Most seasonal hiring is done in early October. 多数季节性招聘是在10月初进行。"},{"word":"odd","phonetic_us":"/ɑd/","translation":"adj. 奇数的；单只的","phonetic_uk":"/ɒd/","example":"It was an odd thing to say. 这话说得很奇怪。"},{"example":"...the lingering odour of car exhaust. …挥之不去的汽车尾气的独特气味。","phonetic_uk":"/'əʊdə/","translation":"n. 气味，香气；味道","phonetic_us":"/'əudə/","word":"odour"},{"phonetic_us":"/ʌv; əv/","translation":"prep. …的；由于","word":"of","example":"the back of the house 房子的后部","phonetic_uk":"/ɒv; (ə)v/"},{"example":"How are you off for sports equipment? (= do you have enough? ) 你的体育运动装备够不够？","phonetic_uk":"/ɒf/","translation":"adv. (离)开；(停)止","phonetic_us":"/ɔf/","word":"off"},{"example":"His remarks deeply offended many Scottish people. 他的话严重冒犯了许多苏格兰人。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'fend/","translation":"v. 冒犯；v. 犯过错","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɛnd/","word":"offend"},{"translation":"n. 过错，犯罪","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɛns/","word":"offense","example":"These efforts have led to a growing confidence among the public that corruption is a serious punishable offense in Albania. 这些努力增强了公众的信心，即人们相信，腐败在阿尔巴尼亚是严重犯罪，能够受到惩罚。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'fens/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'fensɪv/","example":"I found her remarks deeply offensive. 我觉得她的话令人非常恼火。","word":"offensive","translation":"adj. 冒犯的，无礼的；进攻的，攻击性的；n.  进攻， 攻势","phonetic_us":"/ə'fɛnsɪv/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɔfɚ/","translation":"v. 提供；提出；n. 提供","word":"offer","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒfə/","example":"A number of groups offer their services free of charge. 一些团体免费提供服务。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɔfɪs/","translation":"n. 办公室；处，局，社","word":"office","example":"The department occupies an office just a mile from the White House. 该部门就在离白宫一英里远的地方有个办公楼。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒfɪs/"},{"word":"officer","translation":"n. 官员；干事；军官","phonetic_us":"/'ɔfɪsɚ/","example":"a commanding officer of the SAS 英国空军特种部队的一名指挥官","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒfɪsə/"},{"word":"official","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 官员的；官方的","phonetic_uk":"","example":""},{"example":"She often works at the weekend. 她周末经常要上班。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒf(tə)n/","word":"often","translation":"adv. 经常，常常","phonetic_us":"/'ɔf(tə)n; 'ɑf(tə)n/"},{"translation":"int. 嗬，哦，唉呀","phonetic_us":"/o/","word":"oh","phonetic_uk":"/əʊ/","example":"Oh, look, I think that’s Harry over there. 噢，你看，我想那边那个人是哈里。"},{"translation":"n. 油；石油；v. 加油于","phonetic_us":"/ɔɪl/","word":"oil","phonetic_uk":"/ɒɪl/","example":"a rise in the price of oil 石油价格的上涨"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'əʊ'keɪ/","example":"","translation":"(缩作OK)a&ad. 对，好","phonetic_us":"/,o'kɛi/","word":"okay"},{"example":"How old are you? 你多大年纪？","phonetic_uk":"/əʊld/","phonetic_us":"/old/","translation":"adj. 老的；…岁的","word":"old"},{"word":"omit","phonetic_us":"/ə'mɪt/","translation":"v. 省略，省去；遗漏","example":"Please don’t omit any details, no matter how trivial they may seem. 请不要忽略任何细节，不管它多细小。","phonetic_uk":"/ə(ʊ)'mɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɒn/","example":"I wanted to punch him on the nose. 我真想一拳打到他鼻子上。","word":"on","phonetic_us":"/ɑn/","translation":"prep. 在…上；在…旁"},{"example":"I’ve only met her once. 我只见过她一面。","phonetic_uk":"/wʌns/","word":"once","translation":"adv. 一次；曾经；n. 一次","phonetic_us":"/wʌns/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/wʌn/","example":"They had one daughter. 他们有一个女儿。","word":"one","translation":"num. 一；pron. 一个人","phonetic_us":"/wʌn/"},{"example":"It is only through study that one really begins to know oneself. 只有通过学习，一个人才能真正了解自己。","phonetic_uk":"/wʌn'self/","word":"oneself","phonetic_us":"/wʌn'sɛlf/","translation":"pron. 自己；亲自"},{"example":"Chop the onions finely. 把洋葱切碎。","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌnjən/","word":"onion","phonetic_us":"/'ʌnjən/","translation":"n. 洋葱，洋葱头"},{"word":"only","phonetic_us":"/'onli/","translation":"adv. 只，仅仅；adj. 唯一的","example":"Naomi was only 17 when she got married. 娜奥米结婚时才17岁。","phonetic_uk":"/'əʊnlɪ/"},{"word":"onto","phonetic_us":"/ˈɑnˌtu, -tə, ˈɔn-/","translation":"prep. 到…上","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒntuː/","example":"She watched him walk onto the platform. 她看着他走上站台。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'əʊp(ə)n/","example":"He threw the door open and ran down the stairs. 他猛地打开门，往楼下跑去。","word":"open","translation":"adj. 开的；开放的；v. 开","phonetic_us":"/'opən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'opənɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 开始的；n. 开始","word":"opening","phonetic_uk":"/'əʊp(ə)nɪŋ/","example":"the opening match of the season 本赛季的首场比赛"},{"example":"We go to the opera (= go to a performance of opera ) regularly. 我们常去听歌剧。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒp(ə)rə/","phonetic_us":"/'ɑprə/","translation":"n. 歌剧","word":"opera"},{"translation":"v. 操作；施行手术","phonetic_us":"/'ɑpə'ret/","word":"operate","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒpəreɪt/","example":"The Lewis family operated a number of boats on the canal. 刘易斯一家在运河上经营着几艘船。"},{"word":"operation","translation":"n. 手术；行动","phonetic_us":"/,ɑpə'reʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɒpəˈreɪʃn/","example":"The UN rescue operation started shortly after dawn. 联合国的救援行动在破晓后不久就开始了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɒpə'reɪʃ(ə)n(ə)l/","example":"The boat should be operational by this afternoon. 今天下午这艘船应该可以使用了。","word":"operational","translation":"adj. 操作上的；可使用的","phonetic_us":"/'ɑpə'reʃənl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɒpəreɪtə/","example":"Hello, operator? Could you put me through to Room 31? 喂，接线员吗？请帮我接31号房间。","word":"operator","translation":"n. 操作人员，接线员","phonetic_us":"/'ɑpəretɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pɪnjən/","example":"When choosing an insurance policy it’s best to get an independent opinion. 选择保险时，最好听听专家的独立意见。","phonetic_us":"/ə'pɪnjən/","translation":"n. 意见，看法，主张","word":"opinion"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pəʊnənt/","example":"Graf’s opponent in today’s final will be Sukova. 格拉芙今天的决赛对手将是苏科娃。","word":"opponent","translation":"n. 对手","phonetic_us":"/ə'ponənt/"},{"word":"opportunity","phonetic_us":"/ˌɑpɚˈtunɪti, -ˈtju-/","translation":"n. 机会，良机","example":"There are fewer opportunities for new graduates this year. 今年新毕业的大学生就业机会较少。","phonetic_uk":"/ɒpə'tjuːnɪtɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pəʊz/","example":"Congress is continuing to oppose the President’s health care budget. 国会继续反对总统的医疗保健预算。","word":"oppose","phonetic_us":"/ə'poz/","translation":"v. 反对；反抗"},{"example":"I thought the medicine would make him sleep, but it had the opposite effect. 我以为这药会让他睡觉，但是它却起了反作用。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɔpəzɪt/","word":"opposite","phonetic_us":"/ˈɑpəzɪt; ˈɑpəsɪt/","translation":"adj. 相反的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ə'pres/","example":"native tribes oppressed by the authorities 受到当局压迫的土著部落","phonetic_us":"/ə'prɛs/","translation":"v. 压迫，压制；压抑","word":"oppress"},{"example":"microscopes and other optical instruments 显微镜和其他光学仪器","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒptɪk(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 眼的；光学的","phonetic_us":"/'ɑptɪkl/","word":"optical"},{"word":"optimistic","translation":"adj. 乐观的","phonetic_us":"/,ɑptɪ'mɪstɪk/","example":"Andrew took a more optimistic view. 安德鲁抱有更为乐观的想法。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɒptɪˈmɪstɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɒpʃ(ə)n/","example":"There are a number of options available. 有多种选择。","word":"option","translation":"n. 选择","phonetic_us":"/'ɑpʃən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɑpʃənl/","translation":"adj. 可以任意选择的","word":"optional","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒpʃ(ə)n(ə)l/","example":"three optional courses 三门选修课"},{"word":"or","phonetic_us":"/ɔr/","translation":"conj. 或，或者；即","phonetic_uk":"/ɔː/","example":"Shall we go out to the cinema or stay at home? 我们是出去看电影还是待在家里？"},{"word":"oral","translation":"adj. 口头的；口的","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrəl/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːr(ə)l/","example":"oral history 口述的历史"},{"translation":"n. 橙(树)；柑(树)","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrɪndʒ/","word":"orange","example":"orange juice 橙汁","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒrɪn(d)ʒ/"},{"word":"orbit","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrbɪt/","translation":"n. 运行轨道；v. 环绕","example":"Mars and Earth have orbits which change with time. 火星和地球的轨道随着时间而发生改变。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːbɪt/"},{"example":"He directed an orchestra. 他指挥一个管弦乐队。","phonetic_uk":"","word":"orchestra","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 管弦乐队"},{"word":"order","translation":"n. 次序；整齐；v. 命令","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrdɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːdə/","example":"There seemed to be no logical order to the sections. 这几部分似乎没有逻辑顺序。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɔrdɚli/","translation":"adj. 整洁的；有秩序的","word":"orderly","example":"She needs to organize her ideas in a more orderly way. 她需要把自己的想法组织得更有条理些。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːd(ə)lɪ/"},{"translation":"adj. 平常的；平凡的","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrdnɛri/","word":"ordinary","example":"It’s just an ordinary camera. 这只是普通的相机。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːdɪn(ə)rɪ; -d(ə)n-/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɔː/","example":"iron ore 铁矿石","phonetic_us":"/ɔr/","translation":"n. 矿，矿石，矿砂","word":"ore"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɔrɡən/","translation":"n. 器官","word":"organ","example":"the liver, heart, and other internal organs 肝脏、心脏及其他内脏器官","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔ:ɡən/"},{"example":"Organic farming is better for the environment. 有机耕作对环境更有利。","phonetic_uk":"/ɔː'gænɪk/","word":"organic","phonetic_us":"/ɔr'gænɪk/","translation":"adj. 有机体的；器官的"},{"example":"All living organisms have to adapt to changes in environmental conditions. 一切生物都要适应环境条件的变化。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːg(ə)nɪz(ə)m/","word":"organism","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrɡənɪzəm/","translation":"n. 生物体；有机体"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ɔrɡənə'zeʃən/","translation":"n. 组织；团体，机构","word":"organization","phonetic_uk":"/ˌɔːɡənaɪ'zeɪʃn/","example":"The public expect high standards from any large organization. 公众对任何大型机构都期望很高。"},{"word":"organize","phonetic_us":"/ɔrɡənˌaɪz/","translation":"v. 组织，编组","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɔ:gənaɪz/","example":"The course was organized by a training company. 这一课程是由一家培训公司组织的。"},{"example":"a beautiful oriental rug 漂亮的东方地毯","phonetic_uk":"/ɔːrɪ'ent(ə)l; ɒr-/","word":"oriental","translation":"adj. 东方的；东方国家的","phonetic_us":"/,orɪ'ɛntəl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɔrɪdʒɪn/","translation":"n. 起源","word":"origin","example":"The tradition has its origins in the Middle Ages. 这一传统源于中世纪。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒrɪdʒɪn/"},{"translation":"adj. 原始的，最初的","phonetic_us":"/ə'rɪdʒənl/","word":"original","example":"The land was returned to its original owner. 这块土地归还给了原主。","phonetic_uk":"/ə'ridʒənl/"},{"example":"How did the plan originate? 这个计划最早是怎么想到的？","phonetic_uk":"/ə'rɪdʒɪneɪt/","phonetic_us":"/əˈrɪdʒəˌnet/","translation":"v. 开始","word":"originate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːnəm(ə)nt/","example":"a shelf covered with books and ornaments 摆满书籍和装饰品的架子","translation":"n. 装饰物；装饰","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrnəmənt/","word":"ornament"},{"example":"The war has left thousands of children as orphans. 这场战争使成千上万的孩子成为孤儿。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɔːf(ə)n/","word":"orphan","phonetic_us":"/'ɔrfn/","translation":"n. 孤儿"},{"translation":"adj. 另外的；其余的","phonetic_us":"/'ʌðɚ/","word":"other","example":"They were just like any other young couple. 他们那时就和其他任何年轻夫妇一样。","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌðə/"},{"translation":"adv. 另外；要不然","phonetic_us":"/'ʌðɚwaɪz/","word":"otherwise","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌðəwaɪz/","example":"You’ll have to go now, otherwise you’ll miss your bus. 你现在就得走，要不然就赶不上公共汽车了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ɔːt/","example":"","translation":"v. aux应当，应该","phonetic_us":"/ɔt/","word":"ought"},{"phonetic_us":"/aʊns/","translation":"n. 盎司，英两","word":"ounce","example":"One ounce of almonds contains nearly half the recommended daily amount. 一盎司杏仁大约包含每日需求量的一半。","phonetic_uk":"/aʊns/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/aʊə/","example":"They partook of our triumph. 他们分享我们的胜利。","translation":"pron. 我们的","phonetic_us":"/aʊr/","word":"our"},{"example":"I’ll show you to your room. Ours is next door. 我带你去你的房间，我们的房间在你的隔壁。","phonetic_uk":"/aʊəz/","word":"ours","phonetic_us":"/ɑrz/","translation":"pron. 我们的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/aʊə'selvz/","example":"We prepared ourselves for the long journey ahead. 我们为将要开始的长途旅行做好了准备。","phonetic_us":"/ɑr'sɛlvz/","translation":"pron. 我们自己","word":"ourselves"},{"word":"out","translation":"adv. 出，在外；现出来","phonetic_us":"/aʊt/","phonetic_uk":"/aʊt/","example":"She opened her suitcase and took out a pair of shoes. 她打开手提箱，拿出一双鞋。"},{"word":"outcome","translation":"n. 结果","phonetic_us":"/'aʊt'kʌm/","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtkʌm/","example":"People who had heard the evidence at the trial were surprised at the outcome. 在审判过程中听过证词的人都对此结果感到吃惊。"},{"word":"outdoor","phonetic_us":"/'aʊt'dɔr/","translation":"adj. 户外的，室外的","example":"a huge outdoor market 一个规模庞大的露天市场","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtdɔː/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/aʊt'dɔːz/","example":"It’s warm enough to eat outdoors tonight. 今晚很暖和，可以在户外用餐。","translation":"adv. 在户外，在野外","phonetic_us":"/'aʊt'dɔrz/","word":"outdoors"},{"example":"Remove the tough outer leaves before cooking. 烹煮之前先把外面的老叶子去掉。","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtə/","translation":"adj. 外部的，外面的","phonetic_us":"/'aʊtɚ/","word":"outer"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtgəʊɪŋ/","example":"We’re looking for someone with an outgoing personality. 我们在找一个性格外向的人。","phonetic_us":"/'aʊt'goɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 开朗的；外出的","word":"outgoing"},{"word":"outlet","phonetic_us":"/'aʊtlɛt/","translation":"n. 出口，出路；排遣","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtlet/","example":"a waste water outlet 污水排放口"},{"example":"a research proposal outline 研究计划梗概","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtlaɪn/","translation":"n. 梗概，提纲，草稿，要点","phonetic_us":"/'aʊtlaɪn/","word":"outline"},{"word":"outlook","phonetic_us":"/'aʊtlʊk/","translation":"n. 观点，看法；展望","example":"Exercise will improve your looks and your outlook. 运动将会改善你的外在形象和人生态度。","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtlʊk/"},{"example":"Output is up 30% on last year. 产量比去年提高了30%。","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtpʊt/","translation":"n. 产量；输出量；输出","phonetic_us":"/'aʊtpʊt/","word":"output"},{"phonetic_us":"/'aʊtsɛt/","translation":"n. 开始，开端","word":"outset","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtset/","example":"It was clear from the outset that there were going to be problems. 从一开始就很清楚会有问题出现的。"},{"example":"...the outside of the building. …该建筑物的外部。","phonetic_uk":"/aʊt'saɪd; 'aʊtsaɪd/","word":"outside","phonetic_us":"/,aʊt'saɪd/","translation":"n. 外部；外表a外部的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtskɜːt/","example":"Mianyang Nanjiao Airport is seated in southern outskirt of Minayang city proper, operating flights to Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou. 绵阳南郊机场位于绵阳南部郊区，有航班开往北京，上海和广州。","word":"outskirt","phonetic_us":"/'aʊt,skɝt /","translation":"n. 外边，郊区"},{"translation":"adj. 突出的，杰出的","phonetic_us":"/'aʊt'stændɪŋ/","word":"outstanding","phonetic_uk":"/aʊt'stændɪŋ/","example":"an outstanding example of a 13th-century castle 13世纪城堡的杰出典范"},{"example":"The economy and outward appearance of the area have changed considerably. 该地区的经济和面貌发生了很大的变化。","phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtwəd/","word":"outward","phonetic_us":"/'aʊtwɚd/","translation":"adj. 外面的；向外的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'aʊtwədz/","example":"The door opens outwards. 这门是朝外开的。","translation":"adv. 向外，往海外","phonetic_us":"/'aʊtwɚdz/","word":"outwards"},{"example":"...the small oval framed picture of a little boy. …一个小男孩的镶在椭圆形框架里的小幅照片。","phonetic_uk":"/'əuvl/","translation":"adj.  椭圆形的；n. 椭圆形","phonetic_us":"/'ovl/","word":"oval"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ʌv(ə)n/","example":"Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C. 把烤箱预热至200摄氏度。","word":"oven","phonetic_us":"/'ʌvn/","translation":"n. 炉，灶；烘箱"},{"example":"A lamp hung over the table. 一盏灯悬挂在桌子上方。","phonetic_uk":"/'əʊvə/","translation":"prep. 在…上方；超过","phonetic_us":"/'ovɚ/","word":"over"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'əʊvərɔːl/","example":"The overall cost of the exhibition was £400,000. 展览会的全部费用是40万英镑。","phonetic_us":"/,ovə'rɔl/","translation":"n. 工装裤；adj. 全面的","word":"overall"},{"word":"overcharge","translation":"v. 向……多收费","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'tʃɑrdʒ/","example":"Rural medics get an average stipend of $65 a year, leading some to overcharge their patients. 这些医生每年仅得到65美元，这导致他们向病人高收费。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvəˈtʃɑ:dʒ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'əʊvəkəʊt/","example":"I sprang 400 pounds for  her overcoat. 给她买那件大衣，我花了400镑。","translation":"n. 外衣，大衣","phonetic_us":"/'ovɚkot/","word":"overcoat"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'kʌm/","translation":"v. 战胜，克服","word":"overcome","phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvə'kʌm/","example":"He struggled to overcome his shyness. 他努力克服自己的羞怯。"},{"word":"overestimate","translation":"v. 对（数量）估计过高","phonetic_us":"/,ovər'ɛstɪmət/","example":"He tends to overestimate his own abilities. 他往往高估自己的能力。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvər'estɪmeɪt/"},{"example":"The drains flooded and water overflowed down the main street. 下水道被淹，水溢到了大街上。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvə'fləʊ/","word":"overflow","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'flo/","translation":"v. 溢出，淹没"},{"example":"The fireworks cracked overhead. 鞭炮在头顶上空噼啪地爆响。","phonetic_uk":"","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 在头顶上的；架空的","word":"overhead"},{"example":"57 percent complained of work overload. 57%的人抱怨工作负担过重。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvə'ləʊd/","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'lod/","translation":"n. 使负担太重","word":"overload"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/əʊvə'lʊk/","translation":"v. 眺望；看漏；放任","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'lʊk/","word":"overlook"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əʊvə'naɪt/","example":"He became a millionaire overnight. 他一夜之间就成了百万富翁。","word":"overnight","translation":"adv. 一夜；突然","phonetic_us":"/'ovənaɪt/"},{"example":"Chris is going to work overseas. 克里斯要去国外工作。","phonetic_uk":"/əʊvə'siːz/","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'siz/","translation":"adv. 海外；adj. 在海外的","word":"overseas"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əʊvə'steɪt/","example":"To say that all motorists speed in residential areas is overstating the case. 说所有驾驶员都在住宅区内超速行驶是言过其实了。","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'stet/","translation":"v. 夸张，夸大","word":"overstate"},{"example":"He pulled out to overtake the van. 他把车驶出所在车道想超过那辆小货车。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvə'teɪk/","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'tek/","translation":"v. 超车","word":"overtake"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'əʊvətaɪm/","example":"The firm wanted to chisel him out of his overtime pay. 公司想要剥夺他的超时加班费。","word":"overtime","translation":"adj. 超时的，加班的","phonetic_us":"/,ovə'taɪm/"},{"word":"overweight","translation":"v. 超重的","phonetic_us":"/'ovə'wet/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvə'weɪt/","example":"I wonder if this letter is overweight. 我想知道这封信是否超重。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'wɛlm/","translation":"v. 压倒，战胜","word":"overwhelm","phonetic_uk":"/əʊvə'welm/","example":"But the various pros and cons should not blindly overwhelm one another. 但是，众多的利弊得失不应盲目的一个压倒另一个。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌəʊvəˈwelmɪŋ/","example":"There is overwhelming evidence that smoking damages your health. 有难以辩驳的证据表明吸烟有损健康。","translation":"adj. 压倒性的","phonetic_us":"/,ovɚ'wɛlmɪŋ/","word":"overwhelming"},{"phonetic_uk":"/əʊ/","example":"How much do I owe you (= often used to show that you want to pay for something )? 我该付你多少钱？","translation":"v. 欠；应把…归功于","phonetic_us":"/o/","word":"owe"},{"word":"owing","translation":"adj.  应付的， 未付的","phonetic_us":"/'oɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/'əuɪŋ/","example":"You need to pay the amount owing, plus the interest. 你需要付清欠款，外加利息。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/aʊl/","example":"Some of the more extreme contacts give you \"cat eyes\" or how about \"owl eyes\"? 一些更酷的隐形眼镜可以给你一双\"猫眼\"或者是\"猫头鹰的眼睛\"。","phonetic_us":"/aʊl/","translation":"n. 猫头鹰，枭","word":"owl"},{"example":"Bring your own equipment. 带上你自己的装备。","phonetic_uk":"/əʊn/","word":"own","translation":"adj. 自己的；v. 有，拥有","phonetic_us":"/on/"},{"example":"He was now the proud owner of a bright red sports car. 他现在拥有了一辆亮红色跑车，很是自豪。","phonetic_uk":"/'əʊnə/","word":"owner","translation":"n. 物主，所有人","phonetic_us":"/'onɚ/"},{"example":"The price of home ownership is increasing. 房价在不断上涨。","phonetic_uk":"/'əʊnəʃɪp/","word":"ownership","translation":"n. 所有(权)，所有制","phonetic_us":"/'onɚʃɪp/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/ɒks/","phonetic_us":"/ɑks/","translation":"n. 牛；公牛，阉牛","word":"ox"},{"example":"The human brain needs to be without oxygen for only four minutes before permanent damage occurs. 人脑缺氧只需4分钟就会造成永久性损伤。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɒksɪdʒən/","word":"oxygen","translation":"n.  氧， 氧气","phonetic_us":"/'ɑksɪdʒən/"},{"word":"pace","phonetic_us":"/pes/","translation":"n. 步，步速；v. 踱步","phonetic_uk":"/peɪs/","example":"He quickened his pace , longing to be home. 他加快步伐，盼望着早点回到家中。"},{"word":"pacific","translation":"adj. 和平的；n. 太平洋","phonetic_us":"/pə'sɪfɪk/","phonetic_uk":"/pə'sɪfɪk/","example":"a normally pacific community 平日里静悄悄的社区"},{"word":"pack","translation":"v. 捆扎；挤满；n. 包","phonetic_us":"/pæk/","phonetic_uk":"/pæk/","example":"Hundreds of people packed into the mosque. 成百上千的人挤进了清真寺。"},{"word":"package","phonetic_us":"/'pækɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 包裹，包，捆","phonetic_uk":"/'pækɪdʒ/","example":"There’s a package here for a Miami Lakes address. 这里有一个寄往迈阿密湖的包裹。"},{"example":"Paul tore open the packet as soon as it arrived. 保罗一收到包裹就拆开了。","phonetic_uk":"/'pækɪt/","translation":"n. 小包(裹)，小捆","phonetic_us":"/'pækɪt/","word":"packet"},{"phonetic_us":"/pæd/","translation":"n. 垫；本子；v. 填塞","word":"pad","phonetic_uk":"/pæd/","example":"Use an abrasive pad for stubborn stains. 用百洁布擦洗顽固污渍。"},{"example":"The full address is given on page 15. 详细地址见第15页。","phonetic_uk":"/peɪdʒ/","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 页","word":"page"},{"phonetic_uk":"/peɪn/","example":"The pain is getting worse. 疼得越来越厉害了。","phonetic_us":"/pen/","translation":"n. 痛，疼痛；辛苦","word":"pain"},{"phonetic_us":"/'penfl/","translation":"adj. 痛苦的，疼痛的，令人不快的","word":"painful","phonetic_uk":"/'peinfl/","example":"stiff painful joints 僵硬疼痛的关节"},{"translation":"v. 画；油漆；v. 绘画","phonetic_us":"","word":"paint","example":"The ceiling needs painting. 天花板需要粉刷了。","phonetic_uk":"/peɪnt/"},{"word":"painter","phonetic_us":"/'pentɚ/","translation":"n. 漆工，画家，绘画者","example":"Gerry’s ambition was to become a portrait painter. 格里的志向是成为一名肖像画家。","phonetic_uk":"/'peɪntə/"},{"translation":"n. 油画；绘画；着色","phonetic_us":"/'pentɪŋ/","word":"painting","example":"a collection of valuable paintings 一批珍贵的画作","phonetic_uk":"/'peɪntɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/peə/","example":"earrings, £5 a pair 耳环，5英镑一副","translation":"n. 一对；v. 成对，配对","phonetic_us":"/pɛr/","word":"pair"},{"example":"Buckingham Palace 白金汉宫","phonetic_uk":"/'pælɪs/","word":"palace","phonetic_us":"/'pælis/","translation":"n. 宫，宫殿"},{"example":"Why do your face look like so pale?What wrong with you? 为什么你的脸色看起来是如此苍白？发生什么事了吗？","phonetic_uk":"","word":"pale","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 苍白的；浅的"},{"example":"He held the pebble in the palm of his hand . 他把那颗卵石握在手心里。","phonetic_uk":"/pɑːm/","word":"palm","phonetic_us":"/pɑm/","translation":"n. 手掌，手心；掌状物"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pæn/","example":"a frying pan 炒锅","translation":"n. 平底锅，盘子","phonetic_us":"/pæn/","word":"pan"},{"word":"panel","translation":"n. 专门小组；面，板","phonetic_us":"/'pænl/","phonetic_uk":"/'pæn(ə)l/","example":"He assembled a panel of scholars to advise him. 他集结了一个学者小组为他出谋划策。"},{"example":"Her face distorted in panic. 她的脸因恐慌而变相了。","phonetic_uk":"/'pænɪk/","word":"panic","phonetic_us":"/'pænɪk/","translation":"adj. 恐慌的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pænts/","example":"She was wearing dark blue pants and a white sweater. 她穿着深蓝色长裤和白色毛衣。","word":"pants","phonetic_us":"/pænts/","translation":"n.  长裤， 便裤； 内裤"},{"word":"paper","phonetic_us":"/'pepɚ/","translation":"n. 纸；官方文件；文章","phonetic_uk":"/'peɪpə/","example":"I’ll get you a piece of paper so you can write the number down. 我给你找张纸，你好把号码写下来。"},{"word":"parade","phonetic_us":"/pə'red/","translation":"n. 游行；检阅；v. 游行","example":"a victory parade 胜利游行","phonetic_uk":"/pə'reɪd/"},{"word":"paradox","translation":"n. 悖论，自相矛盾","phonetic_us":"/'pærədɑks/","example":"It’s a paradox that in such a rich country there can be so much poverty. 在如此富有的国家却有这么多的贫穷现象，真是矛盾。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈpærədɒks/"},{"example":"the opening paragraphs of the novel 小说开篇的几个段落","phonetic_uk":"/'pærəgrɑːf/","word":"paragraph","translation":"n. (文章的)段，节","phonetic_us":"/'pærəɡræf/"},{"word":"parallel","translation":"adj. 平行的；相同的","phonetic_us":"/'pærəlɛl/","phonetic_uk":"/'pærəlel/","example":"Lines AB and CD are parallel. AB 线与CD线平行。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːs(ə)l/","example":"The parcel was delivered last week. 那个邮包上周送到了。","word":"parcel","translation":"n. 包裹，小包，邮包","phonetic_us":"/'pɑrsl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'pɑrdn/","translation":"n. 原谅；赦免；v. 原谅","word":"pardon","example":"Walter begged her pardon for all the pain he had caused her. 沃尔特请求她原谅自己给她造成那么多痛苦。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈpɑːdn/"},{"example":"Children under 14 should be accompanied by a parent. 14 岁以下儿童须由一位家长陪同。","phonetic_uk":"/'peər(ə)nt/","word":"parent","phonetic_us":"/'pɛrənt/","translation":"n. 父亲，母亲，双亲"},{"example":"Let’s go for a walk in the park. 我们去公园散步吧。","phonetic_uk":"/pɑːk/","translation":"n. 公园；停车场","phonetic_us":"/pɑrk/","word":"park"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːləm(ə)nt/","example":"They demanded a free parliament and press. 他们要求议会自由和新闻自由。","word":"parliament","phonetic_us":"/'pɑrləmənt/","translation":"n. 议会，国会"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pɑːt/","example":"For part of the day, you will be outside doing practical work. 你们每天将有一部分时间在户外实际操作。","phonetic_us":"/pɑrt/","translation":"n. 一部分；零件；本份","word":"part"},{"phonetic_us":"/'pɑrʃəl/","translation":"adj. 部分的；不公平的","word":"partial","example":"The exhibition was only a partial success. 那次展会只获得部分成功。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːʃ(ə)l/"},{"translation":"v. 参与，参加","phonetic_us":"/pɑr'tɪsə'pet/","word":"participate","phonetic_uk":"/pɑ:'tɪsɪpeɪt/","example":"Some members refused to participate. 有些会员拒绝参加。"},{"word":"particle","translation":"n. 微粒","phonetic_us":"/'pɑrtɪkl/","example":"dust particles 尘埃","phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːtɪk(ə)l/"},{"word":"particular","translation":"adj. 特别的，挑剔的","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'tɪkjəlɚ/","example":"In this particular case, no one else was involved. 这件事没有其他人牵涉其中。","phonetic_uk":"/pəˈtɪkjələ(r)/"},{"example":"Steve was in a particularly bad mood when he got back. 史蒂夫回来时情绪特别不好。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'tɪkjʊləlɪ/","word":"particularly","translation":"adv. 特别，尤其，格外","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'tɪkjəlɚli/"},{"word":"partly","translation":"adv. 部分地，不完全地","phonetic_us":"/'pɑrtli/","example":"The poor weather was partly responsible for the crash. 天气不好是造成坠机事故的部分原因。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːtlɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 伙伴；搭挡；配偶","phonetic_us":"/'pɑrtnɚ/","word":"partner","example":"Discuss your worries with your partner. 和伴侣谈谈你的忧虑。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːtnə/"},{"translation":"n. 党，党派；聚会","phonetic_us":"/'pɑrti/","word":"party","example":"We’re having a small party this evening to celebrate our wedding anniversary. 我们今晚有个小聚会，庆祝我们的结婚纪念日。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːtɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/pæs/","translation":"v. 经过；通过；度过","word":"pass","example":"The crowd parted to let the truck pass. 人群分开让卡车通过。","phonetic_uk":"/pɑːs/"},{"example":"My office is just along the passage. 我的办公室就在过道旁边。","phonetic_uk":"/'pæsɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 通过；通路，通道","phonetic_us":"/'pæsɪdʒ/","word":"passage"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pæsɪndʒə/","example":"Neither the driver nor the passengers were hurt. 司机和乘客均未受伤。","translation":"n. 乘客，旅客，过路人","phonetic_us":"/'pæsɪndʒɚ/","word":"passenger"},{"example":"The issue arouses strong passions . 那件事激起了人们强烈的情绪。","phonetic_uk":"/'pæʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 热情，激情","phonetic_us":"/'pæʃən/","word":"passion"},{"translation":"adj. 热情的","phonetic_us":"/'pæʃənət/","word":"passionate","phonetic_uk":"/ˈpæʃənət/","example":"He had a brief but passionate love affair with an older woman. 他和一个比他年长的女子有过一段短暂而炽热的情史。"},{"word":"passive","phonetic_us":"/'pæsɪv/","translation":"adj. 被动的","phonetic_uk":"/ˈpæsɪv/","example":"Kathy seems to take a very passive role in the relationship. 凯茜在这一关系中似乎扮演着十分被动的角色。"},{"word":"passively","translation":"adv. 消极地","phonetic_us":"","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'pæsivli/"},{"word":"passport","phonetic_us":"/'pæspɔrt/","translation":"n. 护照","example":"I have an Irish passport. 我持爱尔兰护照。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɑːspɔːt/"},{"word":"past","phonetic_us":"/pæst/","translation":"adj. 过去的；n. 过去","phonetic_uk":"/pɑːst/","example":"Judging by her past performance, Jane should do very well. 从以往的表现来看，简应该会干得很好。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/peɪst/","example":"Mix the powder with enough water to make a smooth paste. 把粉末和足够的水混合调成均匀的糊状。","translation":"n. 糊，酱；浆湖","phonetic_us":"/pest/","word":"paste"},{"translation":"n&vt&n. 轻拍","phonetic_us":"/pæt/","word":"pat","example":"He patted the dog affectionately. 他亲热地轻轻拍了拍那只狗。","phonetic_uk":"/pæt/"},{"word":"patch","phonetic_us":"/pætʃ/","translation":"n. 补钉；碎片；v. 补缀","example":"a jacket with leather patches at the elbows 肘部有皮革补丁的短上衣","phonetic_uk":"/pætʃ/"},{"example":"I walked nervously up the garden path towards the front door. 我提心吊胆地沿着花园的小道向前门走去。","phonetic_uk":"/pɑːθ/","translation":"n. 路，小道；道路","phonetic_us":"/pæθ/","word":"path"},{"phonetic_us":"/'peʃns/","translation":"n. 忍耐，容忍，耐心","word":"patience","example":"He doesn't have the patience to wait. 他没有耐心等。","phonetic_uk":"/'peɪʃ(ə)ns/"},{"example":"You’ll just have to be patient and wait till I’m off the phone. 你只能耐心点，等我打完电话。","phonetic_uk":"/'peɪʃ(ə)nt/","phonetic_us":"/'peʃnt/","translation":"adj. 忍耐的；n. 病人","word":"patient"},{"phonetic_us":"/'peʃəntli/","translation":"adv. 耐心地","word":"patiently","phonetic_uk":"/'peɪʃntlɪ/","example":"The teacher told him to weigh this matter patiently. 老师让他耐心考虑这事。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pætn/","example":"Weather patterns have changed in recent years. 气候模式近年已经发生了变化。","word":"pattern","phonetic_us":"/'pætɚn/","translation":"n. 模式"},{"word":"pause","translation":"n&vi. 中止，暂停","phonetic_us":"/pɔz/","phonetic_uk":"/pɔːz/","example":"There was a pause while Alice changed the tape. 艾丽斯换磁带的时候出现了短暂的停顿。"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"This month alone, my wife and I spent $600 on one Labrador retriever with a bladder infection who needed some kidney tests and $300 on the other one for an injured paw. 仅这个月，我和我妻子就为一患膀胱感染而需要肾测试的拉布拉多犬花费了600美元，同时为另外一只爪子受伤的拉布拉多犬支付了300美元。","translation":"n. 脚爪，爪子","phonetic_us":"","word":"paw"},{"phonetic_uk":"/peɪ/","example":"How would you like to pay? 你想怎么付款？","phonetic_us":"/pe/","translation":"v. 支付；付给；给予","word":"pay"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'peɪm(ə)nt/","example":"You can make a payment in any bank. 你可以在任何一家银行付款。","word":"payment","phonetic_us":"/'pemənt/","translation":"n. 支付，支付的款项"},{"example":"roast chicken with peas and carrots 烤鸡配豌豆胡萝卜","phonetic_uk":"/piː/","word":"pea","translation":"n. 豌豆；豌豆属植物","phonetic_us":"/pi/"},{"phonetic_us":"/pis/","translation":"n. 和平；和睦；平静","word":"peace","example":"The country is at peace with its neighbours for the first time in years. 这是多年来该国与其邻国第一次和平共处。","phonetic_uk":"/piːs/"},{"word":"peaceful","phonetic_us":"/'pisfəl/","translation":"adj. 平静的，和平的","example":"We had a peaceful afternoon without the children. 孩子们不在，我们度过了一个宁静的下午。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈpi:sfl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/pitʃ/","translation":"n. 桃子，桃树","word":"peach","phonetic_uk":"/piːtʃ/","example":"Those boys rifled the peach trees in our garden. 那些男孩子把我们花园里的桃树抢摘光了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/pik/","translation":"n. 山顶，巅；adj. 最高的","word":"peak","phonetic_uk":"/piːk/","example":"snow-capped mountain peaks 白雪覆盖的山顶"},{"phonetic_uk":"/peə/","example":"I took this apple for a pear until I tasted it. 我误将这个苹果当作梨子，直到我尝了才知道。","phonetic_us":"/pɛr/","translation":"n. 梨子，梨树","word":"pear"},{"example":"Most villagers are peasant farmers. 大多数村民是农民。","phonetic_uk":"/'pez(ə)nt/","word":"peasant","phonetic_us":"/'pɛznt/","translation":"n. 农民"},{"phonetic_us":"/pɪ'kjulɪɚ/","translation":"adj. 特有的；特别的","word":"peculiar","phonetic_uk":"/pɪ'kjuːlɪə/","example":"He’s been a little peculiar lately. 最近他有点怪异。"},{"example":"American children did less well in math than their peers in Japan. 美国儿童的数学成绩不如日本的同龄儿童。","phonetic_uk":"/pɪə/","word":"peer","phonetic_us":"/pɪr/","translation":"n. 同龄人"},{"translation":"n. 钢笔，自来水笔","phonetic_us":"/pɛn/","word":"pen","example":"a ballpoint pen 圆珠笔","phonetic_uk":"/pen/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pen(ə)ltɪ/","example":"No littering. Penalty $500. 禁止乱扔垃圾。 违者罚款500美元。","word":"penalty","phonetic_us":"/'pɛnəlti/","translation":"n. 惩罚"},{"translation":"n. 铅笔","phonetic_us":"/'pɛnsl/","word":"pencil","phonetic_uk":"/'pens(ə)l; -sɪl/","example":"a sharp pencil 尖尖的铅笔"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"bullets that penetrate thick armour plating 穿过厚装甲的子弹","word":"penetrate","translation":"vt. 穿过；vi. 穿入","phonetic_us":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/'penɪ/","example":"Unleaded petrol rose more than a penny a gallon. 无铅汽油每加仑涨了一个多便士。","word":"penny","translation":"n. (英)便士；(美)分","phonetic_us":"/'pɛni/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'penʃ(ə)n/","example":"At what age can you start drawing your pension ? 从多少岁可以开始领取养老金？","translation":"n. 养老金","phonetic_us":"/'pɛnʃən/","word":"pension"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'piːp(ə)l/","example":"How many people were at the meeting? 有多少人到会？","word":"people","translation":"n. 人民，民族；人","phonetic_us":"/'pipl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pepə/","example":"salt and pepper 盐和胡椒粉","word":"pepper","translation":"n. 胡椒，胡椒粉；vt.  在…上撒； 使布满","phonetic_us":"/'pɛpɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pɜː/","example":"The park attracts four million visitors per year. 那座公园每年吸引400万游客。","word":"per","phonetic_us":"/pɚ/","translation":"prep. 每"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pə'si:v/","example":"That morning, he perceived a change in Franca’s mood. 那天早上，他注意到弗兰卡情绪的变化。","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'siv/","translation":"v. 察觉","word":"perceive"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pə'sent/","example":"At the end of the day, add up the percent DVs. 在一天结束后，把所有营养素的百分比加起来。","word":"percent","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'sɛnt/","translation":"n. 百分之…"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pə'sentɪdʒ/","example":"Interest rates fell by six percentage points (= 6% ) . 利息下降了6个百分点。","translation":"n. 百分比，百分率","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'sɛntɪdʒ/","word":"percentage"},{"translation":"n. 感知","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'sɛpʃən/","word":"perception","example":"And when they do, what do you think their perception will be? 当他们这样做时，你觉得他们的知觉是怎样的？","phonetic_uk":"/pəˈsepʃn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈpəːfɪkt; (for v.) pəˈfekt/","example":"His English was perfect. 他的英语很地道。","phonetic_us":"/ˈpɝfɪkt; (for v.) pɝˈfɛkt/","translation":"adj. 完美的；完全的","word":"perfect"},{"word":"perform","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'fɔrm/","translation":"v. 履行，执行；演出","example":"Chenier and the band are performing at the Silver Palace tomorrow. 车尼尔和乐队明天将在银宫演出。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'fɔːm/"},{"example":"This evening’s performance will begin at 8.00 pm. 今晚的演出8点开始。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'fɔ:məns/","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'fɔrməns/","translation":"n. 演出，履行，表现","word":"performance"},{"word":"perhaps","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'hæps/","translation":"adv. 也许，可能，多半","phonetic_uk":"/pə'hæps/","example":"Perhaps she’s next door. 她也许在隔壁。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɪərɪəd/","example":"Tomorrow’s weather will be dry with sunny periods. 明天天气干燥，间或晴朗。","word":"period","translation":"n. 时期；学时；句号","phonetic_us":"/'pɪrɪəd/"},{"translation":"adj. 永久的","phonetic_us":"/'pɝmənənt/","word":"permanent","example":"He gave up a permanent job in order to freelance. 他放弃了固定工作，为的是当一名自由职业者。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɜːm(ə)nənt/"},{"translation":"n. 允许，许可，同意","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'mɪʃən/","word":"permission","phonetic_uk":"/pə'mɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"He asked permission to leave the room. 他请求离开房间的许可。"},{"example":"Smoking is only permitted in the public lounge. 只允许在公共休息室里抽烟。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'mɪt/","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'mɪt/","translation":"v. 允许；n. 执照","word":"permit"},{"word":"persist","translation":"v. 坚持，固执；持续","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'sɪst/","example":"‘I don’t think it’s right,’ John persisted. “我认为那不对。”约翰坚持说道。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'sɪst/"},{"translation":"n. 坚持不懈","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'sɪstəns/","word":"persistence","example":"Her persistence paid off when she was offered the job of manager. 她得到了经理的职位，不懈坚持终于有了回报。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'sɪstəns/"},{"translation":"adj. 持续的，坚持的","phonetic_us":"/pə'zɪstənt/","word":"persistent","example":"persistent rumours 持续流传的谣言","phonetic_uk":"/pəˈsɪstənt/"},{"word":"person","translation":"n. 人；人身；本人","phonetic_us":"/'pɝsn/","example":"He was a very nice person, always pleasant and friendly. 他是个很好的人，始终彬彬有礼。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɜːs(ə)n/"},{"word":"personal","translation":"adj. 个人的；本人的","phonetic_us":"/'pɝsənl/","phonetic_uk":"/'pɜːs(ə)n(ə)l/","example":"My personal view is that we shouldn’t offer him the job. 我个人认为我们不该给他这份工作。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌpɜ:səˈnæləti/","example":"Despite their different personalities, they became the best of friends. 尽管个性不同，他们还是成了最好的朋友。","translation":"n. 个性，性格","phonetic_us":"/,pɝsə'næləti/","word":"personality"},{"word":"personnel","phonetic_us":"/,pɝsə'nɛl/","translation":"n. 全体人员，全体职员","example":"All personnel are to receive security badges. 所有人员都将拿到安保徽章。","phonetic_uk":"/pɜːsə'nel/"},{"example":"the artist’s use of perspective 那位画家对透视法的运用","phonetic_uk":"/pə'spektiv/","word":"perspective","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'spɛktɪv/","translation":"n. 视角，观点；远景"},{"word":"persuade","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'swed/","translation":"v. 说服","example":"He was fairly easily persuaded . 他很轻易就被说服了。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'sweɪd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/pɚ'sweʒn/","translation":"n. 劝说","word":"persuasion","phonetic_uk":"/pə'sweɪʒn/","example":"After a little gentle persuasion , Debbie agreed to let us in. 好言劝说了几句后，黛比就同意让我们进去了。"},{"example":"Trevor can be very persuasive. 特雷弗有时很会说服人。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'sweɪsɪv/","translation":"adj.  劝诱的； 有说服力的","phonetic_us":"/pɚ'swesɪv/","word":"persuasive"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,pesɪ'mɪstɪk/","example":"a pessimistic view of life 对人生的悲观看法","word":"pessimistic","phonetic_us":"/,pɛsɪ'mɪstɪk/","translation":"adj. 悲观的；厌世的"},{"word":"pet","translation":"n. 爱畜；宠儿a宠爱的","phonetic_us":"/pɛt/","phonetic_uk":"/pet/","example":"They have two pets – a cat and a dog. 他们有两只宠物，一只猫和一只狗。"},{"example":"unleaded petrol 无铅汽油","phonetic_uk":"/'petr(ə)l/","word":"petrol","translation":"n. (英)汽油","phonetic_us":"/'pɛtrəl/"},{"example":"petroleum-based products 石油产品","phonetic_uk":"/pə'trəʊlɪəm/","word":"petroleum","translation":"n. 石油","phonetic_us":"/pə'trolɪəm/"},{"example":"a new drug that is in the experimental phase 处于试验阶段的一种新药","phonetic_uk":"/feɪz/","translation":"n. 阶段；方面；相位","phonetic_us":"/fez/","word":"phase"},{"word":"phenomenon","phonetic_us":"/fə'nɑmɪnən/","translation":"n. 现象","phonetic_uk":"/fəˈnɒmɪnən/","example":"Homelessness is not a new phenomenon . 无家可归已不是什么新现象。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɪ'lɒsəfə/","example":"Plato, Aristotle, and other Greek philosophers 柏拉图、亚里士多德和其他希腊哲学家","phonetic_us":"/fə'lɑsəfɚ/","translation":"n. 哲学家","word":"philosopher"},{"phonetic_uk":"/fɪ'lɒsəfɪ/","example":"Emma studies philosophy at university. 埃玛在大学攻读哲学。","phonetic_us":"/fə'lɑsəfi/","translation":"n. 哲学；哲理；人生观","word":"philosophy"},{"example":"Much of his work is done by phone . 他的工作大部分是通过电话进行的。","phonetic_uk":"/fəʊn/","translation":"n. 电话，电话机；耳机","phonetic_us":"/fon/","word":"phone"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'fəʊtəʊ/","example":"Can you take a photo of me and Rachel? 你能给我和雷切尔拍张照吗？","word":"photo","phonetic_us":"/'foto/","translation":"n. 照片，相片"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fotəɡræf/","translation":"n. 照片，相片","word":"photograph","phonetic_uk":"/'fəʊtəgrɑːf/","example":"a colour photograph 彩色照片"},{"phonetic_uk":"/freɪz/","example":"Who first used the phrase ‘survival of the fittest’? “适者生存”这一说法最早是谁说的？","translation":"n. 短语；习惯用语","phonetic_us":"/frez/","word":"phrase"},{"phonetic_us":"/'fɪzɪkl/","translation":"adj. 身体上的","word":"physical","phonetic_uk":"/ˈfɪzɪkl/","example":"She was in constant physical pain. 她一直感到身上疼痛。"},{"example":"...your family physician. …你的家庭医生。","phonetic_uk":"/fɪ'zɪʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 医生，内科医生","phonetic_us":"/fɪ'zɪʃən/","word":"physician"},{"example":"...a nuclear physicist. …一位核物理学家。","phonetic_uk":"/'fɪzɪsɪst/","phonetic_us":"/'fɪzɪsɪst/","translation":"n. 物理学家","word":"physicist"},{"word":"physics","translation":"n. 物理，物理学","phonetic_us":"/'fɪzɪks/","phonetic_uk":"/'fiziks/","example":"...the laws of physics. …物理学定律。"},{"translation":"n. 钢琴","phonetic_us":"/pɪ'æno/","word":"piano","phonetic_uk":"/pɪ'ænəʊ/","example":"Jean accompanied her on the piano . 琼为她钢琴伴奏。"},{"word":"pick","translation":"n. 镐，鹤嘴锄","phonetic_us":"/pɪk/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/pɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈpɪki/","example":"He’s a very picky eater . 他很挑食。","phonetic_us":"/'pɪki/","translation":"adj. 挑剔的","word":"picky"},{"word":"picnic","translation":"n. 郊游，野餐；v. 野餐","phonetic_us":"/'pɪknɪk/","example":"We decided to have a picnic down by the lake. 我们决定在湖边野餐。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɪknɪk/"},{"example":"The room had several pictures on the walls. 那个房间墙上有几幅画。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɪktʃə/","translation":"n. 画，图片；v. 画","phonetic_us":"/'pɪktʃɚ/","word":"picture"},{"phonetic_uk":"/paɪ/","example":"I had a steak and kidney pie with chips. 我吃了一份牛肉腰子馅饼加薯条。","word":"pie","phonetic_us":"/paɪ/","translation":"n. (西点)馅饼"},{"word":"piece","phonetic_us":"/pis/","translation":"n. 碎片，块；v. 拼合","example":"Cut off a piece of wood 5 cm in length. 截下一段五厘米长的木头。","phonetic_uk":"/piːs/"},{"example":"Steam the corn until it can easily be pierced with a fork. 把玉米蒸到用叉子可以轻易扎透。","phonetic_uk":"/pɪəs/","translation":"v. 剌穿；v. 穿入","phonetic_us":"/pɪrs/","word":"pierce"},{"word":"pig","phonetic_us":"/pɪɡ/","translation":"n. 猪，小猪，野猪","phonetic_uk":"/pɪg/","example":"He kept pigs and poultry. 他养过猪和家禽。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɪdʒɪn; 'pɪdʒ(ə)n/","example":"Many journalists here choose to pigeon all but the most innocuous of stories. 除了平淡乏味的报道，这儿的新闻记者将一切通过鸽子传递出去。","translation":"n. 鸽子","phonetic_us":"/'pɪdʒɪn/","word":"pigeon"},{"example":"He balanced the plate on the top of a pile of books. 他把盘子在一摞书上放稳。","phonetic_uk":"/paɪl/","word":"pile","phonetic_us":"/paɪl/","translation":"n. 堆；v. 堆叠，累积"},{"word":"pill","phonetic_us":"/pɪl/","translation":"n. 药丸，丸剂","example":"He has to take pills to control his blood pressure. 他必须服药控制血压。","phonetic_uk":"/pɪl/"},{"example":"Mr Fitzwilliam had been seen as a pillar of the community. 菲茨威廉先生已被视为社区的骨干。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɪlə/","translation":"n. 柱，柱子；栋梁","phonetic_us":"/'pɪlɚ/","word":"pillar"},{"example":"I’ll be asleep as soon as my head hits the pillow. 我头一碰到枕头就会睡着。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɪləʊ/","translation":"n. 枕头","phonetic_us":"/'pɪlo/","word":"pillow"},{"word":"pilot","translation":"n. 领航员；飞行员","phonetic_us":"/'paɪlət/","phonetic_uk":"/'paɪlət/","example":"an airline pilot 航空公司飞行员"},{"word":"pin","translation":"n. 针，饰针；n. 别住","phonetic_us":"/pɪn/","phonetic_uk":"/pɪn/","example":"...necklaces, bracelets, and pins. …项链、手镯和胸针。"},{"phonetic_us":"/pɪntʃ/","translation":"v. 捏，拧，掐掉","word":"pinch","phonetic_uk":"/pɪn(t)ʃ/","example":"We have to stop her pinching her baby brother. 我们不能让她再掐她小弟弟了。"},{"example":"an ancient pine forest 一片古老的松树林","phonetic_uk":"/paɪn/","word":"pine","translation":"n. 松树，松木","phonetic_us":"/paɪn/"},{"word":"pink","phonetic_us":"/pɪŋk/","translation":"n. 粉红色；adj. 粉红色的","example":"Her room was decorated in bright pinks and purples. 她的房间装饰成明亮的粉红色和紫色。","phonetic_uk":"/pɪŋk/"},{"word":"pint","translation":"n. 品脱","phonetic_us":"/paɪnt/","example":"He’s gone down the pub for a quick pint. 他去小酒馆匆匆喝上一品脱啤酒。","phonetic_uk":"/paɪnt/"},{"translation":"v. 开拓，开发","phonetic_us":"/,paɪə'nɪr/","word":"pioneer","example":"The new cancer treatment was pioneered in the early eighties by Dr Sylvia Bannerjee. 这种新的癌症治疗方法是由西尔维娅·班纳基医生在80年代初期开创的。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌpaɪə'nɪə(r)/"},{"example":"a water pipe 水管","phonetic_uk":"/paɪp/","phonetic_us":"/paɪp/","translation":"n. 管子，导管；烟斗","word":"pipe"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pɪt/","example":"Dad first went down the pit (= worked in a coal mine ) when he was 15 years old. 爸爸第一次下煤矿井时才15岁。","phonetic_us":"/pɪt/","translation":"n. 坑，地坑；煤矿","word":"pit"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pɪtʃ/","example":"The night was as black as pitch (= very dark ) . 夜晚一片漆黑。","word":"pitch","phonetic_us":"/pɪtʃ/","translation":"n. 沥青"},{"translation":"n. 怜悯；遗憾；v. 同情","phonetic_us":"/'pɪti/","word":"pity","phonetic_uk":"/'pɪtɪ/","example":"It’s a great pity Joyce wasn’t invited. 乔伊斯没有受到邀请太遗憾了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/ples/","translation":"n. 地方，地点；住所","word":"place","example":"Make sure you keep the key in a safe place. 一定要把钥匙放在安全的地方。","phonetic_uk":"/pleɪs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pleɪg/","example":"Financial problems continued to plague the company. 资金问题持续困扰着该公司。","translation":"v. 使困扰","phonetic_us":"/pleɡ/","word":"plague"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pleɪn/","example":"The grassy plain gave way to an extensive swamp. 青草覆盖的平原被广阔的沼泽地所取代。","translation":"n. 平原；adj. 清楚的","phonetic_us":"/plen/","word":"plain"},{"example":"His plan is to get a degree in economics and then work abroad for a year. 他计划先取得经济学学位，然后去国外工作一年。","phonetic_uk":"/plæn/","translation":"n&vt. 计划，打算","phonetic_us":"/plæn/","word":"plan"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pleɪn/","example":"It is a big airline with a large fleet of planes. 这是一家大航空公司，拥有庞大的机群。","phonetic_us":"/plen/","translation":"n. 平面；飞机","word":"plane"},{"word":"planet","translation":"n. 行星","phonetic_us":"/'plænɪt/","phonetic_uk":"/'plænit/","example":"The picture shows six of the nine planets in the solar system. 这张图片展示太阳系9个行星中的6个行星。"},{"word":"plant","phonetic_us":"/plænt/","translation":"n. 工厂","phonetic_uk":"/plɑːnt/","example":"a huge chemical plant 一座大型化工厂"},{"translation":"n. 种植园；栽植","phonetic_us":"/plæn'teʃən/","word":"plantation","phonetic_uk":"/plæn'teɪʃ(ə)n; plɑːn-/","example":"a rubber plantation 橡胶园"},{"word":"plastic","phonetic_us":"/'plæstɪk/","translation":"adj. 塑料的","example":"a plastic spoon 塑料汤匙","phonetic_uk":"/'plæstɪk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pleɪt/","example":"Anita pushed her plate away; she had eaten virtually nothing. 安妮塔把盘子推开；她其实什么都没吃。","word":"plate","phonetic_us":"/pleɪt/","translation":"n. 板，片，盘；v. 电镀"},{"word":"platform","translation":"n. 平台；站台；讲台","phonetic_us":"/'plæt'fɔrm/","phonetic_uk":"/'plætfɔːm/","example":"The Edinburgh train will depart from platform six. 开往爱丁堡的火车将从六号站台发车。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pleɪ/","example":"Kids were playing and chasing each other. 孩子们在互相追逐嬉闹。","word":"play","phonetic_us":"/ple/","translation":"v. 玩，游戏；演奏"},{"word":"player","translation":"n. 游戏的人；比赛者","phonetic_us":"/'pleɚ/","example":"a guitar player 一名吉他手","phonetic_uk":"/'pleɪə/"},{"example":"children shouting and running in the playground 在操场上叫嚷奔跑的孩子们","phonetic_uk":"/'pleɪgraʊnd/","word":"playground","translation":"n. 操场，运动场","phonetic_us":"/'ple'graʊnd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'plɛznt/","translation":"adj. 令人愉快的，舒适的","word":"pleasant","phonetic_uk":"/'plez(ə)nt/","example":"It had been a pleasant evening. 那是个愉快的夜晚。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pliːz/","example":"a business that wants to please its customers 希望让顾客满意的一家公司","word":"please","phonetic_us":"/pliz/","translation":"v. 使高兴，请vi满意"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pleʒə/","example":"the simple pleasures of life 生活中的简单乐趣","translation":"n. 愉快，快乐；乐事","phonetic_us":"/ˈplɛʒɚ/","word":"pleasure"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pledʒ/","example":"The meeting ended with a pledge to step up cooperation between the six states of the region. 会议以加快该地区6个州之间合作的承诺结束。","word":"pledge","translation":"n. 保证，誓言","phonetic_us":"/plɛdʒ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'plentɪfʊl; -f(ə)l/","example":"a plentiful supply of food 食物的大量供应","translation":"adj. 丰富的，富裕的","phonetic_us":"/'plɛntɪfəl/","word":"plentiful"},{"example":"a land of plenty 一片富饶的土地","phonetic_uk":"/'plentɪ/","word":"plenty","translation":"n. 丰富，充足，大量","phonetic_us":"/'plɛnti/"},{"phonetic_us":"/plɑt/","translation":"n. 小块土地；v. 密谋","word":"plot","phonetic_uk":"/plɒt/","example":"a two-acre plot of land 一块两英亩的土地"},{"word":"plough","translation":"n. 犁；vt&vi. 犁，耕","phonetic_us":"/plaʊ/","phonetic_uk":"/plaʊ/","example":"There are new tractors and new ploughs in the machinery lot. 机器设备场里有新拖拉机和新耕犁。"},{"translation":"n. 塞子；插头；v. 塞","phonetic_us":"/plʌɡ/","word":"plug","phonetic_uk":"/plʌg/","example":"the bath plug 浴缸塞子"},{"word":"plunge","phonetic_us":"/plʌndʒ/","translation":"v. 使投入；使陷入","example":"The government's political and economic reforms threaten to plunge the country into chaos. 该政府的政治和经济改革有可能使这个国家陷入混乱之中。","phonetic_uk":"/plʌn(d)ʒ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'plʊər(ə)l/","example":"\"Data\" is the Latin plural form of \"datum.\" “”是“”的拉丁语复数形式。","translation":"adj. 复数的；n. 复数","phonetic_us":"/'plʊrəl/","word":"plural"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pluərəlɪzəm/","example":"a nation characterized by cultural pluralism 以多元文化为特色的国家","word":"pluralism","translation":"n.  多重性； 兼职， 兼任","phonetic_us":"/'plʊər(ə)lɪz(ə)m/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/plʌs/","example":"Three plus six equals nine (3+6=9). 3 加6等于9。","translation":"prep. 加，加上；adj. 正的","phonetic_us":"/plʌs/","word":"plus"},{"word":"pocket","phonetic_us":"/'pɑkɪt/","translation":"n. 衣袋；n. 袖珍的","example":"Luke came in with his hands in his pockets. 卢克走了进来，双手插在口袋里。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒkɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pəʊɪm/","example":"...a book of love poems. …一本爱情诗集。","word":"poem","translation":"n. 诗，韵文，诗体文","phonetic_us":"/'poəm/"},{"example":"He was a painter and poet. 他是一位画家兼诗人。","phonetic_uk":"/'pəʊɪt/","phonetic_us":"/'poət/","translation":"n. 诗人","word":"poet"},{"word":"poetry","phonetic_us":"/'poətri/","translation":"n. 诗，诗歌，诗作","example":"He reads a lot of poetry. 他大量阅读诗歌。","phonetic_uk":"/'pəʊɪtrɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pɒɪnt/","example":"That’s a very interesting point. 那个观点很有趣。","word":"point","phonetic_us":"/pɔɪnt/","translation":"n. 点；要点；细目；分"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɒɪntlɪs/","example":"Life just seemed pointless to me. 生活对我来说简直没什么意义。","phonetic_us":"/'pɔɪntləs/","translation":"adj. 无意义的","word":"pointless"},{"translation":"v. 使中毒","phonetic_us":"/'pɔɪzn/","word":"poison","example":"The rumours that she had poisoned him could never be proved. 说她毒死了他的谣言永远不可能得到证实。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɔɪzn/"},{"translation":"adj. 有毒的，有害的","phonetic_us":"/'pɔɪzənəs/","word":"poisonous","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒɪzənəs/","example":"Some mushrooms are extremely poisonous. 一些蘑菇有剧毒。"},{"word":"pole","translation":"n. 杆，柱","phonetic_us":"/pol/","example":"a telephone pole 电话线杆","phonetic_uk":"/pəʊl/"},{"example":"Police surrounded the courthouse. 警察围在法院大楼四周。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'liːs/","phonetic_us":"/pə'lis/","translation":"n. 警察；警察当局","word":"police"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pə'liːsmən/","example":"He tried to corrupt the policeman with money. 他设法用金钱向警察行贿。","phonetic_us":"/pə'lismən/","translation":"n. 警察","word":"policeman"},{"phonetic_us":"/'pɑləsi/","translation":"n. 政策，方针","word":"policy","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒləsɪ/","example":"...plans that include changes in foreign policy and economic reforms. …包括外交政策调整和经济改革的计划。"},{"example":"They just need to polish their technique. 他们只需要改进一下自己的技艺。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒlɪʃ/","translation":"v. 磨光；使优美","phonetic_us":"/'pɑlɪʃ/","word":"polish"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pə'laɪt/","example":"She’s always very polite. 她总是很有礼貌。","phonetic_us":"/pə'laɪt/","translation":"adj. 有礼貌的；有教养的","word":"polite"},{"phonetic_us":"/pə'lɪtɪkl/","translation":"adj. 政治的，政治上的","word":"political","phonetic_uk":"/pə'lɪtɪk(ə)l/","example":"All other political parties there have been completely banned. 那里的其他所有政党都已经完全被取缔了。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pɒlɪ'tɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"politicians who are trying to get the minority vote 努力争取少数族群选票的政治家","word":"politician","phonetic_us":"/,pɑlə'tɪʃən/","translation":"n. 政治家；政客"},{"word":"politics","phonetic_us":"/'pɑlətɪks/","translation":"n. 政治，政治学；政纲","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒlɪtɪks/","example":"a good understanding of politics in China 对中国政治很好的了解"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pəʊl/","example":"A recent poll found that 80% of Californians support the governor. 最近的一项民意调查发现80%的加利福尼亚人支持州长。","phonetic_us":"/pol/","translation":"n. 民意调查","word":"poll"},{"word":"pollute","translation":"v. 弄脏，污染，沾污","phonetic_us":"/pə'lut/","example":"beaches polluted by raw sewage 受未经处理的污水污染的海滩","phonetic_uk":"/pə'luːt/"},{"word":"pollution","phonetic_us":"/pə'luʃən/","translation":"n. 污染","phonetic_uk":"/pə'luːʃ(ə)n/","example":"California’s tough anti-pollution laws 加利福尼亚州严厉的反污染法"},{"phonetic_us":"/pɑnd/","translation":"n. 池塘","word":"pond","example":"The path descends to  the pond. 小路下斜通到池塘。","phonetic_uk":"/pɒnd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/puːl/","example":"They have a nice pool in their backyard. 他们后院有个漂亮的游泳池。","word":"pool","phonetic_us":"/pul/","translation":"n. 水塘，游泳池，水池"},{"word":"poor","phonetic_us":"/pʊr/","translation":"adj. 贫穷的；贫乏的","phonetic_uk":"/pɔː; pʊə/","example":"Her family were so poor they couldn’t afford to buy her new clothes. 她家穷得甚至买不起新衣服给她。"},{"word":"pop","phonetic_us":"/pɑp/","translation":"v. 突然出现，跳出","example":"The lid popped open and juice spilled all over the floor. 盖子噗的一声弹开，果汁溅了一地。","phonetic_uk":"/pɒp/"},{"word":"popular","translation":"adj. 民众的；流行的","phonetic_us":"/'pɑpjəlɚ/","example":"Hilary was popular at school. 希拉里在学校里很受欢迎。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒpjʊlə/"},{"word":"popularity","translation":"n.  普及， 流行； 声望","phonetic_us":"/,pɑpju'lærəti/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌpɒpju'lærəti/","example":"The president’s popularity has declined considerably. 总统的支持率大大下降了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'pɑpjələraɪz/","translation":"vt.  普及","word":"popularize","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒpjələraɪz/","example":"Skinner was the psychologist who popularized behavior modification. 斯金纳就是那位使行为矫正概念得到普及的心理学家。"},{"word":"population","translation":"n. 人口；全体居民","phonetic_us":"/,pɑpju'leʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/pɒpjʊ'leɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Nearly 70 percent of the population still live in the countryside. 人口中差不多有70%仍住在乡村。"},{"example":"pork chops 猪排","phonetic_uk":"/pɔːk/","phonetic_us":"/pɔrk/","translation":"n. 猪肉","word":"pork"},{"word":"port","translation":"n. 港，港口","phonetic_us":"/pɔrt/","phonetic_uk":"/pɔːt/","example":"Britain’s largest port 英国最大的港口城市"},{"translation":"adj. 轻便的；手提的","phonetic_us":"/'pɔrtəbl/","word":"portable","phonetic_uk":"/'pɔːtəb(ə)l/","example":"a portable radio 便携式收音机"},{"translation":"n. 搬运工","phonetic_us":"/'pɔrtɚ/","word":"porter","phonetic_uk":"/'pɔ:tə(r)/","example":"Our taxi pulled up at Old Delhi station and a porter sprinted to the door. 我们的出租车停在老德里车站，一个搬运工疾步跑向车门。"},{"word":"portion","translation":"n. 一部分；一分","phonetic_us":"/'pɔrʃən/","example":"Do you have any children’s portions? 你们有儿童餐吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'pɔːʃ(ə)n/"},{"example":"a family portrait 全家福","phonetic_uk":"/'pɔːtrɪt/","translation":"n. 消像，画像","phonetic_us":"/'pɔrtrɪt/","word":"portrait"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pəuz/","example":"Ann struck a pose (= stood or sat in a particular position ) and smiled for the camera. 安摆好姿势露出笑脸准备拍照。","translation":"v. 摆姿势，装腔作势；n. 姿势","phonetic_us":"/poz/","word":"pose"},{"word":"position","phonetic_us":"/pə'zɪʃən/","translation":"n. 职位","phonetic_uk":"/pəˈzɪʃn/","example":"Our hotel was in a superb central position near St Mark’s Square. 我们的酒店处于极佳的中心位置，在圣马克广场附近。"},{"translation":"adj. 确定的；积极的","phonetic_us":"/'pɑzətɪv/","word":"positive","example":"the power of positive thinking 正向思考的力量","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒzɪtɪv/"},{"example":"Different workers possess different skills. 不同的工人拥有不同技能。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'zes/","word":"possess","phonetic_us":"/pə'zɛs/","translation":"v. 占用，拥有(财产)"},{"example":"That information is not in our possession. 那则信息不归我们所有。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'zeʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/pə'zɛʃən/","translation":"n. 有，所有；占有物","word":"possession"},{"example":"There’s always a possibility that he might go back to Seattle. 他也许会回到西雅图去，这种可能性一直存在。","phonetic_uk":"/,pɒsɪ'bɪlɪtɪ/","phonetic_us":"/,pɑsə'bɪləti/","translation":"n. 可能；可能的事","word":"possibility"},{"translation":"adj. 可能的；可能存在的","phonetic_us":"/'pɑsəbl/","word":"possible","example":"Is it possible toget tickets for the game? 有没有可能弄到比赛的门票？","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒsɪb(ə)l/"},{"translation":"adv. 可能地；也许","phonetic_us":"/'pɑsəbli/","word":"possibly","example":"This last task is possibly the most difficult. 这最后一项任务也许是最难的。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒsɪblɪ/"},{"word":"post","phonetic_us":"/post/","translation":"n. 柱，桩，杆；v. 贴出","phonetic_uk":"/pəʊst/","example":"a fence post 篱笆桩"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pəʊstɪdʒ/","example":"How much is the postage for a postcard? 寄一张明信片的邮资是多少？","phonetic_us":"/'postɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 邮费，邮资","word":"postage"},{"example":"\"Given the level of competition in law, I definitely think that my postgraduate degree helped to distinguish me from the crowd, \" he says. 他说，“考虑到在法律行业的竞争水平，我确实认为我的研究生学位让我从众人中脱颖而出”。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌpəʊstˈgrædʒuət/","translation":"n. 研究生","phonetic_us":"/post'ɡrædjet/","word":"postgraduate"},{"word":"postman","phonetic_us":"/'postmən/","translation":"n. 邮递员","example":"That postman is in charge of this route. 那个邮递员负责这条投递线路。","phonetic_uk":"/'pəʊs(t)mən/"},{"word":"postpone","translation":"v. 延迟，推迟，延缓","phonetic_us":"/po'spon/","example":"The match had to be postponed until next week. 比赛不得不推迟到下周举行。","phonetic_uk":"/pəʊs(t)'pəʊn; pə'spəʊn/"},{"word":"pot","phonetic_us":"/pɑt/","translation":"n. 锅，壶，罐，盆","example":"herbs growing in pots 长在花盆里的草本植物","phonetic_uk":"/pɒt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/pə'teto/","translation":"n. 马铃薯，土豆","word":"potato","phonetic_uk":"/pə'teɪtəʊ/","example":"Marie stood at the sink, peeling potatoes (= cutting off the skin ) . 玛丽站在洗涤槽边削土豆皮。"},{"example":"The boy has great potential. 这个男孩有很大的潜力。","phonetic_uk":"/pə'tenʃəl/","word":"potential","phonetic_us":"/pə'tɛnʃl/","translation":"n. 潜力；adj. 有可能的；潜在的"},{"example":"Moira weighs about 130 pounds . 莫伊拉的体重约为130磅。","phonetic_uk":"/paʊnd/","phonetic_us":"/paʊnd/","translation":"n. 磅；英磅","word":"pound"},{"word":"pour","phonetic_us":"/pɔr/","translation":"v. 灌，倒；v. 倾泻","phonetic_uk":"/pɔː/","example":"She poured coffee for everyone. 她为每个人都倒了咖啡。"},{"example":"Millions of elderly people live in poverty . 数百万老年人生活在贫困之中。","phonetic_uk":"/'pɒvətɪ/","word":"poverty","phonetic_us":"/'pɑvɚti/","translation":"n. 贫穷，贫困"},{"example":"curry powder 咖喱粉","phonetic_uk":"/'paʊdə/","phonetic_us":"/'paʊdɚ/","translation":"n. 粉末；药粉；火药","word":"powder"},{"phonetic_us":"/'paʊɚ/","translation":"n. 能力；力；权；幂","word":"power","example":"They seized power in a military coup. 他们在一场军事政变中夺取了政权。","phonetic_uk":"/'paʊə/"},{"example":"He was one of the most powerful men in Bohemia. 他是波希米亚最有权势的人物之一。","phonetic_uk":"/'paʊəfʊl; -f(ə)l/","word":"powerful","translation":"adj. 强有力的；有权威的","phonetic_us":"/'paʊɚfl/"},{"example":"Candidates should have training and practical experience in basic electronics. 应征者应该具备基础电子学方面的培训和实践经验。","phonetic_uk":"/'præktɪk(ə)l/","word":"practical","phonetic_us":"/'præktɪkl/","translation":"adj. 实践的；实用的"},{"translation":"adv. 实际上；几乎","phonetic_us":"/'præktɪkli/","word":"practically","phonetic_uk":"/'præktɪk(ə)lɪ/","example":"I’ve read practically all of his books. 我差不多读过他所有的书。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'præktɪs/","translation":"n. 实践；练习；业务","word":"practice","example":"It takes hours of practice to learn to play the guitar. 学习弹吉他需要长时间的练习。","phonetic_uk":"/'præktɪs/"},{"example":"They moved the furniture back to practise their dance routine. 他们把家具往后挪以便练习舞蹈动作。","phonetic_uk":"/'præktɪs/","translation":"v. 练习，实习，训练","phonetic_us":"/'præktɪs/","word":"practise"},{"example":"Jane was praised by her teacher. 简受到了老师的表扬。","phonetic_uk":"/preɪz/","word":"praise","phonetic_us":"/prez/","translation":"v. 赞扬，赞美"},{"phonetic_us":"/pre/","translation":"vt&vi. 请求；祈祷","word":"pray","phonetic_uk":"/preɪ/","example":"They went to the mosque to pray. 他们去清真寺祷告。"},{"translation":"n.  祷告， 祈祷； 祷文； 祈求， 祈望","phonetic_us":"/prɛr/","word":"prayer","phonetic_uk":"/preə/","example":"Our thoughts and prayers are with you at this difficult time. 在这艰难时期我们时刻思念你，为你祈祷。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'kɔːʃ(ə)n/","example":"Fire precautions were neglected. 防火措施被忽视了。","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'kɔʃən/","translation":"n. 预防；警惕","word":"precaution"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'siːdɪŋ/","example":"As we saw in the preceding chapter, groups can be powerful agents of socialization. 如我们在前一章所见，团组可以是社会化的有力动因。","phonetic_us":"/'prisidɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 在前的；在先的","word":"preceding"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'preʃəs/","example":"planes delivering precious supplies of medicine and food 运送药品、食品等宝贵物资的飞机","word":"precious","phonetic_us":"/'prɛʃəs/","translation":"adj. 珍贵的，宝贵的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'saɪs/","example":"precise sales figures 准确的销售数据","word":"precise","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'saɪs/","translation":"adj. 精确的，准确的"},{"phonetic_us":"/prɪ'sɪʒn/","translation":"n. 精确，精密，精密度","word":"precision","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'sɪʒ(ə)n/","example":""},{"example":"Sales were five percent lower than predicted. 销售额比预期低5%。","phonetic_uk":"/pri'dikt/","translation":"v. 预言，预测，预告","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'dɪkt/","word":"predict"},{"translation":"adj.  可预料的","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'dɪktəbl/","word":"predictable","example":"The snow had a predictable effect on traffic. 这场雪对交通造成的影响可以预见。","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'dɪktəbl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'prɛfəs/","translation":"n. 序言，前言，引语","word":"preface","example":"...the preface to Kelman's novel. …凯尔曼小说的前言。","phonetic_uk":"/'prefəs/"},{"phonetic_us":"/prɪ'fɝ/","translation":"v. 宁可，宁愿","word":"prefer","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'fɜː/","example":""},{"phonetic_us":"/'prɛfrəbl/","translation":"adj. 更可取的，更好的","word":"preferable","phonetic_uk":"/'pref(ə)rəb(ə)l/","example":"For this dish, fresh herbs and garlic are preferable. 做这道菜，用新鲜香草和大蒜更好。"},{"word":"preference","translation":"n. 偏爱","phonetic_us":"/'prɛfrəns/","example":"Do you have a colour preference ? 你有什么颜色上的偏好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'pref(ə)r(ə)ns/"},{"translation":"adv. 优先地","phonetic_us":"/,prefə'renʃəli/","word":"preferentially","phonetic_uk":"/,prefə'renʃəli/","example":"Heterosexuals should not be treated preferentially when the state carries out that role. 当国家执行这个作用的时候不应该优先对待异性恋者。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈpregnənt/","example":"care for pregnant women 孕妇保健","phonetic_us":"/'prɛɡnənt/","translation":"adj. 怀孕的","word":"pregnant"},{"phonetic_us":"/'prɛdʒədɪs/","translation":"n &v. 偏见","word":"prejudice","example":"Women still face prejudice in the workplace. 女性在职场中仍然面临歧视。","phonetic_uk":"/'predʒʊdɪs/"},{"word":"preliminary","translation":"adj. 预备的，初步的","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'lɪmɪnɛri/","example":"the preliminary stages of the competition 竞赛的预赛阶段","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'lɪmɪn(ə)rɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 准备，预备；制备","phonetic_us":"/,prɛpə'reʃən/","word":"preparation","example":"This dish is good for dinner parties because much of the preparation can be done ahead of time. 这道菜适合宴会，因为很多准备工作可以事先做好。","phonetic_uk":"/,prepə'reɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"word":"prepare","translation":"v. 做准备","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'pɛr/","phonetic_uk":"/prɪˈpeə(r)/","example":"The prosecution wanted more time to prepare their case. 原告想要有更多的时间来准备诉讼。"},{"word":"preposition","translation":"n. 前置词，介词","phonetic_us":"/,prɛpə'zɪʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/,prepə'zɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"There is nothing in the rules of grammar to suggest that ending a sentence with a preposition is wrong. 在语法规则中没有哪一条表明以介词结束一个句子是错误的。"},{"word":"prescribe","translation":"v. 命令；处(方)","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'skraɪb/","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'skraɪb/","example":"The physician examines the patient then diagnoses the disease and prescribes medication. 内科医生检查了病人，然后对疾病作出诊断，并开出药方。"},{"word":"prescription","translation":"n. 处方","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'skrɪpʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/prɪˈskrɪpʃn/","example":"We are trying to cut the price of prescription drugs . 我们正努力降低处方药的价格。"},{"word":"presence","phonetic_us":"/'prɛzns/","translation":"n. 出席，到场；在","example":"Your presence is requested at the club meeting on Friday. 敬请出席于周五举行的俱乐部会议。","phonetic_uk":"/'prez(ə)ns/"},{"word":"present","translation":"adj. 现在的；n. 目前","phonetic_us":"/'prɛznt/","example":"the present situation of the millions of people who are suffering poverty and disease 遭受贫困和疾病折磨的数百万人民的现状","phonetic_uk":"/'prez(ə)nt/"},{"example":"the presentation ceremony 颁奖仪式","phonetic_uk":"/ˌprezn'teɪʃn/","word":"presentation","phonetic_us":"/,prizɛn'teʃən/","translation":"n.  提供， 显示； 外观， 图像； 授予， 赠送； 报告， 介绍； 表演"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prez(ə)ntlɪ/","example":"The doctor will be here presently. 医生一会儿就到。","phonetic_us":"/'prɛzntli/","translation":"adv. 一会儿；目前","word":"presently"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌprezəˈveɪʃn/","example":"methods of food preservation 保存食物的各种方法","translation":"n. 保存，保留","phonetic_us":"/,prɛzɚ'veʃən/","word":"preservation"},{"example":"We must encourage the planting of new trees and preserve our existing woodlands. 我们必须鼓励栽种新树木，同时也要保护现有的林地。","phonetic_uk":"/prɪˈzɜ:v/","word":"preserve","translation":"v. 保护","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'zɝv/"},{"translation":"n. 总统；校长；会长","phonetic_us":"/'prɛzɪdənt/","word":"president","example":"President Bush 布什总统","phonetic_uk":"/'prezɪd(ə)nt/"},{"word":"press","phonetic_us":"/prɛs/","translation":"v. 压，按，揿；催促","phonetic_uk":"/pres/","example":"Manville kept his back pressed flat against the wall. 曼维尔后背紧紧地贴在墙上。"},{"word":"pressure","translation":"n. 压力；压力；压，按","phonetic_us":"/'prɛʃɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'preʃə/","example":"They are putting pressure on people to vote yes. 他们正在向民众施加压力，要求他们投赞成票。"},{"phonetic_us":"/prɪ'zuməbli/","translation":"adv.  大概， 可能， 据推测","word":"presumably","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'zjuːməbli/","example":"It’s raining, which presumably means that your football match will be cancelled. 下雨了，这可能意味着你们的足球比赛要取消。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'tend/","example":"Let’s pretend we’re on the moon. 我们假装自己是在月球上吧。","translation":"v. 假托，借口vi假装","phonetic_us":"/prɪ'tɛnd/","word":"pretend"},{"example":"a pretty little girl 漂亮的小姑娘","phonetic_uk":"/'prɪtɪ/","translation":"adj. 漂亮的，标致的","phonetic_us":"/'prɪti/","word":"pretty"},{"translation":"v. 流行，盛行","phonetic_us":"/pri'vel/","word":"prevail","example":"A similar situation prevails in Canada. 同样的情况在加拿大也普遍存在。","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'veɪl/"},{"example":"The rules are intended to prevent accidents. 这些规定旨在预防事故。","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'vent/","translation":"v. 预防","phonetic_us":"/pri'vɛnt/","word":"prevent"},{"example":"Forty thousand children a day die from preventable diseases. 每天有四万儿童死于本可以防止的疾病。","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'ventəbl/","phonetic_us":"/pri'vɛntəbl/","translation":"adj. 可预防的","word":"preventable"},{"word":"preventive","phonetic_us":"/pri'vɛntɪv/","translation":"adj.  预防性的","example":"preventive health programs 预防性的保健计划","phonetic_uk":"/prɪ'ventɪv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈpri:viəs/","example":"She has a teenage daughter from a previous marriage. 她有个出自前一次婚姻的十几岁的女儿。","phonetic_us":"/'privɪəs/","translation":"adj. 之前的；adv. 先前地","word":"previous"},{"example":"Guyana's railways were previously owned by private companies. 圭亚那的铁路先前为私营公司所拥有。","phonetic_uk":"/'pri:vɪəslɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'priviəsli/","translation":"adv. 事先","word":"previously"},{"phonetic_uk":"/praɪs/","example":"They may pay a high price for their few years of glory. 为了短短几年的辉煌，他们也许要付出高昂的代价。","phonetic_us":"/praɪs/","translation":"n. 价格，价钱；代价","word":"price"},{"word":"pride","phonetic_us":"/praɪd/","translation":"n. 骄傲；自豪；v. 自夸","example":"He wore his medals with pride. 他自豪地戴着奖章。","phonetic_uk":"/praɪd/"},{"word":"priest","translation":"n.  神父， 牧师","phonetic_us":"/prist/","phonetic_uk":"/priːst/","example":"He had trained to be a Catholic priest. 他接受培训成了一名天主教神父。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prai'mərili/","example":"The advertisement is aimed primarily at children. 这则广告的对象主要是儿童。","translation":"adv. 主要地，首先","phonetic_us":"/praɪ'mɛrəli/","word":"primarily"},{"phonetic_us":"/'praɪmɛri/","translation":"adj. 主要的，基本的","word":"primary","phonetic_uk":"/ˈpraɪməri/","example":"Our primary concern is to provide the refugees with food and health care. 我们的头等大事是向难民提供食品和医疗。"},{"example":"Smoking is the prime cause of lung disease. 抽烟是引发肺部疾病的首要原因。","phonetic_uk":"/praɪm/","word":"prime","translation":"adj. 首要的；n. 春，青春","phonetic_us":"/praɪm/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'prɪmətɪv/","translation":"adj. 原始的；简单的","word":"primitive","phonetic_uk":"/'primitiv/","example":"a primitive society 原始社会"},{"word":"prince","translation":"n. 王子，亲王","phonetic_us":"/prɪns/","example":"Prince William 威廉王子","phonetic_uk":"/prɪns/"},{"word":"princess","phonetic_us":"/prɪnˌsɛs/","translation":"n. 公主，王妃","phonetic_uk":"/prɪn'ses/","example":"Princess Anne 安妮公主"},{"example":"His principal reason for making the journey was to visit his family. 他那次旅程的首要目的是探访家人。","phonetic_uk":"/'prɪnsəp(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 主要的；n. 负责人","phonetic_us":"/'prɪnsəpl/","word":"principal"},{"word":"principle","translation":"n. 原则，原理","phonetic_us":"/'prɪnsəpl/","example":"Schools try to teach children a set of principles. 学校设法教给孩子们一套道德准则。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈprɪnsəpl/"},{"word":"print","translation":"v. 印刷；n. 印刷；正片","phonetic_us":"/prɪnt/","example":"Over five million copies of the paper are printed every day. 这份报纸每日印量超过五百万。","phonetic_uk":"/prɪnt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'praɪə/","example":"You do not need any prior knowledge of the subject. 你无需事先具备该方面的知识。","word":"prior","translation":"adj. 在先的；优先的","phonetic_us":"/'praɪɚ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/praɪ'ɔrəti/","translation":"n. 优先，优先权","word":"priority","phonetic_uk":"/praɪ'ɒrətɪ/","example":"The club’s priority is to win the League. 该俱乐部首先考虑的是要赢得联赛。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prɪz(ə)n/","example":"He visits his dad in prison every week. 他每周都去探望狱中的父亲。","phonetic_us":"/'prɪzn/","translation":"n. 监狱，监禁","word":"prison"},{"example":"Relationships between the staff and the prisoners are good. 狱警和犯人相处良好。","phonetic_uk":"/'prɪz(ə)nə/","word":"prisoner","phonetic_us":"/'prɪznɚ/","translation":"n. 囚犯"},{"word":"privacy","translation":"n. 隐私","phonetic_us":"/'praɪvəsi/","phonetic_uk":"/'prɪvəsɪ/","example":"each individual’s right to privacy 每个人的隐私权"},{"example":"Morris has a private jet. 莫里斯拥有一架私人喷气式飞机。","phonetic_uk":"/'praɪvət/","phonetic_us":"/'praɪvət/","translation":"adj. 私人的","word":"private"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈprɪvəlɪdʒ/","example":"He had no special privileges and was treated just like every other prisoner. 他不享受特权，待遇和任何其他犯人一样。","phonetic_us":"/ˈprɪvəlɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 特权，优惠","word":"privilege"},{"translation":"n. 奖赏，奖金；v. 珍视","phonetic_us":"/praɪz/","word":"prize","example":"In this month’s competition you could win a prize worth £3,000. 在本月的竞赛中您可以赢得价值3,000英镑的奖品。","phonetic_uk":"/praɪz/"},{"example":"You must decide whether, on the balance of probabilities , he committed the crime. 你们一定要权衡正反两方面的可能性，然后再裁定他是否犯罪。","phonetic_uk":"/prɒbə'bɪlɪtɪ/","word":"probability","phonetic_us":"/'prɑbə'bɪləti/","translation":"n. 可能性；概率"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prɒbəb(ə)l/","example":"The probable cause of the fire was faulty wiring. 起火的原因很可能是电路故障。","phonetic_us":"/'prɑbəbl/","translation":"adj. 或有的；大概的","word":"probable"},{"word":"probably","translation":"adv. 或许，大概","phonetic_us":"","example":"","phonetic_uk":""},{"example":"She was older than me, but that wasn’t really a problem. 她比我年长，不过那不算什么问题。","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒbləm/","phonetic_us":"/'prɑbləm/","translation":"n. 问题；习题，问题","word":"problem"},{"phonetic_us":"/prə'sidʒɚ/","translation":"n. 程序","word":"procedure","example":"On board, we were given the usual talk on safety procedures (= what to do if an accident happens, or to prevent an accident ) . 在飞机上，我们听了例行的飞行安全讲解。","phonetic_uk":"/prəˈsi:dʒə(r)/"},{"phonetic_us":"/pro'sid/","translation":"v. 进行；继续进行","word":"proceed","example":"Before proceeding further, we must define our terms. 我们必须先定义术语，然后再往下展开。","phonetic_uk":"/prə'siːd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prəuses/","example":"the Israeli-Egyptian peace process 以－埃和平进程","phonetic_us":"/'prɑsɛs/","translation":"n. 过程，进程；工序；(法律)程序；v. 处理","word":"process"},{"example":"They marched in procession to the Capitol building. 他们列队向国会大厦行进。","phonetic_uk":"/prə'seʃ(ə)n/","word":"procession","phonetic_us":"/prə'sɛʃən/","translation":"n. 队伍，行列"},{"translation":"v. 生产；产生；展现","phonetic_us":"/prə'dus/","word":"produce","phonetic_uk":"/prə'djuːs/","example":"New drugs are producing remarkable results . 新药正在产生显著的效果。"},{"word":"product","translation":"n. 产品，产物；(乘)积","phonetic_us":"/'prɑdʌkt/","example":"The London factory assembles the finished product . 伦敦工厂组装成品。","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒdʌkt/"},{"example":"That model won't go into production before late 2007. 那种型号要到2007年底才会投入生产。","phonetic_uk":"/prə'dʌkʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/prə'dʌkʃən/","translation":"n. 生产；产品；总产量","word":"production"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prəˈdʌktɪv/","example":"Most of us are more productive in the morning. 我们大多数人在早上更有效率。","word":"productive","phonetic_us":"/prə'dʌktɪv/","translation":"adj. 富有成效的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prə'feʃ(ə)n/","example":"people who work in the professions 从事专业性工作的人","word":"profession","translation":"n. 职业","phonetic_us":"/prə'fɛʃən/"},{"translation":"adj. 专业的","phonetic_us":"/prə'fɛʃənl/","word":"professional","phonetic_uk":"/prəˈfeʃənl/","example":"This business plan looks very professional. 这个商业计划看上去很有专业水平。"},{"example":"The professor improvised a poem in the class. 教授在课堂上即兴创作了一首诗。","phonetic_uk":"","translation":"n. 教授","phonetic_us":"","word":"professor"},{"phonetic_us":"/'profaɪl/","translation":"n. 侧面；人物简介；轮廓，形象；姿态，引人注目的状态；vt.  为…描绘； 写…的传略","word":"profile","example":"Dani has a lovely profile. 达尼的侧面轮廓很好看。","phonetic_uk":"/'prəufaɪl/"},{"word":"profit","phonetic_us":"/'prɑfɪt/","translation":"n. 益处；利润；v. 得益","example":"The shop’s daily profit is usually around $500. 这家商店每天的利润一般在500美元左右。","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒfɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈprɒfɪtəbl/","example":"The advertising campaign proved very profitable. 事实证明，这次广告宣传活动卓有成效。","word":"profitable","phonetic_us":"/'prɑfɪtəbl/","translation":"adj. 有利可图的，有益的"},{"phonetic_us":"/prə'faʊnd/","translation":"adj. 深厚的","word":"profound","phonetic_uk":"/prə'faʊnd/","example":"a profound sense of guilt 强烈的内疚感"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prəʊɡræm/","example":"a word processing program 文字处理程序","word":"program","phonetic_us":"/'proɡræm/","translation":"n. 节目单；大纲；程序"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prəʊgræmə/","example":"The computer programmer botched (up) the job and had to start over. 计算机程序设计员把文件弄坏了，只好重做。","translation":"n. 程序设计员","phonetic_us":"/'progræmɚ/","word":"programmer"},{"example":"a course in computer programming 计算机编程的课程","phonetic_uk":"/'prəugræmiŋ/","phonetic_us":"/'proɡræmɪŋ/","translation":"n. 计划，节目(单)，程序；；vt. 编程","word":"programming"},{"word":"progress","translation":"n. 前进，进展；进步","phonetic_us":"/'prɑɡrɛs/","example":"We made good progress despite the snow. 尽管下雪，我们的行程还是很顺利。","phonetic_uk":"/'prəʊgres/"},{"translation":"adj. 进步的；向前进的","phonetic_us":"/prə'ɡrɛsɪv/","word":"progressive","example":"a progressive administration 进步的政府","phonetic_uk":"/prə'gresɪv/"},{"word":"prohibit","translation":"v. 禁止，阻止，防止","phonetic_us":"/prə'hɪbɪt/","phonetic_uk":"/prə'hɪbɪt/","example":"Smoking is strictly prohibited inside the factory. 厂区严禁吸烟。"},{"translation":"adv. 过分地，非常地","phonetic_us":"","word":"prohibitively","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/prəʊˈhɪbɪtɪvlɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/prəˈdʒɛkt; prɑdʒɛkt/","translation":"n. 工程，作业","word":"project","phonetic_uk":"/prəˈdʒekt/","example":"The project aims to provide an analysis of children’s emotions. 该计划旨在对儿童情绪作出分析。"},{"word":"prolong","translation":"vt.  拉长， 延长","phonetic_us":"/prəˈlɑːŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/prə'lɒŋ/","example":"I was trying to think of some way to prolong the conversation. 我在想方设法拖长这次谈话。"},{"example":"a prominent Russian scientist 杰出的俄罗斯科学家","phonetic_uk":"/'prɔminənt/","translation":"adj. 杰出的，突起的，凸出的","phonetic_us":"/'prɑmɪnənt/","word":"prominent"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prɒmɪs/","example":"If you make a promise, you should keep it. 如果你许下一个诺言，你就应该遵守它。","phonetic_us":"/'prɑmɪs/","translation":"n. 诺言；指望；v. 允诺","word":"promise"},{"translation":"adj. 有希望的，有前途的","phonetic_us":"/'prɑmɪsɪŋ/","word":"promising","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒmɪsɪŋ/","example":"a promising career in law 很有前途的法律职业"},{"example":"You don't have to sacrifice environmental protection to promote economic growth. 你们没有必要牺牲环保来促进经济增长。","phonetic_uk":"/prə'məut/","word":"promote","phonetic_us":"/prə'mot/","translation":"v. 促进，提升，推销"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prə'məʊʃənl/","example":"\"Jeans,\" according to one company's promotional material, \"are designed and made to be worn hard.\" 根据一家公司促销材料上所说的，“牛仔裤为耐穿而设计和制作。”","word":"promotional","translation":"adj. 促销的","phonetic_us":"/prə'moʃənl/"},{"example":"Prompt action must be taken. 必须立即采取行动。","phonetic_uk":"/prɒmpt/","translation":"adj. 敏捷的；v. 敦促","phonetic_us":"/prɑmpt/","word":"prompt"},{"example":"Now if we could only figure out the pronoun problem. 现在我们可以解决这个代词问题了。","phonetic_uk":"/'prəʊnaʊn/","word":"pronoun","translation":"n. 代名词","phonetic_us":"/'pronaʊn/"},{"word":"pronounce","phonetic_us":"/prə'naʊns/","translation":"v. 发…的音；宣布","phonetic_uk":"/prə'naʊns/","example":"How do you pronounce your name? 你的名字怎么念？"},{"phonetic_us":"/prə,nʌnsɪ'eʃən/","translation":"n. 发音，发音法","word":"pronunciation","phonetic_uk":"/prə,nʌnsɪ'eɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"She gave the word its French pronunciation. 她给出了这个单词的法语发音。"},{"example":"There is no proof that the document is authentic. 没有证据证明这份文件是真的。","phonetic_uk":"/pruːf/","translation":"n. 证据；证明；校样","phonetic_us":"/pruf/","word":"proof"},{"example":"Everything was in its proper place (= where it should be ) . 每样东西都放在恰当的位置。","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒpə/","word":"proper","translation":"adj. 适合的；合乎体统的","phonetic_us":"/'prɑpɚ/"},{"translation":"n. 财产，资产；性质","phonetic_us":"/'prɑpɚti/","word":"property","example":"The hotel is not responsible for any loss or damage to guests’ personal property . 宾馆对住客个人财物的丢失和损坏概不负责。","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒpətɪ/"},{"word":"proportion","translation":"n. 比例，部分","phonetic_us":"/prə'pɔrʃən/","example":"A large proportion of the dolphins in that area will eventually die. 那个地区的很大一部分海豚最终都会死去。","phonetic_uk":"/prə'pɔ:ʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prə'pɔːʃ(ə)n(ə)l/","example":"The fee charged by the realtor is directly proportional to the price of the property. 房产代理人收取的费用和房产价格是成正比的。","translation":"adj. 比例的；相称的","phonetic_us":"/prə'pɔrʃənl/","word":"proportional"},{"phonetic_uk":"/prə'pəʊz(ə)l/","example":"The president is to put forward new proposals for resolving the country's constitutional crisis. 总统将提出解决国家宪法危机的新议案。","word":"proposal","translation":"n. 提议","phonetic_us":"/prə'pozl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/prə'poz/","translation":"v. 提议；v. 求婚","word":"propose","phonetic_uk":"/prə'pəʊz/","example":"the changes currently proposed by the local planning authorities 目前由地方规划局提议的改革"},{"word":"prospect","translation":"n. 前景","phonetic_us":"/'prɑspɛkt/","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒspekt/","example":"I had no job, no education, and no prospects . 我没有工作，没受过什么教育，前途渺茫。"},{"word":"prosper","translation":"v. 繁荣","phonetic_us":"/'prɑspɚ/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒspə/"},{"example":"a time of economic prosperity 经济繁荣时期","phonetic_uk":"/prɒˈsperəti/","phonetic_us":"/prɑ'spɛrəti/","translation":"n. 繁荣","word":"prosperity"},{"word":"prosperous","phonetic_us":"/'prɑspərəs/","translation":"adj. 繁荣的，昌盛的","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒsp(ə)rəs/","example":"a prosperous landowner 富裕的土地拥有者"},{"example":"Are we doing enough to protect the environment? 我们在保护环境方面做得够吗？","phonetic_uk":"/prə'tekt/","translation":"v. 保护，保卫，警戒","phonetic_us":"/prə'tɛkt/","word":"protect"},{"phonetic_us":"/prə'tɛkʃən/","translation":"n. 保护，警戒","word":"protection","example":"protection money 保护费","phonetic_uk":"/prə'tekʃ(ə)n/"},{"example":"protective clothing 防护服","phonetic_uk":"/prə'tektɪv/","phonetic_us":"/prə'tɛktɪv/","translation":"adj. 保护的，防护的","word":"protective"},{"phonetic_us":"/'protin/","translation":"n. 蛋白质，朊","word":"protein","example":"Where do you get your protein? 你从哪里获得蛋白质？","phonetic_uk":"/'prəʊtiːn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prəʊtest/","example":"‘I don’t see why I should take the blame for this!’ she protested. “我不明白为什么我要对此承担责任！”她抗议道。","phonetic_us":"/ˈproʊtest/","translation":"v. 抗议","word":"protest"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'prəutəkɒl/","example":"a breach of diplomatic protocol 违反外交礼节","phonetic_us":"/'protə'kɔl/","translation":"n.  礼仪， 礼节； 草案， 议定书","word":"protocol"},{"phonetic_us":"/praʊd/","translation":"adj. 骄傲的；自豪的","word":"proud","phonetic_uk":"/praʊd/","example":"Seth was the proud owner of a new sports car. 赛思因为有了新跑车而扬扬得意。"},{"example":"You’re wrong, and I can prove it. 你错了，我可以证明。","phonetic_uk":"/pruːv/","word":"prove","phonetic_us":"/pruv/","translation":"v. 证明；v. 结果是"},{"translation":"v. 提供；装备，供给","phonetic_us":"/prə'vaɪd/","word":"provide","phonetic_uk":"/prə'vaɪd/","example":"Tea and biscuits will be provided. 有茶水和饼干供应。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"","translation":"conj. 以…为条件","phonetic_us":"","word":"provided"},{"phonetic_us":"/prə'vaɪdɪŋ/","translation":"conj.  倘若","word":"providing","phonetic_uk":"/prə'vaɪdɪŋ/","example":""},{"example":"a Chinese province 中国的一个省","phonetic_uk":"/'prɒvɪns/","translation":"n. 省；领域，部门","phonetic_us":"/'prɑvɪns/","word":"province"},{"word":"provision","translation":"n. 供应；预备；存粮","phonetic_us":"/prə'vɪʒn/","phonetic_uk":"/prə'vɪʒ(ə)n/","example":"He made provisions for his wife and his children in his will. 在遗嘱里他为妻子和孩子都做好了安排。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,prɑvə'keʃən/","translation":"n.  激怒， 刺激； 挑衅， 挑拨","word":"provocation","phonetic_uk":"/ˌprɒvə'keɪʃn/","example":"He was accused of deliberate provocation . 他被指责故意挑衅。"},{"phonetic_us":"/prə'vok/","translation":"v. 激起，挑起","word":"provoke","example":"The novel has provoked fierce debate in the US. 那部小说在美国引发了激烈的争论。","phonetic_uk":"/prə'vəʊk/"},{"example":"Sleep disorders are a serious psychological problem . 睡眠障碍是严重的心理疾病。","phonetic_uk":"/,saikə'lɔdʒikəl/","word":"psychological","translation":"adj. 心理上的","phonetic_us":"/,saɪkə'lɑdʒɪkl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/saɪ'kɑlədʒɪst/","translation":"n. 心理学家","word":"psychologist","phonetic_uk":"/saɪˈkɒlədʒɪst/","example":"a clinical psychologist 临床心理学家"},{"word":"public","phonetic_us":"/'pʌblɪk/","translation":"adj. 公众的；n. 公众","example":"We have to show that publishing this story is in the public interest (= helpful or useful to ordinary people ) . 我们必须证明刊登这篇报道有利于公众。","phonetic_uk":"/'pʌblɪk/"},{"example":"The guide is being translated into several languages for publication near Christmas. 这本指南正被翻译成好几种语言，准备在圣诞节前后出版。","phonetic_uk":"/,pʌblɪ'keɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"publication","phonetic_us":"/,pʌblɪ'keʃən/","translation":"n. 公布；出版；出版物"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pʌb'lɪsəti/","example":"Much advance publicity was given to the talks. 会谈之前做了大量的宣传。","word":"publicity","translation":"n.  公众的注意， 名声； 宣传， 宣扬","phonetic_us":"/pʌb'lɪsəti/"},{"example":"television’s failure to publicize the unemployment issue 电视未能报道失业问题","phonetic_uk":"/'pʌblɪsaɪz/","translation":"v. 宣布","phonetic_us":"/'pʌblɪsaɪz/","word":"publicize"},{"word":"publish","translation":"v. 公布；发表；出版","phonetic_us":"/'pʌblɪʃ/","example":"The first edition was published in 1765. 第一版于1765年出版。","phonetic_uk":"/'pʌblɪʃ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pʊl/","example":"Mom! Davey’s pulling my hair! 妈妈! 戴维拽我的头发！","word":"pull","phonetic_us":"/pʊl/","translation":"v. 拉，拖；拉，拉力"},{"word":"pulse","translation":"n. 脉搏；脉冲，脉动","phonetic_us":"/pʌls/","example":"His breathing was shallow and his pulse was weak . 他呼吸很浅，脉搏微弱。","phonetic_uk":"/pʌls/"},{"word":"pump","phonetic_us":"/pʌmp/","translation":"n. 泵；v. 用抽机抽","phonetic_uk":"/pʌmp/","example":"...pumps that circulate the fuel around in the engine. …使燃料在发动机内循环的压泵。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pʌn(t)ʃ/","example":"This new sort of punch could stamp out 3,000 bonnets an hour. 这种新型冲床每小时可冲压出三千个汽车引擎盖。","phonetic_us":"","translation":"v. 冲出；n. 冲压机","word":"punch"},{"example":"She’s always very punctual for appointments. 她一向准时赴约。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈpʌŋktʃuəl/","translation":"adj. 准时的","phonetic_us":"/'pʌŋtʃʊəl/","word":"punctual"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pʌnɪʃ/","example":"Smacking is not an acceptable way of punishing a child. 要惩罚孩子，不应该用打的方式。","phonetic_us":"/'pʌnɪʃ/","translation":"v. 罚，惩罚，处罚","word":"punish"},{"word":"pupil","phonetic_us":"/pjupl/","translation":"n. 学生，小学生","example":"About 20 pupils study music here. 大约20名小学生在这里学习音乐。","phonetic_uk":"/'pjuːpɪl; -p(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɜ:tʃəs/","example":"She paid for her purchases and left. 她付钱买好东西离开了。","translation":"n. 买，购买；v. 买","phonetic_us":"/'pɝtʃəs/","word":"purchase"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pjʊə/","example":"rings made of pure gold 纯金制成的戒指","phonetic_us":"/pjʊr/","translation":"adj. 纯粹的；纯洁的","word":"pure"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɜːp(ə)l/","example":"A purple may be made by dyeing a blue over a red. 红色染上蓝色便可成为紫色。","word":"purple","translation":"n. 紫色；adj. 紫的","phonetic_us":"/'pɝpl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'pɜːpəs/","example":"Nick had no particular purpose in mind when he started. 尼克开始的时候头脑中并没有明确的目标。","phonetic_us":"/'pɝpəs/","translation":"n. 目的；意图；效果","word":"purpose"},{"word":"purse","translation":"n. 钱包，小钱袋，手袋","phonetic_us":"/pɝs/","phonetic_uk":"/pɜːs/","example":"I locked the door and dropped the keys in my purse. 我锁上门，然后把钥匙丢进手提包里。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/pə'sju:/","example":"She plans to pursue a career in politics. 她计划从政。","word":"pursue","phonetic_us":"/pə'sʊ/","translation":"v. 追求"},{"phonetic_us":"/pʊʃ/","translation":"v. 推，逼迫；v. 推","word":"push","example":"It didn’t move, so she pushed harder. 它一动不动，因此她加力去推。","phonetic_uk":"/pʊʃ/"},{"word":"put","phonetic_us":"/pʊt/","translation":"v. 放，摆；使处于","example":"He put the coffee on the table. 他把咖啡放在桌上。","phonetic_uk":"/pʊt/"},{"translation":"n&v. 迷惑","phonetic_us":"/'pʌzl/","word":"puzzle","phonetic_uk":"/'pʌz(ə)l/","example":"My sister puzzles me and causes me anxiety. 我的妹妹常会让我不解，使我焦虑。"},{"word":"puzzling","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 令人困惑的","phonetic_uk":"/'pʌzlɪŋ/","example":"a puzzling fact 令人费解的情况"},{"example":"He left school without any qualifications. 他离校时没有拿到任何文凭。","phonetic_uk":"/,kwɔlifi'keiʃən/","phonetic_us":"/,kwɑlɪfɪ'keʃən/","translation":"n. 资格(证明)，合格证书","word":"qualification"},{"example":"Free school lunches are given to children who qualify. 符合条件的儿童可获得免费的学生午餐。","phonetic_uk":"/'kwɒlɪfaɪ/","translation":"v. 使……有资格","phonetic_us":"/ˈkwɑləˌfaɪ/","word":"qualify"},{"word":"quality","phonetic_us":"/'kwɑləti/","translation":"n. 品质","example":"Much of the land was of poor quality. 很多地的土质很差。","phonetic_uk":"/'kwɒlɪtɪ/"},{"word":"quantity","translation":"n. 量，数量","phonetic_us":"/'kwɑntəti/","example":"Your work has improved in quantity and quality this term. 这学期你的作业在完成数量和质量上都有提高。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈkwɒntəti/"},{"example":"I had a terrible quarrel with my other brothers. 我和其他几个兄弟大吵了一架。","phonetic_uk":"/'kwɒr(ə)l/","word":"quarrel","phonetic_us":"/'kwɔrəl/","translation":"n. 争吵，吵架，口角"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'kwɔːtə/","example":"It’s about a page and a quarter. 大概是一又四分之一页。","translation":"n. 四分之一；一刻钟","phonetic_us":"/'kwɔrtɚ/","word":"quarter"},{"phonetic_uk":"/kwiːn/","example":"the queen of diamonds 方块Q，方块王后","phonetic_us":"/kwin/","translation":"n. 王后；女王","word":"queen"},{"translation":"n. 发问；问题；疑问","phonetic_us":"/'kwɛstʃən/","word":"question","phonetic_uk":"/'kwestʃ(ə)n/","example":"Can I ask you a question? 我能问你个问题吗？"},{"phonetic_us":"/kju/","translation":"n. 行列；v. 排队等候","word":"queue","phonetic_uk":"/kjuː/","example":"You’ll have to join the queue. 你得排队。"},{"example":"That was quick! I thought you’d be another hour. 很快啊！我以为你还要一个小时呢。","phonetic_uk":"/kwɪk/","translation":"adj. 快的；敏捷的","phonetic_us":"/kwɪk/","word":"quick"},{"phonetic_us":"/'kwaɪət/","translation":"adj. 寂静的；安静的","word":"quiet","phonetic_uk":"/'kwaɪət/","example":"We’ll have to be quiet so as not to wake the baby. 我们得安静点，免得吵醒宝宝。"},{"word":"quit","translation":"v. 放弃","phonetic_us":"/kwɪt/","example":"There are no failures in life, only those who quit before success. 生活中没有失败者，只有那些在成功前就放弃的人。","phonetic_uk":"/kwɪt/"},{"word":"quite","translation":"adv. 完全；相当；的确","phonetic_us":"/kwaɪt/","example":"I felt quite bitter about it at the time. 当时我对此感到相当痛苦。","phonetic_uk":"/kwaɪt/"},{"translation":"n. 智力竞赛，问答比赛；小测验；vt.  考查， 盘问","phonetic_us":"/kwɪz/","word":"quiz","phonetic_uk":"/kwɪz/","example":"a love quiz in a magazine 杂志上的爱情问答"},{"word":"quotation","phonetic_us":"/kwo'teʃən/","translation":"n. 引文","example":"The following quotation is taken from a nineteenth century travel diary. 下文引自19世纪的一篇旅行日记。","phonetic_uk":"/kwəʊˈteɪʃn/"},{"translation":"v. 引用，引证；报价","phonetic_us":"/kwot/","word":"quote","example":"He quoted a short passage from the Bible. 他引用了《圣经》里的一小段。","phonetic_uk":"/kwəʊt/"},{"word":"rabbit","phonetic_us":"/'ræbɪt/","translation":"n. 兔子，野兔","example":"The rabbit disappeared in the bushes. 那只兔子消失在树丛中。","phonetic_uk":"/'ræbɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/reɪs/","example":"The women's race was won by the only American in the field, Patti Sue Plumer. 女子赛跑被田赛场上惟一的一名美国人帕蒂·休·普卢默赢得了。","phonetic_us":"/res/","translation":"n. 比赛，竞赛，竞争","word":"race"},{"word":"racial","translation":"adj. 种族的，人种的","phonetic_us":"/'reʃl/","phonetic_uk":"/'reɪʃ(ə)l/","example":"a victim of racial discrimination 种族歧视的受害者"},{"translation":"adv. 种族上地","phonetic_us":"","word":"racially","example":"Mr. Obama is the first president since Richard M. Nixon to be elected while living in a city neighborhood, in his case, Chicago’s racially and economically diverse Hyde Park. 奥巴马是自理查德.尼克松总统以来第一位住在城市社区中当选的总统，奥巴马住在芝加哥种族和经济多元化的海德公园。","phonetic_uk":"/'reʃəli/"},{"word":"rack","phonetic_us":"/ræk/","translation":"n. 搁物架；行李架","phonetic_uk":"/ræk/","example":"a wine rack 酒架"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'reɪdɑː/","example":"The coastline can now be monitored by radar. 现在能用雷达监测海岸线了。","word":"radar","phonetic_us":"/'redɑr/","translation":"n. 雷达，无线电探测器"},{"example":"An accident at the power station could result in large amounts of radiation being released. 发电站事故会造成大量核辐射泄漏。","phonetic_uk":"/reɪdɪ'eɪʃ(ə)n/","phonetic_us":"/,redɪ'eʃən/","translation":"n. 放射，发射；辐射能","word":"radiation"},{"word":"radical","phonetic_us":"/'rædɪkl/","translation":"adv. 根本的，基本的；激进的，激进派的；n.  激进分子","example":"radicals on the extreme left wing of the party 党内极左翼激进分子","phonetic_uk":"/'rædɪkl/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'rædɪkli/","translation":"adv. 完全地，彻底地","word":"radically","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'rædɪklɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'reɪdɪəʊ/","example":"The last 12 months have been difficult ones for local radio. 最近的12个月对地方广播电台来说是艰难的。","word":"radio","phonetic_us":"/'redɪo/","translation":"n. 无线电；收音机"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,reɪdɪəʊ'æktɪv/","example":"the problem of how to dispose of radioactive waste 如何处理放射性废物的问题","translation":"adj. 放射性的","phonetic_us":"/'redɪo'æktɪv/","word":"radioactive"},{"example":"The shock of the explosion was felt over a radius of forty miles. 爆炸引起的剧烈震动在方圆40英里内都能感觉得到。","phonetic_uk":"/'reɪdɪəs/","word":"radius","phonetic_us":"/'redɪəs/","translation":"n. 半径"},{"word":"rag","translation":"n. 破布，碎布，抹布","phonetic_us":"/ræɡ/","phonetic_uk":"/ræg/","example":"He wiped his boots dry with an old rag. 他用一块旧布把他的靴子擦干。"},{"translation":"vi.  狂吹； 汹涌； 激烈进行； 发怒， 发火；n. 狂怒，盛怒；风靡一时的事物，时尚","phonetic_us":"/redʒ/","word":"rage","phonetic_uk":"/reɪdʒ/","example":"‘How was I to know!’ Jenny raged. “我怎么会知道！”珍妮怒道。"},{"example":"a bombing raid 轰炸","phonetic_uk":"/reɪd/","word":"raid","phonetic_us":"/red/","translation":"n&vt.  袭击； 突入查抄， 突入搜捕； 劫掠"},{"translation":"n. 横条，横杆；铁轨","phonetic_us":"/rel/","word":"rail","example":"Several passengers were leaning against the ship’s rail. 几名乘客斜靠在轮船的栏杆上。","phonetic_uk":"/reɪl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'reɪlrəʊd/","example":"The supplies were sent on the railroad. 补给经由铁路运送。","translation":"n. 铁路；v. 由铁路运输","phonetic_us":"/'relrod/","word":"railroad"},{"example":"a railway company 铁路公司","phonetic_uk":"/'reɪlweɪ/","word":"railway","translation":"n. 铁路，铁道","phonetic_us":"/'relwe/"},{"word":"rain","phonetic_us":"/reɪn/","translation":"n. 雨，雨水；v. 下雨","example":"a night of wind and rain 风雨交加的夜晚","phonetic_uk":"/reɪn/"},{"word":"rainbow","translation":"n. 虹，彩虹","phonetic_us":"/'renbo/","phonetic_uk":"/'reɪnbəʊ/","example":"...silk and satin in every shade of the rainbow. …如彩虹般五颜六色的丝绸与锦缎。"},{"translation":"adj. 下雨的，多雨的","phonetic_us":"/'reni/","word":"rainy","phonetic_uk":"/'reɪnɪ/","example":"a cold rainy day in October 十月里一个寒冷的雨天"},{"phonetic_us":"/rez/","translation":"v. 提高，筹款，抚养","word":"raise","phonetic_uk":"/reɪz/","example":"Many shops have raised their prices. 很多商店都提价了。"},{"word":"rally","translation":"v.  集合， 团结； 恢复， 重新振作；n. 集会；公路汽车赛","phonetic_us":"/'ræli/","example":"an attempt to rally support for the party 为政党争取支持的努力","phonetic_uk":"/'ræli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/reɪndʒ/","example":"a temperature range of 72-85˚ 72 度到85度之间的温度范围","word":"range","phonetic_us":"/rendʒ/","translation":"n. 范围；v. 在范围内变化"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ræŋk/","example":"We rank among the safest countries in the world. 我们是世界上最安全的国家之一。","phonetic_us":"/ræŋk/","translation":"v. 分等级；n. 衔，阶层","word":"rank"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ræpɪd/","translation":"adj. 快的；n. 急流","word":"rapid","phonetic_uk":"/'ræpɪd/","example":"The patient made a rapid recovery. 病人迅速康复。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/reə(r)/","example":"This species of plant is becoming increasingly rare. 这种植物越来越罕见。","translation":"adj. 罕有的，少见的","phonetic_us":"/rɛr/","word":"rare"},{"translation":"adv. 很少，难得","phonetic_us":"/'rɛrli/","word":"rarely","phonetic_uk":"/'reəlɪ/","example":"We rarely see someone go after the health area. 我们很少见到有人在健康领域做文章。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ræt/","example":"But you promised to help us, you rat! 可你答应过要帮我们的，你这小人！","word":"rat","translation":"n. 老鼠，耗子","phonetic_us":"/ræt/"},{"example":"Immediately his heart rate (= the number of beats per minute ) increased. 他的心率立即加快了。","phonetic_uk":"/reɪt/","word":"rate","translation":"n. 比率，速率","phonetic_us":"/ret/"},{"word":"rather","phonetic_us":"/'ræðɚ/","translation":"adv. 宁可，宁愿；相当","example":"I grew up in rather unusual circumstances. 我在相当不寻常的环境中长大。","phonetic_uk":"/'rɑːðə/"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'reɪʃɪəʊ/","phonetic_us":"/'reʃɪo/","translation":"n. 比，比率","word":"ratio"},{"example":"Did he come across as a sane, rational person? 他看上去是不是一个头脑清醒而理智的人？","phonetic_uk":"/'ræʃnəl/","word":"rational","phonetic_us":"/'ræʃnəl/","translation":"adj. 神智清楚的"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɔ/","translation":"adj. 未煮过的；未加工的","word":"raw","phonetic_uk":"/rɔː/","example":"raw meat 生肉"},{"word":"ray","translation":"n. 光线，射线，辐射线","phonetic_us":"","phonetic_uk":"","example":"The room darkened as a cloud hid the sun’s rays. 一朵云挡住了阳光，房间暗了下来。"},{"example":"Chelsea could reach the final of the European Cup. 切尔西队会进入欧洲杯决赛。","phonetic_uk":"/riːtʃ/","word":"reach","translation":"v. 抵达；伸出vi达到","phonetic_us":"/ritʃ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ri'ækt/","translation":"v. 对……作出反应","word":"react","phonetic_uk":"/riˈækt/","example":"He reacted angrily to the suggestion that he had lied. 说他撒谎，他非常生气。"},{"translation":"n. 反应；反作用","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'ækʃən/","word":"reaction","example":"What was Jeff’s reaction when you told him about the job? 你告诉杰夫这个工作时，他是什么反应？","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'ækʃ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/riːd; (read, read) red/","example":"I can’t read your writing. 我看不懂你写的东西。","word":"read","translation":"v. 读，看懂；v. 读","phonetic_us":"/rid; (read, read) rɛd/"},{"translation":"n. 读者；读物，读本","phonetic_us":"/'ridɚ/","word":"reader","example":"The book will appeal to young readers. 这本书会吸引年轻读者。","phonetic_uk":"/'riːdə/"},{"example":"Boats are readily available to visitors. 游客可以很方便地租到船只。","phonetic_uk":"/'redɪli/","phonetic_us":"/'rɛdɪli/","translation":"adv.  乐意地， 欣然地； 容易地； 很快地， 立即","word":"readily"},{"word":"reading","translation":"n. 读，阅读；读书","phonetic_us":"/'ridɪŋ/","example":"She loves reading. 她喜欢看书。","phonetic_uk":"/'riːdɪŋ/"},{"example":"Come on. Aren’t you ready yet? 快点，你还没准备好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'redɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'rɛdi/","translation":"adj. 准备好的；愿意的","word":"ready"},{"example":"There is a real danger that the disease might spread. 这种疾病确实有蔓延的危险。","phonetic_uk":"/riːl/","translation":"adj. 真的；现实的","phonetic_us":"/'riəl/","word":"real"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:əˈlɪstɪk/","example":"Is this a realistic target? 这个目标能够实现吗？","word":"realistic","translation":"adj. 现实的，实际的","phonetic_us":"/,riə'lɪstɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'æləti/","translation":"n. 现实；真实","word":"reality","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'ælɪtɪ/","example":"the distinction between fantasy and reality 幻想和现实之间的区别"},{"word":"realize","translation":"v. 实现；认识到","phonetic_us":"/rɪəˌlaɪz/","phonetic_uk":"/'riːəlaɪz/","example":"It took us a while to realize the extent of the tragedy. 我们过了一段时间才意识到这场悲剧有多严重。"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"","word":"really","translation":"adv. 真正地；实在","phonetic_us":""},{"translation":"n. 王国，国土；领域","phonetic_us":"/rɛlm/","word":"realm","phonetic_uk":"/relm/","example":"the spiritual realm 精神领域"},{"word":"rear","phonetic_us":"/rɪr/","translation":"n. 后部，后面；背面","example":"Carole was left to bring up the rear. 卡萝尔被落在最后。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪə/"},{"word":"rearrange","translation":"v. 重新安排","phonetic_us":"/,riə'rendʒ/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:ə'reɪndʒ/","example":"She set about rearranging the furniture in the living room. 她开始重新摆放起居室的家具。"},{"word":"reason","translation":"n. 理由；理性；v. 推理","phonetic_us":"/ˈrizən/","example":"She has reason to feel guilty. 她有理由感到内疚。","phonetic_uk":"/'riːz(ə)n/"},{"example":"a reasonable request 合情合理的要求","phonetic_uk":"/'riːz(ə)nəb(ə)l/","word":"reasonable","translation":"adj. 合情合理的；公道的","phonetic_us":"/'riznəbl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:əˈses/","example":"This has caused us to reassess the way we approach our planning. 这件事让我们重新审视了我们的规划方式。","word":"reassess","translation":"v. 重新评估","phonetic_us":"/'riə'sɛs/"},{"word":"rebel","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'bɛl/","translation":"v. 造反；n. 造反者","example":"Voters rebelled against high property taxes. 投票者们反对高额财产税。","phonetic_uk":"/'reb(ə)l/"},{"translation":"v.  重建， 改造； 复原","phonetic_us":"/,ri'bɪld/","word":"rebuild","example":"The church was completely rebuilt in the last century. 这座教堂在上个世纪全面重建。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌriː'bɪld/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'kɔːl/","example":"You don’t happen to recall his name, do you? 你不会恰巧还想得起他的名字吧？","word":"recall","translation":"v. 回想；叫回；收回","phonetic_us":"/'rikɔl/"},{"example":"Keep your receipt in case you want to bring it back. 保留收据以备退货之需。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'siːt/","word":"receipt","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'sit/","translation":"n. 收到；收条，收据"},{"word":"receive","translation":"v. 收到；得到；接待","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'siv/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'siːv/","example":"All the children will receive a small gift. 每个孩子都会收到一份小礼物。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'siːvə/","example":"The business is in the hands of the receivers . 公司现在由破产管理人接管。","translation":"n. 收受者，收件人","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'sivɚ/","word":"receiver"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'riːs(ə)nt/","example":"Irving’s most recent book 欧文最新的书","word":"recent","phonetic_us":"/'risnt/","translation":"adj. 新近的，最近的"},{"word":"recently","translation":"adv. 最近，新近","phonetic_us":"/'risntli/","example":"He has recently been promoted to Assistant Manager. 他最近晋升为经理助理。","phonetic_uk":"/'riːsntlɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈsepʃn/","example":"She was unsure of her reception after everything that had happened. 发生了这些事后，她对自己是否还受欢迎没把握。","word":"reception","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'sɛpʃən/","translation":"n. 接待"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'sɛʃən/","translation":"n. 衰退","word":"recession","phonetic_uk":"/ri'seʃən/","example":"the economic recession of the early 1980s 20世纪80年代初的经济衰退"},{"example":"The device can recharge a battery in about 25 minutes. 该充电器可在约25分钟内完成给电池充电。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:'tʃɑ:dʒ/","word":"recharge","phonetic_us":"/ri:'tʃɑ:dʒ, 'ri:tʃɑ:dʒ/","translation":"v. 再充电"},{"example":"‘There’s nothing we can do about it.’ ‘You reckon (= used to express doubt or disagreement ) ?’ “这件事我们无能为力。”“是吗？”","phonetic_uk":"/'rekən/","phonetic_us":"/'rɛkən/","translation":"vt.  认为， 估计； 指望， 盼望； 测算， 测量","word":"reckon"},{"translation":"n. 认出，识别；承认","phonetic_us":"/,rɛkəɡ'nɪʃən/","word":"recognition","example":"He stared at her, but there was no sign of recognition . 他盯着她看，但似乎没认出她来。","phonetic_uk":"/rekəg'nɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"word":"recognize","translation":"v. 认识，认出；承认","phonetic_us":"/ˈrɛkəɡˌnaɪz/","phonetic_uk":"/'rekəɡnaɪz/","example":"I didn’t recognize you in your uniform. 你穿上制服我认不出你了。"},{"translation":"v. 推荐，劝告，使受欢迎","phonetic_us":"/'rɛkə'mɛnd/","word":"recommend","example":"Doctors strongly recommend that fathers should be present at their baby’s birth. 医生极力建议孩子出生时父亲应该在场。","phonetic_uk":"/,rekə'mend/"},{"example":"Try to get letters of recommendation from bosses and colleagues. 设法得到老板和同事的推荐信。","phonetic_uk":"/,rekəmen'deɪʃ(ə)n/","word":"recommendation","phonetic_us":"/,rɛkəmɛn'deʃən/","translation":"n. 推荐，介绍；劝告"},{"phonetic_uk":"/(for v.)rɪˈkɔːd; (for n.) ˈrekɔːd/","example":"According to official records, five people were killed last year near that road junction. 据官方记录，去年有五人在那个路口附近丧生。","translation":"n. 记录；履历；v. 记录","phonetic_us":"/(for v.) rɪˈkɔrd; (for n. adj.) ˈrɛkɚd/","word":"record"},{"word":"recorder","translation":"n. 记录者；录音机","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'kɔrdɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'kɔːdə/","example":"Rodney put the recorder on the desk top and pushed the play button. 罗德尼把录音机放在桌面上，按下了播放键。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'kʌvə(r)/","example":"After a few days of fever, she began to recover. 发烧几天之后，她开始恢复。","word":"recover","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'kʌvɚ/","translation":"v. 恢复，重新获得"},{"word":"recovery","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 重获；痊愈，恢复","phonetic_uk":"","example":"Hopes of economic recovery are fading. 经济复苏的希望越来越渺茫。"},{"word":"recreation","translation":"n.  娱乐活动， 消遣","phonetic_us":"/,rɛkrɪ'eʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/ˌrekri'eɪʃn/","example":"His only recreations are drinking beer and watching football. 他唯一的消遣就是喝啤酒和看足球比赛。"},{"translation":"adj.  休养的； 娱乐的","phonetic_us":"/,rɛkri'eʃənəl/","word":"recreational","phonetic_uk":"/ˌrekri'eɪʃənl/","example":"...parks and other recreational facilities. …公园及其它娱乐设施。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'krut/","translation":"v. 招募，吸收；n. 新兵，新成员","word":"recruit","phonetic_uk":"/rikru:t/","example":"We’re having difficulty recruiting enough qualified staff. 我们难以招聘到足够的合格职员。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ri'saɪkl/","translation":"v. 循环，再利用","word":"recycle","phonetic_uk":"/riː'saɪk(ə)l/","example":"We take all our bottles to be recycled. 我们把我们所有的瓶子都回收利用。"},{"word":"red","phonetic_us":"/rɛd/","translation":"adj. 红色的；n. 红色","phonetic_uk":"/red/","example":"We painted the door bright red . 我们把门漆成鲜红色。"},{"word":"reduce","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'dʊs/","translation":"v. 减少","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'djuːs/","example":"The governor announced a new plan to reduce crime. 州长宣布了一项降低犯罪率的新计划。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'dʌkʃən/","translation":"n. 减少，减小，缩减","word":"reduction","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'dʌkʃ(ə)n/","example":"strategies for noise reduction 减少噪音的对策"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'fɜː/","example":"In his speech, he referred to a recent trip to Canada. 在他的讲话中，他提到了最近的加拿大之行。","word":"refer","translation":"v. 使求助于；v. 谈到","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'fɝ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ref(ə)r(ə)ns/","example":"...a reference from the Koran. …一段《可兰经》的引文。","word":"reference","translation":"n. 参考；出处；提及","phonetic_us":"/'rɛfrəns/"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'faɪn/","translation":"v. 改善，精炼","word":"refine","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈfaɪn/","example":"Car makers are constantly refining their designs. 汽车制造商在不断完善他们的设计。"},{"word":"reflect","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'flɛkt/","translation":"v. 反映","example":"The drop in consumer spending reflects concern about the economy. 消费支出的下降反映出人们对经济的担忧。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'flekt/"},{"translation":"n. 反射；映象；反映","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'flɛkʃən/","word":"reflection","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'flekʃ(ə)n/","example":"Can you see your reflection in the glass? 你能看到玻璃里你的影像吗？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'flekʃ(ə)n/","example":"Maxwell equations: Lorentz force, plane electromagnetic waves, radiation, light waves, reflexion, refraction, Huyghens principle, diffraction, interference phenomena. 麦克斯韦方程组：洛仑兹力，平面电磁波，辐射，光波，反射，折射，惠更斯原理，衍射，干涉现象。","word":"reflexion","translation":"n. 反射；映象；反映","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'flɛkʃən/"},{"word":"reform","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'fɔrm/","translation":"vt&n. 改革，改良","example":"plans to radically reform the tax system 彻底改革税收制度的计划","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'fɔːm/"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"v. 重新装裱","word":"reframe","example":"How could you reframe them? 你将如何重新定义它们？","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'freɪm/"},{"example":"A shower will refresh you. 洗个淋浴你就凉快了。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'freʃ/","word":"refresh","translation":"v. 使清新vi恢复精神","phonetic_us":"/ri'frɛʃ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'freʃɪŋ/","example":"Herbs have been used for centuries to make refreshing drinks. 草药用于调制清凉饮料已有几百年的历史了。","phonetic_us":"/ri'frɛʃɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 恢复活力的","word":"refreshing"},{"word":"refrigerator","translation":"n. 冰箱，冷藏库","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'frɪdʒəretɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'frɪdʒəreɪtə/","example":""},{"example":"The plane was refuelled in Dubai. 飞机在迪拜加过油。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:'fju:əl/","phonetic_us":"/ri'fjʊəl/","translation":"v. （给）加油，加燃料","word":"refuel"},{"phonetic_us":"/'rɛfjʊdʒi/","translation":"n.  难民","word":"refugee","phonetic_uk":"/ˌrefju'dʒiː/","example":"Refugees were streaming across the border. 难民正涌过边境。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈfju:zl/","example":"Her country suffered through her refusal to accept change. 她的国家因为她拒绝接受变革而受了害。","word":"refusal","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'fjuzl/","translation":"n. 拒绝"},{"phonetic_us":"/ri'fjʊz/","translation":"v. 拒绝；v. 拒绝","word":"refuse","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'fjuːz/","example":"She asked him to leave, but he refused. 她叫他走，但他不肯。"},{"example":"He was regarded as the most successful president of modern times. 他被看成是近代最成功的总统。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'gɑːd/","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'ɡɑrd/","translation":"v. 把…看作；尊敬","word":"regard"},{"word":"regarding","translation":"prep. 关于","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'ɡɑrdɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'gɑːdɪŋ/","example":"Regarding your recent inquiry, I have enclosed a copy of our new brochure. 关于你最近的咨询，我随信附上一本我们最新的手册。"},{"translation":"adv. 不顾一切地","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'ɡɑrdləs/","word":"regardless","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'gɑːdlɪs/","example":"Despite her recent surgery she has been carrying on regardless. 尽管她最近动了手术，她却一直在不顾一切地继续工作。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'riːdʒ(ə)n/","example":"efforts to bring peace to the region 给这个地区带来和平的努力","word":"region","translation":"n. 地区，地带；领域","phonetic_us":"/'ridʒən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'redʒɪstə/","example":"Have you signed the hotel register ? 你在酒店登记簿上签名了吗？","translation":"n&vt. 登记，注册","phonetic_us":"/'rɛdʒɪstɚ/","word":"register"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'gret/","example":"We regret any inconvenience caused to our customers. 我们对于给顾客造成的不便表示歉意。","word":"regret","translation":"v. 懊悔；抱歉；n. 懊悔","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'ɡrɛt/"},{"word":"regular","translation":"adj. 有规律的，经常的","phonetic_us":"/'rɛgjəlɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈregjələ(r)/","example":"The company holds regular meetings with employees. 公司定期召集雇员开会。"},{"word":"regularly","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adv. 定期地，有规律地","phonetic_uk":"/'reɡjələli/","example":"We meet regularly, once a month. 我们定期见面，每月一次。"},{"example":"strict rules regulating the use of chemicals in food 限制化学品在食物中使用的严格规定","phonetic_uk":"/'reɡjʊleɪt/","translation":"v. 管理","phonetic_us":"/'rɛɡjulet/","word":"regulate"},{"example":"There seem to be so many rules and regulations these days. 如今好像条条框框很多。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌregjuˈleɪʃn/","word":"regulation","translation":"n. 管理；规则","phonetic_us":"/ˌrɛɡjəˈleʃən/"},{"example":"The film reinforces the idea that women should be pretty and dumb. 这部影片强化了这个观点——女人要漂亮，而且要笨一些。","phonetic_uk":"/riːɪn'fɔːs/","word":"reinforce","phonetic_us":"/,riɪn'fɔrs/","translation":"v. 加强，强化"},{"translation":"v. 拒绝，驳回","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'dʒɛkt/","word":"reject","example":"Sarah rejected her brother’s offer of help. 萨拉拒绝了她弟弟的帮助。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'dʒekt/"},{"example":"I don’t understand how the two ideas relate. 我不明白这两个观点有什么联系。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'leɪt/","translation":"v. 叙述；使联系","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'let/","word":"relate"},{"example":"The price the meat is sold for bears no relation to (= is not connected to ) the price the farmer receives. 肉的售价和农民拿到的价格无关。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'leɪʃ(ə)n/","translation":"n. 关系，联系；家属","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'leʃən/","word":"relation"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'leɪʃ(ə)nʃɪp/","example":"He’s never had a sexual relationship before. 他以前从未与人有过性关系。","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'leʃən'ʃɪp/","translation":"n. 关系，联系","word":"relationship"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈrelətɪv/","example":"The relative merits of both approaches have to be considered. 两种方法的相对优点都得考虑在内。","word":"relative","phonetic_us":"/'rɛlətɪv/","translation":"adj. 相对的；n. 亲戚"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/relə'tɪvɪtɪ/","word":"relativity","translation":"n. 相关性；相对性","phonetic_us":"/,rɛlə'tɪvəti/"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'læks/","translation":"v. 使松弛；v. 松弛","word":"relax","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'læks/","example":"Gentle exercise can relax stiff shoulder muscles. 和缓的运动可以使僵硬的肩部肌肉放松。"},{"word":"release","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'lis/","translation":"v. 发布，释放","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'li:s/","example":"Police arrested several men, who were later released. 警察逮捕了几个人，后来都释放了。"},{"example":"Relevant documents were presented in court. 法庭上出示了相关的文件。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈreləvənt/","word":"relevant","translation":"adj. 有关的，中肯的","phonetic_us":"/'rɛləvənt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ,laɪə'bɪlətɪ/","example":"I can assure you of the reliability of the information. 我可以向你保证这消息是可靠的。","translation":"n. 可靠性","phonetic_us":"/rɪ,laɪə'bɪləti/","word":"reliability"},{"word":"reliable","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'laɪəbl/","translation":"adj. 可靠的，可信赖的","example":"a birth control method that is cheap and reliable 既便宜又可靠的避孕方法","phonetic_uk":"/ri'laiəbl/"},{"example":"Marijuana can provide pain relief for some cancer patients. 大麻可以为一些癌症患者减轻疼痛。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'liːf/","translation":"n. 减轻；救济；援救","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'lif/","word":"relief"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'li:v/","example":"Drugs helped to relieve the pain. 药物有助于舒缓疼痛。","word":"relieve","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'liv/","translation":"v. 解除，减轻，缓解"},{"word":"religion","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'lɪdʒən/","translation":"n. 宗教；宗教信仰","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'lɪdʒ(ə)n/","example":"The U.S. Constitution promises freedom of religion. 美国宪法保证宗教信仰自由。"},{"translation":"adj. 宗教的；虔诚的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'lɪdʒəs/","word":"religious","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'lɪdʒəs/","example":"I don’t share her religious beliefs . 她的宗教信仰和我的不同。"},{"example":"She gave a reluctant smile. 她勉强笑了笑。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈlʌktənt/","translation":"adj. 不愿意的，勉强的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'lʌktənt/","word":"reluctant"},{"translation":"v. 依赖，依靠；信赖","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'laɪ/","word":"rely","example":"They relied heavily on the advice of their professional advisers. 他们非常依赖专业顾问的建议。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'laɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'meɪn/","example":"The refugees were allowed to remain in the UK. 难民获准留在英国。","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'men/","translation":"v. 剩下，余留；保持","word":"remain"},{"word":"remark","translation":"vt&vi&n. 评论，谈论","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'mɑrk/","example":"Unfortunately, a local journalist overheard the remark. 不巧一名当地记者无意中听到了这些话。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'mɑːk/"},{"word":"remarkable","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'mɑrkəbl/","translation":"adj. 异常的，非凡的","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'mɑːkəb(ə)l/","example":"She has made remarkable progress. 她取得了显著的进步。"},{"word":"remedy","phonetic_us":"/'rɛmədi/","translation":"n. 药物","phonetic_uk":"/'remədɪ/","example":"a home remedy (= one that you make at home ) for sore throats 治疗喉咙疼痛的家庭疗法"},{"example":"Do you remember Rosa Davies? 你记得罗莎·戴维斯吗？","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'membə/","translation":"v. 记得，想起；记住","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'mɛmbɚ/","word":"remember"},{"word":"remind","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'maɪnd/","translation":"v. 提醒，使想起","example":"Yes, I’ll be there. Thanks for reminding me. 是的，我会去那里的。 谢谢提醒。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'maɪnd/"},{"example":"He remonstrated with the referee. 他曾向裁判抗议。","phonetic_uk":"/'remənstreɪt/","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'mɑnstret/","translation":"v.  抗议","word":"remonstrate"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'məʊt/","example":"a remote border town 一个偏远的边境小镇","word":"remote","translation":"adj. 相隔很远的；冷淡的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'mot/"},{"example":"stain removal 去污","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'muːv(ə)l/","translation":"n. 移动；迁移；除掉","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'muvl/","word":"removal"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'muv/","translation":"v. 消除，移除","word":"remove","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈmu:v/","example":"a cleaner that will remove wine stains 可去除葡萄酒酒渍的清洁剂"},{"word":"render","phonetic_us":"/'rɛndɚ/","translation":"v. 给予","example":"an obligation to render assistance to those in need 为有困难的人提供援助的义务","phonetic_uk":"/'rendə(r)/"},{"word":"renew","translation":"v. 更新","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'nʊ/","example":"Local people have renewed their efforts to save the school. 当地居民再一次作出努力，挽救这所学校。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'nju:/"},{"example":"I pay the rent at the beginning of every month. 我每逢月初交付房租。","phonetic_uk":"/rent/","word":"rent","translation":"n. 租金，租；v. 出租","phonetic_us":"/rɛnt/"},{"word":"rental","phonetic_us":"/'rɛntl/","translation":"n. 租","phonetic_uk":"/'rent(ə)l/","example":"Video rental is usually £3. 录像带的租金通常是3英镑。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'peə/","example":"Dad was up the ladder, repairing the roof. 爸爸在梯子上修补屋顶。","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'pɛr/","translation":"vt&n. 修理，修补","word":"repair"},{"word":"repave","phonetic_us":"","translation":"v. 再铺，重新铺砌","phonetic_uk":"/ri:'peɪv/","example":"Therefore, lots of pavements need to repair in large. scale even repave wholly after using a long time, which will bring large numbers of waste asphalt mixture. 因此，沥青路面使用一定年限后必须进行大面积的维修，甚至全路段铣刨，重新铺筑。"},{"example":"Can you repeat your question? 你能重复一遍你的问题吗？","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'piːt/","word":"repeat","translation":"v. 重说，重做；n. 重复","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'pit/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'piːtɪdlɪ/","example":"Graham was repeatedly warned not to work so hard. 格雷厄姆一再被提醒工作不要这么拼命。","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'pitɪdli/","translation":"adv. 重复地；一再","word":"repeatedly"},{"word":"repetition","phonetic_us":"/'rɛpə'tɪʃən/","translation":"n. 重复，反复","phonetic_uk":"/repɪ'tɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Children used to learn by repetition. 过去小孩子是通过背诵来学习的。"},{"word":"replace","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'ples/","translation":"v. 代替","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'pleɪs/","example":"I’m replacing Sue on the team. 我将接替队里的休。"},{"word":"replacement","translation":"n. 代替","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'plesmənt/","example":"Our old car is badly in need of replacement. 我们的旧车急需更换。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈpleɪsmənt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'plaɪ/","example":"I asked Clive where he was going, but he didn’t reply. 我问克莱夫到哪儿去，但他没有回答。","word":"reply","translation":"vi&n. 回答，答复","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'plai/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'pɔːt/","example":"This is Gavin Williams, reporting from the United Nations in New York. 我是加文·威廉斯，在纽约联合国总部为您报道。","word":"report","translation":"vt&vi. 报告；汇报","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'pɔrt/"},{"translation":"n. 记者，通讯员","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'pɔrtɚ/","word":"reporter","example":"a news reporter 新闻记者","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'pɔːtə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌreprɪ'zent/","example":"Mr Kobayashi was chosen to represent the company at the conference. 小林先生被选中代表公司出席会议。","phonetic_us":"/,rɛprɪ'zɛnt/","translation":"v. 代表","word":"represent"},{"word":"representative","phonetic_us":"/'rɛprɪ'zɛntətɪv/","translation":"n. 代表","example":"a union representative 工会代表","phonetic_uk":"/ˌreprɪˈzentətɪv/"},{"word":"reproduce","phonetic_us":"/,riprə'dus/","translation":"v. 复制, 再生","phonetic_uk":"/riːprə'djuːs/","example":"Klimt’s artwork is reproduced in this exquisite book. 这本精美的书里翻印了克里木特的艺术作品。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:prəˈdʌktɪv/","example":"the human reproductive system 人类生殖系统","phonetic_us":"/,riprə'dʌktɪv/","translation":"adj. 生殖的，再生的","word":"reproductive"},{"example":"the former Federal Republic of Germany 前德意志联邦共和国","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'pʌblɪk/","translation":"n. 共和国，共和政体","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'pʌblɪk/","word":"republic"},{"example":"Lower taxes made Republican voters happier with their party. 更低的税率使共和党选民对该党更加满意。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'pʌblɪkən/","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'pʌblɪkən/","translation":"adj. 共和政体的；共和党的；n.  共和党人","word":"republican"},{"example":"Alice Munro has a reputation for being a very depressing writer. 艾丽斯•门罗有文风抑郁的名声。","phonetic_uk":"/,repju'teiʃən/","word":"reputation","translation":"n. 名气，名声，名誉","phonetic_us":"/,rɛpju'teʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'kwest/","example":"France had agreed to his request for political asylum. 法国已经同意了他政治避难的请求。","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'kwɛst/","translation":"n. 要求","word":"request"},{"word":"require","translation":"v. 要求，命令","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'kwaɪr/","phonetic_uk":"/ri'kwaiə/","example":"Campbell’s broken leg will probably require surgery. 坎贝尔的一条腿骨折，可能需要手术。"},{"example":"The refugees’ main requirements are food and shelter. 难民的主要需求是食物和住所。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'kwaɪəm(ə)nt/","word":"requirement","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'kwaɪɚmənt/","translation":"n. 需要；要求"},{"phonetic_us":"/'rɛskju/","translation":"v. 营救，援救","word":"rescue","phonetic_uk":"/'reskju:/","example":"Survivors of the crash were rescued by helicopter. 空难的生还者被直升机救了出来。"},{"example":"It’s amazing how closely Brian and Steve resemble each other. 布赖恩和史蒂夫真是惊人地相像。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zemb(ə)l/","translation":"v. 像，相似","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zɛmbl/","word":"resemble"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌrezə'veɪʃn/","example":"a dinner reservation 预订晚餐","word":"reservation","translation":"n. 预定","phonetic_us":"/,rɛzɚ'veʃən/"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zɝv/","translation":"v. 留出，预定","word":"reserve","example":"Do you have to reserve tickets in advance? 你必须预先订票吗？","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zɜːv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"","word":"reservior","translation":"n. 水库；蓄水池","phonetic_us":""},{"translation":"n.  水库， 蓄水池； 储藏， 汇集","phonetic_us":"/'rɛzɚ,vɔr/","word":"reservoir","phonetic_uk":"/'rezəvwɑː/","example":""},{"example":"a residence permit 居留许可证","phonetic_uk":"/'rezɪd(ə)ns/","translation":"n. 居住；驻扎；住处","phonetic_us":"/'rɛzɪdəns/","word":"residence"},{"word":"resident","translation":"n. 居民","phonetic_us":"/'rɛzɪdənt/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈrezɪdənt/","example":"As one local resident put it in May, \"By day there is government. 正如一位当地居民在五月份对它的描述”白天有政府。"},{"translation":"v. 辞职","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zaɪn/","word":"resign","phonetic_uk":"/ri'zain/","example":"A hospital administrator has resigned over claims he lied to get the job. 一位医院主管因为有人声称他的职位是骗来的而辞职了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zɪst/","translation":"v. 抵抗，抗拒","word":"resist","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zɪst/","example":"He resisted pressure to resign. 他顶住压力，没辞职。"},{"example":"disease resistance 抗病能力","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zɪst(ə)ns/","word":"resistance","translation":"n. 抵制, 抵抗力","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zɪstəns/"},{"word":"resistant","translation":"adj. 抵抗的，抵制的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zɪstənt/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zɪstənt/","example":"Some people are very resistant to the idea of exercise. 一些人对锻炼的主意非常抵制。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rezə'luːʃ(ə)n/","example":"a resolution calling for a ban on dumping nuclear waste 要求禁止倾倒核废物的决议","word":"resolution","translation":"n. 坚决，坚定；决定","phonetic_us":"/,rɛzə'luʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zɒlv/","example":"Barnet was desperate for money to resolve his financial problems. 巴尼特急需钱来解决他的经济问题。","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zɑlv/","translation":"v. 解决，下决心","word":"resolve"},{"translation":"vi&n. 求助，凭借;诉诸于","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zɔrt/","word":"resort","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zɔːt/","example":"His punishing work schedule had made him resort to drugs. 他那累人的工作日程已经使他不得不求助于毒品了。"},{"translation":"n.  资源； 财力； 应付办法， 谋略","phonetic_us":"/'risɔrs/","word":"resource","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'sɔːs; rɪ'zɔːs/","example":"Canada’s vast mineral resources 加拿大丰富的矿产资源"},{"word":"resourceful","translation":"adj. 机智的；资源丰富的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'sɔrsfl/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'sɔːsfl/","example":"a woman who is energetic and resourceful 精力充沛且足智多谋的女人"},{"word":"respect","translation":"n. 尊敬；尊重；问候；方面；vt.  尊敬； 尊重","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɛkt/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'spekt/","example":"The boys showed a complete lack of respect for authority. 这些男孩子根本无视权威。"},{"word":"respectful","translation":"adj. 有礼貌的，尊重的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɛktfəl/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈspektfl/","example":"They listened in respectful silence. 他们毕恭毕敬地静听。"},{"example":"We all went back to our respective homes to wait for news. 我们都各自回家等待消息。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'spektɪv/","word":"respective","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɛktɪv/","translation":"adj. 各自的，各个的"},{"word":"respectively","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɛktɪvli/","translation":"adv. 各自地","example":"The cups and saucers cost £5 and £3 respectively. 茶杯和茶碟的价钱分别为5英镑和3英镑。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'spɛktɪvli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'spɒnd/","example":"They are likely to respond positively to the president's request for aid. 他们有可能积极地回应该总统的援助请求。","word":"respond","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɑnd/","translation":"v. 作答；响应"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'spɒndənt/","example":"Only 62 percent of respondents said they were satisfied. 回复调查的人中只有62%表示满意。","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɑndənt/","translation":"n.  回答者； 响应者； 被告","word":"respondent"},{"word":"response","translation":"n. 反应","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɑns/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈspɒns/","example":"His immediate response was one of disbelief. 他的第一反应是不相信。"},{"example":"Kelly’s promotion means more money and more responsibility. 凯利获得提升，这意味着钱多了，责任也更大了。","phonetic_uk":"/ri,spɔnsə'biliti/","word":"responsibility","phonetic_us":"/rɪˌspɑːnsəˈbɪləti/","translation":"n. 责任"},{"translation":"adj. 负责的，有责任的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɑnsəbl/","word":"responsible","example":"We are determined to bring the people responsible to justice. 我们决意要将肇事者绳之以法。","phonetic_uk":"/ri'spɔnsəbl/"},{"translation":"adj.  响应的； 敏感的， 易受影响的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'spɑnsɪv/","word":"responsive","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'spɒnsɪv/","example":"a car with highly responsive steering 方向盘操纵灵活的汽车"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈrestləs/","example":"After a few weeks in Marseille, I grew restless and decided to move on. 在马赛住了几星期后，我开始待不住了，决定换个地方。","translation":"adj. 不安定的，焦虑的","phonetic_us":"/'rɛstləs/","word":"restless"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:'stɒk/","example":"I have to restock the freezer. 我得补充冷冻柜里的东西了。","translation":"v. 重新进货，再储存","phonetic_us":"","word":"restock"},{"word":"restore","translation":"v. 修复","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'stɔr/","example":"She was hoping that the Mediterranean climate would restore her to full health. 她希望地中海的气候能使她的身体完全复原。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'stɔ:(r)/"},{"translation":"v. 抑制，遏制；限制","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'stren/","word":"restrain","example":"Renwick restrained a feeling of annoyance. 伦威克忍住了不悦的情绪。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'streɪn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'strent/","translation":"n. 抑制；遏制；克制","word":"restraint","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'streɪnt/","example":"The police were praised for their restraint in handling the demonstrators. 警方因对待示威者时所表现出的克制而受到赞扬。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'strɪkt/","translation":"v. 限制，限定","word":"restrict","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'strɪkt/","example":"The new law restricts the sale of hand guns. 新法规限制手枪的销售。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'strɪkʃən/","translation":"n. 限制，限定","word":"restriction","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'strɪkʃn/","example":"a 50 mph speed restriction 每小时50英里的限速"},{"example":"How would you cope with unemployment and the resulting loss of income? 你会如何应付失业及由此造成的收入损失？","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'zʌlt/","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'zʌlt/","translation":"vi.  发生； 结果；n. 结果；成果；比分","word":"result"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈzjuːm; ˈrɛzjʊmeɪ/","example":"Peace talks will resume tomorrow. 和平谈判明天重新启动。","word":"resume","phonetic_us":"","translation":"v. 恢复；重新开始"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ri:teɪl/","example":"a retail price of £8.99 8.99英镑的零售价","translation":"v & n. 零售","phonetic_us":"/'ritel/","word":"retail"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'riːteɪlə/","example":"Furniture and carpet retailers are among those reporting the sharpest annual decline in sales. 家具和地毯零售商们是在那些报告最大年销售下滑的商家之中。","translation":"n. 零售商","phonetic_us":"/'ri:teilə/","word":"retailer"},{"word":"retain","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'ten/","translation":"v. 保留,留用","example":"You have the right to retain possession of the goods. 你有权保留这些物品。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'teɪn/"},{"example":"At the age when most people retire, he is ready to face a new career. 在大多数人退休的年纪，他准备要面对一项新事业。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'taɪə/","word":"retire","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'taɪɚ/","translation":"v. 退下；引退；就寝"},{"example":"She took early retirement (= retired at an earlier age than usual ) last year. 她去年提前退休了。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈtaɪəmənt/","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'taɪɚmənt/","translation":"n. 退休","word":"retirement"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"v. 再教育；再训练","word":"retrain","phonetic_uk":"/ˌri:ˈtreɪn/","example":"One solution is to retrain the long-term unemployed. 一个解决办法是对长期失业的人进行再培训。"},{"word":"retreat","translation":"v. 退避，后退","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'trit/","example":"The rebels retreated to the mountains. 叛乱分子撤退到山区。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪˈtri:t/"},{"example":"He may be prosecuted for revealing secrets about the security agency. 他可能因泄露安全部门的机密而被起诉。","phonetic_uk":"/ri'vi:l/","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'vil/","translation":"v. 揭露，揭示","word":"reveal"},{"example":"The attackers were said to be taking revenge on the 14-year-old, claiming he was a school bully. 攻击者被称是在报复一名14岁男孩，称他是学校一霸。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'vendʒ/","translation":"n. 报仇","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'vɛndʒ/","word":"revenge"},{"example":"advertising revenue 广告收入","phonetic_uk":"/'revənju:/","word":"revenue","translation":"n. 收入","phonetic_us":"/'rɛvənu/"},{"word":"reverse","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'vɝs/","translation":"a & n. （使）反转","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'vɜ:s/","example":"I owe you nothing. If anything, the reverse is true (= you owe me ) . 我不欠你什么。 如果说欠的话，是你欠我才对。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'vjuː/","example":"a journalist who will review the events of the past six months 将对过去六个月里所发生的事件进行回顾的记者","word":"review","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'vju/","translation":"n&v. 回顾；复习"},{"translation":"v. 修订","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'vaɪz/","word":"revise","example":"The college has revised its plans because of local objections. 由于地方上的反对，学院已经修改了计划。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'vaɪz/"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪ'volt/","translation":"vi&n. 反抗，造反","word":"revolt","example":"The prime minister is now facing a revolt by members of his own party. 首相现在面临着党内倒戈。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'vəʊlt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌrevə'lu:ʃn/","example":"the French Revolution of 1789 1789年法国大革命","word":"revolution","phonetic_us":"/'rɛvə'lʊʃən/","translation":"n. 革命"},{"word":"revolutionary","phonetic_us":"/'rɛvə'lʊʃə'nɛri/","translation":"adj. 革命的；n. 革命者","example":"The new cancer drug is a revolutionary breakthrough. 这种抗癌新药是一个革命性突破。","phonetic_uk":"/revə'luːʃ(ə)n(ə)rɪ/"},{"word":"reward","translation":"n & v. 报答，奖赏","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'wɔrd/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'wɔ:d/","example":"The school has a system of rewards and punishments to encourage good behaviour. 学校有奖惩制度以鼓励良好行为。"},{"word":"rhythm","translation":"n. 韵律，格律；节奏","phonetic_us":"/'rɪðəm/","phonetic_uk":"/'rɪð(ə)m/","example":"Drums are basic to African rhythm. 非洲音乐节奏少不了鼓。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪb/","translation":"n. 肋，肋骨","word":"rib","example":"She was taken to hospital with a broken arm and ribs. 她胳膊和肋骨断了，被送进医院。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪb/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'rɪbən/","example":"little girls with ribbons in their hair 头发上系着丝带的小姑娘们","translation":"n. 缎带，丝带；带","phonetic_us":"/'rɪbən/","word":"ribbon"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɪd/","translation":"v. 使摆脱，使去掉","word":"rid","example":"The proposals are an attempt to rid the country of political corruption. 这些提议是使该国摆脱政治腐败的一种尝试。","phonetic_uk":"/rɪd/"},{"word":"ridge","phonetic_us":"/rɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 脊；岭，山脉；垄","phonetic_uk":"/rɪdʒ/","example":"We made our way carefully along the ridge. 我们沿着山脊小心前行。"},{"word":"ridiculous","translation":"adj. 荒谬的，可笑的","phonetic_us":"/rɪ'dɪkjələs/","example":"That’s a ridiculous idea! 那主意很荒唐！","phonetic_uk":"/rɪ'dɪkjʊləs/"},{"example":"They shot him at point blank range with an automatic rifle. 他们用一支自动步枪在近距离射程内射中了他。","phonetic_uk":"/'raɪf(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/'raɪfl/","translation":"n. 步枪，来复枪","word":"rifle"},{"word":"rigid","phonetic_us":"/'rɪdʒɪd/","translation":"adj. 刚硬的；僵硬的","phonetic_uk":"/'rɪdʒɪd/","example":"rigid and authoritarian methods of education 死板、专断的教育方法"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈrɪgərəs/","example":"a rigorous analysis of defence needs 对国防需求的缜密分析","word":"rigorous","translation":"adj. 严格的","phonetic_us":"/'rɪɡərəs/"},{"word":"ring","translation":"n. 拳击台","phonetic_us":"/rɪŋ/","phonetic_uk":"/rɪŋ/","example":""},{"phonetic_us":"/'raɪət/","translation":"n. 暴乱","word":"riot","example":"urban riots 城市骚乱","phonetic_uk":"/'raɪət/"},{"example":"Their riotous behaviour led to their arrest. 他们因暴乱行为被捕。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈraɪətəs/","word":"riotous","phonetic_us":"/'raɪətəs/","translation":"adj. 狂暴的"},{"translation":"adj. 熟的；时机成熟的","phonetic_us":"/raɪp/","word":"ripe","example":"Those tomatoes aren’t ripe yet. 那些番茄还没熟。","phonetic_uk":"/raɪp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪsk/","example":"It was a risk, sending a letter to my house. 将信寄到我家是冒险。","translation":"n. 风险，危险，冒险","phonetic_us":"/rɪsk/","word":"risk"},{"phonetic_us":"/'raɪvl/","translation":"n. 对手","word":"rival","phonetic_uk":"/'raɪvl/","example":"This gives the company a competitive advantage over its rivals. 这使该公司与其对手相比具有一项竞争优势。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rɔr/","translation":"v. 吼叫；呼喊；n. 吼","word":"roar","phonetic_uk":"/rɔː/","example":"We heard a lion roar. 我们听到狮子在吼叫。"},{"word":"roast","phonetic_us":"/rost/","translation":"vt&vi. 烤，炙，烘","example":"Are you going to roast the chicken? 这鸡你是准备烤的吗？","phonetic_uk":"/rəʊst/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɒb/","example":"They killed four policemen while robbing a bank. 他们抢劫一家银行的时候杀了4名警察。","word":"rob","phonetic_us":"/rɑb/","translation":"vt.  抢劫， 盗窃"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'rəʊbɒt/","example":"cars built by robots 机器人制造的汽车","phonetic_us":"/'robɑt/","translation":"n. 机器人；自动机","word":"robot"},{"example":"The rocket was launched from a space research base. 火箭从一个太空研究基地发射升空。","phonetic_uk":"/'rɒkɪt/","translation":"n. 火箭；v. 猛增","phonetic_us":"/'rɑkɪt/","word":"rocket"},{"word":"rod","phonetic_us":"/rɑd/","translation":"n. 杆，竿，棒","example":"a measuring rod 测量杆","phonetic_uk":"/rɒd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/rol/","translation":"vi&vt. 滚动；转动","word":"roll","phonetic_uk":"/rəʊl/","example":"There was silence as the cameras started to roll. 摄影机开始转动，大家安静了下来。"},{"word":"roller","translation":"n. 滚柱，滚筒，滚轴","phonetic_us":"/'rolɚ/","example":"a paint roller 刷漆滚筒","phonetic_uk":"/'rəʊlə/"},{"word":"Roman","translation":"n. 古罗马人；adj. 罗马的","phonetic_us":"/'romən/","example":"When they conquered Britain, the Romans brought this custom with them. 当古罗马人征服不列颠时，他们把这一习俗也带了过去。","phonetic_uk":"/'rəʊmən/"},{"example":"‘Tom always sends me red roses on my birthday.’ ‘How romantic!’ “我过生日时汤姆总是给我送红玫瑰。”“多浪漫啊！”","phonetic_uk":"/rə(ʊ)'mæntɪk/","word":"romantic","phonetic_us":"/ro'mæntɪk/","translation":"adj. 浪漫的；传奇的"},{"example":"They tied a rope around my waist and pulled me up. 他们在我腰间系了一根粗绳子，把我拉了上去。","phonetic_uk":"/rəup/","phonetic_us":"/rop/","translation":"n. 绳，索；vt.  用绳捆","word":"rope"},{"phonetic_us":"/'rotəri/","translation":"adj. 旋转的，转动的","word":"rotary","phonetic_uk":"/'rəʊt(ə)rɪ/","example":"the rotary movement of the helicopter blades 直升机螺旋桨叶的转动"},{"translation":"v. 旋转；v. 使旋转","phonetic_us":"/'rotet/","word":"rotate","phonetic_uk":"/rə(ʊ)'teɪt/","example":"The Earth rotates on its axis once every 24 hours. 地球每24小时绕地轴自转一周。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rə(ʊ)'teɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"The blades spin at 100 rotations per minute. 叶片每分钟转100圈。","word":"rotation","phonetic_us":"/ro'teʃən/","translation":"n. 旋转，转动；循环"},{"word":"rotten","phonetic_us":"/'rɑtn/","translation":"adj. 腐烂的，发臭的","example":"the smell of rotten eggs 坏鸡蛋的气味","phonetic_uk":"/'rɒt(ə)n/"},{"translation":"adj. 表面不平的；粗略的","phonetic_us":"/rʌf/","word":"rough","example":"Her hands were rough from hard work. 她的双手因为干重活而变得很粗糙。","phonetic_uk":"/rʌf/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/raʊz/","example":"His banging roused the neighbours. 他重重的关门声把邻居都吵醒了。","phonetic_us":"/raʊz/","translation":"v. 唤醒，唤起；惊起","word":"rouse"},{"word":"route","translation":"n. 路，路线，路程","phonetic_us":"/raʊt/","phonetic_uk":"/ruːt/","example":"the most direct route home 最直接的回家路线"},{"example":"John’s departure had upset their daily routine . 约翰的离去打乱了他们的日常生活。","phonetic_uk":"/ruː'tiːn/","translation":"n. 例行公事；adj. 日常的","phonetic_us":"/rʊ'tin/","word":"routine"},{"word":"routinely","translation":"adv. 例行公事地","phonetic_us":"/rʊ'tinli/","phonetic_uk":"/ru:'ti:nlɪ/","example":"This vaccine is already routinely used. 这种疫苗的使用已经常规化。"},{"example":"(= many rows ) of shelves stacked with books 一排又一排堆满书的架子","phonetic_uk":"/rəʊ/","phonetic_us":"/ro/","translation":"n. (一)排，(一)行","word":"row"},{"translation":"adj. 王的；皇家的","phonetic_us":"/'rɔɪəl/","word":"royal","phonetic_uk":"/'rɒɪəl/","example":"the royal palace 王宫"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rʌb/","example":"You’ll have to rub harder if you want to get it clean. 如果你想把它弄干净，就得更使劲地擦。","translation":"vt.  擦， 摩擦","phonetic_us":"/rʌb/","word":"rub"},{"word":"rude","translation":"adj. 粗鲁的","phonetic_us":"/rud/","phonetic_uk":"/ru:d/","example":"a rude remark 粗鲁的话"},{"word":"rug","phonetic_us":"/rʌɡ/","translation":"n. 小地毯；毛毯","example":"The old lady was seated in her chair at the window, a rug over her knees. 这位老妇人坐在靠窗的椅子上，膝上盖着一块小毛毯。","phonetic_uk":"/rʌg/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ruːɪn/","example":"This illness has ruined my life. 这个病毁掉了我的生活。","word":"ruin","translation":"v.  毁坏；n. 毁灭；废墟","phonetic_us":"/'ruɪn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ruːmə/","example":"His name has come up in the rumour mill as a possible director for the project. 有谣传说他可能出任这个项目的主管。","word":"rumour","phonetic_us":"/'ru:mə/","translation":"n.  谣传， 谣言"},{"word":"rural","translation":"adj. 农村的，田园的","phonetic_us":"/'rʊrəl/","example":"a rural setting 乡村环境","phonetic_uk":"/'rʊər(ə)l/"},{"word":"rush","translation":"v. 冲，奔；v. 催促","phonetic_us":"/rʌʃ/","phonetic_uk":"/rʌʃ/","example":"A small girl rushed past her. 一个小女孩从她身边匆匆经过。"},{"phonetic_us":"/rʌst/","translation":"n. 锈；v. 生锈，氧化","word":"rust","phonetic_uk":"/rʌst/","example":"There were large patches of rust on the car. 车上有大片锈斑。"},{"example":"They’ve never actually given anyone the sack . 他们从未真的辞退过什么人。","phonetic_uk":"/sæk/","word":"sack","translation":"n. 袋，麻袋；开除","phonetic_us":"/sæk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sækrɪfaɪs/","translation":"n&vt. 牺牲；南祭","word":"sacrifice","phonetic_uk":"/'sækrɪfaɪs/","example":"The minister stressed the need for economic sacrifice. 部长强调了在经济上作出牺牲的必要性。"},{"word":"saddle","translation":"n. 鞍子，马鞍","phonetic_us":"/'sædl/","phonetic_uk":"/'sæd(ə)l/","example":"It looks like a saddle. 它看起来像一个马鞍。"},{"word":"sail","phonetic_us":"/sel/","translation":"n. 帆；船；v. 航行","example":"a yacht with white sails 扬着白帆的游艇","phonetic_uk":"/seɪl/"},{"example":"Six British sailors drowned. 六名英国海员溺水身亡。","phonetic_uk":"/'seɪlə/","word":"sailor","translation":"n.  水手， 海员","phonetic_us":"/'selɚ/"},{"example":"Saint Patrick 圣帕特里克","phonetic_uk":"/seɪnt/","translation":"n. 圣人","phonetic_us":"/sent/","word":"saint"},{"word":"sake","translation":"n. 缘故，理由","phonetic_us":"/[sek]/","phonetic_uk":"/seɪk/","example":"He moved to the seaside for the sake of his health. 他为了健康而迁居海滨。"},{"example":"Would you like some salad with your pasta? 你的意大利面要配些色拉吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'sæləd/","phonetic_us":"/'sæləd/","translation":"n.  色拉， 凉拌菜","word":"salad"},{"word":"salary","translation":"n.  薪金， 薪水","phonetic_us":"/'sæləri/","example":"The average salary for a teacher is $39,000 a year. 教师的平均工资是39,000美元一年。","phonetic_uk":"/'sæləri/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'seɪlzmən/","example":"...an insurance salesman. …一位男保险推销员。","translation":"n.  售货员， 推销员","phonetic_us":"/'selzmən/","word":"salesman"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɑːmp(ə)l/","example":"They took a blood sample to test for hepatitis. 他们取了血样做肝炎化验。","translation":"n. 样品；实例，标本","phonetic_us":"/'sæmpl/","word":"sample"},{"word":"sanction","translation":"vt. 批准，认可；n.  批准， 认可； 约束因素， 约束力；  国际制裁","phonetic_us":"/'sæŋkʃən/","phonetic_uk":"/'sæŋkʃn/","example":"The church refused to sanction the king’s second marriage. 教会拒绝批准国王的第二次婚姻。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sætəlaɪt/","example":"the launch of a communications and weather satellite 气象通信卫星的发射","phonetic_us":"/'sætəlaɪt/","translation":"n. 卫星；人造卫星","word":"satellite"},{"translation":"adj. 令人满意的，良好的","phonetic_us":"/,sætɪs'fæktəri/","word":"satisfactory","phonetic_uk":"/sætɪs'fækt(ə)rɪ/","example":"His progress this term has been satisfactory. 他这学期的进步令人满意。"},{"word":"sauce","translation":"n.  调味汁， 作料","phonetic_us":"/sɔs/","example":"spaghetti sauces 意大利面酱","phonetic_uk":"/sɔːs/"},{"word":"saucer","phonetic_us":"/'sɔsɚ/","translation":"n. 茶托，浅碟","example":"a china cup and saucer 一套瓷茶杯和杯托","phonetic_uk":"/'sɔːsə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɒsɪdʒ/","example":"pork sausages 猪肉香肠","word":"sausage","phonetic_us":"/'sɔsɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 香肠，腊肠"},{"phonetic_us":"/sev/","translation":"v. 节省","word":"save","phonetic_uk":"/seɪv/","example":"We’ll save a lot of time if we go by car. 我们要是开车去，可以节省很多时间。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sevɪŋ/","translation":"n.  节省， 节约； 储蓄金， 存款","word":"saving","phonetic_uk":"/'seɪvɪŋ/","example":"Buying a house had taken all their savings. 买房子花掉了他们所有的积蓄。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sɔː/","example":"She was in the back yard sawing logs. 她在后院锯木头。","word":"saw","phonetic_us":"/sɔ/","translation":"n. 锯子；v. 锯，锯开"},{"phonetic_us":"/se/","translation":"v. 比如说[用于举例]","word":"say","example":"‘I’m so tired,’ she said. “我太累了。”她说。","phonetic_uk":"/seɪ/"},{"translation":"n. 规模，比例","phonetic_us":"/skel/","word":"scale","example":"A structural survey revealed the full scale of the damage. 结构检验揭示了实际受损程度。","phonetic_uk":"/skeɪl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/skæn/","example":"He scanned the horizon, but there was no sign of the ship. 他朝地平线处仔细眺望，但是找不到那艘船的踪影。","word":"scan","translation":"v. 细看；浏览；扫描","phonetic_us":"/skæn/"},{"word":"scandal","phonetic_us":"/'skændl/","translation":"n.  丑事， 丑闻； 流言蜚语； 反感， 愤慨","example":"It caused quite a scandal when he left his wife. 他离开妻子成了一大丑闻。","phonetic_uk":"/'skændl/"},{"example":"Food was often scarce in the winter. 冬季常常粮食短缺。","phonetic_uk":"/skeəs/","translation":"adj.  缺乏的， 不足的； 稀少的， 罕见的","phonetic_us":"/skɛrs/","word":"scarce"},{"example":"The city had scarcely changed in 20 years. 这座城市20年中几乎没有什么改变。","phonetic_uk":"/'skeəslɪ/","translation":"adv. 仅仅；几乎不","phonetic_us":"/'skɛrsli/","word":"scarcely"},{"phonetic_uk":"/skeə/","example":"Loud noises can scare animals or birds. 噪声太大会惊吓到鸟兽。","phonetic_us":"/skɛr/","translation":"v.  吓， 使害怕； 受惊吓， 感到害怕；n. 惊恐，恐慌","word":"scare"},{"word":"scary","translation":"adj.  引起惊慌的","phonetic_us":"/'skɛri/","phonetic_uk":"/'skeəri/","example":""},{"word":"scatter","translation":"v. 使消散；撒；散播","phonetic_us":"/'skætɚ/","example":"The sound of gunfire made the crowd scatter in all directions. 枪声使人群四散奔逃。","phonetic_uk":"/'skætə/"},{"example":"The best part of the trip was the fantastic scenery. 此次旅行最精彩之处就是那美妙绝伦的风景。","phonetic_uk":"/'siːn(ə)rɪ/","word":"scenery","translation":"n. 舞台布景；风景","phonetic_us":"/'sinəri/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'skɛdʒul; (canadian) ˈʃɛdʒʊl; ˈʃɛdjʊl/","translation":"n. 日程表","word":"schedule","example":"How can he fit everything into his busy schedule ? 他是怎么把所有的事情都排进自己忙碌的时间表的？","phonetic_uk":"/'skedʒul/"},{"word":"scheme","translation":"n. 计划，规划；诡计","phonetic_us":"/skim/","phonetic_uk":"/skiːm/","example":"The money will be used for teacher training schemes. 这笔钱将用于教师培训计划。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'skɑlɚ/","translation":"n. 学者(尤指文学方面)","word":"scholar","example":"the great Dutch scholar Erasmus 荷兰的大学问家伊拉斯谟","phonetic_uk":"/'skɒlə/"},{"word":"scholarship","translation":"n. 奖学金","phonetic_us":"/'skɑlɚʃɪp/","phonetic_uk":"/'skɔləʃip/","example":"He got a scholarship to the Pratt Institute of Art. 他得到了一笔普拉特艺术学院的奖学金。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,saɪən'tɪfɪk/","translation":"adj. 科学(上)的","word":"scientific","phonetic_uk":"/saɪən'tɪfɪk/","example":"We believe in investing in scientific research. 我们相信科学研究的投资价值。"},{"translation":"n. 剪刀，剪子","phonetic_us":"/'sɪzɚz/","word":"scissors","example":"a pair of scissors 一把剪刀","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪzəz/"},{"example":"Do not scold the puppy, but simply and firmly say ‘no’. 不要责骂小狗，但要干脆利落地说“不”。","phonetic_uk":"/skəuld/","translation":"v.  责骂， 训斥","phonetic_us":"/skold/","word":"scold"},{"example":"measures to limit the scope of criminals’ activities 限制罪犯活动范围的措施","phonetic_uk":"/skəʊp/","phonetic_us":"/skop/","translation":"n. 范围","word":"scope"},{"translation":"n. 得分，比数，成绩","phonetic_us":"/skɔ/","word":"score","phonetic_uk":"/skɔː/","example":"At half-time the score was one all. 半场时的比分是一比一。"},{"word":"scout","phonetic_us":"/skaʊt/","translation":"n. 侦察员，侦察机","example":"He sent three scouts ahead to take a look at the bridge. 他派出三名侦察兵到前面侦察大桥的情况。","phonetic_uk":"/skaʊt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/skreɪp/","example":"Scrape the carrots and slice them thinly. 把这些胡萝卜去皮切成薄片。","word":"scrape","translation":"vt&vi&n. 刮，擦","phonetic_us":"/skrep/"},{"example":"There were deep scratches all over her face. 她脸上全是深深的伤痕。","phonetic_uk":"/skrætʃ/","word":"scratch","phonetic_us":"/skrætʃ/","translation":"n. 抓，划痕"},{"example":"After the first few shots, people started screaming. 几声枪响过后，人们开始尖叫起来。","phonetic_uk":"/skriːm/","phonetic_us":"/skrim/","translation":"vi. 尖叫，呼啸；n.  尖叫声","word":"scream"},{"example":"All women over 50 will be regularly screened. 所有50岁以上女性都将定期接受检查。","phonetic_uk":"/skri:n/","word":"screen","phonetic_us":"/skrin/","translation":"v. 筛查"},{"example":"Fix the frame in position and tighten the screws . 把框子固定在正确位置上，拧紧螺丝。","phonetic_uk":"/skruː/","word":"screw","phonetic_us":"/skru/","translation":"n. 螺旋，螺丝；v. 拧紧"},{"phonetic_uk":"/skrɪpt/","example":"a diary entry written in neat black script 用工整的黑色字写下的一则日记","word":"script","phonetic_us":"/skrɪpt/","translation":"n.  剧本， 广播稿； 书写用的字母； 笔迹， 手迹"},{"example":"The seal on the box broke when it fell from its hiding-place. 盒子从隐藏处掉下时上面的封口破了。","phonetic_uk":"/sil/","phonetic_us":"/sil/","translation":"n. 封蜡；印记；v. 封","word":"seal"},{"translation":"adj. 第二的；次要的","phonetic_us":"/'sɛkəndɛri/","word":"secondary","phonetic_uk":"/'sek(ə)nd(ə)rɪ/","example":"the novel’s secondary characters 这本小说中的次要人物"},{"word":"secretary","translation":"n. 秘书；书记；大臣","phonetic_us":"/'sɛkrətɛrɪ/","phonetic_uk":"/'sekrɪt(ə)rɪ/","example":"My secretary will fax you all the details. 我的秘书会把所有的细节发传真给你。"},{"word":"section","phonetic_us":"/'sɛkʃən/","translation":"n. 切片；一段；部门","example":"The plane’s tail section was found in a cornfield. 飞机的尾部在玉米田里找到了。","phonetic_uk":"/'sekʃ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sektə/","example":"...the nation's manufacturing sector. …该国的制造部门。","translation":"n.  部门， 部分； 防御地段， 防区； 扇形","phonetic_us":"/'sɛktɚ/","word":"sector"},{"phonetic_us":"/sə'kjʊr/","translation":"v. 确保……安全","word":"secure","example":"Troops were sent to secure the border. 军队被派去保卫边境。","phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'kjʊə(r)/"},{"example":"The trial was held under tight security . 这场审讯是在戒备森严的情况下进行的。","phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'kjʊərətɪ/","word":"security","phonetic_us":"/sə'kjʊrəti/","translation":"n. 安全，安保"},{"phonetic_us":"/sid/","translation":"n. 种(子)，籽，萌芽","word":"seed","phonetic_uk":"/siːd/","example":"I sow the seed in pots of soil-based compost. 我把种子种在一盆盆施有堆肥的土里。"},{"example":"new graduates seeking employment 正在求职的刚毕业的大学生","phonetic_uk":"/siːk/","phonetic_us":"/sik/","translation":"v. 寻找，探索；试图","word":"seek"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'siːmɪŋlɪ/","example":"seemingly unrelated bits of information 似乎互不相关的零星信息","translation":"adv. 表面上看","phonetic_us":"/'simɪŋli/","word":"seemingly"},{"example":"Decorate with orange segments. 用几瓣橙子作点缀。","phonetic_uk":"/'segmənt/","translation":"n.  部分， 片段； 瓣","phonetic_us":"/'sɛɡmənt/","word":"segment"},{"phonetic_us":"/siz/","translation":"v. 抓住","word":"seize","phonetic_uk":"/si:z/","example":"Suddenly he seized my hand. 他突然抓住我的手。"},{"example":"Karen had seldom seen him so angry. 卡伦很少见他这么生气过。","phonetic_uk":"/'seldəm/","phonetic_us":"/'sɛldəm/","translation":"adv. 很少，罕见","word":"seldom"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'lekt/","example":"The party was small and select. 团里人员不多，都是经过精心挑选的。","word":"select","phonetic_us":"/sə'lɛkt/","translation":"adj.  精选的， 挑选出来的； 优等的， 第一流的；vt. 选择，挑选"},{"example":"The judges have made their final selection. 评委已经作出最后的评选。","phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'lekʃn/","word":"selection","translation":"n. 选择，挑选","phonetic_us":"/sɪ'lɛkʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/si'lektiv/","example":"selective schools 择优录取学生的学校","word":"selective","translation":"adj. 选择的,精选的","phonetic_us":"/sɪ'lɛktɪv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'selfiʃ/","example":"How can you be so selfish? 你怎能这样自私？","word":"selfish","phonetic_us":"/'sɛlfɪʃ/","translation":"adj. 自私的"},{"example":"the fall semester 秋季学期","phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'mestə/","word":"semester","phonetic_us":"/səˈmɛstɚ/","translation":"n.  学期"},{"phonetic_uk":"/,semɪkən'dʌktə/","example":"In semiconductor receivers transistors take the place of vacuum tubes. 在半导体收音机中晶体管代替了真空管。","word":"semiconductor","translation":"n. n.；n. 半导体","phonetic_us":"/,sɛmɪkən'dʌktɚ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'semɪnɑː/","example":"a Shakespeare seminar 莎士比亚研讨班","word":"seminar","translation":"n.  研究班， 研讨会","phonetic_us":"/'sɛmɪnɑr/"},{"word":"senate","translation":"n. 参议院，上院","phonetic_us":"/'sɛnət/","example":"The Senate approved the bill. 参议院批准了这项议案。","phonetic_uk":"/'senɪt/"},{"word":"senator","phonetic_us":"/'sɛnətɚ/","translation":"n.  参议员","phonetic_uk":"/'senətə/","example":"Senator Kennedy 肯尼迪参议员"},{"example":"Seniors can get a 10% discount. 老年人可以享受10%的折扣。","phonetic_uk":"/'siːnɪə/","word":"senior","translation":"n. 老年人","phonetic_us":"/'sinɪɚ/"},{"example":"She seems very sensible. 她好像很明智。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsensəbl/","phonetic_us":"/'sɛnsəbl/","translation":"adj. 明智的","word":"sensible"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɛnsətɪv/","translation":"adj. 敏感的","word":"sensitive","example":"a very sensitive child 一个很敏感的小孩","phonetic_uk":"/'sensətɪv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sentəns/","example":"She received an eight-year prison sentence. 她被判八年徒刑。","phonetic_us":"/'sɛntəns/","translation":"v & n. 判决","word":"sentence"},{"phonetic_us":"/(for v.) sɛpəˌret; (for adj.) sɛprɪt/","translation":"adj. 分离的；个别的","word":"separate","phonetic_uk":"/(for v.) ˈsepəreɪt; (for adj.) ˈseprət/","example":"The gym and the sauna are in separate buildings. 健身房和桑拿浴室在不同的大楼里。"},{"example":"Cook each vegetable separately until just tender. 把每样蔬菜单独烹煮，直到煮软就行了。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈseprətli/","word":"separately","phonetic_us":"/'sɛprətli/","translation":"adv. 分别地，另行"},{"word":"sequence","translation":"n. 连续，继续；次序","phonetic_us":"/'sikwəns/","phonetic_uk":"/'siːkw(ə)ns/","example":"Be careful to perform the actions in the correct sequence . 注意要按正确的顺序来完成动作。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɪriz/","translation":"n. 连续，系列；丛书","word":"series","example":"the series of events that led to the outbreak of war 导致战争爆发的一系列事件","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪəriːz; -rɪz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"There was only one girl serving customers . 只有一个女孩在接待顾客。","translation":"vt. 为…服务；招待","phonetic_us":"","word":"serve"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɛʃən/","translation":"n. 开会，会议","word":"session","phonetic_uk":"/ˈseʃn/","example":"Board members met in closed session (= with nobody else present ) . 委员会成员举行了闭门会议。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈsetɪŋ/","example":"I’ve worked with children in various settings, mainly in secondary school. 我在许多地方教过孩子，主要是在中学。","word":"setting","translation":"n. 背景，环境","phonetic_us":"/'sɛtɪŋ/"},{"example":"Albert settled himself on the sofa. 阿尔伯特在沙发安坐下来。","phonetic_uk":"/'set(ə)l/","word":"settle","translation":"v. 安排；安放；调停","phonetic_us":"/'sɛtl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'set(ə)lm(ə)nt/","example":"Union leaders and company bosses will meet tomorrow in an attempt to reach a settlement . 工会领导人和公司老板将于明天举行会议以期达成协议。","translation":"n. 解决；殖民，殖民地","phonetic_us":"/'sɛtlmənt/","word":"settlement"},{"word":"severe","phonetic_us":"/sɪ'vɪr/","translation":"adj. 严重的","phonetic_uk":"/sɪ'vɪə/","example":"His injuries were quite severe. 他的伤势很严重。"},{"word":"sew","translation":"v. 缝制；v. 缝纫","phonetic_us":"/so/","example":"I learned to sew at school. 我在学校学会了缝纫。","phonetic_uk":"/səʊ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɛk'sɪzəm/","translation":"n.  性别偏见， 性别歧视","word":"sexism","phonetic_uk":"/'seksɪzəm/","example":"sexism in the workplace 工作场所的性别歧视"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sekʃuəl/","example":"a disease passed on by sexual contact 由性接触传染的疾病","word":"sexual","phonetic_us":"/sɛkʃʊəl/","translation":"adj.  性的， 两性的； 性别的"},{"example":"a plant that needs a lot of shade 喜阴植物","phonetic_uk":"/ʃeɪd/","word":"shade","phonetic_us":"/ʃed/","translation":"n. 阴凉处"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ʃæləu/","example":"a shallow river 浅河","translation":"adj. 浅的；浅薄的；n.  浅滩， 浅水处","phonetic_us":"/'ʃælo/","word":"shallow"},{"example":"He hadn’t shaved for days. 他已经好几天没刮脸了。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃeɪv/","word":"shave","translation":"v. 剃，刮；v. 修面","phonetic_us":"/ʃev/"},{"example":"Though shorn of some of its powers, the party remains in control. 虽然被削去了一些权力，该党仍然掌握着控制权。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃɪə/","word":"shear","phonetic_us":"/ʃɪr/","translation":"v. 剪；剥夺；v. 剪"},{"example":"He strode across the bathroom, shedding wet clothes as he went. 他大步走过浴室，边走边把湿衣服脱下来。","phonetic_uk":"","word":"shed","phonetic_us":"","translation":"vt. 流出；散发；脱落"},{"word":"sheer","translation":"adv. 垂直地，陡峭地；vi.  急转向， 偏离；adj. 完全的，十足的；陡峭的，垂直的；极薄的，透明的","phonetic_us":"/ʃɪr/","phonetic_uk":"/ʃɪə/","example":"cliffs which rose sheer from the sea 从海面垂直拔起的悬崖"},{"word":"sheet","phonetic_us":"/ʃit/","translation":"n. 被单；纸张；薄板","phonetic_uk":"/ʃiːt/","example":"I’ll go and find you some clean sheets and blankets. 我去给你们找些干净的床单和毯子。"},{"word":"shelf","phonetic_us":"/ʃɛlf/","translation":"n. 搁板，架子","phonetic_uk":"/ʃelf/","example":"shelves of books 一层层书架的书"},{"example":"We ran for cover as shells dropped all around us. 周围炮弹四处飞落，我们奔跑着寻找地方躲避。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃel/","word":"shell","phonetic_us":"/ʃɛl/","translation":"n. 壳，贝壳；外壳，框架；炮弹；vt.  剥…的壳； 炮击"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ʃeltə/","example":"The men took shelter in a bombed-out farmhouse. 那些男人躲在一间被炸毁的农舍里。","word":"shelter","phonetic_us":"/'ʃɛltɚ/","translation":"n. 隐蔽处；掩蔽，庇护"},{"example":"He used his left hand as a shield against the reflecting sunlight. 他用左手遮挡反射过来的阳光。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃiːld/","translation":"n. 盾；防护物；v. 保护","phonetic_us":"/ʃild/","word":"shield"},{"word":"shift","translation":"v. 替换，转移；n. 转换","phonetic_us":"/ʃɪft/","example":"They need to shift from farming to industry, and they need to do so desperately. 他们需要从农业领域转移到工业领域。 他们需要拼命地那么做。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃɪft/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ʃɪvɚ/","translation":"v. 颤抖，哆嗦；n. 冷颤","word":"shiver","example":"Jake stood shivering in the cold air. 大冷天里，杰克站着冻得瑟瑟发抖。","phonetic_uk":"/'ʃɪvə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ʃɑk/","translation":"v. 感到震惊","word":"shock","example":"The hatred in her voice shocked him. 她语气中的仇恨让他震惊。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃɒk/"},{"example":"Police shot one suspect when he pulled a gun on them. 警方在一名嫌疑人拔枪指着他们时击毙了他。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃuːt/","word":"shoot","phonetic_us":"/ʃut/","translation":"v. 发射；射中；n. 发芽"},{"example":"We could see a boat about a mile from shore. 我们看见离岸边大约一英里的地方有一艘船。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃɔː/","phonetic_us":"/ʃɔr/","translation":"n. 滨，岸","word":"shore"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ʃɔːtɪdʒ/","example":"There is no heating available due to fuel shortages. 因为燃料短缺，所以没有供暖。","word":"shortage","phonetic_us":"/'ʃɔrtɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 不足，缺少，不足额"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ʃɔrtkʌmɪŋ/","translation":"n.  短处， 缺点","word":"shortcoming","example":"Peter was painfully aware of his own shortcomings. 彼得痛苦地认识到了自己的短处。","phonetic_uk":"/'ʃɔːtkʌmɪŋ/"},{"example":"I tried to take a shortcut and got lost. 我试着走近路，结果迷路了。","phonetic_uk":"/'ʃɔ:tkʌt/","translation":"n. 捷径，近路","phonetic_us":"/'ʃɔrt,kʌt/","word":"shortcut"},{"example":"Ms Jones will be back shortly. 琼斯女士很快就会回来。","phonetic_uk":"/'ʃɔːtlɪ/","word":"shortly","translation":"adv. 立刻；简短地","phonetic_us":"/'ʃɔrtli/"},{"translation":"n. 发射；弹丸；射门","phonetic_us":"/ʃɑt/","word":"shot","phonetic_uk":"/ʃɒt/","example":"He shot all his bullets, but no one hit. 他射出了所有的子弹却没有一发命中。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ʃaʊə/","example":"Why does the phone always ring when I’m in the shower? 为什么电话铃总是在我洗澡的时候响？","word":"shower","phonetic_us":"/'ʃaʊɚ/","translation":"n. 阵雨；(一)阵；淋浴"},{"example":"Michael has influenced so many artists, some of whom are picking up on the grandeur and showmanship of his live performances. 迈克尔影响了众多艺术家，他们中的有些人在演出上的火爆与高超本领上正得自他的绝技。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈʃəʊmənʃɪp/","word":"showmanship","translation":"n. 主技演出的技巧","phonetic_us":"/'ʃomənʃɪp/"},{"word":"shriek","phonetic_us":"/ʃrik/","translation":"v. 尖声喊叫；n. 尖叫声","example":"They were dragged from their homes, shrieking and weeping. 他们哭喊着被人从家里拖出去。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃriːk/"},{"translation":"v.  起皱； 收缩； 退缩， 畏缩","phonetic_us":"/ʃrɪŋk/","word":"shrink","phonetic_uk":"/ʃrɪŋk/","example":"I’m worried about washing that shirt in case it shrinks. 我不太敢洗那件衬衫，怕它会缩水。"},{"example":"I just shrugged my shoulders and ignored him. 我只是耸耸肩，没有理睬他。","phonetic_uk":"/ʃrʌg/","word":"shrug","translation":"n&v.  耸肩","phonetic_us":"/ʃrʌɡ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'saɪdwez/","translation":"adv. 向侧面","word":"sideways","example":"They brought the piano sideways through the front door. 他们把钢琴侧着从前门抬进来。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsaɪdweɪz/"},{"phonetic_us":"/saɪ/","translation":"vi.  叹气， 叹息；n. 叹息","word":"sigh","phonetic_uk":"/saɪ/","example":"‘Well, there’s nothing we can do about it now,’ she sighed. “唉，我们现在对此无能为力。”她叹口气说。"},{"translation":"n. 观光","phonetic_us":"/'saɪtsiɪŋ/","word":"sightseeing","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsaɪtsi:ɪŋ/","example":"She swam and sunbathed, went sightseeing and relaxed. 她游泳，晒日光浴，观光，放松。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/saɪn/","example":"the dollar sign 美元符号","translation":"n. 符号；招牌；n. 签名","phonetic_us":"/saɪn/","word":"sign"},{"example":"At a prearranged signal the lights went out. 预定的信号一发出，灯就全灭了。","phonetic_uk":"/'signəl/","phonetic_us":"/'sɪgnl/","translation":"n & v. 信号，发信号","word":"signal"},{"example":"Her signature is totally illegible (= cannot be read ) . 她的签字完全无法辨认。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪgnətʃə/","phonetic_us":"/'sɪgnətʃɚ/","translation":"n. 签名","word":"signature"},{"translation":"n. 意义，意味；重要性","phonetic_us":"/sɪɡ'nɪfɪkəns/","word":"significance","example":"Ideas about the social significance of religion have changed over time. 有关宗教的社会意义的观念已随时间的流逝发生了改变。","phonetic_uk":"/sɪg'nɪfɪk(ə)ns/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sig'nifikənt/","example":"His most significant political achievement was the abolition of the death penalty. 他政治上最重大的成就是废除了死刑。","word":"significant","translation":"adj. 重要的","phonetic_us":"/sɪɡ'nɪfɪkənt/"},{"word":"silence","phonetic_us":"/'saɪləns/","translation":"n. 沉默；v. 使沉默","phonetic_uk":"/'saɪləns/","example":"There was a brief silence before anyone answered. 沉默了片刻才有人回答。"},{"word":"silent","translation":"adj. 沉默的；寂静无声的","phonetic_us":"/'saɪlənt/","example":"The large house was silent and lonely. 这幢大房子寂静荒凉。","phonetic_uk":"/'saɪlənt/"},{"example":"pure silk stockings 生丝面料的漂亮连衣裙","phonetic_uk":"/sɪlk/","word":"silk","phonetic_us":"/sɪlk/","translation":"n. 蚕丝，丝，丝织品"},{"word":"silly","translation":"adj. 傻的，愚蠢的","phonetic_us":"/'sɪli/","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪlɪ/","example":"Stop asking silly questions. 别再问傻问题了。"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 银；银子；银器","word":"silver","phonetic_uk":"","example":""},{"word":"similar","translation":"adj. 相似的","phonetic_us":"/'sɪməlɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'similə/","example":"We have similar tastes in music. 我们对音乐的品位相近。"},{"translation":"adv. 类似地，相似地","phonetic_us":"/'sɪməlɚli/","word":"similarly","phonetic_uk":"","example":"The first letter she wrote me was less than a page long, and her second letter was similarly brief. 她写给我的第一封信不到一页，第二封信也一样简短。"},{"phonetic_us":"/sɪm'plɪsəti/","translation":"n. 简单","word":"simplicity","phonetic_uk":"/sɪm'plɪsɪtɪ/","example":"Mona wrote with a beautiful simplicity of style. 莫娜的文笔朴实优美。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɪmplɪfaɪ/","translation":"v. 简化","word":"simplify","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsɪmplɪfaɪ/","example":"an attempt to simplify the tax system 简化税制的尝试"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɪmpli/","translation":"adv. 简单地；朴素地","word":"simply","example":"Try to express yourself more simply. 尽量把你的意思表达得更简单明了。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪmplɪ/"},{"example":"The Spanish Inquisition charged him with sinning against God and man. 西班牙宗教法庭指控他违背了上帝和人类的律法。","phonetic_uk":"/sɪn/","word":"sin","translation":"vi.  犯戒律， 犯过失；n. 罪，罪孽","phonetic_us":"/sɪn/"},{"word":"sincere","translation":"adj. 真诚的；真挚的","phonetic_us":"/sɪn'sɪr/","example":"Please accept my sincere apologies . 请接受我真诚的道歉。","phonetic_uk":"/sɪn'sɪə/"},{"example":"A single tree gave shade from the sun. 唯有一棵树遮阴。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪŋgl/","translation":"adj. 单一的；独身的；单程的；n. 单程票；","phonetic_us":"/'sɪŋɡl/","word":"single"},{"example":"the singular form of the noun 该名词的单数形式","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪŋgjʊlə/","word":"singular","translation":"adj. 单一的；非凡的","phonetic_us":"/'sɪŋɡjəlɚ/"},{"example":"an archaeological site 考古现场","phonetic_uk":"/saɪt/","word":"site","phonetic_us":"/saɪt/","translation":"n. 场所，地址"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌsɪtʃuˈeɪʃn/","example":"I explained the situation to everyone. 我向大家介绍了一下情况。","translation":"n. 情况","phonetic_us":"/,sɪtʃu'eʃən/","word":"situation"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sketʃ/","example":"...thumbnail sketches of heads of state and political figures. …国家首脑和政治要员们的简要陈述。","word":"sketch","phonetic_us":"/skɛtʃ/","translation":"n. 略图；速写；概略"},{"phonetic_uk":"/skɪld/","example":"Skilled craftsmen, such as carpenters, are in great demand. 对木工之类的熟练工匠需求量很大。","word":"skilled","translation":"adj. 有技能的，熟练的","phonetic_us":"/skɪld/"},{"word":"skillful","translation":"adj. 灵巧的，娴熟的","phonetic_us":"/'skɪlfəl/","example":"With a skillful movement he rounded the small fishing-boat. 他以灵巧的动作使小渔船调过头来。","phonetic_uk":"/'skilful/"},{"phonetic_us":"/skɪm/","translation":"v. 掠过，擦过；略读","word":"skim","phonetic_uk":"/skɪm/","example":"Julie skimmed the sports page. 朱莉浏览了体育版。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'skaɪrɒkɪt/","example":"The trade deficit has skyrocketed. 贸易逆差已经急剧增长。","word":"skyrocket","translation":"v. 突升，猛涨","phonetic_us":"/'skaɪ'rɑkɪt/"},{"word":"slam","translation":"v. 使劲关，砰地放下","phonetic_us":"/slæm/","phonetic_uk":"/slæm/","example":"We heard a car door slam. 我们听到有车门砰的一声关上了。"},{"word":"slap","phonetic_us":"/slæp/","translation":"vt. 掴，掌击，拍；啪的一声放；n.  掴， 掌击， 拍","phonetic_uk":"/slæp/","example":"Sarah slapped Aaron across the face. 萨拉在阿龙的脸上掴了一巴掌。"},{"word":"slave","phonetic_us":"/sleɪv/","translation":"n. 奴隶","phonetic_uk":"/sleɪv/","example":"a slave to fashion 时尚的奴隶"},{"example":"a dress with long sleeves 长袖连衣裙","phonetic_uk":"/sliːv/","phonetic_us":"/sliv/","translation":"n. 袖子，袖套","word":"sleeve"},{"phonetic_us":"/'slɛndɚ/","translation":"adj. 细长的；微薄的","word":"slender","phonetic_uk":"/'slendə/","example":"She is slender and stylish. 她身材修长，穿着时髦。"},{"phonetic_us":"/slaɪs/","translation":"n. 薄片，切片；部分","word":"slice","example":"pizza slices 比萨块","phonetic_uk":"/slaɪs/"},{"phonetic_us":"/slaɪd/","translation":"v. 滑；v. 使滑动；n. 滑","word":"slide","phonetic_uk":"/slaɪd/","example":"He slid open the door of the glass cabinet. 他滑开玻璃柜的门。"},{"word":"slight","phonetic_us":"/slaɪt/","translation":"adj. 轻微的，微小的；v. 侮慢；轻视，冷落","phonetic_uk":"/slaɪt/","example":"a slight improvement 些许的改进"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈslaɪtli/","example":"His family then moved to a slightly larger house. 他的家后来搬到了一间稍微大一点儿的房子。","word":"slightly","translation":"adv. 轻微地","phonetic_us":"/'slaɪtli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/slɪm/","example":"a slim young woman 身材苗条的年轻女子","phonetic_us":"/slɪm/","translation":"adj. 苗条的；薄的；少的；v.  减轻体重， 变苗条","word":"slim"},{"word":"slip","phonetic_us":"/slɪp/","translation":"v. 滑跤，滑落，溜；下降，跌落；悄悄放进；n.  疏漏， 差错","example":"Ben slipped quietly out of the room. 本悄悄地溜出了房间。","phonetic_uk":"/slɪp/"},{"example":"In places, the path can be wet and slippery. 路上有些地方可能又湿又滑。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈslɪpəri/","word":"slippery","translation":"adj. 模糊的，不明确的，滑的","phonetic_us":"/'slɪpəri/"},{"word":"slit","translation":"n. 裂缝；v. 切开，撕开","phonetic_us":"/slɪt/","example":"light shining through a slit in the door 透过门缝照进来的光线","phonetic_uk":"/slɪt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sləʊp/","example":"a steep slope 陡坡","word":"slope","translation":"n. 倾斜；斜面；v. 倾斜","phonetic_us":"/slop/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/smɑːt/","example":"The smart kids get good grades and go off to college. 聪明的孩子成绩好，可以去上大学。","phonetic_us":"/smɑrt/","translation":"adj. 巧妙的；洒脱的","word":"smart"},{"phonetic_us":"/smæʃ/","translation":"v. 粉碎，打烂；狠打，猛击；破灭，失败；猛撞，猛冲；n.  破碎 ； 猛击， 猛撞； 轰动的演出， 巨大的成功","word":"smash","phonetic_uk":"/smæʃ/","example":"Vandals had smashed all the windows. 破坏分子打碎了所有的窗子。"},{"word":"smooth","phonetic_us":"/smʊð/","translation":"adj. 光滑的","example":"Her skin felt smooth and cool. 她的皮肤摸上去又滑又凉。","phonetic_uk":"/smuːð/"},{"example":"I grabbed a quick snack. 我赶紧吃了点零食。","phonetic_uk":"/snæk/","phonetic_us":"/snæk/","translation":"n. 零食，小吃","word":"snack"},{"example":"A twig snapped under my feet. 一根细枝在我脚下嚓一声断开了。","phonetic_uk":"/snæp/","translation":"v. 咔嚓折断，啪地绷断；吧嗒一声；猛咬；厉声说话，怒声责骂；adj.  仓促的， 突然的；n. 吧嗒声；快照","phonetic_us":"/snæp/","word":"snap"},{"phonetic_us":"/,so'kɔld/","translation":"adj.  所谓的， 号称的","word":"so-called","example":"The so-called experts couldn’t tell us what was wrong. 那些所谓的专家说不出问题出在哪里。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌsəu'kɔːld/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/səʊk/","example":"Soak the clothes in cold water. 把衣服浸泡在冷水里。","word":"soak","phonetic_us":"/sok/","translation":"v. 浸，泡；v. 浸泡"},{"translation":"v. 猛增","phonetic_us":"/sɔr/","word":"soar","phonetic_uk":"/sɔ:(r)/","example":"Her temperature soared. 她的体温骤然升高。"},{"example":"social issues, such as unemployment and education 失业和教育之类的社会问题","phonetic_uk":"/'səuʃl/","phonetic_us":"/'soʃl/","translation":"adj.  社会的； 交际的， 社交的","word":"social"},{"word":"socialism","translation":"n.  社会主义","phonetic_us":"/'soʃəlɪzəm/","phonetic_uk":"/'səuʃəlɪzəm/","example":"From then on we proceeded to build socialism. 从那时起，我们开始建设社会主义。"},{"translation":"n.  社会主义者","phonetic_us":"/'soʃəlɪst/","word":"socialist","example":"Esperanto has always been popular among socialists. 世界语在社会主义者中一直很受欢迎。","phonetic_uk":"/'səuʃəlɪst/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'soʃəlaɪz/","translation":"v. 交往，联谊","word":"socialize","phonetic_uk":"/'səʊʃəlaɪz/","example":"...an open meeting, where members socialized and welcomed any new members. …让会员们相互交流、欢迎所有新成员的一次公开集会。"},{"word":"sociology","phonetic_us":"/,sosɪ'ɑlədʒi/","translation":"n.  社会学","phonetic_uk":"/ˌsəusi'ɒlədʒi/","example":"Basic courses in sociology and psychology as well as other humanities courses give students plenty of opportunity to explore their own emotions. 社会学和心理学的基础，以及其他人文学科的课程，赋予学生大量的机会去探索其个人情感。"},{"word":"soda","translation":"n.  碳酸钠， 纯碱； 汽水， 苏打水","phonetic_us":"/'sodə/","phonetic_uk":"/'səudə/","example":"a Scotch and soda 一杯加苏打水的苏格兰威士忌"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɒftweə/","example":"She loaded the new software . 她给电脑装上新的软件。","translation":"n.  软件","phonetic_us":"/'sɔftwɛr/","word":"software"},{"example":"She moistenend  the soil round the plant. 她把植物周围的土壤弄湿。","phonetic_uk":"/sɒɪl/","phonetic_us":"/sɔɪl/","translation":"v. 弄脏；v. 变脏","word":"soil"},{"phonetic_us":"/'solɚ/","translation":"adj. 太阳的，日光的","word":"solar","phonetic_uk":"/'səʊlə/","example":"a solar eclipse 日食"},{"phonetic_us":"/sol/","translation":"n. 脚底，鞋底，袜底","word":"sole","example":"The soles of his feet were caked in mud. 他的脚掌上沾满了泥巴。","phonetic_uk":"/səʊl/"},{"word":"solely","translation":"adv. 单独地，唯一地","phonetic_us":"/'solli/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsəʊlli/","example":"Scholarships are given solely on the basis of financial need. 奖学金完全是根据经济需要发放的。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɑləm/","translation":"adj. 庄严的；隆重的","word":"solemn","phonetic_uk":"/'sɒləm/","example":"a solemn expression 严肃的表情"},{"word":"solicitor","phonetic_us":"/sə'lɪsɪtɚ/","translation":"n.  律师， 法律顾问","phonetic_uk":"/sə'lɪsɪtə/","example":"You need to see a solicitor. 你需要找个律师。"},{"word":"solid","phonetic_us":"/'sɑlɪd/","translation":"adj. 扎实的，坚实的","example":"The lake was frozen solid . 湖水冻得结结实实。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsɒlɪd/"},{"word":"soluble","phonetic_us":"/'sɑljəbl/","translation":"adj. 可溶的；可以解决的","example":"soluble aspirin 可溶性阿司匹林","phonetic_uk":"/'sɒljʊb(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/sə'luʃən/","translation":"n. 解决，解答，解决办法","word":"solution","phonetic_uk":"/sə'lu:ʃən/","example":"The best solution would be for them to separate. 最好的解决方法是他们分开。"},{"word":"solve","phonetic_us":"/sɔlv/","translation":"v. 解决","example":"Charlie thinks money will solve all his problems. 查理认为钱能解决他所有的问题。","phonetic_uk":"/sɒlv/"},{"example":"There’s somebody waiting to see you. 有人等着要见你。","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌmbədɪ/","word":"somebody","translation":"pron. 某人，有人","phonetic_us":"/'sʌmbədi/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sʌmhaʊ/","translation":"adv. 由于某种原因","word":"somehow","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌmhaʊ/","example":"Somehow, I just don’t think it’ll work. 不知为什么，我总觉得那样行不通。"},{"translation":"adv. 在某一时候；从前","phonetic_us":"/'sʌmtaɪm/","word":"sometime","example":"The sales figures won't be released until sometime next month. 销售数据要到下个月的某个时候才会公布。","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌmtaɪm/"},{"translation":"pron. 一点儿；adv. 有点","phonetic_us":"/'sʌmwʌt/","word":"somewhat","example":"Things have changed somewhat since then. 从那时候起，情况就有些不一样了。","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌmwɒt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sə'fɪstɪkeɪtɪd/","example":"sophisticated software 很先进的软件","translation":"adj. 复杂的；世故的","phonetic_us":"/sə'fɪstɪketɪd/","word":"sophisticated"},{"phonetic_us":"/sɔr/","translation":"adj. 痛的；恼火的；n. 疮","word":"sore","phonetic_uk":"/sɔː/","example":"I had a sore throat and aching limbs. 我喉咙疼，四肢酸痛。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɒrəʊ/","example":"the family’s joys and sorrows 这家人的喜与悲","phonetic_us":"/sɑro/","translation":"n. 悲痛，悲哀，悲伤","word":"sorrow"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sɔːt/","example":"Most of the victims developed psychological problems of one sort or another (= of various different types ) . 大多数受害者都出现了这样那样的心理问题。","word":"sort","translation":"n. 种类；类别；v. 整理","phonetic_us":"/sɔrt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/saʊnd/","example":"a sound understanding of money and banking systems 对货币和银行业体制的透彻理解","translation":"adj. 健康的；完好的","phonetic_us":"/saʊnd/","word":"sound"},{"word":"sour","phonetic_us":"/'saʊɚ/","translation":"adj. 酸的；脾气坏的","phonetic_uk":"/saʊə/","example":"Rachel sampled the wine. It was sour. 雷切尔尝了尝葡萄酒，是酸的。"},{"example":"They get their money from various sources. 他们从各种途径弄到钱。","phonetic_uk":"/sɔːs/","phonetic_us":"/sɔrs/","translation":"n. 来源","word":"source"},{"translation":"v. 播(种)；v. 播种","phonetic_us":"/so/","word":"sow","example":"Sow the seeds in late March. 三月底播种。","phonetic_uk":"/səʊ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'speɪskrɑːft/","example":"...the world's largest and most expensive unmanned spacecraft. …世界上最大、最贵的无人航天器。","translation":"n. 航天器，宇宙飞船","phonetic_us":"/'speskræft/","word":"spacecraft"},{"example":"...a garden spade. …一把花园里使用的锹。","phonetic_uk":"/speɪd/","translation":"n. 铲，铁锹","phonetic_us":"/sped/","word":"spade"},{"phonetic_uk":"/spæn/","example":"It’ll be difficult to hire that many new staff in such a short time span . 在这么短的时间里要想招聘到那么多新员工是很难的。","word":"span","phonetic_us":"/spæn/","translation":"n. 跨距；一段时间"},{"example":"Have you got any spare boxes? 你有没有多余的盒子？","phonetic_uk":"/speə(r)/","translation":"adj. 空闲的","phonetic_us":"/spɛr/","word":"spare"},{"word":"spark","translation":"n. 火花，；n. 火星","phonetic_us":"/spɑrk/","example":"sparks from the fire 火里飞出的火星","phonetic_uk":"/spɑːk/"},{"word":"specialist","translation":"n. 专家","phonetic_us":"/'spɛʃəlɪst/","phonetic_uk":"/'speʃ(ə)lɪst/","example":"a heart specialist 心脏专科医生"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'speʃəlaɪz/","translation":"v. 专业从事","phonetic_us":"/'spɛʃəlaɪz/","word":"specialize"},{"example":"Seven species of birds of prey have been observed. 已有七种猛禽被观察到。","phonetic_uk":"/'spiːʃiːz/","phonetic_us":"/'spiʃiz/","translation":"n.  种， 类","word":"species"},{"example":"games suitable for specific age groups 适合特定年龄组的游戏","phonetic_uk":"/spi'sifik/","translation":"adj. 特定的，具体的","phonetic_us":"/spɪ'sɪfɪk/","word":"specific"},{"example":"advertising that specifically targets children 专门针对儿童的广告","phonetic_uk":"/spə'sɪfɪkli/","word":"specifically","translation":"adv.  特别地， 特定地； 明确地， 具体地","phonetic_us":"/spə'sɪfɪkli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈspesɪfaɪ/","example":"Payments will be made for a specified number of months. 款项将在规定的几个月内支付。","translation":"v. 指定，具体说明","phonetic_us":"/'spɛsɪfaɪ/","word":"specify"},{"example":"a blood specimen 血样","phonetic_uk":"/'spesɪmɪn/","word":"specimen","translation":"n. 样本，标本，样品","phonetic_us":"/'spɛsəmən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/spek'tækjələ/","example":"a mountainous area with spectacular scenery 景色壮丽的山区","word":"spectacular","translation":"adj. 壮观的，引人注目的；n.  壮观的演出； 惊人之举","phonetic_us":"/spɛk'tækjəlɚ/"},{"example":"She refused to speculate. 她拒绝猜测。","phonetic_uk":"/'spekjuleɪt/","word":"speculate","translation":"v.  推测， 推断； 投机， 做投机买卖","phonetic_us":"/'spɛkjə'let/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'spelɪŋ/","example":"Her spelling has improved. 她的拼写进步了。","translation":"n.  拼字， 拼法， 拼写法","phonetic_us":"/'spɛlɪŋ/","word":"spelling"},{"example":"Because the earth spins, it is not a perfect sphere. 因为地球旋转，所以它不是个完完全全的球体。","phonetic_uk":"/sfɪə/","word":"sphere","translation":"n. 球体, 范围","phonetic_us":"/sfɪr/"},{"translation":"n.  蜘蛛","phonetic_us":"/'spaɪdɚ/","word":"spider","phonetic_uk":"/'spaɪdə/","example":"What should I find but an enormous spider! 我居然发现了一只巨大的蜘蛛！"},{"translation":"v. 使溢出；v. 溢出","phonetic_us":"/spɪl/","word":"spill","example":"Katie almost spilled her milk. 凯蒂差点把牛奶洒出来。","phonetic_uk":"/spɪl/"},{"translation":"v. 纺；使旋转；n. 旋转","phonetic_us":"/spɪn/","word":"spin","phonetic_uk":"/spɪn/","example":"The plane’s propellers were spinning. 飞机的螺旋桨在快速旋转。"},{"word":"spiritual","phonetic_us":"/'spɪrɪtʃʊəl/","translation":"adj.  精神的， 心灵的； 宗教的","phonetic_uk":"/'spɪrɪtʃuəl/","example":"Painting helps fill a spiritual need for beauty. 绘画可以满足对美的精神需求。"},{"phonetic_us":"/spɪt/","translation":"v. 吐唾沫，吐出；n.  唾沫， 唾液","word":"spit","example":"Nick rolled down his window and spat. 尼克摇下窗子，啐了口唾沫。","phonetic_uk":"/spɪt/"},{"word":"spite","translation":"n. n.；n. 恶意,怨恨,不顾；n. vt.；n. 刁难,欺侮","phonetic_us":"/spaɪt/","phonetic_uk":"/spaɪt/","example":"We went out in spite of the rain. 尽管下着雨，我们还是出去了。"},{"word":"splendid","translation":"adj.  壮丽的； 极好的","phonetic_us":"/'splɛndɪd/","example":"a splendid idea 很妙的主意","phonetic_uk":"/'splendɪd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/splɪt/","example":"The branch split under their weight. 树枝承受不住他们的重量断裂了。","translation":"v. 劈开；v. 被劈开","phonetic_us":"/splɪt/","word":"split"},{"word":"spoil","phonetic_us":"/spɔɪl/","translation":"v. 损坏，糟蹋；宠坏","example":"The whole park is spoiled by litter. 整个公园环境都给垃圾破坏了。","phonetic_uk":"/spɒɪl/"},{"example":"a White House spokesman 白宫发言人","phonetic_uk":"/'spəuksmən/","word":"spokesman","translation":"n.  发言人","phonetic_us":"/'spoksmən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'spɒnsə(r)/","example":"Dozens of companies, including Hewlett-Packard, are sponsoring the event. 包括惠普在内的许多公司都在赞助这项赛事。","word":"sponsor","translation":"v. 赞助","phonetic_us":"/'spɑnsɚ/"},{"word":"spontaneous","phonetic_us":"/spɑn'tenɪəs/","translation":"adj. 自发的","example":"The crowd gave a spontaneous cheer. 人群自发地欢呼起来。","phonetic_uk":"/spɒnˈteɪniəs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'spɔːtsmən/","example":"He’s a very keen sportsman . 他是个非常喜爱运动的人。","translation":"n. 运动员","phonetic_us":"/'spɔrtsmən/","word":"sportsman"},{"example":"a nice quiet spot on the beach 海滩上一个安静的好地方","phonetic_uk":"/spɒt/","translation":"n. 点，斑点；地点，处所；少量；vt.  认出， 发现； 玷污","phonetic_us":"/spɑt/","word":"spot"},{"phonetic_uk":"/spreɪ/","example":"a new hair styling spray 一种新的定型喷发剂","phonetic_us":"/spreɪ/","translation":"n. 浪花；喷雾；v. 喷","word":"spray"},{"word":"spread","phonetic_us":"/sprɛd/","translation":"v. 传播，扩撒","phonetic_uk":"/spred/","example":"The industrial revolution, which started a couple of hundred years ago in Europe, is now spreading across the world. 几百年前始于欧洲的工业革命现在正向全世界扩散。"},{"word":"spring","translation":"v. 跳，跃；n. 跳跃；泉","phonetic_us":"/sprɪŋ/","example":"He sprang to his feet (= stood up suddenly ) and rushed after her. 他腾地站起身，冲过去追她。","phonetic_uk":"/sprɪŋ/"},{"word":"spur","phonetic_us":"/spɝ/","translation":"n. 刺激物；v. 刺激","phonetic_uk":"/spɜː/","example":"The band were spurred on by the success of their last two singles. 乐队因最近两张单曲唱片的成功而深受鼓舞。"},{"phonetic_us":"/skwɛr/","translation":"n. 正方形；广场","word":"square","phonetic_uk":"/skweə/","example":"First of all, draw a square. 首先，画一个正方形。"},{"word":"squeeze","translation":"v. 压，榨","phonetic_us":"/skwiz/","example":"She smiled as he squeezed her hand. 他捏了捏她的手，她笑了。","phonetic_uk":"/skwiːz/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/stə'bɪlɪtɪ/","example":"a period of relative stability 相对稳定的一段时期","word":"stability","phonetic_us":"/stə'bɪləti/","translation":"n. 稳定，稳定性，巩固"},{"translation":"adj. 稳定的，不变的","phonetic_us":"/'stebl/","word":"stable","phonetic_uk":"/'steɪb(ə)l/","example":"A wide base will make the structure much more stable. 宽大的底座会使结构牢固许多。"},{"example":"stacks of dirty dishes 一摞摞脏盘子","phonetic_uk":"/stæk/","word":"stack","translation":"n. 堆，垛；v. 堆积","phonetic_us":"/stæk/"},{"word":"stadium","translation":"n.  运动场， 体育场","phonetic_us":"/'stedɪəm/","example":"the new Olympic Stadium 新的奥林匹克体育场","phonetic_uk":"/'steɪdiəm/"},{"word":"staff","phonetic_us":"/stæf/","translation":"n. 工作人员；参谋","example":"10 staff were allocated to the task. 10名员工被分派做这项任务。","phonetic_uk":"/stɑːf/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/steɪdʒ/","example":"We’re getting to the stage where we hardly ever go out together. 我们快要到几乎不一起外出的地步了。","word":"stage","phonetic_us":"/stedʒ/","translation":"n. 舞台；戏剧；阶段"},{"example":"We’ve decided to stain the shelves blue. 我们决定把架子涂成蓝色。","phonetic_uk":"/steɪn/","phonetic_us":"/sten/","translation":"v. 沾污；给…着色","word":"stain"},{"phonetic_uk":"/steə/","example":"We walked up four flights of stairs (= sets of stairs ) . 我们往上走了四段楼梯。","word":"stair","phonetic_us":"/stɛr/","translation":"n. 楼梯"},{"phonetic_uk":"/steɪk/","example":"They have to win the contract – thousands of jobs are at stake. 他们必须拿下这份合同，这关系到数千个工作岗位。","phonetic_us":"/stek/","translation":"n. 风险","word":"stake"},{"example":"French bread goes stale (= becomes stale ) very quickly. 法式面包极易变味。","phonetic_uk":"/steɪl/","phonetic_us":"/stel/","translation":"adj. 乏味的，没有新意的","word":"stale"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'stændədaiz/","example":"Attempts to standardize English spelling have never been successful. 统一英语拼写的尝试从未成功过。","translation":"v. 使标准化","phonetic_us":"/'stændɚdaɪz/","word":"standardize"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈstændpɔɪnt/","example":"a discussion of marriage from the standpoint of women 从女性角度对婚姻的探讨","translation":"n. 立场","phonetic_us":"/'stændpɔɪnt/","word":"standpoint"},{"example":"She sat there staring into space (= looking for a long time at nothing ) . 她坐在那里，出神地凝视前方。","phonetic_uk":"/steə/","word":"stare","translation":"n&vi.  盯， 凝视","phonetic_us":"/stɛr/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'stɑ:tl/","example":"Sorry, I didn’t mean to startle you. 抱歉，我不是故意吓你一跳的。","phonetic_us":"/'stɑrtl/","translation":"v. 吃惊","word":"startle"},{"word":"startup","phonetic_us":"/'stɑrt'ʌp/","translation":"n. 启动，开办","example":"You should see something like  Figure 3 after startup. 启动后，您应该看到类似于  图 3 的画面。","phonetic_uk":"/stɑ:tʌp/"},{"word":"starve","translation":"v.  挨饿， 饿死","phonetic_us":"/stɑrv/","example":"Thousands of people will starve if food doesn’t reach the city. 如果食品不能运到那座城市，成千上万的人就要饿死。","phonetic_uk":"/stɑːv/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'steɪtmənt/","example":"In an official statement, she formally announced her resignation. 在一份官方声明中，她正式宣布辞职。","word":"statement","phonetic_us":"/'stetmənt/","translation":"n.  陈述， 声明； 结算单， 报表"},{"word":"static","translation":"adj. 静的；静态的","phonetic_us":"/'stætɪk/","phonetic_uk":"/'stætɪk/","example":"Economists predict that house prices will remain static for a long period. 经济学家预测，房价将长期保持稳定。"},{"word":"statistic","translation":"n.  统计数值， 统计资料； 统计学","phonetic_us":"/stə'tɪstɪk/","example":"The statistic comes from a study recently conducted by the British government. 这项统计数据来自英国政府最近进行的一项研究。","phonetic_uk":"/stə'tɪstɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/stə'tɪstɪkl/","translation":"adj. 统计的，统计学的","word":"statistical","example":"The report contains a great deal of statistical information. 该报告包含大量统计资料。","phonetic_uk":"/stə'tɪstɪk(ə)l/"},{"example":"statistics for earnings by different age groups","phonetic_uk":"/stə'tɪstɪks/","translation":"n. 统计学；数据","phonetic_us":"/stə'tɪstɪks/","word":"statistics"},{"word":"statue","phonetic_us":"/'stætʃu/","translation":"n. 塑像，雕像，铸像","phonetic_uk":"/'stætjuː; -tʃuː/","example":"Churchill’s statue stands outside the parliament building. 丘吉尔的塑像矗立在议会大厦外。"},{"example":"These documents have no legal status in Britain. 这些文件在英国并无法律效力。","phonetic_uk":"/'steɪtəs/","phonetic_us":"/ˈstætəs; ˈstetəs/","translation":"n. 地位","word":"status"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'stedɪ/","example":"Paul is making steady progress. 保罗逐渐在进步。","word":"steady","translation":"adj. 稳定的，逐步的","phonetic_us":"/'stɛdi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sti:l/","example":"Boys broke into a shop and stole £45 in cash. 男孩们闯进一家商店，盗走了45英镑现金。","translation":"v. 偷窃","phonetic_us":"/stil/","word":"steal"},{"phonetic_uk":"/stiːm/","example":"Steam rose from the hot tub. 水蒸气从热腾腾的浴缸里升起。","phonetic_us":"/stim/","translation":"n. 蒸汽；v. 蒸发；v. 蒸","word":"steam"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'stiːmə/","example":"The steamer touched at 3 ports. 这艘轮船曾停靠3个港口。","translation":"n. 轮船，汽船","phonetic_us":"/'stimɚ/","word":"steamer"},{"example":"a steel bridge 钢铁大桥","phonetic_uk":"/stiːl/","translation":"n. 钢，钢铁","phonetic_us":"/stil/","word":"steel"},{"phonetic_us":"/stip/","translation":"adj. 急剧升/降的；陡峭的","word":"steep","phonetic_uk":"/stiːp/","example":"The road became rocky and steep. 路变得崎岖陡峭起来。"},{"phonetic_us":"/stɪr/","translation":"v. 驾驶","word":"steer","phonetic_uk":"/stɪə(r)/","example":"He was steering with only one hand. 他只用一只手在驾驶。"},{"word":"stem","translation":"n. 茎，(树)干；v. 起源","phonetic_us":"/stɛm/","example":"long-stemmed wine glasses 高脚酒杯","phonetic_uk":"/stem/"},{"word":"stereotype","phonetic_us":"/'stɛrɪətaɪp/","translation":"n. 老套，固定模式","example":"There's always been a stereotype about successful businessmen. 对成功的商人们总有一种成见。","phonetic_uk":"/'steriətaip/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'stɪki/","translation":"adj. 粘的","word":"sticky","example":"There’s some sticky stuff in your hair. 你的头发上有什么黏糊糊的东西。","phonetic_uk":"/'stɪkɪ/"},{"translation":"adj. 硬的；僵直的","phonetic_us":"/stɪf/","word":"stiff","phonetic_uk":"/stɪf/","example":"I never felt stiff after training until I was in my thirties. 三十岁之前，我训练后从不会感到身体发僵。"},{"translation":"v. 刺激","phonetic_us":"/'stɪmjə'let/","word":"stimulate","phonetic_uk":"/'stɪmjʊleɪt/","example":"Her interest in art was stimulated by her father. 她对艺术的兴趣是她父亲激发的。"},{"example":"He was stung by a bee. 他被蜜蜂蜇了。","phonetic_uk":"/stɪŋ/","word":"sting","translation":"v. 刺；刺痛；vi&n. 刺","phonetic_us":"/stɪŋ/"},{"translation":"v. 搅动；煽动，激起","phonetic_us":"/stɝ/","word":"stir","example":"Stir the paint to make sure it is smooth. 将油漆搅拌至均匀。","phonetic_uk":"/stɜː/"},{"word":"stock","translation":"n. 库存，股票","phonetic_us":"/stɑk/","phonetic_uk":"/stɒk/","example":"the trading of stocks and shares 股票交易"},{"word":"stocking","phonetic_us":"/'stɑkɪŋ/","translation":"n. 长(统)袜","example":"I want you stuffed in my stocking. 我只要你塞在我的袜子里。","phonetic_uk":"/'stɒkɪŋ/"},{"translation":"v. 俯身；弯身；n. 弯腰","phonetic_us":"/stʊp/","word":"stoop","phonetic_uk":"/stuːp/","example":"We had to stoop to pass through the low entrance. 我们得弯腰通过那低矮的入口。"},{"example":"the storage of highly radioactive material 高放射性材料的存放","phonetic_uk":"/'stɔːrɪdʒ/","phonetic_us":"/'stɔrɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 贮藏；贮藏量","word":"storage"},{"word":"store","translation":"n. 贮藏；贮存品；商店","phonetic_us":"/stɔr/","example":"At Christmas the stores stay open late. 在圣诞节期间，商店营业到很晚。","phonetic_uk":"/stɔː/"},{"translation":"n. (层)楼","phonetic_us":"/'stɔri/","word":"storey","example":"...long brick buildings, two storeys high. …很长的两层砖楼。","phonetic_uk":"/'stɔːrɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/stəʊv/","example":"a wood-burning stove 烧木柴的火炉","phonetic_us":"/stov/","translation":"n. 炉，火炉，电炉","word":"stove"},{"phonetic_uk":"/streɪn/","example":"I’ve strained a muscle in my leg. 我的腿有一处肌肉拉伤。","translation":"v. 扭伤，拉伤","phonetic_us":"/stren/","word":"strain"},{"example":"strange noises 奇怪的噪声","phonetic_uk":"/streɪn(d)ʒ/","phonetic_us":"/strendʒ/","translation":"adj. 陌生的；奇怪的","word":"strange"},{"example":"Children must not talk to strangers. 小孩子千万不要同陌生人说话。","phonetic_uk":"/'streɪn(d)ʒə/","translation":"n. 陌生人；新来者","phonetic_us":"/'strendʒɚ/","word":"stranger"},{"phonetic_uk":"/stræp/","example":"a bra strap 胸罩肩带","translation":"n. 带子；v. 捆扎","phonetic_us":"/stræp/","word":"strap"},{"phonetic_us":"/strə'tidʒɪk/","translation":"adj.  对全局有重要意义的， 关键的； 战略的","word":"strategic","phonetic_uk":"/strə'tiːdʒɪk/","example":"UN forces made a strategic withdrawal. 联合国部队作了战略性撤退。"},{"example":"the government’s long-term economic strategy 政府的长期经济策略","phonetic_uk":"/'strætədʒɪ/","word":"strategy","translation":"n. 策略，战略","phonetic_us":"/'strætədʒi/"},{"word":"straw","translation":"n. 稻草，麦杆吸管","phonetic_us":"/strɔ/","phonetic_uk":"/strɔː/","example":"She sipped her lemonade through a straw. 她用吸管吸着柠檬水。"},{"example":"Tears streamed down their faces. 泪水顺着他们的脸颊流下来。","phonetic_uk":"/striːm/","translation":"v.  流出， 涌出；n. 河，溪流；一股，一串","phonetic_us":"/strim/","word":"stream"},{"translation":"v. 加强，巩固","phonetic_us":"/'strɛŋθn/","word":"strengthen","example":"Our friendship has steadily strengthened over the years. 我们的友谊逐年加深。","phonetic_uk":"/'streŋθ(ə)n; -ŋkθ(ə)n/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/stres/","example":"Your headaches are due to stress. 你的头痛是压力造成的。","translation":"n. 压力,重音","phonetic_us":"/strɛs/","word":"stress"},{"phonetic_us":"/'strɛsfl/","translation":"adj. 充满著压力的，充满著紧张的","word":"stressful","phonetic_uk":"/'stresfəl/","example":"Moving to a new house is a very stressful experience. 搬新家是件很劳心的事。"},{"word":"stretch","translation":"v. 伸展；v. 伸；n. 伸展","phonetic_us":"/strɛtʃ/","phonetic_uk":"/stretʃ/","example":"Carl sat up in bed, yawned, and stretched. 卡尔从床上坐起来，打了个呵欠，伸了伸懒 腰。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/strɪkt/","example":"a strict teacher 严格的老师","translation":"adj. 严格的","phonetic_us":"/strɪkt/","word":"strict"},{"phonetic_us":"/'straɪkɪŋ/","translation":"adj.  显著的， 突出的； 惹人注目的， 容貌出众的","word":"striking","phonetic_uk":"/'straɪkɪŋ/","example":"a dark man with striking features 相貌出众、肤色黝黑的男子"},{"phonetic_us":"/strɪŋ/","translation":"n. 线，细绳；一串","word":"string","example":"Her key hung on a string around her neck. 她的钥匙穿了根绳子挂在脖子上。","phonetic_uk":"/strɪŋ/"},{"word":"strip","translation":"v. 剥；夺去；n. 条带","phonetic_us":"/strɪp/","example":"Strip the beds and wash the sheets. 把床单撤下来清洗。","phonetic_uk":"/strɪp/"},{"example":"a shirt with black and white stripes 黑白条纹衬衫","phonetic_uk":"/straɪp/","word":"stripe","phonetic_us":"/straɪp/","translation":"n. 条纹，条子"},{"word":"stroke","phonetic_us":"/strok/","translation":"n. 打，击；鸣声；中风","example":"She died following a massive stroke. 她重度中风后去世了。","phonetic_uk":"/strəʊk/"},{"word":"structural","phonetic_us":"/'strʌktʃərəl/","translation":"adj. 结构的，构造的","phonetic_uk":"/'strʌktʃ(ə)r(ə)l/","example":"structural changes in the computer industry 电脑行业的结构性改变"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈstrʌktʃə(r)/","example":"challenges to the existing power structure 对现有权力结构的挑战","translation":"n. 结构","phonetic_us":"/'strʌktʃɚ/","word":"structure"},{"example":"They had to struggle against all kinds of adversity. 他们不得不同各种困境斗争。","phonetic_uk":"/'strʌɡl/","word":"struggle","translation":"v. 搏斗","phonetic_us":"/'strʌɡl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'stjuːdiəu/","example":"a TV studio 电视演播室","word":"studio","phonetic_us":"/'studɪo/","translation":"n.  画室， 摄影室； 播音室， 录音室， 摄影棚"},{"translation":"n. 材料；v. 装，填，塞","phonetic_us":"/stʌf/","word":"stuff","example":"Volunteers were busy stuffing envelopes. 志愿者正忙着装信封。","phonetic_uk":"/stʌf/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌsʌbdɪˈvɪʒn/","example":"Months are a conventional subdivision of the year. 月份是年的常规分支。","word":"subdivision","phonetic_us":"/,sʌbdɪ'vɪʒn/","translation":"n. 分区"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈsʌbdʒɪkt;(for adj.)ˈsʌbdʒɪkt;(for v.)səbˈdʒekt/","example":"Paul has strong opinions on most subjects. 保罗在大多数问题上观点激烈。","phonetic_us":"/ˈsʌbdʒɪkt;(for adj.)ˈsʌbdʒɪkt;(for v.)səbˈdʒɛkt/","translation":"n.  题目； 学科； 主语；vt.  使隶属","word":"subject"},{"translation":"adj. 水下的；n. 潜水艇","phonetic_us":"/,sʌbmə'rin/","word":"submarine","example":"The captain dived his submarine deep to escape from the destroyers. 海军上校使他的潜艇深深下潜以逃避驱逐艇。","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌbməriːn; sʌbmə'riːn/"},{"example":"Alice submerged herself in work to try and forget about Tom. 艾丽斯埋头工作，试图忘记汤姆。","phonetic_uk":"/səb'mɜːdʒ/","phonetic_us":"/səb'mɝdʒ/","translation":"v. 浸没；v. 潜入水中","word":"submerge"},{"phonetic_uk":"/səbˈmɪt/","example":"They submitted their reports to the chancellor yesterday. 他们昨天向财政大臣提交了他们的报告。","translation":"v. 提交","phonetic_us":"/səb'mɪt/","word":"submit"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sʌbsɪkw(ə)nt/","example":"These skills were passed on to subsequent generations. 这些技能代代相传。","word":"subsequent","translation":"adj. 随后的，后来的","phonetic_us":"/'sʌbsɪkwənt/"},{"example":"Around the world, governments have subsidized the housing of middle- and upper-income groups. 全世界各政府都补贴过中高收入人群的住房。","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌbsɪdaɪz/","word":"subsidize","phonetic_us":"/'sʌbsə'daɪz/","translation":"v. 提供补贴"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sʌbst(ə)ns/","example":"The leaves were covered with a strange sticky substance. 树叶上覆着一层黏糊糊的怪东西。","translation":"n. 物质；实质；本旨","phonetic_us":"/'sʌbstəns/","word":"substance"},{"phonetic_us":"/səbˈstænʃəl/","translation":"adj. 大量的","word":"substantial","example":"We have the support of a substantial number of parents. 我们有相当多家长的支持。","phonetic_uk":"/səb'stænʃl/"},{"translation":"v & n. 代替","phonetic_us":"/'sʌbstɪtut/","word":"substitute","example":"Germany brought on a substitute at half time. 德国队在比赛半场时换上一名替补队员。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsʌbstɪtju:t/"},{"word":"subtract","translation":"v. 减，减去，去掉","phonetic_us":"/səb'trækt/","phonetic_uk":"/səb'trækt/","example":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sʌbɜːb/","example":"a London suburb 一个伦敦郊区","word":"suburb","phonetic_us":"/'sʌbɝb/","translation":"n.  郊区， 郊外， 近郊"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sʌbweɪ/","example":"the New York City subway 纽约市的地铁","word":"subway","phonetic_us":"/'sʌbwe/","translation":"n. 地道；地下铁路"},{"example":"Over the succeeding weeks things went from bad to worse. 接下来的几周，事情越来越糟。","phonetic_uk":"/sək'siːdɪŋ/","word":"succeeding","translation":"adj.  以后的， 随后的","phonetic_us":""},{"example":"She won the championship four times in succession. 她连续四次夺得冠军。","phonetic_uk":"/sək'seʃ(ə)n/","word":"succession","phonetic_us":"/sək'sɛʃən/","translation":"n. 连续；继任，继承"},{"word":"successive","phonetic_us":"/sək'sɛsɪv/","translation":"adj. 连续的；接连的","example":"The team has had five successive victories. 这支球队已经连胜五场了。","phonetic_uk":"/sək'sesɪv/"},{"word":"suck","translation":"v. 吸，吮，啜；吸收","phonetic_us":"/sʌk/","phonetic_uk":"/sʌk/","example":"Don’t suck your thumb, dear. 不要吮大拇指，宝贝。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sʌfə(r)/","example":"At least he died suddenly and didn’t suffer. 至少他死得突然，没有遭罪。","phonetic_us":"/'sʌfɚ/","translation":"v. 受痛苦","word":"suffer"},{"translation":"adj. 足够的","phonetic_us":"/səˈfɪʃənt/","word":"sufficient","phonetic_uk":"/səˈfɪʃnt/","example":"We can only prosecute if there is sufficient evidence. 有了足够的证据，我们才能提出起诉。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sə'dʒestʃən/","example":"Any suggestions would be welcome. 任何建议都欢迎。","word":"suggestion","phonetic_us":"/sə'dʒɛstʃən/","translation":"n.  建议， 意见； 细微的迹象； 暗示"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'suːɪsaɪd/","example":"More people commit suicide at Christmas than at any other time. 圣诞节期间自杀的人比其他任何时候都多。","translation":"n&v.  自杀","phonetic_us":"/'suɪsaɪd/","word":"suicide"},{"example":"Johnson has filed suit against her. 约翰逊对她提起了诉讼。","phonetic_uk":"/sju:t; su:t/","phonetic_us":"/sut/","translation":"n. 起拆，诉讼；v. 适合","word":"suit"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sʌlfɚ/","translation":"n. 硫(磺)，硫黄","word":"sulfur","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌlfə/"},{"translation":"n. 硫(磺)，硫黄","phonetic_us":"/'sʌlfə/","word":"sulphur","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌlfə/","example":"Burning sulphur creates poisonous fumes. 燃烧的硫磺会产生有毒烟雾。"},{"translation":"n. 总数；金额；v. 共计","phonetic_us":"/sʌm/","word":"sum","example":"He owes me a large sum of money . 他欠我一大笔钱。","phonetic_uk":"/sʌm/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sʌməraiz/","example":"The authors summarize their views in the introduction. 作者在序言里概述了他们的观点。","translation":"v. 概括，概述，总结","phonetic_us":"/'sʌməraɪz/","word":"summarize"},{"word":"summary","translation":"adj.  概括的， 概要的； 实时的， 即决的；n. 摘要，概要，一览","phonetic_us":"/'sʌməri/","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌməri/","example":"a summary execution 立即处决"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sʌmɪt/","translation":"n.  最高点， 峰顶； 最高级会议","word":"summit","example":"the European summit 欧洲首脑会议","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌmɪt/"},{"example":"The water sparkled in the bright sunlight. 水面在灿烂的阳光下闪闪发亮。","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌnlaɪt/","translation":"n.  日光， 阳光","phonetic_us":"/'sʌnlaɪt/","word":"sunlight"},{"word":"sunrise","phonetic_us":"/'sʌnraɪz/","translation":"n.  日出； 朝霞","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌnraɪz/","example":"a picture of sunrise over Mount Fuji 富士山日出的照片"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sʌnsɛt/","translation":"n.  日落； 晚霞","word":"sunset","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌnset/","example":"a glorious sunset 壮丽的日落景象"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sʌnʃaɪn/","example":"We had three days of spring sunshine. 我们享受了三天的春日阳光。","phonetic_us":"/'sʌnʃaɪn/","translation":"n.  日光， 阳光","word":"sunshine"},{"translation":"adj.  极好的； 高质量的","phonetic_us":"//suːˈpɜːrb//","word":"superb","example":"The food was superb. 食物好吃极了。","phonetic_uk":"/sjʊː'pɜːb; sʊː'pɜːb/"},{"example":"They only have the most superficial understanding of prison life. 他们对监狱生活只有最粗浅的了解。","phonetic_uk":"/,supə'fɪʃl/","phonetic_us":"/,supɚ'fɪʃl/","translation":"adj. 肤浅的","word":"superficial"},{"phonetic_uk":"/su:'piəriə/","example":"She had that superior tone of voice. 她带着那种傲慢的语气。","word":"superior","phonetic_us":"/səˈpɪriər/","translation":"adj. 上级的，较高的；n. 上级，长官"},{"phonetic_us":"/,sʊpɚ'vɪʒən/","translation":"n. 监督","word":"supervision","example":"The baby needs constant supervision. 宝宝时刻都要有人照看。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌsju:pə'vɪʒn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sʌplɪmənt/","translation":"n&vt. 增补，补充","word":"supplement","phonetic_uk":"/'sʌplɪm(ə)nt/","example":"vitamins and other dietary supplements 各种维生素和其他膳食补充剂"},{"translation":"n&vt.  供给， 供应","phonetic_us":"/sə'plaɪ/","word":"supply","phonetic_uk":"/sə'plaɪ/","example":"The nation’s fuel supplies will not last forever. 这个国家的燃料供应不会无穷无尽。"},{"example":"The bill was supported by a large majority in the Senate. 这项法案得到参议院绝大多数人的支持。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'pɔːt/","translation":"vt. 支撑；支持；供养；证实；n.  支持， 支撑物， 支持者","phonetic_us":"/sə'pɔrt/","word":"support"},{"example":"There were many more deaths than was first supposed. 死亡人数远远超过最初的预料。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'pəuz/","word":"suppose","phonetic_us":"/sə'poz/","translation":"v. 料想，以为；假定；期望"},{"phonetic_us":"/suˈprim/","translation":"adj. 最高的；最大的","word":"supreme","phonetic_uk":"/suː'priːm/","example":"the Supreme Allied Commander in Europe 欧洲盟军最高指挥官"},{"word":"surf","phonetic_us":"/sɝf/","translation":"v. 冲浪","example":"I'm going to buy a surfboard and learn to surf. 我要去买个冲浪板来学冲浪。","phonetic_uk":"/sɜ:f/"},{"translation":"vi. 蜂拥而出；洋溢，奔放；汹涌，奔腾；n.  大浪， 波涛； 高涨； 汹涌","phonetic_us":"/sɝdʒ/","word":"surge","phonetic_uk":"/sɜːdʒ/","example":"The photographers and cameramen surged forward. 那些摄影和摄像师们涌向前去。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːdʒ(ə)rɪ/","example":"Dr. Hanson is in surgery. 汉森医生在手术室。","phonetic_us":"/'sɝdʒəri/","translation":"n. 外科，外科手术","word":"surgery"},{"phonetic_uk":"/səˈpɑ:s/","example":"He had surpassed all our expectations . 他超越了我们所有的预期。","translation":"v. 超过","phonetic_us":"/sə'pæs/","word":"surpass"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'sɜːpləs/","example":"Ethiopia has no surplus food. 埃塞俄比亚没有多余的食物。","phonetic_us":"/'sɝpləs/","translation":"adj.  过剩的， 多余的；n. 过剩，剩余，盈余","word":"surplus"},{"phonetic_us":"/sə'rɛndɚ/","translation":"v. 交出；v. 投降","word":"surrender","phonetic_uk":"/sə'rendə/","example":"Nadja had to fill out forms surrendering all rights to her property. 纳贾不得不填写表格，放弃对她财产的所有权利。"},{"word":"surround","phonetic_us":"/sə'raʊnd/","translation":"vt.  围， 围绕； 圈住","example":"He glared at the people who surrounded the tent. 他怒视着围住帐篷的那些人。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'raund/"},{"phonetic_us":"/sə'raʊndɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 附近的；四周的","word":"surrounding","example":"Troops sealed off the surrounding area . 军队封锁了周围地区。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'raundɪŋ/"},{"word":"surroundings","phonetic_us":"/sə'raʊndɪŋz/","translation":"n. 周围的事物，环境","example":"I need to work in pleasant surroundings. 我需要在舒适的环境下工作。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'raʊndɪŋz/"},{"example":"Of the 100 companies surveyed, 10% had a turnover of £50 m to £99 m. 被调查的 100 家公司中，10% 的公司营业额在 5,000 万到 9,900 万英镑之间。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɜ:veɪ/","word":"survey","phonetic_us":"/ˈsɝˌve; (for v.) sɝˈve/","translation":"v. 调查，审视，仔细考虑；n. 勘测，测量，测绘，调查"},{"translation":"n. 幸存","phonetic_us":"/sɚ'vaɪvl/","word":"survival","phonetic_uk":"/səˈvaɪvl/","example":"The doctors gave him a one in ten chance of survival . 医生说他有十分之一的生存希望。"},{"translation":"v. 幸免于；v. 活下来","phonetic_us":"/sɚ'vaɪv/","word":"survive","example":"When the market economy is introduced, many factories will not survive. 一旦推行市场经济，很多工厂将无法存活下去。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'vaɪv/"},{"word":"survivor","translation":"n.  生还者； 残存物","phonetic_us":"/sɚ'vaɪvɚ/","example":"Don’t worry about Kurt; he’s a survivor. 不用担心库尔特，他是个坚强的人。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'vaɪvə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/sʌspɛkt; (for v.) səˈspɛkt/","translation":"v. 怀疑，猜想；n. 嫌疑犯","word":"suspect","example":"She strongly suspected he was lying to her. 她非常怀疑他在对她撒谎。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'spekt/"},{"example":"...instruments that are suspended on cables. …悬挂在电缆上的仪器。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'spend/","word":"suspend","phonetic_us":"/sə'spɛnd/","translation":"v. 吊，悬；推迟"},{"phonetic_us":"","translation":"n. 怀疑，疑心，猜疑","word":"suspicion","example":"","phonetic_uk":""},{"example":"His reluctance to answer my questions made me suspicious . 他不愿回答我的问题，这引起我的怀疑。","phonetic_uk":"/sə'spɪʃəs/","word":"suspicious","translation":"adj. 怀疑的；可疑的","phonetic_us":"/sə'spɪʃəs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sə'steɪn/","example":"Wants, or desires, are things we would like to have but they do not sustain us. 想法或愿望，是我们想要拥有的东西但是他们不能维持我们的生活。","word":"sustain","phonetic_us":"/sə'sten/","translation":"n. 维持"},{"example":"The government should do more to promote sustainable agriculture. 政府应该做更多工作来推动可持续农业的发展。","phonetic_uk":"/səˈsteɪnəbl/","phonetic_us":"/sə'stenəbl/","translation":"adj. 可持续的","word":"sustainable"},{"example":"He swallowed the last of his coffee and asked for the bill. 他喝完最后一口咖啡，要求结账。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈswɒləʊ/","word":"swallow","translation":"v. 咽下，吞下","phonetic_us":"/'swɑlo/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sweɪ/","example":"Don’t allow yourself to be swayed by his promises. 你可不要听了他的许诺就改变主意呀。","word":"sway","phonetic_us":"/swe/","translation":"v. 影响"},{"example":"Remember that you have sworn an oath and so must tell the truth. 记住你已经宣过誓了，所以必须讲真话。","phonetic_uk":"/sweə/","word":"swear","phonetic_us":"/swɛr/","translation":"v. 宣(誓)；v. 诅咒"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'swetə/","word":"sweater","phonetic_us":"/'swɛtɚ/","translation":"n. 厚运动衫，毛线衫"},{"phonetic_uk":"/swiːp/","example":"Bert swept the path in front of the house. 伯特清扫了屋前的小路。","translation":"v. 扫；刮起；扫过","phonetic_us":"/swip/","word":"sweep"},{"translation":"v. 膨胀；隆起；增长","phonetic_us":"/swɛl/","word":"swell","phonetic_uk":"/swel/","example":"The wind swelled the sails. 风鼓起了船帆。"},{"phonetic_us":"/swɪft/","translation":"adj. 迅速的","word":"swift","example":"My letter received a swift reply. 我的信很快就得到了回复。","phonetic_uk":"/swɪft/"},{"example":"Let your arms swing as you walk. 边走边摆动双臂。","phonetic_uk":"/swɪŋ/","word":"swing","translation":"v. 摇摆；回转；n. 摇摆","phonetic_us":"/swɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/swɪtʃ/","example":"The terrorists will switch tactics . 恐怖分子会改变战术。","phonetic_us":"/swɪtʃ/","translation":"v. 转变，改变","word":"switch"},{"example":"The treaty hung like a sword of Damocles over French politics. 这个条约好像一把达摩克利斯之剑悬在法国政坛之上。","phonetic_uk":"/sɔːd/","word":"sword","phonetic_us":"/sɔːrd/","translation":"n. 剑，刀"},{"phonetic_us":"/'sɪmbl/","translation":"n. 象征，标志","word":"symbol","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪmbl/","example":"The symbol on the packet is a guarantee that the food has been produced organically. 包装盒上的这个标识保证这种食物是有机生产的。"},{"example":"Crime often symbolizes a wider social problem. 犯罪问题往往反映出更广泛的社会问题。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈsɪmbəlaɪz/","word":"symbolize","phonetic_us":"/'sɪmbəlaɪz/","translation":"v. 象征"},{"phonetic_uk":"/sɪmpə'θetɪk/","example":"a sympathetic friend 一个有同情心的朋友","word":"sympathetic","phonetic_us":"/,sɪmpə'θɛtɪk/","translation":"adj. 同情的；和谐的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'simpəθaiz/","example":"I sympathize, but I don’t know how to help. 我很同情，但不知道如何帮忙。","phonetic_us":"/'sɪmpə'θaɪz/","translation":"v. 同情；同感，共鸣","word":"sympathize"},{"word":"sympathy","phonetic_us":"/'sɪmpəθi/","translation":"n. 同情心","example":"Our sympathies are with the families of the victims. 我们向受害者家庭表示慰问。","phonetic_uk":"/'simpəθi/"},{"word":"symptom","phonetic_us":"/'sɪmptəm/","translation":"n. 症状","example":"One of the most common symptoms of schizophrenia is hearing imaginary voices. 精神分裂症最常见的症状之一是幻听。","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪm(p)təm/"},{"translation":"adj. 合成的，人造的","phonetic_us":"/sɪn'θɛtɪk/","word":"synthetic","example":"synthetic chemicals 合成化学品","phonetic_uk":"/sɪnˈθetɪk/"},{"translation":"n.  系统； 制度， 体制； 方法， 做法； 身体","phonetic_us":"/'sɪstəm/","word":"system","example":"an alarm system 警报系统","phonetic_uk":"/'sɪstəm/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌsɪstə'mætɪk(l)/","example":"They went about their business in a systematic way. 他们按部就班地做生意。","phonetic_us":"/'sɪstə'mætɪk/","translation":"adj.  有系统的， 有计划的","word":"systematic"},{"example":"Excellent ability of systematical management. 有极强的系统管理能力。","phonetic_uk":"","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 有系统的；有计划的","word":"systematical"},{"translation":"v. 处理","phonetic_us":"/'tækl/","word":"tackle","phonetic_uk":"/'tæk(ə)l/","example":"There is more than one way to tackle the problem. 解决这个问题不止一个办法。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tæg/","example":"Staff wore name tags and called inmates by their first names. 工作人员戴着姓名标签，对同僚直呼其名。","phonetic_us":"/tæɡ/","translation":"n. 附加语；标签","word":"tag"},{"phonetic_us":"/'telɚ/","translation":"v. 调整使适应","word":"tailor","phonetic_uk":"/'teɪlə(r)/","example":"We can tailor the programme to the patient's needs. 我们可以根据病人的需要调整这个方案。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'teɪkɔ:f/","example":"What time is takeoff? 起飞时间是什么时候？","phonetic_us":"/'tekɔf/","translation":"n. 起飞","word":"takeoff"},{"example":"a book of old Japanese folk tales 日本古老民间故事书","phonetic_uk":"/teɪl/","word":"tale","translation":"n. 故事，传说","phonetic_us":"/tel/"},{"translation":"n. 天才；才能；人才","phonetic_us":"/'tælənt/","word":"talent","example":"He has a lot of talent , and his work is fresh and interesting. 他很有天赋，作品新颖有趣。","phonetic_uk":"/'tælənt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tɔːk/","example":"I could hear Sarah and Andy talking in the next room. 我听到萨拉和安迪在隔壁讲话。","word":"talk","phonetic_us":"/tɔk/","translation":"v. 讲话；v. 谈论"},{"phonetic_uk":"/teɪm/","example":"tame elephants 驯养的大象","phonetic_us":"/teɪm/","translation":"adj. 驯服的；顺从的","word":"tame"},{"phonetic_us":"/tæŋk/","translation":"n. 油箱，水箱","word":"tank","example":"The water tank is leaking. 水箱在漏水。","phonetic_uk":"/tæŋk/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tæp/","example":"He tapped the table nervously with his fingers. 他紧张地用手指轻轻地敲打桌子。","phonetic_us":"/tæp/","translation":"vt&vi&n. 轻叩","word":"tap"},{"word":"target","translation":"n. 目标；vt.  把…作为目标； 瞄准","phonetic_us":"/'tɑrɡɪt/","phonetic_uk":"/'tɑːgɪt/","example":"There is no target date for completion of the new project. 这个新的项目何时完工没有预定日期。"},{"phonetic_us":"/tæsk/","translation":"n. 任务，工作","word":"task","phonetic_uk":"/tɑːsk/","example":"Sara had the task of preparing the agenda for meetings. 萨拉的任务是准备会议议程。"},{"word":"taste","phonetic_us":"/test/","translation":"n. 味觉，品味","phonetic_uk":"/teɪst/","example":"It palls on my taste. 我觉得它毫无滋味。"},{"word":"tasteless","phonetic_us":"/'testləs/","translation":"adj. 无味的","example":"The fish was mushy and tasteless. 这鱼烧得烂而无味。","phonetic_uk":"/'teɪstləs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tæks/","example":"No-one enjoys paying tax. 没人喜欢缴税。","phonetic_us":"/tæks/","translation":"n. 税，税款；负担；vt.  对…征税； 使负担重， 使费尽力气","word":"tax"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈteknɪkl/","example":"Our staff will be available to give you technical support . 有我们的员工向你提供技术支持。","word":"technical","translation":"adj. 技术的","phonetic_us":"/'tɛknɪkl/"},{"word":"technician","translation":"n. 技术员，技师","phonetic_us":"/tɛk'nɪʃən/","example":"a laboratory technician 实验室技术人员","phonetic_uk":"/tek'nɪʃ(ə)n/"},{"example":"He’s a great player, with brilliant technique. 他是个伟大的球员，球技十分精湛。","phonetic_uk":"/tek'ni:k/","phonetic_us":"/tɛk'nik/","translation":"n. 技术，技能；技巧，手艺","word":"technique"},{"phonetic_us":"/tɛkˈnɑlədʒɪ/","translation":"n.  工艺学； 工艺， 技术","word":"technology","example":"Modern technology makes moving money around much easier than it used to be. 现代科技使货币流动比以前便捷得多。","phonetic_uk":"/tek'nɒlədʒi/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈti:diəs/","example":"The audience coughed down the tedious speaker. 听众用咳嗽声阻挠演讲人的沉闷发言。","word":"tedious","translation":"adj. 单调沉闷的","phonetic_us":"/'tidɪəs/"},{"word":"teenager","phonetic_us":"/'tinedʒɚ/","translation":"n.  青少年","phonetic_uk":"/'tiːneɪdʒə/","example":"a TV sex education series aimed at teenagers 一部针对青少年的性教育电视系列片"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'telɪgræm/","example":"The president received a briefing by telegram. 总裁收到了一份电报简报。","word":"telegram","translation":"n. 电报","phonetic_us":"/'tɛlɪɡræm/"},{"word":"telescope","translation":"n. 望远镜","phonetic_us":"/'tɛlɪskop/","example":"The captain was rectifying his telescope. 船长正在调他的望远镜。","phonetic_uk":"/'telɪskəʊp/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'tɛmpɚ/","translation":"n. 韧度；心情，情绪；vt.  调和， 使缓和； 【冶】使回火","word":"temper","example":"Pete hit his brother in a fit of temper . 皮特一气之下打了他弟弟。","phonetic_uk":"/'tempə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈtempl/","example":"","word":"temple","phonetic_us":"/'tɛmpl/","translation":"n. 圣堂，神殿，庙宇"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'temp(ə)rərɪ/","example":"temporary pain relief 疼痛的暂时缓解","translation":"adj. 暂时的，临时的","phonetic_us":"/'tɛmpə'rɛri/","word":"temporary"},{"word":"tempt","phonetic_us":"/tɛmpt/","translation":"v. 引诱，诱惑；吸引","example":"If you leave valuables in your car it will tempt thieves. 如果把贵重物品留在车上，会招来小偷的。","phonetic_uk":"/tem(p)t/"},{"example":"Resist the temptation to buy the item until you’re certain you need it. 要抵挡住购买的诱惑，除非你确有需要。","phonetic_uk":"/tempˈteɪʃn/","word":"temptation","phonetic_us":"/tɛmp'teʃən/","translation":"n. 诱惑，引诱"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈtemptɪŋ/","example":"a tempting job offer 一个诱人的工作机会","translation":"adj. 诱人的，吸引人的","phonetic_us":"/'tɛmptɪŋ/","word":"tempting"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tend/","example":"Sofia was in the bedroom tending to her son. 索菲娅在卧室里照料她的儿子。","word":"tend","translation":"v. 照管，照料，护理","phonetic_us":"/tɛnd/"},{"word":"tendency","phonetic_us":"/'tɛndənsi/","translation":"n. 趋向，趋势，倾向","phonetic_uk":"/'tend(ə)nsɪ/","example":"children with aggressive or anti-social tendencies 具有攻击性倾向或反社会倾向的儿童"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'tendə/","example":"Continue cooking until the meat is tender. 把肉一直烧到松软为止。","word":"tender","phonetic_us":"/'tɛndɚ/","translation":"adj. 嫩的；脆弱的"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tens/","example":"It was as though Corinne was already dead: they were speaking of her in the past tense. 就好像科琳已经死了似的：他们当时在用过去时态谈起她。","word":"tense","phonetic_us":"/tɛns/","translation":"n. 时态，时"},{"word":"tension","translation":"n. 紧张","phonetic_us":"/'tɛnʃən/","example":"The tension was becoming unbearable, and I wanted to scream. 这种紧张变得难以忍受，我真想大声尖叫。","phonetic_uk":"/'tenʃn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tent/","example":"We looked for a flat spot where we could pitch our tent (= put up our tent ) . 我们寻找一个平缓的地方搭帐篷。","word":"tent","phonetic_us":"/tɛnt/","translation":"n. 帐篷"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'tɜːmənl/","example":"the airport’s passenger terminal 机场航站楼","word":"terminal","phonetic_us":"/ˈtɜːrmɪnl/","translation":"n. 终点站，航空站"},{"example":"The hotel was absolutely terrible. 这家宾馆糟糕透了。","phonetic_uk":"/'terɪb(ə)l/","translation":"adj. 可怕的；极度的","phonetic_us":"/'tɛrəbl/","word":"terrible"},{"phonetic_us":"/'tɛrəbli/","translation":"adv. 可怕地，非常","word":"terribly","phonetic_uk":"/'terəbli/","example":"I’m terribly sorry to have kept you waiting. 很抱歉，让你久等了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'tɛrətɔri/","translation":"n. 领土，领域","word":"territory","phonetic_uk":"/'terɪt(ə)rɪ/","example":"Hong Kong is a Chinese territory. 香港是中国的领土。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'terə/","example":"There was a look of sheer terror (= complete terror ) on his face. 他脸上的表情异常惊恐。","word":"terror","phonetic_us":"/'tɛrɚ/","translation":"n. 恐怖，惊骇"},{"word":"textile","translation":"n. n.；n. 纺织品；adj. 纺织的","phonetic_us":"/'tɛkstaɪl/","phonetic_uk":"/'tekstaɪl/","example":"Their main exports are textiles, especially silk and cotton. 他们的主要出口商品是纺织品，尤其是丝绸和棉布。"},{"example":"The book’s theme is the conflict between love and duty. 本书的主题是爱与责任之间的冲突。","phonetic_uk":"/θiːm/","translation":"n.  主题， 题目","phonetic_us":"/θim/","word":"theme"},{"phonetic_uk":"/θɪə'retɪk(ə)l/","example":"theoretical physics 理论物理","translation":"adj. 理论(上)的","phonetic_us":"/,θiə'rɛtɪkəl/","word":"theoretical"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'θɪərɪ/","example":"Freudian theory has had a great influence on psychology. 弗洛伊德理论对心理学产生过巨大影响。","translation":"n. 理论","phonetic_us":"/'θiəri/","word":"theory"},{"word":"therapy","phonetic_us":"/'θɛrəpi/","translation":"n. 疗法 治疗","phonetic_uk":"/'θerəpi/","example":"new drug therapies 新的药物疗法"},{"translation":"adv. 因此，从而，由此","phonetic_us":"/,ðɛr'baɪ/","word":"thereby","example":"Our bodies can sweat, thereby losing heat by evaporation. 我们的身体会流汗，由此能通过蒸发散热。","phonetic_uk":"/ðeə'baɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ðeəfɔː/","example":"Their car was bigger and therefore more comfortable. 他们的车大些，所以更舒适些。","phonetic_us":"/'ðɛrfɔr/","translation":"adv. 因此，所以","word":"therefore"},{"word":"thermometer","phonetic_us":"/θɚ'mɑmɪtɚ/","translation":"n. 温度计，寒暑表","phonetic_uk":"/θə'mɒmɪtə/","example":"The thermometer registered over 100˚C. 温度计显示高于100摄氏度。"},{"translation":"adv.  厚厚地；adj. 厚的，密的，浓的；不清楚的，口音重的","phonetic_us":"/θɪk/","word":"thick","phonetic_uk":"/θɪk/","example":"peanut butter spread thick 抹得很厚的花生酱"},{"example":"The thickness of the walls is 5 feet. 墙体厚度为5英尺。","phonetic_uk":"/'θɪknɪs/","word":"thickness","phonetic_us":"/ˈθɪknɪs/","translation":"n. 厚(度)；密(度)"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'θɪŋkɪŋ/","example":"the thinking man’s pop band 有思想的男士喜欢的流行乐队","word":"thinking","phonetic_us":"/'θɪŋkɪŋ/","translation":"adj.  深思的， 有理性的；n. 想法，意见，见解"},{"example":"Can I have a glass of water? I’m really thirsty. 我能喝一杯水吗？ 我太渴了。","phonetic_uk":"/'θɜːsti/","translation":"adj.  渴的； 渴望的","phonetic_us":"/'θɝsti/","word":"thirsty"},{"phonetic_us":"/ˈθʌrəʊ; θʌro/","translation":"adj. 彻底的；详尽的","word":"thorough","example":"The doctor gave him a thorough check-up. 医生给他做了一次全面的体检。","phonetic_uk":"/'θʌrə/"},{"word":"thoughtful","translation":"adj. 沉思的；体贴的","phonetic_us":"/'θɔtfl/","example":"Paul is very thoughtful. 保罗非常体贴人。","phonetic_uk":"/'θɔːtfʊl; -f(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_us":"/θrɛd/","translation":"n. 线；丝；螺纹；头绪","word":"thread","phonetic_uk":"/θred/","example":"I’m looking for a needle and thread. 我在找针线。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/θret/","example":"Your threats don’t scare me. 你的那些威胁吓不倒我。","phonetic_us":"/θrɛt/","translation":"n. 威胁，恐吓，凶兆","word":"threat"},{"example":"Postal workers are threatening a strike if they don’t receive a pay increase. 邮政工人威胁如果不加薪，他们就要罢工。","phonetic_uk":"/'θretn/","phonetic_us":"/'θrɛtn/","translation":"v. 威胁","word":"threaten"},{"translation":"v. 兴旺，繁荣，旺盛","phonetic_us":"/θraɪv/","word":"thrive","phonetic_uk":"/θraɪv/","example":"plants that thrive in tropical rain forests 在热带雨林蓬勃生长的植物"},{"word":"throat","phonetic_us":"/θrot/","translation":"n. 咽喉，喉咙；嗓音","example":"The singer complained of a sore throat after Wednesday’s show. 星期三演出后，这位歌手说喉咙痛。","phonetic_uk":"/θrəʊt/"},{"example":"a large organization with offices throughout the world 在世界各地都设有办事处的一家大型机构","phonetic_uk":"/θruː'aʊt/","word":"throughout","phonetic_us":"/θrʊ'aʊt/","translation":"prep. 遍及；adv. 到处"},{"phonetic_us":"/θrʌst/","translation":"v. 插，刺；n. 插；讽刺","word":"thrust","phonetic_uk":"/θrʌst/","example":"They thrust him into the back of a jeep. 他们把他猛推入吉普车的后部。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/θʌm/","example":"I thumbed a lift into town. 我拦顺路车进了城。","phonetic_us":"/θʌm/","translation":"v.  示意要求搭车；n. 拇指","word":"thumb"},{"phonetic_us":"/'θʌndɚ/","translation":"n. 雷；v. 打雷；v. 吼出","word":"thunder","example":"We were woken in the night by thunder. 晚上我们被雷声惊醒。","phonetic_uk":"/'θʌndə/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ðʌs/","example":"Most of the evidence was destroyed in the fire. Thus it would be almost impossible to prove him guilty. 大多数证据已在大火中烧毁，因而要证明他有罪几乎是不可能的。","translation":"adv. 如此，这样；因而","phonetic_us":"/ðʌs/","word":"thus"},{"example":"Strong tides make swimming dangerous. 遇上大潮时游泳很危险。","phonetic_uk":"/taɪd/","word":"tide","phonetic_us":"/taɪd/","translation":"n & v. 顺应潮水航行"},{"word":"tidy","translation":"adj. 整洁的；整齐的","phonetic_us":"/'taɪdi/","phonetic_uk":"/'taɪdɪ/","example":"a tidy desk 整洁的书桌"},{"example":"","phonetic_uk":"/'taɪtn/","word":"tighten","translation":"adj. 紧的，紧缩的","phonetic_us":"/'taɪtn/"},{"translation":"n.  木材， 原木； 大木料， 栋木","phonetic_us":"/'tɪmbɚ/","word":"timber","phonetic_uk":"/'tɪmbə/","example":"a bench made of timber 木制长椅"},{"example":"an old tin bath 旧的锡浴缸","phonetic_uk":"/tɪn/","translation":"n. 锡；罐头","phonetic_us":"/tɪn/","word":"tin"},{"example":"a tiny community in the Midwest 中西部地区一个极小的社区","phonetic_uk":"/'taɪnɪ/","word":"tiny","phonetic_us":"/'taɪni/","translation":"adj. 微小的"},{"translation":"v. 轻击；v. 给小费","phonetic_us":"/tɪp/","word":"tip","phonetic_uk":"/tɪp/","example":"Did you tip the waiter? 你给侍应生小费了吗？"},{"word":"tire","translation":"v. 疲劳，累；厌倦","phonetic_us":"/'taɪɚ/","example":"As we neared the summit, we were tiring fast. 接近山顶时，我们感到越来越累了。","phonetic_uk":"/taɪə/"},{"example":"As we age we lose muscle tissue. 随着年纪的增大，我们会失去一些肌肉组织。","phonetic_uk":"/'tɪʃuː; 'tɪsjuː/","phonetic_us":"/'tɪʃu/","translation":"n. 薄绢；薄纸；组织","word":"tissue"},{"example":"\"Patience and Sarah\" was first published in 1969 under the title \"A Place for Us.\" 《耐心与萨拉》于1969年以《我们的地方》为书名首次出版。","phonetic_uk":"/'taɪtl/","translation":"n.  标题， 题目； 称号， 头衔； 权利， 权益","phonetic_us":"/'taɪtl/","word":"title"},{"example":"I had a piece of toast for breakfast. 我早饭吃了一片吐司。","phonetic_uk":"/təʊst/","translation":"n. 烤面包；v. 烘，烤","phonetic_us":"/tost/","word":"toast"},{"translation":"n. 脚趾，足尖","phonetic_us":"/to/","word":"toe","phonetic_uk":"/təʊ/","example":"He stubbed his toe (= hurt it by kicking it against something ) on a rock. 他的脚趾踢到一块石头上受了伤。"},{"translation":"n. 厕所，盥洗室，浴室","phonetic_us":"/'tɔɪlət/","word":"toilet","example":"public toilets 公共厕所","phonetic_uk":"/ˈtɔɪlɪt/"},{"example":"...his tolerance and understanding of diverse human nature. …他对各种人性的宽容和理解。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈtɒlərəns/","word":"tolerance","phonetic_us":"/'tɑlərəns/","translation":"n. 宽容，容忍"},{"phonetic_us":"/'tɑləret/","translation":"v. 忍受，容忍，宽恕","word":"tolerate","phonetic_uk":"/'tɒləreɪt/","example":"We simply will not tolerate vigilante groups on our streets. 我们决不容许有自行惩办犯罪的组织出现在我们的街头。"},{"example":"Her tone was sharp with anger. 她很气愤，语气尖刻。","phonetic_uk":"/təʊn/","translation":"n. 音；腔调；声调","phonetic_us":"/ton/","word":"tone"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈtu:θeɪk/","example":"I’ve got toothache . 我牙痛。","translation":"n. 牙痛，牙疼","phonetic_us":"/'tuθek/","word":"toothache"},{"example":"The environment is a popular topic these days. 如今环境是一个热门话题。","phonetic_uk":"/'tɒpɪk/","translation":"n.  题目， 论题， 话题","phonetic_us":"/'tɑpɪk/","word":"topic"},{"phonetic_us":"/tɔrtʃ/","translation":"n. 火炬，火把；手电筒","word":"torch","phonetic_uk":"/tɔːtʃ/","example":"We shone our torches around the cavern. 我们用手电筒照着山洞。"},{"example":"He died after five days of excruciating torture. 遭受了五天的严刑拷打之后，他死了。","phonetic_uk":"/'tɔːtʃə/","word":"torture","translation":"n. 拷问；折磨；v. 拷打","phonetic_us":"/'tɔrtʃɚ/"},{"example":"a total ban on cigarette advertising 香烟广告的全面禁止","phonetic_uk":"/'təʊt(ə)l/","phonetic_us":"/'totl/","translation":"adj. 总的；v. 合计，总共","word":"total"},{"phonetic_uk":"/tʌtʃ/","example":"She reached out to touch his arm. 她伸手去碰他的胳膊。","translation":"v. 触摸；触动；感动；n. 触","phonetic_us":"/tʌtʃ/","word":"touch"},{"translation":"adj. 困难的","phonetic_us":"/tʌf/","word":"tough","phonetic_uk":"/tʌf/","example":"It was a tough race. 比赛打得很艰难。"},{"phonetic_uk":"","example":"He devilled her during the tour. 他在旅行中拿她打趣逗乐。","phonetic_us":"","translation":"n&vi. 旅行，游历","word":"tour"},{"word":"tourist","translation":"n. 旅游者，观光者","phonetic_us":"/'tʊrɪst/","example":"Cambridge is always full of tourists in the summer. 剑桥在夏季总是挤满了游客。","phonetic_uk":"/'tʊərɪst/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'taʊəl/","translation":"n. 毛巾，手巾","word":"towel","phonetic_uk":"/'taʊəl/","example":"Have you got a clean towel I could use? 你有没有干净毛巾给我用？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'taʊə/","example":"the Eiffel Tower 埃菲尔铁塔","translation":"n. 塔；v. 屹立，高耸","phonetic_us":"/'taʊɚ/","word":"tower"},{"word":"trace","translation":"n. 痕迹","phonetic_us":"/tres/","example":"There was no trace of anyone having entered the room since then. 没有任何迹象表明在那以后有人进过这房间。","phonetic_uk":"/treɪs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/træk/","example":"We followed the tyre tracks across a muddy field. 我们顺着车辙穿过一块泥泞的田地。","translation":"n &v. 跟踪,足迹","phonetic_us":"/træk/","word":"track"},{"translation":"n. 拖拉机；牵引车","phonetic_us":"/'træktɚ/","word":"tractor","phonetic_uk":"/'træktə/","example":"Iron-ox is another name for tractor. 铁牛是拖拉机的别名。"},{"word":"trade","phonetic_us":"/tred/","translation":"n. 贸易；职业；v. 交易","phonetic_uk":"/treɪd/","example":"international trade agreements 国际贸易协定"},{"phonetic_uk":"/trə'dɪʃn/","example":"the traditions of South East Asia 东南亚的传统","phonetic_us":"/trə'dɪʃən/","translation":"n.  传统， 惯例","word":"tradition"},{"translation":"n. 交通，通行；交通量","phonetic_us":"/'træfɪk/","word":"traffic","example":"There wasn’t much traffic on the roads. 路上车辆不多。","phonetic_uk":"/'træfɪk/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'trædʒədi/","translation":"n. 悲剧；惨事，惨案","word":"tragedy","phonetic_uk":"/'trædʒɪdɪ/","example":"The tragedy happened as they were returning home from a night out. 悲剧发生在他们夜里外出归来的路上。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/treɪl/","example":"The trail led over Boulder Pass before descending to a lake. 小路越过博尔德山口，然后向下通往湖边。","translation":"n. 痕迹；小径；v. 跟踪","phonetic_us":"/trel/","word":"trail"},{"phonetic_uk":"/treɪt/","example":"","word":"trait","phonetic_us":"/tret/","translation":"n. 性格"},{"example":"The bank charges a fixed rate for each transaction. 银行对每一笔业务收取固定费用。","phonetic_uk":"/trænˈzækʃn/","translation":"n. 交易，业务，事务","phonetic_us":"/træn'zækʃən/","word":"transaction"},{"word":"transfer","phonetic_us":"/træns'fɝ/","translation":"v & n. 转换，调换","phonetic_uk":"/træns'fɜː/","example":"Ideas that work well in one school often don’t transfer well to another. 在一所学校行得通的理念套用在另一所学校上往往行不通。"},{"example":"Increased population has transformed the landscape. 人口的增加使景观发生了变化。","phonetic_uk":"/træns'fɔːm/","word":"transform","translation":"v. 改变","phonetic_us":"/træns'fɔrm/"},{"example":"In recent years, the movie industry has undergone a dramatic transformation . 近些年，电影业经历了巨大的变革。","phonetic_uk":"/trænsfə'meɪʃ(ə)n; trɑːns-; -nz-/","word":"transformation","phonetic_us":"/,trænsfɚ'meʃən/","translation":"n. 变化；改造；转变"},{"translation":"n. 变压器，转换器","phonetic_us":"/træns'fɔrmɚ/","word":"transformer","example":"By using a transformer, he translated the codes into translation he could read. 通过运用一个变压器，他将密码翻译成他读得懂的译文。","phonetic_uk":"/træns'fɔːmə; trɑːns-; -nz-/"},{"phonetic_us":"/træn'zɪstɚ/","translation":"n. 晶体管","word":"transistor","example":"Every transistor has at least three electrodes. 每个晶体管至少有三个电极。","phonetic_uk":"/træn'zɪstə; trɑːn-; -'sɪ-/"},{"word":"translation","translation":"n.  翻译； 译文， 译本","phonetic_us":"/træns'leʃən/","example":"She read the letter and gave us a rough translation (= she did not translate everything exactly ) . 她看了信，给我们大概翻译了一下。","phonetic_uk":"/træns'leɪʃn; trænz'leɪʃn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/træns'mɪʃən/","translation":"n. 传送；传动；发射","word":"transmission","example":"worldwide data transmission 全球数据传输","phonetic_uk":"/trænz'mɪʃ(ə)n; trɑːnz-; -ns-/"},{"phonetic_us":"/trænzˈmɪt/","translation":"v. 传送，传达；发射","word":"transmit","example":"The US Open will be transmitted live via satellite. 美国公开赛将通过卫星现场直播。","phonetic_uk":"/trænz'mɪt; trɑːnz-; -ns-/"},{"word":"transparent","translation":"adj. 透明的；易识破的","phonetic_us":"/træns'pærənt/","phonetic_uk":"/træn'spær(ə)nt; trɑːn-; -'speə-/","example":"a transparent plastic container 透明的塑料容器"},{"word":"transport","phonetic_us":"/'trænspɔrt/","translation":"v. 运输；n. 运输","phonetic_uk":"/træn'spɔːt; trɑːn-/","example":"trucks used for transporting oil 运输石油的卡车"},{"phonetic_us":"/,trænspɔr'teʃən/","translation":"n. 运输","word":"transportation","phonetic_uk":"/ˌtrænspɔ:ˈteɪʃn/","example":"The city needs to improve its public transportation (= buses, trains etc ) . 这座城市需要改善公共交通。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/træp/","example":"The only way to catch mice is to set a trap . 抓老鼠的唯一办法就是放置捕鼠器。","phonetic_us":"/træp/","translation":"n. 陷阱；诡计；v. 诱骗","word":"trap"},{"word":"trash","phonetic_us":"/træʃ/","translation":"n. 垃圾，废物；拙劣的文学作品；没用的人，社会渣滓，败类；vt.  捣毁， 破坏","example":"Will someone take out the trash (= take it outside the house ) ? 谁把垃圾拿出去好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/træʃ/"},{"translation":"n. (浅)盘，托盘，碟","phonetic_us":"/tre/","word":"tray","example":"The waiter brought drinks on a tray. 服务员用托盘端来饮料。","phonetic_uk":"/treɪ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'trɛʒɚ/","translation":"v. 珍爱","word":"treasure","example":"Jim treasured the gold pocket watch that his grandfather had given him. 吉姆十分珍爱祖父送给他的金怀表。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈtreʒə(r)/"},{"word":"treat","phonetic_us":"/trit/","translation":"v. 对待；处理；n. 款待","phonetic_uk":"/triːt/","example":"sewage treated so that it can be used as fertilizer 经过处理可用作肥料的污水"},{"word":"treatment","phonetic_us":"/'tritmənt/","translation":"n. 治疗，对待","phonetic_uk":"/ˈtri:tmənt/","example":"Just lately, Kyra has been giving me the silent treatment (= refusing to speak to me because she is angry with me ) . 就在最近，凯拉一直对我不理不睬。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'triti/","translation":"n. 条约；协议，协定","word":"treaty","phonetic_uk":"/'triːtɪ/","example":"Both sides have agreed to sign the treaty . 双方都同意签署该条约。"},{"example":"His lip started to tremble and then he started to cry. 他的嘴唇开始颤抖，接着就哭了起来。","phonetic_uk":"/'trembl/","phonetic_us":"/'trɛmbl/","translation":"v. 颤抖","word":"tremble"},{"example":"Suddenly, there was a tremendous bang, and the whole station shook. 突然一声巨响，整个车站都晃动了。","phonetic_uk":"/trəˈmendəs/","word":"tremendous","translation":"adj. 巨大的","phonetic_us":"/trə'mɛndəs/"},{"example":"He characterized briefly the main trend in the world today. 他简单扼要地描述了当前世界的主要倾向。","phonetic_uk":"/trend/","translation":"v. 伸向；倾向；n. 倾向","phonetic_us":"/trɛnd/","word":"trend"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'traɪəl/","example":"The trial is due to start next week. 审理定于下周开始。","translation":"n. 试，试验；审判","phonetic_us":"/'traɪəl/","word":"trial"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'traɪæŋg(ə)l/","example":"a triangle of land 一块三角地","word":"triangle","translation":"n. 三角(形)","phonetic_us":"/'traɪæŋɡl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/trɪk/","example":"Pretending he doesn’t remember is an old trick of his. 假装不记得是他的老花招了。","word":"trick","translation":"n. 诡计；窍门；v. 哄骗","phonetic_us":"/trɪk/"},{"word":"trigger","phonetic_us":"/'trɪɡɚ/","translation":"v. 引发，引起","phonetic_uk":"/'trɪgə/","example":"The assassination triggered off a wave of rioting. 这次暗杀事件引发了一阵骚乱。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/trɪm/","example":"trim suburban gardens 修剪齐整的郊区花园","translation":"adj. 整齐的；v. 使整齐","phonetic_us":"/trɪm/","word":"trim"},{"translation":"n. 胜利","phonetic_us":"/'traɪʌmf/","word":"triumph","example":"Winning the championship is a great personal triumph . 赢得冠军是伟大的个人成就。","phonetic_uk":"/'traɪʌmf/"},{"example":"Both countries agreed to withdraw their troops . 两国都同意撤军。","phonetic_uk":"/truːp/","word":"troop","phonetic_us":"/trʊp/","translation":"n. 军队；一群，大量"},{"translation":"adj. 热带的","phonetic_us":"/'trɑpɪkl/","word":"tropical","phonetic_uk":"/'trɒpɪk(ə)l/","example":"the tropical rain forests 热带雨林"},{"word":"troublesome","translation":"adj. 令人烦恼的；麻烦的","phonetic_us":"/'trʌblsəm/","phonetic_uk":"/'trʌb(ə)ls(ə)m/","example":"a troublesome child 烦人的孩子"},{"example":"His work is truly original. 他的作品确实十分独特。","phonetic_uk":"/'truːli/","word":"truly","translation":"adv.  真正地； 忠实地","phonetic_us":"/ˈtruːli/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'trʌmpɪt/","example":"I played the trumpet in the school orchestra. 我在学校管弦乐队吹小号。","word":"trumpet","translation":"n. 喇叭，小号","phonetic_us":"/'trʌmpɪt/"},{"translation":"n. 树干；大衣箱，皮箱","phonetic_us":"/trʌŋk/","word":"trunk","example":"He left his bicycle leaning against a tree trunk . 他把他的自行车斜靠在树干上。","phonetic_uk":"/trʌŋk/"},{"word":"trust","phonetic_us":"/trʌst/","translation":"n. 信任；v. 相信；委托","phonetic_uk":"/trʌst/","example":"At first there was a lack of trust between them. 起初，他们之间缺乏信任。"},{"phonetic_us":"/trʊθ/","translation":"n. 真理；真实；真实性","word":"truth","example":"How do we know you’re telling us the truth? 我们怎么知道你告诉我们的是真话？","phonetic_uk":"/truːθ/"},{"example":"a tube of toothpaste 一管牙膏","phonetic_uk":"/tjuːb/","phonetic_us":"/tub/","translation":"n. 管；电子管，显像管","word":"tube"},{"example":"I had to have extra tuition in maths. 我不得不上数学补习课。","phonetic_uk":"/tjuˈɪʃn/","translation":"n. 学费","phonetic_us":"/tʊ'ɪʃən/","word":"tuition"},{"word":"tumor","translation":"n. 瘤","phonetic_us":"/'tjʊmɚ/","example":"The tumor will soon be resolved. 这个肿瘤很快就会消掉的。","phonetic_uk":"/'tju:mə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/tun/","translation":"n. 调子；和谐；v. 调谐","word":"tune","example":"That’s a nice tune. 那曲调很美。","phonetic_uk":"/tjuːn/"},{"translation":"n. 隧道，坑道，地道","phonetic_us":"/'tʌnl/","word":"tunnel","example":"a railway tunnel 铁路隧道","phonetic_uk":"/'tʌnl/"},{"example":"The new ship will be powered by two gas turbines and four diesel engines. 那艘新轮船将由2台燃气涡轮机和4台柴油机驱动。","phonetic_uk":"/'tɜːbaɪn; -ɪn/","word":"turbine","translation":"n. 叶轮机，汽轮机","phonetic_us":"/'tɝbaɪn/"},{"translation":"v.  当…导师， 当…家庭教师；n. 导师；家庭教师，私人教师","phonetic_us":"/'tʊtɚ/","word":"tutor","phonetic_uk":"/'tjuːtə/","example":"He was privately tutored. 他是由家庭教师教的。"},{"phonetic_us":"/twɪn/","translation":"adj. 孪生的；n. 孪生儿","word":"twin","phonetic_uk":"/twɪn/","example":"I always confounded him with his twin brother. 我总分不清他和他的孪生兄弟。"},{"word":"twist","translation":"v. 扭曲，使弯曲","phonetic_us":"/twɪst/","phonetic_uk":"/twɪst/","example":"Her hands began to twist the handles of the bag she carried. 她的双手开始拧她拎着的那个包的拎柄。"},{"word":"type","phonetic_us":"/taɪp/","translation":"n. 型，类型；v. 打字","example":"Jo’s not really the sporty type. 乔可不是那种喜欢运动的人。","phonetic_uk":"/taɪp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'taɪpraɪtə/","example":"She tapped out a letter on the typewriter. 她用打字机打出了一封信。","translation":"n. 打字机","phonetic_us":"/'taɪpraɪtɚ/","word":"typewriter"},{"example":"typical British weather 典型的英国天气","phonetic_uk":"/'tɪpɪk(ə)l/","word":"typical","phonetic_us":"/'tɪpɪkl/","translation":"adj. 典型的，代表性的"},{"phonetic_us":"/'taɪpɪst/","translation":"n. 打字员","word":"typist","phonetic_uk":"/'taɪpɪst/","example":"I’m a slow typist. 我打字很慢。"},{"word":"tyre","phonetic_us":"/'taɪɚ/","translation":"n. 轮胎，车胎","example":"I had a flat tyre (= all the air went out of it ) on the way home. 回家的路上我的轮胎瘪了。","phonetic_uk":"/'taɪə/"},{"word":"ugly","phonetic_us":"/'ʌɡli/","translation":"adj.  丑陋的； 可怕的","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌgli/","example":"a very ugly man 非常丑陋的男子"},{"example":"The ultimate outcome of the experiment cannot be predicted. 试验的最后结果无法预测。","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌltɪmət/","phonetic_us":"/'ʌltəmət/","translation":"adj. 最后的，最终的","word":"ultimate"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ʌltɪmətli/","translation":"adv. 最后，最终","word":"ultimately","phonetic_uk":"/ˈʌltɪmətli/","example":"Ultimately, the decision rests with the child’s parents. 最终，决定权在这孩子的父母手中。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ʌm'brelə/","example":"It started to rain, so Tricia stopped to put up her umbrella. 开始下雨了，所以特里西娅停下来撑起雨伞。","word":"umbrella","translation":"n.  伞， 雨伞","phonetic_us":"/ʌm'brɛlə/"},{"word":"unaffordable","phonetic_us":"","translation":"adj. 买不起的，负担不起的","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌnə'fɔ:dəbl/","example":"You have to become awfully large to be unaffordable -- there's lots of cash, lots of capital out there for acquisitions. 制药业者坐拥很多现金,进行收购的资本雄厚,你必须变成让人买不起的超大公司."},{"word":"unbearable","translation":"adj. 无法忍受的","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'bɛrəbl/","phonetic_uk":"/ʌnˈbeərəbl/","example":"The pain was almost unbearable. 那疼痛几乎难以忍受。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ʌnˈsɜ:tn/","example":"My whole future now seemed uncertain. 现在我的前途似乎是个未知数。","word":"uncertain","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'sɝtn/","translation":"adj. 不确定的"},{"translation":"adj. 不省人事的","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'kɑnʃəs/","word":"unconscious","example":"She was found alive but unconscious. 她被找到时还活着，但已不省人事。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'kɒnʃəs/"},{"phonetic_us":"/ʌn'kʌvɚ/","translation":"v. 揭开…的盖子","word":"uncover","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'kʌvə/","example":"When the seedlings sprout, uncover the tray. 幼苗发芽后，揭开盘上的遮盖物。"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ʌndɚ'ɡo/","translation":"v. 承受","word":"undergo","example":"The country has undergone massive changes recently. 这个国家最近经历了巨大的变化。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌndəˈgəʊ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ʌndɚ'ɡrædʒuət/","translation":"n. 大学在校生","word":"undergraduate","phonetic_uk":"/ʌndə'grædjʊət/","example":"second-year undergraduates 大学二年级学生"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ʌndəgraund/","example":"This animal spends most of its life underground. 这种动物一生中的大部分时间都待在地下。","word":"underground","translation":"adv. 在地下，往地下；秘密地，不公开地；adj. 地下的；秘密的，不公开的；n.  地铁； 地下组织","phonetic_us":"/ʌndɚˈɡraʊnd/"},{"translation":"v. 强调","phonetic_us":"/'ʌndəlaɪn/","word":"underline","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌndəˈlaɪn/","example":"This tragic incident underlines the need for immediate action. 这一悲剧事件突显了立即采取行动的必要性。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ʌndə'maɪn/","example":"The continued fighting threatens to undermine efforts to negotiate an agreement. 持续的战斗有可能破坏通过谈判达成协议的努力。","translation":"v. 暗中破坏","phonetic_us":"/'ʌndɚ'maɪn/","word":"undermine"},{"word":"underneath","phonetic_us":"/,ʌndɚ'niθ/","translation":"adv. 在下面，在底下","phonetic_uk":"/ʌndə'niːθ/","example":"He has on his jeans and a long-sleeved blue denim shirt with a white T-shirt underneath. 他身穿牛仔裤和一件蓝色长袖粗斜纹棉布衬衫，里面还有件白色T恤衫。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌndə'stændɪŋ/","example":"Luckily, I have a very under­standing boss. 幸运的是，我有一个非常通情达理的上司。","word":"understanding","translation":"adj.  体谅的， 宽容的， 通情达理的；n. 理解，理解力；谅解；协议；相互理解，融洽","phonetic_us":"/,ʌndɚ'stændɪŋ/"},{"example":"He undertook to pay the money back in six months. 他保证在六个月之内还钱。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌndəˈteɪk/","translation":"v. 承担","phonetic_us":"/,ʌndɚ'tek/","word":"undertake"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ʌndɚ'vælju/","translation":"v. 低估","word":"undervalue","example":"Society undervalues staying at home and looking after children. 社会低估了待在家里照看孩子的意义。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌndə'væljuː/"},{"example":"The screws can be undone by hand. 这些螺丝可以用手拧开。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'duː/","word":"undo","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'du/","translation":"v. 解开，打开；取消"},{"word":"undoubtedly","translation":"adv. 无疑","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'daʊtɪdli/","example":"This is undoubtedly important. 这无疑是重要的。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'daʊtɪdlɪ/"},{"word":"uneasy","translation":"adj. 心神不安的，忧虑的","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'izi/","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'iːzɪ/","example":"She eventually fell into an uneasy sleep. 她终于睡着了，但睡得并不踏实。"},{"example":"The experiment produced some unexpected results. 这次试验产生了一些意想不到的结果。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌnɪk'spektɪd; ʌnek-/","word":"unexpected","phonetic_us":"/'ʌnɪk'spɛktɪd/","translation":"adj. 想不到的，意外的"},{"example":"Unfortunately, you were out when we called. 很遗憾，我们来的时候你出去了。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'fɔːtʃənətli/","word":"unfortunately","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'fɔrtʃənətli/","translation":"adv.  不幸地"},{"phonetic_us":"/'junɪfɔrm/","translation":"adj. 一样的；n. 制服","word":"uniform","example":"Grade A eggs must be of uniform size. A 级鸡蛋必须大小相同。","phonetic_uk":"/'juːnɪfɔːm/"},{"phonetic_us":"/,ʌnɪn'tɛndɪd/","translation":"adj. 意想不到的","word":"unintended","example":"...the unintended consequences of human action. ...人类行为无心的结果。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌnɪnˈtendɪd/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'junɪən/","translation":"n. 联合；团结；协会","word":"union","example":"Are you planning to join the union? 你打算加入工会吗？","phonetic_uk":"/'juːnjən; -ɪən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/juː'niːk/","example":"a unique opportunity to study these rare creatures 研究这些珍稀动物的难得机会","phonetic_us":"/jʊ'nik/","translation":"adj. 独特的，唯一的","word":"unique"},{"translation":"n. 单位；单元；部件","phonetic_us":"/'junɪt/","word":"unit","example":"The man is in the hospital’s intensive care unit. 那名男子在医院的重症监护室。","phonetic_uk":"/'juːnɪt/"},{"example":"Our goal is to unite the opposition parties and defeat the President. 我们的目标是联合各反对党挫败总统。","phonetic_uk":"/juː'naɪt/","word":"unite","phonetic_us":"/ju'naɪt/","translation":"v. 联合；v. 使联合"},{"example":"economic unity 经济统一","phonetic_uk":"/ˈjuːnəti/","word":"unity","translation":"n. 单一；统一；团结","phonetic_us":"/'junəti/"},{"word":"universal","translation":"adj. 普遍的，宇宙的，全世界的","phonetic_us":"/'jʊnə'vɝsl/","example":"free universal healthcare 免费的全民保健制度","phonetic_uk":"/,ju:ni'və:səl/"},{"word":"universe","phonetic_us":"/'junɪvɝs/","translation":"n.  宇宙， 世界； 领域， 范围","phonetic_uk":"/'juːnɪvɜːs/","example":"Einstein's equations showed the universe to be expanding. 爱因斯坦的方程式表明宇宙正在扩大。"},{"example":"The murderer’s identity remains unknown. 杀人凶手身份仍然不明。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'nəʊn/","word":"unknown","translation":"adj. 不知道的；未知的","phonetic_us":"/,ʌn'non/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'les/","example":"Unless some extra money is found, the theatre will close. 要是不能找到更多资金，剧院将要关闭。","phonetic_us":"/ən'lɛs/","translation":"conj. 除非，如果不","word":"unless"},{"example":"Now I see that, unlike her, they were my positive models. 现在我知道了，那些人不像她，他们是我的正面的表率。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'laɪk/","word":"unlike","phonetic_us":"/'ʌn'laɪk/","translation":"adj. 不同的；prep. 不象…"},{"word":"unlikely","translation":"adj. 未必的，未必可能的","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'laɪkli/","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'laɪklɪ/","example":"Donna might be able to come tomorrow, but it’s very unlikely. 唐娜明天也许能来，不过这可能性很小。"},{"translation":"v. 卸(货)；v. 卸货","phonetic_us":"/'ʌn'lod/","word":"unload","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'ləʊd/","example":"Unload everything from the boat and clean it thoroughly. 从小船上卸下所有的货物并彻底地清洗。"},{"example":"There is growing unrest throughout the country. 全国各地日益动荡不安。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌn'rest/","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'rɛst/","translation":"n. 不安定，动荡","word":"unrest"},{"word":"unusual","phonetic_us":"/ʌnˈjuʒəl/","translation":"adj.  不平常的， 少有的； 独特的， 与众不同的","example":"an unusual feature 不寻常的特点","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌn'juːʒuəl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ʌnˈwɪlɪŋ/","example":"an unwilling helper 勉强来帮忙的人","phonetic_us":"/ʌn'wɪlɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 不愿意的","word":"unwilling"},{"word":"up-to-date","phonetic_us":"/'ʌptə 'det/","translation":"adj.  直到最近的， 现代的； 跟上时代的","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌptə'deɪt/","example":"...the most up-to-date information available on foods today. …今日有关食品的最新消息。"},{"word":"upbringing","translation":"n. 养育，培养，教养","phonetic_us":"/'ʌpbrɪŋɪŋ/","example":"Mike had had a strict upbringing. 迈克从小家教很严。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈʌpbrɪŋɪŋ/"},{"example":"The files need updating. 这些档案需要更新。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌʌpˈdeɪt/","word":"update","phonetic_us":"/,ʌp'det/","translation":"v. 更新，使现代化"},{"word":"upper","translation":"adj. 上面的；地位较高的","phonetic_us":"/'ʌpɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌpə/","example":"the upper lip 上唇"},{"translation":"adj. 垂直的；正直的","phonetic_us":"/'ʌpraɪt/","word":"upright","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌpraɪt/","example":"Katie was still awake, sitting bolt upright(= sitting with her back very straight ) staring at the television. 凯蒂还醒着，坐得笔直，眼睛盯着电视。"},{"example":"He upset a bowl of soup. 他打翻了一碗汤。","phonetic_uk":"/ʌp'set/","phonetic_us":"/ʌp'sɛt/","translation":"v. 弄翻，打翻，倾覆","word":"upset"},{"word":"upward","phonetic_us":"/'ʌpwɚd/","translation":"adj. 向上的，上升的","example":"upward pressure on bank interest rates 针对银行利率的越来越大的压力","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌpwəd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ɜːb(ə)n/","example":"unemployment in urban areas 城市地区的失业状况","translation":"adj. a.；adj. 都市的,住在都市的","phonetic_us":"/'ɝbən/","word":"urban"},{"translation":"v. 推进；催促；n. 冲动","phonetic_us":"/ɝdʒ/","word":"urge","example":"The charity urged quick action. 慈善机构敦促迅速采取行动。","phonetic_uk":"/'ɜːdʒ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ɝdʒənt/","translation":"adj. 紧急的；强求的","word":"urgent","phonetic_uk":"/ˈɜːdʒənt/","example":"He was in urgent need of medical attention. 他急需治疗。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'juːsɪdʒ/","example":"a book on modern English usage 关于现代英语用法的书","word":"usage","phonetic_us":"/'jusɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 使用，对待；惯用法"},{"translation":"n. 使用，公共设施","phonetic_us":"/ju'tɪləti/","word":"utility","phonetic_uk":"/ju:ˈtɪləti/","example":"Does your rent include utilities? 你的房租包括公用事业费吗？"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈjuːtɪˌlaɪz/","example":"We must consider how best to utilize what resources we have. 我们必须考虑怎样充分利用现有的资源。","word":"utilize","translation":"v. 利用","phonetic_us":"/'juːtəlaɪz/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'ʌt'most/","translation":"adj. 最远的；n. 极限","word":"utmost","phonetic_uk":"/'ʌtməʊst/","example":"It is a matter of the utmost urgency to find out what has happened to these people. 当务之急是弄清楚这些人出了什么事。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ʌtə/","example":"That’s utter nonsense! 真是一派胡言！","word":"utter","translation":"adj. 完全的，彻底的","phonetic_us":"/'ʌtɚ/"},{"translation":"adj. 空的；未被占用的","phonetic_us":"/'vekənt/","word":"vacant","example":"Only a few apartments were still vacant. 只有几套公寓仍然空着。","phonetic_uk":"/'veɪk(ə)nt/"},{"translation":"n.  假期， 休假","phonetic_us":"/veˈkeʃən/","word":"vacation","example":"We’re planning a vacation in Europe. 我们正计划去欧洲度假。","phonetic_uk":"/və'keɪʃn; veɪ'keɪʃn/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'vækjʊəm/","translation":"n. 真空；真空吸尘器","word":"vacuum","example":"His presence should fill the power vacuum that has been developing over the past few days. 他的出现应该能填补过去几天中形成的权力空缺。","phonetic_uk":"/'vækjʊəm/"},{"example":"The governor gave only a vague outline of his tax plan. 州长只是含糊地大致说了一下他的税务计划。","phonetic_uk":"/veɪg/","translation":"adj. 模糊的，含糊的","phonetic_us":"/veɡ/","word":"vague"},{"word":"vain","translation":"adj. 徒劳的；自负的","phonetic_us":"/ven/","example":"Men can be just as vain as women. 男人有时会和女人一样虚荣。","phonetic_uk":"/veɪn/"},{"translation":"adj. 有效的","phonetic_us":"/'vælɪd/","word":"valid","phonetic_uk":"/'vælɪd/","example":"a valid credit card 有效信用卡"},{"word":"value","translation":"v. 重视","phonetic_us":"/'vælju/","example":"Shelley valued her privacy. 谢利很重视自己的隐私。","phonetic_uk":"/'vælju:/"},{"example":"a delivery van 运货车","phonetic_uk":"/væn/","word":"van","phonetic_us":"/væn/","translation":"n. 大篷车，运货车"},{"example":"My keys were here a minute ago but now they’ve vanished. 我的钥匙刚刚还在这里，现在却不翼而飞了。","phonetic_uk":"/'vænɪʃ/","word":"vanish","phonetic_us":"/'vænɪʃ/","translation":"v. 消失"},{"example":"water vapour 水蒸气","phonetic_uk":"/'veɪpə/","translation":"n. 汽，蒸气","phonetic_us":"/'vepɚ/","word":"vapour"},{"word":"variable","translation":"adj. 易变的；n. 变量","phonetic_us":"/'vɛrɪəbl/","phonetic_uk":"/'veərɪəb(ə)l/","example":"Expect variable cloudiness and fog tomorrow. 预计明天多云有雾，天气多变。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/veərɪ'eɪʃ(ə)n/","example":"Most of his poems are variations on the theme of love. 他的大部分诗作都是有关爱情主题的形式不同的作品。","word":"variation","translation":"n. 变化，变动；变异","phonetic_us":"/,vɛrɪ'eʃən/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/və'raɪətɪ/","example":"The girls come from a variety of different backgrounds. 这些女孩出身背景各不相同。","word":"variety","phonetic_us":"/və'raɪəti/","translation":"n. 多样"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'veərɪəs/","example":"The jacket is available in various colours. 这种夹克有好多种颜色可选。","word":"various","translation":"adj. 各种各样的，不同的","phonetic_us":"/'vɛrɪəs/"},{"example":"Test scores vary from school to school. 测验成绩各校不同。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈveəri/","word":"vary","translation":"v. 变化；不同","phonetic_us":"/ˈveri/"},{"phonetic_us":"/væst/","translation":"adj. 巨大的；大量的","word":"vast","phonetic_uk":"/vɑːst/","example":"The refugees come across the border in vast numbers. 大量难民涌过边境。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈvi:əkl/","example":"a description of the stolen vehicle 对被盗车辆的描述","word":"vehicle","translation":"n. 车辆","phonetic_us":"/'viːɪkl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/vəˈlɒsəti/","example":"the velocity of light 光速","translation":"n. 速度，速率","phonetic_us":"/vəˈlɑsəti/","word":"velocity"},{"word":"venture","phonetic_us":"/'vɛntʃɚ/","translation":"n&vi. 冒险；v. 敢于","phonetic_uk":"/'ventʃə/","example":"When darkness fell, he would venture out. 天黑以后，他就会壮着胆子出去。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'verɪfaɪ/","example":"His statement was verified by several witnesses. 他的说法得到了几位证人的证实。","word":"verify","translation":"v. 证实，查证；证明","phonetic_us":"/'vɛrɪfaɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈvə:ʃən/","example":"the human version of mad cow disease 疯牛病的人类变体","word":"version","phonetic_us":"/'vɝʒn/","translation":"n. 版本"},{"translation":"adj. 垂直的，竖式的","phonetic_us":"/'vɝtɪkl/","word":"vertical","example":"a vertical line  垂直线","phonetic_uk":"/'vɜːtɪk(ə)l/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'ves(ə)l/","example":"a fishing vessel 渔船","word":"vessel","phonetic_us":"/'vɛsl/","translation":"n. 容器；船，飞船；管"},{"translation":"n. 老兵，老手","phonetic_us":"/'vɛtərən/","word":"veteran","example":"a Vietnam veteran 越战老兵","phonetic_uk":"/'vet(ə)r(ə)n/"},{"example":"We flew to Athens via Paris. 我们经由巴黎飞往雅典。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈvaɪə/","phonetic_us":"/ˈvaɪə, ˈviə/","translation":"prep. 通过","word":"via"},{"phonetic_uk":"/vaɪ'breɪt/","example":"The floor was vibrating to the beat of the music. 地板随着音乐的节奏在颤动。","word":"vibrate","phonetic_us":"/vaɪ'breɪt/","translation":"v. 使颤动；v. 颤动"},{"translation":"n. 罪恶；恶习；缺点","phonetic_us":"/vaɪs/","word":"vice","example":"the fight against vice on the streets 打击街头犯罪","phonetic_uk":"/vaɪs/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'vɪktɪm/","example":"The victim received head injuries from which she died a week later. 受害人头部受伤，一周后死亡。","phonetic_us":"/'vɪktɪm/","translation":"n.  牺牲者， 受害者","word":"victim"},{"word":"victimize","translation":"vt.  使受害， 使牺牲","phonetic_us":"/'vɪktɪmaɪz/","example":"The men claim they have been victimized because of their political activity. 那些人声称他们因为自己的政治活动而受到了迫害。","phonetic_uk":"/'vɪktɪmaɪz/"},{"example":"video production 录像制作","phonetic_uk":"/'vɪdiəu/","word":"video","translation":"adj. 录像的；电视的；n.  录像","phonetic_us":"/'vɪdɪo/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/vju:/","example":"an opportunity to view the film before it goes on general release 在影片公映之前观影的机会","phonetic_us":"/vju/","translation":"v. 看待","word":"view"},{"example":"Different viewpoints produce different images. 角度不同，产生的画面也不同。","phonetic_uk":"/'vjuːpɔɪnt/","word":"viewpoint","phonetic_us":"/'vjupɔɪnt/","translation":"n.  观点， 看法， 见解"},{"word":"vigorous","phonetic_us":"/'vɪɡərəs/","translation":"adj. 朝气蓬勃的","phonetic_uk":"/'vɪg(ə)rəs/","example":""},{"phonetic_uk":"/'vɪnɪgə/","example":"The  sugared  vinegar is  refined from the sugarcane and  pine. 加糖的醋是从甘蔗和松木中精炼出来的.","phonetic_us":"/'vɪnɪɡɚ/","translation":"n. 醋","word":"vinegar"},{"translation":"v. 违反","phonetic_us":"/'vaɪəlet/","word":"violate","phonetic_uk":"/'vaɪəleɪt/","example":"34 protesters were arrested for violating criminal law. 34名抗议者因违反刑法而被逮捕。"},{"word":"violence","translation":"n.  猛烈， 激烈； 暴力","phonetic_us":"/'vaɪələns/","phonetic_uk":"/'vaɪələns/","example":"She spoke with a violence that surprised them both. 她言辞激烈，令他们俩都很惊讶。"},{"phonetic_us":"/'vaɪələnt/","translation":"adj. 猛烈的；狂暴的","word":"violent","phonetic_uk":"/'vaɪəl(ə)nt/","example":"the increase in violent crime 暴力犯罪的增多"},{"example":"She inhaled the violet perfume, saying “How sweet!” 她一边闻紫罗兰的芳香， 一边说“好香啊！”","phonetic_uk":"/'vaɪələt/","phonetic_us":"/'vaɪələt/","translation":"n. 紫罗兰","word":"violet"},{"example":"He plays the violin in an orchestra. 他在管弦乐队中演奏小提琴。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌvaɪə'lɪn/","word":"violin","phonetic_us":"/,vaɪə'lɪn/","translation":"n.  小提琴"},{"example":"The website allows you to take a virtual tour of the art gallery. 这个网站可让你对美术馆作一番虚拟参观。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈvɜ:tʃuəl/","word":"virtual","translation":"adj. 虚拟的","phonetic_us":"/[ˈvɜ:rtʃuəl]/"},{"example":"Virtually all the children come to school by bus. 几乎所有的孩子都乘公交车上学。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈvɜ:tʃuəli/","phonetic_us":"/ˈvɜrtʃuəli/","translation":"adv. 几乎，差不多","word":"virtually"},{"example":"Women have often been used as symbols of virtue. 女性常被用作美德的象征。","phonetic_uk":"/'vɜːtjuː; -tʃuː/","phonetic_us":"/'vɝtʃʊ/","translation":"n. 善；美德；优点","word":"virtue"},{"word":"virus","phonetic_us":"/'vaɪrəs/","translation":"n. 病毒","example":"children infected with the Aids virus 感染艾滋病病毒的儿童","phonetic_uk":"/'vaɪrəs/"},{"example":"Visibility on the roads is down to 20 metres due to heavy fog. 道路能见度因浓雾降至20米。","phonetic_uk":"/,vizi'biliti/","phonetic_us":"/'vɪzə'bɪləti/","translation":"n. 能见度","word":"visibility"},{"example":"The comet is visible to the naked eye (= can be seen without using special equipment ). 这颗彗星肉眼看得见。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈvɪzəbl/","translation":"adj. 看得见的","phonetic_us":"/'vɪzəbl/","word":"visible"},{"word":"vision","translation":"n. 视；想象力；梦幻","phonetic_us":"/'vɪʒən/","phonetic_uk":"/'vɪʒ(ə)n/","example":"She suffered temporary loss of vision after being struck on the head. 她头部受撞击以后出现暂时性失明。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'vɪʒjʊəl; -zj-/","example":"Artists translate their ideas into visual images. 画家把自己的思想转换成视觉画面。","word":"visual","phonetic_us":"/'vɪʒʊəl/","translation":"adj. 看的；看得见的"},{"example":"The work she does is absolutely vital. 她所做的工作至关重要。","phonetic_uk":"/'vaɪtl/","phonetic_us":"/'vaɪtl/","translation":"adj. 重要的","word":"vital"},{"example":"A sensible diet is vitally important if you want to remain in good health. 如想保持健康，合理的饮食十分重要。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈvaɪtəli/","word":"vitally","phonetic_us":"/'vaɪtəli/","translation":"adv. 极其重要地"},{"example":"Try to eat foods that are rich in vitamins and minerals. 尽量吃富含维生素和矿物质的食物。","phonetic_uk":"/'vɪtəmɪn; 'vaɪt-/","word":"vitamin","translation":"n. 维生素，维他命","phonetic_us":"/'vaɪtəmɪn/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'vɪvɪd/","example":"I’ve got vivid memories of that summer. 我对那年夏天记忆犹新。","word":"vivid","phonetic_us":"/'vɪvɪd/","translation":"adj. 鲜艳的；生动的"},{"example":"Teachers were impressed by his vocabulary. 他的词汇量给老师们留下了深刻的印象。","phonetic_uk":"/və'kæbjələrɪ/","phonetic_us":"/və'kæbjəlɛri/","translation":"n. 词汇","word":"vocabulary"},{"translation":"n. 火山","phonetic_us":"/vɑl'keno/","word":"volcano","example":"Pompeii was destroyed when the volcano erupted in 79 AD. 庞贝城于公元79年在火山爆发中毁灭。","phonetic_uk":"/vɒl'keɪnəʊ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/volt/","translation":"n. 伏特，伏","word":"volt","example":"That is one electron volt. 就是一单位的电子伏特。","phonetic_uk":"/vəʊlt; vɒlt/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'vəʊltɪdʒ; 'vɒltɪdʒ/","example":"The systems are getting smaller and using lower voltages. 这些系统正变得更小而且使用更低的电压。","word":"voltage","phonetic_us":"/'voltɪdʒ/","translation":"n. 电压"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'vɒljuːm/","example":"the volume of trade 贸易量","phonetic_us":"/'vɑljum/","translation":"n. 卷，册；容积；音量","word":"volume"},{"word":"voluntary","translation":"adj. 自愿的，主动的","phonetic_us":"/'vɑləntɛri/","phonetic_uk":"/ˈvɑ:lənteri/","example":"Workers are being encouraged to take voluntary redundancy. 工人被鼓励主动离职。"},{"example":"I volunteered my services as a driver. 我主动提出来当司机。","phonetic_uk":"/ˌvɒlən'tɪə/","word":"volunteer","phonetic_us":"/,vɑlən'tɪr/","translation":"v.  自愿提供； 自愿， 志愿；n. 志愿者；志愿兵"},{"phonetic_uk":"/vəʊt/","example":"In 1918 British women got the right to vote. 1918年，英国妇女获得了选举权。","word":"vote","translation":"v. 投票，选举","phonetic_us":"/vot; voʊt/"},{"example":"The voyage from England to India used to take six months. 过去从英格兰到印度要航行六个月。","phonetic_uk":"/'vɒɪɪdʒ/","translation":"n&vi. 航海，航空；n. 字","phonetic_us":"/'vɔɪɪdʒ/","word":"voyage"},{"phonetic_uk":"/weɪdʒ/","example":"The government, along with the three factions that had been waging a civil war, signed a peace agreement. 政府和发动了内战的3方一起签订了1份和平协议。","phonetic_us":"/wedʒ/","translation":"v. 开展(运动)","word":"wage"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'wæɡən/","example":"","word":"waggon","translation":"n. 四轮运货马车","phonetic_us":"/'wægən/"},{"example":"In the wagon. 在货车里。","phonetic_uk":"/'wægən/","phonetic_us":"/'wægən/","translation":"n.  四轮马车， 大篷车； 铁路货车， 客货两用车","word":"wagon"},{"translation":"n.  腰， 腰部","phonetic_us":"/west/","word":"waist","phonetic_uk":"/weɪst/","example":"The skirt was too big around the waist. 那条裙子腰围太大。"},{"word":"waken","phonetic_us":"/'wekən/","translation":"v. 醒来；v. 弄醒","phonetic_uk":"/'weɪk(ə)n/","example":"She gently wakened the sleeping child. 她轻轻地唤醒睡梦中的孩子。"},{"word":"wander","translation":"v. 漫游；迷路；离题","phonetic_us":"/'wɑndɚ/","phonetic_uk":"/'wɒndə/","example":"Don’t let any of the kids wander off. 不要让任何一个小孩走开去。"},{"word":"want","phonetic_us":"/wɑnt/","translation":"n. 需要；缺乏","phonetic_uk":"/wɒnt/","example":"The gallery closed down for want of funding. 那家画廊由于缺乏资金关闭了。"},{"phonetic_us":"/wɔrmθ/","translation":"n. 暖和，温暖；热烈","word":"warmth","phonetic_uk":"/wɔːmθ/","example":"She went further into the room, drawn by the warmth of the fire. 她被火的温暖吸引着，走进了房间。"},{"word":"water","translation":"n. 水；v. 使湿，灌溉","phonetic_us":"/ˈwɔtɚ; ˈwɑtɚ/","example":"There’s water all over the bathroom floor. 浴室地面上都是水。","phonetic_uk":"/'wɔːtə/"},{"example":"a waterproof jacket 防水上衣","phonetic_uk":"/'wɔːtəpruːf/","word":"waterproof","translation":"adj. 不透水的，防水的","phonetic_us":"/'wɔtɚpruf/"},{"phonetic_us":"/wev/","translation":"n. 波；波涛；v. 波动","word":"wave","phonetic_uk":"/weɪv/","example":"Dee watched the waves breaking on the shore. 迪伊凝视着拍岸的波涛。"},{"word":"wax","phonetic_us":"/waks/","translation":"n. 蜡，蜂蜡","phonetic_uk":"/waks/","example":"wax crayons 蜡笔"},{"example":"Over the last two years the president’s position has weakened. 过去两年来，总统的地位被削弱了。","phonetic_uk":"/'wiːk(ə)n/","translation":"v. 减少，减弱","phonetic_us":"/'wikən/","word":"weaken"},{"phonetic_us":"/'wiknəs/","translation":"n. 虚弱，软弱；弱点","word":"weakness","phonetic_uk":"/ˈwiːknəs/","example":"The legislation has a fundamental weakness. 这项立法有一个根本性缺陷。"},{"phonetic_us":"/wɛlθ/","translation":"n.  财富， 财产； 丰富","word":"wealth","example":"The country’s wealth comes from its oil. 这个国家的财富来自石油。","phonetic_uk":"/welθ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'wɛlθi/","translation":"adj.  富有的， 富裕的","word":"wealthy","phonetic_uk":"/'welθi/","example":"the wealthy nations of the world 世界上的富国"},{"example":"They all had sticks which they planned to use as weapons. 他们都持有棍棒，打算当武器用。","phonetic_uk":"/'wepən/","word":"weapon","phonetic_us":"/'wɛpən/","translation":"n.  武器， 兵器"},{"word":"wear","phonetic_us":"/wɛr/","translation":"v. 磨损","example":"The cushions are starting to wear a little. 这些靠垫开始有点磨破了。","phonetic_uk":"/weə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/wiv/","translation":"v. 织，编；v. 纺织","word":"weave","phonetic_uk":"/wiːv/","example":"hand-woven scarves 手织围巾"},{"phonetic_us":"/'wɛdɪŋ/","translation":"n. 婚礼","word":"wedding","phonetic_uk":"/ˈwedɪŋ/","example":"She’s busy planning her daughter’s wedding. 她正忙着筹备女儿的婚礼。"},{"example":"the constant battle against weeds 对付杂草的长期斗争","phonetic_uk":"/wiːd/","word":"weed","translation":"n. 杂草，野草；v. 除草","phonetic_us":"/wid/"},{"translation":"adv.  每周；adj. 每周的","phonetic_us":"/'wikli/","word":"weekly","example":"The group meets weekly. 小组每周见面一次。","phonetic_uk":"/'wiːkli/"},{"translation":"v. 哭泣，流泪","phonetic_us":"/wip/","word":"weep","example":"James broke down and wept. 詹姆斯控制不住感情，哭了起来。","phonetic_uk":"/wiːp/"},{"example":"The new handle will have to be welded on. 新的把手得焊上去。","phonetic_uk":"/weld/","translation":"vt&n. 焊接，熔接","phonetic_us":"/wɛld/","word":"weld"},{"translation":"n. 福利","phonetic_us":"/'wɛl'fɛr/","word":"welfare","example":"Our only concern is the children’s welfare. 我们唯一关心的是孩子们的幸福。","phonetic_uk":"/'welfeə/"},{"word":"well-known","phonetic_us":"/,wɛl'non/","translation":"adj.  众所周知的， 著名的","phonetic_uk":"/ˌwel'nəun/","example":"This is probably their best-known song. 这可能是他们最有名的歌曲。"},{"example":"The whale nearest to the photographer is releasing air to aid its descent. 这只离摄影师最近的白鲸正呼出空气以帮助其下潜。","phonetic_uk":"/weɪl/","phonetic_us":"/wel/","translation":"n.  鲸","word":"whale"},{"example":"She has shown no interest whatever in anything scientific. 凡是与科学有关的她都没有表现出任何兴趣。","phonetic_uk":"/ wɒt'evə/","translation":"adv.  [用于否定句中以加强语气]任何； 无论什么","phonetic_us":"/wət'ɛvɚ/","word":"whatever"},{"word":"wheat","phonetic_us":"/wit/","translation":"n. 小麦","example":"a field of wheat 小麦地","phonetic_uk":"/wiːt/"},{"phonetic_us":"/wil/","translation":"n. 轮，车轮","word":"wheel","example":"Shall I take the wheel (= drive instead of someone else )? 我来开车好吗？","phonetic_uk":"/wiːl/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/weər'æz/","example":"The old system was fairly complicated whereas the new system is really very simple. 旧系统相当复杂，而新系统却很简单。","translation":"conj.  然而， 但是， 尽管","phonetic_us":"/'wɛr'æz/","word":"whereas"},{"phonetic_uk":"/wɪtʃ'evə/","example":"Letting taxes rise abruptly would hurt not only the recovery but also whichever party the electorate ended up blaming. 突然的增税不但会妨害经济复苏，而且无论哪个政党这样做都会受到选民指责。","translation":"pron&adj.  无论哪个， 无论哪些","phonetic_us":"/wɪtʃ'ɛvɚ/","word":"whichever"},{"word":"whilst","translation":"conj&n. 当…的时候","phonetic_us":"/hwailst/","example":"","phonetic_uk":"/waɪlst/"},{"word":"whip","phonetic_us":"/wɪp/","translation":"v. 鞭笞；搅打；n. 鞭子","example":"He whipped the horse into a canter. 他抽了一下鞭子，马儿就小跑起来。","phonetic_uk":"/wɪp/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'wɪspə/","example":"You don’t have to whisper, no one can hear us. 你不必轻声轻语，没人听得到我们说话。","word":"whisper","phonetic_us":"/'wɪspɚ/","translation":"v. 低声地讲；v. 低语"},{"example":"The lifeguard blew his whistle. 救生员吹响哨子。","phonetic_uk":"/'wɪs(ə)l/","word":"whistle","translation":"n. 口哨；v. 吹口哨","phonetic_us":"/'wɪsl/"},{"word":"whoever","translation":"pron.  谁； 无论谁； 究竟是谁","phonetic_us":"/hʊ'ɛvɚ/","example":"I’ll take whoever wants to go. 谁想去我就带谁去。","phonetic_uk":"/huː'evə/"},{"example":"a wholly satisfactory solution 完全令人满意的解决办法","phonetic_uk":"/'həʊllɪ; 'həʊlɪ/","phonetic_us":"/'holli/","translation":"adv. 完全地，全部","word":"wholly"},{"translation":"adj. 坏的；令人厌恶的","phonetic_us":"/'wɪkɪd/","word":"wicked","example":"the wicked stepmother in ‘Hansel and Gretel’ 《糖果屋》中那个恶毒的继母","phonetic_uk":"/'wɪkɪd/"},{"example":"They’re widening the road. 他们正在拓宽马路。","phonetic_uk":"/'waɪd(ə)n/","word":"widen","phonetic_us":"/'waɪdn/","translation":"v. 加宽；v. 变宽"},{"word":"widespread","translation":"adj. 普遍的，广泛的","phonetic_us":"/ˈwʌɪdsprɛd/","phonetic_uk":"/'waɪdspred/","example":"the widespread use of chemicals in agriculture 化学品在农业中的广泛使用"},{"word":"widow","phonetic_us":"/'wɪdo/","translation":"n. 寡妇","example":"an elderly widow who was attacked and robbed last month 上个月遭到行凶抢劫的一位寡居老妇","phonetic_uk":"/'wɪdəʊ/"},{"word":"width","phonetic_us":"/wɪdθ/","translation":"n. 宽阔，广阔；宽度","phonetic_uk":"/wɪtθ; wɪdθ/","example":"a covered terrace extending the full width of the house 和房子同宽的有顶露台"},{"word":"willing","phonetic_us":"/'wɪlɪŋ/","translation":"adj. 愿意的，心甘情愿的","example":"I soon had an army of willing helpers. 我很快就拥有了一批热心的帮手。","phonetic_uk":"/'wɪlɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_us":"/wɪnd; (for v.) waɪnd/","translation":"v. 绕，缠绕；v. 卷曲","word":"wind","phonetic_uk":"/wɪnd; (for v.) waɪnd/","example":"a winding path 蜿蜒的小路"},{"phonetic_uk":"/wɪŋ/","example":"The bird flapped its wings furiously. 那只鸟使劲地拍打着翅膀。","word":"wing","translation":"n. 翼，翅膀，翅","phonetic_us":"/wɪŋ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/waɪə/","example":"copper wire 铜丝","word":"wire","phonetic_us":"/'waɪɚ/","translation":"n. 金属线；电缆；电信"},{"word":"wisdom","translation":"n.  智慧， 才智； 名言","phonetic_us":"/'wɪzdəm/","example":"a man of great wisdom 一个有大智慧的男人","phonetic_uk":"/'wɪzdəm/"},{"word":"wise","translation":"adj. 聪明的，有智慧的","phonetic_us":"/waɪz/","phonetic_uk":"/waɪz/","example":"a wise precaution 明智的预防措施"},{"phonetic_us":"/wɪt/","translation":"n. 智力，才智，智能","word":"wit","phonetic_uk":"/wɪt/","example":"The information is there and waiting to be accessed by anyone with the wit to use it. 信息是现成的，等着有头脑的人去获取和利用。"},{"translation":"v. 收回；撤回vi撤退","phonetic_us":"/wɪð'drɔ/","word":"withdraw","example":"calls for Britain to withdraw from the European Union 要求英国退出欧盟的呼声","phonetic_uk":"/wɪð'drɔː/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/wɪð'stænd/","example":"The Chancellor has withstood the criticism and held firm. 总理顶住批评，坚持立场。","phonetic_us":"/wɪð'stænd/","translation":"v. 抵挡，反抗","word":"withstand"},{"translation":"n. 目击者，目击","phonetic_us":"/ˈwɪtnɪs/","word":"witness","phonetic_uk":"/'wɪtnɪs/","example":"Police have appealed for witnesses to come forward. 警方呼吁目击者站出来。"},{"word":"wolf","phonetic_us":"/wʊlf/","translation":"n.  狼","phonetic_uk":"/wulf/","example":"a pack of wolves 一群狼"},{"phonetic_us":"/'wʊdn/","translation":"adj. 木制的；呆板的","word":"wooden","phonetic_uk":"/'wʊd(ə)n/","example":"a wooden bench 木制长椅"},{"word":"wool","phonetic_us":"/wʊl/","translation":"n. 羊毛；毛线，绒线","phonetic_uk":"/wʊl/","example":"a ball of wool 一团毛线"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'wɜːkmən/","example":"In University Square workmen are building a steel fence. 在大学广场工人们正在筑一个钢栅栏。","word":"workman","translation":"n. 工人，劳动者，工匠","phonetic_us":"/'wɝkmən/"},{"word":"workshop","phonetic_us":"/'wɝkʃɑp/","translation":"n. 车间，工场；创作室","phonetic_uk":"/'wɜːkʃɒp/","example":"...a modestly equipped workshop. …一个装备普通的车间。"},{"translation":"adj.  遍及全球的","phonetic_us":"","word":"world-wide","example":"Today, doctors are fearing a worldwide epidemic. 如今，医生们在担心一次世界性的流行。","phonetic_uk":"/'wɜːldwaɪd/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'wɜːl(d)waɪd/","example":"His books have sold more than 20 million copies worldwide. 他的书在全世界卖出了两千多万本。","word":"worldwide","phonetic_us":"/'wɝldwaɪd/","translation":"adv. 全世界范围地"},{"translation":"n. 虫，蠕虫","phonetic_us":"/wɝm/","word":"worm","phonetic_uk":"/wɜːm/","example":"...a new computer worm that disables security software. …一种使安全软件失灵的新型计算机蠕虫病毒。"},{"translation":"v. （使）变得更坏","phonetic_us":"/'wɝsn/","word":"worsen","phonetic_uk":"/'wɜ:sn/","example":"A lot of teachers expect the situation to worsen over the next few years. 许多老师认为接下来的几年情形会更糟。"},{"word":"worship","translation":"n. 礼拜；崇拜；v. 崇拜","phonetic_us":"/'wɝʃɪp/","phonetic_uk":"/'wə:ʃip/","example":"The ceremony must take place in a recognized place of worship . 该仪式必须在获得认可的敬拜场所举行。"},{"word":"worst","phonetic_us":"/wɝst/","translation":"adj. 最坏的；adv. 最坏地","phonetic_uk":"/wə:st/","example":"This is the worst recession for fifty years. 这是50年来最严重的一次经济衰退。"},{"example":"You should not deprecate your own worth. 你不应该贬低你自己的价值。","phonetic_uk":"/wɜːθ/","word":"worth","translation":"adj. 值…的；n. 价值","phonetic_us":"/wɝθ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/ˈwəːθlɪs/","example":"The house was full of worthless junk. 这房子里堆满了没有用的东西。","word":"worthless","phonetic_us":"/ˈwərthləs/","translation":"adj. 无价值的，无用的"},{"example":"He wanted to do a worthwhile job. 他想做有意义的工作。","phonetic_uk":"/wɜːθ'waɪl/","phonetic_us":"/'wɝθ'waɪl/","translation":"adj. 有价值的","word":"worthwhile"},{"word":"worthy","phonetic_us":"/wɜði/","translation":"adj. 有价值的；值得的","example":"Leeds United were worthy winners of the competition. 利兹联队是比赛当之无愧的获胜者。","phonetic_uk":"/ˈwəːði/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/wuːnd/","example":"A nurse cleaned and bandaged the wound. 护士把伤口清洗包扎好。","translation":"n. 创伤，伤；v. 使受伤","phonetic_us":"/wund/","word":"wound"},{"word":"wrap","phonetic_us":"/ræp/","translation":"v. 裹，包，捆；n. 披肩","phonetic_uk":"/ræp/","example":"I’ve still got a few Christmas presents to wrap up. 我还有一些圣诞礼物要包起来。"},{"word":"wreck","phonetic_us":"/rɛk/","translation":"n. 失事；残骸；v. 破坏","example":"...the wreck of a sailing ship. …一艘帆船的残骸。","phonetic_uk":"/rek/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/rɪst/","example":"He broke his wrist climbing rocks for a cigarette ad. 他为了一个香烟广告攀岩折断了手腕。","word":"wrist","translation":"n. 腕，腕关节","phonetic_us":"/rɪst/"},{"word":"writer","translation":"n.  作者， 作家","phonetic_us":"/'raɪtɚ/","example":"She’s one of my favourite writers. 她是我最喜欢的作家之一。","phonetic_uk":"/'raɪtə/"},{"phonetic_us":"/'raɪtɪŋ/","translation":"n.  书写， 写； 著作","word":"writing","example":"Some of his most powerful writing is based on his childhood experiences. 他的一些最震慑人心的作品是根据儿时经历写成的。","phonetic_uk":"/'raɪtɪŋ/"},{"example":"The X-ray showed that her leg was not broken. X光片显示她的腿没有骨折。","phonetic_uk":"/'eks'reɪ/","word":"X-ray","translation":"n.  X射线， X光","phonetic_us":"/'eksreɪ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/jɑːd/","example":"a builder’s yard 建筑工地","word":"yard","translation":"n. 院子，庭院；场地","phonetic_us":"/jɑrd/"},{"word":"yawn","translation":"v. 打呵欠；n. 呵欠","phonetic_us":"/jɔn/","phonetic_uk":"/jɔːn/","example":"Alan stretched and yawned. 艾伦伸伸懒腰，打了个呵欠。"},{"phonetic_uk":"/'jɪəlɪ; 'jɜː-/","example":"Salary levels are reviewed on a yearly basis. 工资水平每年都要审查。","word":"yearly","phonetic_us":"/'jɪrli/","translation":"adj. 每年的；adv. 一年一度"},{"word":"yield","translation":"v. 屈服，产出；n. 产量","phonetic_us":"/jild/","phonetic_uk":"/ji:ld/","example":"Our research has only recently begun to yield important results. 直到最近我们的研究才开始取得重要成果。"},{"word":"youngster","phonetic_us":"/'jʌŋstɚ/","translation":"n.  青年， 年轻人， 孩子","example":"Other youngsters are not so lucky. 其他的年轻人没有这么幸运。","phonetic_uk":"/'jʌŋstə/"},{"translation":"n. 青春；青年们；青年","phonetic_us":"/jʊθ/","word":"youth","example":"Despite his youth, he had travelled alone. 他虽然年纪还小，却已独自旅行过了。","phonetic_uk":"/juːθ/"},{"phonetic_uk":"/zəʊn/","example":"San Francisco and Tokyo are both located in earthquake zones. 旧金山和东京都位于地震带。","word":"zone","phonetic_us":"/zon/","translation":"n. 地区，区域，范围"}]